INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (1,'A','','','','','a.一,一个,一只,一件.',' I don\'t care what a car looks like as long as it gets me from A to B.<br>     我倒不在乎汽车的样子, 只要能把我从一处载到另一处就行了.<br>\n Would you do me a favor?<br>     你能帮我一个忙吗？<br>'),(2,'a.m.','','','','','上午<br>\nabbr. (ante meridiem的缩写)上午,午前<br>\nad. 上午,由午夜至中午',''),(3,'abacus','','','','abacuses','n. 算盘',' I can use abacus skillfully.<br>     我会熟练地打算盘。<br>\n The clerk reckoned the expenditure last week with an abacus.<br>     那位职员用算盘将上周的花销计算出来。<br>'),(4,'abandon','abandoned','abandoned','abandoning','','v. 放弃,遗弃,沉溺',' The cruel man abandoned his wife and child.<br>     那个狠心的男人抛弃了他的妻儿。<br>\n They had abandoned all hope.<br>     他们已经放弃了一切希望。<br>'),(5,'abatement','','','','abatements','n. 减少,减轻,缓和',' A noise abatement notice is served on the club.<br>     向俱乐部发停止大声喧哗的通知。<br>'),(6,'abbreviate','abbreviated','abbreviated','abbreviating','','v. 缩写,使...简略',' In writing, the title `Doctor\' is abbreviated to `Dr\'.<br>     在书写时, Doctor头衔的缩写是Dr.<br>'),(7,'abbreviation','','','','abbreviations','n. 缩写',' Scratch the subject of defence and acronym, abbreviation, and buzzwords fly out.<br>     话题触及国防，缩合字，缩写字和行话就满天飞。<br>\n An abbreviation for formula calculation language, a high-level programming language not too widely used.<br>     公式计算语言的简称，应用不太广泛的一种高级程序设计语言。<br>'),(8,'ABC','','','','','n. 基本要素,字母表<br>\nabbr. 美国广播公司<br>\nabbr. 澳大利亚广播公司',' Shipment to be effected on a container liner of ABC Line.<br>     交由ABC班轮公司的集装箱班轮运载。<br>\n Inquire firm work jointly with abc company impression quite reliable president rather calculating.<br>     咨询公司与ABC公司合作，印象中此公司值得信赖。该公司董事长式于心计。<br>'),(9,'abdomen','','','','abdomens','n. 腹部',' The spider has a bulgy abdomen.<br>     蜘蛛长着凸出的腹部。<br>\n He always feels pain in his abdomen.<br>     他的腹部经常疼痛。<br>'),(10,'abdominal','','','','','a. 腹部的',' I\'ll have an abdominal operation tomorrow.<br>     我明天要做个腹部手术。<br>\n She had abdominal pains yesterday.<br>     她昨天腹痛。<br>'),(11,'abend','','','','','异常结束',''),(12,'abide','abode','abode','abiding','','v. 遵守,忍受,居留',' Everyone must abide by the law.<br>     所有的人都应遵守法律。<br>\n She can\'t abide that man.<br>     她不能忍受那个人。<br>'),(13,'ability','','','','abilities','n. 才能,能力',' I don\'t doubt your ability to do the work.<br>     我不怀疑你有能力担任这项工作。<br>\n He is a man of many abilities.<br>     他是一个有多方面才能的人。<br>'),(14,'able','','','','','a. 能干的,有能力的',' He is an able man.<br>     他是一个能人。<br>\n As I had plenty of money I was able to help her.<br>     我钱很宽裕，能帮助她。<br>'),(15,'abnormal','','','','','a. 反常的,不正常的,不规则的',' The weather is abnormal this year.<br>     今年的气候不正常。<br>\n An abnormal fear of high places.<br>     恐高症对于高处的一种不正常的恐惧<br>'),(16,'aboard','','','','','ad. 在船上,在火车上,在飞机上<br>\nprep. 在...之上',' It\'s time to go aboard.<br>     该上船/飞机/车了。<br>\n Welcome aboard!<br>     st. 请上船(车,飞机)<br>'),(17,'abolish','abolished','abolished','abolishing','','v. 废止,革除','Abraham Lincoln abolished slavery in the United States.\n     \n亚伯拉罕·林肯在美国废除了奴隶制/n\n There are many bad customs and laws that ought to be abolished     有许多不良的习俗和法规应予以废'),(18,'aboriginal','','','','aboriginals','a. 原始的,土著的',' An Australian aboriginal dance festival held at night to celebrate tribal victories or other events./r     狂欢会澳大利亚土著的一种舞蹈节，在晚上召开以庆祝部落胜利或其他事件/r\n Any of the languages of the aboriginal peoples of Australia./     澳洲土著语任何澳洲土著民族的语言'),(19,'abort','aborted','aborted','aborting','','v. 流产,打胎,堕胎',' Some suspicious looking men were loitering abort near the house<br>     几个形迹可疑的人在屋子附近荡来荡去。<br>\n An aborted organism.<br>     流产的生物体<br>'),(20,'abortion','','','','abortions','n. 流产,堕胎',' Abortion is illegal in this country.<br>     人工流产在这个国家是不合法的。<br>\n They are discussing the morality of abortion.<br>     他们正在讨论堕胎的道德性。<br>'),(21,'abound','abounded','abounded','abounding','','v. 富于,充满','Tropical plants abound in the jungle.\n丛林中有大量的热带植物。\nHe abounds in courage.\n他很有胆量。'),(22,'about','','','','','a. 准备<br>\nad. 大约<br>\nprep. 关于',' It is about six o\'clock now.<br>     现在是六点钟左右。<br>\n He was about to start.<br>     他即将动身。<br>'),(23,'above','','','','','a. 上面的<br>\nad. 在上面<br>\nn. 上面<br>\nprep. 在...上面',' The sun rose above the horizon.<br>     太阳升到地平线上。<br>\n My bedroom is just above.<br>     我的卧室就在上面。<br>'),(24,'aboveboard','','','','','ad. 光明正大地,率直地<br>\na. 光明正大的,率直的',''),(25,'abrasion','','','','','n. 磨减,磨损,磨损之处',' An implement with cutting edges or a pointed end for boring holes in hard materials, usually by a rotating abrasion or repeated blows; a bit.<br>     钻带切割刃或尖端的工具，用于在坚硬材料上钻孔，一般靠旋转磨损或反复击打实现钻孔<br>\n A minor scratch or abrasion.<br>     擦伤一个轻微的擦伤或磨损<br>'),(26,'abrasive','','','','','n. 研磨剂<br>\na. 磨平的',' An abrasive or filler used in a soap or detergent.<br>     增清剂肥皂或去污剂中用的研磨剂或填料<br>\n Jeff is usually an abrasive character, but he can be as sweet as honey when he wants something.<br>     杰弗通常是一个生硬粗暴的人，但他想得到某物时，他会象蜜一样甜。<br>'),(27,'abridge','abridged','abridged','abridging','','v. 删节,缩短',' It was abridged from the original work.<br>     这是原书的节录本。<br>\n This is an abridged edition of \"war and peace\".<br>     这是“战争与和平”的节略版。<br>'),(28,'abridgement','','','','abridgements','节略,缩写',''),(29,'abroad','','','','','a. 在国外,海外(一般作表语)<br>\nad. 到国外,在国外',' He lived abroad for many years.<br>     他在国外居住了许多年。<br>\n She is hungry for news of her husband working abroad.<br>     她渴望得到国外工作的丈夫的消息。<br>'),(30,'abrupt','','','','','a. 突然的,唐突的',' That young man has an abrupt manner.<br>     那个年轻人态度很无礼。<br>\n The meeting came to an abrupt end.<br>     会议突然结束了。<br>'),(31,'abruption','','','','','中断,分离',''),(32,'abscess','','','','','n. 脓疮,溃疡',' The tip of an abscess, a boil, or a pimple, in which pus forms.<br>     脓头中间有脓液的脓疮、疖或丘疹的顶端<br>\n I think I have an abscess on my gums. This could be serious.<br>     我想我的牙床上有个脓疮，这可能是严重的。<br>'),(33,'absence','','','','absences','a. 不在,缺席<br>\nn. 缺乏,缺少,缺席',' Please look after my house during my absence.<br>     我不在时，请帮我看房子。<br>\n We must invent an excuse for our absence.<br>     我们必须为缺席编造一个藉口。<br>'),(34,'absent','','','','','a. 缺席的<br>\nvt. 使缺席',' How many students are absent today?<br>     今天有多少学生缺席？<br>\n Why was it that he was absent?<br>     他为什么缺席呢？<br>'),(35,'absentminded','','','','','a. 心不在焉的,茫然的,恍惚的',''),(36,'absolute','','','','absolutes','a. 绝对的,完全的<br>\nn. 绝对',' We now have the absolute proof of his guilt.<br>     我们现在有他犯罪的确凿证据。<br>\n That\'s absolute nonsense!<br>     真是一派胡言！<br>'),(37,'absolutely','','','','','ad. 绝对地,完全地;独立地;确实地',' I trust his discretion absolutely.<br>     我完全相信他的判断。<br>\n I\'m absolutely starving.<br>     我饿极了。<br>'),(38,'absorb','absorbed','absorbed','absorbing','','v. 吸收,吸引...的注意,使全神贯注',' His business absorbs him.<br>     他的业务使他全神贯注。<br>\n The clever boy absorbed all the knowledge his teacher could give him.<br>     那个聪明的男孩把他老师所能教他的所有的知识都吸收了。<br>'),(39,'absorption','','','','','n. 吸收',' I really appreciate his complete absorption in his work.<br>     我很欣赏他对工作的极端专注。<br>\n A medicine or an agent that induces absorption.<br>     吸收剂导致吸收的药品或药剂<br>'),(40,'abstract','','','','','n. 摘要<br>\na. 抽象的<br>\nv. 摘要,抽炼',' He has some abstract notion of wanting to change the world.<br>     他有一种要改造世界的空想。<br>\n We may talk of beautiful things, but beauty itself is abstract.<br>     我们尽可谈论美的事物，然而美本身却是抽象的。<br>'),(41,'absurd','','','','','a. 荒唐的',' What an absurd suggestion!<br>     多荒谬的建议啊！<br>\n It was absurd of you to suggest such a thing.<br>     你居然建议这样的事，太可笑了。<br>'),(42,'abundance','','','','','n. 丰富,充裕',' There was an abundance of corn last year.<br>     去年玉米丰收。<br>\n The state of being profuse; abundance.<br>     丰富极其丰富的状态；充沛<br>'),(43,'abundant','','','','','a. 丰富的,充裕的',' There is abundant firewood in the forest.<br>     森林里有充裕的薪柴可用。<br>\n Our abundant resources and stable policy provide foreigners with the advantages they invest here.<br>     我们丰富的资源和稳定的政策为外商投资提供了有利条件。<br>'),(44,'abuse','','','','','n. 滥用,恶习<br>\nv. 滥用,辱骂,虐待',' It\'s easy to abuse one\'s power.<br>     人容易滥用权力。<br>\n They talked about how the uses and abuses of figures to prove things in politics.<br>     他们谈到人们如何在政治问题上使用及滥用数字来混淆视听。<br>'),(45,'academic','','','','academics','a. 学院的,理论的,学术性的',' The new academic year is coming.<br>     新学年就要来了。<br>\n The question is purely academic.<br>     这是一个纯学术性的问题。<br>'),(46,'academy','','','','academies','n. 学院,学术,学会',' He is a student in an academy of music.<br>     他是一所音乐学院的学生。<br>\n A member of an art, literary, or scientific academy or society.<br>     学会会员艺术、文学、科学学会或团体的成员<br>'),(47,'accelerate','accelerated','accelerated','accelerating','','v. 加速',' The car accelerated as it overtook me.<br>     那辆汽车一加速就超越了我.<br>\n The leader is losing ground as the rest of the runners accelerate.<br>     领先者在其余赛跑者加速时就逐渐失去了优势。<br>'),(48,'acceleration','','','','','n. 加速,促进,加速度',' A flight garment worn by astronauts and jet pilots that presses on the lower body to maintain the blood supply to the brain during rapid vertical acceleration.<br>     抗荷衣宇航员或喷气机飞行员穿的飞行服，在快速垂直加速中增加身体下部的压力以保持脑部血液供应<br>\n An instrument used to measure acceleration.<br>     加速计，测震仪用于测量加速度的仪器<br>'),(49,'accelerator','','','','','n. 加速者,加速器,油门',' I pressed the accelerator until the engine screamed.<br>     我猛踩油门踏板，发动机发出了尖利的声音。<br>\n The brake (pedal) is between the clutch and the accelerator.<br>     制动器（踏板）在离合器和加速器之间.<br>'),(50,'accent','accented','accented','accenting','accents','n. 重音,口音<br>\nv. 重读,强调',' In the word `today\' the accent is on the second syllable.<br>     today一字的重音在第二个音节上.<br>\n The accent in the word\" importance\" is on the second syllable.<br>     “importance”一词的重音在第二音节上。<br>'),(51,'accentuate','accentuated','accentuated','accentuating','','v. 以重音念,强调,重读',' The tight jumper only accentuated his fat stomach.<br>     那件紧身套头毛衣反更突出了他那肥胖的肚子.<br>'),(52,'accept','accepted','accepted','accepting','','vt.接受,同意,承担(责任等)',' It is generally accepted that smoking is harmful to our health.<br>     吸烟有害健康，这是大家公认的。<br>\n The police are not allowed to accept rewards.<br>     警察是不允许接受酬金的。<br>'),(53,'acceptable','','','','','a. 合意的,受欢迎的,可接受的',' The solution to this problem is acceptable.<br>     这个问题的解决方案是可接受的。<br>\n Do you think the proposal is acceptable?<br>     你认为这个建议可接受吗？<br>'),(54,'acceptance','','','','acceptances','n. 接受,容纳,承诺,验证',' Within two days I received a letter of acceptance from the manager.<br>     不到两天，我就收到了经理写来的录取信。<br>\n The proposal was met with general acceptance.<br>     这建议得到普遍的赞同。<br>'),(55,'access','accessed','accessed','accessing','accesses','n. 通路,进入,使用之权<br>\nv. 存取',' Citizens may have free access to the library.<br>     市民可以免费使用这个图书馆。<br>\n He is a man of easy access.<br>     他是一个很好接近的人。<br>'),(56,'accessible','','','','','a. 可得到的,易接近的,可进入的',' A manager should be accessible to his staff.<br>     一个管理人员应该让职员感到平易近人。<br>\n This island is accessible only by boat.<br>     这个小岛只能坐小船去。<br>'),(57,'accessory','','','','accessories','a. 附属的(副的,辅助的)<br>\nn. 附件',' He asked me to buy him some accessories for a car.<br>     他让我给他买些汽车附件。<br>\n He is Tom\'s accessory.<br>     他是汤姆的帮凶。<br>'),(58,'accident','','','','accidents','n. 事故,意外的事',' We got back without accident.<br>     我们平安无事地回来了。<br>\n She was injured badly in the accident.<br>     她在事故中受重伤。<br>'),(59,'accidental','','','','accidentals','a. 意外的,偶然的',' Our meeting was quite accidental.<br>     我们的相遇是很偶然的。<br>\n A sequence of events that although accidental seems to have been planned or arranged.<br>     巧合，凑巧虽是偶然的，但似乎是经计划或安排的一系列事件<br>'),(60,'accidentally','','','','','ad. 偶然地,意外地',' Willie accidentally lets off his father\'s shotgun and made a hole in the wall.<br>     威利玩他父亲的手枪时不小心走火了, 把墙壁打出一个洞。<br>\n He accidentally knocked on (the pass from Jones).<br>     他非故意犯规, 用手向前击了（从琼斯传来的）球.<br>'),(61,'acclaim','acclaimed','acclaimed','acclaiming','','n. 喝采,欢呼,赞同<br>\nv. 欢呼,喝采,称赞',' Acclaim or praise for exceptional achievement.<br>     名声，威信对杰出成就所作的称赞或颂扬<br>\n A person of remarkable talent or ability who achieves great success or acclaim at an early age.<br>     少年得志因早年具有非凡的才智和能力而获得极大成功或受到称赞的人<br>'),(62,'accommodate','accommodated','accommodated'