arances','n. 外表,出现,出场',' We should not judge a person by his appearance.<br>     我们不应该以貌取人。<br>\n The journal makes its appearance once two months.<br>     这本刊物两个月出版一次。<br>'),(458,'appearances','','','','','出现',''),(459,'append','appended','appended','appending','','v. 附加,添加,悬挂<br>\nn.[计算机] DOS 命令建立数据文件的子目录搜索路经',' Additional information appended to the manuscript, as of a book or an article.<br>     附言，续篇如一本书或一篇文章正文后的附加信息<br>\n I append a list of those shops which sell our products.<br>     我附上一张出售我们产品的商店名单。<br>'),(460,'appendectomy','','','','appendectomies','n. 阑尾切除术',''),(461,'appendicitis','','','','','n. 阑尾炎,盲肠炎',' She\'s got appendicitis.<br>     她得了阑尾炎.<br>\n It\'s acute appendicitis. We ought to operate.<br>     这是急性阑尾炎。应当开刀。<br>'),(462,'appendix','appendixed','appendixed','appendixing','appendixes','n. 附录',' This dictionary has several appendices.<br>     这本词典有几项附录。<br>\n The doctor said the appendix is not important for us.<br>     那个大夫说阑尾对我们来说并不重要。<br>'),(463,'appetite','','','','appetites','n. 爱好,嗜好,食欲,胃口,欲望',' She is suffering from lack of appetite.<br>     她食欲不振。<br>\n The long walk gave him a good appetite.<br>     长时间的走路使他食欲旺盛。<br>'),(464,'applaud','applauded','applauded','applauding','','v. 拍手喝采,称赞,赞同',' We all applaud you for your decision.<br>     我们一致赞成你的决定。<br>\n He was loudly applauded.<br>     他受到热烈的掌声欢迎。<br>'),(465,'applause','','','','','n. 鼓掌,喝彩,赞许<br>\nv. 鼓掌',' His speech won the applause of the audience.<br>     他的讲话赢得了听众的掌声。<br>\n Let\'s have a good round of applause for the next performer.<br>     咱们为下一个表演者热烈鼓掌吧。<br>'),(466,'apple','','','','apples','n. 苹果',' An apple is a kind of fruit.<br>     苹果是一种水果。<br>\n The apple trees are blossoming.<br>     苹果树正在开花。<br>'),(467,'appliance','','','','appliances','n. 器具,器械,装置',' These appliances are made of stainless iron.<br>     这些器具是用不锈钢制成的。<br>\n There are many household appliances in this shop.<br>     这个商店有许多家用用具。<br>'),(468,'applicable','','','','','a. 合适的,适用的',' Applicable to or characteri