','','ad. 适当地',''),(485,'approval','','','','','n. 批准,认可,同意,赞同',' I hope the arrangements meet with your approval.<br>     我希望这些安排会得到你的同意。<br>\n We can\'t start building without the council\'s approval.<br>     未经委员会批准，我们不能动工。<br>'),(486,'approve','approved','approved','approving','','v. 赞同,核准,证实',' The city council approved the building plan.<br>     市议会批准了这项建筑计划。<br>\n The equipment must be bought from a supplier approved by the company.<br>     设备必须从公司认可的供应商那里购买。<br>'),(487,'approximate','approximated','approximated','approximating','','a. 大约的,近似的<br>\nv. 接近,约等于',' Your guess only approximates to the facts.<br>     你的猜测仅仅是接近事实。<br>\n The color of the curtains approximates that of the rug.<br>     窗帘的颜色和地毯相近。<br>'),(488,'approximately','','','','','ad. 近似地,大约',' The plane will be taking off in approximately five minutes.<br>     飞机大约五分钟后就起飞。<br>\n At a time near to; at approximately<br>     将近。。。的时候；大约在。。。<br>'),(489,'approximation','','','','','n. 近似值',''),(490,'April','','','','','n. 四月',' He moved into this house in April.<br>     他是四月份搬进这所房子的。<br>\n The manuscript bears the date 10 April 1937.<br>     手稿上注著1937年4月10日.<br>'),(491,'apron','','','','aprons','n. 围裙',' My apron is so dirty that I have to wash it.<br>     我的围裙太脏了，我不得不洗它。<br>\n Could you tie this apron round me?<br>     你受累把围裙给我系上行吗?<br>'),(492,'apt','','','','','a. 倾向于,易于',' It\'s apt to rain this afternoon.<br>     今天下午可能下雨。<br>\n He is a very apt student.<br>     他是一个很聪明的学生。<br>'),(493,'aptitude','','','','aptitudes','n. 才能,资质',' He has an aptitude for languages.<br>     他具有学习语言的才能。<br>\n Edison had a remarkable aptitude for inventing new things.<br>     爱迪生具有发明创造的非凡才能。<br>'),(494,'aquarium','','','','aquariums','n. 水族馆,养鱼池,玻璃缸',' A large aquarium for the study or display of marine life.<br>     海洋水族馆研究或陈列海洋生物的巨大水族馆<br>'),(495,'aquatic','','','','aquatics','n. 水生动物,水草<br>\na. 水生的,水中的,水上的',' Aquatic animals that live in the substrate of a body of water, especially in a soft sea bottom.<br>     底内动物生活在水体底部的水生动物，尤指栖于松软海底的水生动物<br>\n An air-filled sac or structure that aids in the flotation of an aquatic organism.<br>     气囊水生动植物器官中用来帮助飘浮用的充满气体的囊或结构<br>'),(496,'Arab','','','','','n. 阿拉伯人,阿拉伯马<br>\na. 阿拉伯人的,阿拉伯的',' \"This, \" he declared, \"has aroused the bitter indignation of the Arab people.\"<br>     他说：\"这就激起了阿拉伯人民的强烈义愤。\"<br>\n One who is favorably disposed toward Arab concerns and policies.<br>     阿拉伯（民族）主义者非常关注阿拉伯事务及政策的人<br>'),(497,'Arabian','','','','','a. 阿拉伯(人)的<br>\nn. 阿拉伯人',' The Arabian Nights\' Entertainment is very interesting.<br>     《一千零一夜》的故事非常有趣。<br>\n A region of western India bordering on the Arabian Sea. An independent kingdom after1401, it was annexed by the Mogul Empire in1572.<br>     古吉拉特印度西部一地区，与阿拉伯海相邻。1401年后成为一独立的王国，1572年被强行并入莫卧帝国<br>'),(498,'Arabic','','','','','n. 阿拉伯语<br>\na. 阿拉伯语的,阿拉伯人的,阿拉伯式的',' He demonstrated a mastery of Arabic.<br>     他显示了对阿拉伯语的精通。<br>\n She needs to perfect her Arabic before going to work in Cairo.<br>     她需要把阿拉伯语学好才能到开罗工作.<br>'),(499,'arbitrage','','','','','n. 仲裁,套利交易,套汇',''),(500,'arbitrary','','','','','a. 任意的,恣意的,专制的',' The choice of players for the team seems completely arbitrary.<br>     对队员的挑选似乎完全是主观决定的。<br>\n Most presidents in this African country are arbitrary rulers.<br>     这个非洲国家的总统大多数是专横的统治者。<br>'),(501,'arc','','','','arcs','n. 弧',' The sun appears to move in an arc across the sky.<br>     太阳看起来在天空以弧线运行。<br>\n Joan of Arc was one of France\'s greatest daughters.<br>     圣女贞德是法国最伟大的女性之一。<br>'),(502,'arch','','','','','n. 拱门,弓形<br>\nv. 成弓形弯曲,成弓形',' The cat arched its back in anger.<br>     那只猫气得拱起了腰。<br>\n The bridge has three arches.<br>     这座桥有三座拱洞。<br>'),(503,'archaeology','','','','','n. 考古学',''),(504,'archaic','','','','','a. 已废的,古老的,古代的',' An archaic word, phrase, idiom, or other expression.<br>     古词，古语古词、古短语、古习语或其它表达（形式）<br>'),(505,'architect','','','','architects','n. 建筑师',' Everyone is the architect of his own fortune.<br>     每个人都是自己命运的创造者。<br>\n The boy made up his mind to become an excellent architect.<br>     这个男孩下定决心成为一个优秀的建筑师。<br>'),(506,'architecture','','','','architectures','n. 建筑学, 建筑业<br>\n [总称]建筑物, 建筑风格',' The architecture of this house is very substantial.<br>     这座房子的结构很牢固。<br>\n He obtained a diploma in architecture.<br>     他获得了建筑学的学位证书。<br>'),(507,'archive','','','','archives','n. 档案文件<br>\nn.（计算机压缩类软件的）压缩包<br>\nvt. 归档(编档保存)',' Place for permanent or long-term storage of data, from which retrieval is infrequent. A computer archive, for instance, may be on magnetic tape.<br>     用于永久或长期存储不常检索的数据的地点（介质）。例如，计算机的档案文件可放在磁带上。<br>'),(508,'archives','','','','','n. 档案',' My leader asked to find him an ancient document in the archives.<br>     我的上级要我给他在档案里找一份老掉牙的文件。<br>\n The company\'s archives goes back to its foundation in1892.<br>     该公司的档案可追溯至其创建的1892年。<br>'),(509,'arctic','','','','','a. 北极的,极寒的<br>\nn. 北极圈,北极地方',' I have never seen an arctic bear.<br>     我从未见过北极熊。<br>\n We can\'t stand this arctic weather.<br>     我们受不了这种严寒的天气。<br>'),(510,'ardent','','','','','a. 热心的,激烈的,燃烧般的',' I am an ardent supporter of the local football team.<br>     我是本地足球队的球迷。<br>\n She was ardent in her admiration of the artist.<br>     她非常倾慕那位艺术家。<br>'),(511,'arduous','','','','','a. 费力的,辛勤的,险峻的',' It\'s an arduous task.<br>     这是一项艰巨的任务。<br>\n He mastered these words through the arduous consultation of the dictionary.<br>     通过勤查字典，他掌握了这些单词。<br>'),(512,'area','','','','areas','n. 地区,区域,面积,方面',' The farm is about 50 or 60 square kilometers in the area.<br>     这个农场的面积约为50 或60 平方公里。<br>\n His special interest lies in the area of literature.<br>     他对文学领域特别感兴趣。<br>'),(513,'arena','','','','arenas','n. 竞技场',' She entered the political arena after her husband\'s death.<br>     她丈夫死后，她进入了政界。<br>\n The Roman arena was very famous.<br>     罗马竞技场是很出名的。<br>'),(514,'argue','argued','argued','arguing','','v. 争论,辩论,争吵,劝说',' The United States should, he argues, attempt to remain aloof.<br>     他认为，美国应保持超然态度。<br>\n They argued the case for hours.<br>     他们就这个案子辩论了几个小时。<br>'),(515,'argument','','','','arguments','n. 辩论,争论,论据,理由',' We accepted the agreement without argument.<br>     我们毫无异议地接受了这一协议。<br>\n There are strong arguments against these measures.<br>     有一些有力的论据反对这些措施。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (516,'arise','arose','arisen','arising','','v. 站立,出现',' Accidents often arise from carelessness.<br>     事故往往起因于粗心。<br>\n The problem may not arise, but there\'s no harm in keeping our powder dry.<br>     问题不一定会发生, 但有备无患并无害处.<br>'),(517,'arithmetic','','','','','n. 算术',' The little boy was not good at arithmetic.<br>     这个小男孩算术不太好。<br>\n I\'m good at history but not so hot at arithmetic.<br>     我的历史成绩不错, 但算术不太好.<br>'),(518,'arm','','','','','n. 手臂,袖子<br>\nv. 武装,装备',' Justice has long arms.<br>     天网恢恢，疏而不漏。<br>\n They were not allowed to use arms.<br>     不许他们使用武器。<br>'),(519,'armchair','','','','armchairs','n. 扶手椅',' This armchair is made of bamboo.<br>     这个扶手椅是用竹子做成的。<br>\n The old man often sits in an armchair.<br>     这个老人经常坐在扶手椅子上。<br>'),(520,'armour','','','','','n. 甲胄,铁甲,防护具',' His body was encased in shining armour.<br>     他全身披着明幌幌的甲胄。<br>\n A hog in armour is still a hog.<br>     猪穿甲胄仍是猪。<br>'),(521,'arms','','','','','n. 武器',' The government intends to cut expenditure on arms.<br>     政府打算削减军备开支。<br>\n They were not allowed to use arms.<br>     不许他们使用武器。<br>'),(522,'army','','','','armies','n. 军队,陆军',' He joined the army a year ago.<br>     一年以前，他参军了。<br>\n The increasing army of the unemployed has attracted the attention of the economist.<br>     不断增长的失业大军引起了这名经济学家的关注。<br>'),(523,'around','','','','','ad. 大约,到处,在周围<br>\nprep. 在...周围',' My sister is around your age.<br>     我妹妹和你年龄相仿。<br>\n He looked around but could see nobody.<br>     他四处望了一下，看不到什么人。<br>'),(524,'arouse','aroused','aroused','arousing','','v. 唤醒,鼓励,引起',' Diana aroused them just before dawn.<br>     戴安娜在黎明前唤醒了他们。<br>\n His sufferings aroused our sympathy.<br>     他的痛苦引起了我们的同情。<br>'),(525,'arrange','arranged','arranged','arranging','','v. 安排,整理,排列<br>\nn. 安排,排列',' I have arranged that one of my staff will meet you at the airport.<br>     我已经安排好派一个职员到飞机场接你。<br>\n I have arranged with him to meet at the restaurant.<br>     我和他约好在饭馆见面。<br>'),(526,'arrangement','','','','arrangements','n. 安排',' We have made all the arrangements for the conference.<br>     我们已做好会议的全部筹备工作。<br>\n There was an arrangement of books in the window.<br>     窗口摆了一些书。<br>'),(527,'array','arrayed','arrayed','arraying','arrays','n. 数组,排列,陈列,大批,一系列<br>\nv. 排列,布署,打扮',' Banners are arrayed on the wall.<br>     墙上张挂着锦旗。<br>\n People are all in holiday array.<br>     人们都穿着节日盛装。<br>'),(528,'arrears','','','','','n. 到期未付之债,拖欠的款项,待做的工作',' I\'m in arrears with the housework.<br>     我的家务事还拖著呢.<br>\n I have fallen into arrears with my rent.<br>     我已经拖欠租金了.<br>'),(529,'arrest','arrested','arrested','arresting','arrests','n. 逮捕,监禁<br>\nv. 拘捕,妨碍,吸引',' The treatment arrested the growth of the disease.<br>     治疗抑制了病情的发展。<br>\n The riot led to the arrest of three young men.<br>     暴乱导致3 个年轻人被捕。<br>'),(530,'arrival','','','','arrivals','n. 到达,到来',' The secretary informed me of his arrival.<br>     秘书通知我他来了。<br>\n Their unexpected arrival threw our plan into confusion.<br>     他们的突然到来打乱了我们的计划。<br>'),(531,'arrive','arrived','arrived','arriving','','v. 到达',' Finally, they arrived at an agreement.<br>     他们最后终于达成了协议。<br>\n We arrived home late.<br>     我们到家时晚了。<br>'),(532,'arrogant','','','','','a. 傲慢的,自大的',' He is an arrogant man.<br>     他是一个自高自大的人。<br>\n He often speaks in an arrogant tone.<br>     他经常以一种傲慢的口气说话。<br>'),(533,'arrow','arrowed','arrowed','arrowing','arrows','n. 箭<br>\nv. 箭(头),射箭',' The airport is arrowed on the map.<br>     飞机场在地图上用箭头标出。<br>\n He shot arrows one by one, but each missed.<br>     他射了一箭又一箭，但都未射中。<br>'),(534,'arsenal','','','','arsenals','n. 兵工厂, 军械库<br>\nn. 音译阿森那（英国－足球队名）',' Arsenals are factories that produce weapons.<br>     军工厂是生产武器的工厂。<br>\n There is an arsenal in this city.<br>     这座城市有一个军工厂。<br>'),(535,'art','','','','arts','a. 美术(品)的,艺术(品)的<br>\nn. 艺术',' He had devoted his whole life to the study of contemporary art.<br>     他把他的一生都献给了当代艺术研究。<br>\n He has a bent for art.<br>     他生性爱好艺术。<br>'),(536,'artery','','','','arteries','n. 动脉,主流,干道',' The Yangtse River is one of the main arteries of traffic in China.<br>     长江是中国的交通要道之一。<br>\n An artery, a vein, a nerve, or another part associated with the thyroid gland or thyroid cartilage.<br>     甲状物与甲状腺或甲状软骨相联系的动脉、静脉、神经或其它部分<br>'),(537,'arthritis','','','','','n. 关节炎',' Gout is a form of arthritis.<br>     痛风是关节炎的一种。<br>\n She was plagued with arthritis.<br>     她患关节炎十分痛苦.<br>'),(538,'article','articled','articled','articling','articles','n. 文章,物品,条款,冠词',' I am articled to a firm of lawyers.<br>     我受雇在一家律师公司做见习生。<br>\n The newspaper article gave a graphic description of the earthquake.<br>     报纸文章生动地描述了地震的情况。<br>'),(539,'articulate','','','','','a. 有关节的,发音清晰的<br>\nv. 以关节连接,接合,明白地说',' She\'s unusually articulate for a ten-year-old.<br>     作为一个十岁的孩子来说，她的表达力是非常强的。<br>\n I\'m a little deaf, please articulate your words carefully.<br>     我有些耳聋，请把话仔细地说清楚。<br>'),(540,'articulation','','','','','n. 关节,接合,清晰发音',' As he drank more wine his articulation became worse.<br>     他又多喝了些酒, 口齿也就更不清楚了.<br>'),(541,'artifacts','','','','','n. 史前古器物',' Found echoes of past civilizations while examining artifacts in the Middle East.<br>     在调查中东的史前古器物时，发现了旧时文明的遗迹<br>\n Fixed the date of the ancient artifacts.<br>     确定这件古代文化遗物的时间<br>'),(542,'artificial','','','','','a. 人造的,虚伪的,武断的',' I can\'t stand his artificial smiles.<br>     我受不了他的假笑。<br>\n This dress is made of artificial fibers.<br>     这件衣服是人造纤维的。<br>'),(543,'artificially','','','','','ad. 人工地,人为地,不自然地',' A naturally occurring or artificially produced radioactive element.<br>     放射性元素自然产生或人为制造的放射性元素<br>'),(544,'artillery','','','','','n. (军)火炮,大炮,炮兵(部队)',' Artillery fire caused heavy loss.<br>     炮火造成重大损失。<br>\n The artillery did great execution.<br>     这种大炮的威力很大。<br>'),(545,'artist','','','','artists','n. 艺术家,美术家',' His dream of becoming an artist has been fulfilled.<br>     他成为一个艺术家的梦想实现了。<br>\n She is a consummate artist.<br>     她是个技艺高超的艺术家。<br>'),(546,'artistic','','','','','a. 艺术的',' She is very artistic.<br>     她酷爱艺术。<br>\n I talked to many artistic people: writers, dancers and filmmakers.<br>     我同许多艺术界的人们谈过话，其中有作家、 舞蹈家、电影制片人。<br>'),(547,'artwork','','','','','n. 艺术品,美术品',' Made of gold and ivory, as certain pieces of sculpture or artwork in ancient Greece.<br>     由黄金和象牙制成的由黄金和象牙制成的，如古希腊某些雕刻或工艺品<br>\n A section of a painting or other piece of artwork; a detail.<br>     细节绘画或其它艺术作品的一部分；细节<br>'),(548,'as','','','','','ad. 同样地,像<br>\nprep. 当做<br>\nconj. 当...之时,像...一样,因为',' It is just as you like.<br>     事情就如你喜欢的那样。<br>\n He can run as fast as I can.<br>     他能跑得和我一样快。<br>'),(549,'ascend','ascended','ascended','ascending','','v. 上升,攀登',' The airplane ascended higher and higher.<br>     飞机渐渐升高。<br>\n The point of greatest intensity or force in an ascending series or progression; a culmination.<br>     顶点，最高点在上升的序列或过程中达到的最大强度或力量；极点<br>'),(550,'ascending','','','','','上升的,升序',' Rising in the sky; ascending.<br>     上升的升到天空中的；上升的<br>\n We watched the mists ascending from the valley below.<br>     我们看著薄雾从下面的山谷中升起.<br>'),(551,'ascent','','','','ascents','n. 上升,上坡路',' Who was the first man to make an ascent in a balloon?<br>     第一个乘气球升空的人是谁?<br>\n The last part of the ascent is very steep.<br>     最后一段上坡路很陡。<br>'),(552,'ascertain','ascertained','ascertained','ascertaining','','v. 确定,探知',' The detective was trying to ascertain exactly who was at the party.<br>     这个侦探试图查明都有谁参加了聚会。<br>\n I ascertain that he was murdered.<br>     我确定他是被谋杀的。<br>'),(553,'ASCII','','','','','美国信息交换标准码',' An ASCII control character, end of medium.<br>     一种ASCII码控制字符，媒体结束符。<br>'),(554,'ascites','','','','','n. 腹水',''),(555,'ascribe','ascribed','ascribed','ascribing','','v. 归因于,归咎于',' This song is often ascribed to Bach.<br>     这首歌曲常被说成是巴赫做的。<br>\n He ascribes his success to good luck.<br>     他把他的成功归功于幸运。<br>'),(556,'asepsis','','','','','n. 无菌,无菌操作',''),(557,'aseptic','','','','','a. 无菌的,洁净的',' An aseptic smile.<br>     漠然的微笑<br>'),(558,'ash','','','','','n. 灰,灰烬',' Don\'t drop 