>\n Such a questionable assertion is sure to provoke criticism.<br>     这种有问题的主张肯定会招致非议。<br>'),(579,'assess','assessed','assessed','assessing','','v. 估定,评定',' She look at the house and assess its market value.<br>     他看了看房子并估算了其市场价值。<br>\n Meanwhile, I am arranging for Mr. Smith, one of our inspectors, to call and assess the damage.<br>     本人同时正安排我行检查员史密斯先生，拜访阁下并计算损失。<br>'),(580,'assessment','','','','assessments','n. 估价,评估',' Continuous assessment is made of all students\' work.<br>     对全体学生的功课作出连贯性的评定。<br>\n Your assessment is substantially correct.<br>     你的估计基本正确.<br>'),(581,'assessor','','','','','n. 估计财产的人,确定税款的人',' The slaves were property they　were on the tax books along with horses and cats, the valuation　of each slave written next to his name in the tax assessors books.<br>     当时，奴隶只是一件财产，他们和马儿、猫儿一起列在税册上，在收税人的册子里，每个奴隶的名字旁边写着他们的价值。<br>'),(582,'asset','','','','assets','n. 资产,有用的东西,优点,长处',' The firm has an important asset in the person of the director of research.<br>     公司有一巨大财富，就是研究部主任这个人。<br>\n The tennis player\'s speed is his great asset.<br>     那个网球运动员动作迅速, 这是他的一大优势.<br>'),(583,'assets','','','','','n. 资产',' If your liabilities exceed your assets, you may go bankrupt.<br>     如果你所负的债超过你的资产，你就会破产。<br>\n The remaining assets of a business after all liabilities have been deducted; net worth.<br>     资产净值一个企业在扣除了所有的债务后所余资产；净值<br>'),(584,'assign','assigned','assigned','assigning','assigns','v. 分配,指派<br>\nn.[计算机] DOS 命令将驱动器符重指向第二个驱动器符',' All the students are assigned to suitable jobs.<br>     所有的学生都分到了合适的工作。<br>\n They assigned his odd behavior to his ill health.<br>     他们把他的古怪行为归因于健康不佳。<br>'),(585,'assigned','','','','','v. 分配(转让,把...归因于)<br>\na. 给定的(赋予的,已知的)',' They assigned his odd behavior to his ill health.<br>     他们把他的古怪行为归因于健康不佳。<br>\n The two large classrooms have been assigned to us.<br>     这两间大教室已经分配给我们了.<br>'),(586,'assignment','','','','assignments','n. 分配,功课,任务,被指定的(课外)作业;(分派的)任务,委派',' He is the best man who can finish the assignment.<