。<br>\n This is one of the few gratifications of an otherwise boring job.<br>     这是枯燥的工作中少有的一项乐趣。<br>'),(1002,'born','','','','','a. 天生的<br>\nvbl. 出生',' The baby was born on 8 o\'clock.<br>     婴儿在8点钟出生。<br>\n I\'ve never heard such nonsense in all my born days!<br>     我一生中从未听到过这种胡言乱语。<br>'),(1003,'borrow','borrowed','borrowed','borrowing','','v. 借,借入,借用',' May I borrow your pen?<br>     我可以借用你的钢笔吗？<br>\n They are poor but proud; they never borrow money or ask for help.<br>     他们虽穷但很自重，他们从不向人借钱或求助。<br>'),(1004,'borrowing','','','','','n. 借款,贷款',' Your proposal will necessitate borrowing more money.<br>     依你的建议就必须增加借款。<br>\n On top of borrowing 50, he asked me to lend him my car.<br>     他向我借了50英镑, 此外还向我借汽车.<br>'),(1005,'bosom','bosomed','bosomed','bosoming','bosoms','n. 胸部',' The girl was fortunate enough to have her mother as a bosom friend.<br>     这个女孩非常幸运，她的妈妈是她的知心朋友。<br>\n The young mother held the baby to her bosom.<br>     那位年轻的母亲把孩子抱在怀里。<br>'),(1006,'boss','','','','','n. 老板,上司<br>\nv. 指挥,控制',' He was dismissed by his boss.<br>     他被他的老板开除了。<br>\n Tom likes to boss younger children.<br>     汤姆喜欢对较年幼的孩子发号施令。<br>'),(1007,'Boston','','','','','n. 波士顿(美国城市)',' I\'m flying to Boston on the shuttle.<br>     我将乘穿梭班机去波士顿.<br>\n He meets his future father-in-law during his visit to boston.<br>     他在波士顿小住期间遇见了他未来的岳父。<br>'),(1008,'both','','','','','a. 两者的<br>\nad. 两者都<br>\nint. 两者',' He is both a soldier and a poet.<br>     他既是个战士，又是个诗人。<br>\n Both are good.<br>     两者都好。<br>'),(1009,'bother','bothered','bothered','bothering','','v. 烦扰',' Don\'t bother yourself about me; I am doing quite well.<br>     别为我操心，我一切都好。<br>\n It bothers me that he can be so insensitive.<br>     他这样麻木不仁，我心里很不痛快。<br>'),(1010,'bothersome','','','','','a. 讨厌的',' An obtuse, boring, or bothersome person; a pest.<br>     讨厌的人愚钝的、无聊的或讨厌的人；害人精<br>'),(1011,'bottle','bottled','bottled','bottling','bottles','n. 瓶子',' They drank a whole bottle!<br>     他们喝了一整瓶酒！<br>\n Why don\'t we crack open a bottle of champagne to celebrate?<br>     我们何不开瓶香槟酒庆祝一下呢？<br>'),(1012,'bottleneck','','','','','n. 瓶颈',''),(1013,'bottom','bottomed','bottomed','bottoming','bottoms','n. 底部;屁股，臀部<br>\na. 底部的',' They sent the enemy ship to the bottom of the sea.<br>     他们把敌舰击沉。<br>\n He was always bottom of the class in maths.<br>     他的数学成绩在班上总是垫底。<br>'),(1014,'bough','','','','boughs','n. 大树枝',' The bough was loaded with fruit.<br>     树枝上果实累累。<br>\n The bird settled on the topmost bough.<br>     这只鸟儿在最高的权枝上停了下来。<br>'),(1015,'bounce','bounced','bounced','bouncing','bounces','n. 跳,反跃,弹力<br>\nv. 弹跳,使...跳',' I bounced the baby on my knee.<br>     我把婴儿放在膝上上下颠着。<br>\n The ball hit the wall and bounced off it.<br>     球打在墙上又反弹回来。<br>'),(1016,'bound','','','','','n. 跳跃,界限,范围<br>\na. 受约束的,装订的,有义务的<br>\nv. 跳跃',' It\'s bound to rain soon.<br>     过一会儿肯定会下雨。<br>\n You are not legally bound to answer these questions.<br>     在法律上，你没有义务非回答这些问题不可。<br>'),(1017,'boundary','','','','boundaries','n. 分界线,边界',' They marked the boundaries of the football fields.<br>     他们画出了足球场地的边界。<br>\n The ball ran (ie rolled) to the boundary.<br>     球向著边线滚去.<br>'),(1018,'bounds','','','','','n. 界限',' The exceeding of due bounds or limits.<br>     越界超过正当的界限或限制<br>\n Our joy knew no bounds. Your remarks exceed the bounds of reason.<br>     我们快乐无比。你的评论超出了合理界限<br>'),(1019,'bounty','','','','bounties','n. 慷慨,宽大,恩惠',' He was awarded a cash bounty by his boss.<br>     他的上司奖给他一笔现金。<br>\n I think we shall drink to the bounty of nature.<br>     我想我们应该为造物主的慷慨赐予而乾杯。<br>'),(1020,'bouquet','','','','bouquets','n. 花束<br>\nn. 酒香',' In his speech there were bouquets for everyone who had helped him.<br>     在他的演讲里，他赞美了每一位帮助他的人。<br>\n The characteristic smell of a wine or liqueur; bouquet.<br>     芳香葡萄酒或酒有特点的气味；酒香<br>'),(1021,'boutique','','','','','n. 专卖流行衣服的小商店',' Chic clothes; a chic boutique.<br>     时髦的服装；一件雅致的饰物<br>\n Boutique clothes; boutique food.<br>     小店服装；小店食品<br>'),(1022,'bow','','','','','n. 弓,船头,鞠躬<br>\nv. 鞠躬,弯腰',' He moved aside for her with a polite bow.<br>     他礼貌地鞠躬，退避一旁让她过去。<br>\n Every one bowed as the Queen walked into the room.<br>     女王走进房间时，每个人都鞠躬致敬。<br>'),(1023,'bowel','boweled','boweled','boweling','bowels','n. 肠',' What is it like in the bowels of the earth?<br>     地球内部是什么样子？<br>\n Do you have a bowel movement today?<br>     你今天上过厕所吗？<br>'),(1024,'bowl','','','','','n. 碗<br>\nv. 打保龄球<br>\nvt. 把(球)投向球瓶',' There is a fruit bowl on the table.<br>     桌上有个水果盘。<br>\n His grandfather gave her an earthenware bowl.<br>     他的祖父给了她一个陶碗。<br>'),(1025,'bowling','','','','','n. 保龄球',' An opening made to fit a thumb, as in a bowling ball.<br>     拇指孔（保龄球）上供拇指插入的孔<br>\n We were bowling along (the motorway) at seventy miles per hour.<br>     我们以每小时七十英里的速度（在高速公路上）飞驰.<br>'),(1026,'box','','','','','n. 盒子,箱<br>\nv. 装...入盒中',' She gave him a box on his ears.<br>     她打了他一耳光。<br>\n He has eaten a whole box of chocolates.<br>     他吃了一整盒巧克力。<br>'),(1027,'boxing','','','','','n. 拳击',' He was done out of the right of boxing.<br>     他被取消了拳击比赛资格。<br>\n I enjoyed all the sports with the exception of boxing.<br>     除了拳击, 我喜欢所有的运动。<br>'),(1028,'boy','','','','boys','n. 男孩',' That boy is about ten years old.<br>     那个男孩大约有十岁。<br>\n Don\'t cry, you are a big boy now.<br>     别哭，你现在已经是大男孩了。<br>'),(1029,'boycott','boycotted','boycotted','boycotting','boycotts','v.抵制（贸易）；不参加。',''),(1030,'BPI','','','','','每英寸位数',''),(1031,'brace','braced','braced','bracing','brace','n. 支柱,曲柄,大括号<br>\nv. 绷紧,顶住,（为困难或坏事）做准备',' The struts are firmly braced.<br>     那些支柱上得很牢固。<br>\n We braced ourselves for a bumpy landing.<br>     我们已做好准备, 著陆时会很颠簸.<br>'),(1032,'brachial','','','','','a. 臂的,上臂的',''),(1033,'bracket','bracketed','bracketed','bracketing','brackets','n. 支架,括号',' Put your name in brackets at the top of each page.<br>     把你的名字填写在每页上端的括号内。<br>\n The worker fixed a bracket on the wall.<br>     工人在墙上固定了一个支架。<br>'),(1034,'bracketed','','','','','加括号的',' The worker fixed a bracket on the wall.<br>     工人在墙上固定了一个支架。<br>\n It\'s wrong to bracket him with the extremists in his party his views are very moderate.<br>     把他跟他们党内的极端分子等同看待是不对的--他的观点其实很温和.<br>'),(1035,'brackets','','','','','括号,大括号',' Put your name in brackets at the top of each page.<br>     把你的名字填写在每页上端的括号内。<br>\n The brackets want an extra screw.<br>     托架需要再加一个螺钉。<br>'),(1036,'brain','brained','brained','braining','brains','n. 脑(子)<br>\nv. 打...的脑袋',' She has a good brain.<br>     她很有头脑。<br>\n Brains are more than just education.<br>     有头脑不仅指受过教育。<br>'),(1037,'brainstorm','','','','','v. 集体自由讨论<br>\nvi. 动脑筋,出主意,想办法,献计献策<br>\nvt. 集思广益以寻找(解决难题的方法等)',' I do some brainstorm.<br>     我开动脑筋。<br>\n The marketing team brainstorm for hour in designing the marketing campaign for the new product.<br>     行销小组脑力激荡多时，集思广益，设计新产品的行销策略。<br>'),(1038,'brake','','','','','n. 煞车<br>\nv. 煞车',' The driver braked his car suddenly.<br>     司机突然煞车。<br>\n The brake doesn\'t grip properly.<br>     刹车不灵了。<br>'),(1039,'branch','branched','branched','branching','branches','n. 分枝,树枝<br>\nv. 分枝<br>\nvi. 分支',' Mr. Smith works in an executive branch of the government.<br>     史密斯先生在政府的行政部门工作。<br>\n The road to the village branches off on the right.<br>     通往该村的道路向右转为一条小路。<br>'),(1040,'branches','','','','','授',' She has lopped branches off yesterday.<br>     她昨天已把树枝修剪过了。<br>\n Follow the main road until it branches, and then turn to the right.<br>     顺着这条大路走，在路的分岔口向右拐。<br>'),(1041,'branching','','','','','分支（的）',' The connection of separate parts of a branching system to form a network, as of leaf veins, blood vessels, or a river and its branches.<br>     并接，联结分支系统的不同部分结合后形成一个网络，如叶脉，血管，或河流及其支流<br>\n His mind kept branching off into the contemplation of side issues.<br>     他的脑子老是岔开去想一些枝节问题。<br>'),(1042,'brand','branded','branded','branding','brands','n. 商标,牌子,烙印<br>\nv. 打烙印,铭刻',' He has his own brand of humor.<br>     他有他独特的幽默感。<br>\n These frightful experiences are branded on his memory.<br>     这些可怕的经历深深印入他的记忆。<br>'),(1043,'brandy','brandied','brandied','brandying','brandies','n. 白兰地酒',' The two are fine brandies.<br>     那是两种优质白兰地。<br>\n Two brandies and soda, please.<br>     劳驾，来两杯白兰地加苏打水。<br>'),(1044,'brashness','','','','','n. 莽撞,无礼,轻率',''),(1045,'brass','','','','brasses','n. 黄铜',' How do you have the brass to say that?<br>     你怎么有脸那么说呢？<br>\n The brass is too loud.<br>     铜管乐器的声音太响了。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (1046,'brave','braved','braved','braving','','a. 勇敢的<br>\nv. 勇敢地面对(危险等)<br>\nvt. 抵抗',' Let us remember the brave who died for the peace of the world.<br>     让我们永远怀念为世界和平献身的勇士们。<br>\n He braved his father\'s displeasure by marrying that girl.<br>     他不顾父亲不高兴，娶了那个女孩子。<br>'),(1047,'bravery','','','','braveries','n. 勇敢',' His bravery was seen by everyone when he saved the child from the burning house.<br>     他从失火的房子里救出小孩时的那种勇敢，是人人都见到的。<br>\n The soldier earned a medal for bravery.<br>     这名战士因作战勇敢而获得了勋章。<br>'),(1048,'breach','breached','breached','breaching','breaches','n. 裂口,违背',' Your action is a breach of our agreement.<br>     你的行动违反了我们的协议。<br>\n You are in breach of your contract.<br>     你违反了你签的合同。<br>'),(1049,'bread','breaded','breaded','breading','','n. 面包',' He earned his bread by writing novels.<br>     他靠写小说维生。<br>\n The bread is baking in the oven.<br>     烤箱里正在烤面包。<br>'),(1050,'breadth','','','','breadths','n. 宽度',' She is a woman of great breadth of mind.<br>     她是一个胸怀非常广阔的女子。<br>\n The area can easily be worked out if you know the length and the breadth.<br>     如果你知道长度和宽度的话，计算面积就很容易了。<br>'),(1051,'break','broke','broken','breaking','breaks','n. 休息,中断,破裂<br>\nv. 打破,弄破,弄坏',' There is a break during the performance for the audience to take a rest.<br>     演出中有一次中场休息，让听众们稍事休息。<br>\n The cold weather at last broke at the end of March.<br>     寒冷的天气终于在三月末结束了。<br>'),(1052,'breakdown','','','','breakdowns','n. 崩溃,故障',' Unless he stops driving himself like this he\'ll have a breakdown.<br>     他要是总这样拚命干下去是吃不消的.<br>\n His frequent depressions were the prelude to a complete mental breakdown.<br>     他经常抑郁寡欢, 後来精神完全崩溃了.<br>'),(1053,'breakfast','breakfasted','breakfasted','breakfasting','breakfasts','n. 早餐<br>\nv. (吃早餐<br>\nvi. 进早餐',' Would you like breakfast now?<br>     你想要现在吃早餐吗？<br>\n We breakfasted early.<br>     我们很早吃早餐。<br>'),(1054,'breakpoint','','','','','断点',''),(1055,'breakthrough','','','','','n. 突破',' The scientists strive for a breakthrough in cancer research.<br>     科学家们力争在癌症研究方面有个突破。<br>\n Several of our research discoveries have been adapted for commercial use, and one particular breakthrough in linear hydraulics is now being used by every oil company in the country.<br>     我们的几项研究发明经转化已被应用于商业领域，特别是在线性液压方面的一项突破性成果现在被国内各家石油公司采用。<br>'),(1056,'breast','breasted','breasted','breasting','breasts','n. 胸脯,乳房<br>\nvt. 挺胸迎...而上',' His guilty conscience forced him to make a clean breast of everything.<br>     他的内疚使得他把一切和盘托出。<br>\n They had chicken breast for supper.<br>     他们晚饭吃鸡胸肉。<br>'),(1057,'breath','','','','breaths','n. 呼吸,气息',' I was out of breath after running for the bus.<br>     我因为追赶公共汽车，弄得上气不接下气。<br>\n There is a breath of autumn in the air today.<br>     今天的天气已露出了一丝秋天的气息。<br>'),(1058,'breathe','breathed','breathed','breathing','','呼吸',' His enthusiasm breathed new life into the company.<br>     他的热情给公司注入了新的生命。<br>\n Fish cannot breathe out of water.<br>     鱼离开水就不能呼吸。<br>'),(1059,'breed','bred','bred','breeding','breeds','n. 品种,族类<br>\nv. 养育,繁殖,引起',' I had bred a dozen of chickens.<br>     我饲养了12只小鸡。<br>\n The bear bred two cubs.<br>     这只熊生了两只小熊。<br>'),(1060,'breeze','breezed','breezed','breezing','breezes','n. 微风,轻而易举的事',' She breezed along, smiling at everyone.<br>     她轻盈地向前走去，对每个人都嫣然含笑。<br>\n We are enjoying the cool breeze that comes from the lake.<br>     我们享受着湖面上吹来的凉爽微风。<br>'),(1061,'breve','','','','','短音符号',''),(1062,'brew','brewed','brewed','brewing','brews','n. 酿造酒,蕴酿<br>\nv. 酿造,蕴酿',' They are brewing a plot behind the scenes.<br>     他们正在幕后策划一个阴谋。<br>\n The tea is brewing and will be served soon.<br>     茶正在泡，一会儿就送来。<br>'),(1063,'bribe','bribed','bribed','bribing','bribes','n. 贿赂<br>\nv. 贿赂',' The businessman offers bribes to him.<br>     这个商人向他行贿。<br>\n He bribed the police to let him go free.<br>     他贿赂警察把他放了。<br>'),(1064,'brick','bricked','bricked','bricking','bricks','a. 砖似的<br>\nn. 砖<br>\nv. 用砖围砌,用砖填补<br>\nvt. (up)用砖砌,用砖堵住',' His new house was built by himself, brick by brick.<br>     他的新房子是他自己一块砖一块砖砌起来的。<br>\n All the windows were bricked up.<br>     所有的窗户都用砖堵住了。<br>'),(1065,'bride','','','','brides','n. 新娘',' The bride wore a beautiful white dress.<br>     新娘穿了一身美丽的白色礼服。<br>\n We must drink to the health of the bride.<br>     我们要为新娘的健康干杯。<br>'),(1066,'bridegroom','','','','bridegrooms','n. 新郎',' Her bridegroom is a handsome young man.<br>     她的新郎是一个英俊的年轻人。<br>\n Good wishes showered (down) on the bride and bridegroom.<br>     大家纷纷向新娘新郎祝福.<br>'),(1067,'bridge','','','','','n. 桥<br>\nv. 渡过,架桥',' They use a bridge to measure the impedance of the transducer.<br>     他们用电桥来测量传感器的阻抗。<br>\n Politeness will bridge over many difficulties.<br>     举止文雅会使你渡过许多难关。<br>'),(1068,'bridges','','','','','布里奇斯',' This city is noted for its various bridges.<br>     这个城市因为各种桥梁而著称。<br>\n The river Thames is spanned by many bridges.<br>     泰晤士河上有很多桥.<br>'),(1069,'bridging','','','','','桥接的',''),(1070,'brief','briefed','briefed','briefing','briefs','n. 摘要,简报,公事包<br>\na. 简短的,简洁的<br>\nv. 对...作简报,摘要',' Please be brief because I am in a hurry.<br>     我有急事，请长话短说。<br>\n He drew up a brief for his speech.<br>     他起草了一份讲话的概要。<br>'),(1071,'briefcase','','','','briefcases','n. 公文包',' They knocked him down and robbed him of his briefcase.<br>     他们把他打倒在地，抢走了他的公文包。<br>\n He put all the files into his briefcase.<br>     他将所有文件都装进公文包。<br>'),(1072,'briefly','','','','','ad. 简短地',' He was briefly associated with that organization.<br>     他同那个组织有过短时间的联系。<br>\n Briefly, I think we should accept his offer.<br>     简而言之，我认为我们应该接受他的提议。<br>'),(1073,'bright','','','','brights','a. 明亮的,阳光的<br>\nad. 亮',' He is not bright, but he always works hard.<br>     他并不聪明，但工作总是勤勤恳恳。<br>\n What a nice bright day!<br>     今天天气多晴朗！<br>'),(1074,'brighten','brightened','brightened','brightening','','v. 变亮,使...生辉',' These flowers will brighten up your garden.<br>     这些花会使你的花园增色。<br>\n The sky/weather is brightening.<br>     天空[天气]转晴.<br>'),(1075,'brightness','','','','',