 the validity of a will.<br>     遗嘱检验文件遗嘱有效的法律证明文件<br>\n A certification on an affidavit declaring when, where, and before whom it was sworn.<br>     宣誓证明附在宣誓书上的证明，声明何时、何地、在何人监誓下进行宣誓<br>'),(1341,'certify','certified','certified','certifying','','v. 证明,保证',' I certify that he has received your money.<br>     我证明他已经收到了你的钱。<br>\n I can certify to her honesty.<br>     我可以证明她是诚实的。<br>'),(1342,'CG','','','','','心(动)电图描记器[缩]',''),(1343,'chain','chained','chained','chaining','chains','n. 链,连锁,束缚<br>\nv. 用铁练锁住,束缚,囚禁',' I bought this loaf of bread in the chain store opposite the street.<br>     我在街道对面的连锁商店里买了这只面包。<br>\n He is chained to his work.<br>     他工作忙得不能分身。<br>'),(1344,'chained','','','','','链接的',' He is chained to his work.<br>     他工作忙得不能分身。<br>\n He chained his bicycle to the post.<br>     他把自行车拴到柱子上。<br>'),(1345,'chair','chaired','chaired','chairing','chairs','n. 椅子,席位,讲座<br>\nv. 担任（某事务）的主席',' The old chair gave a groan when the fat man sat down on it.<br>     那个胖子坐下时，旧椅子发出嘎吱的响声。<br>\n Father sits in the same chair every evening.<br>     父亲每晚都坐在同一张椅子上，<br>'),(1346,'chairman','','','','chairmen','n. 主席,会长',' He was elected chairman of the meeting.<br>     他被选为会议主席。<br>\n We were appalled when we heard that the chairman had been murdered.<br>     听说主席被谋杀，我们都吓坏了。<br>'),(1347,'chalk','chalked','chalked','chalking','chalks','n. 粉笔<br>\nv. 用粉笔写,记录',' The teacher wrote on the blackboard with a piece of chalk.<br>     老师用一支粉笔在黑板上写字。<br>\n Dust yourself down you\'re covered in chalk.<br>     把你自己身上掸掸--上面都是粉笔末.<br>'),(1348,'challenge','challenged','challenged','challenging','challenges','n. 挑战<br>\nv. 向...挑战',' Nowadays no one will challenge the fact that the earth is round.<br>     现在没有人会对地球是圆的这一事实提出异议。<br>\n This career offers a challenge.<br>     这份职业具有挑战性。<br>'),(1349,'chamber','chambered','chambered','chambering','chambers','n. 室,房间,会所,枪膛<br>\nv. 放在枪膛内,关在室内',' The judge met the two lawyers in his chambers.<br>     法官在他的办公室里会见了两位律师。<br>\n In Britain the upper Chamber is