n chaos.<br>     电力供应中断，城市陷于混乱之中。<br>\n He sees that human stupidity and greed are about to plunge Europe into chaos.<br>     他看到人间的愚蠢和贪婪即将使欧洲陷入一片混乱。<br>'),(1359,'chap','','','','','n. 小伙子<br>\nv. 皲裂',' His chapped lips were bleeding.<br>     他干裂的嘴唇流出血来。<br>\n Poor chap, his wife has just died.<br>     不幸的小伙子啊, 他刚刚死了妻子.<br>'),(1360,'chapel','','','','chapels','n. 小礼拜堂,礼拜',' They go to chapel every Sunday evening.<br>     他们每个星期天晚上做礼拜。<br>\n The ghost of Lady Margaret is supposed to haunt this chapel.<br>     据说玛格丽特女士的鬼魂常在这个礼拜堂出没.<br>'),(1361,'chapter','chaptered','chaptered','chaptering','chapters','n. 章,回,篇',' I had nearly finished chapter 8.<br>     我就要把第8章看完了。<br>\n The opening chapter gives a general overview of the subject.<br>     开篇第一章是对主题的概述.<br>'),(1362,'char','','','','','n. 木炭(散工,茶,字符)<br>\nvt 烧成炭(做散工)',''),(1363,'character','charactered','charactered','charactering','characters','n. 个性,字符,人物',' I wish this book was written in bigger character.<br>     我希望这本书的字再大一点儿。<br>\n The statements were of political character.<br>     这种声明具有政治性质。<br>'),(1364,'characteristic','','','','characteristics','a. 特有的,典型的<br>\nn. 特性,特征,特色',' Sympathy is the feeling characteristic of mankind.<br>     同情心是人类特有的感情。<br>\n Ambition is a characteristic of all successful businessmen.<br>     雄心勃勃是所有成功生意人的共同特点。<br>'),(1365,'characterize','characterized','characterized','characterizing','','v. 表示...的特色,赋予...特色',' Your work is characterized by lack of attention to details.<br>     你的工作特点是缺乏对细节的注意。<br>\n He may be characterized as a man of hobbies.<br>     他可以被称作是一个有癖好的人。<br>'),(1366,'charge','charged','charged','charging','charges','n. 电荷,指控,费用<br>\nv. 控诉,加罪于,要价,赊帐,充电,管理',' As long as you\'ve paid in advance we won\'t charge you for delivery.<br>     只要你预先付款，我们就不收你送货费。<br>\n He became his uncle\'s charge after his parents died.<br>     他在父母去世後，由叔父抚养。<br>'),(1367,'charity','','','','charities','a. 仁慈的、宽厚的<br>\nn. 慈善机关(团体),仁慈,宽厚',' She was always very generous in her charity.<br>     她行