ion.<br>     我讨厌这种肤浅的感情。<br>\n Her shoes look cheap.<br>     她的那双鞋看上去很便宜。<br>'),(1378,'cheat','cheated','cheated','cheating','cheats','n. 骗子,欺骗行为<br>\nv. 欺骗,作弊',' His father was cheated of his land.<br>     他的父亲被人骗走了地产。<br>\n He never cheats to pass examination.<br>     他考试从不作弊。<br>'),(1379,'check','checked','checked','checking','checks','n. 检查,支票,阻止物<br>\nv. 检查,阻止,核对',' I\'m just going to check in these books at the library.<br>     我要去图书馆还这些书。<br>\n They checked their steps.<br>     他们突然停住脚步。<br>'),(1380,'checker','','','','','n. 检验器(检查员,方格)<br>\nvt 制成方格式(交错)',' The checker checks on the quality of our products.<br>     检查者检查我们的产品的质量。<br>\n The checker made a check on all the victims\' friends.<br>     检查者对所有受害者的朋友进行了调查。<br>'),(1381,'checkout','','','','','n. 检查(调整,验算,检查输出结果,工时扣除)',' Be there an express checkout service?<br>     有没有快速退房手续的服务？<br>'),(1382,'checkpoint','','','','','n. 检查站',''),(1383,'checkup','','','','checkups','n. 审查,检定,健康检查',' For the present we are made a general checkup.<br>     目前，我们正做总的检查。<br>\n I went to see my doctor and had a checkup yesterday.<br>     昨天我去请医生作了一次检查。<br>'),(1384,'cheek','cheeked','cheeked','cheeking','cheeks','n. 面颊,脸蛋<br>\nv. 粗鲁地向...讲',' She kissed him on both cheeks.<br>     她吻了他的双颊。<br>\n I\'m going to put up with your cheek!<br>     我可不想容忍你这个厚脸皮。<br>'),(1385,'cheer','cheered','cheered','cheering','cheers','n. 愉快,激励,欢呼<br>\nv. 加油,鼓舞,快活起来',' He\'s always full of cheer in summer.<br>     夏天他总是高高兴兴的。<br>\n They cheered loudly for their football team.<br>     他们大声地为自己的足球队喊加油。<br>'),(1386,'cheerful','','','','','a. 高兴的,快乐的',' She remained cheerful throughout the trip.<br>     旅行中她始终兴致勃勃。<br>\n I have a cozy and cheerful room.<br>     我有一个舒适的令人愉快的房间。<br>'),(1387,'cheese','','','','','n. 乳酪,干酪',' There are many kinds of cheese.<br>     奶酪有许多种。<br>\n We had a homely meal of bread and cheese.<br>     我们吃了一顿面包加乳酪的家常便餐。<br>'),(1388,'chef','','','','chefs','n. 厨师',' I commended the chef on the excellent meal. I later wrote to commend him to his employer, the restaurant owner.<br>     我称赞厨师做的菜味道好. 随後我给雇用他的餐馆老板写了封信表扬他.<br>\n The chef sprinkle poppy seed on the cake.<br>     厨师往蛋糕上撒罂粟籽。<br>'),(1389,'chemical','','','','chemicals','a. 化学的<br>\nn. 化学制品',' We are doing a chemical experiment.<br>     我们正在做化学实验。<br>\n My major is the subject of chemical engineering.<br>     我的专业是化学工程学。<br>'),(1390,'chemist','','','','chemists','n. 化学家,药剂师',' I bought aspirin at the chemist\'s on the corner.<br>     我在大街拐角的药房买了阿司匹林。<br>\n The chemist made a mistake when making up the prescription.<br>     药剂师配错了药.<br>'),(1391,'chemistry','','','','chemistries','n. 化学',' We have three periods of chemistry a week.<br>     我们一星期三节化学课。<br>\n I prefer chemistry to physics.<br>     我喜欢化学甚于物理。<br>'),(1392,'chemotherapy','','','','','n. 化学疗法',''),(1393,'cheque','','','','cheques','n. 支票',' Payments by cheque easily outnumbered cash transactions.<br>     用支票付款在数量上大大超过现金交易。<br>\n They forged their manager\'s signature on the cheque.<br>     他们在支票上伪造了经理的签名。<br>'),(1394,'cherish','cherished','cherished','cherishing','','v. 珍爱,抚育,珍藏',' One of our cherished privileges is the right of free speech.<br>     我们所珍视的权利之一是言论自由。<br>\n A mother cherishes her baby.<br>     母亲疼爱孩子。<br>'),(1395,'cherry','','','','cherries','n. 樱桃',' He went to the cherry orchard to see flowers.<br>     他去樱桃园看花。<br>\n We have different pies, such as apple, cherry, and strawberry pies.<br>     我们有不同的派，例如苹果、樱桃和草莓派。<br>'),(1396,'chess','','','','','n. 国际象棋',' Chess is played by two people.<br>     国际象棋是两个人玩的。<br>\n I like to play chess with my father.<br>     我喜欢和爸爸一起下国际象棋。<br>'),(1397,'chest','','','','chests','n. 胸,胸部,衣柜',' He put some food into the ice chest.<br>     他把一些食物放进冰箱里。<br>\n The doctor gave him an examination to see if he had chest trouble.<br>     医生给他做了检查，看他是否有肺病。<br>'),(1398,'chestnut','','','','chestnuts','n. 栗子<br>\na. 栗色的',' These chestnuts are of bright reddish-brown.<br>     这些栗子是鲜亮的红褐色。<br>\n Grab yourself a roast chestnut.<br>     你自己拿一只烤栗子