稚。<br>'),(1410,'children','','','','','n. 孩子们(child的复数形式)',' It\'s very important to teach the children about road safety.<br>     把交通安全常识教给孩子们是非常重要的。<br>\n The children are rushing about.<br>     孩子们到处乱闯。<br>'),(1411,'chill','chilled','chilled','chilling','chills','n. 寒冷,寒意,失意<br>\na. 寒冷的,冷漠的<br>\nv. 使...寒心,冷冻',' The sight sent a chill to her heart.<br>     这情景使她心寒。<br>\n There was a chill in the air this morning.<br>     今天早上有点冷冰冰的。<br>'),(1412,'chilly','','','','','a. 寒冷的',' He had a chilly welcome of our coming.<br>     他冷淡地迎接我们的到来。<br>\n It\'s a chilly morning.<br>     这是一个寒冷的早晨。<br>'),(1413,'chimney','','','','chimneys','n. 烟囱',' The factory chimneys poured smoke into the air.<br>     工厂的烟囱向空中排烟。<br>\n Volumes of black smoke poured fromthe chimney.<br>     烟囱里冒出来团团黑烟.<br>'),(1414,'chimpanzee','','','','','n. 黑猩猩',' Some folks seem to have descend from the chimpanzee much later than others.<br>     有些人，看来像是比其他人晚了好久才从黑猩猩分支而传下来的后裔。<br>'),(1415,'chin','chinned','chinned','chinning','chins','n. 下巴,颏',' He was so fat that he had a double chin.<br>     他胖得有双下巴了。<br>\n His chin was covered with bristles.<br>     他的下巴上长满了胡子茬。<br>'),(1416,'china','','','','','n. 中国,瓷器',' China is an oriental country with a long history.<br>     中国是一个有着悠久历史的东方国家。<br>\n This set of ancient china is invaluable.<br>     这套古瓷器非常珍贵。<br>'),(1417,'Chinese','','','','Chinese','a. 中国的<br>\nn. 汉语,中国人',' Chinese people are working hard to make the country richer and more beautiful.<br>     中国人民正在努力工作，把国家建设得更加富饶美丽。<br>\n I\'m proud I am Chinese.<br>     我骄傲我是中国人。<br>'),(1418,'chip','chipped','chipped','chipping','chips','n. 薄片,芯片<br>\nv. 削,切,削成碎片',' The entire content of a book will be located on a single silicon chip.<br>     整本书的内容只用一片硅芯片就可以装下。<br>\n The paint has chipped off where the table touches the wall.<br>     桌子接触墙壁的地方漆皮已剥落。<br>'),(1419,'chisel','chiseled','chiseled','chiseling','chisels','n. 凿子<br>\nv. 用凿子刻,雕,凿<br>\nvt. 凿,雕,凿子,錾子',' He cut the figure of a woman out of that rock with a chisel.<br>     他用凿子把那块石头刻成了一个女人像。<br>\n He chiseled that rock into the figure of a woman.<br>     他把那块石头凿成一个女人像。<br>'),(1420,'chloroform','chloroformed','chloroformed','chloroforming','','n. 氯仿',''),(1421,'chlorophyll','','','','','n. 叶绿素',' Chlorophyll is a green substance in plants that absorbs energy from sunlight and helps them grow.<br>     叶绿素是生长在植物中的绿色物质，它能吸收阳光，促进植物生长。<br>'),(1422,'chocolate','','','','chocolates','n. 巧克力',' Never eat chocolate before dinner.<br>     饭前不要吃巧克力。<br>\n Would you like a cup of chocolate?<br>     你想要杯巧克力饮料吗？<br>'),(1423,'choice','','','','choices','a. 上等的,精选的<br>\nn. 选择',' She can exercise little choice.<br>     她几乎没有选择余地。<br>\n They are the choice of the men.<br>     他们是队伍中的精英。<br>'),(1424,'choir','choired','choired','choiring','choirs','n. 唱诗班,唱诗班的席位',' He is a member of the choir.<br>     他是唱诗班的一员。<br>\n The choir sang the amens beautifully.<br>     唱诗班唱的阿门非常优美.<br>'),(1425,'choke','choked','choked','choking','chokes','v. 窒息,阻塞',' An old woman was found choked to death.<br>     发现一个老妇人被掐死了。<br>\n She choked with emotion.<br>     她激动得说不出话来。<br>'),(1426,'choose','chose','chosen','choosing','','v. 选择',' Have you chosen a coat yet?<br>     你挑好了上衣没有？<br>\n He chose not to go home until later.<br>     他决定晚一点才回家。<br>'),(1427,'chop','','','','','n. 厚肉片,排骨<br>\nv. 剁碎,砍,切',' He chopped in with a sarcastic remark.<br>     他突然插进一句讽刺的话。<br>\n She chopped the block of wood in two with a single blow.<br>     她一斧头把木块劈成两半。<br>'),(1428,'chord','','','','','n. 弦,和音,情绪',' This story may strike a chord for other women in the same situation.<br>     这个故事会触动其他与她处境相同的妇女的心弦。<br>\n He struck a chord on the piano.<br>     他在钢琴上敲出和音。<br>'),(1429,'chore','','','','chores','n. 零工',' She finds shopping a chore.<br>     她认为买东西是烦人的事.<br>\n All this was done to relieve women of household chores.<br>     这一切都是为了把妇女从家务劳动中解放出来。<br>'),(1430,'chorus','chorused','chorused','chorusing','choruses','n. 合唱队,齐声说道',' The papers all chorused the praises of the President.<br>     各报都异口同声地对总统表示赞扬。<br>\n The chorus is dressed as fairies.<br>     歌舞队的人都装扮成仙子。<br>'),(1431,'Christ','','','','','int. 天啊!<br>\nn. 基督',' To Christians, Jesus Christ is the Savior.<br>     对基督徒来说，主耶稣是他们的救世主。<br>\n Apostles were sent out by Christ to spread his teachings.<br>     基督派基督十二使徒之一宣传他的教义。<br>'),(1432,'Christian','','','','','a. 基督教的<br>\nn. 基督教徒',' He is an earnest Christian.<br>     他是一个虔诚的基督教徒。<br>\n The man was excommunicated from the Christian Church.<br>     那人被驱逐出基督教会。<br>'),(1433,'Christmas','','','','','n. 圣诞节',' Merry Christmas!<br>     圣诞快乐！<br>\n We usually sing carols at Christmas.<br>     圣诞节时，我们一般会唱颂歌。<br>'),(1434,'chroma','','','','','色度,浓度',''),(1435,'chromatic','','','','','a. 彩色的,五彩的',''),(1436,'chronic','','','','','a. 长期的,慢性的',' There is a chronic unemployment problem in America.<br>     在美国存在长期失业问题。<br>\n My brother has chronic bronchitis.<br>     我的哥哥患有慢性支气管炎。<br>'),(1437,'chronological','','','','','a. 按时间顺序的',' A literary or cinematic device in which an earlier event is inserted into the normal chronological order of a narrative.<br>     倒叙，闪回镜头一种文学或电影的表现手法，往往在一段按正常时间顺序记叙的叙事中插入一件以前发生过的事情<br>\n A period of time as reckoned from a specific date serving as the basis of its chronological system.<br>     年代从某一具体日期算起的一段时间，也用作其年代系统的根据<br>'),(1438,'chunk','','','','chunks','n. 大块,矮胖的人或物',' I\'ve completed a fair chunk of my article.<br>     我已经把文章的一大部分写完了.<br>\n The giant shovel is biting off big chunks from the hill.<br>     巨型铲土机正在把小山头一大口一大口地啃掉。<br>'),(1439,'church','churched','churched','churching','churches','n. 教堂',' I\'m just going to the church to see the priest.<br>     我正要去教堂去见见牧师。<br>\n The Church has a duty to condemn violence.<br>     基督徒有责任谴责暴力。<br>'),(1440,'cigar','','','','cigars','n. 雪茄烟',' He lit up a cigar.<br>     他点燃了雪茄。<br>\n He fired up a cigar.<br>     他点着一支雪茄烟。<br>'),(1441,'cigaret','','','','cigarets','n. 香烟',''),(1442,'cigarette','','','','cigarettes','n. 香烟',' In our city, the shops were not allowed to sell cigare