s on the line.<br>     把衣服晾在绳子上。<br>'),(1520,'clothing','','','','','n. (总称)衣服',' We have to put on warm clothing in winter.<br>     冬天的时候，我们不得不穿上温暖的衣服。<br>\n He discarded his winter clothing.<br>     他把冬天穿的衣服都脱掉了。<br>'),(1521,'cloud','clouded','clouded','clouding','clouds','n. 云,忧色,云状的烟<br>\nv. 以云遮敝,笼罩',' The sad news of her father\'s death was the only cloud on an otherwise happy year.<br>     她父亲的死讯是她愉快的一年中唯一伤心的事。<br>\n When there are black clouds you can tell it\'s going to rain.<br>     有乌云的时候，就知道快下雨了。<br>'),(1522,'cloudy','','','','','a. 多云的',' It\'s cloudy today.<br>     今天阴天。<br>\n In that cloudy sky only one lone star can be seen.<br>     在那多云的天上，只能看到孤零零的一颗星星。<br>'),(1523,'club','clubbed','clubbed','clubbing','clubs','n. 俱乐部<br>\nv. 用棍棒打',' He is an active member of the school\'s stamp club.<br>     他是学校集邮俱乐部的一名活跃会员。<br>\n The tennis club has organized a dance.<br>     网球俱乐部组织了一次舞会。<br>'),(1524,'clue','clued','clued','cluing','clues','n. 线索<br>\nv. 提示',' She\'s really clued up on politics.<br>     她对政治非常博学多闻。<br>\n Don\'t ask him to do it he hasn\'t a clue. \'<br>     ｀不要叫他做--他没本事.＇<br>'),(1525,'clump','clumped','clumped','clumping','clumps','n. 丛,块,笨重的脚步声',' He was clumping about in heavy boots that time.<br>     那时他正穿着笨重的靴子走来走去。<br>\n Do you hear the clump of boots?<br>     你听到靴子的咯咯声吗？<br>'),(1526,'clumsy','','','','','a. 笨拙的',' You clumsy oaf ---that\'s the second glass you\'ve broken today.<br>     你这个笨家伙!这是你今天打坏的第二个玻璃杯。<br>\n It\'s not easy walking in these clumsy shoes.<br>     穿着这双笨重的鞋走路真难受。<br>'),(1527,'cluster','clustered','clustered','clustering','clusters','n. 串,丛,群<br>\nv. 聚合,成串,丛生,使...聚集',' You can see stars in clusters in the night sky.<br>     你可以看到夜空中的星群。<br>\n The men clustered together round the fire and sang songs.<br>     人们聚集在篝火周围唱歌。<br>'),(1528,'clutch','','','','','n. 抓紧,掌握,离合器<br>\nv. 抓牢,踩汽车之离合器,孵小鸡',' The boy clutched the marbles and ran away.<br>     那男孩一把抢去弹珠便逃之夭夭。<br>\n The child clutched his toy.<br>     那个孩子紧抓着他的玩具不放。<br>'),(1529,'coach','coached','coached','coaching','coaches','n. 长途汽车,(火车)客车车厢,教练<br>\nv. 训练,指导',' The football coach was criticized by the local paper.<br>     这位足球教练受到了当地报纸的批评。<br>\n I coach people for English exams.<br>     我为准备英语考试的人做辅导。<br>'),(1530,'coal','coaled','coaled','coaling','coals','n. 煤',' A coal fell from the fire and burned the mat.<br>     一块煤炭从火中掉出来，烧坏了地席。<br>\n Ships coal at Gibraltar.<br>     船在直布罗陀上煤。<br>'),(1531,'coalesce','coalesced','coalesced','coalescing','','v. 合并,联合,接合',' The views of party leaders coalesced to form a coherent policy.<br>     党的领导人的各种观点已统一为一致的政策.<br>'),(1532,'coalition','','','','coalitions','n. 结合,合并,联合',' Some of the parties in Spain formed a coalition government.<br>     西班牙的一些政党组成了一个联合政府。<br>\n The two parties have united to form a coalition.<br>     这两个党已结成联盟.<br>'),(1533,'coarse','','','','','a. 粗糙的,下等的,粗俗的',' His coarse manners shocked everyone.<br>     他的粗鲁的举止使每个人震惊。<br>\n Gross; coarse. Used of speech or language.<br>     言谈粗俗的粗野的；粗俗的。用语谈话或语言<br>'),(1534,'coast','coasted','coasted','coasting','coasts','n. 海岸,海滨',' Fishing boats were anchored all along the coast.<br>     渔船沿着岸抛锚停泊。<br>\n The disabled ship coasted the island, looking for a harbor.<br>     那艘损坏的船只在海岛沿岸航行以寻找港口。<br>'),(1535,'coat','coated','coated','coating','coats','n. 外套<br>\nv. 外面覆盖',' Jane bought a fur coat yesterday.<br>     简昨天买了一件裘皮大衣。<br>\n The table was coated in dust.<br>     桌子上覆盖了一层灰尘。<br>'),(1536,'coating','','','','','涂层, 衣料',' There was a coating of slime on the unwashed sink.<br>     未刷洗的水槽上有一层污垢.<br>\n The chocolate coating has all been licked off the cream buns.<br>     奶油小面包外面的一层巧克力都被舔光了。<br>'),(1537,'coax','coaxed','coaxed','coaxing','','v. 哄,诱骗,灵巧慢慢的做',' He coaxed her into letting him take her to the cinema.<br>     他哄她同意带她去看电影。<br>\n She coaxed him out of his bad temper.<br>     她循循善诱地劝他改掉坏脾气。<br>'),(1538,'coaxial','','','','','同轴的',''),(1539,'COBOL','','','','','通用商业语言',' A COBOL mnemonic name associated with the console typewriter.<br>     和控制台打字机有关的一种COBOL助记忆名。<br>\n In the COBOL system, the information represented by a data item, arithmetic expression, or conditional expression.<br>     在COBOL系统中，由一个数据项、算术表达式或条件表达式表示的信息。<br>'),(1540,'cocaine','','','','','n. 可卡因',' Analysis showed that cocaine was present in the mixture.<br>     分析的结果表明混合物中含有可卡因.<br>\n He have all the apparatus, including a blowtorch, for freebasing cocaine.<br>     他有加热吸用可卡因的所有器具，包括喷灯都有。<br>'),(1541,'cock','cocked','cocked','cocking','cocks','n. 公鸡,公鸟<br>\nv. 耸立,耸起',' He cocked his eye at me.<br>     他对我使了个眼色。<br>\n The cock crowed at dawn.<br>     公鸡在黎明时啼叫。<br>'),(1542,'cocktail','','','','cocktails','a. 鸡尾酒(的)<br>\nn. 鸡尾酒',' An allergy to cocktail parties.<br>     对鸡尾酒会的厌恶<br>\n Found cocktail parties distasteful.<br>     发现鸡尾酒会令人反感<br>'),(1543,'cocoa','','','','cocoas','n. 可可粉,可可饮料,可可色',' He made a mug of cocoa for me.<br>     他给我冲了杯可可饮料。<br>\n The seed of this plant, used in making chocolate, cocoa, and cocoa butter.<br>     可可种可可树的种子，用于制造巧克力、可可粉和可可油<br>'),(1544,'cocoon','cocooned','cocooned','cocooning','cocoons','n. 茧',' A cocoon is a kind of silk covering made by an insect.<br>     蚕茧是由昆虫制造的一种由丝组成的外包层。<br>\n Silkworms make cocoons.<br>     蚕做茧。<br>'),(1545,'code','coded','coded','coding','codes','n. 码,密码,法规<br>\nv. 把...编码,制成法典',' I can break the code of this box.<br>     我能破译这个箱子的密码。<br>\n The Highway Code has been carried.<br>     公路法规已经被执行。<br>'),(1546,'coder','','','','','编码器',''),(1547,'coding','','','','','编码',' A plan for the solution of a problem; consists of planning and coding, numerical analysis, systems analysis, specification of printing formats, and any other functions necessary to the integration of a computer in a system.<br>     为解决某一问题而作出的计划，包括规划和编码、数值分析、系统分析、打印格式规定以及把计算机结合进一个系统所必需的其它功能。<br>\n A program or other coding sequence that produces a result of specified type and format(\"a macro generator\";\"a microcode generator\").<br>     产生某种指定类型和格式的结果的程序或另一种编码序列（如“宏生成程序”、“微代码生成程序”）。<br>'),(1548,'coed','','','','','n. 男女同校的学生',' Is your school coed?<br>     你们学校是男女合校吗?<br>\n A coed dorm; a coed pool.<br>     男女合住的宿舍；男女联营<br>'),(1549,'coeducation','','','','','n. 男女同校',''),(1550,'coenzyme','','','','','n. 辅酶',''),(1551,'coerce','coerced','coerced','coercing','','v. 强制,强迫,逼勒',' Power or ability to coerce.<br>     强制的权力或能力<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (1552,'coexist','coexisted','coexisted','coexisting','','v. 共存<br>\nvi. 同时存在,共存',' Now it is generally accepted that the countries with different social systems can coexist peacefully.<br>     ＂现在一般都承认，不同社会制度的国家可以和平共处。＂<br>\n The capitalist countries have to coexist with the socialist countries peacefully.<br>     资本主义国家不得不与社会主义国家和平共处。<br>'),(1553,'coexistence','','','','','n. 共存',''),(1554,'coffee','','','','coffees','n. 咖啡',' Brazil exports a lot of coffee.<br>     巴西出口大量咖啡。<br>\n Would you like a cup of coffee?<br>     想喝杯咖啡吗？<br>'),(1555,'cognitive','','','','','a. 认知的,认识的,有认识力的',''),(1556,'coherent','','','','','a. 互相偶合的,清晰的，明了的，凝聚性的,连贯的',' The combining of separate elements or substances to form a coherent whole.<br>     综合把分别的元素或物质连接成连贯的一个整体<br>\n The views of party leaders coalesced to form a coherent policy.<br>     党的领导人的各种观点已统一为一致的政策.<br>'),(1557,'cohesive','','','','','a. 粘性的(有结合性的,有粘聚性的)',' Absence of any cohesive principle, such as a common standard or purpose.<br>     混乱，无秩序无任何凝聚性准则，如共同标准或目标<br>'),(1558,'coil','coiled','coiled','coiling','coils','n. 卷,骚动<br>\nv. 盘绕,卷<br>\nn. 【电】线圈, 绕组',' He passed me a coil of thread.<br>     他递给我一卷线。<br>\n She coiled her hair at the back of her head.<br>     她把头发盘在脑后。<br>'),(1559,'coin','coined','coined','coining','coins','n. 硬币,金钱,货币<br>\nv. 制造钱币',' Many hands make light work, to coin a phrase.<br>     常言说，人多好干活。<br>\n He paid me in coin.<br>     他付给我的都是硬币。<br>'),(1560,'coincide','coincided','coincided','coinciding','','v. 与...一致,符合,暗合',' They didn\'t coincide in opinion.<br>     他们的意见不统一。<br>\n The demonstration had been carefully stage-managed to coincide with the Prime Minister\'s visit.<br>     这次示威活动事先作了精心安排, 正好在首相访问时进行.<br>'),(1561,'coincidence','','','','coincidences','a. 同时发生的<br>\nn. 巧合',' What a coincidence!<br>     多巧的事啊！<br>\n By coincidence, we arrived here at the same time.<br>     我们凑巧一同到达这儿。<br>'),(1562,'coke','','','','','n. 焦炭',' The refuse left when coke or charcoal is made.<br>     焦炭渣，煤屑焦炭或木炭做成后剩下的渣滓<br>\n Coke consists mainly of carbon.<br>     焦炭的主要成分是碳。<br>'),(1563,'cold','','','','colds','adj.冷的<br>\nn. 感冒<br>\nv. 冷(的)',' He caught a cold.<br>     他感冒了。<br>\n It\'s cold today, you should put a coat on.<br>     今天很冷，你应该穿件大衣。<br>'),(1564,'coldly','','','','','ad. 冷淡地',' His boss looked at him coldly because he made several big mistakes.<br>     他的老板冷漠地看着他因为他犯了几个大错误。<br>\n How did Mrs. Lin look at Mr. Lin? She looked at Mr. Lin coldly.<br>     林太太怎样注视林先生？ 她冷漠地注视林先生。<br>'),(1565,'collaborate','collaborated','collaborated','collaborating','','v. 合作,通敌',' She collaborated with her sister/She and her sister collaborated on a biography of their father.<br>     她和姐姐合作写父亲的传记.<br>\n He was suspected of collaborating (with the enemy).<br>     怀疑他（与敌人）勾结.<br>'),(1566,'collaboration','','','','','n. 合作,通敌',''),(1567,'collaborative','','','','','a. 协作的,合作的',''),(1568,'collagen','','','','','n. 胶原',''),(1569,'collapse','collapsed','collapsed','collapsing','collapses','n. 崩溃,倒塌<br>\nv. 倒塌,崩溃,瓦解',' The wind caused the tent to collapse.<br>     风把帐篷吹塌了。<br>\n Talks between management and unions have collapsed.<br>     资方和工会的谈判失败了。<br>'),(1570,'collar','collared','collared','collaring','collars','n. 衣领<br>\nv. (非正式)抓住',' The lawyer was collared by some journalists as he left his office.<br>     律师在离开办公室时被记者拦住了。<br>\n Where are the dog\'s collar and lead?<br>     狗的颈圈和皮带哪去了？<br>'),(1571,'collateral','','','','collaterals','a. 并行的,附随的,旁系的<br>\nn. 支亲,副保,附属担保物',' The bank will insist on collateral for a loan of that size.<br>     银行对这样的大笔贷款一定要有抵押物。<br>\n Lacking the protection of insurance or collateral security.<br>     未经保险的未发保险的，无附加担保的<br>'),(1572,'collator','','','','','整理器,校对机',''),(1573,'colleague','','','','','n. 同事',' The Prime Minister\'s cabinet colleague refused to accept the proposal.<br>     首相的内阁同僚拒绝接受这个建议。<br>\n David and I are colleagues.<br>     戴维和我是同事。<br>'),(1574,'collect','','','','','ad.&a. 对方付费(的)<br>\nv. 聚集,堆积,收集',' This department collects information on political extremists.<br>     这个部门搜集有关政治极端分子的情报。<br>\n We are collecting money for the famine victim.<br>     我们在为遭受饥荒的灾民募捐。<br>'),(1575,'collection','','','','collections','n. 收藏品,收集物',' There are two collections a day from this letter box.<br>     这个邮箱每天开两次。<br>\n You are invited to view our autumn collection.<br>     您被邀请参观我们的秋季时装展览。<br>'),(1576,'collective','','','','collectives','a. 集体的,共同的<br>\nn. 集体',' In a system of collective bargaining, the workers as a group negotiate with the managers of the company.<br>     在劳资集体谈判制度下，工人作为一个团体同公司经理进行谈判。<br>\n Only with organization can the wisdom of the collective be given full play.<br>     ＂只有组织起来，才能充分地发挥集体的智慧。＂<br>'),(1577,'collectively','','','','','ad. 共同的(集体地,总起来说)',' A relatively small, often rural community whose members share common interests, work, and income and often own property collectively.<br>     公社一个比较小、常在乡村的公社，它的成员分享公共财产、工作和收入，并常集中自己的财产<br>\n Having made the necessary changes, he was satisfied that he had a team which would collectively handle the task.<br>     经过一些必要的变动后，现在的小组成员将会齐心协力开展工作，他对此感到很满意。<br>'),(1578,'college','','','','colleges','n. 学院',' He is at law college.<br>     他在法学院读书。<br>\n She is a member of the Royal College of Nursing.<br>     她是皇家护士协会的会员。<br>'),(1579,'collide','collided','collided','colliding','','v. 碰撞,互撞,砥触',' The ships collided in the fog.<br>     轮船在雾中相撞.<br>\n The bus and the van collided.<br>     公共汽车与客货车相撞.<br>'),(1580,'collision','','','','collisions','n. 碰撞,冲突',' The liner is reported to have been in collision with an oil tanker.<br>     据报道，这艘客轮与一艘油轮相撞。<br>\n Five persons died during the collision between two buses.<br>     5个人死于公共汽车相撞。<br>'),(1581,'colon','','','','','n. 冒号<br>\nn. 结肠，直肠',' The old man died from colon cancer.<br>     这位老人死于结肠癌。<br>\n There is a colon omitted in this sentence.<br>     这个句子中丢了一个冒号。<br>'),(1582,'colonel','','','','','n. 上校',' The colonel ordered their soldiers to gather on the deck.<br>     上校命令士兵们在甲板上集合。<br>\n Has he any right to use the style of Colonel?<br>     他有资格使用上校头衔吗？<br>'),(1583,'colonial','','','','colonials','a. 殖民地的<br>\nn. 殖民地居民',' The new house he bought was colonial architecture.<br>     他新买的房子是美国初期的建筑。<br>\n The resistance movement started a campaign of terror against the colonial rulers.<br>     抵抗运动开展了一场反对殖民统治者的恐怖活动。<br>'),(1584,'colonist','','','','colonists','n. 殖民地居民,殖民者',' The colonists took up weapons to rebel against the British ruler.<br>     殖民地的人们拿起武器反抗英国统治者。<br>\n English Pilgrim colonist who sailed to America on the Mayflower(1620) and was the religious leader of Plymouth Colony.<br>     布鲁斯特，威廉1567－1644英国清教徒殖民主义者，乘五月花号航行至美洲（1620年），是普利茅斯殖民地的宗教领袖<br>'),(1585,'colony','','','','colonies','n. 殖民地',' This country used to be a British colony in Asia.<br>     这个国家曾是英国在亚洲的殖民地。<br>\n Britain was mandated to govern the former colony of German East Africa.<br>     英国受权代管德国在东非的前殖民地.<br>'),(1586,'color','colored','colored','coloring','colors','n. 颜色,气色,风格<br>\nv. 把...涂颜色,粉饰,脸红',' She loved the life, noise, and color of the market.<br>     她爱市场上的生趣、喧哗与多姿多彩。<br>\n What color did you paint the door?<br>     你把门漆成什么颜色？<br>'),(1587,'colors','','','','','n. 彩色',' I throw my eyes out of focus, so that I see no particular object but only a seething kaleidoscope of colors.<br>     我的目光没有聚焦，以致我没有看到特别的目标，仅仅是那川流不息的彩色万花筒。<br>\n The photograph of the painting reproduces the colors of the original extremely well.<br>     这幅画的照片绝妙地再现了原作的色彩。<br>'),(1588,'colossal','','','','','a. 巨大的',' It requires government spending on a colossal scale.<br>     这要求政府付出巨额开支。<br>'),(1589,'colour','coloured','coloured','colouring','colours','n. 颜色<br>\nv. 给...着色,染<br>\nvt. 给...着色',' She loved the life, noise, and colour of the market.<br>     她爱市场上的生趣、喧哗与多姿多彩。<br>\n What colour did you paint the door?<br>     你把门漆成什么颜色？<br>'),(1590,'column','','','','columns','n. 柱，圆柱；柱形物,专栏<br>\n[计算机] 列',' He used to write a column for this newspaper.<br>     他过去曾为这家报纸写专栏文章。<br>\n His column is syndicated throughout the world.<br>     他的专栏文章通过报业辛迪加在世界许多报刊上发表.<br>'),(1591,'comb','combed','combed','combing','combs','n. 头梳,鸡冠<br>\nv. 梳头发,梳毛',' She wore a small comb as an ornament.<br>     她佩戴了一把小梳子作为装饰品。<br>\n The police have combed the city for the murderer.<br>     警察在全市到处搜查凶手。<br>'),(1592,'combat','combated','combated','combating','combats','n. 争斗,战斗<br>\nv. 奋斗,争斗',' The ship is combating the wind and waves.<br>     那只船正与风浪搏斗。<br>\n The combat arm that deploys armored vehicles, such as tanks.<br>     装甲部队部署装甲车辆的战斗部队，如坦克<br>'),(1593,'combination','','','','combinations','n. 结合,联合',' These players made a very good combination.<br>     这些球员们配合得很好。<br>\n We tried it in every conceivable combination.<br>     我们把能想到的各种组合都试了一遍.<br>'),(1594,'combine','','','','','n. 集团,联合收割机<br>\nv. 化合,结合,联合<br>\nvi. 结合,联合<br>\nvt. 使结合,使联合',' We can\'t always combine work with pleasure.<br>     我们并不总是能在工作中享受到乐趣。<br>\n Two atoms of hydrogen combine with one atom of oxygen to form a molecule of water.<br>     两个氢原子和一个氧原子结合而成一个水分子。<br>'),(1595,'combustible','','','','','a. 易燃的,燃烧性的,易动激情的<br>\nn. 燃质物,可燃物',' Petrol is (highly) combustible.<br>     汽油（极）易燃.<br>\n A hypothetical substance formerly thought to be a volatile constituent of all combustible substances released as flame in combustion.<br>     燃素，热素原来假设的在所有燃烧物质中挥发性的一种物质成分，在燃烧中作为火焰而被释放出来<br>'),(1596,'come','came','come','coming','','v. 来',' Your family should always come before your job.<br>     你的家庭应该比你的工作重要。<br>\n The train slowly came to the station.<br>     火车缓缓地进站。<br>'),(1597,'comedy','','','','comedies','n. 喜剧',' There is not much comedy in modern war.<br>     现代战争并不是好玩的事。<br>\n He prefers comedies to tragedies.<br>     他比较喜欢喜剧而不太喜欢悲剧。<br>'),(1598,'comet','','','','comets','n. 慧星',' Comets move around the sun like planets, but in long oval course.<br>     彗星象行星一样绕太阳运转，然而其轨道呈狭长的椭圆形。<br>\n If I had binoculars, I could see that comet clearly.<br>     如果我有望远镜，我就可以清楚地看见那颗彗星。<br>'),(1599,'comfort','comforted','comforted','comforting','comforts','n. 舒适,安慰,安慰者<br>\nv. 安慰',' My husband was a great comfort to me when my son was ill.<br>     我儿子生病时，丈夫给了我极大的安慰。<br>\n He spoke a few words of comfort to me before leaving.<br>     走之前，他向我说了几句安慰的话。<br>'),(1600,'comfortable','','','','comfortables','a. 舒适的',' My house is not big, but it is comfortable.<br>     我的房子不大，但很舒服。<br>\n I won\'t be comfortable until I know what happened.<br>     我只有知道发生了什么事后，才会放下心来。<br>'),(1601,'comic','','','','comics','n. 连环图画,杂耍滑稽演员<br>\na. 滑稽的,有趣的,喜剧的',' This famous comic actor is loved by the people even after his death.<br>     这位著名的戏剧演员即便是在死后，也仍受到人们的喜爱。<br>\n Children like to read comics.<br>     孩子们喜欢看连环漫画。<br>'),(1602,'comma','','','','commas','n. 逗号',' Stop quibbling about the use of the comma.<br>     别再争辩逗号的用法了.<br>\n The two clauses are separated by a comma.<br>     这两个分句由一个逗号分开。<br>'),(1603,'command','commanded','commanded','commanding','commands','n. 命令,指挥,控制<br>\nv. 命令,指挥,支配<br>\nn.[计算机] DOS命令 : 引用辅助命令处理器',' This great man is able to command everyone\'s respect.<br>     这位伟人有资格获得大家的尊敬。<br>\n The general commanded his men to attack the city.<br>     将军下令部下攻城。<br>'),(1604,'commander','','','','commanders','n. 司令官,指挥官',' He is the commander of the expedition.<br>     他是远征军的司令/探险队的队长。<br>\n An army commander must be skilled in tactics.<br>     一名军事指挥官必须精通战术。<br>'),(1605,'commemorate','commemorated','commemorated','commemorating','','v. 纪念,庆祝<br>\nvt.&n. 纪念',' Christmas commemorates the birth of Christ.<br>     圣诞节是为了纪念耶酥的诞生。<br>\n A monument was built to commemorate the victory.<br>     为了纪念胜利，建造了一座纪念碑。<br>'),(1606,'commence','commenced','commenced','commencing','','开始',' The second term commences in March.<br>     第二学期自三月开始。<br>\n I commence from this point.<br>     我从此点开始。<br>'),(1607,'commend','commended','commended','commending','','v. 委托,推荐,嘉奖',' She commended the child to her sister\'s care.<br>     她将孩子委托给她妹妹照管。<br>\n His work was highly commended.<br>     他的工作备受赞赏。<br>'),(1608,'comment','commented','commented','commenting','comments','注释,评论',' What comments have you about my son\'s behaviour?<br>     你对我儿子的行为有什么意见？<br>\n The king refuses to comment on the election results.<br>     国王拒绝评论选举的结果。<br>'),(1609,'commentary','','','','commentaries','n. 注释,评论,批评',' I think his commentary on this issue is not correct.<br>     我认为他对这个问题的评论是不正确的。<br>\n This commentary was excellently written.<br>     这篇解说词写得非常好。<br>'),(1610,'commentator','','','','commentators','n. 注释者(注释者,解说员,新闻广播员)',' I prefer soccer commentator to report a match blow by blow.<br>     我宁愿足球比赛广播实况播音员详尽地报导比赛。<br>\n Our commentator will now set the scene in the stadium.<br>     讲解员现在就要在体育场向我们报道。<br>'),(1611,'commerce','','','','','n. 商业,贸易',' He majored in international commerce in college.<br>     他大学时的专业是国际贸易。<br>\n The practices, methods, aims, and spirit of commerce or business.<br>     利润第一主义商业或营业的实践、方法、目的和精神<br>'),(1612,'commercial','','','','','a. 商业的<br>\nn. 商业广告',' New York is a big commercial city.<br>     纽约是一座大的商业城市。<br>\n Is commercial correspondence taught at the school?<br>     学校里是否教授商业函件?<br>'),(1613,'commission','commissioned','commissioned','commissioning','commissions','n. 委任状,任官令,佣金<br>\nv. 委任,委托,使服役',' He has secured two commissions to design buildings for a local authority.<br>     他已承包两项为当地政府设计建筑物的业务。<br>\n He commissioned a statue of his wife.<br>     他请人制作他妻子的雕像。<br>'),(1614,'commissioner','','','','commissioners','n. 委员,理事,行政长官',' The old man was a police commissioner before his retirement.<br>     这位老人退休前是警察局长。<br>\n Australian politician who served three terms as prime minister between1908 and1915 and was Australian high commissioner in London(1916-1921).<br>     费歇尔，约翰·阿巴思诺特1841－1920英国海军上将，改革英国海军使之重振威风，为一战作了准备<br>'),(1615,'commit','committed','committed','committing','','v. 委托(托付),犯罪,作...事,承诺<br>\n[计算机] 委托',' The girl was committed to the care of an aunt.<br>     这女孩被交给姨母照顾。<br>\n She committed herself to philanthropy.<br>     她专心从事慈善事业。<br>'),(1616,'commitment','','','','','n. 委托,实行,承诺,保证(律）拘禁令<br>\nn. 奉献，献身',' His political commitment is only skin-deep.<br>     他政治上的承诺只是表面文章。<br>\n The President affirmed America\'s commitment to its transatlantic (ie European) allies.<br>     总统申明美国履行对其欧洲盟国承担的义务.<br>'),(1617,'committee','','','','committees','n. 委员会',' The committee meets at three today.<br>     委员会今天三点开会。<br>\n He was criticized by the committee for failing to report the accident.<br>     他因未对事故进行汇报而受到委员会的批评。<br>'),(1618,'commodity','','','','commodities','n. 商品,日用品',' The country is heavily dependent on its exports of agricultural commodities.<br>     这个国家很大程度上依靠农产品的出口。<br>\n The goods were inspected by the China Commodity Inspection Bureau before shipment.<br>     这批货在装船前由中国商品检验局进行过检验。<br>'),(1619,'common','','','','commons','a. 共同的,平常的,普通的<br>\nn. 平民,普通,公地,公园',' Rabbits and foxes are common in Britain.<br>     兔子和狐狸在英国很常见。<br>\n Does the common man oppose the ideas of political union between European countries?<br>     一般人是不是反对欧洲国家政治联合的构想呢？<br>'),(1620,'commonly','','','','','ad. 一般,普通,通常',' It was commonly believed that he was an honest man.<br>     一般都认为他是一个诚实的人。<br>\n The question is more complicated than(is) commonly supposed.<br>     这问题比一般人想象的更复杂一些。<br>'),(1621,'commonplace','','','','commonplaces','n. 常事,老生常谈,普通的东西<br>\na. 平凡的,陈腐的',' Many movies deal with commonplace themes.<br>     许多电影的主题很平庸。<br>\n Soon it will be commonplace for people to travel to the moon.<br>     不用多久，人们到月球旅行会变成常见的事了。<br>'),(1622,'commonsense','','','','','a. 具有常识的',' He has no commonsense he always does silly things.<br>     他毫无常识，总是做些傻事。<br>'),(1623,'commonwealth','','','','commonwealths','n. 共和国,联邦',' The Commonwealth agreed to make a compact with this country.<br>     英联邦同意和这个国家订约。<br>\n The official report of the proceedings and debates of a legislature in the Commonwealth of Nations, especially of the British or Canadian parliament.<br>     英国议会议事录在不列颠联邦内产生的立法争论和议事进程的官方报告，尤指英国或加拿大议会<br>'),(1624,'commotion','','','','commotions','n. 骚动,暴乱',' You are maki