ealth.<br>     我们都非常关心他的健康。<br>'),(1707,'concerning','','','','','prep. 关于',' They show great anxiety concerning their retirement allowance.<br>     他们对自己的养老金问题显得十分焦虑。<br>\n Concerning each of two or more persons or things.<br>     交互的，相互的关于两个或多个人或物中的每一个的<br>'),(1708,'concert','concerted','concerted','concerting','concerts','n. 音乐会,一致,和谐',' The concert will be given on Saturday.<br>     音乐会将于星期六举行。<br>\n He refused to concert with his partners.<br>     他拒绝和他的伙伴们合作。<br>'),(1709,'concerted','','','','','a. 商议好的,协定的,预定的',' A vigorous concerted movement for a cause or against an abuse.<br>     圣战赞成某一事业或反对某一弊病而进行的有力的统一运动<br>\n He woke his audience to the need for concerted action.<br>     他使听众意识到有必要采取一致的行动。<br>'),(1710,'concession','','','','concessions','n. 让步,妥协',' We will make some concession in price.<br>     我们将在价格上做些让步。<br>\n I hope you can make some concession.<br>     我希望你能做些让步。<br>'),(1711,'concise','','','','','a. 简明的,简要的',' The act or procedure of giving or receiving concise preparatory instructions, information, or advice.<br>     简介给予或接受简洁的预备性的指令、信息或忠告的行为或步骤<br>\n Teaching content should be concise.<br>     教学内容要少而精。<br>'),(1712,'conclude','concluded','concluded','concluding','','v. 结束,作结论,推断',' From his appearance we may safely conclude that he is a chain smoker.<br>     从他的外表，我们可以有把握地断定他烟抽得很凶。<br>\n Once the price had been agreed, a deal was quickly concluded.<br>     价格一经商定，交易很快就达成了。<br>'),(1713,'conclusion','','','','conclusions','n. 结论',' The conclusion of the movie was anticlimactic.<br>     电影的结局真没劲。<br>\n What conclusion did you come to?<br>     你得出了什么结论？<br>'),(1714,'conclusive','','','','','a. 决定性的,确实的,最后的',' Having the power to decide; conclusive.<br>     决定性的有权决定的；结论性的<br>\n Supplying or being a final settlement or decision; conclusive.<br>     最后的提供或成为最后的解决办法或决定的；决定性的<br>'),(1715,'concoct','concocted','concocted','concocting','','v. 混合而制,调合,捏造',' She\'d concocted some unlikely tale about the train being cancelled.<br>     她胡编了一通瞎话, 说什麽那班火车给取消了.<