ntroversies','n. 争论,争议',' The new government appointments have caused much controversy.<br>     政府在人事上作的新的委任，引起了许多争论。<br>\n The mayor will try to accord the controversy over the housing scheme.<br>     市长试图调解在住房建筑规划方面的争议。<br>'),(1856,'convalescent','','','','convalescents','a. 恢复期的',' At last she was pronounced upon the mend and then convalescent.<br>     她的病情终于宣告有了好转—不久就恢复健康了。<br>'),(1857,'convene','convened','convened','convening','','v. 集合,召集,召唤<br>\nv. 聚集,集合',' People were convened here for an emergency meeting.<br>     人们被召集到这里举行紧急会议。<br>\n The tribunal will convene tomorrow.<br>     法庭将于明日开庭。<br>'),(1858,'convenience','','','','conveniences','n. 便利,方便',' It\'s a great convenience to live in town.<br>     住在城市里有很大的方便。<br>\n We find our folding table a great convenience.<br>     我们发现可折叠的桌子使用非常方便。<br>'),(1859,'convenient','','','','','a. 方便的',' Will it be convenient for you to come in the morning?<br>     你上午来方便吗？<br>\n We must arrange a convenient time and place for the meeting.<br>     我们必须安排一个合适的时间和地点开会。<br>'),(1860,'convention','','','','conventions','n. 大会,协定,惯例<br>\n[计算机] 约定',' The convention looms as political battle.<br>     这场大会将是一场政治角斗。<br>\n She redeemed her reputation with a powerful speech to the party convention.<br>     她由于向党代表大会做了有力的演说而挽回了自己的声誉。<br>'),(1861,'conventional','','','','','a. 普通的,常见的,习惯的,常规的',' \"How are you?\" is a conventional greeting.<br>     “你好”是一个习惯问候语。<br>\n He often speaks a few conventional remarks.<br>     他总是喜欢说老生常谈的那几句话。<br>'),(1862,'converge','converged','converged','converging','','v. 聚合,集中于一点(或一块)',' Some say that capitalism and socialism will eventually converge.<br>     有人说资本主义和社会主义最终会合而为一。<br>\n The roads converge just before the station.<br>     四面八方的道路会聚在火车站前。<br>'),(1863,'converged','','','','','收敛的,聚合的',' Angry crowds converged on the speaker.<br>     愤怒的群众涌向演讲者。<br>\n In time, our views and our efforts converged.<br>     我们的观点和努力迟早要达成一致<br>'),(1864,'convergence','','','','','会聚,聚焦',' Correspondence between parts or organs arising from evolutionary convergence.<br>     异体同功由进化趋同而产生的部分或器官之间的对应现象<br>\n A town at the convergence of two rivers.<br>     位于两条河流交点处的城镇<br>'),(1865,'conversation','','','','conversations','n. 会话,谈话',' The professor invited his students to his home for conversation.<br>     教授邀请学生们到自己家里会晤。<br>\n Did you have a conversation with him?<br>     你和他谈过话了吗？<br>'),(1866,'conversational','','','','','a. 会话的,对话的,健谈的',' Our English course places great emphasis on conversational skills.<br>     我们的英语课程非常重视会话技能。<br>\n Pertaining to an application in which each entry calls forth a response from a system or program, as in an inquiry system or an airline reservation system. An interactive system may also be conversational, implying a continuous dialog between the user and the system.<br>     用来修饰说明某种应用软件，其中每一输入都会从系统或程序那里得到响应。如查询系统、飞机订票系统。一个交互系统也可以是会话式的，即用户和系统之间的连续对话。<br>'),(1867,'conversely','','','','','ad. 相反地',' Conversely, intelligent beings which are just beginning to develop on remote worlds may be ready to pick up our signals in thousands of years.<br>     反过来说，其他星球上的刚刚开始进化的智力生命，他们要过几千年之后，也许才可能收到我们的信号。<br>\n Conversely, work in applied science and technology frequently acts as a direct stimulus to the development of pure science.<br>     相反，应用科学技术的成果在纯科学的发展中经常起到直接的促进作用。<br>'),(1868,'conversion','','','','conversions','n. 转变,改变信仰,换位',' Conversion to gas central heating will save you a lot of money.<br>     改用煤气集中供暖将节省大笔开支。<br>\n When he saw how the theory increased unemployment, he underwent quite a conversion.<br>     当他看到这个理论加重了失业后，他彻底改变了看法。<br>'),(1869,'convert','','','','','v. 使转变,使...改变信仰,倒置<br>\nn. 皈依者,改宗者',' Coal can be converted to gas.<br>     煤可以转化成煤气。<br>\n He is a recent convert to Christianity.<br>     他最近改信基督教了。<br>'),(1870,'converted','','','','','转换的,修改的',' Coal can be converted to gas.<br>     煤可以转化成煤气。<br>\n Sugar is converted into alcohol through the process of fermentation.<br>     糖经过发酵变成酒精。<br>'),(1871,'converter','','','','','转换器',' For a