r>     画家是具有创造性的艺术家。<br>\n The writing of poems, stories or plays is often called creative writing.<br>     诗歌、小说和剧本的写作常常被称作创作。<br>'),(1992,'creator','','','','creators','[计算机] 创建者',' Do you know who is the creator of the electric bulb?<br>     你知道谁是电灯的发明者？<br>\n The creator of a new television series; a born creator of trouble.<br>     新的电视系列片的创造者；一个天生多麻烦的人<br>'),(1993,'creature','','','','creatures','n. 生物,动物,人',' He is a creature of habit.<br>     他是个墨守成规的人。<br>\n Pandas are precious creatures.<br>     熊猫是珍贵的动物。<br>'),(1994,'credential','','','','credentials','n. 国书,凭据,印信',' She has the perfect credentials for the job.<br>     她做这工作完全够格.<br>\n I examined his credentials.<br>     我查验了他的证件.<br>'),(1995,'credible','','','','','a. 可信的,可靠的',' It seems credible.<br>     这似乎是可信的。<br>\n Looks credible.<br>     看来可信。<br>'),(1996,'credit','credited','credited','crediting','credits','n. 信用,荣誉,贷款,学分<br>\nv. 归功于,赞颂,信任',' No credit is given at this shop.<br>     这家商店概不赊欠。<br>\n He is a credit to the family.<br>     他是家族中的光荣。<br>'),(1997,'creditor','','','','','n. 债权人',' The poor man ran away from his creditors.<br>     这个穷人躲避他的债主。<br>\n A homestead cannot be the subject of a sale by court order to satisfy creditor.<br>     宅地不能成为法院命令的满足债权人所要求的销售对象。<br>'),(1998,'creek','','','','creeks','n. 小湾,小溪',' I was really up the creek when I lost my keys.<br>     我丢掉钥匙之后，真正遇到了麻烦。<br>\n I\'ll be up the creek if I don\'t pass this history test.<br>     我若不能通过这次历史考试，麻烦可就大了。<br>'),(1999,'creep','crept','crept','creeping','creeps','n. 爬,徐行,蠕动<br>\nv. 爬,蔓延',' We crept upstairs so as not to wake the baby.<br>     为了不吵醒婴儿，我们蹑手蹑脚地上了楼梯。<br>\n The cat was creeping silently towards the mouse.<br>     猫悄悄地朝着老鼠爬过去。<br>'),(2000,'crevice','','','','crevices','n. (岩石、墙等)裂缝',' There is a crevice in the wall.<br>     墙上有个裂缝。<br>\n A winding channel, passage, or crevice.<br>     弯曲的沟渠，弯曲的通道，弯曲的裂缝<br>'),(2001,'crew','','','','crews','n. 全体船员,全体乘务员<br>\nvi. 一起工作',' The plane crashed, killing all its passengers and crew.<br>     飞机失事了，所有乘客和机组人员都遇难了。<br>\n We are a happy crew in our office.<br>     我们办公室的一伙人相处得很愉快。<br>'),(2002,'cricket','','','','','n. 板球,蟋蟀',' I don\'t find cricket very exciting.<br>     我觉得打板球没有劲。<br>\n A cricket team is comprised of eleven players.<br>     一个板球队由11名队员组成。<br>'),(2003,'crime','crimed','crimed','criming','crimes','n. 犯罪',' Murder is a vile and loathsome crime.<br>     谋杀是邪恶而令人发指的罪行。<br>\n It\'s a crime the way he bullies his children.<br>     像他那样欺负自己的孩子真缺德。<br>'),(2004,'criminal','','','','criminals','a. 犯罪的,刑事的<br>\nn. 罪犯',' Murder and stealing are criminal acts.<br>     谋杀和偷盗都是犯罪行为。<br>\n The police had to make a forcible entry into the house where the criminal was hiding.<br>     警察不得不强行进入罪犯藏身的那座房子。<br>'),(2005,'cripple','crippled','crippled','crippling','cripples','n. 跛者,残废<br>\nv. 使...跛,使...成残废,削弱',''),(2006,'crisis','','','','crises','n. 危急关头,危机',' Relation between the two countries has reached a crisis point.<br>     两国关系已达到出现危机的地步。<br>\n In times of crisis it\'s good to have a friend to turn to.<br>     危难时好在有朋友可以投奔。<br>'),(2007,'crisp','crisped','crisped','crisping','crisps','a. 脆的,易碎的<br>\nn. 油炸马铃薯片<br>\nv. (使)发脆',' I like the delicious salad of crisp lettuce and tomatos.<br>     我喜欢这种脆莴苣和番茄做的沙拉，很好吃。<br>\n It tastes sweet and crisp.<br>     吃起来又甜又脆。<br>'),(2008,'criteria','','','','','n. 标准',' What are the criteria for deciding (ie How do we decide) who gets the prize?<br>     评定获奖者以什麽作标准?<br>\n An experiment was made to check up on the reliability of certain criteria.<br>     已经进行了一项实验以检查某些标准的可靠性。<br>'),(2009,'criterion','','','','criteria','n. 标准,准则',' A gentleman may have money or may sponge on his friends; the criterion of a gentleman is that however poor he may be he still refuses to do useful work.<br>     绅士可能有钱、或者可能依赖朋友过活；绅士的准则是，无论他怎么穷也罢，他依然是拒绝做任何有用的工作的。<br>\n A standard of measurement or judgment; a criterion.<br>     标准测量或判断的标谁；标准<br>'),(2010,'critic','','','','critics','n. 批评家,评论家',' Have you read the article written by that famous critic?<br>     你读过那个著名的批评家写的这篇文章吗？<br>\n She is a very discerning art critic.<br>     她是位眼光敏锐的艺术评论家.<br>'),(2011,'critical','','','','','a. 批评的,决定性的,危险的,挑剔的<br>\na. 临界的',' In the current critical climate her work is not popular.<br>     在当前评论风气影响下，她的作品不怎么受欢迎。<br>\n Why are you always so critical?<br>     你怎么总是这样吹毛求疵？<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (2012,'criticism','','','','criticisms','n. 批评,评论',' I don\'t like to read his literary criticism.<br>     我不喜欢读他的文学批评。<br>\n His criticism doesn\'t worry me.<br>     他的批评不会使我不安。<br>'),(2013,'criticize','criticized','criticized','criticizing','','v. 批评,吹毛求疵,非难',' He criticized my taking risks.<br>     他批评了我的冒险活动。<br>\n Stop criticizing (my work)!<br>     别再挑剔（我那作品）了!<br>'),(2014,'critique','','','','','n. 批评,批评法,评论',' Presented us with a dry critique.<br>     向我们表述了不带偏见的观点<br>\n A pointed critique.<br>     尖锐的批判<br>'),(2015,'crocodile','','','','crocodiles','n. 鳄鱼',' There are crocodiles in this river.<br>     这条河里有鳄鱼。<br>\n Leather made from crocodile skin.<br>     鳄鱼皮革用鳄鱼皮做成的皮革<br>'),(2016,'crooked','','','','','a. 弯曲的,歪的,邪恶的',' The picture on the wall is crooked.<br>     挂在墙壁上的画是歪的。<br>\n She crooked her little finger as she drank her tea.<br>     她喝茶时弯起小指头。<br>'),(2017,'crop','cropped','cropped','cropping','crops','n. 农作物,产量,平头<br>\nv. 收割,修剪,种植',' The flood did a lot of damage to the crops.<br>     洪水毁坏了大量农作物。<br>\n We have had the biggest wheat crop ever this year.<br>     今年我们的小麦收获量是有史以来最好的。<br>'),(2018,'cross','crossed','crossed','crossing','crosses','n. 十字架,十字架形物件,交叉路<br>\na. 生气的,交叉的,相反的<br>\nv. 交叉,横过,越过',' If you can\'t sign your name, make a cross instead.<br>     你如果不会签名，画一个十字也可以。<br>\n He crossed me in everything.<br>     他事事阻挠我。<br>'),(2019,'crosshatch','crosshatched','crosshatched','crosshatching','','v. 交互配血',''),(2020,'crossing','','','','crossings','n. 人行横道,十字路口',' The place is marked on the map with a crossing.<br>     那个地方在地图上以十字形记号标出。<br>\n We came to a crossing.<br>     我们来到一个十字路口。<br>'),(2021,'crouch','crouched','crouched','crouching','','n. 蹲伏,蜷缩<br>\nv. 蹲下,蜷著,缩著',' He crouched down among the tangled foliage.<br>     他蹲下把身子藏在紊乱的叶丛中。<br>\n They did not crouch under the oppression.<br>     他们受压迫而不屈服。<br>'),(2022,'crow','','','','','n. 啼叫,乌鸦<br>\nv. 啼叫,报晓',' He gets up at the crow of the rooster every day.<br>     他每天鸡鸣