,'designs','n. 设计,图样<br>\nv. 设计,计划',' He designed us a beautiful house.<br>     他为我们设计了一所很美的房子。<br>\n This dress is of the latest design.<br>     这件衣服是最新设计。<br>'),(2322,'designate','designated','designated','designating','','v. 指定,标示',' The chairman has designated that boy as his successor.<br>     主席已经指定那个男孩作他的继承人。<br>\n The town has been designated a development area.<br>     该城市已被定为开发区。<br>'),(2323,'designated','','','','','指定的,特指的',' A small, usually rectangular board, used as a game of chance, that contains many holes each filled with a folded slip of paper that when punched out indicates a designated prize, win, or loss.<br>     抽彩盘一种用作赌具盘的通常呈长方形的小盘子，同分布有许多小孔，每个小孔中放有折叠在一起的纸条，纸条被抽出后表明预先指定的价钱、胜利或失败<br>\n The chairman has designated that boy as his successor.<br>     主席已经指定那个男孩作他的继承人。<br>'),(2324,'designation','','','','','n. 指示,指定,指名',' His official designation is Financial Controller.<br>     他的职称是财务总监.<br>\n A name or designation, especially for a class or group.<br>     名称，称谓名称或称谓，尤指一个阶层或团体的名称<br>'),(2325,'desirable','','','','desirables','a. 令人想要的<br>\n[计算机] 希望的',' It isn\'t really desirable to have him working here.<br>     让他在这里工作其实并不必要。<br>\n A procedure causing a system, process, or operation to take on its most desirable configuration or procedures in the best or most efficient way; for example, when arranging instructions and data in storage so that a minimum of machine time or space is used for storing or accessing them.<br>     使一个系统、一个过程或一个操作能取其最希望的结构的方法，或以最好、最有效的方式进行所采取的一些措施。例如，在存储器中合理安排指令和数据的存放位置以便存入和访问时花费的机器时间或空间最小。<br>'),(2326,'desire','desired','desired','desiring','desires','n. 愿望,欲望,情欲<br>\nv. 向往,要求,请求<br>\nvt. 渴望',' I am filled with desire to go back home.<br>     我心中充满了回家的渴望。<br>\n I desire happiness.<br>     我渴望幸福。<br>'),(2327,'desired','','','','','a. 渴望的, 想得到的',' A process of behavior modification by which a subject comes to associate a desired behavior with a previously unrelated stimulus.<br>     条件作用某一对象逐步将渴望的行为和先前无关的刺激因素联系起来的行为改变过程<br>\n I have long desired to meet them.<br>     我一直渴望见到他们.<br>'),(2328,'desk','','','','desks','n. 书桌',' There is a desk in the boy\'s room.<br>     小男孩的房间里有张写字台。<br>\n You may leave your key at the reception desk.<br>     你可以把钥匙留在服务台。<br>'),(2329,'desktop','','','','','[计算机] 桌面',' The amount of space, desktop or floor, needed by a computer system or peripheral. Systems and peripherals with smaller footprints have the advantage of leaving more room available for other things.<br>     计算机系统或外设在地板或台上所需要占用的空间面积。具有较小占地面积的系统和外设，其优点是可留出更多的空间留做其它用途。<br>\n The mouse is a small, handheld object that is pushed around a desktop to move the cursor on the screen or to select choices from menus displayed on the screen.<br>     鼠标是一个可以用手在桌面上推动的小东西，通过它可以在屏幕上移动光标或者选中菜单上的某项功能。<br>'),(2330,'desolate','','','','','a. 荒凉的',' The rocky, desolate surface of the moon.<br>     月球多石的、荒凉的表面<br>\n Bands of outlaws lived in the desolate mountains after breaking the laws.<br>     成群的歹徒犯法后栖身于荒山中。<br>'),(2331,'despair','despaired','despaired','despairing','','n. 绝望,失望',' He gave up the attempt in despair.<br>     他绝望之下放弃了尝试。<br>\n Trying to keep this garden in order is the despair of my life.<br>     把这个花园管理好是我力不能及的事。<br>'),(2332,'despatch','despatched','despatched','despatching','','v. 派遣',' We soon despatched the chocolate cake.<br>     我们很快就吃完了巧克力蛋糕。<br>\n A messenger was despatched to take the news to the soldiers at the front.<br>     一名通讯员被派去给前线士兵送消息。<br>'),(2333,'desperate','','','','','a. 不顾一切的,绝望的',' The desperate look of hunger; a desperate cry for help.<br>     饥饿者脸上那绝望的样子；绝望的呼救声<br>\n They invoked help in the desperate situation.<br>     他们在走投无路的情况下恳求援助。<br>'),(2334,'despise','despised','despised','despising','','v. 轻视',' I despise his refusing to accept responsibility.<br>     他拒不承担责任，我鄙视他。<br>\n A dish of strawberries and cream is not to be despised.<br>     一盘草莓加乳酪应该算不差了。<br>'),(2335,'despite','','','','','prep. 不管,尽管<br>\nv.憎恨，轻视',' He came to the meeting despite his illness.<br>     尽管生病，他还是来参加会议。<br>\n Say all you want about her (ie Despite any criticism you can make), she\'s still a fine singer.<br>     不管你怎麽说, 她唱得还算不错.<br>'),(2336,'dessert','','','','desserts','n. 甜食',' I like to have ice cream for dessert.<br>     我喜欢在正餐后吃冰淇淋当甜点。<br>\n He served us brownies as dessert.<br>     他给我们吃核桃仁巧克力饼作为甜点。<br>'),(2337,'destination','','','','destinations','n. 目的地,终点',' We eventually arrived at our destination.<br>     我们终于到达了目的地。<br>\n The parcel was sent to the wrong destination.<br>     包裹送错了地方。<br>'),(2338,'destine','destined','destined','destining','','v. 注定',''),(2339,'destiny','','','','destinies','n. 命运',' Destiny is sometimes cruel.<br>     命运有时是残酷的。<br>\n Some people believe that the Fates preside over man\'s destiny.<br>     有些人相信，命运之神支配人类的命运。<br>'),(2340,'destroy','destroyed','destroyed','destroying','','v. 破坏,毁坏<br>\n[计算机] 撤消',' An atom bomb would destroy a city.<br>     一颗原子弹能摧毁一座城市。<br>\n We want to nurture the new project, not destroy it.<br>     我们要支持这个新工程, 不要破坏它.<br>'),(2341,'destruction','','','','','n. 破坏,毁灭',' It will cause pollution and the destruction of our seas and oceans.<br>     这会引起污染，破坏我们的海洋和江河。<br>\n The intentional, usually remote-controlled destruction of a space vehicle, rocket, or missile after launching, as for defective performance or reasons of safety.<br>     毁灭，摧毁因为方案不完善或为了安全的原因，经常通过遥控对已发射的宇宙飞船、火箭或导弹实施的有意的摧毁<br>'),(2342,'destructive','','','','','a. 破坏性的',' The destructive force of the storm is huge.<br>     暴风雨的破坏力是巨大的。<br>\n Are all small children so destructive?<br>     是不是儿童都喜欢破坏?<br>'),(2343,'detach','detached','detached','detaching','','v. 分离<br>\n[计算机] 脱离',' He detached a link from a chain.<br>     他从链子上拆下一个链环。<br>\n A number of soldiers were detached to guard the building.<br>     许多士兵被派去保护这座建筑物。<br>'),(2344,'detached','','','','','a. 超然的,分离的<br>\nv. 分离<br>\nvbl. 分离',' He detached a link from a chain.<br>     他从链子上拆下一个链环。<br>\n A number of soldiers were detached to guard the building.<br>     许多士兵被派去保护这座建筑物。<br>'),(2345,'detachment','','','','detachments','n. 分离,分遣,分遣队',' He answered with an air of detachment.<br>     他以超然的神态回答。<br>\n He showed detachment in his judgements.<br>     他表现出独到的见解。<br>'),(2346,'detail','detailed','detailed','detailing','details','n. 细节,详情<br>\nvt.详述，详细说明',' He told us the accident in detail.<br>     他详细地把事故讲给我们听。<br>\n The full details of the agreement haven\'t been made public.<br>     协议的细节尚未公布。<br>'),(2347,'detailed','','','','','a. 详细的',' Please send a detailed resume to our company.<br>     请给我们公司寄一份详细的简历。<br>\n Elaborate detailed maps had been prepared for the campaign.<br>     为了这次战役，还准备了详细的地图。<br>'),(2348,'details','','','','','n. 详细资料',' I understood the tenor of their conversation but not the details.<br>     我听懂了他们谈话的大意，但没有听懂其中的细节。<br>\n Tell me all the juicy details.<br>     把有趣的细节都讲给我听。<br>'),(2349,'detain','detained','detained','detaining','','v. 扣留,扣押',' The act of detaining.<br>     扣押，拘留拘留的行为<br>\n A period of time during which a vehicle, person, or material suspected of carrying a contagious disease is detained at a port of entry under enforced isolation to prevent disease from entering a country.<br>     检疫期，隔离期当运输工具、人或材料被怀疑带有传染性疾病，被扣留在港口进行强行隔离的一段期限，以防止疾病传入某个国家<br>'),(2350,'detect','detected','detected','detecting','','v. 发现<br>\n[计算机] 检测',' Small quantities of poison were detected in the dead man\'s stomach.<br>     在死者胃中找到了少量的毒药。<br>\n I seemed to detect some anger in his voice.<br>     我似乎在他的声音中听出一些怒气。<br>'),(2351,'detectable','','','','','a. 可发现的(可察觉的,可探测出的,可检波的)',' Detectable only by microscopic examination or chemical analysis, as a minute blood sample.<br>     通过显微镜观察测知的只能通过显微镜观察或化学分析才能发现的，如微量的血样<br>'),(2352,'detection','','','','','n. 察觉,发觉,侦查,探测',' Given that we do not have complete information about animal detection capabilities, we can only guess as to what the animals are actually sensing.<br>     鉴于我们对动物的察觉能力没能完整的资料，对动物真正感觉到什么我们只有推测。<br>\n Pertaining to the detection and isolation of a malfunction or mistake.<br>     用于修饰或说明与故障或错误的检测和隔离有关的特性。<br>'),(2353,'detective','','','','detectives','a. 侦探的<br>\nn. 侦探',' The company hired a detective to investigate the accident.<br>     公司雇佣了一名侦探来调查这次事故。<br>\n I could now see what the detective was driving at: he was trying to establish my whereabouts on the night of the crime.<br>     我现在能够明白侦探的意思了：他那时正试图确定案发那天夜晚我的行踪。<br>'),(2354,'detector','','','','detectors','n. 探测器',' A device for converting energy form one form to another. In relation to computers, the term is applied to a read/write head, to detector of sector marks in a magnetic disc system, and to electronic/sonic pulse converters of delay line memory.<br>     把能量从一种形式转换成另一种形式的装置。在与计算机有关时，这个术语用在磁盘系统中的读／写磁头、扇面标记的检测上，以及用在延迟线存储器的电子或声波脉冲变换器上。<br>'),(2355,'detent','','','','','制动器',''),(2356,'deter','deterred','deterred','deterring','','v. 制止,使...断念',' Repulse after repulse failed to deter Alec, who persisted day by day, at first with a marriage license and holy words.<br>     苔丝一次又一次的严辞拒绝未能制止亚历克，他整天缠住苔丝，先是用结婚证书和神圣的誓言来说服她。<br>\n Several factors deter new industry from coming to the city.<br>     许多因素造成了新工业无法进入这座城市。<br>'),(2357,'detergent','','','','detergents','n. 清洁剂',' I\'ve tried this new detergent with excellent results.<br>     我试用了这种新型洗涤剂, 效果很好.<br>\n A hard detergent.<br>     抗腐蚀清洁剂<br>'),(2358,'deteriorate','deteriorated','deteriorated','deteriorating','','v. 恶化',' Relation between the two countries have deteriorate sharply in recent week.<br>     最近几周那两个国家间的关系严重恶化了。<br>\n Food is apt to deteriorate in summer.<br>     食物在夏天容易变质。<br>'),(2359,'determinant','','','','','n. 行列式(决定因素)<br>\na. 决定性的',' The number of rows or columns in a determinant or matrix.<br>     行列数行列式或矩阵中行或列的数目<br>\n Fundamental, underlying character as a determinant of the class to which a thing belongs; nature or essence.<br>     本质，天性基础的和根本的特性，如一种事物归属种类的决定因素；天性或本质<br>'),(2360,'determination','','','','determinations','n. 决心',' The police chief spoke of his determination to catch the killer.<br>     警长谈到他决意要抓获凶手。<br>\n He was utterly ruthless in his determination to succeed.<br>     他下定决心争取成功。<br>'),(2361,'determine','determined','determined','determining','','v. 决定,决心要<br>\n[计算机] 确定',' We determined to go to the railway station at once.<br>     我们决定立刻去火车站。<br>\n The court determined that the man was guilty of assault.<br>     法庭裁定那个人犯了侵犯人身罪。<br>'),(2362,'determined','','','','','a. 坚决的',' I am determined to pay him100 dollars.<br>     我决心付给他100美元。<br>\n He determined to form a club.<br>     他决心成立一个俱乐部。<br>'),(2363,'detest','detested','detested','detesting','','v. 厌恶',' She detests having to talk to people at parties.<br>     她讨厌在宴会上为应酬而和人交谈。<br>\n I detest all affectation.<br>     我厌恶一切矫揉造作的行为.<br>'),(2364,'detoxify','detoxified','detoxified','detoxifying','','v. 除去...的毒物',''),(2365,'detriment','','','','','名 损害;损伤[的原因]',' This tax can not be introduced without detriment to the economy.<br>     这一税收制度一旦施行，必定会危害国民经济。<br>\n He works long hours to the detriment of his health.<br>     他长时间的工作，有损健康。<br>'),(2366,'detrimental','','','','','a. 有害的',' Smoking is detrimental to health.<br>     吸烟封健康是有害的。<br>\n Something useless, detrimental, or worthless, especially an animal unfit for breeding.<br>     废物无用的、有害的或无价值的东西，尤指不适于配种的动物<br>'),(2367,'devalue','devalued','devalued','devaluing','','v.&n. 贬值',' It\'s unfair to devalue anyone\'s work unjustly.<br>     不公正地贬低任何人的工作都是不公平的。<br>\n Let\'s not devalue his work unjustly.<br>     我们不可不公正地贬低他的作品。<br>'),(2368,'devastate','devastated','devastated','devastating','','v. 毁坏',' Our Embassy was devastated by three bombs of NATO.<br>     我们的使馆被北约的三枚炸弹炸毁了。<br>\n I was devastated by the news of the wreck.<br>     我获悉失事的消息感到十分震惊。<br>'),(2369,'devastating','','','','','a. 破坏性的, 全然的',' The area is subject to devastating seasonal winds.<br>     这个地区常遭破坏性季风的袭击。<br>'),(2370,'develop','developed','developed','developing','','v. 发展,发达,进步,开发,冲洗照片',' The machine developed the same fault again.<br>     这台机器有出现了同样的毛病。<br>\n Modern music was first developed in Italy.<br>     现代音乐最初是在意大利发展起来的。<br>'),(2371,'developer','','','','','n. 开发者',' Developer can install ole control onto the palette or choose from among the ole control include in delphi2.0.<br>     开发者们可以把OLE控制安装到调色板上或从包括在Delphi2。0中的OLE控制中选择。<br>\n City officials yesterday politely rejected Donald Trump\'s offer to take over renovations at the Central Park Zoo, but privately said the developer was trying to make a monkey out of Mayor Koch.<br>     市府官员婉言谢绝了特鲁普按管整修中央公园动物园的提议，可是私底下说这位地产开发商是想出葛市长的洋相。<br>'),(2372,'developing','','','','','a. 发展中的',' China is a developing country.<br>     中国是一个发展中国家。<br>\n Ours is a developing country.<br>     我们的国家是一个发展中的国家。<br>'),(2373,'development','','','','developments','n. 发展,显影',' This new rose is a development from a very old kind of rose.<br>     这种玫瑰新品种是从一种很早的玫瑰品种进化而来的。<br>\n This is an important stage in our country\'s development.<br>     这是我国发展的重要阶段。<br>'),(2374,'deviate','deviated','deviated','deviating','','v. 脱离,出轨',' Tending to deviate, as from a normal or recognized type; aberrant.<br>     变异的倾向于偏离，如从一个正常的或被承认了的类型；畸变的<br>\n If the multitude ever deviate into the right, it is always for the wrong reason.<br>     纵使大众也曾偏向正途也罢，那总是出于错误的原因。<br>'),(2375,'deviation','','','','','n. 偏差(偏差数)',' A deviation from a vertical or horizontal line, plane, position, or direction.<br>     倾角来自垂直或水平线、面、位置或方向的偏差<br>\n A systematic deviation of a value from a reference value.<br>     某数值偏离参考值的一种系统偏差。<br>'),(2376,'device','','','','','n. 装置,设计,策略,设备',' They use television advertising as a device for stimulating demand.<br>     他们利用电视广告作为刺激需求的方法。<br>\n The device will be in production by the end of the year.<br>     该装置将於年底投入生产.<br>'),(2377,'devil','deviled','deviled','deviling','devils','n. 魔鬼,恶魔',' There will be the devil to pay.<br>     后果不堪设想。<br>\n She found out her husband was a devil soon after her marriage.<br>     结婚后不久她就发现她丈夫是一个邪恶的人。<br>'),(2378,'devise','devised','devised','devising','','v. 设计',' The government devised a scheme for redeveloping the city center.<br>     政府制定了市中心重建计划。<br>\n He devises a new type of transistor.<br>     他发明了一种新的晶体管。<br>'),(2379,'devote','devoted','devoted','devoting','','v. 投入于,献身',' He devoted himself entirely to music.<br>     他将一生奉献给了音乐。<br>\n Please devote more time to your work.<br>     请把更多的时间用于工作。<br>'),(2380,'devotion','','','','devotions','n. 献身,忠诚',' He works with greater devotion.<br>     他工作得更专心了。<br>\n His devotion to music is plain to see.<br>     他对音乐的挚爱是显而易见的。<br>'),(2381,'devour','devoured','devoured','devouring','','v. 吞食',' The child devours fairy tales.<br>     这孩子专注地听着童话故事。<br>\n He sat by the fire, devouring beef and onions.<br>     他坐在火炉旁，狼吞虎咽地吃着牛肉和洋葱。<br>'),(2382,'dew','dewed','dewed','dewing','','n. 露水',' The grass was wet with dew.<br>     草被露水打湿了。<br>\n The grass was sprinkled with dew.<br>     草上沾满了露珠.<br>'),(2383,'diabetes','','','','','n. 糖尿病',''),(2384,'diacritic','','','','','发音符号的,可区别的',''),(2385,'diacritical','','','','','可区分的',''),(2386,'diaeresis','','','','diaereses','分音符',''),(2387,'diagnose','diagnosed','diagnosed','diagnosing','','v. 诊断<br>\nvi. 判断,诊断(疾病)<br>\nvt. 诊断(疾病)',' The doctor diagnosed measles.<br>     医生诊断出麻疹.<br>'),(2388,'diagnosis','','','','diagnoses','n. 诊断',' The two doctors made different diagnosis of my disease.<br>     两位医生对我的病作出了不同的诊断。<br>\n We waited in great suspense for the doctor\'s diagnosis.<br>     我们焦急万分地等候医生做出诊断。<br>'),(2389,'diagnostic','','','','','a. 特征的,诊断的',' Diagnostic imaging in which ultrasound is used to visualize an internal body structure or a developing fetus.<br>     超声波扫描术利用超声波来显示耳体结构或胚胎发育情况的诊断用的成像法<br>\n The removal and examination of a sample of tissue from a living body for diagnostic purposes.<br>     活组织检查因诊断目的而从生命体中取出、消除和观察样品组织<br>'),(2390,'diagnostics','','','','','诊断学',' A person who diagnoses, especially a physician specializing in medical diagnostics.<br>     诊断医生做出诊断的人，尤指做出医学诊断的医生<br>\n Diagnostic or distinctive.<br>     诊断的诊断或区别的<br>'),(2391,'diagonal','','','','diagonals','a. 对角线的,斜的,斜纹的<br>\nn. 对角线,斜线,斜列',' The wood surface of the furniture is full of diagonal stripes.<br>     这件家具的木头表面上布满了斜纹。<br>\n A diagonal line or plane.<br>     对角线或对角面<br>'),(2392,'diagonally','','','','','斜(对)地,对角地',''),(2393,'diagram','diagramed','diagramed','diagraming','diagrams','n. 图解,图表<br>\nv. 用图解法表示',' She gave me a diagram of railway network.<br>     她给了我一张铁路网图解。<br>\n The diagram had been copied with great precision.<br>     该图表的复印件很精确。<br>'),(2394,'dial','dialed','dialed','dialing','dials','n. 刻度盘,针面,转盘<br>\nv. 拨<br>\n[计算机] 拨号',' Put in the money before dialing.<br>     拨电话前先把钱放进去。<br>\n Can you read the number on the dial?<br>     你能读出刻度盘上的读数吗？<br>'),(2395,'dialect','','','','dialects','n. 方言',' Do you speak Sichuan dialect?<br>     你会说四川话吗？<br>\n The dialect is spoken principally in the rural areas.<br>     这种方言主要在农村地区使用。<br>'),(2396,'dialing','','','','','拨号,呼叫',' That\'s all there is to make a speed dial call.<br>     在那里全部要进行快速拨号呼叫。<br>\n Put in the money before dialing.<br>     拨电话前先把钱放进去。<br>'),(2397,'dialog','','','','dialogs','n. 对话,对白',' The writer is not very good at writing dialogs.<br>     这个作家不太擅长写对白。<br>\n At last there can be a reasonable dialog between our two governments.<br>     我们两国最后终于能理智地进行对话了。<br>'),(2398,'dialogue','','','','dialogues','n. 对话',' At last there can be a reasonable dialogue between our two governments.<br>     我们两国最后终于能理智地进行对话了。<br>\n The novel contains more narrative than dialogue.<br>     这部小说里的叙述比对话多.<br>'),(2399,'dialysis','','','','dialyses','n. 透析',''),(2400,'diameter','','','','diameters','n. 直径',' This lens can magnify 20 diameter.<br>     这个透镜能放大20倍。<br>\n The diameter of the tree-trunk is about 2 meters.<br>     这树干的直径大约是2米。<br>'),(2401,'diamond','','','','diamonds','n. 钻石',' She wears a diamond ring on her left hand.<br>     她左手上戴着一枚钻石戒指。<br>\n The diamond ring on her finger glittered in the light.<br>     她手指上的钻石戒指在灯光下闪闪发光。<br>'),(2402,'diaphragm','','','','diaphragms','n. 横隔膜,控光装置',' The diaphragm is between the chest and the abdomen.<br>     横隔膜位于胸腔与腹部之间。<br>'),(2403,'diary','','','','diaries','n. 日记,日记簿',' I keep a diary every day.<br>     我每天记日记。<br>\n She was angry for her mother\'s peeping at her diary.<br>     她因母亲偷看她的日记而生气。<br>'),(2404,'dictate','','','','','v. 听写,口述,口授<br>\nn. 命令,指挥,指令',' He was dictating a letter to his secretary.<br>     他在向秘书口授信稿。<br>\n I will not be dictated to.<br>     我不愿受人摆布。<br>'),(2405,'dictation','','','','dictations','n. 听写',' On dictation equipment, a device for removing a recording from the recording medium.<br>     在口述记录设备上，用来除去记录媒体上记录的一种装置。<br>\n I hated it if I ever had to take dictation from him.<br>     如果我总是不得不作他的口授记录员，我会感到讨厌的。<br>'),(2406,'dictator','','','','dictators','n. 独裁者',' Hitler is a notorious dictator.<br>     希特勒是一个臭名昭著的独裁者。<br>\n They are the dictator and his minions.<br>     他们就是那个独裁者和他的奴仆。<br>'),(2407,'dictionary','','','','dictionaries','n. 词典,字典,辞典',' Please pass the dictionary to me.<br>     请把字典递给我。<br>\n A dictionary is an invaluable aid in learning a new language.<br>     在学习一种新语言时，词典是非常有用的工具。<br>'),(2408,'die','died','died','dying','','n. 金属模子,印模<br>\nv. 死<br>\nn. 骰子（一个小的正六面体）',' His secret died with him, for he never told anyone.<br>     他的秘密至死也不为人知，因为他从未告诉过别人。<br>\n She\'s dying to know where you\'ve been.<br>     她极想知道你到哪儿去了。<br>'),(2409,'diesel','','','','','n. 柴油机,内燃机',' The steam locomotives were superseded by diesel units.<br>     蒸汽机车已被柴油内燃机车所取代。<br>\n Drawing on their practical experience, they designed an air-cooled diesel motor.<br>     他们利用自己的实践经验，设计了一台气冷柴油机。<br>'),(2410,'diet','','','','','n. 日常饮食<br>\nv. 照规定饮食',' Proper diet and exercise are both important for health.<br>     适当的饮食和运动对身体健康都很重要。<br>\n He is on a diet to reduce some weight.<br>     他正在节食以减轻体重。<br>'),(2411,'differ','','','','','v. 不一致,不同',' We differ about moral standards.<br>     我们对道德标准看法不一致。<br>\n Although our looks differ, we are both attractive.<br>     尽管我俩相貌不同，但都讨人喜欢。<br>'),(2412,'difference','differenced','differenced','differencing','differences','n. 不同,差异',' Flowers make no difference to this room.<br>     这房间有没有花没什么区别。<br>\n It won\'t make much difference whether you go today or tomorrow.<br>     你今天或明天去没有多大关系。<br>'),(2413,'different','','','','','a. 不同的',' He\'s a different man from what he was 10 years ago.<br>     他和十年前不一样。<br>\n The two doctors made different diagnosis of my disease.<br>     两位医生对我的病作出了不同的诊断。<br>'),(2414,'differentiate','differentiated','differentiated','differentiating','','v. 区别,差别',' Can you differentiate between the two varieties?<br>     你能辨别这两个品种吗?<br>\n It is wrong to differentiate between people according to their family background.<br>     根据出身不同而区别待人是不对的.<br>'),(2415,'difficult','','','','','a. 困难的',' She is just being difficult.<br>     她正在闹别扭呢。<br>\n He found it difficult to stop smoking.<br>     他觉得戒烟是件难事。<br>'),(2416,'difficulty','','','','difficulties','n. 困难',' He finished the work without any difficulty.<br>     他轻而易举地完成了这项工作。<br>\n She found great difficulties in understanding him.<br>     她觉得很难理解他。<br>'),(2417,'diffuse','','','','','v. 散播',' The light was diffused by the leaves.<br>     树叶使光线漫射。<br>\n Fashion trends diffuse themselves rapidly around the globe.<br>     时装新潮很快就在全世界流行起来。<br>'),(2418,'dig','dug','dug','digging','digs','v. 挖,翻土',' You are just digging your own grave if you go on smoking so heavily.<br>     你继续这样大量吸烟，就是在自掘坟墓。<br>\n We dug up the rose bushes and planted some cabbages.<br>     我们把玫瑰丛挖出来，然后种了一些卷心菜。<br>'),(2419,'digest','digested','digested','digesting','digests','消化',' It took me some time to digest what I had heard.<br>     我花了一些时间才把听到的东西弄明白。<br>\n This rich food doesn\'t digest easily.<br>     这种油腻的食物不易消化。<br>'),(2420,'digestion','','','','digestions','n. 消化',' He has a good digestion.<br>     他消化能力很强。<br>\n The pancreas can produce substances which help in the digestion of food.<br>     胰脏能产生助消化的物质。<br>'),(2421,'digestive','','','','digestives','a. 消化的',' She suffered from digestive trouble.<br>     她患有消化系统疾病。<br>\n Although he is thin, he has good digestive power.<br>     尽管他很瘦，他的消化能力挺好。<br>'),(2422,'digit','','','','','n. 数字,位数,指头',' In the decimal form of a number, a digit that is not significant.<br>     占位符号在一个数的小数形式中，没有意义的数字<br>\n The number represented by the digit or digits in2.<br>     在释文2。中所说的由一位或几位数字表示的数。<br>'),(2423,'digital','','','','','a. 数字的',' Most of the computers we are using are digital computers.<br>     我们正在使用的计算机大多数是数字计算机。<br>\n The only error you shall receive back is from the dts clerk on the digital machine.<br>     应该接收回来的唯一错误来自于Digital机上的DTS职员机。<br>'),(2424,'digitalis','','','','','n. 洋地黄,毛地黄',''),(2425,'digitize','digitized','digitized','digitizing','','vt. 数字化',''),(2426,'dignity','','','','dignities','n. 尊严',' The real dignity of a man lies in what he is, not in what he has.<br>     一个人的真正尊严在于他的品格，而非他的财富。<br>\n There was something impressive about Julia\'s quiet dignity.<br>     朱丽亚的宁静端庄给人印象很深。<br>'),(2427,'dike','diked','diked','diking','dikes','n. 堤防',' Solidifying chiefly as a minor intrusion, especially as a dike or sill, before reaching the earth\'s surface. Used of rocks.<br>     半深成的，浅成的在到达地球表面之前的主要作为小型岩石群固化的，尤其象岩脉或岩床的凝固用于指岩石<br>\n A closely woven mat of brush and poles used to protect an embankment, a dike, or a dam from erosion.<br>     （用以护堤、坝等的）柴排，沉排，沉床荆棘和杆子的密织席，用于保护堤、坝，使不受侵蚀<br>'),(2428,'dilapidated','','','','','a. 毁坏的,荒废的,要塌似的',' The house is very dilapidated but it has possibilities.<br>     这房子已破旧不堪, 但还有可利用的价值.<br>'),(2429,'dilate','dilated','dilated','dilating','','v. 扩大,详述',' The cat dilated its eyes in the darkness.<br>     猫在黑暗中睁大眼睛。<br>\n The horse dilated its nostrils.<br>     那匹马张大它的鼻孔。<br>'),(2430,'dilemma','','','','dilemmas','n. 困境,进退两难',' Faced with that dilemma, he was perplexed.<br>     他面对进退两难的局面，不知如何是好。<br>\n The bad weather put us in a dilemma.<br>     糟糕的天气使我们进退两难<br>'),(2431,'diligent','','','','','a. 勤奋的,用功的',' Their students are diligent about their studies.<br>     他们的学生勤奋学习。<br>\n The diligent student gets up before dawn every day.<br>     这个勤奋的学生每天天亮以前就起床了。<br>'),(2432,'dilute','diluted','diluted','diluting','','v. 冲淡,稀释',' An inert substance used to dilute.<br>     稀释剂一种惰性物质<br>'),(2433,'dim','dimmed','dimmed','dimming','','adj. 暗淡的, 模糊的<br>\nvt. 使暗淡, 使失去光泽<br>\nn. <美俚>笨蛋、傻子',' The light was too dim for me to read easily.<br>     光线太暗，我看书有困难。<br>\n She is rather dim about the importance of keeping records.<br>     她不明白作记录的重要性。<br>'),(2434,'dime','','','','dimes','n. 一角硬币',' on someone\'s dime<br>     由某人付费<br>\n The car can turn on a dime.<br>     这车能在极小的地方转弯。<br>'),(2435,'dimension','dimensioned','dimensioned','dimensioning','dimensions','n. 尺寸,次元,容积,维度',' Time is sometimes called the fourth dimension.<br>     时间有时被称为第四度空间。<br>\n There is another dimension to this problem which you haven\'t considered.<br>     这个问题还有你尚未考虑到的另一个方面。<br>'),(2436,'dimensional','','','','','a. 空间的',' A cube is a three-dimensional object.<br>     立方体是三维物体。<br>\n A square is two-dimensional and a cube is three-dimensional.<br>     正方形是二维的（平面的）, 而正六面体则是三维的（立体的）.<br>'),(2437,'dimensionality','','','','','维数,度数',''),(2438,'diminish','diminished','diminished','diminishing','','v. 减少,变小',' He likes to diminish the skills of others.<br>     他喜欢贬低别人的技能。<br>\n As he turned the knob, the sound diminished.<br>     他一转旋钮，声音就变小了。<br>'),(2439,'dimmed','','','','','暗淡的,无效的',' The lamp threw out a dim light.<br>     灯发出暗淡的光。<br>\n The light of a candle is dimmed by sunlight.<br>     烛光在日光下显得很黯淡。<br>'),(2440,'din','dinned','dinned','dinning','','n. 喧嚣<br>\nv. 絮聒不休地说,暄闹',' They were unable to sleep because of the din coming from the bar.<br>     酒吧里传来的喧闹声吵得他们无法入睡。<br>\n The shouts of the boys dinned his ear.<br>     孩子们的吵闹声把他的耳朵都快吵聋了。<br>'),(2441,'dine','dined','dined','dining','','v. 用正餐,进餐',' My friend invited me to dine out.<br>     我的朋友邀请我出去吃饭。<br>\n Every weekend, we dine at a nice little restaurant in the neighbourhood.<br>     每个周末，我们在附近一家别致的小餐馆进餐。<br>'),(2442,'dingy','','','','','a. 昏暗的(微黑的)<br>\nn. 小船',' He lives in a dingy room.<br>     他住在一个肮脏的屋子里。<br>\n Rooms in cheap hotels are often dingy.<br>     在低级旅馆中全是又黑又脏的房间。<br>'),(2443,'dinner','','','','dinners','n. 主餐,晚餐,晚宴',' It\'s time for dinner.<br>     该吃晚饭了。<br>\n I am busy cooking dinner.<br>     我正忙着做饭。<br>'),(2444,'dint','dinted','dinted','dinting','dints','n. 凹痕<br>\nvt 打出凹痕',' He succeeded by dint of hard work.<br>     他通过辛勤努力才获得成功。<br>'),(2445,'diode','','','','','二极管',' A diode is used as a rectifier.<br>     二极管用作整流器。<br>\n A device, such as a diode, that converts alternating current to direct current.<br>     整流器；整流管一种将交流电流转化为直流电流的装置，如二极管<br>'),(2446,'dioxide','','','','dioxides','n. 二氧化物',' Plants can absorb carbon dioxide and release oxygen.<br>     植物可以吸收二氧化碳释放氧气。<br>\n Soft drinks contain carbon dioxide.<br>     软饮料中含有二氧化碳。<br>'),(2447,'dip','dipped','dipped','dipping','dips','蘸;下沉;倾斜;汲出;舀取;翻阅;涉猎',' The land dips gently to the south.<br>     地面缓缓向南倾斜。<br>\n The sun dipped below the horizon.<br>     太阳落到地平线下。<br>'),(2448,'diphtheria','','','','','n. 白喉',' Diphtheria is a serious infectious disease.<br>     白喉是一种严重的传染病。<br>\n German physiologist. He won a1901 Nobel Prize for work on serum immunization against diphtheria and tetanus.<br>     贝林，埃米尔·冯1854－1917德国生理学家，因其在抗白喉与破伤风血清免疫方面的工作获1901年诺贝尔奖<br>'),(2449,'diphthong','','','','','连元音字,双重元音,双元音字',''),(2450,'diploma','','','','diplomas','n. 文凭',' He obtained a diploma in architecture.<br>     他获得了建筑学的学位证书。<br>\n The diploma is very important for him to get the job.<br>     对他来说，要得到那份工作，文凭是很重要的。<br>'),(2451,'diplomacy','','','','','n. 外交',' The defeat constitutes a major set-back for our diplomacy.<br>     这次失败是我们外交上的重大挫折。<br>\n The spy\'s activities were concealed by the cloak of diplomacy.<br>     间谍的活动是在外交的掩护下暗中进行的.<br>'),(2452,'diplomat','','','','diplomats','a. 外交官,外交家<br>\nn. 外交家',' The diplomat solved the international problem by negotiating.<br>     外交官通过谈判解决了那个国际问题。<br>\n The diplomat is over weight.<br>     那个外交官很胖。<br>'),(2453,'diplomatic','','','','','a. 外交的',' They can\'t be prosecuted for this offence - they have diplomatic immunity.<br>     他们不会因这次违法行为而受到检控 - 他们享有外交豁免权。<br>\n He tried to be diplomatic when he refused their invitation.<br>     他在拒绝他们的邀请时，尽可能地婉转些。<br>'),(2454,'dipping','','','','','(可)调,浸渍(法)',' It is a better book to dip into than to read from cover to cover.<br>     这本书随便翻阅一下还可以，不值得从头到尾读一遍。<br>\n Some models are configurable for either type of output via internal dip switch or jumper.<br>     一些MODELS可以通过内DIP开关或JUMPER进行两种形式的配置。<br>'),(2455,'direct','directed','directed','directing','','a. 笔直的,直接的,坦白的<br>\nv. 指示,指挥,命令',' He directed the building of the new bridge.<br>     他主持修建这座桥的建筑工程。<br>\n The general directed that the prisoners should be set free.<br>     将军下令释放犯人。<br>'),(2456,'direction','','','','directions','n. 方向,指导,用法说明',' Which direction does your room face?<br>     你的房间面向哪个方向？<br>\n The investigation was carried out under the direction of a senior police officer.<br>     调查是在一位高级警官的指导下进行的。<br>'),(2457,'directive','','','','','a. 指导的,指挥的,管理的<br>\nn. 指令<br>\n[计算机] 指令',''),(2458,'directly','','','','','ad. 直接地(立即,完全)',' He answered me very directly and openly.<br>     他非常直接坦率地回答了我。<br>\n They bought the machine directly from the manufacturer.<br>     他们直接从厂商那里购买了这台机器。<br>'),(2459,'director','','','','directors','n. 董事,经理,主管,指导者,导演',' The director told the actress to have a rest.<br>     导演叫这名女演员休息一下。<br>\n Her career culminated in her appointment as director.<br>     她一生事业的顶峰是当上董事。<br>'),(2460,'directory','','','','directories','n. 目录,工商名录,指南<br>\n[计算机] 目录',' The telephone directory gives people\'s names, addresses, and telephone numbers.<br>     电话号码簿提供人名、地址和电话号码。<br>\n I once saw a man tear a telephone directory in half.<br>     我有一次看见一个人把电话簿撕成了两半.<br>'),(2461,'dirt','','','','','n. 污垢,泥土',' Wash the dirt off your hands.<br>     把你手上的泥污洗掉。<br>\n She cleaned the dirt from her finger-nails.<br>     她从指甲里剔掉污垢.<br>'),(2462,'dirty','dirtied','dirtied','dirtying','','a. 肮脏的',' They sat drinking and telling dirty stories.<br>     他们坐在那里，边喝酒边讲下流故事。<br>\n Repairing cars is a dirty work.<br>     修汽车是一个脏活。<br>'),(2463,'disability','','','','disabilities','n. 无力,无能,残疾',' A physical or mental disability.<br>     身心的缺陷体力或智力上的无能<br>\n As a matter of fact, many people have a disability.<br>     事实上，许多人身体都有某种缺陷。<br>'),(2464,'disable','disabled','disabled','disabling','','v. 使...失去能力',' He was disabled from walking by the accident.<br>     由于车祸，他不能走路了。<br>\n Old age disabled him for hard labour.<br>     年迈使他不能干繁重的工作。<br>'),(2465,'disabled','','','','','a. 残废的<br>\nn. 残疾人',' This book sentimentalizes the suffering of the disabled.<br>     这本书以柔懦的笔调渲染了残疾人的痛苦。<br>\n Her latest book discusses the problems of the disabled.<br>     她 的新书论述残疾人的问题.<br>'),(2466,'disadvantage','disadvantaged','disadvantaged','disadvantaging','disadvantages','n. 不利,不利条件,损害,损失',' If you don\'t speak good English, you\'ll be at a big disadvantage when you try to get a job.<br>     你要是英语讲得不好，找工作时就会处于非常不利的地位。<br>\n One of the main disadvantages of this system is that it uses very large amounts of fuel.<br>     该系统的主要弱点之一是消耗大量燃料。<br>'),(2467,'disadvantageous','','','','','a. 不利的',''),(2468,'disagree','disagreed','disagreed','disagreeing','','v. 不一致,不适宜',' I disagree with you on this point.<br>     我不同意你的意见。<br>\n These two reports of the accident disagree with each other.<br>     这两篇关于事故的报道不太一致。<br>'),(2469,'disagreement','','','','disagreements','n. 不合,争论,不一致',' Divergence or disagreement, as between facts or claims; difference.<br>     矛盾，不相符不符合或不一致，如在事实和宣称之间；差异<br>\n A disagreement or quarrel.<br>     争执不一致或争吵<br>'),(2470,'disallow','disallowed','disallowed','disallowing','','v. 不许,不准,驳回',' The judge disallowed that evidence.<br>     法官驳回那项证据。<br>\n Her claim was disallowed on the ground(s) that she had not paid her premium.<br>     她要求赔款遭到拒绝, 原因是她事先没有交纳保险费.<br>'),(2471,'disappear','disappeared','disappeared','disappearing','','v. 消失',' My wallet has disappeared from the table.<br>     我放在桌子上的钱包不见了。<br>\n The sun disappeared behind a cloud.<br>     太阳消失在一片云后面。<br>'),(2472,'disappearance','','','','disappearances','n. 消失',' The act or an instance of gradually diminishing in brightness, loudness, or strength until actual disappearance occurs.<br>     逐渐消失在亮度、响度或精力上逐渐减弱直至全部消失的活动或例子<br>\n He was hard put (to it) to explain her disappearance.<br>     他难以说明她为什麽不见了.<br>'),(2473,'disappoint','disappointed','disappointed','disappointing','','v. 使...失望',' The result disappointed him.<br>     结果使他失望。<br>\n I\'m sorry to disappoint your plans.<br>     我很抱歉妨碍了你的计划。<br>'),(2474,'disappointed','','','','','a. 失望的',' The condition or feeling of being disappointed.<br>     失望，扫兴失望的状态或沮丧的感觉<br>\n If you were expecting our life in the country to be the New Jerusalem, you\'re going to be very disappointed.<br>     如果你期望我们在乡下的生活会像天堂那样美丽，那你是会非常失望的。<br>'),(2475,'disappointment','','','','disappointments','n. 失望',' He expressed keen disappointment that the hearing had been postponed.<br>     他对听证会延期表示大为沮丧。<br>\n That defeat was a surprise and a disappointment.<br>     那次失败令人吃惊，令人失望。<br>'),(2476,'disapproval','','','','','n. 不赞成',' He shook his head in disapproval.<br>     他摇了摇头表示反对。<br>\n She gestured her disapproval.<br>     她用姿势表示不赞成.<br>'),(2477,'disapprove','disapproved','disapproved','disapproving','','v. 不赞成',' Father disapproved of our marriage.<br>     父亲不同意我们俩人的婚事。<br>\n The plan was disapproved<br>     计划没有被通过。<br>'),(2478,'disarm','disarmed','disarmed','disarming','','v. 解除武装,回复平常的编制,缓和',' We didn\'t trust him at first, but his charming manner completely disarmed us.<br>     我们开始时并不信任他，但他令人愉快的举止完全消除了我们的疑虑。<br>\n The police disarmed the criminal.<br>     警察缴下了罪犯的枪械。<br>'),(2479,'disarray','disarrayed','disarrayed','disarraying','','v. 弄乱,使混乱,使脱去衣服<br>\nn. 无秩序,杂乱,不整齐的衣服',' Changing offices has left my papers in complete disarray.<br>     办公室搬迁, 使我的文件全部乱了套了.<br>\n The troops fled in disarray.<br>     部队仓皇逃散.<br>'),(2480,'disassemble','disassembled','disassembled','disassembling','','v. 解开,分解<br>\n[计算机] 反汇编',' Disassemble a toaster.<br>     拆卸烤面包炉<br>'),(2481,'disaster','','','','disasters','n. 灾难',' They had led the country into economic disaster.<br>     他们把国家带入了经济灾难中。<br>\n The disaster caused him to waver in his faith.<br>     这件灾难使他对信仰发生了动摇。<br>'),(2482,'disastrous','','','','','a. 灾难性的',' The new system has had a disastrous effect on productivity.<br>     新制度已对生产力造成了灾难性的影响。<br>\n This environmental effect of this new factory could be disastrous.<br>     这家新工厂给自然环境带来的影响可能是灾难性的。<br>'),(2483,'disburse','disbursed','disbursed','disbursing','','vt. 支付',''),(2484,'disbursement','','','','','n. 支付,支出',''),(2485,'disc','','','','discs','n. 断开(折扣,发现的,发现者,鉴别器)',' I have many discs.<br>     我有许多唱片。<br>\n You can\'t copy your file with this disc; it\'s full.<br>     你不能用这张磁盘拷文件，这张盘满了。<br>'),(2486,'discard','','','','','n. 丢弃,扔掉<br>\nv. 丢弃,抛弃',' He discarded his winter clothing.<br>     他把冬天穿的衣服都脱掉了。<br>\n You\'ve got to discard before you can pick up another card.<br>     你得先打出一张牌，才能拿另一张牌。<br>'),(2487,'discarded','','','','','放弃的,删除的',' History discarded him.<br>     他被历史所抛弃。<br>\n He discarded his winter clothing.<br>     他把冬天穿的衣服都脱掉了。<br>'),(2488,'discern','discerned','discerned','discerning','','v. 辨别,看清楚',' He was just able to discern the road from the dark.<br>     他在黑暗中只能勉强辨认出道路。<br>\n I soon discerned that the man was lying.<br>     我马上察觉出那人在撒谎。<br>'),(2489,'discharge','discharged','discharged','discharging','discharges','v. 卸下,放出,解雇,放电,解除',' The judge discharged the prisoner.<br>     法官把囚犯释放了。<br>\n How long will the discharge of the cargo take?<br>     卸货需要多久？<br>'),(2490,'disciplinary','','','','','a. 训练的,规律的,训戒的',' A governing, advisory, or disciplinary body of some colleges and universities composed of faculty members and sometimes student representatives.<br>     大学评议会某些学院和大学中由全体教员及有学衔的行政人员，有时还有学生代表，组成的管理，顾问，或纪律机构<br>\n Controlled behavior resulting from disciplinary training; self-control.<br>     自制遵守纪律训练而养成的克制行为；自控<br>'),(2491,'discipline','disciplined','disciplined','disciplining','disciplines','n. 训练,纪律,惩罚<br>\nv. 训练,惩罚',' She never disciplines her children and they are uncontrollable.<br>     她从不管教自己的孩子，弄得他们无法无天。<br>\n The teacher can\'t keep discipline in her class.<br>     那位老师无法维持教室纪律。<br>'),(2492,'disclaim','disclaimed','disclaimed','disclaiming','','v. 放弃,弃权,拒绝',' The manufacturers disclaim all responsibility for the damage caused by misuse.<br>     因使用不当造成的损坏，生产厂家不负任何责任。<br>\n The manufacturer disclaim all responsibility for damage cause by misuse.<br>     使用不当而造成的损坏，生产厂家不负任何责任。<br>'),(2493,'disclose','disclosed','disclosed','disclosing','','v. 揭露',' I have no intention of disclosing their names.<br>     我无意泄露他们的姓名。<br>\n The authorities finally disclosed the truth to the press.<br>     当局终于向新闻界透露了真相。<br>'),(2494,'disco','','','','discos','n. 迪斯科舞厅',' This disco is a magnet for young people.<br>     这家迪斯科舞厅经常吸引大批年轻的顾客.<br>\n We danced to the disco music.<br>     我们跟著迪斯科乐曲跳舞.<br>'),(2495,'discolor','discolored','discolored','discoloring','','vt. 使...变色(或褪色)',' Discolored, as from a bruise; black-and-blue.<br>     青黑色的尤指由于瘀伤而变色的；青黑色的<br>'),(2496,'discomfort','discomforted','discomforted','discomforting','discomforts','n. 不便之处,不适',' She still suffers considerable discomfort from her injury.<br>     她因那次受伤至今仍感不适。<br>\n I was unhappy because of the discomforts of travel.<br>     我因为旅行的不适而感到不快。<br>'),(2497,'disconnect','disconnected','disconnected','disconnecting','','v. 断开<br>\nvt. 拆开,分开',' If you don\'t pay your bills they\'ll disconnect your electricity/gas.<br>     若不付费用, 就要停止供应电力[煤气].<br>'),(2498,'disconnection','','','','','n. 断开',''),(2499,'discontinue','discontinued','discontinued','discontinuing','','v. 搁下,中止,停止',' I\'m so busy that I have to discontinue weekly visits.<br>     我很忙，所以不得不中断每周的访问。<br>\n You must discontinue your actions.<br>     你必须中断你的行动。<br>'),(2500,'discord','','','','','n. 不调和',' He\'s been a source of discord and worry.<br>     他成为不和和烦恼的根源。<br>\n What has brought discord into the family?<br>     什么事使得这个家庭不和？<br>'),(2501,'discotheque','','','','','n. 唱片舞会,迪斯科舞（厅）',' Mary wore handsome go-go boots to the discotheque last night.<br>     玛丽穿着一双入时的马靴参加昨晚的舞会。<br>'),(2502,'discount','discounted','discounted','discounting','discounts','n. 折扣,贴现率<br>\nv. 打折扣,贴现',' The discount was very huge.<br>     折扣的幅度非常大。<br>\n We give 10 percent discount for cash.<br>     现金付款，我们九折优惠。<br>'),(2503,'discourage','discouraged','discouraged','discouraging','','v. 使气馁,阻碍',' I was never discouraged against learning English.<br>     我从未对学习英语失去信心。<br>\n Inflation discourages saving.<br>     通货膨胀阻碍储蓄的积累。<br>'),(2504,'discourse','','','','','n. 演讲<br>\nvi. 讲述,著述',' The judges had solemn discourse together.<br>     法官们在一起严肃地交谈。<br>\n They listened to his discourse on human relations.<br>     他们听他作关于人际关系的演讲。<br>'),(2505,'discover','','','','','v. 发现',' She discovered the joy of writing.<br>     她感到了写作的乐趣。<br>\n Columbus is said to have discovered America in 1492.<br>     据说哥伦布于1492年发现了美洲。<br>'),(2506,'discovery','','','','discoveries','n. 发现,发现物',' A collector of rare insects will show us some of his latest discoveries.<br>     一位稀有昆虫采集家将给我们看一些他的最新发现。<br>\n The new discovery caused a great sensation.<br>     这项新发现很轰动。<br>'),(2507,'discreet','','','','','a. 谨慎的',' It was not discreet of you to say that.<br>     你那样说有欠考虑。<br>\n I\'ll certainly be most discreet in my conversation.<br>     我在谈话中当然会十分小心的。<br>'),(2508,'discreetly','','','','','ad. 谨慎地, 小心地',' Before changes were mad in the law, some prostitutes literally went on the streets. Now, they operate more discreetly from bars and clubs.<br>     在法律未修改之前，一些妓女直接在街上拉客；现在，他们偷偷摸摸地活动在酒吧或夜总会了。<br>\n His utterances were discreetly academic.<br>     他的言论严谨；具有学术性。<br>'),(2509,'discrepancy','','','','discrepancies','n. 相差,差异,差别',' The price tag says$100 and you charged me for$120; how do you explain the discrepancy?<br>     ＂货物标签上写的是一百美元，你向我索价一百二十美元，这个差异该怎么解释？＂<br>\n I thought I had explained away the discrepancy but he had the actual figure and so I left myself wide open to a charge of telling lies.<br>     我以为我已经有矛盾之处作了辩解，但是他掌握了确凿的数字，因此当他把控我说谎时，我毫无招架之势。<br>'),(2510,'discrete','','','','','a. 不连续的  离散的<br>\n[计算机] 分离  离散',' Any of several devices that convert incident electromagnetic radiation of mixed frequencies to one or more discrete frequencies of highly amplified and coherent ultraviolet, visible, or infrared radiation.<br>     激光器使偶然的混杂频率的电磁辐射，变为一个或更多的高度强化和连续的紫外线、可见光或红外线辐射的分离频率仪器中的一种<br>\n A discrete part or portion of a work, such as a painting, building, or decorative object, especially when considered in isolation.<br>     细部某项作品（例如绘画、建筑、装饰）的一部分，尤指这些部分被分开来独立考虑的部分<br>'),(2511,'discretion','','','','','n. 慎重,辨别力,考虑<br>\n[计算机] 判定',' The hours of the meetings will be fixed at the monitor\'s discretion.<br>     开会时间将由班长自行决定。<br>\n I won\'t tell you what time to leave, you\'re old enough to use your own discretion.<br>     我不告诉你什么时候离开，你已经长大了，该自己作出决定。<br>'),(2512,'discriminant','','','','','判别式',''),(2513,'discriminate','discriminated','discriminated','discriminating','','v. 区别,差别待遇',' People should not be discriminated against.<br>     人们不应该被区别对待。<br>\n Can you discriminate good books from bad?<br>     你能区别好书与坏书吗？<br>'),(2514,'discrimination','','','','','n. 歧视',' We are strongly opposed to racial discrimination.<br>     我们强烈反对种族歧视。<br>\n We should not have racial discrimination.<br>     我们不该有种族歧视。<br>'),(2515,'discriminator','','','','discriminators','鉴别器',''),(2516,'discuss','discussed','discussed','discussing','','v. 讨论',' They said they had an important matter to discuss with you.<br>     他们说有要事与你相商。<br>\n What does the book discuss?<br>     这本书讲了什么？<br>'),(2517,'discussion','','','','discussions','n. 讨论<br>\nv. 讨论,商议',' When will the matter come up for discussion?<br>     这件事什么时候提出来讨论？<br>\n Their case is now under discussion.<br>     他们的案件现在正在讨论中。<br>'),(2518,'disdain','disdained','disdained','disdaining','','n. 轻蔑<br>\nv. 蔑视',' He disdained that man for snobbishness and was unwilling to talk to him.<br>     他鄙视那个势利小人，不愿和他说话。<br>\n I have nothing but disdain for such a person.<br>     对这样一个人，我只有鄙视。<br>'),(2519,'disease','diseased','diseased','diseasing','diseases','n. 疾病',' Many diseases are caused by bacteria.<br>     许多疾病是由细菌引起的。<br>\n The poor man has a serious disease of the liver.<br>     这个可怜的人患有严重的肝病。<br>'),(2520,'diseased','','','','','a. 害病的,病态的,不健全的',' The diseased trees are marked by protuberances on their bark.<br>     有病的树木可由其树皮上的结节看出.<br>\n The surgeon cut the diseased tissue out from the girl\'s leg.<br>     外科医生切除了女孩腿上有病的组织。<br>'),(2521,'disgrace','disgraced','disgraced','disgracing','','n. 耻辱,不名誉<br>\nv. 耻辱,使...失体面',' He fell into disgrace with his companions.<br>     他的朋友都看不起他。<br>\n He quit in disgrace over the bribe.<br>     他因受贿而不光彩地辞职了。<br>'),(2522,'disgraceful','','','','','a. 可耻的,不名誉的',' This newspaper article is a disgraceful intrusion into my private life.<br>     报纸上的这篇文章是对我私生活的侵扰，这种做法很不光彩。<br>\n Please account for your disgraceful conduct.<br>     对你的可耻行为请作解释.<br>'),(2523,'disguise','disguised','disguised','disguising','disguises','n. 假面目,假装<br>\nv. 假装',' His illness was a blessing in disguise, because he afterwards married his nurse.<br>     他生病倒是因祸得福，因为后来他和他的护士结了婚。<br>\n It proved difficult to disguise his anxiety.<br>     他的焦虑难以掩饰。<br>'),(2524,'disgust','disgusted','disgusted','disgusting','','n. 厌恶,嫌恶<br>\nv. 令人厌恶',' He returned downstairs in disgust.<br>     他厌恶地转身下楼。<br>\n His behavior filled her with disgust.<br>     她对他的行为充满了厌恶。<br>'),(2525,'disgustful','','','','','a. 令人生厌的',''),(2526,'dish','dished','dished','dishing','dishes','n. 盘子<br>\nvt. 上菜<br>\nn.一样菜，一道菜',' His favorite dish is roast duck.<br>     他最喜欢吃的菜是烤鸭。<br>\n The careless waiter dropped the dish onto the ground.<br>     那个粗心的侍者把盘子摔到了地上。<br>'),(2527,'dishonest','','','','','a. 不诚实的',' He is a dishonest merchant.<br>     他是一个不诚实的商人。<br>\n Susceptibility to bribery or corruption, as in the use of a position of trust for dishonest gain.<br>     甘受贿赂，贪污腐化易受贿赂或腐败的影响性，如在使用不诚实的收益的信托状况时<br>'),(2528,'dishonor','dishonored','dishonored','dishonoring','','n. 不名誉<br>\nv. 玷辱,使...蒙羞',' He was a dishonor to his regiment.<br>     他是那个团的耻辱。<br>\n His behaviors have brought dishonor onto his family.<br>     他的行为给他的家庭带来了耻辱。<br>'),(2529,'dishonorable','','','','','a. 不名誉的',' He is ashamed for his former dishonorable action.<br>     他对他以前不光彩的行为感到羞愧。<br>\n He has done many dishonorable things these years<br>     这些年，他干了许多可耻的事情。<br>'),(2530,'disillusion','disillusioned','disillusioned','disillusioning','','n. 觉醒,幻减<br>\nv. 醒悟,使幻想破减',' She still believes in Santa Claus and it would be cruel to disillusion her.<br>     她仍然相信有圣诞老人, 要是使她这一幻想破灭就於心不忍了.<br>\n Disillusion voter want an alternative to the two main parties.<br>     失望的选民需要一个党派以取代这两个大党。<br>'),(2531,'disinclined','','','','','a. 不愿的, 不想的',' Overloading his stomach with a heavy meal, he was disinclined for any serious work.<br>     吃了不易消化的东西，他不愿去干那些难做的工作。<br>\n Be disinclined to do sth.<br>     无意干某事，不愿干某事<br>'),(2532,'disinfect','disinfected','disinfected','disinfecting','','v. 消毒',''),(2533,'disinfectant','','','','','a. 消毒的<br>\nn. 消毒剂',' Disinfectant kills germs.<br>     消毒剂灭杀细菌。<br>\n Dip your injured finger in the disinfectant to soak out the poison.<br>     把你受伤的手指浸在消毒剂里，把毒浸泡出来。<br>'),(2534,'disinflation','','','','','n. 反通货膨胀',''),(2535,'disintegration','','','','','n. 瓦解',' The breakdown and disintegration of organic tissue.<br>     组织溶解器官组织的分解和破坏<br>\n Decomposition into fragments or parts; disintegration.<br>     分裂，分解碎片或几部分；分解<br>'),(2536,'disjunction','','','','','析取,分离,分裂',''),(2537,'disk','','','','disks','n. 磁盘片<br>\n[计算机] 磁盘',' I have many disks.<br>     我有许多唱片。<br>\n You can\'t copy your file with this disk; it\'s full.<br>     你不能用这张磁盘拷文件，这张盘满了。<br>'),(2538,'diskette','','','','','软盘',' In System/32, the system processing that prepares a diskette file for processing.<br>     在IBMSystem／32中，为处理准备一个软盘文件的系统操作。<br>\n Insert a diskette into one of your computer\'s disk drive, as describe on page1.<br>     把一张软盘插入计算机的磁盘驱动器中，如第1页所述。<br>'),(2539,'dislike','disliked','disliked','disliking','dislikes','v. 不喜欢,厌恶<br>\nvt.&n. 不喜爱,厌恶',' He dislikes dogs.<br>     他不喜欢狗。<br>\n If you behave like that, you\'ll get yourself disliked.<br>     如果你的行为那样，你会让人厌恶的。<br>'),(2540,'dislikes','','','','','vt. 不喜欢',' He dislikes dogs.<br>     他不喜欢狗。<br>\n He dislikes his wide nostrils.<br>     他不喜欢自己的宽大的鼻孔。<br>'),(2541,'dislocate','dislocated','dislocated','dislocating','','v. 脱臼,弄乱',' Flights have been dislocated by thefog.<br>     大雾将飞机的班次搅乱了.<br>'),(2542,'disloyal','','','','','a. 不忠的',' He was disloyal to his country.<br>     他对祖国不忠。<br>\n That person is disloyal to his associates.<br>     那人对同事不守信义。<br>'),(2543,'disloyalty','','','','disloyalties','a. 不忠<br>\nn. 不忠实',' He was/felt deeply wounded by their disloyalty.<br>     因为他们不忠, 他十分伤心.<br>\n I know he suspect me of disloyalty, but I suppose I\'ll just have to brave it out.<br>     我知道他怀疑我不忠，但是我想我不得不硬着头皮去见他。<br>'),(2544,'dismal','','','','dismals','a. 阴沉的,凄凉的,暗的',' We were all depressed by the dismal weather.<br>     阴沉的天气让我们都感到压抑。<br>\n Dismal weather; took a dismal view of the economy.<br>     阴沉的天气；对经济抱着不乐观的看法<br>'),(2545,'dismay','dismayed','dismayed','dismaying','','n. 沮丧<br>\nv. 使...灰心,使...害怕',' To my dismay, he made the same mistakes.<br>     使我惊讶的是，他又犯了同样的错误。<br>\n It dismayed us that the project had been canceled.<br>     那个计划取消了，这让我们非常惊讶。<br>'),(2546,'dismiss','dismissed','dismissed','dismissing','','v. 解散,开除',' If you are late again, you will be dismissed.<br>     如果你再迟到，你将被解雇。<br>\n He dismissed the unpleasant subject and talked about something else.<br>     他不谈论这个令人不愉快的话题，而去谈论别的事情。<br>'),(2547,'dismissal','','','','dismissals','n. 免职,解雇',' His rash dismissal of the offer annoyed me.<br>     他对该提议轻率的拒绝激怒了我。<br>\n The dismissals led to a strike.<br>     雇主解雇工人导致了罢工事件。<br>'),(2548,'dismount','dismounted','dismounted','dismounting','','v. 使...下马,下马',' Two soldiers dismounted the gun from the base.<br>     两个战士把炮从底座上卸下来。<br>\n One have to dismount from an idea and get into saddle again at every parenthesis.<br>     每当遇上一个括号，就叫人不得不从一种想法下马，然后再次骑上马鞍。<br>'),(2549,'disobey','disobeyed','disobeyed','disobeying','','v. 违反',' He disobeyed his mother and went to the party.<br>     他不听母亲的劝告，参加了那次聚会。<br>\n Those who disobey must be punished by law.<br>     违法分子必须受到法律惩罚。<br>'),(2550,'disorder','disordered','disordered','disordering','disorders','n. 杂乱,混乱<br>\nv. 扰乱',' Anxiety may disorder the stomach.<br>     忧虑可能会引起胃部不适。<br>\n The room is in dreadful disorder.<br>     房间里乱七八糟。<br>'),(2551,'disparity','','','','disparities','n. 不一致',' Rich and poor live side by side but in conditions of extraordinary disparity.<br>     虽然富人和穷人住在一起，但是条件相差极为悬殊。<br>'),(2552,'dispatch','dispatched','dispatched','dispatching','dispatches','v. 派遣<br>\n[计算机] 分派',' We soon dispatched the chocolate cake.<br>     我们很快就吃完了巧克力蛋糕。<br>\n A messenger was dispatched to take the news to the soldiers at the front.<br>     一名通讯员被派去给前线士兵送消息。<br>'),(2553,'dispatcher','','','','','调度器,调度程序,分配器',''),(2554,'dispel','dispelled','dispelled','dispelling','','v. 驱散,驱逐',' The company is trying to dispel rumour about a take-over.<br>     公司力图澄清有关接管的流言。<br>\n How can we dispel their doubt?<br>     我们怎么才能驱散他们的疑虑呢？<br>'),(2555,'dispense','dispensed','dispensed','dispensing','','v. 分发',' The doctor dispensed a prescription to his patient.<br>     医生开处方给病人配药。<br>\n She cannot dispense with a servant.<br>     她不能没有佣人。<br>'),(2556,'disperse','dispersed','dispersed','dispersing','','v. 分散,传播,散开',' The police dispersed the crowd.<br>     警方驱散群众。<br>\n The wind dispersed the cloud from the sky.<br>     风吹散了天上的云。<br>'),(2557,'displace','displaced','displaced','displacing','','v. 移置,替换',' The indigenous population was soon displaced by the settlers.<br>     没过多久，外来移民就把当地人赶出了家园。<br>\n Weeds tend to displace other plants.<br>     杂草越来越