isputed','disputed','disputing','disputes','n. 争论<br>\nv. 争论',' They are disputing about the rights and wrongs of the case.<br>     他们正在激烈争论这个事件的是非曲直。<br>\n His honesty is beyond dispute.<br>     他的诚实是无可争议的。<br>'),(2567,'disregard','disregarded','disregarded','disregarding','','n. 忽视<br>\nv. 忽视,不顾',' He disregarded his doctor\'s advice.<br>     他无视医生的劝告。<br>\n Disregarding all the difficulties, we arrived here in time.<br>     尽管有那么多困难，我们仍然及时地到达了这儿。<br>'),(2568,'disrupt','disrupted','disrupted','disrupting','','a. 分裂的,分散的<br>\nv. 使...分裂,使...瓦解',' His speech disrupted the meeting.<br>     他的讲演使会场陷入混乱。<br>\n An accident has disrupted railway services into and out of the city.<br>     一次交通事故使进出这座城市的铁路交通陷于混乱。<br>'),(2569,'disruptive','','','','','a. 捣乱的,破坏性的,制造混乱的',' The police detained several suspects for questioning. The disruptive students were detained after school until their parents had been notified.<br>     警察拘留了许多疑犯进行审问，捣乱的学生在放学后被拘禁了，直到通知他们的家长<br>\n One engaged in diversionary, disruptive, or subversive activities.<br>     背离既定路线者；阴谋破坏者采用不同路线，进行分裂或从事破坏活动的人<br>'),(2570,'dissatisfaction','','','','','n. 不满',' Private members voice public dissatisfaction at have to pay higher taxes.<br>     下议院议员道出了公众对增加税收的不满。<br>\n The condition or fact of being displeased; dissatisfaction.<br>     不愉快，不满意不高兴的情况或事实；不满<br>'),(2571,'dissatisfy','dissatisfied','dissatisfied','dissatisfying','','v. 使感觉不满,不满足',' I\'m thoroughly dissatisfied with your work.<br>     我完全不满意你的工作。<br>\n She\'s very dissatisfied at not getting a bonus.<br>     她因未能获得奖金而深感不满。<br>'),(2572,'dissector','','','','','析象管',''),(2573,'disseminate','disseminated','disseminated','disseminating','','v. 散播,传播,宣传',' They use the press to disseminate right-wing views.<br>     他们利用报刊来传播右翼观点.<br>'),(2574,'dissemination','','','','','传播,宣传,传染(病毒)',''),(2575,'dissertation','','','','dissertations','n. 论文',' I\'m working my notes up into a dissertation.<br>     我正在把我的笔记修改成论文。<br>'),(2576,'dissimilar','','','','','a. 不同的',' Similarity of structure between organs or parts, possibly of dissimilar function, that are related by common descent.<br>     同构发生，同源发生源于同一祖先，可能功能不同的器官或部分在结构上的相似<br>\n The quality or condition of being unlike or dissimilar.<br>     不同，相异性质或条件上的不相同或不一致<br>'),(2577,'dissipate','dissipated','dissipated','dissipating','','vt. 使...消散(浪费)',' He soon dissipated his fortune.<br>     他很快就把财产浪费光了。<br>\n The sun dissipated the mist.<br>     太阳驱散了雾。<br>'),(2578,'dissipation','','','','','损耗',' Given over to dissipation; dissolute.<br>     放荡的沉迷于挥霍无度的；放荡的<br>\n The reduction in size of components and circuits for increasing package density and reducing power dissipation and signal propagation delays.<br>     减少元件和电路的几何尺寸，以达到增加电路的封装密度、减少功耗和减小信号传播延迟的目的。<br>'),(2579,'dissolution','','','','dissolutions','n. 分解',' He obtained the dissolution of his marriage with her.<br>     他解除了和她的婚姻。<br>\n The President announced the dissolution of Parliament.<br>     总统宣布了议会解散。<br>'),(2580,'dissolve','dissolved','dissolved','dissolving','','v. 溶解,解散',' The parliament was dissolved.<br>     议会解散了。<br>\n Ice dissolved in the warm weather.<br>     冰在温暖的天气中溶化了。<br>'),(2581,'distance','distanced','distanced','distancing','distances','n. 距离',' My house is four miles distance from the sea.<br>     我家离海四英里。<br>\n We can see the mountain from the distance.<br>     我们从远处就可以看到那座山。<br>'),(2582,'distant','','','','','a. 遥远的,远的',' He is a distant cousin of mine.<br>     他是我的一位远房表亲。<br>\n My company is five miles distant from my home.<br>     公司距离我家五英里远。<br>'),(2583,'distend','distended','distended','distending','','v. 扩大,扩张,吹大',' Having eyes with greatly distended pupils.<br>     眼珠暴突的具有带有膨大的瞳孔的眼睛的<br>\n Swollen or distended beyond normal size by fluid or gaseous material.<br>     肿胀的液体或气体材料超过正常尺寸的肿胀或膨胀<br>'),(2584,'distil','distilled','distilled','distilling','','v. 蒸馏, 提取....的精华',' Water can be made pure by distilling it.<br>     水可以通过蒸馏而提纯。<br>\n Tears distilled slowly from her eyes.<br>     泪水从她的眼睛里慢慢地滴下来。<br>'),(2585,'distill','distilled','distilled','distilling','','v. 蒸馏,滴下',' Water can be made pure by distilling it.<br>     水可以通过蒸馏而提纯。<br>\n Tears distilled slowly from her eyes.<br>     泪水从她的眼睛里慢慢地滴下来。<br>'),(2586,'distillation','','','','distillations','n. 蒸馏',' Purification of water may be achieved by distillation.<br>     水的净化可由蒸馏获得。<br>\n We may purge water by distillation.<br>     我们可以用蒸馏法使水净化。<br>'),(2587,'distinct','','','','','a. (from)独特的,不同的,明显的,清楚的',' There is a distinct posibility that she\'ll be your teacher next term.<br>     她下学期当你们的老师的可能性非常大。<br>\n Those two ideas are quite distinct from each other.<br>     这两种观点截然不同。<br>'),(2588,'distinction','','','','distinctions','n. 差别,不同,对比,区分,辨别',' He passed the examination with distinction.<br>     他以优异成绩通过考试。<br>\n We should make a distinction between right and wrong.<br>     我们应该分清是非。<br>'),(2589,'distinctive','','','','','a. 有特色的,出众的',' Soldiers wear a distinctive uniform.<br>     士兵们穿着特制的制服。<br>\n This is a distinctive room.<br>     这是一间独具一格的房间。<br>'),(2590,'distinctly','','','','','ad. 显然地,明显地,清楚地',' He spoke very distinctly.<br>     他说话十分清晰。<br>\n The choir was (singing) distinctly out of tune in places.<br>     合唱团有些地方明显（唱）走调了.<br>'),(2591,'distinguish','distinguished','distinguished','distinguishing','','v. 区别,辨别,表现突出',' He distinguished himself by his courage.<br>     他因英勇而扬名。<br>\n The twins were so much alike that it was impossible to distinguish one from the other.<br>     这对孪生子像得使人无法分辨。<br>'),(2592,'distinguished','','','','','a. 卓著的<br>\nv. 区别<br>\nvbl. 区别',' Premier Zhou is a distinguished politician.<br>     周总理是一位卓越的政治家。<br>\n I think grey hair makes you look rather distinguished.<br>     我觉得你灰白的头发使你看上去很有尊严。<br>'),(2593,'distort','distorted','distorted','distorting','','v. 扭曲',' You have distorted my motives.<br>     你曲解了我的动机。<br>\n The reporter distorted the facts.<br>     记者们歪曲了事实。<br>'),(2594,'distortion','','','','','n. 扭曲,变形,曲解',' A distortion of shape.<br>     变形形状的扭曲<br>\n A distortion or twist, especially in a piece of wood.<br>     弯曲歪曲、变形、尤指某一木头<br>'),(2595,'distract','distracted','distracted','distracting','','v. 转移,分心',' The film managed to distract me from these problems for a while.<br>     这部影片分散了我的注意力, 让我暂时忘记了这些难题.<br>\n Don\'t distract my attention I\'m trying to study!<br>     别分散我的注意力--我正要学习呢!<br>'),(2596,'distraction','','','','distractions','n. 娱乐,分心的事物,分心',' The child\'s continual crying drove me to distraction.<br>     那孩子不断的哭声弄得我几乎要发狂。<br>\n TV can be a welcome distraction after a hard day\'s work.<br>     辛苦一天之后，看电视有时是很美的逍遣。<br>'),(2597,'distrain','distrained','distrained','distraining','','n. 为抵债而扣押',''),(2598,'distress','distressed','distressed','distressing','','n. 苦恼,贫困<br>\nv. 使...苦恼',' What are you looking so distressed for?<br>     什么事情使你看起来如此烦恼？<br>\n The lifeboat went out to a ship in distress.<br>     救生船去救一艘遇险的船只。<br>'),(2599,'distribute','distributed','distributed','distributing','','v. 分配,散布',' The mother distributed candy among children.<br>     母亲给孩子们发糖果。<br>\n The books in the library were distributed according to subjects.<br>     图书馆里的藏书按科目分类。<br>'),(2600,'distributed','','','','','分布的,分布式的',' The mother distributed candy among children.<br>     母亲给孩子们发糖果。<br>\n They distributed leaflets to customers.<br>     他们给客户散发传单。<br>'),(2601,'distribution','','','','distributions','n. 分发,分配,散布,分布',' The distribution of the magazine is 2000.<br>     该杂志的销售量为2000份。<br>\n They could not agree about the distribution of the profits.<br>     他们对于利润的分配意见不一致。<br>'),(2602,'distributor','','','','','经销商',' The meeting with the German distributor has been advanced from11: 00 to9: 30.<br>     与德国销售人员的会晤由11：00提前到9：30。<br>\n I\'ll take some back with me to show to our distributor.<br>     我要带一些回去给我们的经销商看看。<br>'),(2603,'district','','','','districts','n. 区,地区,行政区<br>\nv. 区,区域,地区',' He lives in a mountainous district.<br>     他住在山区。<br>\n This district grew cotton on a large scale.<br>     这个地区过去大量种棉花。<br>'),(2604,'disturb','disturbed','disturbed','disturbing','','v. 扰乱,妨碍,使...不安',' He put his oars in the water and disturbed the smooth surface of the lake.<br>     他把桨放入水中，搅乱了平静的湖面。<br>\n They took the phone off the hook so no calls would disturb them.<br>     他们摘下电话听筒，以免电话打扰他们。<br>'),(2605,'disturbance','','','','disturbances','n. 扰乱,骚动',' The noise of cars passing along the road is a continual disturbance to our quiet at home.<br>     马路上来往的车辆声音不断地破坏我们家的安宁。<br>\n Those men were charged by the police with causing a disturbance.<br>     那些人因制造骚乱被警方控诉。<br>'),(2606,'disturbing','','','','','a. 烦扰的',' He\'s constantly disturbing me.<br>     他老是打扰我.<br>\n I wouldn\'t think of disturbing them at this hour of the night.<br>     我不能想象这样深更半夜去打扰他们。<br>'),(2607,'disunite','disunited','disunited','disuniting','','v. 使分离,不和',''),(2608,'disuse','','','','','v.&n. 废止',' Here are some words that have fallen into disuse.<br>     这是一些废弃不用的词。<br>\n The spoon has been rusty from disuse.<br>     汤匙因弃置不用而生锈了。<br>'),(2609,'ditch','ditched','ditched','ditching','ditches','n. 沟渠<br>\nv. 坠沟中',' The frog jumped into the ditch.<br>     青蛙跳进了沟里。<br>\n The cart overturned and precipitated us to the ditch.<br>     车子翻了，我们被摔进了沟里。<br>'),(2610,'dither','dithered','dithered','dithering','','n. 抖,发抖,兴奋<br>\nv. 发抖',' Stop dithering about which film you want to see or you\'ll miss them both!<br>     到底看哪一部影片, 别再犹豫了, 不然的话, 两部影片你都要耽误了!<br>'),(2611,'dithering','','','','','抖动',' Stop dithering about which film you want to see or you\'ll miss them both!<br>     到底看哪一部影片, 别再犹豫了, 不然的话, 两部影片你都要耽误了!<br>\n The best thing the Administration and Congress could do for the whole economy,…, is to rein in those deficits. Yet on this vital front, all hands dither.<br>     政府与国会处理整体经济上上之策，……在于控制赤字。然而在此一极端重要层面，大家却不能沉着应付。<br>'),(2612,'ditto','dittoed','dittoed','dittoing','dittos','n. 同上,同上符号,很相似的东西<br>\na. 同样的,前项的<br>\nad. 与前同地',' I shall act ditto.<br>     我将同样办理。<br>'),(2613,'diuretic','','','','','n.&a. 利尿剂',' Coffee is a diuretic.<br>     咖啡是一种利尿剂.<br>'),(2614,'dive','dived','dived','diving','dives','n. 潜水,跳水<br>\nv. 跳水,俯冲',' The eagle dived down on the rabbit.<br>     那只鹰向兔子猛扑下来。<br>\n He dived from the bridge and rescued the drowning child.<br>     他从桥上跳入水中，救起溺水的孩子。<br>'),(2615,'diver','','','','divers','n. 潜水员',' The young diver is working under the water with a diving suit.<br>     潜水员穿着潜水衣正在水下工作。<br>\n Ned used to be a scuba diver and now he\'s gone to the other extreme and taken up hang gliding.<br>     内德过去是一名深水潜水员，现在他已走到另一个极端，开始从事悬挂式滑行运动。<br>'),(2616,'diverge','diverged','diverged','diverging','','v. 分歧',' Our views diverged so greatly that it was impossible to agree.<br>     我们的观点存在着严重的分歧，绝无调和余地。<br>\n The stream diverges here.<br>     小溪在这儿分岔。<br>'),(2617,'divergence','','','','','n. 分歧<br>\nn. 散度（数学用语）',' A point of divergence, especially one of great moment.<br>     转折点分岔点，尤指需要作出重大决择的时刻<br>\n Divergence or disagreement, as between facts or claims; difference.<br>     矛盾，不相符不符合或不一致，如在事实和宣称之间；差异<br>'),(2618,'divergent','','','','','a. 分歧的',' A divergent section of a river, especially near the mouth.<br>     河流分支河流的分岔部分，特别是近河口地区<br>'),(2619,'diverse','','','','','a. 不同的,相异的,多种多样的',' Her interests are very diverse.<br>     她的兴趣非常广泛。<br>\n The program deals with subjects as diverse as pop music and Beijing Opera.<br>     节目涉及从流行音乐到京剧这样形形色色的题材。<br>'),(2620,'diversion','','','','diversions','n. 转向,转移,娱乐活动',' I think your last argument was a diversion to make us forget the main point.<br>     我认为你最后的那个论点是在转移目标，以便我们忘掉要点。<br>\n Chess is his favorite diversion.<br>     象棋是他最喜欢的娱乐活动.<br>'),(2621,'diversity','','','','diversities','n. 差异,多样性<br>\nvt. 使不同,使多样化',' We should get a thorough understanding about the cultural diversity of the United States.<br>     我们应该对美国文化的多样性有一个全面的了解。<br>\n A diversity lead to prosperity.<br>     穷则变，变则通。<br>'),(2622,'divert','diverted','diverted','diverting','','v. 转移',' I found a computer game to divert the children.<br>     我发现了一种供孩子娱乐的电脑游戏。<br>\n They diverted the river to supply water to the town.<br>     他们使河流改道以便向城市供水。<br>'),(2623,'divide','divided','divided','dividing','divides','v. 除,分割,划分,隔开',' She divided the food into four equal shares.<br>     她把食物分成相同的四份。<br>\n Six divided by two is three.<br>     六除以二得三。<br>'),(2624,'dividend','','','','dividends','n. 红利,股息,彩金,被除数',' The company declared a large dividend at the end of the year.<br>     公司在年底宣布分发高额股息。<br>\n An expression to be divided by another; a dividend.<br>     被除数被另一个数除的表达式；被除数<br>'),(2625,'divider','','','','','除法器',''),(2626,'divine','divined','divined','divining','divines','a. 神的,神圣的',' My mother asked me to attend divine service.<br>     我妈妈要求我做礼拜。<br>\n At last I divined the truth.<br>     我终于看穿了事情的真相。<br>'),(2627,'divisibility','','','','','可除性,可约性',''),(2628,'division','','','','divisions','n. 区分,分开,除法,公司,部门，师（军队里）',' The divisions between the various classes of society are not so sharply marked as they used to be.<br>     现在社会上各阶级的区分不象过去那样明显了。<br>\n Is that a fair division of the money?<br>     那样分款公平吗？<br>'),(2629,'divisor','','','','','除数',''),(2630,'divorce','','','','','n. 离婚<br>\nv. 与...办离婚',' She got a divorce after years of unhappiness.<br>     经过多年的不幸之后，她终于离了婚。<br>\n He divorced his wife.<br>     他和他妻子离了婚。<br>'),(2631,'dizziness','','','','','n. 头昏眼花',' A fit of dizziness came over her.<br>     她感到一阵头晕目眩.<br>\n He had a sensation of dizziness.<br>     他有一种晕眩的感觉。<br>'),(2632,'dizzy','dizzied','dizzied','dizzying','','a. 晕眩的',' The room was so hot that she felt dizzy.<br>     房间里热得她头晕目眩。<br>\n We were dizzy by the strong wind.<br>     我们被大风刮得头晕目眩。<br>'),(2633,'DNA','','','','','deoxyribonucleic acid 脱氧核糖核酸',''),(2634,'do','did','done','doing','','aux. 助动词(无词意)<br>\nv. 干,做',' I do miss you.<br>     我真想念你啊！<br>\n The firm did badly last year.<br>     公司去年生意不好。<br>'),(2635,'dock','','','','','n. 码头,船坞<br>\nv. 靠码头,入坞',' They have docked us of two days of our annual leave.<br>     他们已从我们每年的休假里扣除了两天。<br>\n The two modules docked in outer space.<br>     两个飞行舱在外层空