oing?<br>     你知道你在做什么吗？<br>'),(2645,'dole','doled','doled','doling','doles','n. 施舍品,失业救剂金',' After she lost a leg, she went on the dole.<br>     在她失去一条腿后，她开始登记领取救济金。<br>\n I doled out the food to all the children.<br>     我把食品发放给所有的孩子们。<br>'),(2646,'doll','dolled','dolled','dolling','dolls','n. 玩具娃娃<br>\nv. 把...打扮得花技招展',' My daughter has many beautiful dolls.<br>     我女儿有许多漂亮的洋娃娃。<br>\n The child cuddled her doll (to her chest).<br>     那孩子（怀里）抱著玩具娃娃.<br>'),(2647,'dollar','','','','dollars','n. 美元',' Can you lend me five dollars?<br>     你能借给我五美元吗？<br>\n She gave the boys a dollar apiece.<br>     她给孩子们每人一美元。<br>'),(2648,'dolphin','','','','dolphins','n. 海豚',' We like to see the performance of dolphins.<br>     我们喜欢看海豚的表演。<br>\n The dolphin balanced the ball on its nose.<br>     海豚用鼻子顶着球，使其保持平衡。<br>'),(2649,'domain','','','','domains','n. 领域<br>\n[计算机] 域',' The kitchen is my wife\'s domain, she doesn\'t like me going into it.<br>     厨房是我妻子的领地，她不愿让我进去。<br>\n Military history is really outside my domain.<br>     我对军队史实在一窍不通。<br>'),(2650,'dome','domed','domed','doming','domes','n. 圆屋顶',' The dome of St. Paul Cathedral is well known in the world.<br>     圣保罗教堂的圆顶闻名于世。<br>\n Upward pressure from underlying magma domes the surface.<br>     地下岩浆的向上推力使地面成圆顶形。<br>'),(2651,'domestic','','','','domestics','a. 国内的,家庭的,驯养的<br>\nn. 家仆,佣人',' He has had many domestic troubles.<br>     他有许多家庭纠纷。<br>\n The newspaper provides more foreign news than domestic news.<br>     这家报纸刊登的国外消息多于国内消息。<br>'),(2652,'domesticate','domesticated','domesticated','domesticating','','v. 养驯,使安于土地,教化',' He\'s become a lot more domesticated since his marriage.<br>     他婚後已非常恋家了.<br>'),(2653,'dominance','','','','','n. 支配(控制,统治,权威,优势)',' Dominance by location; extent of view.<br>     控制定位控制；观察的范围<br>\n Only humiliations seemed left, but even here George took a long view, foreseeing as he did the eventual dominance of this country.<br>     剩下的似乎只有羞辱，即使如此，乔治仍从长计议，预见他最终要统治这个国家。<br>'),(2654,'dominant','','','','dominants','a. 占优势的',' Peace was the dominant theme of the conference.<br>     和平是大会的首要议题。<br>\n The right hand is dominant in most people.<br>     大多数人的右手是优势手。<br>'),(2655,'dominate','dominated','dominated','dominating','','v. 支配,占优势',' He has authority, but he doesn\'t try to dominate others.<br>     他有权威，但并不想控制别人。<br>\n She dominated the meeting by sheer force of character.<br>     她单凭个人气势就镇住了会场。<br>'),(2656,'donate','donated','donated','donating','','v. 捐赠',' I can donate one hundred dollars at best.<br>     我充其量只能捐助100美元。<br>\n The government calls on the youth to donate their blood voluntarily.<br>     政府号召青年义务献血。<br>'),(2657,'donation','','','','donations','n. 捐赠物,捐款,捐赠',' A wealthy sponsor came to our rescue with a generous donation.<br>     有个富有的赞助人慷慨捐赠来解救我们.<br>\n The donation aggregated to$10,000.<br>     捐款合计达一万美元。<br>'),(2658,'donkey','','','','','a. 驴子<br>\nn. 驴',' He is as stubborn as a donkey.<br>     他像驴子一样倔强。<br>\n The bray of the donkey absorbed us.<br>     驴叫声吸引了我们。<br>'),(2659,'donor','','','','donors','n. 捐赠人<br>\n[计算机] 施主',''),(2660,'doom','doomed','doomed','dooming','','n. 命运,不幸,宣告     判决<br>\nv. 命中注定,宣告',' People sent the criminal to his doom.<br>     人们将这个罪犯处死。<br>\n Everyone is doomed to die.<br>     每个人都是注定要死的。<br>'),(2661,'door','','','','doors','n. 门',' Open the door, please.<br>     请把门打开。<br>\n Diligence is often the door to success.<br>     勤奋常会引向成功。<br>'),(2662,'doors','','','','','门点',' The doors of the palace were made of beaten gold.<br>     宫殿的门由金箔做成。<br>\n It\'s my responsibility to lock the doors.<br>     我负责锁门。<br>'),(2663,'doorway','','','','doorways','n. 门口',' She stood in the doorway, unable to decide whether to go in.<br>     她站在门口，拿不定主意是否进去。<br>\n She had to duck her head to get through the low doorway.<br>     她不得不低下头才能穿过低矮的门口。<br>'),(2664,'dorm','','','','','n. (集体)宿舍',' How come everyone at the dorm talk on the phone so long?<br>     为什么住在宿舍在学生打电话都打那么久？<br>\n A coed dorm; a coed pool.<br>     男女合住的宿舍；男女联营<br>'),(2665,'dormant','','','','','a. 睡眠状态的,静止的<br>\n[计算机] 静止的',' A protective case, covering, or structure, such as a plant bud, in which an organism remains dormant for the winter.<br>     离体条芽一种保护性的外壳、表皮或结构，例如植物的芽，在其内部一个有机体处于冬眠状态<br>\n He would try to awake their dormant and sluggish faculties.<br>     这位教授应该试图唤醒他们沉睡和懒散的天赋。<br>'),(2666,'dormitory','','','','dormitories','n. (集体)宿舍',' A small sleeping compartment, especially within a dormitory.<br>     小卧室小卧室，尤指宿舍内的小卧室<br>\n He hangs out in the school dormitory.<br>     他住在学校的宿舍里。<br>'),(2667,'DOS','','','','','n.[计算机] 磁盘操作系统<br>\nDOS 命令 : 在常规、扩展或保留内存中装入操作系统',' Come on, fair dos you\'ve had a long go on the computer and now it\'s my turn.<br>     行了, 机会均等--你用计算机已经很长时间了, 现在该轮到我了.<br>\n In everyday conversation, you request people to do things, not \"order\" them.<br>     在日常会话中，你是请求别人做事，而不是\"命令\"他们。<br>'),(2668,'dose','dosed','dosed','dosing','doses','n. 剂量,服用量<br>\nv. 配',' In the accident, the workers received a heavy dose of radiation.<br>     在这次事故中，工人受到大剂量的辐射。<br>\n Take one dose of this cough syrup three times a day.<br>     每天服三次这种止咳糖浆，每次服一剂量。<br>'),(2669,'dot','','','','','n. 点,圆点,小孩子,小东西<br>\nv. 作小点记号,加小点于,点缀<br>\n[计算机] 点',' The train arrived on the dot of three o\'clock.<br>     那辆火车三点钟准时到达。<br>\n The lake was dotted with little boats.<br>     湖面上布满了小船。<br>'),(2670,'double','doubled','doubled','doubling','doubles','n. 两倍<br>\na. 两倍的,双重的<br>\nv. 加倍的,快步走,加倍努力',' He is my double, though we are not related.<br>     我们两人虽然没有亲缘关系，他却和我长得一模一样。<br>\n Is the material single width or double width?<br>     这幅料子是单幅的还是双幅的？<br>'),(2671,'doubling','','','','','n. 加倍,双倍',' A fold in cloth made by doubling the material upon itself and then pressing or stitching it into place.<br>     褶皱衣服上的褶，通过将衣服的材料对折叠，然后在衣料上再压紧或缝在一起而制成<br>'),(2672,'doubt','doubted','doubted','doubting','doubts','n. 怀疑,疑惑<br>\nv. 怀疑,不信',' There is no doubt that we will be successful.<br>     毫无疑问我们会成功的。<br>\n I doubt the truth of it.<br>     我怀疑此事的真实程度。<br>'),(2673,'doubtful','','','','','a. 可疑的,疑心的,不确的',' Because of a long drought, the farmers are doubtful about the prospect of a good yield.<br>     因为长时间的干旱，农民们对于好收成的前景是怀疑的。<br>\n It is doubtful whether he can read my fortune or not.<br>     他能否算出我的运气还是个疑问。<br>'),(2674,'doubtless','','','','','a. 无疑的,确定的<br>\nad. 无疑地,确定地',' John will doubtless come early as he always does.<br>     约翰无疑会像平时一样很早就来。<br>\n I shall doubtless see you tomorrow.<br>     我大概明天会见到你。<br>'),(2675,'dough','','','','','n.生面团(揉好的陶土,捏塑体),浆糊',' She is kneading dough.<br>     她正在揉面。<br>\n The way to make dough is very simple as you need only to mix flour with water.<br>     和面的方法很简单，只要把水和在面粉里就行了。<br>'),(2676,'doughnut','','','','doughnuts','n. 油炸圈饼',' No, I\'m going to the snack bar to get a doughnut and some milk.<br>     不，我要到小吃店买一个油炸圈饼和一些牛奶。<br>\n Glaze a doughnut; glaze pottery.<br>     在甜甜圈上浇糖浆；给陶器上釉<br>'),(2677,'dove','','','','','n. 鸽子',' The dove is the symbol of peace.<br>     鸽子是和平的象征。<br>\n The dove is an emblem of peace.<br>     鸽子是和平的象征。<br>'),(2678,'down','','','','','a. 向下的<br>\nad. 向下<br>\nn. 绒毛,汗毛<br>\nprep. 沿着...而下',' The tears ran down her cheeks.<br>     泪水沿着她的面颊流下。<br>\n It gets cold quickly when the sun goes down.<br>     太阳下山后天气很快就会冷下来。<br>'),(2679,'download','','','','','v. 下载',''),(2680,'downpour','','','','downpours','n. 倾盆大雨',' A deep ditch or channel cut in the earth by running water after a prolonged downpour.<br>     隘谷，冲沟长期的倾盆大雨冲击地面之后形成深的沟壑或沟渠<br>\n The rescue work had been going very well until a sudden downpour loused the whole thing up.<br>     营救工作本来一直进行得很顺利，后来突然下了一场倾盆大雨，把整个事情弄得一团糟。<br>'),(2681,'downstairs','','','','','a. 楼下的<br>\nad. 在楼下<br>\nn. 楼下',' She was ill and stayed in the downstairs bedroom for a whole day.<br>     她病了，在楼下的卧室里呆了一整天。<br>\n Is anyone downstairs?<br>     有人在楼下吗？<br>'),(2682,'downstream','','','','','ad. 下游地<br>\na. 下游的',' Downstream the river twists and turns a lot.<br>     这条河的下游弯弯曲曲.<br>\n The logs are drifted downstream to the mill.<br>     那些原木沿河顺水漂到工厂.<br>'),(2683,'downtown','','','','downtowns','n. 市中心区,市中心<br>\na. 市中心的<br>\nad. 往闹区',' We will go downtown tomorrow.<br>     明天我们去市中心。<br>\n The park is only five minutes from downtown.<br>     这个花园离市中心只有五分钟的路程。<br>'),(2684,'downward','','','','','a. 向下的<br>\nad. 向下',' The monkey was hanging head downwards from the branch.<br>     猴子头向下倒挂在树枝上。<br>\n A downward movement; descent.<br>     向下的运动；下降<br>'),(2685,'downwards','','','','','ad. 向下',' The monkey was hanging head downwards from the branch.<br>     猴子头向下倒挂在树枝上。<br>\n He lay face downwards on his bed.<br>     他脸向下伏在床上。<br>'),(2686,'doze','dozed','dozed','dozing','','v. 打瞌睡,假寐',' I had a quick doze on the train.<br>     我在火车上打了一会儿瞌睡。<br>\n He fell into a doze.<br>     他打起盹儿来了。<br>'),(2687,'dozen','','','','dozen','n. (一)打,十二个',' My mother bought a dozen eggs.<br>     我妈妈买了一打鸡蛋。<br>\n I had bred a dozen of chickens.<br>     我饲养了12只小鸡。<br>'),(2688,'draft','drafted','drafted','drafting','drafts','n. 草稿,草图,汇票<br>\nv. 起草,征兵',' He drew a draft of the car.<br>     他画了一张汽车的草图。<br>\n John was drafted into the Army last year.<br>     约翰去年被应征入伍。<br>'),(2689,'drag','dragged','dragged','dragging','drags','n. 拖,拖累<br>\nv. 拖累,拖拉,慢条斯理地走',' The protesters were dragged away by the police.<br>     抗议者被警察拖走了。<br>\n She dragged herself out of bed, still half asleep.<br>     她挣扎著起了床，犹自睡眼惺松。<br>'),(2690,'dragon','','','','dragons','n. 龙',' Dragons are described as monsters in most western countries.<br>     在大多数西方国家，龙被认为是怪物。<br>\n This jade dragon is a genuine antique.<br>     这件玉龙是真正的古玩。<br>'),(2691,'drain','drained','drained','draining','drains','n. 下水道,排水沟,消耗<br>\nv. 耗尽,排出沟外',' This country is being drained of its best talents.<br>     这个国家最优秀的人才在不断外流。<br>\n Boil the vegetables for 20 minutes and then drain off the water.<br>     把蔬菜煮上20分钟，然后把水沥掉。<br>'),(2692,'drainage','','','','','v. 排水<br>\nn. 排水系统,污水',' The drainage system has been aged.<br>     排水系统已经老化了。<br>\n The city was even equipped with a drainage system, for a great many clay pipes were found beneath the narrow streets.<br>     这座城市甚至还敷设过排水系统，因为在窄窄的街道底下发现了许多陶土制的管道。<br>'),(2693,'DRAM','','','','','动态随机访问存储器',' He is very fond of his dram.<br>     他喜欢喝一点酒。<br>\n She has not one dram of learning.<br>     她一点学问也没有。<br>'),(2694,'drama','','','','dramas','n. 剧本,戏剧<br>\n刺激的事情',' I have no interest in drama.<br>     我对戏剧不感兴趣。<br>\n The drama of international politics interested her.<br>     国际政治的戏剧性使她深感兴趣。<br>'),(2695,'dramatic','','','','','a. 戏剧性的,引人注目的,给人深刻印象的<br>\nn. (pl.)戏剧作品,戏曲',' Her opening words were dramatic.<br>     她的开场白十分动听。<br>\n The play is a dramatic representation of a real event.<br>     这出话剧改编出自真人真事。<br>'),(2696,'dramatically','','','','','ad. 戏剧地,引人注目地<br>\n从戏剧角度,显著地',' The story begins dramatically but the plot peters out before the end.<br>     这故事有些虎头蛇尾.<br>\n Accounting and banking have changed dramatically in the light of recent developments in computers.<br>     由于当今电子计算机的飞速发展，会计和银行业发生了急剧的变化。<br>'),(2697,'dramatist','','','','dramatists','n. 剧作家',' The dramatist was respected by people in his country.<br>     这个剧作家受到了本国人民的尊敬。<br>\n With his new play he has consolidated his position as the country\'s leading dramatist.<br>     他有了新创作的剧本, 巩固了他在国内的杰出剧作家的地位.<br>'),(2698,'dramatize','dramatized','dramatized','dramatizing','','v. 使戏剧化<br>\nvt. 把(小说等)改编成戏剧,渲染',' The affair was dramatized by the press.<br>     新闻界把事情夸大了。<br>\n He is dramatizing the story of his life.<br>     他把自己的一生改编成戏剧。<br>'),(2699,'drastic','','','','','a. 激烈的,猛烈的',' Drastic measures will have to be taken to restore order.<br>     为恢复秩序必须采取严厉措施.<br>\n Our budget needs drastic revision.<br>     我们的预算需作重大修改。<br>'),(2700,'draw','drew','drawn','drawing','draws','v. (drew,drawn) 拉,拖,挨近,提取,画,绘制',' That film was a great draw.<br>     那部影片很叫座。<br>\n We have several drawn matches this year.<br>     今年我们打和了几场比赛。<br>'),(2701,'drawable','','','','','可拉的',''),(2702,'drawback','','','','drawbacks','n. 不利点,退税',' Everything has its drawbacks.<br>     凡事都有不足之处。<br>\n The great drawback to living near a main road is noise.<br>     住在大街旁最大的缺点是噪音。<br>'),(2703,'drawer','','','','drawers','n. 抽屉',' He locked his diary in the upper drawer.<br>     他把日记锁在上层抽屉里。<br>\n Line the drawer with paper, please.<br>     请在抽屉里铺上纸。<br>'),(2704,'drawing','','','','drawings','n. 绘图,图画',' You jogged my elbow and spoiled what I was drawing.<br>     你撞到了我的手肘，弄坏了我正在画的图画。<br>\n In computer graphics, the simple function for drawing on the screen. Typical primitives are rectangle, line, polygon, etc.<br>     在计算机图形学中，在荧光屏上绘图的简单程序。典型的图元是长方块、线段、多边形等。<br>'),(2705,'dread','dreaded','dreaded','dreading','dreads','n. 恐惧,可怕的人,可怕的事<br>\na. 可怕的,可怖的<br>\nv. 恐惧,害怕',' The Jews lived in dread of being caught.<br>     这些犹太人生活在会遭到拘捕的恐惧之中。<br>\n I dread to think what will happen if she finds out the truth.<br>     我不敢去想她知道真相后会怎么样。<br>'),(2706,'dreaded','','','','','a. 令人畏惧的',' Something dreaded or despised.<br>     恐惧的事物；讨厌的事物<br>\n The Jews lived in dread of being caught.<br>     这些犹太人生活在会遭到拘捕的恐惧之中。<br>'),(2707,'dreadful','','','','','a. 可怕的',' We are waiting for God\'s dreadful judgement.<br>     我们在等待上帝令人生畏的审判。<br>\n His face pale as ashes, and his lips trembling, he stammered out the dreadful news.<br>     他脸色苍白，嘴唇颤抖，结结巴巴说出了那可怕的消息。<br>'),(2708,'dream','dreamed','dreamed','dreaming','dreams','n. 梦<br>\nv. 做梦',' He thinks she is in love with him, but it\'s only a dream.<br>     他以为她爱上他，但只是梦想而已。<br>\n Their new house is a real dream.<br>     他们的新房子真像梦一般美好。<br>'),(2709,'dreary','','','','','a. 沉闷的',' It is very dreary to do the same job everyday.<br>     每天都做同样工作是很单调的。<br>\n I\'m tired of his dreary speech.<br>     我厌倦了他的枯燥无味的演说。<br>'),(2710,'drench','drenched','drenched','drenching','','v. 湿透',' The poster wouldn\'t stick even though I drenched it with glue.<br>     我涂了大量胶水，可那张海报就是贴不住。<br>\n We were caught in the storm and got drenched.<br>     我们遇上大雨全都被浇透了。<br>'),(2711,'dress','dressed','dressed','dressing','dresses','n. 女装,服装<br>\nv. 穿著',' She always dresses in black.<br>     她总穿着黑衣服。<br>\n She wears a beautiful evening dress.<br>     她穿着一件漂亮的晚礼服。<br>'),(2712,'dressing','','','','dressings','n. 调味品,穿衣',' A nurse came to put on a clean dressing for him.<br>     一位护士来给他包上干净的绷带。<br>\n Dressing is difficult for her since her accident.<br>     在她出了事故以来，穿衣服一直都很费劲。<br>'),(2713,'drift','drifted','drifted','drifting','drifts','n. 漂移,漂流物,观望,漂流,吹积物,趋势<br>\nv. 漂移,漂流,吹积',' The road was edged with snow drifts.<br>     路边上有一个个雪堆。<br>\n A tiny fishing boat was drifting slowly along.<br>     一只小小的渔船在缓缓地漂去。<br>'),(2714,'drill','','','','','n. 钻孔机,钻子,播种机<br>\nv. 训练,钻孔',' The dentist\'s drill made a lot of noise.<br>     牙钻发出很大的噪音。<br>\n The workman is drilling in the wall.<br>     工人正在墙上打孔。<br>'),(2715,'drilling','','','','','n. 演练,钻孔',' A hole or passage made by or as if by use of a drill.<br>     钻孔，打洞用或似用钻打孔或通道<br>\n Valuable deposits of oil have been found by drilling.<br>     通过钻探发现很有开采价值的油层.<br>'),(2716,'drink','drank','drank','drinking','drinks','n. 饮料<br>\nv. 喝,喝酒',' He doesn\'t smoke or drink.<br>     他不抽烟也不喝酒。<br>\n We must drink to the health of the bride.<br>     我们要为新娘的健康干杯。<br>'),(2717,'drip','dripped','dripped','dripping','drips','n. 滴,点滴,乏味的人,水滴<br>\nv. 滴下,漏水',' The rainwater drips from the eaves.<br>     雨水从屋檐滴下。<br>\n Moonlight dripped through the leaves.<br>     月光透过树叶洒下来。<br>'),(2718,'drive','drove','driven','driving','drives','n. 驾车,快车道,推进力,驱使<br>\nv. 开车,驱使,驾进力<br>\n[计算机] 驱动器<br>\nn.路，街',' Don\'t drink and drive.<br>     别喝了酒开车。<br>\n He is clever but he won\'t succeed because he lacks drive.<br>     他聪明是聪明，但是没有干劲，做事不会成功。<br>'),(2719,'driver','','','','drivers','n. 驾驶员,司机',' The bus driver asked the passengers to buy tickets.<br>     公共汽车司机要求乘客买票。<br>\n The driver braked his car suddenly.<br>     司机突然煞车。<br>'),(2720,'driving','','','','','n. 赶,操纵,驾驶<br>\na. 推进的,强劲的,精力旺盛的<br>\nvbl. 骑',' Dangerous driving should be severely punished.<br>     危险驾驶应受严惩。<br>\n The process of driving or propelling.<br>     推进驱使或推进的过程<br>'),(2721,'droop','drooped','drooped','drooping','','v. 下垂,消沉',' The flowers were drooping for want of water.<br>     这些花因缺水而凋萎。<br>\n Her head drooped sadly.<br>     她悲哀地垂着头。<br>'),(2722,'drop','dropped','dropped','dropping','drops','n. 滴,微量,落下<br>\nv. 放下,掉下',' He likes to eat chocolate drops.<br>     他喜欢吃巧克力糖球。<br>\n The fruit dropped down from the tree.<br>     水果从树上掉下来。<br>'),(2723,'droplet','','','','','n. 小滴',''),(2724,'dropout','','','','','n. 中途退出者',' My disease is an asthma and a dropout and, what is less curable, seventy- five.<br>     我的病是气喘和水肿，还有无可救药的是七十五（岁）。<br>'),(2725,'drought','','','','droughts','n. 干旱',' We have not enough food to eat because of the drought.<br>     因为旱灾，我们没有足够的食物可吃。<br>\n The crops failed because of the drought.<br>     干旱造成农作物歉收。<br>'),(2726,'drown','drowned','drowned','drowning','','v. 淹死',' The band drowned our conversation.<br>     乐队的演奏声把我们谈话的声音淹没了。<br>\n The little girl drowned in the river.<br>     小女孩在河里淹死了。<br>'),(2727,'drowse','drowsed','drowsed','drowsing','','v.&n. 瞌睡',' Oh, no! Looks like they catch me drowse.<br>     喔，糟了。他们好像发觉我在打瞌睡。<br>'),(2728,'drudgery','','','','','n. 苦差事,苦工',' Washing machines take the drudgery out of laundry.<br>     洗衣机把洗衣工作带出了洗衣房。<br>\n Labor-saving devices have emancipated women from kitchen drudgery.<br>     许多节省劳力的设备于妇女摆脱掉乏味的厨房杂役。<br>'),(2729,'drug','drugged','drugged','drugging','drugs','n. 药,麻药<br>\nv. 下药',' The man formed a habit of taking harmful drugs.<br>     这人养成了服用有害麻醉品的习惯。<br>\n The drug is wanted bitterly.<br>     这药有人急着要用。<br>'),(2730,'drugstore','','','','drugstores','n. 药房,杂货店',' A place where drugs are sold; a drugstore.<br>     药房，药店出售药品的地方；药店<br>\n Raymond: Yes, I just picked up some drug at the corner drugstore.<br>     雷蒙：有，我刚刚在街角的药房买了一些药品，<br>'),(2731,'drum','drummed','drummed','drumming','drums','n. 鼓,鼓声<br>\nv. 击鼓,作鼓声',' He drummed on the table with his fingers.<br>     他用手指咚咚地敲打着桌子。<br>\n She drummed it into the children that they must not cross the road alone.<br>     她反复地给孩子们说，他们不可以独自横过马路。<br>'),(2732,'drunk','','','','','a. 喝醉了的<br>\nvbl. 喝,喝酒',' He is slightly drunk.<br>     他有些醉了。<br>\n Several drunks lay on the floor.<br>     好几个醉汉躺在地板上。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (2733,'drunkard','','','','drunkards','n. 酒鬼',' She divorced with her husband because she found him a drunkard.<br>     她和丈夫离婚了，因为她发现他是个酒鬼。<br>\n A drunkard is like a whisky bottle, all neck and belly and no head.<br>     酒鬼好比威士忌瓶，全是脖子跟肚子而没脑子。<br>'),(2734,'dry','dried','dried','drying','','a. 干的,枯燥无味的<br>\nv. 把...弄干,干掉',' The book is as dry as dust.<br>     这本书枯燥无味。<br>\n The soil is too dry for planting.<br>     土太干了，不能种东西。<br>'),(2735,'dryer','','','','dryers','n. 干衣机,干燥剂',' She put her clothes in the dryer, so she could wear them this afternoon.<br>     她把衣服放在干衣机里，这样她下午就能穿这些衣服了。<br>\n He bought an electric hair-dryer for Mary.<br>     他给玛丽买了一个电吹风。<br>'),(2736,'dual','','','','duals','a. 双重的',' She has dual nationality.<br>     她有双重国籍。<br>\n His dual role as a composer and a conductor made him very busy.<br>     他作曲家和指挥家的双重身份使他非常繁忙。<br>'),(2737,'dub','','','','','v. 配音,轻点',' The papers dubbed them The Fab Four\'.<br>     报刊给他们起了个绰号叫｀四绝＇.<br>\n Is the film dubbed or does it have subtitles?<br>     这部影片是经过配音的还是配上字幕的？<br>'),(2738,'dubious','','','','','a. 怀疑的,可疑的',' I feel dubious about what to do next.<br>     我不知道下一步该怎么办。<br>\n I feel dubious about his honesty.<br>     我对他的诚实表示怀疑。<br>'),(2739,'duck','','','','','n. 鸭子<br>\nv. 没入水中,闪避',' She had to duck her head to get through the low doorway.<br>     她不得不低下头才能穿过低矮的门口。<br>\n The children ducked each other in the swimming pool.<br>     孩子们在游泳池里互相把对方按入水中。<br>'),(2740,'due','','','','dues','n. 应得物<br>\na. 预定的,应付的,到期的,应有的',' Her baby is due next week.<br>     她的宝宝预计在下个月出世。<br>\n His success is entirely due to hard work.<br>     他的成功完全是努力工作的结果。<br>'),(2741,'duke','','','','dukes','n. 公爵',' The duke ordered the servant to send a letter to the king.<br>     公爵命令仆人把一封信送给国王。<br>\n The duke wrote a letter with a quill pen.<br>     公爵用一根羽毛笔写信。<br>'),(2742,'dull','dulled','dulled','dulling','','a. 钝的,迟钝的,无趣的<br>\n[计算机] 暗淡的',' This book is rather dull.<br>     这本书很枯燥。<br>\n It\'s impossible to cut a pineapple with such a dull knife.<br>     用一把这么钝的刀子切菠萝是不可能的。<br>'),(2743,'duly','','','','','ad. 的确,当然地,适当地',' Your suggestion has been duly noted.<br>     你的建议已受到注意。<br>\n The carriage that he had ordered duly arrived, and we drove off.<br>     他叫的马车按时到，我们就坐上去走了。<br>'),(2744,'dumb','','','','','a. 无言的,哑的',' We were struck dumb with horror and grief.<br>     惊恐和忧伤使我们哑口无言。<br>\n The man is as dumb as an oyster.<br>     那人极少说话。<br>'),(2745,'dummy','dummied','dummied','dummying','dummies','n. 傀儡,假人,哑巴<br>\na. 虚拟<br>\n[计算机] 伪的',' A crude figure or dummy representing a hated person or group.<br>     雕像代表可憎的人或一群人的粗糙的图象或木偶<br>\n A life-size full or partial representation of the human body, used for the fitting or displaying of clothes; a dummy.<br>     人体模型如真人大小的、全身或半身的人体模型，用于量试衣服是否合适或展示服装；人体模型<br>'),(2746,'dump','','','','','n. 垃圾场<br>\nv. 倾卸,切断电源,倾倒',' Just dump everything over there.<br>     先把东西堆在那边。<br>\n Some people just dump their rubbish in the river.<br>     有些人径直往河里倒垃圾。<br>'),(2747,'dumping','','','','','n. 倾销',' A fine for dumping trash on public land; dumped the extra gear overboard.<br>     因在公用土地上倾倒垃圾而受的罚款；把多余的装备丢到船外<br>\n An instance or the result of dumping stored data.<br>     转出，转储转出内存数据的例子或结果<br>'),(2748,'dung','dunged','dunged','dunging','','n. 粪(粘结物)<br>\nvt 上粪',' Animal dung may be used as manure.<br>     动物的粪便可以作为肥料使用。<br>\n He dunged his vegetable garden regularly.<br>     他经常给他的菜园施肥。<br>'),(2749,'dungeon','dungeoned','dungeoned','dungeoning','dungeons','n. 地牢,土牢',' The poor peasant was thrown into a dungeon.<br>     那个可怜的农民被投进了地牢。<br>\n In the first act the curtain goes up on a dungeon in a landlord\'s house.<br>     第一幕启幕时，舞台上现出了地主家里的一个地牢。<br>'),(2750,'duodecimal','','','','','十二进位,十二进制的',''),(2751,'duodenum','','','','duodenums','n. 十二指肠',''),(2752,'dupe','','','','','n. 受骗的人,上当者<br>\nvt. 欺骗,愚弄',' One who is easily swindled; a dupe.<br>     傻瓜容易上当受骗的人；易被愚弄的人<br>\n A fool or dupe.<br>     蠢人，容易受骗的人<br>'),(2753,'duplex','','','','','[计算机] 双方的',''),(2754,'duplicate','','','','','n. 副本,复本,复制品<br>\na. 复制的,二重的<br>\nv. 复制<br>\n[计算机] 复制',' This research merely duplicates work already done elsewhere.<br>     这项研究仅仅是重复别人已经做过的工作。<br>\n He gave me a duplicate key of his house.<br>     他给了我另配了一套他房子的钥匙。<br>'),(2755,'duplication','','','','','n. 副本,复制',' We must avoid wasteful duplication of effort.<br>     我们必须避免无谓的重复劳动.<br>\n A copy made by this method of duplication.<br>     油印品通过这种方法印制的印刷品<br>'),(2756,'duplicator','','','','','复印机',' In a duplicator, a tank that may or may not be an integral part of the machine, providing a reservoir of fluid for the damping system.<br>     复印机中的一个箱体，它可以是也可以不是复印机整体的组成部分，作为减震系统的液体容器。<br>'),(2757,'durability','','','','','n. 持久性(耐久性,耐用年限,寿命)',' Durability is one yardstick of quality.<br>     耐久性是质量好坏的一个尺度.<br>\n One, such as a person or corporation, that makes or gives a promise, assurance, or pledge typically relating to quality, durability, or performance.<br>     保证人一个人或一个公司，对与质量、耐用性或性能相关的方面提供担保、保证或誓约<br>'),(2758,'durable','','','','durables','a. 耐久的<br>\nn. 耐用品',' This pair of shoes is durable.<br>     这双鞋很耐磨。<br>\n The durable, aromatic wood of any of these plants, especially that of the red cedar, often used to make chests.<br>     雪松木这些植物的耐久的、带香味的木材，尤指红雪松的木材，常用于制作箱子<br>'),(2759,'duration','','','','','n. 持续,持久',' He finished the work of three years\' duration.<br>     他用三年的时间完成了这项工作。<br>\n Well, I\'m stuck here for the duration.<br>     哎，这段时间我只得呆在这儿了。<br>'),(2760,'during','','','','','prep. 在...期间',' He swims every day during the summer.<br>     他夏天每天游泳。<br>\n The thief broke into the house during the night.<br>     小偷在夜间破门进入住宅。<br>'),(2761,'dusk','dusked','dusked','dusking','','n. 黄昏',' He usually goes out for a walk at dusk.<br>     他通常在黄昏时出去散步。<br>\n The lights go on at dusk.<br>     一到黄昏灯就亮了。<br>'),(2762,'dust','dusted','dusted','dusting','','n. 灰尘,尘埃<br>\nv. 拂去灰尘',' The car raised quite a dust as we drove off.<br>     我们走时车子扬起了一阵尘土。<br>\n Please dust all the books on the bottom shelf.<br>     请把底层书架上的书都掸一掸。<br>'),(2763,'dustbin','','','','','n. 垃圾箱',' Please put all your sweet wrappers in the dustbin.<br>     请把你们的糖纸都放进垃圾箱里去。<br>\n The dustbin is chock-full (of rubbish).<br>     垃圾箱塞满了（垃圾）.<br>'),(2764,'dusty','','','','','a. 满是灰尘的',' The dusty road made the travelers dusty too.<br>     满是尘土的路弄得行人也满面尘土了。<br>\n My eye alighted on a dusty old book at the back of the shelf.<br>     我偶然发现在书架後面有一本满是灰尘的旧书.<br>'),(2765,'Dutch','','','','','a. 荷兰的<br>\nn. 荷兰人',' Do Dutch people really go Dutch at a restaurant?<br>     荷兰人在饭馆吃饭时真的各自付帐吗？<br>\n The Dutch settled in South Africa.<br>     荷兰人在南非殖民.<br>'),(2766,'duties','','','','','n. 关税',' Heavy duties on imports and exports are a barrier to international trade.<br>     进出口的高关税是国际贸易的障碍。<br>\n The imposition of heavy emergency custom duties have render our position exceedingly difficult.<br>     由于海关征收繁重的紧急关税，使得我们处于极其困难的境地。<br>'),(2767,'duty','','','','duties','n. 责任,职责',' It\'s my duty to help you.<br>     帮你忙是我份内该做的事。<br>\n I\'m duty bound to visit my old aunt.<br>     我有义务去探望年老的姑妈。<br>'),(2768,'dwarf','dwarfed','dwarfed','dwarfing','dwarves','n. 矮子,侏儒',' The kind dwarf asked the little princess to have dinner with him.<br>     善良的小矮人邀请小公主和他一起吃晚饭。<br>\n There is a dwarf apple tree in our garden.<br>     在我们的花园里有一棵矮苹果树。<br>'),(2769,'dwell','dwelt','dwelt','dwelling','','v. 居住; 细说;',' He decided to dwell on our island.<br>     他决定到我们的岛上居住。<br>\n Stop dwelling on your problems and do something about them!<br>     别老唠叨你的那些问题，还是做些实际工作解决它们吧！<br>'),(2770,'dweller','','','','dwellers','n. 居民',' Dwellers here live a happy life now.<br>     现在这里居民的生活很幸福。<br>\n The noise of traffic is a constant irritant to city dwellers.<br>     车辆的噪音对城市居民是永无止境的骚扰.<br>'),(2771,'dwelling','','','','dwellings','n. 住处',' He changed his dwelling recently.<br>     他最近搬了家。<br>\n A structure serving as a dwelling for one or more persons, especially for a family.<br>     房屋作为一个人或多个人，特别是作为一家人的住处的建筑物<br>'),(2772,'dwindle','dwindled','dwindled','dwindling','','v. 减少,缩小',' My money had dwindled away.<br>     我的钱渐渐花光了。<br>\n Drought has dwindled the crops.<br>     干旱使农作物歉收。<br>'),(2773,'dye','dyed','dyed','dyeing','dyes','n. 染料,染色<br>\nv. 染,染色',' A good dye will not fade.<br>     染得好的颜色不会褪色。<br>\n The wounded soldier\'s blood dyed the ground red.<br>     受伤士兵的血染红了地面.<br>'),(2774,'dying','','','','','a. 垂死的,临终的<br>\nn. 死,死亡',' The little girl cried when she saw her dying cat.<br>     看到快死的小猫，小女孩哭了。<br>\n The dying were rushed to the hospital.<br>     垂死的人被急速送往医院。<br>'),(2775,'dynamic','','','','','a. 动态的,有动力的,有力的',' We are looking for dynamic persons to be salesmen.<br>     我们正在寻找充满活力的销售人员。<br>\n He has a dynamic personality.<br>     他是个性活跃的人。<br>'),(2776,'dynamical','','','','','a. 动力的,电动的,有生气的',''),(2777,'dynasty','','','','dynasties','n. 朝代,王朝',' How many dynasties are there in China\'s history?<br>     中国历史上有多少个朝代？<br>\n The Qing Dynasty ended in 1911.<br>     清朝结束于1911年。<br>'),(2778,'dyne','','','','','n. 达因(力的单位)',''),(2779,'dyspepsia','','','','','n. 消化不良',' Many people think they have religion when they are merely troubled with dyspepsia.<br>     许多人，当他们只是在患消化不良之时，却以为自己有了宗教信仰。<br>'),(2780,'each','','','','','a. 每个,每,每一<br>\nad. 每个<br>\nint. 每个,个人,个自',' Each man has his own name.<br>     每个人都有自己的名字.<br>\n We each have our private views about it.<br>     我们每个人对这件事都有自己的看法。<br>'),(2781,'eager','','','','','a. 渴望的,热切的',' He is eager for you to meet his friends.<br>     他热切希望你见见他的朋友。<br>\n The company is eager to expand into new markets.<br>     那家公司急欲开辟新的市场。<br>'),(2782,'eagerness','','','','','n. 热心',' She has a strong eagerness for success.<br>     她热切地渴望成功。<br>\n Her eagerness moved all the people.<br>     她的热心感动了所有的人。<br>'),(2783,'eagle','','','','eagles','n. 鹰',' The eagle is his favorite bird.<br>     鹰是他最喜欢的鸟类。<br>\n The eagle dived down on the rabbit.<br>     那只鹰向兔子猛扑下来。<br>'),(2784,'ear','','','','ears','n. 耳朵',' Don\'t shout into my ears like that, I can hear you perfectly well.<br>     别那样对我大声嚷嚷，我能听清楚。<br>\n The corn will soon ear.<br>     玉米不久就要结穗了。<br>'),(2785,'earl','','','','earls','n. 伯爵',' The earl lives in a castle.<br>     伯爵住在一座古堡里。<br>\n The young earl didn\'t allow the poor people to enter his earldom.<br>     那个年青的伯爵不允许这些穷人进入他的领地。<br>'),(2786,'early','','','','','ad.&a. 早',' It\'s too early for getting up.<br>     现在起床还太早。<br>\n We shall find out the truth early or late.<br>     我们迟早会查明事实真相。<br>'),(2787,'earmark','earmarked','earmarked','earmarking','','n. 耳上记号,特徵,记号<br>\nv. 在耳朵做记号,弄上记号,充作',''),(2788,'earn','earned','earned','earning','','v. 赚得,获得,博得',' His skill in negotiating earned him a reputation as a shrewd tactician.<br>     他的谈判技巧使他赢得了精明战略家的名声。<br>\n How does she earn her living?<br>     她靠什么谋生？<br>'),(2789,'earnest','','','','','n. 定金,诚挚,认真<br>\na. 认真的,热心的,重要的',' I\'m sure he was earnest when he said he would come.<br>     我相信他说他会来是认真的。<br>\n The current economic slump is an earnest of the major recession to come.<br>     当前的经济滑坡预示着一次大的衰退即将来临。<br>'),(2790,'earnings','','','','earnings','n. 所得,收入',' I\'ve spent all my earnings.<br>     我把赚的钱都花光了。<br>\n He has spent all his earnings.<br>     他把所有的工资都花光了。<br>'),(2791,'earphone','','','','','n. 耳机',''),(2792,'earth','earthed','earthed','earthing','earths','n. 地球',' The earth in the garden is good, soft soil.<br>     花园里的泥土松软肥沃。<br>\n The moon goes round the earth.<br>     月亮绕着地球转。<br>'),(2793,'earthenware','','','','','n. 陶器',' His grandfather gave her an earthenware bowl.<br>     他的祖父给了她一个陶碗。<br>\n Earthenware has an advantage over wood in being more easily kept clean.<br>     陶器的优点在于比木器更容易保持清洁。<br>'),(2794,'earthly','','','','','a. 地球的,俗世的,可能的',' You haven\'t an earthly chance.<br>     你根本没有机会。<br>\n No earthly sovereign can do what he pleases.<br>     没有一个世间君王可以为所欲为。<br>'),(2795,'earthquake','','','','earthquakes','n. 地震',' The San Francisco earthquake was one of the worst catastrophes of the century.<br>     旧金山地震是世纪性的灾难之一。<br>\n The city was razed by an earthquake.<br>     地震把这个城市夷为平地。<br>'),(2796,'ease','eased','eased','easing','','n. 安乐,安逸,悠闲<br>\nv. 使...安乐,使...安心,减轻,放松',' I don\'t feel at ease in the strange place.<br>     在这个陌生的地方，我觉得很不自在。<br>\n My parents are retired and now live a life of ease.<br>     我的父母都退休了，现在过着安闲舒适的生活。<br>'),(2797,'easily','','','','','a. 容易地,不费力地<br>\nad. 容易地',' She is easily the best lawyer in the city.<br>     她无疑是本市最好的律师。<br>\n I can easily finish this work today.<br>     我今天可以很轻易地把这份工作做完。<br>'),(2798,'east','','','','','a. 东方的<br>\nad. 向东方<br>\nn. 东,东方',' The sun rises in the east and sets in the west.<br>     太阳从东方升起，在西方落下。<br>\n Take the east road; it\'s the shortest way.<br>     走东边这条路吧，这是最近的路。<br>'),(2799,'Easter','','','','','n. 复活节',' Each of my cousins received an Easter egg on Easter Day.<br>     我的表兄弟们每人在复活节都得到了一枚复活节彩蛋。<br>\n With the coming of Easter, winter ends and spring comes.<br>     随着复活节的来临，冬天结束而春天来了。<br>'),(2800,'eastern','','','','easterns','a. 东部的,东方的',' China is an eastern country.<br>     中国是一个东方国家。<br>\n The mountain was sharply defined against the eastern sky.<br>     那座山在东方天空的衬托下显得轮廓分明.<br>'),(2801,'eastward','','','','','a. 向东的<br>\nad. 向东',' He walked eastward.<br>     他向东走去。<br>\n The hospital is on the eastward slope of the hill.<br>     医院在小山的东坡。<br>'),(2802,'eastwards','','','','','ad.&a. 向东方(的),朝东(的)<br>\nn. 向东的方向',' The hospital is on the eastward slope of the hill.<br>     医院在小山的东坡。<br>\n The ship is working eastwards.<br>     轮船在向东行驶。<br>'),(2803,'easy','','','','','a. 容易的,安逸的,不费力的',' We talk about reducing our costs, but it\'s easier said than done.<br>     我们谈如何降低成本，但说起来容易，做起来就难了。<br>\n He has stopped working and leads a very easy life.<br>     他现在不做事了，过着很舒服的日子。<br>'),(2804,'eat','ate','eaten','eating','','v. 吃',' The Chinese eat with chopsticks.<br>     中国人用筷子吃饭。<br>\n Since he left, she\'s been sitting at home eating her heart out.<br>     他走了以後，她一直坐在家里，心如刀割。<br>'),(2805,'ebb','ebbed','ebbed','ebbing','','n. 退潮,衰退<br>\nv. 潮退,衰退',' Painting was then at its lowest ebb.<br>     那时绘画艺术非常不景气。<br>\n A crab was left stranded on the beach when the tide ebbed.<br>     退潮时，一只蟹被困留在沙滩上。<br>'),(2806,'eccentric','','','','eccentrics','n. 怪人<br>\na. 古怪的,反常的',' The club seemed full of eccentrics.<br>     这个俱乐部里好象都是怪人。<br>\n She is an eccentric old lady.<br>     她是个古怪的老太太。<br>'),(2807,'eccentricity','','','','eccentricities','n. 古怪,古怪的行为,怪癖',' One of his eccentricities is sleeping under the bed instead of on it.<br>     他的怪僻之一是睡觉睡在床底下而不睡在床上.<br>\n His eccentricity had become legendary long before he died.<br>     在他去世之前他的古怪脾气就早已闻名遐尔了。<br>'),(2808,'echo','echoed','echoed','echoing','echoes','n. 回声,回音,回波<br>\nv. 发回声,随声附和,摹仿<br>\nn.[计算机] DOS命令 :禁止(或允许)批处理命令行显示屏幕上',' His voice echoed in the big empty hall.<br>     他的声音在空荡的大厅里发出回声。<br>\n The room echoed with their happy laughter.<br>     房间里回荡着他们的欢笑声。<br>'),(2809,'eclipse','eclipsed','eclipsed','eclipsing','eclipses','n. 日蚀,月蚀,衰落<br>\nv. 引起日蚀,引起月蚀,使...黯然失色',' Our happiness was soon eclipsed by the terrible news.<br>     我们的快乐没多久就被可怕的消息蒙上了一层阴影。<br>\n It was reported that there would be an annular eclipse tomorrow.<br>     据报道说，明天有日环食。<br>'),(2810,'ecological','','','','','a. 生态的,生态学的',' The destruction of these big forests could have serious ecological consequences.<br>     这些大森林的毁坏会带来生态上的严重后果。<br>\n The function or position of an organism or a population within an ecological community.<br>     功能，位置有机体或其数量在生态环境中的作用或地位<br>'),(2811,'ecology','','','','','n. 生态学',' He started to study ecology and decided to devote his whole life to the science.<br>     他开始研究生态学，并决心将他的一生献身于这门科学。<br>\n Holistic medicine; holistic ecology.<br>     全身治疗的药物；注重整体的生态学<br>'),(2812,'economic','','','','','a. 经济的,经济学的<br>\nn. [-s]经济学(状况等)',' Do you know the economic policy of this year?<br>     你知道今年的经济政策吗？<br>\n The economic sanctions could not prevent the development of that country.<br>     经济制裁不能阻碍那个国家的发展。<br>'),(2813,'economical','','','','','a. 节俭的,经济的,合算的',' She is economical in her use of salt when cooking.<br>     她烹饪时用盐很少。<br>\n This is not an economical method of heating.<br>     这不是一种经济的取暖方式。<br>'),(2814,'economically','','','','','ad. 经济地',' Economically, the country is in a very healthy state.<br>     从经济学的观点来说，国家处于很兴旺的状态之中。<br>\n I dress very economically because I make all my clothes myself.<br>     我衣着节俭，衣服都是自己做的。<br>'),(2815,'economics','','','','economics','n. 经济学',' A manager has to learn some economics if he wants to improve his management.<br>     一个管理人员要想改善管理的话，就必须学点经济学。<br>\n When they start talking about economics, I\'m out of my depth.<br>     他们一谈起经济学, 我就一窍不通了.<br>'),(2816,'economize','economized','economized','economizing','','v. 节约,节省,有效地利用',' Our electricity bills are higher than we can afford we must start to economize.<br>     我们的电费已经高得付不起了--得节省些了.<br>\n The need to economize scarce energy resources.<br>     节约使用稀有能源的必要性<br>'),(2817,'economy','','','','economies','n. 节约,经济',' We are trying to make a few economies.<br>     我们正想办法节省一些。<br>\n Most of the countries in the region have unstable economies.<br>     这个地区大多数国家的经济都不稳定。<br>'),(2818,'ecosystem','','','','','n. 生态系统',' An organism, often a bacterium or fungus, that feeds on and breaks down dead plant or animal matter, thus making organic nutrients available to the ecosystem.<br>     腐生菌；腐生物一种有机物，通常是细菌以死的动植物为食并把它们分解，藉此为生态系统提供有机养分<br>'),(2819,'ecstasy','','','','ecstasies','n. 狂喜',' We were in ecstasy at the thought of going home.<br>     一想到回家，我们就兴奋不已。<br>\n He listened to the music with ecstasy.<br>     他听音乐听得入神。<br>'),(2820,'eddy','eddied','eddied','eddying','eddies','n. 逆流,漩涡<br>\nv. 起漩涡',' The mist eddied round the old castle.<br>     薄雾在那座古老的城堡的周围打转转。<br>\n The little paper boat was caught in an eddy and spun round and round in the water.<br>     小纸船卷进了漩涡中，在水中直打转。<br>'),(2821,'edge','edged','edged','edging','edges','n. 边,边缘,优势<br>\nv. 侧身移动,挤进',' Please sharpen the edge of this axe.<br>     请把这把斧头的刃磨快。<br>\n She lost a handkerchief edged with blue.<br>     她丢了一块镶蓝边的手绢。<br>'),(2822,'edible','','','','edibles','n. 食品,食物<br>\na. 可食用的',' These are edible wild berries.<br>     这些野莓可以食用。<br>\n This food is scarcely edible.<br>     这种食物真是难以下咽。<br>'),(2823,'edit','edited','edited','editing','','v. 编辑,编校,修订',' He edit a daily paper before he come to teach at our college.<br>     他来我们学院任教之前充任过一份日报的主编。<br>\n In word processing, the ability to define information so as to move it from one point to another within a text element or into another text element, or to edit it.<br>     在字（词）处理技术中，定义信息的一种能力，以便将该信息从正文部分的一点移到另一点或移入另一个正文部分中或进行编辑。<br>'),(2824,'editing','','','','','a. 编辑的',' He spent his last years (in) teaching and editing earlier writings.<br>     他把晚年用在教书和编纂以前的著作。<br>\n The editing of the manuscript is now in hand.<br>     这部手稿的编辑工作现在已经开始。<br>'),(2825,'edition','','','','editions','n. 版,版本',' The edition is limited to 500 copies.<br>     该版限出500本。<br>\n She is an improved edition of her mother.<br>     她长得像她母亲但胜过她母亲。<br>'),(2826,'editor','','','','editors','n. 编辑,编者',' The editor often gives some opinion on topical issues.<br>     这个编辑常对一些时事问题发表意见。<br>\n The editor remarked that article was well written.<br>     编者评论说那篇文章写得很好。<br>'),(2827,'editorial','','','','editorials','n. 社论<br>\na. 编辑的',' I have made a lot of editorial changes in their book.<br>     我在他们的书上做了许多编辑上的修改。<br>\n I work in an editorial office.<br>     我在编辑部工作。<br>'),(2828,'educate','educated','educated','educating','','v. 教育,培养<br>\nvt. 教育',' He had paid out good money to educate his daughter at a boarding school.<br>     他花了很多钱让他的女儿在寄宿学校受教育。<br>\n It is not the way to educate a child by making him do things against his will.<br>     勉强他做事不是教育孩子的办法。<br>'),(2829,'educated','','','','','a. 受过教育的,有教养的',' Educated people considered as a group; the literati.<br>     文人，学者被作为一个群体看待的受过教育的人；文人<br>\n Educated; polished; refined.<br>     有教养的；文雅的；精炼的<br>'),(2830,'education','','','','educations','n. 教育,培养',' No country can afford to neglect education.<br>     任何国家都不容忽视教育。<br>\n He was handicapped by lack of education.<br>     他因文化水平低而吃了亏。<br>'),(2831,'educational','','','','','a. 教育的',' It was the most educational experience I had ever had.<br>     这是我有过的教育意义最大的一次经历。<br>\n National wealth depends to a high degree on a country\'s educational standard.<br>     国民财富在很大程度上取决于一个国家的教育水准。<br>'),(2832,'educator','','','','','n. 教育家',' That educator published many articles in these magazines.<br>     那位教育工作者在这些杂志上发表了许多文章。<br>\n Canadian-born American sports educator who originated the game of basketball(1891).<br>     奈史密斯，詹姆斯1861－1939加拿大裔美国体育教育家，他创造了篮球运动（1891年）<br>'),(2833,'EEG','','','','','脑(动)电图描记器[缩]',''),(2834,'eel','','','','eels','n. 鳗鱼,鳝鱼',' Eels are long and difficult to catch.<br>     鳝鱼很长而且很难抓住。<br>\n The taste of eel is delicious.<br>     鳝鱼的味道很好。<br>'),(2835,'effect','effected','effected','effecting','effects','n. 结果,影响,效果<br>\nv. 招致,引起,完成',' A new system of taxation will be brought into effect next year.<br>     新的税收制度将于明年实行。<br>\n The advertising campaign didn\'t have much effect on sales.<br>     这些广告攻势对销售额并没有起到多大作用。<br>'),(2836,'effective','','','','effectives','a. 有效的,有影响的',' When does the new system become effective?<br>     新制度何时生效？<br>\n That\'s rather an effective use of color.<br>     这种使用颜色的手法效果相当好。<br>'),(2837,'effectively','','','','','ad. 有效地',' Effectively, their response was a refusal.<br>     实际上，他们的答复是拒绝。<br>\n Chances of a settlement were effectively wrecked by his speech.<br>     和解的机会事实上被他的演讲破坏了。<br>'),(2838,'effectiveness','','','','','n. 效力',' Equal in force, power, effectiveness, or significance.<br>     相等的力量、能力、效力、或重要性等相等<br>\n Lacking vigor, force, or effectiveness; inadequate.<br>     缺乏活力、力量或效力的；不充足的<br>'),(2839,'efficacious','','','','','a. 有效的,灵验的',''),(2840,'efficacy','','','','','n. 功效,效力,（疗法、药物的）疗效',' The efficacy of the medicine is satisfactory.<br>     这药的药效令人满意。<br>\n We are testing the efficacy of a new drug.<br>     我们正在测试新药的功效。<br>'),(2841,'efficiency','','','','','a. 有效的,生效的<br>\nn. 效率',' We must improve our efficiency as soon as possible.<br>     我们必须尽快地提高工作效率。<br>\n Their labor efficiency is very high.<br>     他们的工作效率很高。<br>'),(2842,'efficient','','','','','a. 效率高的,有能力的',' He\'s efficient at his job.<br>     他胜任工作。<br>\n This is a highly efficient new heating system.<br>     这是个高效的新取暖系统。<br>'),(2843,'efficiently','','','','','ad. 有效地',' It is hard to work efficiently in such a confined space.<br>     在这样狭小的空间里工作很难提高效率。<br>\n Washing powders containing enzymes are said to remove stains more efficiently.<br>     据说含有人造酶的洗衣粉去污力强.<br>'),(2844,'effort','','','','efforts','n. 努力,努力的成果',' Despite all our efforts we still lost the game.<br>     尽管我们尽了全力，我们还是输掉了比赛。<br>\n It\'s quite an effort to lift this heavy box.<br>     抬起这只沉重的箱子要花费相当大的力气。<br>'),(2845,'egg','','','','','n. 蛋;(俚语)人',' This hen lays beautiful brown eggs.<br>     这只母鸡下很漂亮的棕色蛋。<br>\n Do you want a boiled egg for breakfast?<br>     你早饭要吃煮鸡蛋吗？<br>'),(2846,'eggplant','','','','','n. 茄子',''),(2847,'ego','','','','egos','n. 自我',' He\'s my alter ego, we go everywhere together.<br>     他是我的知己--彼此形影不离.<br>\n Holding the view that the ego is the center, object, and norm of all experience.<br>     自我中心的认为自我是所有的中心、对象和经验的标准的<br>'),(2848,'Egypt','','','','','n. 埃及',' These travelers came from Egypt.<br>     这些游客来自埃及。<br>\n Many Pharaohs in ancient Egypt believe they can live forever.<br>     古埃及的许多法老相信他们可以永生。<br>'),(2849,'Egyptian','','','','','a. 埃及的<br>\nn. 埃及人',' The ancient Egyptians had advanced civilization.<br>     古埃及人曾经拥有高度文明。<br>\n There are many mysterious stories about the Egyptian pyramids.<br>     关于埃及金字塔有许多神秘的故事。<br>'),(2850,'eigenvalue','','','','','特征值',''),(2851,'eight','','','','eights','num. 八<br>\npron. 八(个,只...)',' There are eight students in the classroom.<br>     教室里有八个学生。<br>\n I am sorry, you can only buy traveler\'s check at Window Eight.<br>     对不起, 你只能在八号窗口买旅行支票。<br>'),(2852,'eighteen','','','','eighteens','num. 十八',' My daughter is eighteen years old and has grown into a beautiful lady.<br>     我的女儿十八岁了，已经长成为美丽的淑女。<br>\n She dolled herself up as though she was a girl of eighteen.<br>     她打扮得花枝招展,好像是个十八岁的姑娘似的。<br>'),(2853,'eighth','','','','eighths','n. 八分之一<br>\nnum. 第八',' August is the eighth month in a year.<br>     八月是一年中的第八个月。<br>\n One eighth of a circle.<br>     八分圆圆的八分之一<br>'),(2854,'eighty','','','','eighties','num.&a. 八十<br>\npron. 八十(个,只...)',' There are eighty pages in this book.<br>     这本书有八十页。<br>\n Although he\'s over eighty his mind is still remarkably alert.<br>     他虽已年过八十，但头脑仍然十分机敏。<br>'),(2855,'either','','','','','a. 任一,两方的<br>\nprep. 任一,随便任一个<br>\nconj. 或,也',' If you do not go, I shall not go either.<br>     你不去，我也不去。<br>\n You may take either of the roads.<br>     两条路你随便走哪一条。<br>'),(2856,'eject','ejected','ejected','ejecting','','v. 逐放,放逐,驱逐',' The noisy youths were ejected from the cinema.<br>     吵闹的年青人都已从影院被逐出去了。<br>\n Cartridges are ejected from the gun after firing.<br>     开枪后子弹从枪膛里弹出去。<br>'),(2857,'ejection','','','','','n. 喷射',' The amount or rate of emission or ejection.<br>     排放量流量、流速，或排出量，排出的速度<br>'),(2858,'eke','eked','eked','eking','','vt. 放长,增加',' They eke out a bare existence (ie They scarcely manage) on his low salary.<br>     他们靠他微薄的薪金勉强　口.<br>\n In old China workers and peasants could hardly eke out a living, let alone send their children to school.<br>     在旧中国，工人农民连生活都难以维持，更谈不上送子女上学了。<br>'),(2859,'elaborate','','','','','a. 精细的,详尽的,精心的<br>\nv. 详细地说明,用心地作,推敲',' What you\'ve told me of your plan sounds most interesting; would you care to elaborate?<br>     你给我讲的这个计划很有意思，你能详细地谈一谈吗？<br>\n The curtains had an elaborate pattern of flowers.<br>     窗帘上绘有精美的花卉图案。<br>'),(2860,'elaboration','','','','elaborations','n. 苦心经营,精巧<br>\nn. 详细说明',' The elaborations of the plot made it a difficult book to read.<br>     这本书因内容节外生枝而很难懂.<br>'),(2861,'elapse','elapsed','elapsed','elapsing','','v. 逝去,过去',' Three years have elapsed since we met last time.<br>     我们上次相见至今已经三年了。<br>\n Three years have elapsed since we last met.<br>     我们上次相见至今已过了三