     谨慎是那人性格的本质。<br>'),(3110,'essential','','','','essentials','n. 要素,要点<br>\na. 必要的,重要的,本质的',' Food is essential to life.<br>     食物对生命是必不可少的。<br>\n Her most essential quality is kindness.<br>     她最主要的品质是善良。<br>'),(3111,'essentially','','','','','ad. 本质上,本来',' He is essentially a very nice person.<br>     他基本上是一个和蔼可亲的人。<br>\n He\'s essentially a very generous man.<br>     他本质上是个十分慷慨的人。<br>'),(3112,'establish','established','established','establishing','','v. 建立,确立,创办',' Our company was established in 1994.<br>     我们的公司成立于1994年。<br>\n His second novel established his fame as a writer.<br>     他的第二部小说确立了他作家之名。<br>'),(3113,'established','','','','','a. 确定的(建成的,建立的,被制定的)<br>\nv. 建立(制定,证实)',' He has established his own firm.<br>     他已建立起自己的公司。<br>\n We\'ve established his innocence/(the fact) that he\'s innocent.<br>     我们已证实他无罪.<br>'),(3114,'establishment','','','','establishments','n. 确立,制定,设施',' He keeps a large establishment.<br>     他拥有巨大家业。<br>\n The establishment of that school took five years.<br>     兴建那所学校花了五年的时间。<br>'),(3115,'estate','','','','estates','n. 财产,房地产',' The old man left an estate of two million dollars when he died.<br>     那老人去世时留下二百万美元的遗产。<br>\n He has a beautiful estate near London.<br>     他在离伦敦不远处有一个美丽的庄园。<br>'),(3116,'esteem','esteemed','esteemed','esteeming','','n. 尊敬<br>\nv. 尊敬,尊重',' She esteemed that she knew what life was.<br>     她认为自己懂得什么是生活。<br>\n We esteem him to be worthy of trust.<br>     我们认为他值得信任。<br>'),(3117,'esthetic','','','','','a. 审美的',''),(3118,'estimate','estimated','estimated','estimating','estimates','n. 估计,估价<br>\nv. 估计,估价,评价',' My estimate of the length of the room was 10 feet.<br>     我估计房间的长度为10 英尺。<br>\n He is highly estimated among his colleagues.<br>     他在同事中受到的评价很高。<br>'),(3119,'estimation','','','','estimations','n. 判断,估计,尊重',' In my estimation, he is a more suitable candidate.<br>     我认为他是更合适的人选。<br>\n She\' s certainly gone up in my estimation since she told the boss what she thought of him.<br>     她对老板讲了自己对他的看法后，我就更加尊敬她了。<br>'),(3120,'eternal','','','','','a. 永久的,永恒的',' The idea that the world is eternal is now seldom advanced.<br>     地球是永恒的这种看法现在很少提出了。<br>\n The bad man will suffer eternal damnation.<br>     坏人将会受到永远的惩罚。<br>'),(3121,'ether','','','','','n. 乙醚,醚',' Ether was used formerly to put a patient to sleep before an operation.<br>     从前人们在手术前用乙醚来使病人昏睡。<br>\n The merciful magic of ether was not used that day, so the poor soul had to bear their pain as best they may.<br>     那天，由于没有使用能够魔术般解除疼痛的乙醚，那些可怜的人得尽量忍受他们的痛苦。<br>'),(3122,'Ethernet','','','','','以太网',' The firewall machine will require two ethernet card, one interface to the outside world and one to the master pop network.<br>     防火墙计算机要求2张以太网卡，一个对外部世界的接口和一个对主POP网络的接口。<br>'),(3123,'ethnic','','','','','a. 民族的，种族的<br>\n某文化群体的（典型的）',' A member of the predominant ethnic group of Iran.<br>     法尔西人伊朗主要种族的一员<br>\n Ethnic enclaves in a large city.<br>     被围于大城市之中的少数民族<br>'),(3124,'ethos','','','','','n. 民族精神,社会思潮,风气',''),(3125,'etiquette','','','','','n. 礼仪,礼节,成规',' The forms of ceremony and etiquette observed by diplomats and heads of state.<br>     外交礼节外交官和国家元首遵守的礼节和礼仪形式<br>\n Let us avoid the etiquette.<br>     让我们免除礼节。<br>'),(3126,'Europe','','','','','n. 欧洲',' Is France in Europe?<br>     法国在欧洲吗？<br>\n At its zenith the Roman Empire covered almost the whole of Europe.<br>     罗马帝国在全盛时期几乎占据了整个欧洲。<br>'),(3127,'European','','','','','a. 欧洲的<br>\nn. 欧洲人',' He looks European.<br>     他看上去像欧洲人。<br>\n She is the only European in the class.<br>     她是班上唯一的欧洲人。<br>'),(3128,'evacuate','evacuated','evacuated','evacuating','','v. 疏散,撤出,排泄',' The region near the erupting volcano was evacuated rapidly.<br>     火山爆发处附近已迅速撤空.<br>\n The soldiers evacuated the area as the enemy advanced.<br>     敌军推进时, 士兵都撤出了那地区.<br>'),(3129,'evade','evaded','evaded','evading','','v. 规避,逃避,躲避',' He could not evade the law.<br>     他逃避不了法律。<br>\n Genius is the capacity of evade hard work.<br>     天才是避免苦干的能力。<br>'),(3130,'evaluate','evaluated','evaluated','evaluating','','v. 评估,评价',' \"The research project has only been under way for three months, so it\'s too early to evaluate its success.\"<br>     ＂这个研究项目进行了不过三个月，所以要对它的成绩作出评价为时尚早。＂<br>\n The school has only been open for six months, so it\'s too early to evaluate its success.<br>     这所学校开办还不过六个月，所以要对它的成绩作出评价为时尚早。<br>'),(3131,'evaluation','','','','evaluations','n. 估价,评价',' In software product evaluation, the totality of features and characteristics of a product or service that bear on its ability to satisfy stated or implied needs. Note: In a contractual environment, needs are specified, whereas in other environments, implied needs should be identified and defined.<br>     在软件产品评价技术中，产品或服务满足规定需求或隐含需求的特征和特性的总和。注：在有合同的环境中，需求是在合同中规定的；而在其它环境中，则应对隐含需求进行验证和定义。<br>\n The opinion derived from such an evaluation.<br>     诊断结果由这种评价取得的结论<br>'),(3132,'evaporate','evaporated','evaporated','evaporating','','v. 蒸发,失去水分,消失',' The water soon evaporated in the sunshine.<br>     水在阳光下不久就蒸发了。<br>\n Heat evaporates water into steam.<br>     水受热变成水蒸汽。<br>'),(3133,'evaporation','','','','','n. 蒸发,脱水,干燥',' Be careful not to lose too much liquid by evaporation.<br>     小心，不要因为蒸发作用而失掉过多的水份。<br>\n The lateral or downward movement of dissolved or suspended material within soil when rainfall exceeds evaporation.<br>     淋溶作用当降雨量超过蒸发量时，土壤中溶解或悬浮物的向侧面或向下的运动<br>'),(3134,'evasion','','','','evasions','n. 逃避,藉口',' The senate was censured for income tax evasion.<br>     这名参议员因逃避缴纳所得税而受到指责。<br>\n Skill in evasion or deception; guile.<br>     狡诈逃避或欺骗的技巧；诡计<br>'),(3135,'eve','','','','','n. 前夜,前夕<br>\nn. [圣]夏娃',' We went to the church to celebrate Christmas Eve.<br>     我们去教堂庆祝圣诞前夕。<br>\n Preparing for the Christmas Eve feast makes me at my wit\'s end.<br>     筹办圣诞宴会简直使我智穷才竭。<br>'),(3136,'even','evened','evened','evening','','a. 平坦的,偶数的,相等的<br>\nad. 甚至,恰好,正当',' John doesn\'t go out even in the summer.<br>     约翰甚至在夏天也不出门。<br>\n He won the first game and I won the second, so now we are even.<br>     他赢了第一局，我赢了第二局，所以我们现在打平。<br>'),(3137,'evening','','','','evenings','n. 傍晚,晚上',' Could you come back home early this evening?<br>     今天晚上你能早回家吗？<br>\n The evening sky flamed with red and orange.<br>     傍晚天空的颜色是一片火红和橘黄相间。<br>'),(3138,'evenly','','','','','ad. 平衡地,平坦地,平等地',' His day is evenly divided between work and relaxation.<br>     他一天的时间一半花在工作上, 一半用在娱乐上。<br>\n Spread a bit of this cream on your face and rub evenly for a while. It can smooth away wrinkles if you persist.<br>     取本面霜少许搽于脸部，并均匀地按摩片刻，长期使用本品能消除皱纹。<br>'),(3139,'event','','','','events','n. 大事,事件',' I\'ll probably see you tomorrow, but in any event I\'ll phone.<br>     明天我可能来看你，万一我来不了，我会打电话的。<br>\n This article discussed the events that led to her suicide.<br>     这篇文章讨论了导致她自杀的一系列事件。<br>'),(3140,'eventful','','','','','a. 变故多的,多事的,重要的',' He has had an eventful life.<br>     他一生有很多大事。<br>\n It is an eventful year.<br>     这是一个有很多大事的一年。<br>'),(3141,'events','','','','','n. 事件',' These events led to the declaration of war.<br>     这些事件导致了宣战。<br>\n History chronicles important events of the past.<br>     历史记载历代重要的事件。<br>'),(3142,'eventually','','','','','ad. 终于,最后',' It was a long journey, but we eventually arrived.<br>     旅程很长，但我们最后还是到达了。<br>\n The road became narrower and rougher and eventually petered out.<br>     这条路越来越窄，越来越难走，最后终于消失了。<br>'),(3143,'ever','','','','','ad. 曾经,永远,究竟',' Have you ever been to Paris?<br>     你去过巴黎吗？<br>\n What ever are you doing?<br>     你究竟在干什么？<br>'),(3144,'evergreen','','','','evergreens','n. 常绿树,常绿植物<br>\na. 常绿的',' Pines are evergreens.<br>     松树是常青树。<br>\n I love these evergreen tunes.<br>     我喜欢这些经久不衰的老曲子。<br>'),(3145,'everlasting','','','','','a. 永恒的,持久的,无止境的',' He believes in life everlasting after death.<br>     他相信死后永生。<br>\n His brave deeds in the battle earned him everlasting glory.<br>     他在那场战斗中的英勇事迹为他赢得了永恒的荣誉。<br>'),(3146,'every','','','','','a. 每,每个,每隔...的',' I enjoyed every minute of the party.<br>     整个晚会我玩得都很愉快。<br>\n He has read every book on the shelves.<br>     书架上所有的书他都读过了。<br>'),(3147,'everybody','','','','','pron. 每人,人人',' The police told everybody to remain in their cars.<br>     警察叫大家都留在车里。<br>\n It\'s impossible to remember everybody\'s name.<br>     把每个人的名字都记住是不可能的。<br>'),(3148,'everyday','','','','','a. 每天的,日常的<br>\nb.平常的日子',' After the explosion it was some time before the town resumed its everyday routines.<br>     爆炸后经过相当一段时间，这个城镇才恢复了正常的生活秩序。<br>\n He does twenty push-ups everyday.<br>     他每天做20个伏卧撑。<br>'),(3149,'everyone','','','','','n. 每个人<br>\npron. 每人,人人',' In a small village, everyone knows everyone else.<br>     在一个小村庄里，人人皆相识。<br>\n Not everyone likes this book.<br>     并不是每个人都喜欢这本书。<br>'),(3150,'everything','','','','','pron. 每件事,一切',' Money isn\'t everything.<br>     金钱不是一切。<br>\n Everything is ready now for the party.<br>     宴会的准备工作现在都已就绪。<br>'),(3151,'everywhere','','','','','ad. 到处,无论何处',' The flowers are blooming everywhere.<br>     鲜花到处盛开。<br>\n I was looking everywhere for Jenny.<br>     我到处找詹妮。<br>'),(3152,'evict','evicted','evicted','evicting','','v. 逐出,赶出,驱逐',' The lessor can evict the lessee for failure to pay rent.<br>     出租人可驱逐不付租金的承租人。<br>\n The tenant was evicted for non-payment of rent.<br>     这个房客因为没有交房租而被赶出去了。<br>'),(3153,'evidence','evidenced','evidenced','evidencing','evidences','n. 根据,证据<br>\nvt. vi. 证实，证明',' When the ship reached port, it bore abundant evidence of the severity of the storm.<br>     船抵港时，船上满是受到暴风雨肆虐的痕迹。<br>\n There wasn\'t enough evidence to prove his guilt.<br>     没有充分的证据能证明他有罪。<br>'),(3154,'evident','','','','','a. 明显的,明白的',' It was evident that the policy was a failure.<br>     显然这项政策是失败的。<br>\n The purpose may not be immediately evident.<br>     这种目的不一定显而易见。<br>'),(3155,'evidently','','','','','ad. 明显地,显著地,必以为是',' The cat was evidently incurable and the old couple had to get it put away.<br>     这只猫的病显然没法治好了，老夫妇只得请人把它杀掉。<br>\n The owner evidently thought his duties ended with collecting the rents and every dwelling we visite