INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (3229,'exile','exiled','exiled','exiling','exiles','n. 放逐,流放,被放逐者<br>\nv. 放逐,流放',' He was exiled from the country for one year.<br>     他被放逐一年。<br>\n The king was sent into exile.<br>     国王遭到放逐。<br>'),(3230,'exist','existed','existed','existing','','v. 存在',' The Roman Empire existed for several centuries.<br>     罗马帝国存在了几百年。<br>\n Man cannot exist without air.<br>     没有空气人就不能生存。<br>'),(3231,'existence','','','','existences','n. 存在,生存',' The newspaper ceased to appear after an existence of three months.<br>     该报发行3 个月后停刊了。<br>\n The family lived a precarious existence.<br>     这家人过着朝不保夕的生活。<br>'),(3232,'existing','','','','','[计算机] 现有的',' We should make a better use of the existing equipment.<br>     我们应该更好地利用现有设备。<br>\n In computer security, any weakness or flaw existing in a system, the susceptibility of a system to a specific threat attack or harmful event, or the opportunity available to a threat agent to mount that attack.<br>     在计算机安全学中，存在于一个系统内的弱点或缺陷，系统对一个特定的威胁攻击或危险事件的敏感性，或进行攻击的威胁作用的可能性。<br>'),(3233,'exit','exited','exited','exiting','','n. 出口,退场,离去<br>\nv. 退出,脱离',' At the end of the third scene the actress exits.<br>     该女演员于第三场结束时退场。<br>\n There are four emergency exits in the department store.<br>     这家百货公司有四个紧急出口。<br>'),(3234,'exonerate','exonerated','exonerated','exonerating','','v. 免除责任,确定无罪<br>\nvt. 使免罪',''),(3235,'exoneration','','','','','n. 免罪,免除',''),(3236,'exorbitant','','','','','a. 过高的',' The practice of lending money and charging the borrower interest, especially at an exorbitant or illegally high rate.<br>     高利贷借给他人钱并要求贷者付很高的利息的做法，尤其利息异常地或非法地高<br>'),(3237,'exotic','','','','','a. 异国的,外来的',' The film retains much of the book\'s exotic flavour.<br>     这部电影保存了原著的许多异国情调.<br>\n Exotic tropical plants in a greenhouse.<br>     温室里引进的热带植物<br>'),(3238,'expand','expanded','expanded','expanding','','v. 使...膨胀,详述,扩张<br>\n[计算机] 扩充',' The petals of many flowers expand in the sunshine.<br>     许多花的花瓣在阳光中绽放。<br>\n Our foreign trade has expanded during recent years.<br>     近年来我们的对外贸易有所扩大。<br>'),(3239,'expander','','','','expanders','扩充器',''),(3240,'expanding','','','','','扩展的,扩充的',' The expanding economy enriched the peasants.<br>     不断发展的经济使农民们富裕起来。<br>\n The project was predicated on the assumption that the economy was expanding.<br>     这一计划是以经济发展的设想为依据的.<br>'),(3241,'expansile','','','','','a. (可)增大的',''),(3242,'expansion','','','','expansions','n. 扩大,膨胀',' Metals undergo expansion when heated.<br>     金属加热时会膨胀。<br>\n This book is an expansion of the play he wrote before.<br>     这本书是他以前写的剧本的扩充。<br>'),(3243,'expect','expected','expected','expecting','','v. 预期,盼望,期待',' The journey was not as nice as we had expected.<br>     旅途不象我们预想的那样好。<br>\n I will do what is expected of me.<br>     我会尽本分的。<br>'),(3244,'expectancy','','','','expectancies','n. 期待(公算)',' Women have a higher life expectancy than men.<br>     女人比男人的预期寿命长.<br>\n A quiver of expectancy ran through the audience.<br>     全场引颈以待, 群情鼎沸.<br>'),(3245,'expectation','','','','','n. 期待,期望<br>\nv. 期待,前程',' He has great expectations from his uncle.<br>     他渴望从叔叔那继承大笔遗产。<br>\n She ate a light lunch in expectation of a good dinner.<br>     她午饭吃得很少，期待晚饭时饱餐一顿。<br>'),(3246,'expedience','','','','','n. 便利,权宜之计',' He acted from expediency, not from principle.<br>     他为求达到目的, 丧失了原则.<br>'),(3247,'expedient','','','','expedients','n. 权宜之计,临时手段<br>\na. 权宜的,方便的,有用的',' He thought it expedient not to tell his wife where he had been.<br>     他认为不告诉妻子他去过哪里是适宜的。<br>\n As he had forgot his keys, he got into the house by the simple expedient of climbing through the window.<br>     他由于忘了带钥匙，便以简单的应急办法从窗户爬进屋里。<br>'),(3248,'expedite','expedited','expedited','expediting','','v. 加快,促进',' Expedite offer afraid buyer ready withdraw as others contact him.<br>     糨公司正与之接触，请速予报价，否则买主准备撤走。<br>\n Shipment is ready, expedite credit.<br>     船已装完，请速开信用证。<br>'),(3249,'expedition','','','','expeditions','n. 远征,探险队,迅速',' The mail is conveyed with expedition.<br>     那封信被迅速地传递出去。<br>\n They planned to organize a scientific expedition.<br>     他们计划组织一次科学考察。<br>'),(3250,'expel','expelled','expelled','expelling','','v. 驱逐,逐出,开除',' He was expelled from the school.<br>     他被学校开除了。<br>\n The bullet was expelled from the gun.<br>     子弹从枪中射出。<br>'),(3251,'expend','expended','expended','expending','','v. 花费,消耗,支出',' I had expended much time on the work but they told me it\'s useless.<br>     我花了很多时间在这件工作上，他们却告诉我说这是无用的。<br>\n The soldiers expended all their ammunition in that fight.<br>     士兵在那场战斗中用尽了所有的弹药。<br>'),(3252,'expenditure','','','','expenditures','n. (时间、劳力、金钱等)支出,使用,消耗',' The expenditure of money on weapons is very large.<br>     购置武器的开支很大。<br>\n Limit your expenditure to what is essential.<br>     你要把开销限制在必要的范围内。<br>'),(3253,'expense','','','','expenses','n. 消费,支出',' It\'s too much of an expense for me to own a car.<br>     对我来说，拥有一辆汽车的花费太大。<br>\n He finished the job at the expenses of his health.<br>     他以牺牲健康完成了这项工作。<br>'),(3254,'expenses','','','','','n. 费用,开支',' The incidental expenses of cars in this city are expensive.<br>     这个城市汽车的附加费用很昂贵。<br>\n Could you detail all your expenses on this form?<br>     请把你的各项开支列在这张表格上，好吗？<br>'),(3255,'expensive','','','','','a. 昂贵的',' The dress is too expensive for me to buy.<br>     那衣服太昂贵，我买不起。<br>\n The manufacture of these small components is expensive.<br>     制造这些小部件是非常昂贵的。<br>'),(3256,'experience','experienced','experienced','experiencing','experiences','n. 经历,经验<br>\nv. 经历,体验',' He experienced great difficulty in getting a visa to leave the country.<br>     他申请出国签证经历了很大的困难。<br>\n We learn from the past, experience the present and hope for success in the future.<br>     我们从过去中学习，体验现在，展望未来的成功。<br>'),(3257,'experienced','','','','','a. 有经验的',' I want some persons more experienced than Tom.<br>     我要一些比汤姆更有经验的人。<br>\n Only experienced pilots fly large passenger aircraft.<br>     只有有经验的飞行员才能驾驶大型客机。<br>'),(3258,'experiment','experimented','experimented','experimenting','experiments','n. 实验,试验,尝试<br>\nv. 实验,尝试',' Some scientists experiment on animals.<br>     有些科学家用动物做试验。<br>\n Small businesses are anxious to experiment with computers.<br>     小型企业都急于试用计算机。<br>'),(3259,'experimental','','','','','a. 实验(性)的,试验(性)的',' The technique is still at the experimental stage.<br>     这项技术正处于实验阶段。<br>\n In experimental plots the yield has been doubled.<br>     在试验田里，产量已（被）提高了一倍。<br>'),(3260,'experimentation','','','','','n. 实验,试验',' The process of conducting such a test; experimentation.<br>     实验过程做这种试验的过程；实验<br>\n A room or building equipped for scientific experimentation or research.<br>     实验室用于科学实验或研究的房屋或建筑<br>'),(3261,'expert','','','','experts','a. 熟练的,内行的<br>\nn. 专家,能手',' According to expert opinions, they gave up the experiment immediately.<br>     根据专家们的意见，他们马上放弃了这项试验。<br>\n He is an well-known expert in finance.<br>     他是知名的金融专家。<br>'),(3262,'expertise','','','','','n. 专家的意见,专门技术',' And the scientist in Boston will be able to call on the expertise of the scientist in Shanghai, and all of it in a matter of seconds.<br>     同样，在美国波士顿的一位科学家，也将能够向上海的一位科学家要求提供专门知识。而这种联系只需要几秒钟的时间就可以接通。<br>\n But the areas of our mutual cooperation continue to expand. We have already agreed to cooperate more closely in trade, technology, investment, and exchanges of scientific and managerial expertise.<br>     但是我们彼此合作的领域还在不断增加。我们已经商定在贸易、技术、投资以及科学与管理专门知识的交流等方面更密切地合作。<br>'),(3263,'expiration','','','','','n. 呼出,呼气,终止',' The expiration of contract is coming.<br>     合同快到期了。<br>\n When is the expiration of your driving license?<br>     你的驾驶执照何时到期？<br>'),(3264,'expire','expired','expired','expiring','','v. 期满,失效,终止,断气',' My passport is due to expire in two months.<br>     我的护照再过两个月就到期了。<br>\n Our current contract is about to expire, and we\'ll need to discuss a new one.<br>     欧文们现有合同快要期满了，需要再谈一个新合同。<br>'),(3265,'expiry','','','','expiries','n. 逾期',''),(3266,'explain','explained','explained','explaining','','解释,说明',' That explains why she is not here.<br>     那就说明了她不在这里的原因。<br>\n The lawyer explained the new law to us.<br>     律师向我们解释了新法律。<br>'),(3267,'explanation','','','','explanations','n. 解释,说明',' Did he provide a satisfactory explanation?<br>     他是否给出了令人满意的解释？<br>\n What did he say in explanation of his stupid behavior?<br>     他说了什么来解释他那愚蠢的行为？<br>'),(3268,'explanatory','','','','','a. 解释的,说明的',' An explanatory table or list of the symbols appearing on a map or chart.<br>     图例对出现在地图上或图表中的有关符号进行解释的一览表或清单<br>\n Serving to explain; explanatory.<br>     作解释用的；说明的<br>'),(3269,'expletive','','','','','a. 填补的(补足的,附加的,多余的)<br>\nn. 填补物',' He uttered several vigorous expletives when he dropped the iron on his foot.<br>     他的熨斗掉下砸在脚上, 他随口骂了几声.<br>\n `Damn!\' is an expletive.<br>     ｀该死!＇是咒骂语.<br>'),(3270,'explicit','','','','','a. 明确的,详述的，明晰的,外在的',' He gave me explicit directions on how to get there.<br>     他清清楚楚地告诉我怎样到达那里.<br>\n She was quite explicit about why she left.<br>     她对自己离去的原因直言不讳.<br>'),(3271,'explicitly','','','','','ad. 明白地, 明确地',' The definition of a global symbol that is not explicitly available for reference by modules linked with the module in which the definition occurs.<br>     一种全局符号定义，它不能被与定义该全局符号的模块相链接的其它模块直接引用。<br>'),(3272,'explode','exploded','exploded','exploding','','v. 爆炸,爆发,激发<br>\n[计算机] 爆炸',' He exploded with rage.<br>     他勃然大怒，暴跳如雷。<br>\n The firework exploded in his hand.<br>     那个爆竹在他手里响了。<br>'),(3273,'exploit','','','','','n. 功绩,勋绩<br>\nv. 开发,利用,开拓',' People should read the related regulations before they exploit natural resources.<br>     在开发自然资源前，人们应该先了解相关的规定。<br>\n Television advertisers can exploit a captive audience.<br>     电视广告商能利用被动观众.<br>'),(3274,'exploitation','','','','','n. 开发,开采,自私的利用',' Generally speaking, mineral exploitation is a feast-or-famine industry.<br>     一般来说，开矿这种事业不是大大成功便是彻底失败。<br>\n Exploitation of unwary consumers.<br>     对粗心消费者的不当利用<br>'),(3275,'exploration','','','','explorations','n. 探险,踏勘,探测',' They decided to make a full exploration of the accident.<br>     他们决定对事故做一次全盘研究。<br>\n It is true during their explorations they often faced difficulties and dangers of the most perilous nature.<br>     确实在探险中，他们经常面临着各种最有危险性的艰难和险阻。<br>'),(3276,'explore','explored','explored','exploring','','v. 探险,探测,探究<br>\n[计算机] 探讨',' The experts are exploring every part of the island.<br>     专家们正在勘查这个岛的各个部分。<br>\n He had an itch to get away and explore.<br>     他等不及要动身去探险。<br>'),(3277,'explorer','','','','explorers','n. 探测者',' This famous explorer finally died in loneliness.<br>     这位著名的探险家最后在孤寂中死去。<br>\n Christopher Columbus was one of the great explorers.<br>     克里斯托弗·哥伦布是伟大的探险家。<br>'),(3278,'explosion','','','','explosions','n. 爆炸,爆发',' The explosion of oil prices caused an economical crisis.<br>     石油价格的急剧上涨引起了经济危机。<br>\n The explosion was heard a mile away.<br>     那爆炸声一英里外也可以听到。<br>'),(3279,'explosive','','','','explosives','a. 爆炸(性)的<br>\nn. 炸药',' Hydrogen is highly explosive.<br>     氢极易爆炸。<br>\n Politics can be an explosive subject.<br>     政治问题容易引起争论。<br>'),(3280,'exponent','','','','exponents','n. 说明者,说明物<br>\na. 说明的<br>\nn. 指数',' Swiss sculptor, painter, and exponent of surrealism who is best known for his elongated sculptures of human figures, such as Walking Man(1960).<br>     贾科尼亚特提，阿尔贝托1901－1966瑞士雕刻家、画家、超现实主义者，他最著名的是他对人体外形的拉长的雕刻，如行走的人（1960年）<br>\n French painter who was a leading exponent and theorist of the cubist movement.<br>     布拉克，乔治斯1882－1963法国画家，是立体派的主要倡导者和理论家<br>'),(3281,'exponential','','','','','指数的',''),(3282,'exponentiation','','','','','求幂',''),(3283,'export','','','','','输出,出口',' What are the chief exports of your country?<br>     你们国家有哪些主要的出口物品？<br>\n Africa is exporting beef to Europe.<br>     非洲向欧洲出口牛肉。<br>'),(3284,'exportation','','','','exportations','n. 出口',''),(3285,'exporter','','','','exporters','n. 出口商',' Argentina is a big exporter of beef products.<br>     阿根廷是牛肉制品的一大出口国。<br>\n Our exporters proudly kept the flag flying at the international trade exhibition.<br>     在国际贸易展览会上，我国的出口商为国争光。<br>'),(3286,'expose','','','','','v. 暴露,揭穿,陈列',' The reporter was killed because he tried to expose a plot.<br>     这名记者因为试图揭露一个阴谋而被杀害。<br>\n You shouldn\'t expose the soldiers to unnecessary risks.<br>     你不应该让士兵们冒不必要的危险。<br>'),(3287,'exposition','','','','expositions','n. 博览会,展览会,说明',' The industrial exposition will be held on September.<br>     工业博览会将于九月召开。<br>\n He made an exposition of the advantages of nuclear power.<br>     他对核动力的优越性做了阐述。<br>'),(3288,'exposure','','','','exposures','n. 暴露,揭露,曝光',' Exposure of the body to strong sunlight can be harmful.<br>     身体受烈日暴晒会造成伤害。<br>\n How many exposures have you left?<br>     还剩多少底片没有照？<br>'),(3289,'express','','','','','n. 快车,快递,专使<br>\na. 急速的,明确的<br>\nv. 表达,表示',' I can\'t express how grateful I am.<br>     我说不出我有多么感激。<br>\n She is the express image of her mother.<br>     她和她母亲长得一模一样。<br>'),(3290,'expression','','','','expressions','n. 表达,表示,表现,表情,措辞,词句',' The scenery was beautiful beyond expression.<br>     那风景美丽得无法形容。<br>\n There was an expression of discontent on her face.<br>     她脸上有不满的表情。<br>'),(3291,'expressive','','','','','a. 表达的',' She gave us an expressive smile.<br>     她意味深长地笑了笑。<br>\n It\'s an expressive piece of music.<br>     这是一首抒情乐曲。<br>'),(3292,'expressly','','','','','ad. 明白地,清楚地,特别地',' You were expressly told not to touch my papers.<br>     已经明确地告诉过你不要动我的文件.<br>\n \"I told you expressly to lock the door, but you didn\'t follow me.\"<br>     ＂我明白地对你说过要锁上门，但你没有听我的话。＂<br>'),(3293,'expressway','','','','expressways','n. 高速公路',' A toll is charged for the use of the expressway.<br>     在那条高速公路上行驶需付通行费。<br>\n The expressway mars the beauty of the countryside.<br>     这条高速公路破坏了农村的田园美景。<br>'),(3294,'expulsion','','','','expulsions','n. 逐出,开除,驱逐',' An agent that destroys or causes the expulsion of parasitic intestinal worms.<br>     驱肠虫剂，灭肠虫剂可消灭或驱除肠内寄生虫的药物<br>\n After his expulsion from the cabinet the minister became the subject of a smear campaign. It seems the media and the public alike take pleasur