>     我们参加了春季展览会。<br>'),(3353,'fairly','','','','','a. 公平地,相当<br>\nad. 相当地',' It\'s a fairly good book.<br>     这是一本相当不错的书。<br>\n I felt I hadn\'t been treated fairly.<br>     我觉得我没有受到公正的对待。<br>'),(3354,'fairy','','','','fairies','n.&a. 仙女,小精灵',' Their love story sounds like a fairy tale.<br>     他们的爱情故事听起来像童话。<br>\n There are many stories about the nymphs in Roman fairy tales.<br>     罗马神话中有许多关于仙女的故事。<br>'),(3355,'faith','','','','faiths','n. 信任,信仰',' I kept faith with him.<br>     我信守了对他的诺言。<br>\n He has great talent, but he has lost his faith.<br>     他很有天赋，但是他已经丧失了信心。<br>'),(3356,'faithful','','','','','a. 如实的,忠诚的,忠实的',' This newspaper gave a faithful account of the event.<br>     这份报纸对那件事进行了如实的报道。<br>\n The dog remained faithful to his master.<br>     这条狗始终忠于它的主人。<br>'),(3357,'faithfully','','','','','ad. 忠实,诚心诚意,深信着',' They swore an oath to carry out their duties faithfully.<br>     他们发誓要忠实履行自己的职责。<br>\n The old nurse have serve the family faithfully for thirty years.<br>     老保姆为这个家庭忠实地服务了三十年。<br>'),(3358,'fake','faked','faked','faking','fakes','n. 假货,欺蹒<br>\na. 假的<br>\nv. 假造,仿造',' That\'s not a real diamond necklace, it\'s just a fake!<br>     那不是真钻石项链, 是假的!<br>\n He looked like a postman but he was really a fake.<br>     他看上去像个邮递员, 但实际上是假冒的.<br>'),(3359,'fall','fell','fallen','falling','falls','n. 秋天,落下,瀑布<br>\nv. 倒下,落下,来临',' He fell into the lake.<br>     他掉进了湖里。<br>\n Six tigers fell to his rifle.<br>     他用步枪射倒了六只老虎。<br>'),(3360,'fallacy','','','','fallacies','n. 谬论',' The fallacy has been exposed in its naked absurdity.<br>     这谬论的荒诞性已被充分揭露。<br>\n The old illustrator never let his pupils fall for the pathetic fallacy, that empty barrels are lonely.<br>     这位年老的插图画家从不让他的学生受到万物有情谬想的感染，认为空桶是孤独的。<br>'),(3361,'fallback','','','','','撤退<br>\n后备计划，后备行动',''),(3362,'fallible','','','','','a. 易错的,可能犯错的',' Human beings are only fallible.<br>     人类本身易犯错误<br>\n Everybody is fallible.<br>     人人都难免有错。<br>'),(3363,'false','','','','','a. 不真实的,错误的,人造的,假的,虚伪的',' Your answer to this question is false.<br>     你对这个问题的回答是错误的。<br>\n They lulled me into a false sense of security.<br>     他们哄骗我，让我产生了一种虚假的安全感。<br>'),(3364,'falter','faltered','faltered','faltering','','v. 支吾地说,迟疑,蹒跚地走<br>\nMy mother\'s taste never falters.我妈是个相当有品味的人.',' The sick man faltered a few steps and then fell.<br>     这个病人摇摇晃晃地走了几步，然后就跌倒了。<br>\n The business faltered and then failed.<br>     商行生意衰退，最后倒闭了。<br>'),(3365,'fame','famed','famed','faming','','n. 名声,名望',' His fame as a poet did not come until after his death.<br>     他死后才获得诗人之名。<br>\n She won her overnight fame by her first novel.<br>     她的第一部小说一问世，便使她一举成名。<br>'),(3366,'familiar','','','','familiars','a. 熟悉的',' I am not really familiar with the local laws.<br>     实际上我对当地的法律并不熟。<br>\n He looks so familiar but I can\'t remember his name.<br>     他看上去非常面熟，但我想不起他的名字来了。<br>'),(3367,'familiarity','','','','familiarities','n. 亲密,熟悉,精通',' Try to discourage such familiarities from your subordinates.<br>     不要让属下对你这样不拘礼仪。<br>\n His familiarity with the local languages surprised me.<br>     他对当地语言如此精通令我吃惊。<br>'),(3368,'familiarize','familiarized','familiarized','familiarizing','','vt. 使熟悉',' It is incumbent upon all users of this equipment to familiarize themselves with the safety procedure.<br>     凡使用这种设备的人都应熟悉安全程序.<br>\n The first repetition drill serves to familiarize the students with the sounds in the dialogue.<br>     第一部分的背诵练习是为了使学生熟悉一下对话的语调。<br>'),(3369,'family','','','','families','a. 家庭的<br>\nn. 家庭',' He had to work hard to support his family.<br>     他不得不努力工作来养家。<br>\n There are five people in my family.<br>     我家里有五口人。<br>'),(3370,'famine','','','','famines','n. 饥荒',' Thousands of people died of famine.<br>     千千万万的人死于饥荒。<br>\n We are collecting money for the famine victim.<br>     我们在为遭受饥荒的灾民募捐。<br>'),(3371,'famous','','','','','a. 著名的',' He is famous for his fine acting.<br>     他以演技精湛著称。<br>\n New York is famous for its skyscrapers.<br>     纽约以其摩天大楼著称。<br>'),(3372,'fan','','','','','n. 风扇,迷,狂热者<br>\nv. 煽,煽动,刺激',' We have an extractor fan in the kitchen to get rid of the smell of cooking.<br>     我们的厨房里有台排气扇，用来消除油烟。<br>\n My boss is a football fan.<br>     我的上司是一位足球迷。<br>'),(3373,'fanatic','','','','fanatics','n. 狂热,狂热者,盲信<br>\na. 狂热的,盲信的',' We call him a politics fanatic.<br>     我们叫他政治狂。<br>\n She\'s fanatic about pop music.<br>     她对流行音乐很狂热。<br>'),(3374,'fancy','fancied','fancied','fancying','fancies','n. 想像力,幻想,喜好<br>\na. 想像的,精美的,新奇的',' I fancy I have met you before.<br>     我想我以前或许见过你。<br>\n The painting took his fancy, so he bought it.<br>     这幅画被他看中了，所以他就把他买了下来。<br>'),(3375,'fantastic','','','','','a. 极好的,难以相信的,奇异的,幻想的',' We watched a fantastic play yesterday evening.<br>     昨天晚上我们看了一场非常精彩的演出。<br>\n My daughter likes to describe her fantastic dreams to me.<br>     我女儿喜欢给我讲她那些奇怪的梦。<br>'),(3376,'fantastical','','','','fantasticals','a. 幻想的(奇异的)',''),(3377,'fantasy','','','','fantasies','n. 幻想',' Stop looking for a perfect job---it\'s just a fantasy.<br>     别想找十全十美的工作了---那简直是幻想。<br>\n The young always live in a world of fantasy.<br>     年轻人总是生活在幻想中。<br>'),(3378,'far','','','','','ad.&a. 远的(地)<br>\nn. 远处',' The far side of the moon is difficult for us to observe.<br>     我们很难观察月亮的另一边。<br>\n We walked far into the woods.<br>     我们步行深入林中。<br>'),(3379,'fare','fared','fared','faring','fares','n. 费用,食物<br>\nv. 进展,进步,经营',' I think I fared quite well in the interview.<br>     我觉得我这次面试考得不错。<br>\n I reminded her how much the fare was.<br>     我提醒她车票的价钱.<br>'),(3380,'farewell','','','','farewells','a. 告别的<br>\nint. 再会,别了<br>\nn. 告别',' Farewell! I hope we meet again soon.<br>     别了！希望很快我们能再见面。<br>\n It\'s time to say our farewells.<br>     是我们该告辞的时候了。<br>'),(3381,'farm','farmed','farmed','farming','farms','n. 农场,农田<br>\nv. 耕种',' We work on the farm.<br>     我们在农场工作。<br>\n My friend is farming in Wales.<br>     我的朋友在威尔士的农场种地。<br>'),(3382,'farmer','','','','farmers','n. 农夫',' That farmer employs many farm laborers.<br>     那位农场主雇佣很多农场工人。<br>\n The farmer wh