格。<br>'),(3392,'fashionable','','','','','a. 流行的,时髦的',' This dress is such a good style; it will be fashionable for many years.<br>     这件衣服的式样真高雅，它一定会流行好几年。<br>\n It\'s fashionable to go to Singapore for your holidays.<br>     到新加坡去度假是时下的时尚。<br>'),(3393,'fashioned','','','','','...式的',' He fashioned the clay into a jar.<br>     他用粘土做成一个陶土罐子。<br>\n In a dignified, noble fashion befitting or characteristic of a lord.<br>     高傲的，贵族的以符合老爷或作为老爷的尊贵的、高贵的方式的或具之特点的<br>'),(3394,'fast','','','','','a. 快速的,耐久的,紧的<br>\nad. 很快地,紧紧地,彻底地<br>\nn. vi. 禁食, 绝食, 斋戒',' I like fast music.<br>     我喜欢节奏快的音乐。<br>\n They run faster and faster.<br>     他们跑得越来越快。<br>'),(3395,'fastback','','','','','快速返回',''),(3396,'fasten','fastened','fastened','fastening','','v. 拴紧,使固定,系',' I fastened the pages together with a paperclip.<br>     我用一个纸夹把那几页纸夹在一起。<br>\n She fastened the notice to the board.<br>     她把通知贴到布告板上。<br>'),(3397,'fastidious','','','','','a. 难取悦的,挑剔的,苛求的<br>\n=particular',' She is so fastidious about her food that I never invite her for dinner.<br>     她对食物过於挑剔，因此我从不请她吃饭<br>\n One who is excessively fastidious in dress, manners, or taste.<br>     爱修饰的人过分讲究穿著、举止或嗜好的人<br>'),(3398,'fat','fatted','fatted','fatting','','a. 肥胖的<br>\nn. 脂肪',' He can\'t eat fat.<br>     他不能吃肥肉。<br>\n The tight jumper only accentuated his fat stomach.<br>     那件紧身套头毛衣反更突出了他那肥胖的肚子.<br>'),(3399,'fatal','','','','','a. 致命的,毁灭性的',' His illness was fatal to our plan.<br>     他的患病给我们的计划带来灾难。<br>\n This was his fatal defect; he was of feeble will.<br>     这是他致命的弱点，他意志薄弱。<br>'),(3400,'fate','fated','fated','fating','fates','n. 命运',' They met with a terrible fate.<br>     他们的结局十分悲惨。<br>\n She wondered what fate had in store for her next.<br>     她不知道以后等待她的将是什么命运。<br>'),(3401,'father','fathered','fathered','fathering','fathers','n. 父亲',' I have loved her like a father should.<br>     我爱她就像爱自己的女儿一样。<br>\n Father sits in the same chair every evening.<br>     父亲每晚都坐在同一张椅子上，<br>'),(3402,'fathom','fathomed','fathomed','fathoming','fathom','n.&v. 测量深度,看穿,彻底了解',' The ship sank in four fathoms.<br>     这条船沉下四英寻。<br>\n I cannot fathom his meaning.<br>     我不能彻底了解他的意思。<br>'),(3403,'fatigue','fatigued','fatigued','fatiguing','fatigues','n. 疲乏,疲劳<br>\nv. 使...疲劳,使...心智衰弱',' Finally, her mind gave in to fatigue and she fell asleep.<br>     最后她的心力疲惫不堪，就睡着了。<br>\n The patient fatigues easily.<br>     病人容易疲劳。<br>'),(3404,'fatuous','','','','','a. 愚昧的, 昏庸的, 发呆的, 愚笨的, 自满的',''),(3405,'fault','faulted','faulted','faulting','faults','n. 故障,过失,缺点<br>\nvt. 挑剔,指责',' My father is always finding fault with the way I do things.<br>     我父亲总是对我做事的方式百般挑剔。<br>\n There are several faults in the page of figures.<br>     那一页的数字中有几个差错。<br>'),(3406,'faultless','','','','','a. 完美的,无缺点的',' The teacher told us the faultless argumentation after the test.<br>     考试后，老师告诉了我们正确的论证方法。<br>\n These musicians gave an absolutely faultless performance.<br>     这些音乐家作了一场绝对完美的演出。<br>'),(3407,'faulty','','','','','a. 有错误的,有缺点的',' My judgement was frequently faulty, but my loyalty to the nation could not be questioned.<br>     我的判断经常出错，但是我对祖国的忠诚是无可置疑的。<br>\n The new TV is faulty in design.<br>     新电视在设计上是有缺点的。<br>'),(3408,'favor','favored','favored','favoring','favors','n. 好意,喜爱<br>\nv. 支持,喜欢,证实',' He did all he could to win his favor.<br>     他尽其所能去赢得他的好感。<br>\n Public opinion was moving strongly in favor of disarmament.<br>     公众舆论正在强烈支持裁军。<br>'),(3409,'favorable','','','','','a. 有利的,赞许的,良好的',' The conditions are favorable for opening a new business.<br>     各种条件有利于开办新企业。<br>\n Most people were favorable to the idea.<br>     大多数人赞成这个主意。<br>'),(3410,'favorably','','','','','ad. 顺利地,亲切地,好意地',' His speech was favorably received.<br>     他的演讲很受欢迎。<br>\n One who is favorably disposed toward Arab concerns and policies.<br>     阿拉伯（民族）主义者非常关注阿拉伯事务及政策的人<br>'),(3411,'favorite','','','','favorites','a. 最喜爱的<br>\nn. 最喜爱的人或物',' I like all the books on the shelf but this one is my favorite.<br>     我喜欢书架上所有的书，但这本是我最喜欢的。<br>\n Who is your favorite writer?<br>     谁是你最喜欢的作家？<br>'),(3412,'favour','favoured','favoured','favouring','favours','n. 帮助(促进,好感,证实,来信,礼物)<br>\nvt 促进',' Cheques should be written in favour of Oxfam.<br>     支票上请写明以牛津饥荒救济委员会为受款人。<br>\n Of the two possible plans I favour the first.<br>     在这两种可行方案中我赞成前者.<br>'),(3413,'fax','','','','','n. 传真<br>\nv. 传真',' Reservations can be made by letter or fax.<br>     可以来信或传真预订。<br>\n After you think it over, please let me know by fax.<br>     你仔细考虑过之后，请用传真相告。<br>'),(3414,'fear','feared','feared','fearing','fears','n. 恐怖,害怕,担心<br>\nv. 害怕,恐惧,敬畏',' She has a great fear of fire.<br>     她对火有恐惧感。<br>\n Do not fear; I will support you.<br>     别担心，我会支持你的。<br>'),(3415,'fearful','','','','','a. 担心的,可怕的',' They were fearful that the river would flood.<br>     他们担心河流会发洪水。<br>\n A fearful person is a weak person.<br>     怕这怕那的人是软弱的人。<br>'),(3416,'fearless','','','','','a. 大胆的,勇敢的,无畏的',' Fearless and daring; courageous.<br>     勇敢的，无畏的；敢作敢为的<br>\n The major impregnated the soldiers with his own fearless courage.<br>     少校把他自己那份无所畏惧的勇气灌输给了士兵们。<br>'),(3417,'feasibility','','','','','n. 可行性',' The department has produced a feasibility report on the development project.<br>     这个部已经拿出了一份开发项目的可行性报告。<br>\n Experts were divided on the feasibility of the project.<br>     专家们对该计划的可行性意见不一。<br>'),(3418,'feasible','','','','','a. 可行的,可能的',' It\'s quite clear that the electric car is technically feasible.<br>     很清楚，电动汽车在工艺技术上是可行的。<br>\n The plan is feasible in reason but impractical.<br>     这个计划道理上行得通, 但不现实。<br>'),(3419,'feast','feasted','feasted','feasting','feasts','n. 宴会,酒席,节会<br>\nv. 款宴,享乐,请客',' He feasted his eye on the beautiful scene.<br>     他尽情欣赏这美丽的景色。<br>\n The king held a feast for us.<br>     国王为我们举行了盛大的宴会。<br>'),(3420,'feat','','','','feats','n. 壮举,功绩,技艺表演',' Apparently impossible feats are now accomplished by science.<br>     许多看起来不可能的伟大业绩现在已经由科学实现了。<br>\n I was amazed to see his dangerous feat.<br>     他的危险技艺让我感到惊讶。<br>'),(3421,'feather','feathered','feathered','feathering','feathers','n. 羽毛',' My daughter asked me to buy her a pillow stuffed with feathers.<br>     我女儿请求我给她买一个羽绒枕头。<br>\n Feather is very light, so that we say\"as light as a feather\".<br>     羽毛很轻，因此我们说“轻如鸿毛”。<br>'),(3422,'feature','featured','featured','featuring','features','n. 特征,容貌<br>\nn. 特点,特色,特性',' Her mouth is her best feature.<br>     她的嘴是她容貌上最好看的部分。<br>\n Wet weather is a feature of life in this area.<br>     天气潮湿是这个地区生活的一个特色。<br>'),(3423,'February','','','','','n. 二月',' He left the city last February.<br>     他于去年二月离开这个城市。<br>\n In February 1916 the French army made a stand at Verdun.<br>     1916年二月，法国军队在凡尔登奋力抵抗。<br>'),(3424,'federal','','','','federals','a. 联邦的<br>\nn. 同盟盟友',' In the USA foreign policy is decided by the federal government and federal laws are made by Congress.<br>     美国外交政策取决于联邦政府，联邦法律由国会制定。<br>\n As the Council on Competitiveness recently noted, some of the700 Federal Laboratories are not pulling their weight and need to be shut down.<br>     美国竞争力咨讯会最近指出，700个联邦试验所之中有些未能发生作用，应予关闭。<br>'),(3425,'federation','','','','federations','n. 联邦,联合,联盟',' The other nations are forming a federation.<br>     其他国家正在结成联盟。<br>\n A principle of allowing each state in a nation or federation to act independently of the central authority, especially in promoting its own economic interests.<br>     独立发展自身利益的原则一种允许一个国家或联邦内的每一个州独立于中央集权而发展的原则，尤指互相提高自身经济利益方面<br>'),(3426,'fee','feed','feed','feeing','fees','n. 费用',' The doctor\'s fee was higher than we expected.<br>     这位医生的收费比我们预料的高。<br>\n She charged only a nominal fee for her work.<br>     她为所做的工作只收取象征性的费用。<br>'),(3427,'feeble','','','','','a. 虚弱的,无力的',' A feeble attempt is liable to fail.<br>     愚蠢的尝试多半是要失败的。<br>\n He bleated out a feeble excuse.<br>     他以微弱的声音作无力的辩解.<br>'),(3428,'feed','fed','fed','feeding','feeds','n. 饲养,饲料,一餐<br>\nv. 喂,饲养,靠...为生',' How many feeds a day does this dog get?<br>     这只狗每天吃几顿？<br>\n Will you feed my cat for me?<br>     请帮我喂我的猫好吗？<br>'),(3429,'feedback','','','','','n. 反馈',' Meanwhile, you are allowed to feedback your thoughts and opinions regularly to develop our program and the club.<br>     及时反馈自己的意见和建议，以便不断提高我们节目的质量和促进俱乐部的发展。<br>\n Part of the energy can be transferred from one part of a mechanism to another, in a direction opposite to its main flow. That\'s what we call feedback.<br>     部分能量能以与它主要传播方向相反的方向从一个机械部件传到另一个机械部件，那就是我们所称的反馈。<br>'),(3430,'feeder','','','','feeders','n. 饲养者,供给者,奶瓶',' The little boy is a noisy feeder.<br>     这个小男孩吃东西时发出响声。<br>'),(3431,'feel','felt','felt','feeling','','v. 感觉,觉得,触摸',' I like the feel of this cloth; it has a warm woolly feel.<br>     我喜欢这块布给我的感觉，它摸上去毛茸茸的很暖和。<br>\n The dead cannot feel.<br>     死人没有知觉。<br>'),(3432,'feeling','','','','feelings','n. 感觉,知觉,感情',' I have a feeling that we are being followed.<br>     我有种感觉我们正被人跟踪。<br>\n You have no feeling for the beauty of nature.<br>     你对大自然的美缺乏欣赏力。<br>'),(3433,'fell','','','','','v. 跌落,落下,降低',' The climber fell from a great height.<br>     攀登者从极高的地方坠落下来.<br>\n I managed to grab hold of the jug before it fell.<br>     我设法抓住了那个罐子才未跌落。<br>'),(3434,'fellow','','','','','n. 人,朋友,同事<br>\na. 同伴的,同事的,同道的',' He was cut off from his fellows.<br>     他和同伴失去联系。<br>\n We\'ve sinned against you, and against our fellow men.<br>     我们得罪了你，也得罪了我们的邻人。<br>'),(3435,'fellowship','','','','fellowships','研究员资格（身份），奖学金，交情',' They offered him the hand of fellowship when he was in difficulties.<br>     当他身处困境时，他们向他伸出了友谊之手。<br>\n He was granted a fellowship.<br>     他被准许入会。<br>'),(3436,'female','','','','','a. 雌的,女(性)的<br>\nn. 雌性的动物,女子',' All the female workers in this factory got a present on March 8.<br>     这家工厂的所有女职工在三八节都得到了一份礼物。<br>\n The male voice is deeper than the female.<br>     男性的嗓音比女性的低沉。<br>'),(3437,'feminine','','','','','a. 女性的',' Jewelry and lace are mostly feminine belongings.<br>     珠宝和蕾丝大多是女性用品。<br>\n There are three genders in German: masculine, feminine and neuter.<br>     德语中有三性: 阳性、 阴性和中性.<br>'),(3438,'fence','fenced','fenced','fencing','fences','n. 围墙,剑术<br>\nv. 用篱笆围住,练习剑术,防护<br>\n[计算机] 栅栏',' Mary talked with me across the garden fence.<br>     玛丽和我隔着花园篱笆交谈。<br>\n The tree was fenced around with wire.<br>     那棵树被铁丝网围了起来。<br>'),(3439,'fend','fended','fended','fending','','v. 抵卫,谋生',' He\'s gone completely round the twist since his mother died and left him to fend for himself.<br>     自从他母亲去世并丢下他去自己谋生之后，他完全疯了。<br>\n In the old society, he was compelled to fend for himself at the age of14.<br>     在旧社会，他十四岁时就被迫自己独立谋生。<br>'),(3440,'fermentation','','','','','n. 发酵',' The fermentation of milk causes it to curdle.<br>     牛奶发酵会凝结起来。<br>\n Sugar is converted into alcohol through the process of fermentation.<br>     糖经过发酵变成酒精。<br>'),(3441,'ferocious','','','','','a. 残忍的,凶猛的',' A person regarded as ferocious or violent.<br>     被认为是残酷和凶猛的人<br>\n The ferocious winds seemed about to tear the ship to pieces.<br>     猛烈的狂风仿佛要把船撕成碎片似的。<br>'),(3442,'ferrite','','','','','铁酸盐',''),(3443,'ferromagnetic','','','','','铁磁体',''),(3444,'ferrous','','','','','a. 含铁的',''),(3445,'ferry','ferried','ferried','ferrying','ferries','n. 渡船,渡口',' We ferried the river on a small boat.<br>     我们用小船渡过那条河。<br>\n He went down to the ferry but found the boat on the other side.<br>     他到了渡口，却发现渡船在对岸。<br>'),(3446,'ferryboat','','','','','n. 渡船',' A ferryboat get us across.<br>     一条渡船把我们送到对岸。<br>\n The ferryboat in the harbor got op steam for the crossing to the island.<br>     泊在港内的渡轮增强了锅炉的汽压，准备驶向那个岛屿。<br>'),(3447,'fertile','','','','','a. 肥沃的,能繁殖的<br>\nn. 多产,肥沃',' Fertile soil yields good crops.<br>     肥沃的土地能种出好庄稼。<br>\n Producing abundantly; fertile.<br>     多产的，富饶的能大量生产的；肥沃的<br>'),(3448,'fertility','','','','','n. 肥沃,丰饶,生产力',' It will be a fertility of year for much raining.<br>     因为雨水多，今年会是丰产的一年。<br>\n The fertility of the soil has been greatly improved by the use of pesticides.<br>     土壤施用杀虫剂後肥力大增.<br>'),(3449,'fertilizer','','','','','n. 肥料',' Crushed bones make one of the best fertilizers.<br>     碎骨是最好的肥料之一。<br>\n Get some more fertilizer for the garden.<br>     给花园再多施些肥料.<br>'),(3450,'fervent','','','','','a. 热的,炎热的,热心的',' She had a fervent farewell speech.<br>     她发表了热情的告别演说。<br>\n Filled with or motivated by zeal; fervent.<br>     热情的充满热情的或为热情所动的；热烈的<br>'),(3451,'fester','festered','festered','festering','','v. 溃烂,生脓,n. 脓疮,溃烂',' The resentment festered in his mind.<br>     他心中的愤恨有增无减。<br>\n His wound became festering.<br>     他的伤口在溃烂。<br>'),(3452,'festival','','','','festivals','a. 节日的,喜庆的,快乐的<br>\nn. 节日,庆祝及祭祀,欢宴',' Christmas is a festival of the Chistian Church.<br>     圣诞节是基督教的节日。<br>\n This city has a music festival every summer.<br>     本市每年举行一次夏季音乐节。<br>'),(3453,'fetch','','','','','n. 取得<br>\nv. 接来,取来,带来<br>\n[计算机] 取',' This house should fetch a good price.<br>     这所房子应该卖个好价钱。<br>\n Could you run and fetch a doctor for me?<br>     你能跑去给我请一个医生吗？<br>'),(3454,'fetter','fettered','fettered','fettering','fetters','v. 加脚镣,束缚<br>\nvt.&n. 脚镣,束缚',' He was fettered by his family and could not travel any longer.<br>     他被家庭束缚，不能再到处去旅游了。<br>\n The prisoner was put into the jail with fetters.<br>     这个犯人被戴上脚镣投进了监狱。<br>'),(3455,'fetus','','','','fetuses','n. 胎,胎儿',' The medical study and treatment of the fetus, especially within the uterus.<br>     胎儿学尤指对子宫内的胎儿的医学研究和治疗<br>\n Diagnostic imaging in which ultrasound is used to visualize an internal body structure or a developing fetus.<br>     超声波扫描术利用超声波来显示耳体结构或胚胎发育情况的诊断用的成像法<br>'),(3456,'feud','','','','','n. 不和,封地,争执',' Because of a family feud, he hasn\'t spoken to his wife\'s parents for years.<br>     由于两家不和，他已经多年不与岳父母说话。<br>\n He eventually killed her because of a long-standing feud.<br>     因为宿怨，他最终杀了她。<br>'),(3457,'feudal','','','','','a. 封建的',' The way some landlords treat their tenants today still seems feudal.<br>     今天有些地主仍以近乎封建的方式对待佃户。<br>\n The feudal barons were cruel to the people.<br>     封建贵族对人民很残酷。<br>'),(3458,'feudalism','','','','','n. 封建制度',' Down with feudalism!<br>     打倒封建主义！<br>'),(3459,'fever','fevered','fevered','fevering','','n. 发烧,发热,热病',' Football fever gripped the town when the local team reached the cup final.<br>     在当地的足球队打进了优胜杯的决赛圈后，全市掀起一阵足球热。<br>\n Her fever passed its crisis.<br>     她发烧已经过了危险期。<br>'),(3460,'few','','','','','a. 很少的,不多的,少数的<br>\nint. 少数的<br>\na. 少数的',' Few of us have his address.<br>     我们中几乎没有人知道他的地址。<br>\n We saw few students there.<br>     我们在那儿几乎没看见学生。<br>'),(3461,'fiber','','','','fibers','n. 纤维',' Scientists are recommending that people eat more fiber.<br>     科学家建议人们多吃些纤维素。<br>\n I love my country with every fiber of my being.<br>     我深爱我的祖国。<br>'),(3462,'fibre','','','','fibres','n. 纤维,纤维组织,织地',' He is a man of real fibre.<br>     他是一个有骨气的男子。<br>\n I love my country with every fibre of my being.<br>     我深爱我的祖国。<br>'),(3463,'fibroma','','','','fibromata','n. 纤维瘤',''),(3464,'fiche','','','','','卡片,缩微胶片',''),(3465,'fickle','','','','','a. 变幻无常的,浮燥的',' He turned out to be fickle - he has left me.<br>     他原来是个善变的人 - 他离开我了。<br>\n Fortune\'s fickle wheel.<br>     多变的命运之轮。<br>'),(3466,'fiction','','','','fictions','n. 小说,虚构',' I like to read science fiction.<br>     我喜欢读科幻小说。<br>\n His account of the crime was a complete fiction.<br>     他所讲述的那种罪刑完全是虚构的。<br>'),(3467,'fictional','','','','','a. 虚构的,编造的,小说式的',' He embellished his account with fictional details.<br>     他以种种虚构的细节来渲染他的叙述。<br>'),(3468,'fiddle','fiddled','fiddled','fiddling','fiddles','n. 小提琴<br>\nv. 虚度时光,拉小提琴',' Put down my pen and stop fiddling!<br>     把我的钢笔放下，别用手玩弄！<br>\n Well, we\'d better get started and stop fiddling about.<br>     我们最好动身，不要再延误了。<br>'),(3469,'fidelity','','','','fedelities','n. 忠实,诚实,忠诚',' Fidelity to engagement is a virtue.<br>     信守诺言是一种美德。<br>\n Good faith; fidelity.<br>     坚定信念；忠诚<br>'),(3470,'field','fielded','fielded','fielding','fields','a. 野外<br>\nn. 地,田地',' Many farmers are working in the fields.<br>     许多农民在田里干活。<br>\n He has become famous in his own field.<br>     他在自己的领域里已经出名了。<br>'),(3471,'fierce','','','','','a. 猛烈的,残忍的,狂暴的,强烈的',' Because there is so much unemployment, the competition for jobs is fierce.<br>     因为失业严重，求职的竞争十分激烈。<br>\n They were having a fierce argument and I thought they might hit each other.<br>     他们正在恶狠狠地争吵，我想他们可能要打架了。<br>'),(3472,'fiery','','','','','a. 炽热的,热烈的,暴躁的',' No one dare to offend the fiery person.<br>     没人敢惹这个脾气急躁的人。<br>\n She gave vent to her indignation in a fiery speech.<br>     她在一篇激烈的演说中发泄怒气。<br>'),(3473,'fifteen','','','','fifteens','num. 十五<br>\npron.&a. 十五(个,只...)',' She is fifteen.<br>     她十五岁。<br>\n After working for fifteen hours I began to tire.<br>     工作了十五个小时之后，我开始感到累了。<br>'),(3474,'fifteenth','','','','fifteenths','num. 第十五',' Most students in this class are fifteen.<br>     这个班的大多数孩子都十五岁。<br>\n He traces his family back to about the fifteenth century.<br>     他把他的家世追溯到十五世纪前後。<br>'),(3475,'fifth','','','','fifths','a. 第五的',' He passed me one fifth of the cake.<br>     他递给我五分之一个蛋糕。<br>\n The team has chalked up its fifth win in a row.<br>     这队一连五次取得胜利.<br>'),(3476,'fifty','','','','fifties','num. 五十',' My mother is fifty years old.<br>     我母亲已经五十岁了。<br>\n These people who were young fifty years back are now gray haired.<br>     50年前的年轻人，现在已经白发苍苍了。<br>'),(3477,'fig','','','','','[植]无花果, 无花果树, 无价值的东西, 少许, 一些, 服装',' You don\'t really care a fig about status.<br>     你对地位真是一点儿也不在乎。<br>\n The richly fig out young woman stand out at the party.<br>     那位衣饰富丽的年轻女郎在宴会上引人注目。<br>'),(3478,'fight','','','','','n. 打架,战斗,斗志<br>\nv. 对抗,打架',' He was always fighting with his neighbors about the noise.<br>     他常常为了噪音和邻居们争吵。<br>\n The news of defeat took all the fight out of us.<br>     失败的消息夺走了我们所有的斗志。<br>'),(3479,'fighter','','','','','n. 斗士,战士,好战者',' The fighter plane was completely destroyed.<br>     这架战斗机彻底毁坏了。<br>\n She won\'t give up easily: she\'s a real fighter.<br>     她不会轻易放弃的，她十分顽强。<br>'),(3480,'fighting','','','','','vbl. 对抗,打架',' He interposed himself between them to stop them fighting.<br>     他挤进两人中间，阻止他们打架。<br>\n The people there are fighting to gain their freedom from foreign control.<br>     那里的人民正在为摆脱外国统治争取自由而战斗。<br>'),(3481,'figurative','','','','','a. 比喻的,形容多的,修饰丰富的',' \"A sweet temper\" is a figurative expression, but \"sweet coffee\" is not.<br>     \"甜蜜的性情\"是个比喻的说法，而\"甜咖啡\"则不是。<br>\n A purifying or figurative cleansing of the emotions, especially pity and fear, described by Aristotle as an effect of tragic drama on its audience.<br>     情绪的净化情绪的净化或象征性清洗，尤指遗憾和恐惧，亚里土多德把他描述为悲剧对观众情绪的影响<br>'),(3482,'figure','figured','figured','figuring','figures','n. 图形,数字,形状<br>\nv. 演算,认为,领会到',' They figured it was better to stay where they were.<br>     他们断定还是呆在原地好。<br>\n Mahatma Gandhi was both a political and a religious figure in Indian history.<br>     甘地在印度历史上是政治和宗教要人。<br>'),(3483,'file','','','','','n. 档案,公文箱,锉刀<br>\nv. 列队行进,归档,申请<br>\n[计算机] 文件',' Put this letter in the main file.<br>     把这封信放在主要文件夹中。<br>\n Please file those letters.<br>     请把这些信件存档。<br>'),(3484,'filename','','','','','文件名',''),(3485,'filing','','','','','n. 锉(文件的整理汇集)',' He filed away at the metal bar.<br>     他不停地锉着金属棒。<br>\n She is the filing clerk of our company.<br>     她是我们公司的档案员。<br>'),(3486,'fill','filled','filled','filling','','v. 装满,填充,弥漫<br>\n[计算机] 填充',' Laughter filled the room.<br>     房间里充满了笑声。<br>\n Please fill the cup with water.<br>     请把这个杯子装满水，<br>'),(3487,'filler','','','','','填充符',''),(3488,'filling','','','','','n. 充填物,填料,填土',' I had to have two fillings at the dentist\'s today.<br>     我今天要请牙医给我补两颗牙。<br>\n I am cooking a sponge cake with jam filling.<br>     我在做果酱松糕。<br>'),(3489,'film','filmed','filmed','filming','films','n. 电影<br>\nv. 把...拍成电影',' He bought two rolls of film for the camera.<br>     他给照相机买了两卷胶卷。<br>\n Joan ran ahead to film us as we crossed the bridge.<br>     我们过桥时，琼跑到前面为我们拍照。<br>'),(3490,'filter','filtered','filtered','filtering','filters','n. 筛选,滤波器,过滤器,滤色镜<br>\nv. 过滤,渗透,走漏<br>\n[计算机] 过滤',' The sunlight filtered through the curtains.<br>     阳光透过窗帘映了进来。<br>\n The teacher gave each 