r>'),(3605,'fodder','','','','','n. 马料,草料',' These documents are useless - they are only wastebasket fodder.<br>     这些文件毫无用处，只配扔进废纸篓里。<br>\n Timothy can be used as fodder for cattle.<br>     猫尾草可以作为喂牛的牧草。<br>'),(3606,'foe','','','','foes','n. 敌人,仇敌',' The knight was murdered by his foes.<br>     那位骑士被他的敌人谋杀了。<br>\n Who goes there friend or foe?<br>     谁在那里--是自己人还是敌人?<br>'),(3607,'fog','fogged','fogged','fogging','fogs','n. 雾<br>\nv. 以雾笼罩,被雾笼罩<br>\nvt. 以雾笼罩',' I was really in a fog after the exam.<br>     考完试后，我真的感到稀里糊涂。<br>\n London used to have bad fogs in winter.<br>     伦敦过去在冬季常有浓雾。<br>'),(3608,'foggy','','','','','a. 有雾的',' His ideas on this subject are a bit foggy.<br>     他对这个问题的看法有些模糊。<br>\n It\'s a foggy morning.<br>     今天早晨有雾。<br>'),(3609,'foil','','','','','n. 箔,烘托,衬托<br>\nv. 衬托,阻止,挡开',' This box of chocolate was wrapped round with foil.<br>     这盒巧克力用箔纸包着。<br>\n Wrapping aluminium foil round a joint allows the meat to cook in its own juice/juices.<br>     用铝箔把肉包住使之在原汁中烹制.<br>'),(3610,'fold','','','','','n. 折层,羊栏,折痕<br>\nv. 折叠,包,交叉',' The paper should be folded in half.<br>     这张纸应该对折。<br>\n I folded the handkerchief and put it in my pocket.<br>     我折好手绢，放进口袋里。<br>'),(3611,'folder','','','','folders','n. 文件夹',' A container, such as a cabinet or folder, for keeping papers in order.<br>     文件夹按顺序放置文件的容器，如档案柜或文件夹<br>\n God, we look like sheep- we are all carrying the same folder.<br>     天啊！我们都带着同样的文件夹，看起来一模一样。<br>'),(3612,'folding','','','','','可折叠的',' A folding or small desk stool at which worshipers kneel to pray, especially one on which the British sovereign kneels at the time of coronation.<br>     祈祷椅礼拜着跪着祈祷时使用的一种可折叠的小凳子，尤指英格兰国王举行加冕礼时使用的<br>\n The comedian had the audience folding up.<br>     那个喜剧演员逗得观众笑得前仰後合。<br>'),(3613,'foliage','','','','','n. 叶子(总称)',' We carried armfuls of foliage to the bonfire.<br>     我们给篝火堆挟来几抱枝叶。<br>\n He crouched down among the tangled foliage.<br>     他蹲下把身子藏在紊乱的叶丛中。<br>'),(3614,'folio','','','','folios','编页码,对开本,页码,张数',' There was a folio missing in the book.<br>     这本书中少了一页。<br>\n We have several early folios for sale.<br>     我们有几本早期的对开本书出售。<br>'),(3615,'folk','','','','folkfolks','a. 民间的<br>\nn. 人们',' I\'d like you to meet my folks.<br>     我想要你见见我的父母。<br>\n He is a very popular folk singer.<br>     他是一位很受欢迎的民歌手。<br>'),(3616,'follow','followed','followed','following','','v. 跟随,沿行,遵循,听得懂',' I didn\'t quite follow; could you explain it again?<br>     我不太明白，你能再解释一下吗？<br>\n The police are following a murderer who\'s in hiding.<br>     警察正在追赶藏匿起来的杀人犯。<br>'),(3617,'follower','','','','followers','n. 从者,属下,追补者',' Many ancient Greeks were followers of Socrates.<br>     许多古希腊人都是苏格拉底的追随者。<br>\n He\'s a follower, not a leader.<br>     他是追随者，不是领导者。<br>'),(3618,'following','','','','','n. 下列各项,部下,党羽<br>\na. 下列的,其次的<br>\nvbl. 跟随',' It rained on the day we arrived, but the following day was sunny.<br>     我们到达的那天正下雨，但次日天气晴朗。<br>\n The police are following a murderer who\'s in hiding.<br>     警察正在追赶藏匿起来的杀人犯。<br>'),(3619,'follows','','','','','n. 跟随<br>\n遵照',' A fan, especially a young woman, who follows a rock group around on tours.<br>     流行乐团迷跟随摇滚乐队巡回演出的迷恋者，尤指年轻女性<br>\n Pain is forgotten where gain follows.<br>     【谚】一朝得了利，痛苦便忘记。<br>'),(3620,'fond','','','','','a. 喜欢的',' My little son is fond of playing practical jokes on me.<br>     我的小儿子喜欢对我玩恶作剧。<br>\n Volleyball is a sport of which I am very fond.<br>     排球是我很喜欢的运动。<br>'),(3621,'font','','','','','字体',''),(3622,'food','','','','foods','n. 食物',' I prefer vegetarian food.<br>     我喜欢吃素食。<br>\n What\'s your favorite food?<br>     你最喜欢的食物是什么？<br>'),(3623,'foodstuff','','','','foodstuffs','n. 食品,食料',' Rice is our essential foodstuff in life.<br>     大米是我们生活的基本食物。<br>\n Nowadays, the foodstuffs in our life are more various.<br>     如今，我们生活中的食品越来越五花八门了。<br>'),(3624,'fool','fooled','fooled','fooling','fools','n. 愚人,受骗者<br>\nv. 愚弄,欺骗',' That silly child never does anything; he just fools about all day long.<br>     那个傻孩子从来不做事，只是整天游手好闲。<br>\n What a fool I was to believe he is a good man.<br>     我竟然相信他是个好人，我真是个傻瓜。<br>'),(3625,'foolish','','','','','a. 愚蠢的',' I felt rather foolish when I couldn\'t answer the teacher\'s question.<br>     当我回答不出老师的提问时，我觉得自己很愚蠢。<br>\n He was angry with himself for having made such a foolish mistake.<br>     他为犯如此愚蠢的错误而对自己气恼不已。<br>'),(3626,'foot','footed','footed','footing','feet','n. 脚',' He got to his feet when he saw her father came in.<br>     他看到她父亲走进来就站了起来。<br>\n He sat on the foot of the bed.<br>     他坐在床脚处。<br>'),(3627,'football','','','','footballs','n. 足球',' I like watching football match on TV.<br>     我喜欢在电视上看足球比赛。<br>\n Which football team is the leader in the football championship?<br>     现在哪个队在足球锦标赛中领先？<br>'),(3628,'footer','','','','','页脚',''),(3629,'footing','','','','','n. 立足点,立场,关系',' The workers want to be on an equal footing with the managers.<br>     工人要求与经理地位平等。<br>\n This enterprise is now on a firm footing and should soon get profits.<br>     现在这家企业基础稳固，很快就会赢利。<br>'),(3630,'footnote','footnoted','footnoted','footnoting','footnotes','n. 脚注(给...作脚注)',' In printing, a term used in footnote meaning\"here and there\".<br>     在印刷技术中，一种在脚注中使用的意为“到处”的术语。<br>\n A political scandal that was but a footnote to modern history.<br>     一件对现代历史无足轻重的政治丑闻<br>'),(3631,'footstep','','','','footsteps','n. 脚步(声),足迹',' There are many footsteps in the snow.<br>     雪地上有许多脚印。<br>\n I heard his footsteps in the hall.<br>     我听见大厅里有他的脚步声。<br>'),(3632,'footsteps','','','','','n. 脚步',' The dog cocked its ears at the sound of footsteps.<br>     狗听到脚步声竖起了耳朵。<br>\n The thief froze when he heard the footsteps approaching.<br>     小偷听到走近的脚步声，吓得呆住了。<br>'),(3633,'for','','','','','conj. 因为<br>\nprep. 给,为',' He shook his head, for he thought differently.<br>     他摇摇头，因为他的想法与此不同。<br>\n What can I do for you?<br>     我能帮你什么忙吗?<br>'),(3634,'forbid','forbade','forbidden','forbidding','','v. 禁止,不准',' I forbid you to tell anyone.<br>     我不许你告诉任何人。<br>\n Lack of time forbids any further discussion at the point.<br>     由于时间不够，现在不能深入讨论这个问题。<br>'),(3635,'forbidden','','','','','a. 被禁止的',' The Forbidden City is one of the world\'s greatest works of architecture.<br>     紫禁城是世界上最伟大的建筑之一。<br>\n Forbidden City is a great magnet for foreign tourists.<br>     紫禁城对外国旅游者来说是个有巨大吸引力的地方。<br>'),(3636,'force','forced','forced','forcing','forces','n. 力量,武力,影响力<br>\nv. 强迫,强夺,加压力<br>\n[计算机] 强制',' The force of the explosion broke all the windows in the building.<br>     爆炸的力量震碎了这座建筑上的所有窗户。<br>\n The rider forced his horse on through the storm.<br>     骑士迫使他的马在暴风雨中前进。<br>'),(3637,'forced','','','','','a. 被迫的,强迫的,用力的<br>\nv. 强迫<br>\nvbl. 强迫',' The boss forced this difficult task upon him.<br>     老板强迫他做此难事。<br>\n Upon reaching an appropriate age, children are encouraged, but not forced, to \"leave the nest\".<br>     一达到适当的年龄，孩子们就被鼓励，而不是被强迫，\"离开老窝\"。<br>'),(3638,'fore','','','','','a. 在前的,以前的<br>\nad. 在前面,在船头<br>\nprep. 在前',' He sat in the fore part of the train.<br>     他坐在火车的前部。<br>\n The captain ordered two flags to be placed fore and aft.<br>     船长吩咐在船头和船尾各挂一面旗子。<br>'),(3639,'forearm','','','','','n. 前臂',' The joint between the hand and the forearm.<br>     腕，腕关节手和前臂之间的关节<br>\n The joint or bend of the arm between the forearm and the upper arm.<br>     肘关节上臂与前臂之间的关节或胳膊弯曲处<br>'),(3640,'forecast','forecast','forecast','forecasting','forecasts','预测,预报',' According to the weather forecast it will rain tomorrow.<br>     天气预报说明天有雨。<br>\n They tried to forecast the result of the football match.<br>     他们试图预测这场足球比赛的结果。<br>'),(3641,'forefather','','','','forefathers','n. 祖先',' One of his forefathers was an early settler in America.<br>     他的祖先之一是美洲的早期移民。<br>\n Japan said on Tuesday that Peru\'s disgraced ex-president Alberto Fujimori has Japanese nationality, a status that allows him to stay in the land of his forefathers and probably avoid facing investigators in Peru.<br>     日本政府周二表示，遭到罢黜的秘鲁前总统藤森具有日本国籍，而这个身分将让他得以继续留在日本这块祖先的土地上，同时也可能让他不必回秘鲁接受调查人员的侦讯。<br>'),(3642,'forefinger','','','','forefingers','n. 食指',' Our foreman, Mr. Li Ming, met an accident on July6. He crushed his forefinger when operating a machine.<br>     我厂领班李明先生在7月6日遇到意外，李先生开动机器时食指被压。<br>'),(3643,'foregoing','','','','','a. 前面的,先前的,前述的',' Coming before in place or order; foregoing.<br>     在前的，处在前面的在地点或计划之前的；在前的<br>\n Refer to the foregoing figures.<br>     涉及到前面所讲的数字<br>'),(3644,'foreground','foregrounded','foregrounded','foregrounding','','n. 前景,最显著的位置<br>\nn.[计算机]前台<br>\n[计算机] 前景',' The figures of the horses in the foreground are out of proportion.<br>     前景中的马画得不成比例.<br>\n Try to draw the figures in the foreground in proportion.<br>     要把前景中的人物画得合比例.<br>'),(3645,'forehead','','','','foreheads','n. 额,前额',' The car bumped and his forehead hit the glass.<br>     汽车颠簸了一下，他的前额撞到了玻璃上。<br>\n His forehead was ridged with anxiety.<br>     他的前额因焦虑而布满了皱纹。<br>'),(3646,'foreign','','','','','a. 外国的',' The swelling on her finger was caused by a foreign body in it.<br>     她的手指肿胀是手指内有异物引起的。<br>\n She\'s a very good woman; unkindness is foreign to her nature.<br>     她是个很好的妇人，冷酷不是她的本性。<br>'),(3647,'foreigner','','','','foreigners','n. 外国人',' He never met a foreigner who spoke such perfect Chinese.<br>     他从未见过中国话讲得这样纯正的外国人。<br>\n His broken English showed he was a foreigner.<br>     他的蹩脚的英语说明他是一个外国人。<br>'),(3648,'foreman','','','','foremen','n. 领班,工头,陪审长',' The foreman is supervising their work.<br>     领班正在检查他们的工作。<br>\n He was deemed as guilty by the foreman.<br>     陪审长认为他有罪。<br>'),(3649,'foremost','','','','','a. 最初的<br>\nad. 在最前面',' Do you know who is the foremost writer in the English language?<br>     你知道谁是最重要的英语作家吗？<br>\n He does a bit of writing, but first and foremost he\'s a teacher.<br>     他也写一些文章, 但他主要是个教师.<br>'),(3650,'forerunner','','','','forerunners','n. 先驱',' Anglo-Saxon is the forerunner of modern English.<br>     盎格鲁撒克逊语是现代英语的先驱。<br>\n One that indicates or foreshadows what is to come; a forerunner.<br>     预言者指明或预示即将发生的事的人；先驱<br>'),(3651,'foresee','foresaw','foreseen','foreseeing','','v. 预见,预知',' He foresaw that his journey would be delayed by bad weather.<br>     他预知自己的旅程会被恶劣天气耽搁。<br>\n Do you foresee any problems with the new system?<br>     对于这种新体制，你看会有什么问题吗？<br>'),(3652,'forest','forested','forested','foresting','forests','n. 森林',' He lost his way in the forest.<br>     他在森林中迷路了。<br>\n The combustion in the forest generated great damage.<br>     森林火灾造成了巨大的损失。<br>'),(3653,'forestry','','','','','n. 林产,森林地',' Very little forestry is left unexplored nowadays.<br>     如今未经勘测的森林是少之又少了。<br>\n The covering of forestry in our town is 60 percent.<br>     我们镇的森林覆盖率是百分之六十。<br>'),(3654,'foretell','foretold','foretold','foretelling','','v. 预言,预告,预示',' The Messiah, as foretold by the prophets of the Old Testament.<br>     救世主《旧约》中的先知们预言的救世主<br>\n She claims to be psychic and to be able to foretell the future.<br>     她自称有特异功能, 能预知未来.<br>'),(3655,'forever','','','','','ad. 永远',' The lovers promised to be faithful forever.<br>     这对情人互相许诺永不变心。<br>\n You\'ll never see life if you stay at home forever.<br>     如果你一直呆在家里，就永远不会有生活经验。<br>'),(3656,'forfeit','forfeited','forfeited','forfeiting','forfeits','n. 没收物,罚金,丧失<br>\nv. 没收,丧失',' He who murders pays the forfeit of his life.<br>     杀人者偿命。<br>\n If man put his country in danger by helping the enemy, his life and possessions were forfeit to the crown.<br>     任何人如帮助敌人危害本国，他的生命财产便被国家没收。<br>'),(3657,'forge','','','','','n. 熔炉,铁工厂<br>\nv. 打制,想出,伪造',' They forged their manager\'s signature on the cheque.<br>     他们在支票上伪造了经理的签名。<br>\n The ship forged ahead under a favorable wind.<br>     船乘风快速前进。<br>'),(3658,'forgery','','','','forgeries','n. 伪造,伪造罪,伪造物',' He was sent to prison for forgery.<br>     他因犯伪造罪被关进监狱。<br>\n He confessed the letter a forgery.<br>     他承认那封信是伪造的。<br>'),(3659,'forget','forgot','forgotten','forgetting','','v. 忘记,忽略',' I\'m sorry; I\'ve forgotten your name.<br>     对不起，我忘了你的名字。<br>\n Don\'t forget your friends when you become rich.<br>     致富后不要忘了老朋友。<br>'),(3