二等于四。<br>\n Our cat has a litter of four kittens.<br>     我们家的猫一窝养了4只小猫。<br>'),(3705,'fourscore','','','','','a. 八十的,八十个的<br>\nn. 八十,八十个,八十岁',''),(3706,'fourteen','','','','fourteens','num. 十四',' His daughter is fourteen years old.<br>     他的女儿十四岁了。<br>\n The cultivator worked fourteen hours a day, laying by the corn.<br>     中耕机每天工作14小时，给玉米作最后一次中耕。<br>'),(3707,'fourth','','','','fourths','n. 四分之一<br>\nnum. 第四',' After her fourth child she decided to have herself sterilized.<br>     她生了第四个孩子后决定做绝育手术。<br>\n One fourth of a ton;500 pounds. Used as a measure of grain.<br>     五百磅四分之一吨；五百磅。用作谷物计量单位<br>'),(3708,'fowl','fowled','fowled','fowling','fowls','n. 家禽',' There are many kinds of fowl.<br>     家禽的种类很多。<br>\n A mixture of ground grain and nutrients fed to livestock and fowl.<br>     麦麸由谷糠和营养物质调成的混合物，用以饲养牲畜和家禽<br>'),(3709,'fox','foxed','foxed','foxing','foxes','n. 狐狸,狡猾的人<br>\nv. 奸狡地行动',' Don\'t trust him, he is a sly old fox.<br>     别相信他，他像老狐狸一样狡猾。<br>\n The fox ran away before the hunter shot it.<br>     那只狐狸在猎人向它射击前跑掉了。<br>'),(3710,'fps','','','','','frames per second 帧数',''),(3711,'fractal','','','','','分形',''),(3712,'fraction','','','','fractions','n. 分数,小部分,破片',' One forth is a proper fraction.<br>     四分之一是一个真分数。<br>\n The door opened a fraction.<br>     门稍微开了条缝。<br>'),(3713,'fractional','','','','','a. 微少的,断片的,分数的',' Speech is fractional; silence is integral.<br>     讲话是分数；沉默是整数。<br>'),(3714,'fracture','fractured','fractured','fracturing','fractures','n. 破碎,骨折<br>\nv. 破碎,破裂',' Her leg fractured in two places.<br>     她的腿有两处骨折。<br>\n Fracture of the leg can be very serious in old people.<br>     老年人腿骨骨折有可能成为严重疾患。<br>'),(3715,'fragile','','','','','a. 易碎的,脆的',' He\'s feeling a bit fragile after last night\'s party.<br>     他参加了昨晚的聚会之后，现在觉得有些虚弱。<br>\n This glass plate is very fragile.<br>     这个玻璃盘子很容易碎。<br>'),(3716,'fragility','','','','','n. 脆弱,虚弱',''),(3717,'fragment','fragmented','fragmented','fragmenting','fragments','n. 碎片,破片,断片<br>\n[计算机] 碎片',' The interruption fragmented his argument.<br>     他的辩论因被打断而显得不完整。<br>\n She dropped the vase on the floor and it broke into fragments.<br>     她把花瓶掉在地上，摔成了碎片。<br>'),(3718,'fragmentation','','','','','分裂,破碎,存储残片','');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (3719,'fragmenting','','','','','分割',' A rock fragment between4 and64 millimeters(0.16 and2.51 inches) in diameter, especially one that has been naturally rounded.<br>     水晶石石英断片，直径4到64毫米（0。16到2。51英寸），尤指天然圆形的石英颗粒<br>\n She dropped the vase on the floor and it broke into fragments.<br>     她把花瓶掉在地上，摔成了碎片。<br>'),(3720,'fragrance','','','','fragrances','n. 香味',' I can smell the fragrance of flowers after showers.<br>     我可以闻到雨后鲜花的清香。<br>\n The rose sends out strong fragrance.<br>     玫瑰散发出浓郁的香味。<br>'),(3721,'fragrant','','','','','a. 芬香的,馥郁的,愉快的',' The air in the garden was warm and fragrant.<br>     花园里的空气一片温馨。<br>\n The flowers gave off a fragrant odor.<br>     花发出一阵幽香。<br>'),(3722,'frail','','','','','a. 脆弱的,虚弱的',' The frail wooden bridge cracked.<br>     这座不牢固的木桥断裂了。<br>\n I accept that he\'s old and frail; be that as it may, he\'s still a good politician.<br>     我承认他年老体衰，然而尽管如此，他仍是优秀的政治家。<br>'),(3723,'frame','framed','framed','framing','frames','n. 框,结构,骨架<br>\nv. 构成,设计,陷害',' The government is framing a new bill to control gambling.<br>     政府在制定新的法案以控制赌博。<br>\n This athlete has a powerful frame.<br>     这位运动员有着魁梧的体格。<br>'),(3724,'framework','','','','frameworks','n. 结构,构架,框架',' It\'s a bridge of steel framework.<br>     那是座钢铁结构的桥梁。<br>\n All the cases can be considered within the framework of the existing rules.<br>     一切情况都可依据现行章程的结构加以考虑。<br>'),(3725,'framing','','','','','成帧',' The government is framing a new bill to control gambling.<br>     政府在制定新的法案以控制赌博。<br>\n In a silver frame on the table there is a photograph of her husband.<br>     在桌上的银相框里有张她丈夫的照片。<br>'),(3726,'France','','','','','n. 法国',' Paris is the capital of France.<br>     巴黎是法国的首都。<br>\n Britain\'s nearest neighbour is France.<br>     英国最近的邻居是法国。<br>'),(3727,'franchise','franchised','franchised','franchising','franchises','n. 特权, 公民权<br>\nv. 赋予特权, 赋予公民权',' He runs his sandwich chain as a franchise operation.<br>     作为一种给予特许专营权业务，他经营三明治连锁店。<br>\n That fast food business have expanded through the sale of franchise.<br>     该快餐店通过出售联营经销权而扩大了生意。<br>'),(3728,'franchisee','','','','','n. 特许经营人',''),(3729,'franchiser','','','','','n. 给别人经营联营特许权的公司或制造厂',''),(3730,'frank','franked','franked','franking','','a. 坦白的,直率的',' To be very frank, I think you have very little chance of getting the job.<br>     坦白地说，我认为你获得这项工作的机会微乎其微。<br>\n He is an extremely frank person.<br>     他是个极其老实的人。<br>'),(3731,'franking','','','','','打印标记',' The Senate started on the right fool. In1986, it limited its franking budget to half the total appropriation for both chambers. That seemed fair because the100 senators represent the same total number of constituents as the435 House members.<br>     参院走出了正确的第一步。1986年把参院的免费邮件预算限制在参众两院该项预算总和的半数。100位参议员与435位众议员的选民人数一样，所以看来这是公平的做法。<br>\n A collector of antique cars asked Frank to look out for a1906 gas head lamp.<br>     一位老式汽车收藏家要弗兰克留神1906年产的煤气前灯。<br>'),(3732,'frankly','','','','','ad. 坦白地',' Quite frankly, I\'m not surprised.<br>     坦白地说，我并不感到意外。<br>\n I feel it my duty to speak frankly to you.<br>     我觉得我有义务要坦白地对你说。<br>'),(3733,'frantic','','','','','a. 疯狂的,狂乱的',' She was frantic with worry.<br>     她愁得要命。<br>\n The child\'s parents were frantic when she did not return home on time.<br>     那孩子没有按时回家，她父母都要急疯了。<br>'),(3734,'fraud','','','','frauds','n. 骗子,欺骗,诈欺',' This hair-tonic is a fraud; I\'m as bald as ever.<br>     这生发剂是骗人的玩艺，我还是和以前一样秃。<br>\n She went through the company\'s accounts, looking for evidence of fraud.<br>     她仔细审核公司的帐目, 查找欺骗作弊的证据.<br>'),(3735,'fraught','','','','','a. 充满的',' The expedition through the jungle was fraught with difficulties and danger.<br>     穿越森林的探险充满了艰辛和危险。<br>\n The expedition into the jungle was fraught with danger.<br>     到原始森林去探险充满了危险。<br>'),(3736,'freak','','','','freaks','n. 怪人,怪事,反复无常<br>\na. 奇异的',' People think she\'s a freak just because she\'s religious.<br>     就因为她信教，人们就把她当成怪物。<br>\n He was really confused by the freak result.<br>     这个异乎寻常的结果让他非常困惑。<br>'),(3737,'free','freed','freed','freeing','','a. 自由的,大方的,免费的<br>\nv. 释放,解放<br>\nad. 自由地,免费',' The prisoners wish to be free again.<br>     囚犯们希望重获自由。<br>\n Don\'t run free on the main street.<br>     别在大街上乱跑。<br>'),(3738,'freedom','','','','freedoms','n. 自由',' I\'m old enough to have the freedom to do as I like.<br>     我已经足够大了，有权去做我喜欢做的事。<br>\n The people there are fighting to gain their freedom from foreign control.<br>     那里的人民正在为摆脱外国统治争取自由而战斗。<br>'),(3739,'freely','','','','','ad. 自由地(免费地,直率地,大量地)',' These goods are freely available.<br>     这些商品大量供应。<br>\n Let us discuss such things as we can talk it freely.<br>     让我们讨论一些咱们可以自由谈论的事吧。<br>'),(3740,'freeze','froze','frozen','freezing','','v. 冻结,冷动,僵硬<br>\n[计算机] 冻结',' Water freezes at the temperature of 0 degrees Celsius.<br>     水在摄氏零度结冰。<br>\n The thief froze when he heard the footsteps approaching.<br>     小偷听到走近的脚步声，吓得呆住了。<br>'),(3741,'freezer','','','','','n. 冰库,冰箱,冷冻库',' There\'s always the food in the freezer if need be.<br>     需要食物的话, 冰箱里就有.<br>\n \"Just one more heave, and the freezer will be in the right place.\"<br>     ＂只要再拉一下，冰箱准能放到合适的位置上。＂<br>'),(3742,'freight','freighted','freighted','freighting','','n. 船货,运费,货运<br>\nv. 装货,运送',' This freight must be carefully handled.<br>     这些货物必须小心搬运。<br>\n They freighted the boat with bananas.<br>     他们把香蕉装上船。<br>'),(3743,'French','','','','','a. 法国(人)的,法语的<br>\nn. 法语',' This student is good at French.<br>     这个学生法语好。<br>\n Do you like French films?<br>     你喜欢法国影片吗？<br>'),(3744,'Frenchman','','','','Frenchmen','n. 法国人',' It is said that Frenchmen are among the most romantic people in the world.<br>     据说法国人是世界上最浪漫的民族之一。<br>\n It is said that the Frenchman may be the best gardener in the world.<br>     据说法国人是世界上最好的园丁。<br>'),(3745,'frequency','','','','frequencies','n.&a. 频繁,频率',' Accidents on that highway are happening with increasing frequency.<br>     那条高速公路上车祸发生得越来越频繁。<br>\n He varied the transmission frequency.<br>     他变换了无线电传送的频率。<br>'),(3746,'frequent','frequented','frequented','frequenting','','a. 经常的,频繁的<br>\nvt. 常到,常去',' He is a frequent visitor to our house.<br>     他是我们家的常客。<br>\n These woods are frequented by all kinds of birds.<br>     这些树林里经常栖息着各种鸟类。<br>'),(3747,'frequently','','','','','ad. 经常地,频繁地',' He comes to visit me frequently.<br>     他经常来看我。<br>\n Many times; frequently.<br>     经常地多次地；频繁地<br>'),(3748,'fresh','','','','','a. 新鲜的,无经验的,淡(水)的',' Open the window and let in some fresh air.<br>     打开窗户，让新鲜的空气进来。<br>\n You can buy fresh vegetables in the market.<br>     你可以在市场上买到新鲜的蔬菜。<br>'),(3749,'freshen','freshened','freshened','freshening','','vt. 使...变新鲜(去咸味,风变强)',' Can I freshen your drink?<br>     我再给你添些酒好吗?<br>\n I\'ll just go and freshen (myself) up before the interview.<br>     我这就去梳洗打扮一番再去会面.<br>'),(3750,'freshman','','','','freshmen','n. 大学一年级学生',' Proctor(exceedingly angry):\"So you confess that this unfortunate freshman was carried to this frog pond and drenched?\"<br>     学监（非常生气）：“现在你承认这可怜的新生被扔进这蛙池里浑身湿透？”<br>\n It\'s important for the college freshman to keep his nose clean.<br>     对大学新生而言洁身自好是很重要的。<br>'),(3751,'fret','','','','','n. 烦躁,磨损,焦急<br>\nv. 烦恼,不满,磨损',' You are fretting yourself needlessly.<br>     你是在不必要地折磨自己。<br>\n Babies often fret (themselves) when their mothers are not near.<br>     婴儿常常因母亲不在身边而哭闹.<br>'),(3752,'friction','','','','frictions','n. 摩擦,摩擦力',' Friction against the rock, combined with the weight of the climber, caused his rope to break.<br>     与岩石之间的摩擦加上攀登者的重量，使得绳子断了。<br>\n My daughter and son always have frictions.<br>     我女儿和儿子总发生矛盾。<br>'),(3753,'Friday','','','','','n. 星期五',' He comes to visit his aged parents after work on every Friday.<br>     每个星期五下班后，他去看望年迈的父母。<br>\n It\'s Friday.<br>     今天星期五。<br>'),(3754,'fridge','','','','','n. 电冰箱',' The butter will soften out of the fridge.<br>     黄油从冰箱中取出会变软.<br>\n If there\'s any food (left) over, put it in the fridge.<br>     食物要是剩下就放进冰箱里.<br>'),(3755,'friend','friended','friended','friending','friends','n. 朋友',' A friend in need is a friend indeed.<br>     患难之交才是真朋友。<br>\n Our friend from china will now tell us about her research.<br>     现在我们的中国朋友要向大家介绍她自己的研究情况。<br>'),(3756,'friendly','','','','','a. 友好的',' He was not very friendly to us.<br>     他对我们不太友善。<br>\n Manchester United beat Celtic in a friendly.<br>     曼彻斯特联队在一场友谊比赛中击败了凯尔特队。<br>'),(3757,'friends','','','','','n. 朋友们',' My friends and I went to the park together on a cloudless day.<br>     在一个晴朗的天气里，我和朋友们一起去公园。<br>\n Please hand on the magazine to your friends.<br>     请把这本杂志传给你的朋友们看。<br>'),(3758,'friendship','','','','friendships','n. 友谊,友好',' Real friendship is more valuable than money.<br>     真正的友谊比金钱更宝贵。<br>\n Take this ring as a pledge of our friendship.<br>     请接受这个戒指作为我们友谊的信物。<br>'),(3759,'fright','frighted','frighted','frighting','frights','n. 惊骇,吃惊',' He gave me a fright by bursting into a sudden laughter.<br>     他突然大笑起来，吓了我一跳。<br>\n The horse took a fright at the sound of the explosion.<br>     马听到爆炸声受了惊。<br>'),(3760,'frighten','frightened','frightened','frightening','','v. 使惊吓,惊恐',' He frightened the old man into giving him all the money.<br>     他恐吓那位老人把所有的钱都给了他。<br>\n The little baby was frightened by the fierce dog.<br>     那个小孩被恶狗吓坏了。<br>'),(3761,'frightening','','','','','a. 令人恐惧的, 引起突然惊恐的',' The magnitude of the epidemic was frightening.<br>     这种流行病传播范围之广令人惶惶不安。<br>\n The jet zoomed low over the houses, frightening everyone.<br>     那架喷气式飞机低飞掠过房顶, 隆隆声把大家吓了一跳.<br>'),(3762,'frightful','','','','','a. 可怕的',' These frightful experiences are branded on his memory.<br>     这些可怕的经历深深印入他的记忆。<br>\n An old woman considered ugly or frightful.<br>     老丑婆一个被认为是丑陋或可怕的老妇人<br>'),(3763,'fringe','fringed','fringed','fringing','fringes','n. 边缘,端<br>\nv. 加饰边于',' A fringe of trees stood round the pool.<br>     池塘四周耸立着一圈树木。<br>\n The estate was fringed with stately elms.<br>     那片地以挺拔的榆树为边界。<br>'),(3764,'frivolous','','','','','a. 轻佻的,妄动的,琐碎的',' She thought that reading romantic novels was a frivolous way of spending her time.<br>     她认为看浪漫小说是虚度时光。<br>\n At 18, he\'s still rather frivolous and needs to grow up.<br>     他到了十八岁仍然很不懂事，很不成熟。<br>'),(3765,'fro','','','','','ad. 向那边,向后',' He is walking to and fro in the room.<br>     他在房间内踱来踱去。<br>\n Trucks shuttled to and fro on the high ways.<br>     车辆在高速公路上穿梭行驶。<br>'),(3766,'frock','','','','frocks','n. 罩袍,僧衣',' This monk wears a gray frock.<br>     这个和尚穿着灰色的僧袍。<br>\n Her frock came from Paris, but she wears them with a strong English accent.<br>     她的罩袍来自巴黎，可是她简直把它们穿成了英国式（的样子）。<br>'),(3767,'frog','','','','frogs','n. 蛙',' The frog jumped away.<br>     青蛙跳走了。<br>\n The frog in the well knows nothing of the great ocean.<br>     【谚】井底之蛙，所见不广。<br>'),(3768,'from','','','','','prep. 从,从...起',' The sky slowly changed from blue to red.<br>     天空慢慢由蓝色变为红色。<br>\n The train starts from Beijing.<br>     这辆火车从北京开出。<br>'),(3769,'front','fronted','fronted','fronting','fronts','n. 前面,开头,前线<br>\nv. 面对,朝向,对付',' The front of the postcard shows a picture of our hotel.<br>     明信片正面是我们旅馆的图片。<br>\n Write your name on the front cover of the exercise book.<br>     在练习簿的封面上写上你的名字。<br>'),(3770,'frontier','','','','frontiers','n. 边界,边境',' The frontiers of medical knowledge are being pushed forwards as time goes on.<br>     医学知识的新领域正随着时间向前推进。<br>\n Sweden has frontiers with Norway and Finland.<br>     瑞典与挪威和芬兰接壤。<br>'),(3771,'frost','frosted','frosted','frosting','frosts','n. 霜,冰冻,冷漠<br>\nv. 覆着霜,冻结,结霜',' The cold has frosted the windows.<br>     寒冷的天气使窗子上结满了霜。<br>\n The grass was covered with frost in the early morning.<br>     清晨，草上覆盖着一层白霜。<br>'),(3772,'frosty','','','','','a. 下霜的,严寒的,冷淡的',' Frosty windows make great surfaces for children to draw on.<br>     有霜的窗户是孩子们画画的好地方。<br>\n The air was frosty.<br>     天气严寒。<br>'),(3773,'frown','frowned','frowned','frowning','frowns','n. 皱眉<br>\nv. 皱眉头',' The teacher frowned angrily at the noisy class.<br>     老师对那班吵吵嚷嚷的学生皱起了眉头。<br>\n The frown on the man\'s face showed that he was displeased.<br>     那人皱着眉头