el for his speech.<br>     报纸上的这篇文章为他的演讲提供了启发。<br>'),(3784,'fulfil','fulfilled','fulfilled','fulfilling','','v. 实践,履行实行,尽',' In spite of all the difficulties, we fulfilled our task ahead of schedule.<br>     尽管有许多困难，我们还是提前完成了任务。<br>\n Jim sets every girl he meets on a pedestal and ten blames them unfairly when they don\'t fulfil his expectations.<br>     吉姆把他遇到的每一个女孩都看得完美无缺，然后当她们不如他所望时他便不公平地责备她们。<br>'),(3785,'fulfill','fulfilled','fulfilled','fulfilling','','v. 完成,履行<br>\nvt. 履行,完成',' Does your job fulfill your expectations?<br>     你的工作符合你的期望吗？<br>\n You must fulfill your promise.<br>     你必须履行诺言。<br>'),(3786,'full','fulled','fulled','fulling','','n. 全部,十分<br>\na. 充满的,完全的,丰富的<br>\nad. 完全地,整整<br>\n[计算机] 全',' The roses are in full bloom.<br>     玫瑰花盛开了。<br>\n They knew full well that he wouldn\'t keep his promise.<br>     他们很清楚地知道他不会遵守诺言。<br>'),(3787,'fully','','','','','ad. 十分地,完全地,全',' I don\'t fully understand his reasons for leaving.<br>     我不完全理解他离开的理由。<br>\n These rosebuds haven\'t fully opened.<br>     这些蔷薇花蕾还没有完全开放。<br>'),(3788,'fumble','fumbled','fumbled','fumbling','fumbles','n. 摸索,漏接<br>\nv. 摸索,摸弄,笨拙的处理',' She fumbled about in her handbag for a pen.<br>     她在手提袋中搜寻钢笔。<br>\n She is fumbling the light switch.<br>     她正找电灯开关。<br>'),(3789,'fume','fumed','fumed','fuming','fumes','n. 臭气,烟,激怒<br>\nv. 熏,冒烟',' He fumed at the delay.<br>     他对耽搁感到愤怒。<br>\n The burnt heaps of wood were still fuming.<br>     燃烧的木堆仍在冒着烟。<br>'),(3790,'fun','funned','funned','funning','','n. 乐趣,玩笑,有趣的人或事物',' People make fun of her because she always speaks foolishly.<br>     人们嘲笑她，因为她常说傻话。<br>\n You\'ll sure to have fun at the party tonight.<br>     你在今晚的晚会上一定会玩得很开心。<br>'),(3791,'function','functioned','functioned','functioning','functions','n. 功能,函数,重大聚会<br>\nvi. 运行,起作用',' The minister has to attend all kinds of functions.<br>     部长必须参加各种集会。<br>\n The function of an adjective is to describe or add to the meaning of a noun.<br>     形容词的作用是描述或增加名词的意思。<br>'),(3792,'functional','','','