ring','furs','n. 毛皮,皮,皮子',' The dog\'s fur was matted with blood.<br>     那只狗的毛皮上沾有血迹。<br>\n She was wearing a silver fox fur across her shoulders.<br>     她肩上披了一件银狐皮披肩。<br>'),(3802,'furious','','','','','a. 狂怒的,猛烈的',' There was a furious knock at the door.<br>     有人在猛烈地敲门。<br>\n After receiving the insulting letter, he became furious.<br>     他收到辱骂信后怒不可遏。<br>'),(3803,'furnace','','','','','n. 炉子,熔炉',' This room is like a furnace.<br>     这屋子热得象火炉一样。<br>\n A furnace that manufactures producer gas.<br>     煤气发生炉制造发生炉煤气的炉子<br>'),(3804,'furnish','furnished','furnished','furnishing','','v. 供给,提供,装设',' The shop furnishes everything that is needed for camping.<br>     这家商店供应各种野营用品。<br>\n They are renting a furnished flat.<br>     他们租用了一套带有家具的公寓房子。<br>'),(3805,'furniture','','','','','n. 家具',' We will buy some furniture for our new house.<br>     我们得给我们的新房子买些家具。<br>\n This old table is a valuable piece of furniture.<br>     这张旧桌子是一件很珍贵的家具。<br>'),(3806,'furrow','furrowed','furrowed','furrowing','furrows','n. 犁沟,皱纹<br>\nv. 犁,耕,弄绉',' The country roads were muddy and full of furrows left by farm carts.<br>     乡间道路泥泞不堪，布满了牛车压出的车辙。<br>\n A furrow or groove formed by running water.<br>     犁沟由流水形成的槽或小沟<br>'),(3807,'further','furthered','furthered','furthering','','a. 更远的<br>\nad. 此外,进一步地<br>\nv. 促进,推动<br>\nvt. 促进',' I was too tired to walk any further.<br>     我累得再也走不动了。<br>\n This house is not large enough for us, and further, it is too far from the town.<br>     这栋房子对我们来说不够大，而且离城太远了。<br>'),(3808,'furthermore','','','','','ad. 而且,此外',' The house isn\'t big enough for me, and furthermore, it\'s too far from the town.<br>     这栋房子不够我们住，而且，它离市区太远。<br>\n Furthermore, he informs Elizabeth, Wickham had been carrying on an intrigue with Darcy\'s sister Georgiana.<br>     而且，他还告诉伊丽莎白，韦翰过去一直同他妹妹乔治亚娜有私通关系。<br>'),(3809,'furthest','','','','','ad.&a. 最远',' Our house is the furthest away.<br>     我们的房屋是离这里最远的一座。<br>\n That\'s the furthest thing from my mind. They explored the furthest reaches of space.<br>     我只能想这么多了。他们在太空探险到最遥远的地方<br>'),(3810,'fury','','','','furies','n. 愤怒,狂暴,狂怒的人<br>\nn. 复仇女神',' In a fury, she could not speak.<br>     她气得连话也说不出来。<br>\n In my fury, I dashed all the dishes to the floor.<br>     气愤之下，我把所有的杯盘都摔到地上去了。<br>'),(3811,'fuse','','','','','n. 保险丝<br>\nv. 融化,融合',' The fuse-box is in the kitchen.<br>     保险丝盒子在厨房里。<br>\n Lead will fuse at quite a low temperature.<br>     铅会在相当低的温度下熔化。<br>'),(3812,'fusing','','','','','熔化,点火,发射,起动',' Lead will fuse at quite a low temperature.<br>     铅会在相当低的温度下熔化。<br>\n The tube was sealed off by fusing the material together.<br>     管子以熔合管端的方法封闭起来了。<br>'),(3813,'fusion','','','','fusions','n. 融合物,结合,融合',' Americans are the fusion of many different races.<br>     美国人是各种种族人的熔合体。<br>\n Brass is formed by the fusion of copper and zinc.<br>     黄铜是由铜和锌熔合制成的。<br>'),(3814,'fuss','fussed','fussed','fussing','','n. 大惊小怪,小题大作<br>\nv. 无事自扰,焦急,焦燥',' There is sure to be a fuss when my parents find the window is broken.<br>     我父母发现窗子被打破后，一定会有一番斥责。<br>\n Don\'t make so much fuss over losing a pen.<br>     别为了丢失一支笔就这样大惊小怪。<br>'),(3815,'fussy','','','','','a. 爱挑剔的,难取悦的,易烦恼的',' Some girls like fussy dresses.<br>     有些女孩喜欢讲究的衣服。<br>\n Are you fussy about what you wear?<br>     你介意自己的穿着吗？<br>'),(3816,'futile','','','','','a. 无效的,无用的',' What a futile remark!<br>     纯属废话!<br>\n He made a futile exercise.<br>     他做了一次无效的练习。<br>'),(3817,'future','','','','futures','a. 将来的<br>\nn. 将来,未来<br>\nn. 期货',' I wish you a very happy future.<br>     我祝你有非常幸福的未来。<br>\n We will meet in Beijing in the near future.<br>     在不久的将来，我们将在北京见面。<br>'),(3818,'futures','','','','','n. 期货',' Generally speaking, futures contract, not the commodity, is sold and bought in the futures market.<br>     一般来说，在期货市场上买进卖出的是期货契约，而不是商品。<br>\n Silver: quiet. Value fluctuate lower in line with other precious metals on both bullion and futures market.<br>     银：清淡。由于受最近交易低潮的影响，银和其他贵重金属一样，期货和现货市场的数量下降。<br>'),(3819,'G','','','','','giga 千兆',''),(3820,'gage','','','','','n. 抵押品(吃水)<br>\nvt 以...做抵押',' It\'s a rain gage.<br>     这是一个测雨器。<br>\n Poor Bill, all his things are at gage.<br>     可怜的比尔，他所有的东西都当掉了。<br>'),(3821,'gaily','','','','','ad. 华丽地,欢乐地',' They gaily went on talking after the film had started.<br>     电影开演后，他们还在毫无顾忌地讲话。<br>\n He rattled away gaily.<br>     他快活地喋喋而言。<br>'),(3822,'gain','gained','gained','gaining','gains','n. 增益,获得,利润<br>\nv. 得到,增进,获利',' No pain, no gain.<br>     一分耕耘,一分收获。<br>\n He has gained rich experience in these years.<br>     这些年来，他取得了丰富的经验。<br>'),(3823,'gainful','','','','','a. 有利益的(唯利是图的)',''),(3824,'gainsay','gainsaid','gainsaid','gainsaying','','v. 否认',''),(3825,'gait','','','','gaits','n. 步态',' The man walked along with an unsteady gait.<br>     那人脚步不稳地向前走去。<br>\n He is awkward in his gait.<br>     他的步态不雅观。<br>'),(3826,'gal','','','','','n. 重力加速度单位伽(加仑)',''),(3827,'gala','','','','galas','n. 祭日,节日,祝贺',' Thanksgiving in the United States is partly a religious festival, and partly a gala day.<br>     感恩节在美国，一部分是宗教的节日，一部分是狂欢的节日。<br>\n People stood at every coign of vantage on both sides of the road to watch the gala parade.<br>     人们站在大路两边每个便于观看的地点来观看节日游行。<br>'),(3828,'galactic','','','','','a. 星系的,银河系的',''),(3829,'Galapagos','','','','','加拉帕戈斯',''),(3830,'galaxy','','','','galaxies','n. 银河,一群显赫之人',' A galaxy of film stars attended the premiere.<br>     一群影星参加了首次公演。<br>\n There may be millions of worlds in the Milky Way Galaxy.<br>     银河系中也许有几百万个世界。<br>'),(3831,'gale','','','','','n. 狂风,大风',' The ship lost her masts in the gale.<br>     这船的桅樯被强风吹断了。<br>\n The gale blustered all night.<br>     大风刮了一夜。<br>'),(3832,'Galileo','','','','','n. 伽利略',' It didn\'t make much sense to Galileo to have different rules for motion on earth and in space.<br>     对伽利略来说，地球上和太空中有不同的运动法则是没有多大意义。<br>\n Galileo demonstrated that objects of different weights fall at the same speed.<br>     伽利略证实不同重量的物体落下的速度相同。<br>'),(3833,'gall','','','','','n. 胆囊,胆汁,苦味<br>\nv. 烦恼,屈辱,磨伤',' He had the gall to sue