eir children.<br>     他们应少到各处游荡, 多用些时间照看子女.<br>'),(3843,'gallon','','','','gallons','n. 加仑',' He added 2 gallons of fuel to his car.<br>     他给汽车加了2加仑油。<br>\n The imperial gallon is not the same as the US gallon.<br>     英制的加仑和与美制的容量不同。<br>'),(3844,'gallop','galloped','galloped','galloping','gallops','n. 疾驰,飞奔<br>\nv. 飞驰,急速进行,急急忙忙的说',' He rode off at a gallop.<br>     他骑马疾驰而去。<br>\n He galloped the horse along the track.<br>     他沿跑道策马疾驰。<br>'),(3845,'gallows','','','','gallows','n. [常作单数]绞刑架',' The murderer was sentenced to the gallows.<br>     杀人犯被判处绞刑。<br>\n Save a thief from gallows and he will help hang you.<br>     你救盗匪下绞架，盗匪送你上绞架。<br>'),(3846,'galore','','','','','a. 丰富的',' Bargains galore!<br>     备有丰富之特价品。<br>'),(3847,'galvanize','galvanized','galvanized','galvanizing','','v. 通电,镀锌；激励',' The manager\'s arrival galvanized the workers into activity.<br>     经理一来, 工人闻风而动.<br>\n How can we galvanize the students into taking the responsibility for their work?<br>     我们怎样才能激励学生对他们的作业负起责任来呢？<br>'),(3848,'Gambia','','','','','n. 甘比亚',''),(3849,'gambit','','','','','n. 以取得优势的开局棋法,开始,话题',' His opening gambit at the debate is a direct attack on government policy.<br>     他在辩论中的策略是先直接抨击政府的政策。<br>\n Peter\'s usual opening gambit is to buy a girl a drink, so that she immediately thinks she owes him something.<br>     彼得通常先是为姑娘买一杯饮料，这样她就马上认为自己欠了他什么。<br>'),(3850,'gamble','gambled','gambled','gambling','gambles','n. 冒险<br>\nv. 赌博,孤注一掷',' He gambled all his winnings on the last race.<br>     他把赢得的钱全都压在最后一场赛马上了。<br>\n The company took a gamble by cutting the price of their products.<br>     公司冒险将产品削价出售。<br>'),(3851,'gambler','','','','','n. 赌徒',' By crafts the gambler tricked them out of all their money.<br>     那个赌徒用诡计赢去了他们所有的钱。<br>\n Money easily finds its way into other hands, if you are a gambler.<br>     如果你嗜赌，钱财很容易落入他人之手。<br>'),(3852,'gambling','','','','','n. 赌博,投机',' The government is framing a new bill to control gambling.<br>     政府在制定新的法案以控制赌博。<br>\n He spends all