over by a gang of thugs after a football match.<br>     他在足球比赛结束以後受到一帮暴徒的殴打。<br>'),(3862,'gangling','','','','','a. 瘦长得难看的',''),(3863,'ganglion','','','','ganglions','n. 节,神经节',''),(3864,'gangster','','','','gangsters','n. 匪徒,歹徒',' These gangsters have been extinguished by the police.<br>     这群匪徒已被警方消灭。<br>\n The gangster killed the only witness to his crime, on the principle that dead men tell no tales.<br>     因为死人是不会告密的，所以那歹徒把他犯罪的唯一见证人杀害了。<br>'),(3865,'gangway','','','','gangways','n. (上下船的)跳板',' Please clear the gangway, thanks for your cooperation.<br>     请别堵住通道，谢谢各位合作。<br>\n Seeing him out of the plane and down the gangway gave me a lump in my throat.<br>     看着他从飞机中出来，走下舷梯，我激动得哽咽起来。<br>'),(3866,'Ganymede','','','','','[希神]Zeus 带去为众神司酒的美少年',''),(3867,'gaol','gaoled','gaoled','gaoling','gaols','n. 监狱<br>\nv. 监禁 [=jail]<br>\nvt. 使...坐牢',' Strikes by prison officers underline the need for reform in our gaols.<br>     监狱工作人员罢工一事，突出地表明我们的监狱制度需要改革。<br>\n Since he escaped from gaol, Tom has been living on a razor\'s edge, terrified of recapture.<br>     汤姆越狱後, 时时如惊弓之鸟, 生怕再次被捕.<br>'),(3868,'gaoler','','','','','n. 监狱长,看守',''),(3869,'gap','gapped','gapped','gapping','gaps','n. (意见、个性等的)差异,缝隙,漏洞,缺口<br>\n嘉普(财富500强公司之一，总部所在地美国,主要经营服装零售)',' The road goes through a gap in the hills.<br>     这条路穿过两条山脉之间的峡谷。<br>\n There is a generation gap between my parents and I.<br>     我父母和我之间有代沟。<br>'),(3870,'gape','gaped','gaped','gaping','gapes','n. 裂口,张嘴<br>\nv. 裂开,张嘴',' She gaped at the tall man, not believing that he was her younger brother.<br>     她张嘴呆看着那个高个子，不相信他就是她的弟弟。<br>\n Dont gape : its rude!<br>     别张著嘴傻瞪著, 太不礼貌了!<br>'),(3871,'gappy','','','','','a. 裂缝多的',''),(3872,'garage','garaged','garaged','garaging','garages','n. 车库,汽车修理厂<br>\nvt. 把...放入车库',' He sent his car to the garage for repair.<br>     他把汽车送到修车厂修理。<br>\n We can\'t afford a car, not to mention the fact that we have no garage.<br>     我们买不起汽车，没有车库的事就更不必说了。<br>'),(3873,'garbage','','','','','n. 垃圾',' She threw th