ust freaked out and shot ten people.<br>     这个平时温和的家伙简直发疯了, 开枪打死了十个人.<br>\n What a downer that guy is!<br>     那家伙多让人泄气呀!<br>'),(4136,'gym','','','','gyms','n. 健身房,体育馆',' We go to play badminton in the nearest gym every Sunday.<br>     每个星期天我们都去最近的体育馆打羽毛球。<br>\n The basketball players are working out at the gym.<br>     篮球运动员们正在体育馆进行训练。<br>'),(4137,'gymnasium','','','','gymnasiums','n. 体育馆,健身房',' A new gymnasium has been built on our campus.<br>     我们大学的校园里新建了一座体育馆。<br>\n The child somersaulted across the gymnasium.<br>     那孩子翻著跟头从体育馆这头翻到那头.<br>'),(4138,'gymnast','','','','','n. 体操运动员',' She has the lithe grace of a gymnast.<br>     她有体操运动员轻盈而优美的体态。<br>\n The gymnast extended her arms horizontally.<br>     那女子体操运动员双臂平伸.<br>'),(4139,'gymnastics','','','','gymnastics','n.&a. 体操',' I don\'t like gymnastics.<br>     我不喜欢体操。<br>\n The sport of gymnastics is popular in our country.<br>     体操运动在我国很流行。<br>'),(4140,'gypsy','','','','','n. 吉布赛人,吉布赛语,像吉布赛的人',' The gypsy earned her money as a fortune-teller.<br>     这个吉普赛人以算命谋生。<br>\n I\'ve never lived in one place too long, it must be the Gypsy in me.<br>     我从来没有在一个地方长住过，一定是我性格中有吉普赛人的特性。<br>'),(4141,'habit','','','','habits','n. 习惯',' My colleague has broken off the habit of smoking.<br>     我的同事已经戒掉了吸烟的习惯。<br>\n He is in the habit of rising early.<br>     他有早起的习惯。<br>'),(4142,'habitat','','','','habitats','n. (动植物的)产地,栖息地',' The polar bear\'s habitat is the icy waters of the Arctic.<br>     北极熊的栖息地是冰冷的北极海域。<br>\n The moth\'s habitat is being destroyed and it has nearly died out.<br>     这种蛾子因栖息地正受到破坏，几乎绝种了。<br>'),(4143,'habitual','','','','','a. 惯常的,习惯的',' His habitual place at the table was occupied by a stranger.<br>     他惯常坐在桌旁的位置被一个陌生人占据了。<br>\n My girlfriend and I are habitual cinema-goers.<br>     我和女友是电影院的常客。<br>'),(4144,'habitus','','','','habitus','n. 状态',''),(4145,'hack','','','','','n. 劈,砍,出租马车<br>\nv. 劈,砍,干咳',' He was hacking at a tree.<br>     他正在砍树。<br>\n The publisher paid his hacks low.<br>     出版商付给他雇佣的