nv. 支持,交给',' Please hand me that book.<br>     请把那本书递给我。<br>\n This clock has three hands.<br>     这块表有三个指针。<br>'),(4170,'handbag','','','','handbags','n. 手提包',' She foraged about in her handbag, but couldn\'t find her keys.<br>     她翻遍了手提包，就是找不到钥匙。<br>\n She extracted a small notebook from her handbag.<br>     她从手提包里取出了一个小笔记本。<br>'),(4171,'handbook','','','','handbooks','n. 手册,指南',' We bought a tourist handbook before going travelling.<br>     出去旅游前，我们先买了一本旅游手册。<br>\n A handbook of directions and other information, especially for travelers or tourists.<br>     旅游指南，参考手册载有说明或其他资料的手册，尤指为旅行者或观光者提供的<br>'),(4172,'handful','','','','handfuls','n. 少数,一把,棘手之事',' That child is quite a handful.<br>     那孩子很难管教。<br>\n We invited twenty people, but only a handful of them came.<br>     我们邀请了20 个人，但只来了寥寥数人。<br>'),(4173,'handicap','handicapped','handicapped','handicapping','handicaps','n. 障碍<br>\nv. 妨碍',' Deafness can be a serious handicap.<br>     耳聋算是严重的缺陷。<br>\n He was handicapped by lack of education.<br>     他因文化水平低而吃了亏。<br>'),(4174,'handicapped','','','','','n. 残疾人, 身体有缺陷的人<br>\na. 残废的',' He was handicapped by lack of education.<br>     他因文化水平低而吃了亏。<br>\n The social worker advised them to put their handicapped child into care.<br>     社会工作者建议他们将其残疾儿送到福利院去。<br>'),(4175,'handkerchief','','','','handkerchieves','n. 手帕',' Please pass me a piece of paper handkerchief.<br>     请递给我一张纸巾。<br>\n She embroidered her initials on the handkerchief.<br>     她把她姓名的起首字母绣在手帕上。<br>'),(4176,'handle','handled','handled','handling','handles','n. 柄,把手<br>\nv. 买卖,处理,操作',' Pick up the typewriter case by the handle.<br>     抓住把手，把打字机箱子拿起来。<br>\n We don\'t handle that sort of book.<br>     我们不经销那一类书。<br>'),(4177,'handler','','','','','处理程序',' He was returned full of enthusiasm for Handler College.<br>     归来时充满着对汉德勒学院的热情。<br>'),(4178,'handling','','','','','n. 处理<br>\na. 操作的<br>\nvbl. 操作<br>\n[计算机] 处理',' The minister was crucified by the press for his handling of the affair.<br>     部长对此事的处理方法受到新闻界的严厉批评。<br>\n The machine was rendered useless by unskillful handling.<br>     由于操作不熟练，机器给弄得没有用了。<br>'),(4179,'handout','','','','handouts','n. 散发材料(免费发给的新闻通报)',' The act of approaching someone for a loan or handout.<br>     向某人借款，要求施舍接近某人以获得贷款或施舍的行为<br>'),(4180,'handset','','','','','电话听筒,手机,手持机',''),(4181,'handshaking','','','','','握手',''),(4182,'handsome','','','','','a. 英俊的',' Her husband is a very handsome young man.<br>     她丈夫是一个非常英俊的年轻人。<br>\n Her bridegroom is a handsome young man.<br>     她的新郎是一个英俊的年轻人。<br>'),(4183,'handwriting','','','','','n. 笔迹,书法',' There is need for improvement in your handwriting.<br>     你的书法需要改进。<br>\n She astonished me with her beautiful handwriting.<br>     她以其秀丽的书法而使我惊异。<br>'),(4184,'handy','','','','','a. 方便的,手边的',' The shops are quite handy.<br>     商店就在附近。<br>\n A few more traveller\'s cheques may come in handy on the holiday.<br>     多带几张旅行支票，度假时会有用的。<br>'),(4185,'hang','hung','hung','hanging','','n. 悬挂,吊死<br>\nv. (hanged,hanged) 悬挂,绞死,逗留',' You may hang your coat on the hook.<br>     你可以把外套挂在钩子上。<br>\n He hanged himself in sorrow after his wife died.<br>     妻子死后，他因悲伤而自缢。<br>'),(4186,'hanger','','','','','n. 挂钩(钩子,悬挂者,悬杆,支架)',' A fighter plane is revving up on the hanger apron.<br>     飞机库前面停机坪上，一架战斗机正在起动。<br>\n One more thing, I also need a couple more of hangers.<br>     还有一件事，我还需要两三个衣架。<br>'),(4187,'haphazard','','','','','a. 偶然的<br>\nad. 杂乱的(地),任意的(地)',' It is just a thing done at haphazard.<br>     这只是件偶然为之的事情。<br>'),(4188,'happen','happened','happened','happening','','v. 发生<br>\nvi. 发生,碰巧',' The accident happened at six o\'clock.<br>     事故发生在六点钟。<br>\n I happened to see her yesterday.<br>     我昨天碰巧见到她。<br>'),(4189,'happening','','','','happenings','n. 事件',' Happening by a fortunate accident or chance.<br>     幸运地发生的因某种幸运事件或机会而发生的<br>\n What\'s happening?<br>     近来怎么样?<br>'),(4190,'happily','','','','','ad. 幸福地,快乐地,幸好',' Happily, the accident was prevented.<br>     很幸运，事故得以避免了。<br>\n How did you do your work? I did my work happily.<br>     你怎样做你的工作？ 我很快乐地做了我的工作。<br>'),(4191,'happiness','','','','','n. 幸福',' His marriage is full of happiness.<br>     他的婚姻生活很幸福。<br>\n Money can\'t buy happiness.<br>     金钱买不来幸福。<br>'),(4192,'happy','','','','','a. 快乐的,幸福的',' That was not a very happy remark.<br>     那不是很恰当的话。<br>\n I wish you a happy birthday.<br>     祝你生日快乐。<br>'),(4193,'harass','harassed','harassed','harassing','','v. 使...困扰,使...烦恼,反复袭击',' Political dissidents complained that they are harassed by the police.<br>     持有不同政见者申斥他们受到警方的骚扰。<br>\n He always looks harassed.<br>     他老是愁眉苦脸。<br>'),(4194,'harassment','','','','','n. 困扰,烦扰,烦恼',' A source of harassment, annoyance, or pain.<br>     使人痛苦的东西骚扰，烦恼或痛苦的来源<br>\n There is a report about a sexual harassment in the office on this newspaper.<br>     今天的报纸上有一篇关于办公室里的性骚扰的报道。<br>'),(4195,'harbinger','harbingered','harbingered','harbingering','','n. 先驱,预兆',' The crowing of the cock is a harbinger of dawn.<br>     鸡啼报晓。<br>\n The cuckoo is a harbinger of spring.<br>     布谷鸟预告春天的来临。<br>'),(4196,'harbor','harbored','harbored','harboring','harbors','n. 港,避难所<br>\nv. 庇护,隐藏,藏匿',' This harbor is a natural harbor.<br>     这个港口是天然港。<br>\n Harboring criminals is an offence in law.<br>     窝藏罪犯是犯法的。<br>'),(4197,'harbour','harboured','harboured','harbouring','','n. 海港<br>\nvt 停泊',' Harbouring criminals is an offence in law.<br>     窝藏罪犯是犯法的。<br>\n He harbours a secret grudge against his father.<br>     他对父亲暗怀不满。<br>'),(4198,'hard','','','','','a. 硬的<br>\nad. 努力地',' It\'s hard to know what he\'s really thinking.<br>     很难知道他真正在想什么。<br>\n That was a hard time.<br>     那是一段艰难的日子。<br>'),(4199,'harden','hardened','hardened','hardening','','v. 变硬,使...坚强,涨价',' Life in the camp had hardened him considerably.<br>     军营生活使他变得坚强多了。<br>\n His face hardened at the word.<br>     他听到这话，脸沉了下来。<br>'),(4200,'hardiness','','','','','n. 大胆(结实,抵抗力,耐寒性)',''),(4201,'hardly','','','','','ad. 几乎不',' I can hardly wait to hear the news.<br>     我迫不及待地想听到这个消息。<br>\n You can hardly blame me if you don\'t like the place, as you were the one who begged me to take you there.<br>     如果你不喜欢那地方，你绝不该怪我，因为是你求我把你带到那去的。<br>'),(4202,'hardness','','','','','n. 坚硬,困难,严厉',' Their hardness was understood by the teacher.<br>     他们的艰难得到老师的理解。<br>\n I can\'t open the door with hardness of stone.<br>     我不能打开那扇石门。<br>'),(4203,'hardship','','','','hardships','n. 艰难,困苦',' A strong man will bear hardship without complaining.<br>     一个坚强的人会忍受困苦而不抱怨。<br>\n Mountaineering is attractive especially to young people because it is accompanied with hardship and adventure.<br>     登山很吸引人，特别是对年轻人来说，因为它伴随着艰难险阻。<br>'),(4204,'hardware','','','','','n. 五金器具<br>\nn. (计算机) 硬件',' I know nothing about computer hardware.<br>     我对计算机硬件一窍不通。<br>\n We deal in hardware but not software.<br>     我们只经营硬件而不经营软件.<br>'),(4205,'hardy','','','','','a. 难的,艰苦的,坚硬的<br>\nad. 努力地,辛苦地,坚硬地',' A few hardy people swam in the icy water.<br>     一些强壮的人在冰冷的水中游泳。<br>\n Strawberry is hardy and easy to grow in all soil.<br>     草莓耐寒，各种土壤里都容易生长。<br>'),(4206,'hare','','','','hares','n. 野兔',' They went hunting for hares.<br>     他们出去打野兔了。<br>\n He took a bead on the hare and then fired.<br>     他瞄准了野兔，然后开枪。<br>'),(4207,'harm','harmed','harmed','harming','','伤害,损害,危害',' It wouldn\'t do him any harm to work a bit harder.<br>     工作努力点对他没什么害处。<br>\n His failures did his reputation a lot of harm.<br>     他屡次失败使他的声誉受到很大损害。<br>'),(4208,'harmful','','','','','a. 有害的',' It is harmful to your health to drink too much.<br>     过量喝酒对你的身体有害。<br>\n The new law was in a measure harmful.<br>     新的法律在某种程度上说是有害的<br>'),(4209,'harmless','','','','','a. 无害的,无恶意的',' The bomb blast killed several harmless passers-by.<br>     炸弹爆炸使几个无辜行人受伤。<br>\n This snake is harmless.<br>     这条蛇是无毒的。<br>'),(4210,'harmonic','','','','','a. 调和的,音乐般的,和声的<br>\nn. 和音,调波<br>\n[计算机] 调和的',' The harmonic combination of these tones.<br>     四度和音音调的和谐组合<br>\n A brief melodic or harmonic unit often constituting the base for a larger phrase or structure.<br>     音型一组短而连贯的音符或和弦构成的基本音型，经常为一更大的乐曲或结构构成基础<br>'),(4211,'harmonious','','','','','a. 和睦的,调和的,和谐的',' Relations with our neighbors are very harmonious at the moment.<br>     我们目前同邻居们的关系十分和谐。<br>\n The sky and the sea make a harmonious picture.<br>     天空和大海构成了一幅和谐的画面。<br>'),(4212,'harmony','','','','harmonies','n. 协调,和睦,调和',' There was not much harmony in international affairs during those years.<br>     那些年国际事态不很协调。<br>\n His tastes are in harmony with mine.<br>     他的爱好和我的相同。<br>'),(4213,'harness','harnessed','harnessed','harnessing','harnesses','n. 马具,系在身上的绳子,甲胄<br>\nv. 束以马具,披上甲胄,利用产生动力',' The farmer harnessed the horse.<br>     农夫给马套上挽具。<br>\n The cashier died in harness.<br>     出纳员以身殉职。<br>'),(4214,'harsh','','','','','a. 粗糙的,刺耳的,严厉的',' The punishment was too harsh for him.<br>     这种惩罚对他来说太严厉了。<br>\n Expulsion from school is a harsh form of punishment.<br>     开除学籍是严厉的惩罚.<br>'),(4215,'harvest','harvested','harvested','harvesting','harvests','n. 收获,成果,收获物<br>\nv. 收割,收获',' The peasants are harvesting rice in the field.<br>     农民们正在田野里收割稻子。<br>\n We all helped the harvest.<br>     我们都帮忙收割。<br>'),(4216,'hashing','','','','','散列法',' I\'m sorry I hashed up the arrangements.<br>     对不起, 我把整个安排给打乱了.<br>\n He has hashed up the whole plan.<br>     他把整个计划搞得一团糟。<br>'),(4217,'haste','hasted','hasted','hasting','','n. 急速,急忙<br>\nv. 匆忙,赶快<br>\nvi. 赶紧,赶快',' Haste makes waste.<br>     欲速而不达。<br>\n In his haste, he forgot to bring his glasses with him.<br>     匆忙之中，他忘了带眼镜。<br>'),(4218,'hasten','hastened','hastened','hastening','','v. 催促,赶快,急忙',' She hastened home after hearing the news.<br>     听到这个消息后，她匆匆忙忙地回家。<br>\n Some of our staff are to be dismissed, but I hasten to add you won\'t be among them.<br>     有些职员要被解雇，不过请放心，你不在此列。<br>'),(4219,'hasty','','','','','a. 匆匆的,轻率的,急忙的',' His hasty temper made him offensive.<br>     他的急躁的脾气使他令人讨厌。<br>\n I don\'t think it\'s right to make such a hasty decision.<br>     我认为如此仓促地做出决定是不正确的。<br>'),(4220,'hat','hatted','hatted','hatting','hats','n. 帽子',' She bought a hat yesterday.<br>     她昨天买了一顶帽子。<br>\n Prizes went to the first three out of the hat.<br>     奖品为随意挑选出来的前三人所得。<br>'),(4221,'hatch','','','','','n. 孵化,舱口<br>\nv. 孵,孵出',' Three of the chickens hatched today.<br>     今天有三只小鸡出壳。<br>\n Chicks are hatching from the eggs.<br>     小鸡正从蛋壳里孵出来。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (4222,'hate','hated','hated','hating','','n. 憎恨,恨,厌恶<br>\nv. 憎恨,憎恶',' She looked at him with hate in her eyes.<br>     她以憎恨的目光看着他。<br>\n They hate each other.<br>     他们彼此憎恨。<br>'),(4223,'hateful','','','','','a. 憎恨的,可恨的,可恶的',' The sight of food was hateful to the seasick girl.<br>     那个晕船的女孩看到食物就感到厌恶。<br>\n Ironing shirts is a hateful job.<br>     熨衬衫是件讨厌的工作。<br>'),(4224,'hatred','','','','','n. 憎恶,憎恨,怨恨',' He looked at me with hatred.<br>     他带有敌意地望着我。<br>\n Strong dislike or hatred; abhorrence.<br>     憎恶强烈的不喜欢或厌恶；憎恨<br>'),(4225,'haughty','','','','','a. 傲慢的',' The nobles treated the common people with haughty contempt.<br>     王公贵族以不屑一顾的傲慢态度对待平民百姓。<br>\n Some of the more haughty of aristocracy did take exception at his neglecting to raise his cap to them.<br>     一些较为傲慢的贵族对于他不记得向他们脱帽致敬大为不满。<br>'),(4226,'haul','hauled','hauled','hauling','hauls','n. 用力拖拉,努力的结果<br>\nv. 拖,改变方向',' They hauled the boat up the beach.<br>     他们把船拖上岸。<br>\n After a good day\'s fishing they hauled in the nets and went home.<br>     他们捕了一天的鱼, 收起鱼网满载而归.<br>'),(4227,'haunt','haunted','haunted','haunting','haunts','n. 常到的地方<br>\nv. 常到,出没,萦绕于心',' The years of the war still haunt me.<br>     战争年代的往事仍常浮现在我的脑海。<br>\n A spirit haunts the castle.<br>     幽灵常出没于古堡。<br>'),(4228,'have','had','had','having','haves','aux. 已经,曾经<br>\nn. 吃,从事,得到,雇用,享有,有,允许<br>\nv. 有',' I had a letter this morning.<br>     我今天收到一封信。<br>\n Have you got a pencil?<br>     你有铅笔吗？<br>'),(4229,'haven','havened','havened','havening','','n. 港口,避难所,安息所<br>\nv. 安置...于港中,庇护',' They have made their home a haven for the homeless orphans.<br>     他们把自己的家变成了无家可归的孤儿们的避难所。<br>\n He came to see us after I have haven my breakfast.<br>     我吃过早饭后，他来看我们了。<br>'),(4230,'havoc','','','','','n. 大破坏,蹂躏',' The earthquake wreaked havoc on the city.<br>     地震对这个城市造成了大破坏。<br>\n The earthquake has made great havoc of the city.<br>     地震给这个城市造成了巨大的破坏。<br>'),(4231,'hawk','','','','','n. 鹰,掠夺他人的人<br>\nv. 放鹰,像鹰一般地袭击',' Hawks will not pick other hawks\' eyes out.<br>     同类不相残。<br>\n The hawk snatched the chicken and flew away.<br>     老鹰抓住小鸡飞走了。<br>'),(4232,'hay','hayed','hayed','haying','','n. 干草',' I adviced him to make hay while the sun shone.<br>     我劝他抓紧时机。<br>\n The children snuggled down on the hay.<br>     孩子们舒适地蜷伏在干草上。<br>'),(4233,'hazard','hazarded','hazarded','hazarding','hazards','n. 冒险,危险,危害<br>\nv. 冒...的危险,赌运气',' There are many serious health hazards associated with smoking.<br>     许多危害健康的情况都与吸烟有关。<br>\n He hazarded all his money in the attempt to save the business.<br>     他为挽救这家企业，不惜冒险投入他的全部金钱。<br>'),(4234,'hazardous','','','','','a. 危险的',' Free of a difficult or hazardous situation; in a position of safety or security.<br>     脱离险境脱离困难或危险的情况；处于安全或保险的位置<br>\n Investment is a hazardous business; even those who are in the swim sometimes come a cropper.<br>     投资是一项风险事业，就是那些懂行的人有时也会栽跟头。<br>'),(4235,'HDTV','','','','','(high-definition TV)高清晰度电视',''),(4236,'he','','','','','pron. 他',' He is a teacher.<br>     他是教师。<br>\n Where\'s your brother?\' He\'s in Paris.\'<br>     ｀你哥哥在哪里?＇｀他在巴黎.＇<br>'),(4237,'head','headed','headed','heading','heads','n. 头,头脑,领袖<br>\nv. 为首,朝向,前进',' He arranged his speech under four main heads.<br>     他把发言内容归纳成四个主要方面。<br>\n Please raise your head and look at the blackboard.<br>     请抬起头来，看黑板。<br>'),(4238,'headache','','','','headaches','n. 头痛',' The boy had a headache and had to see the doctor.<br>     这个男孩头疼，不得不去看医生。<br>\n I\'ve got a headache.<br>     我头痛。<br>'),(4239,'header','','','','','页眉,标题,报头,电子邮件头',''),(4240,'headers','','','','','消息头',' A record that follows a header.<br>     跟在标头后面的一个记录。<br>\n He stumbled and took a header into the ditch.<br>     他跌了一跤而栽到沟去了。<br>'),(4241,'heading','','','','','n. 标题',' What heading do these items fall under?<br>     这几项应列在哪个标题下面?<br>\n What heading does this come under?<br>     这个编在什麽标题之下?<br>'),(4242,'headline','headlined','headlined','headlining','headlines','n. (pl.)新闻提要,大字标题',' A bold black headline screamed out from the front page.<br>     在（报纸的）头版上出现了一条令人触目惊心的粗黑体大字标题。<br>\n A headline on the front page draws attention to the fuller story inside.<br>     扉页上的大字标题为的是吸引你注意里面的详细内容。<br>'),(4243,'headlong','','','','','a. 头向前的,匆促而用力的,轻率的<br>\nad. 头向前地,猛然的用力的',' Don\'t rush headlong into danger; think it through carefully before you make any decisions.<br>     不要轻率地奔赴险境，做任何决定之前都要认真想想。<br>\n Little Marry carried on for ten minutes after she fell headlong.<br>     小玛丽摔了个倒栽葱后,哭闹了十分钟。<br>'),(4244,'headmaster','','','','','n. 校长',' The professor was assigned headmaster of the school.<br>     教授被任命为这所学校的校长。<br>\n Our headmaster is a despotic person.<br>     我们的校长是个专横的人。<br>'),(4245,'headphone','','','','headphones','n. 戴在头上的收话器,双耳式耳机',''),(4246,'headquarters','','','','headquarters','n. 司令部,指挥部,总部',' Are their any orders coming from the headquarters?<br>     有司令部的任何命令吗？<br>\n The company wants to situate its headquarters in the north.<br>     公司想把总部设在北方.<br>'),(4247,'headstrong','','','','','a. 顽固的,刚愎的,任性的',' Foolishly or irrationally stubborn; headstrong.<br>     顽固的，刚愎自用的愚蠢地或无理地顽固的；任性的<br>\n She\'s hopelessly headstrong; she always gets up against people around her.<br>     她任性得无要救药，老是同周围的人闹别扭。<br>'),(4248,'heal','healed','healed','healing','','v. 痊愈,使...复原,和解',' The medicine and rest will soon heal your wound.<br>     药物治疗和休息会使你的伤口很快愈合。<br>\n Time heals most troubles.<br>     时间会消除痛苦。<br>'),(4249,'health','','','','','n. 健康,卫生,保健',' Fresh air and exercise are good for the health.<br>     新鲜空气和运动有益于健康。<br>\n Smoking is not good for your health.<br>     吸烟对你的健康没有好处。<br>'),(4250,'healthy','','','','','a. 健康的',' His grandpa is healthy.<br>     他的祖父身体健康。<br>\n His inmost thoughts are not healthy.<br>     他心灵深处的思想是不健康的。<br>'),(4251,'heap','heaped','heaped','heaping','heaps','n. 堆,许多,累积<br>\nv. 堆积<br>\n[计算机] 堆',' The books lay in a heap on the floor.<br>     书堆放在地板上。<br>\n We have heaps of time.<br>     我们有很多时间。<br>'),(4252,'heaps','','','','','ad. 很, 非常地',' We have heaps of time.<br>     我们有很多时间。<br>\n I\'ve got heaps to tell you.<br>     我有很多话要跟你说.<br>'),(4253,'hear','heard','heard','hearing','','v. 听到,听说,听取',' We listened but could hear nothing.<br>     我们注意听，但什么也听不见。<br>\n If we don\'t give her what she wants we\'ll never hear the end of it.<br>     我们若不满足她的要求，这事就没完没了了。<br>'),(4254,'hearing','','','','hearings','n. 听力',' Please keep within hearing distance.<br>     请保持在听得见的距离之内。<br>\n Her hearing is poor.<br>     她的听觉不灵。<br>'),(4255,'heart','','','','hearts','n. 心,中心,要点<br>\nv. 鼓起勇气,激励',' He has a kind heart.<br>     他心地善良。<br>\n Let\'s get to the heart of the matter.<br>     让我们谈谈这件事的核心部分。<br>'),(4256,'heartbeat','','','','','n. 心跳',' An irregularity in the force or rhythm of the heartbeat.<br>     心律失常不规则的心跳强度或节奏<br>\n Although there was still a faint heartbeat, he was to all intents and purposes dead.<br>     他虽然仍有隐隐心搏, 但从身体各方面看已经死亡.<br>'),(4257,'heartburn','','','','','n. (消化不良)胃灼热感',''),(4258,'heartfelt','','','','','a. 衷心的,真心真意的',' She helps me with heartfelt feeling.<br>     她真心真意的帮助我。<br>\n They expressed their heartfelt gratefulness to us.<br>     他们向我们表达了他们衷心的感激。<br>'),(4259,'hearth','','','','hearths','n. 炉床,灶台,炉边',' The soldiers swore to fight for the hearth and the altar.<br>     战士们宣誓为保卫家庭和宗教而战。<br>\n An open recess for holding a fire at the base of a chimney; a hearth.<br>     壁炉用于在烟囱底部燃火的敞口的凹窝；炉床<br>'),(4260,'heartily','','','','','ad. 衷心地,真实地,热心地',' I am heartily grateful to your help.<br>     我衷心地感激你的帮助。<br>\n Tell him you Aunt Celeste heartily approves and wishes you both happiness forever.<br>     请转告他，Celeste姑妈完全赞成这门婚事，并衷心地祝福你们永远幸福。<br>'),(4261,'hearty','','','','hearties','a. 诚恳的,热烈的,旺盛的',' They gave him a hearty welcome.<br>     他们衷心欢迎他。<br>\n Grandfather will be80 years old, but he is hale and hearty.<br>     祖父就要80高龄了，但仍精神矍铄。<br>'),(4262,'heat','heated','heated','heating','heats','n. 热,热度,高潮<br>\nv. 加热,激昂,加热',' I can\'t walk about in this heat.<br>     我不能在这种酷热下走路。<br>\n We\'ll heat some water to wash clothes.<br>     我们会热点儿水洗衣服。<br>'),(4263,'heated','','','','','a. 热的,激昂的,兴奋的<br>\nv. 加热,变热,使变暖<br>\nvbl. 加热,变暖,使激昂',' Metals undergo expansion when heated.<br>     金属加热时会膨胀。<br>\n The act or process of pressing clothes with a heated iron.<br>     熨用加过热的熨斗熨压衣物的行为或过程<br>'),(4264,'heater','','','','heaters','n. 加热器,火炉,加热之人',' The heater in my car doesn\'t work properly.<br>     我汽车里的暖气设备出了点毛病。<br>\n He is bathing by heater.<br>     他正用加热器洗澡。<br>'),(4265,'heating','','','','','a. 加热的,供暖的<br>\nn. 加热,供暖,暖气装置',' The heating system in this block doesn\'t work well.<br>     这个街区的供暖系统不太好用。<br>\n Switch the heating on Im cold!<br>     把暖气打开吧--我冷!<br>'),(4266,'heave','heaved','heaved','heaving','heaves','n. 举,抛,起伏<br>\nv. 用力举起,抛出,凸起',' He hove a chair through the window.<br>     他把椅子从窗户中抛出。<br>\n Heave ho, my hearties!<br>     伙伴们, 用力呀!<br>'),(4267,'heaven','','','','heavens','n. 天堂',' The house is a little heaven.<br>     这所房子是一个小乐园。<br>\n If there\'s a heaven on earth, this is it!<br>     人间若有天堂, 非此莫属!<br>'),(4268,'heavenly','','','','','a. 天上的,神圣的,天国似的',' We spent a heavenly day at the beach.<br>     我们在海滨痛痛快快地玩了一天。<br>\n The sun, moon and stars are heavenly bodies.<br>     太阳、月亮和星星都是天体。<br>'),(4269,'heavily','','','','','ad. 很重地,沉重地,沉闷地',' The crime lies heavily on his conscience.<br>     那罪行沉重地压在他心上。<br>\n The truck was heavily loaded.<br>     这辆卡车装载很重。<br>'),(4270,'heaviness','','','','','n. 重,重量',' A measure of the heaviness of an object.<br>     重量一个物体的重量的度量法<br>\n Nobody can lift the heaviness that the sad news have leave with her.<br>     谁也无法减轻这个坏消息给她带来的悲痛。<br>'),(4271,'heavy','','','','heavies','a. 重的<br>\nad. 沉闷地',' How heavy is this box?<br>     这个箱子有多重？<br>\n Dont go so heavy on the sauce!<br>     沙司不要加得太多!<br>'),(4272,'hectic','','','','','a. 兴奋的,繁忙的',' The journalist lead a hectic life.<br>     新闻记者过着紧张兴奋的生活。<br>'),(4273,'hedge','hedged','hedged','hedging','hedges','n. 树篱,障 碍',' Will the hedge keep the sheep out of the field?<br>     这篱笆能将羊群挡在田地外面吗？<br>\n We had better get under the lee of the hedge until the rain stops.<br>     我们最好在树篱下躲一躲等雨停。<br>'),(4274,'hedgehog','','','','hedgehogs','n. 刺猬',' We found a little hedgehog in the field.<br>     我们在田里发现了一只小刺猬。<br>\n The hedgehog rolled up into a spiky ball.<br>     刺　卷起身子成了一个刺球.<br>'),(4275,'heed','heeded','heeded','heeding','','n. 注意,留心<br>\nv. 注意到,留心到',' Now heed what I say.<br>     现在注意听我要说的话。<br>\n Storm warnings are clearly displayed on motorways, but many drivers still take no heed of them.<br>     汽车道上醒目地放着有暴风雪的告示，但许多司机们却没留心。<br>'),(4276,'heel','','','','','n. 脚后跟<br>\nv. 倾侧',' I\'m just kicking my heels until the beginning of the new term.<br>     新学期开学前，我一直无所事事。<br>\n The police were on our heels.<br>     警察紧追着我们。<br>'),(4277,'heels','','','','','残余料',' He saluted with a click of his heels.<br>     他立正敬礼，鞋后跟发出咔嗒一声。<br>\n The police were on our heels.<br>     警察紧追着我们。<br>'),(4278,'height','','','','heights','n. 高度,高处',' His height makes him stand out in the crowd.<br>     他身材高大，因此在人群中很突出。<br>\n They looked down from a giddy height.<br>     他们从令人眩晕的高度往下看。<br>'),(4279,'heighten','heightened','heightened','heightening','','v. 增高,提高,加强',' When she heard the news she was heightening tension.<br>     当她听到那则消息后，她变得越来越紧张。<br>\n It\'s the music to heighten the dramatic effect.<br>     那是用于提高戏剧效果的配乐。<br>'),(4280,'heir','','','','heirs','n. 继承人',' Prince Charles is the legal heir of the crown.<br>     查尔斯王子是王位的合法继承人。<br>\n He is the only legal heir of the rich man.<br>     他是这位富翁的唯一法定继承人。<br>'),(4281,'heiress','','','','heiresses','n. 女继承人',' He took an heiress to wife and was regarded with suspicion by her family.<br>     他娶了个女继承人为妻子，女方家庭对他的结婚动机抱有怀疑。<br>\n The robber abduct the heiress and hold her to ransom.<br>     强盗劫持了女继承人并向她索取赎金。<br>'),(4282,'helicopter','helicoptered','helicoptered','helicoptering','helicopters','n. 直升飞机',' The criminal escaped by a helicopter.<br>     罪犯乘直升机逃走了。<br>\n Three men were lifted by helicopter from the burning ship.<br>     直升飞机把三个男人从燃烧著的船上吊起.<br>'),(4283,'hell','','','','hells','n. 地狱',' The priest said they would go to hell for their sins.<br>     牧师说，他们将因罪恶而下地狱。<br>\n His life has been hell since his wife came back.<br>     他妻子回来以后，他的生活苦不堪言。<br>'),(4284,'hello','helloed','helloed','helloing','hellos','int.（见面打招呼或打电话用语）喂,哈罗',' Hello? Tony here.<br>     喂? 我是托尼。<br>\n Hello, it\'s me.<br>     喂, 是我呀.<br>'),(4285,'helmet','','','','helmets','n. 头盔',' These policemen wear helmets to protect them.<br>     这些警察戴着头盔保护自己。<br>\n Jerry: I never had a beard. I kept my hair inside the helmet.<br>     杰端：我以前是从不留胡子，我头发是在头盔里。<br>'),(4286,'help','helped','helped','helping','helps','n. 帮助,援助<br>\nv. 帮助',' Could you help me up the stairs?<br>     你能扶我上楼梯吗？<br>\n Trade helps industry to develop.<br>     贸易促进工业发展。<br>'),(4287,'helper','','','','helpers','n. 帮忙者,助手',' He is a good helper.<br>     他是一个好帮手。<br>\n One that assists; a helper.<br>     助手（提供）帮助的人；助手<br>'),(4288,'helpful','','','','','a. 有帮助的,有益的',' It\'s often helpful during an illness to talk to other sufferers.<br>     病中与同病者谈天常是有益的。<br>\n Lionel asked me how things were going at work, but I suspect he was just fishing for information that might be helpful to his own company.<br>     莱昂内尔问我工作情况如何，不过我怀疑他只是想探听一些可能对他自己公司有帮助的消息。<br>'),(4289,'helpless','','','','','a. 无助的,无依靠的',' He is as helpless as a baby.<br>     他像一个婴儿一样依赖人。<br>\n In a situation of great difficulty or perplexity; helpless.<br>     处于一个非常困难或迷惑的境地；无助的<br>'),(4290,'hemisphere','','','','hemispheres','n. 半球',' The Western Hemisphere refers to North and South America.<br>     西半球是指南北美洲。<br>\n In the northern hemisphere, spring is in March and April.<br>     在北半球，春季是三月和四月。<br>'),(4291,'hemoglobin','','','','','n. 血红蛋白',' The presence of hemoglobin in the urine.<br>     血红蛋白尿尿液中出现血红蛋白<br>\n The protein that is a constituent of hemoglobin.<br>     球蛋白由血红蛋白构成的蛋白<br>'),(4292,'hemorrhage','','','','','n. 出血,溢血',' The stoppage of bleeding or hemorrhage.<br>     止血阻止流血或大出血<br>\n A hemorrhage of corporate ea