iced our enthusiasm.<br>     他的拒绝浇熄了我们的热情。<br>\n In winter the lake is covered with ice.<br>     冬天时湖面上覆盖着冰。<br>'),(4516,'icebound','','','','','a. 冰封的',''),(4517,'Iceland','','','','','n. 冰岛',' Scandinavia refers to Denmark, Norway, Sweden and Iceland.<br>     斯堪的那维亚是指丹麦、挪威、瑞典和冰岛。<br>\n I refuse to put money into some half-baked plan to grow pineapples in Iceland.<br>     我拒绝把钱投到在冰岛种植菠萝的不周全的计划中去。<br>'),(4518,'icon','','','','','n. 圣像,画像,肖像<br>\nn. [计算机] 图标,图符',' An icon appears in the upper portion of the screen to indicate when the microphone is muted.<br>     当对麦克风进行消音时，会在屏幕的上部出现一个图标。<br>\n Arrange the icon of all minimize application across the bottom of the screen.<br>     沿着屏幕的底部排列所有最小化的应用程序。<br>'),(4519,'icterus','','','','','n. 黄疸',''),(4520,'icy','','','','','a. 冰的,冷淡的,滑溜的',' Icy roads are dangerous.<br>     覆盖着冰的道路很危险。<br>\n He felt hurt by their icy welcome.<br>     他们冷淡的欢迎让他觉得受到伤害。<br>'),(4521,'ID','','','','','n. 身份证<br>\nn. 遗传素质,本能冲动',''),(4522,'idea','','','','ideas','n. 主意,想法,观念',' You have no idea how worried I was.<br>     你想像不出来我有多么担心。<br>\n He has some pretty strange political ideas.<br>     他有一些很奇怪的政治信念。<br>'),(4523,'ideal','','','','ideals','a. 理想的<br>\nn. 理想',' He is looking for a wife but he hasn\'t found his ideal mate.<br>     他正在寻找未来的妻子，但还没有找到理想人选。<br>\n It is an ideal day for a picnic.<br>     这是一个出外野餐的理想日子。<br>'),(4524,'idealism','','','','','n. 唯心论(唯心主义,观念论,理想主义)',' Idealism increase in direct proportion to one\'s distance from the problem.<br>     理想主义，是按和问题的距离成正比例而增大的。<br>\n Jefferson\'s courage and idealism were based on knowledge.<br>     杰斐逊的勇气和理想主义是建立在知识的基础上的。<br>'),(4525,'idealize','idealized','idealized','idealizing','','v. 使理想化',' He tends to idealize his life in the army.<br>     他总想使自己在军队里的生活理想化。<br>'),(4526,'idempotent','','','','','幂等,幂等的',''),(4527,'identical','','','','','a. 相同的,同一的',' Your appearance is identical to hers.<br>     你的相貌和她的一模一样。<br>\n This is the identical hotel we stayed at last year.<br>     这就是我们去年住过的旅馆。<br>'),(4528,'identically','','','','','相等地',''),(4529,'identification','','','','identifications','n. 身份的证明<br>\nn. 视为同一,证明同一,确认',' The identification of the accident victims took some time.<br>     验明事故遇难者身分的工作费了不少时间<br>\n The study of fingerprints as a method of identification.<br>     指纹学对指纹作为确认身份的一种方法的研究<br>'),(4530,'identifier','','','','','(ID)标识符',''),(4531,'identify','identified','identified','identifying','','v. 识别,认明,鉴定',' Can you identify your umbrella among this lot?<br>     你能在这些伞中认出你自己的伞吗？<br>\n One can not identify happiness with wealth.<br>     幸福和财富不能混为一谈。<br>'),(4532,'identity','','','','identities','n. 身份',' The identity of the murdered man has not yet been established.<br>     那名被害人的身份尚未确定。<br>\n The police asked him to show his identity card.<br>     警察让他出示身份证。<br>'),(4533,'ideology','','','','ideologies','n. 观念学,空论,意识形态',' The ideology of the political left.<br>     左派，左翼政治左派的意识形态、观点<br>\n An advocate of a particular ideology, especially an official exponent of that ideology.<br>     理论家，倡导者某一理论的提倡者，尤指对此意识形态的正式阐释<br>'),(4534,'idiom','','','','idioms','n. 成语,惯用语',' To my knowledge, there is no such idiom in English.<br>     据我所知, 英文里并没有这样的成语。<br>\n A word, a phrase, or an idiom peculiar to the English language, especially as spoken in England; a Briticism.<br>     英国习语，英国特有用词，英国式的语言现象英语，尤其是在英语口语中所特有的单词、短语或习惯用语；英国式语言现象<br>'),(4535,'idiomatic','','','','','a. 惯用的,通顺的',' An idiomatic word, phrase, or expression.<br>     习语，成语惯用的词语、短语或表达方式<br>\n He speaks idiomatic English.<br>     他说道地的英语。<br>'),(4536,'idiot','','','','idiots','n. 白痴',' He is an idiot to agree.<br>     他要是同意，就太傻了。<br>\n What a stupid idiot!<br>     真是个愚蠢的白痴!<br>'),(4537,'idle','idled','idled','idling','','a. 懒惰的,闲散的,停顿的<br>\nv. 不作事,闲散,浪费,(机器)空转',' Don\'t idle away your time.<br>     不要虚度光阴。<br>\n We can\'t afford to have all this expensive machinery lying idle.<br>     让所有这些机器闲置着，我们可负担不起损失。<br>'),(4538,'idleness','','','','','n. 懒惰,闲散,失业',' Idleness is the root of all evil.<br>     懒惰乃万恶之源。<br>\n The closure of the large factory made many workers live in idleness.<br>     那家大工厂倒闭，使许多工人失业。<br>'),(4539,'idol','','','','idols','n. 偶像<br>\nn.菩萨',' Don\'t make an idol of money.<br>     不要崇拜财富。<br>\n The fans of the actress craned their necks to catch a glimpse of their idol.<br>     那位女演员的崇拜者们伸长了脖子想看一看他们崇拜的偶像。<br>'),(4540,'ie','','','','','n. 指标误差(工业工程师,工业管理学)',' Who said I can\'t cook? ie Of course I can!<br>     谁说我不会做饭?<br>\n Where does this belong? ie Where is it kept?<br>     这个应该在什麽地方?<br>'),(4541,'if','','','','ifs','conj. 如果<br>\nn. 条件,设想',' If weather permit, we will go to the park tomorrow.<br>     如果天气好的话，明天我们去公园。<br>\n Listen to the tune see if you can remember the words.<br>     请听这曲子－－看你能不能想得起歌词来。<br>'),(4542,'ignite','ignited','ignited','igniting','','v. 点燃,使燃烧<br>\nvi. 着火<br>\nvt. 点燃',' In a modern coal burning electric generating plant the steam may be hot enough to ignite wood.<br>     在一个烧煤的现代化发电厂内，蒸汽允许能热到足以把木头点燃起来。<br>\n A small solid cylinder of a spark-producing alloy, used in lighters to ignite the fuel.<br>     （打火机用的）电石一种由能产生火星的、坚硬的合金小圆柱体，用于点燃打火机燃料<br>'),(4543,'ignorance','','','','','n. 无知',' Ignorance of the law is no excuse.<br>     不懂法律不是藉口。<br>\n Pleading ignorance of the law won\'t help you if you are caught.<br>     假若因犯法被抓住，藉口不知是犯法亦无济於事。<br>'),(4544,'ignorant','','','','','a. 不知道的,无知的,愚昧的',' He\'s so ignorant that he cannot write his own name.<br>     他很无知，连自己的名字都写不出。<br>\n She regarded her critics as ignorant and prejudiced.<br>     她认为那些批评她的人既无知又存有偏见。<br>'),(4545,'ignore','ignored','ignored','ignoring','','v. 不顾,不理,忽视',' We could ignore him and go direct to the chairman, but we\'d be skating on very thin ice.<br>     我们可以不理会他而直接去找主席, 但那样做我们就如履薄冰了.<br>\n If you ignore your diet, trouble will follow.<br>     如果你忽视自己的饮食，必然会遇到麻烦<br>'),(4546,'ill','','','','ills','a. 坏的,有病的<br>\nad. 坏,不利地<br>\nn. 不幸,祸害<br>\nv. 生病',' Did you really feel ill this morning?<br>     今天早晨你真的感到身体不适吗？<br>\n You should not speak ill of your friend.<br>     你不应该说你朋友的坏话。<br>'),(4547,'illegal','','','','illegals','a. 不合法的,非法的',' He admitted that he was an illegal immigrant.<br>     他承认他是非法移民。<br>\n Their speculative buying of grain is illegal.<br>     他们投机购买谷物是不合法的。<br>'),(4548,'illegible','','','','','a. 难辨认的',' Her signature was an illegible scrawl.<br>     她的签字潦草难辩。<br>\n The lettering on the gravestone was badly worn and almost illegible.<br>     墓碑上的文字已严重磨损难以辨认.<br>'),(4549,'illicit','','','','','a. 不法的,不正的,禁止的',' He makes a lot of money by traffic illicit merchandise.<br>     他做违禁商品买卖赚了许多钱。<br>\n Kept or done in secret, often in order to conceal an illicit or improper purpose.<br>     秘密的，暗中的保密的或秘密进行的，常为隐藏一个非法的或不正当的目的<br>'),(4550,'illiteracy','','','','illiteracies','n. 文盲',' Illiteracy is a major problem in some developing countries.<br>     在一些发展中国家, 文盲是个大问题.<br>\n Illiteracy, a serious handicap in life.<br>     文盲，生活中的严重障碍<br>'),(4551,'illiterate','','','','illiterates','a. 文盲的<br>\nn. 文盲',' The boy is an illiterate child.<br>     那个孩子不识字。<br>\n You must be an illiterate if you\'ve never heard of Marx.<br>     要是连马克思也没听说过，那你一定是个文盲。<br>'),(4552,'illness','','','','illnesses','n. 病,疾病',' There was no illness in the village this winter.<br>     今年冬天这村里没什么疾病。<br>\n Too much work and too little rest often lead to illness.<br>     过量的工作和过少的休息会引起疾病。<br>'),(4553,'illuminate','illuminated','illuminated','illuminating','','v. 照明,阐释,说明',' A sudden smile illuminated her face.<br>     突然的微笑使她容光焕发。<br>\n The lights that illuminate the audience section of a concert hall, a theater, or an auditorium.<br>     观众席照明灯照亮音乐厅、戏院或报告厅的观众席的灯<br>'),(4554,'illumination','','','','illuminations','n. 照明,阐释,启发',' The illumination in this room is very bad.<br>     这个屋子的照明很不好。<br>\n The illumination of the manuscript is delicate.<br>     这个手稿的装饰很精致。<br>'),(4555,'illusion','','','','illusions','n. 幻觉,错觉,错误的信仰(或观念)',' He cherished the illusion that she loved him, but he was wrong.<br>     他抱有她爱他的幻觉，但他错了。<br>\n I was under the illusion that he was honest until he was caught stealing some money.<br>     他偷钱当场被人抓住，在此之前我一直误以为他是个老实人。<br>'),(4556,'illusive','','','','','a. 幻影的,错觉的,迷惑人的',''),(4557,'illustrate','illustrated','illustrated','illustrating','','v. 举例说明,作图解',' Our textbook is very well illustrated.<br>     我们的课本插图丰富。<br>\n He pointed at the diagram to illustrate his point.<br>     他指着图表来说明他的论点。<br>'),(4558,'illustration','','','','illustrations','n. 插图,例证,说明',' Children like books filled with illustrations.<br>     孩子们喜欢插图丰富的书。<br>\n To give a definition of a word is more difficult than to give an illustration of its use.<br>     给一个词下定义要比举例说明它的用法困难。<br>'),(4559,'image','imaged','imaged','imaging','images','n. 图像,影像,肖像,想像',' How can we improve our image?<br>     我们该怎样来改善自己的形象呢？<br>\n They concentrated on better definition of the optical image.<br>     他们致力於提高该光学影像的鲜明度.<br>'),(4560,'imaginable','','','','','a. 可想像的,可能的',' We had the greatest difficulty imaginable getting here in time.<br>     我们为了及时赶到此地, 经历了可能想见的最大的困难.<br>\n It would be the greatest imaginable privation for her to have to leave London.<br>     对她来说, 不得不离开伦敦大概是能想像到的最大的损失.<br>'),(4561,'imaginary','','','','','a. 想象的,虚构的',' All the characters in this book are imaginary.<br>     这本书中的人物都是虚构的。<br>\n People still have a general fear for the imaginary infernal powers.<br>     人们对于虚构的地狱中的鬼神仍具有一种普遍的恐惧。<br>'),(4562,'imagination','','','','imaginations','n. 想象,想象力',' These plans reveal a complete failure of imagination.<br>     这些计划显得毫无想象力。<br>\n You didn\'t really see a ghost, it\'s only imagination.<br>     你并没有真地看见鬼，这仅仅是幻象。<br>'),(4563,'imaginative','','','','','a. 富于想象力的',' The story is imaginative.<br>     这个故事是虚构的。<br>\n He is an imaginative writer.<br>     他是个富有想象力的作家。<br>'),(4564,'imagine','imagined','imagined','imagining','','v. 想像,幻想,猜测',' I imagined she was quite surprised when she heard the truth.<br>     我想她听说真相后一定很惊讶。<br>\n You can imagine how surprised I was.<br>     你可以想象我是多么惊讶。<br>'),(4565,'imaging','','','','','成像',' Diagnostic imaging in which ultrasound is used to visualize an internal body structure or a developing fetus.<br>     超声波扫描术利用超声波来显示耳体结构或胚胎发育情况的诊断用的成像法<br>'),(4566,'imitate','imitated','imitated','imitating','','v. 模仿<br>\nvt. 仿制,仿造,模仿,仿效',' He can imitate his teacher perfectly.<br>     他能维妙维肖地模仿他的老师。<br>\n You should imitate great and good people.<br>     你应仿效伟大善良的人。<br>'),(4567,'imitation','','','','imitations','n. 模仿,效法<br>\na. 假造的,冒充的',' That\'s not an original Rembrandt, it\'s an imitation.<br>     这不是伦勃朗的真品，是赝品。<br>\n The house was built in imitation of a Roman villa.<br>     这所房子是仿造古罗马别墅式的建筑。<br>'),(4568,'immaterial','','','','','a. 非物质的,无形的,精神的',' The body is material but the soul is immaterial.<br>     躯体是有形的，而灵魂是无形的。<br>\n The doctrine that the material world is an immaterial product of the senses.<br>     物质世界幻觉说认为物质世界是感觉的精神上产物的信仰<br>'),(4569,'immature','','','','','a. 不成熟的',' Silly, immature behavior.<br>     愚蠢的，不成熟的行为<br>\n Not ripe or matured; immature.<br>     不成熟的未熟或成熟的；不成熟的<br>'),(4570,'immediate','','','','','a. 立即的,即刻的,直接的,最接近的',' There\'s no post office in the immediate neighbourhood.<br>     附近没有邮局.<br>\n This work demands your immediate attention.<br>     这件工作急需你立即处理。<br>'),(4571,'immediately','','','','','ad. 立即<br>\nconj. 一...(就)',' I came here immediately after having my supper.<br>     我一吃完晚饭就来这里了。<br>\n The purpose may not be immediately evident.<br>     这种目的不一定显而易见。<br>'),(4572,'immense','','','','','a. 巨大的,广大的',' It\'s almost impossible to find him in the immense ocean.<br>     在无边无际的海洋中要找到他几乎是不可能的。<br>\n The performance was immense.<br>     演出极为成功。<br>'),(4573,'immerse','immersed','immersed','immersing','','v. 浸,陷入',' He immersed himself totally in his work.<br>     他埋头于工作。<br>\n Please immerse the plant in water for a few minutes.<br>     把那棵植物在水里浸泡几分钟。<br>'),(4574,'immigrant','','','','immigrants','a. 移民的<br>\nn. 移民,侨民',' California has many immigrants from other states.<br>     加利福尼亚有许多来自其他州的移民。<br>\n This country has assimilated immigrants from most of the countries of Europe.<br>     这个国家同化了从欧洲大多数国家迁来的移民。<br>'),(4575,'immigrate','immigrated','immigrated','immigrating','','v. 移居入境',' People from many countries immigrated to the United States and Canada.<br>     许多国家的人移居到美国和加拿大。<br>\n My family and I are planning to immigrate to America next year. I have so many questions. Can you help me?<br>     我的家人和我打算明年移民到美国，我有很多问题，你能帮我忙吗？<br>'),(4576,'immigration','','','','','n. 移居,移民',' There are strict controls on immigration into this country.<br>     移民到这个国家有严格的限制。<br>\n The immigration officer stamped my passport.<br>     移民官员在我的护照上盖了戳。<br>'),(4577,'imminent','','','','','a. 逼近的,即将发生的',' An announcement of further cuts in government expenditure is imminent.<br>     最近将发布进一步削减政府开支的公告。<br>\n No one has given out a warning of the imminent danger.<br>     没有人对即将发生的危险发出警告。<br>'),(4578,'immoral','','','','','a. 不道德的',' Some people still think it is immoral to have sex before marriage.<br>     有些人仍然认为婚前的性行为是不道德的。<br>\n An evil, degrading, or immoral practice or habit.<br>     不道德行为，恶习邪恶的、堕落的或者不道德的行为或者习惯<br>'),(4579,'immortal','','','','immortals','a. 不朽的<br>\nn. 不朽的人物',' The little girl is very interested in the old legend of immortal creatures.<br>     小女孩对有关永生的精灵的古老传奇非常感兴趣。<br>\n He left behind an immortal example to all posterity.<br>     他给后世留下了不朽的典范。<br>'),(4580,'immune','','','','','a. 免除的,免疫的<br>\nn. 免疫者',' He seems to be immune to criticism.<br>     他似乎不受批评的影响。<br>\n The criminal was told he would be immune if he helped the police.<br>     这个罪犯被告知，如果他协助警方就可以免于被起诉。<br>'),(4581,'immunity','','','','immunities','n. 免疫,免疫性,免除',' He has diplomatic immunity.<br>     他有外交豁免权。<br>\n They can\'t be prosecuted for this offence - they have diplomatic immunity.<br>     他们不会因这次违法行为而受到检控 - 他们享有外交豁免权。<br>'),(4582,'immunization','','','','','n. 免疫',' German physiologist. He won a1901 Nobel Prize for work on serum immunization against diphtheria and tetanus.<br>     贝林，埃米尔·冯1854－1917德国生理学家，因其在抗白喉与破伤风血清免疫方面的工作获1901年诺贝尔奖<br>'),(4583,'immunize','immunized','immunized','immunizing','','v. 使免疫,赋予免疫性',' Have you been immunized (against smallpox) yet?<br>     你接种过（抗天花）疫苗没有?<br>'),(4584,'immunoglobulin','','','','','n. 免疫球蛋白',''),(4585,'impact','','','','','n. 冲击,冲突,影响<br>\nv. 挤入,撞击,对...发生影响',' It\'s difficult to assess the impact of the President\'s speech.<br>     总统讲话的巨大影响很难估计.<br>\n The front of the car crumpled on impact.<br>     汽车的前部被撞扁了。<br>'),(4586,'impair','impaired','impaired','impairing','','v. 损害<br>\n[计算机] 损伤',' His illness has impaired his efficiency.<br>     生病降低了他的效率。<br>\n On a communications link, noise or unwanted signals that impair the receipt or correct interpretation of speech or data.<br>     在通信链路上出现的噪音或无用的信号，它损害语音、数据的接收或正确的解释。<br>'),(4587,'impart','imparted','imparted','imparting','','v. 传授,告知',' A teacher\'s aim is to impart knowledge.<br>     教师的作用是传授知识。<br>\n Any of various water-soluble pigments that impart to flowers and other plant parts colors ranging from violet and blue to most shades of red.<br>     花青素一种可溶性颜料，可以使花和其它植物部位产生颜色，其颜色变化从紫色和蓝色到大多数红色<br>'),(4588,'impartial','','','','','a. 公平的,不偏不倚的',' People in the city held the impartial judge in high regard.<br>     这个城市的人们都很尊敬这位公正的法官。<br>\n Impartial; just; equitable.<br>     公平的；公正的；无私的<br>'),(4589,'impatience','','','','','n. 不耐烦',' She has impatience to wait for the bus.<br>     她没有耐心等公共汽车到来。<br>\n The governments showed growing impatience at the unions.<br>     政府对工会表现得越来越不耐烦。<br>'),(4590,'impatient','','','','','a. 不耐烦的,急躁的',' He was impatient of any interruption.<br>     他对任何打扰都感到不耐烦。<br>\n I am impatient for his arrival.<br>     我渴盼着他的到来。<br>'),(4591,'impedance','','','','','阻抗',' They use a bridge to measure the impedance of the transducer.<br>     他们用电桥来测量传感器的阻抗。<br>\n The reciprocal of impedance.<br>     导纳阻抗的对等物<br>'),(4592,'impede','impeded','impeded','impeding','','v. 妨碍,阻碍,阻止',' What impedes you to make progress?<br>     什么事妨碍你取得进步？<br>\n He impedes me to do the job well.<br>     他妨碍我把工作做好。<br>'),(4593,'imperative','','','','imperatives','n. 命令,诫命,需要<br>\na. 命令式的,急需的',' Prompt action is imperative.<br>     果断的行动是必要的。<br>\n Job creation has become an imperative for the government.<br>     创造就业机会是政府必须做的事。<br>'),(4594,'imperfect','','','','','a. 有缺点的,半过去的,未完了时式的',' We live in an imperfect society.<br>     我们生活在一个不完美的社会中。<br>\n Imperfect articles are rejected by our quality control.<br>     我们进行质量检验时，有缺陷的产品均予剔除。<br>'),(4595,'imperial','','','','imperials','a. 帝国的',' The imperial gallon is not the same as the US gallon.<br>     英制的加仑和与美制的容量不同。<br>\n The time has come to abandon the romantic view of Imperial history.<br>     现在已经到了抛弃帝国历史的幻想的时候了。<br>'),(4596,'imperialism','','','','','n. 帝国主义',' Leaders of other republics mutter openly now about a new Russian imperialism, while former chieftains shed crocodile tears over the violation of\"human rights.\"<br>     其他共和国现在公开抱怨新俄罗斯帝国主义，同时以前的那些头儿们也假惺惺地为违反“人权”一掬同情之泪。<br>\n The expansion of Marxism to include both Lenin\'s concept of imperialism as the final form of capitalism and a shift in the focus of struggle from the developed to the underdeveloped countries.<br>     马克思列宁主义马克思主义的延伸，包含了列宁的帝国主义是资本主义的最终表现形式的理论，并指出了斗争中心从发达国家到不发达国家的转移<br>'),(4597,'imperialist','','','','','n. 帝国主义者',' Imperialist powers always tend to gobble up their weaker neighbors.<br>     帝国主义强国总是要想兼并弱小的邻国。<br>\n Like other imperialists, they played naked big-power politics.<br>     和别的帝国主义者一样，他们也玩弄赤裸裸的强权政治。<br>'),(4598,'impetus','','','','','n. 动力,推动力',' The present conflict may provide fresh impetus for peace talk.<br>     目前的冲突可能会给和谈提供新的推动力。<br>\n The historic strike gave an enormous impetus to the whole American labor movement.<br>     这次历史性的罢工对整个美国的劳工运动起了很大的推动作用。<br>'),(4599,'impingement','','','','','冲击',''),(4600,'implant','implanted','implanted','implanting','','v. 深植,灌输,嵌入',' Milton implanted in his daughters a great fear of, if not respect for, their father.<br>     密尔顿对他女儿们灌输的思想不是尊父，就是惧父。<br>\n Implant a pacemaker; implant a drug capsule.<br>     植入一个起搏器；植入一个药物胶囊<br>'),(4601,'implement','','','','','n. 工具,器具<br>\nvt. 实现,执行,使...生效',' What implements are needed for gardening?<br>     园艺需要些什么工具？<br>\n The government is implementing a new policy to help the unemployed.<br>     政府正在实施一项新的帮助失业者的政策。<br>'),(4602,'implementation','','','','','n. 安装启用,实行,履行<br>\n<br>\n工具',''),(4603,'implements','','','','','n. 工具',' A pool of implements for the use of all the workers on the estate; forming a pool of our talents.<br>     种植园中所有工人共同使用的工具；将我们的才能聚集起来<br>\n An electrical gate or mechanical device which implements the logical OR operator. An output signal occurs whenever there are one or more inputs on a multichannel input. An OR gate performs the function of the logical\"inclusive OR operation\".<br>     一种实现逻辑“或”算法的门电路或机械器件。当在其多通道输入端有一个或多个输入时就产生一个输出信号。“或”门实现逻辑“或操作”的功能。同ORelement。<br>'),(4604,'implicate','implicated','implicated','implicating','','vt. 纠缠(使...绕住,暗示)<br>\nn. 包含的东西(暗指的东西)',' He was deeply implicated (ie involved) in the plot.<br>     他与该阴谋牵涉颇深.<br>\n His enemies tried to implicate him (in the murder).<br>     他的仇人竭力想把他牵扯进谋杀案中.<br>'),(4605,'implication','','','','implications','n. 暗示,含意',' Failure to say `No\' may, by implication, be taken to mean `Yes\'.<br>     没表示否定, 其含义可能理解为是肯定的.<br>\n Study the implications of the president\'s statement.<br>     研究总统声明的含义.<br>'),(4606,'implicit','','','','','a. 暗示的,盲从的<br>\n[计算机] 隐式',' Her attitude was implicit in the answer she gave us.<br>     她在给我们的答复中态度是含蓄的。<br>\n The system of rules implicit in a language, viewed as a mechanism for generating all sentences possible in that language.<br>     语法规则隐含在一种语言中的规则体系，被看作在该语言中生成所有可能的语句的机制<br>'),(4607,'implied','','','','','v. 意思是(包含)<br>\na. 储蓄的',' I think freedom does imply responsibility.<br>     我认为自由一定包含着责任。<br>\n One journalist, an Italian, walked over and just calmly stood in front of the wretched men, implying that if the soldiers shot them, they would have to shoot him too.<br>     一位意大利记者，走过去镇定地挡在了那群可怜无助的人身前，意思是说，士兵们要杀他们的话，得先把他杀了。<br>'),(4608,'implore','implored','implored','imploring','','v. 恳求,哀求',' She implored me to do her a favor.<br>     她恳求我帮她这个忙。<br>\n I implore you to go now.<br>     我恳求你现在就走吧。<br>'),(4609,'implosion','','','','','n. 内爆(从外向内的压力作用)',''),(4610,'imply','implied','implied','implying','','v. 暗示,意味',' I don\'t wish to imply that you are wrong.<br>     我无意暗示你错了。<br>\n His silence implied agreement.<br>     他沉默不语意味着同意了。<br>'),(4611,'import','','','','','n. 进口<br>\nv. 进口,输入<br>\nvt. 输入,进口',' The government has an interest in importing scientific equipment.<br>     政府对引进科学设备非常感兴趣。<br>\n The import of cotton goods went up sharply in 1986.<br>     在1986年，棉织品的进口猛增。<br>'),(4612,'importance','','','','','n. 重要(性)',' He is a man of great importance.<br>     他是一位非常重要的人物。<br>\n We cannot emphasize too much the importance of learning English.<br>     我们再怎样强调学英文的重要性也不为过。<br>'),(4613,'important','','','','','a. 重要的',' She was clearly an important person.<br>     她显然是个有影响的人。<br>\n It\'s not as if he was very important in the company hierarchy.<br>     他在公司的领导层中似乎无多大权力。<br>'),(4614,'importation','','','','importations','n. 进口',' The importation of tobacco is the country\'s largest imports.<br>     烟草进口是这个国家最大的进口商品。<br>\n The advocacy, system, or theory of protecting domestic producers by impeding or limiting, as by tariffs or quotas, the importation of foreign goods and services.<br>     贸易保护主义通过关税或进口配额等措施阻碍或限制外国商品和服务性产业的进口从而保护国内生产者的主张、制度或理论<br>'),(4615,'importer','','','','','n. 进口商',' I can offer them to you at price which you will find to compare very favourably with those of their importer.<br>     如将我方的报价与其他进口商的比较，你会发现我方价格是非常优惠的。<br>\n That importer wishes to insure against All Risks.<br>     那个进口商想要投保一切险。<br>'),(4616,'impose','imposed','imposed','imposing','','v. 加上,课征,强迫,征收(税款)',' Don\'t try to impose your wishes on us.<br>     不要试图把你的愿望强加给我们。<br>\n The judge imposed a fine of ten dollars on him.<br>     法官判他罚款10 美元。<br>'),(4617,'imposing','','','','','a. 令人难忘的,壮丽的<br>\nvbl. 强迫,利用',' Imposing a lenient sentence for such a serious crime sets a dangerous precedent.<br>     对这样严重的罪行轻判就开了个危险的先例.<br>\n She\'d never think of imposing herself.<br>     她决不想勉强别人接纳自己.<br>'),(4618,'imposition','','','','impositions','n. 徵收,课税,税款',' The imposition of the tax on books caused a sharp rise in price.<br>     对书籍课税造成书价急剧上涨。<br>\n I\'d like to stay if it\'s not too much of an imposition on you.<br>     要是不给你添太多麻烦的话，我倒是愿意留下来。<br>'),(4619,'impossibility','','','','impossibilities','n. 不可能之事,不可能',' It\'s a physical impossibility to be in two places at one time.<br>     同时在两地是自然规律上不可能的事。<br>\n It is an impossibility for you to do so.<br>     你那样做是不可能的事。<br>'),(4620,'impossible','','','','','a. 不可能的',' You are the most impossible person I\'ve ever met!<br>     你是我遇到的最难以忍受的人！<br>\n It\'s impossible for us to finish the work in one day.<br>     我们在一天之内完成这份工作是不可能的。<br>'),(4621,'impost','','','','','n. 拱基,台轮,税款<br>\nv. 决定关税,分类课税',' My company impost general merchandise.<br>     我公司经营杂货进口业务。<br>\n Either of the sides of an arch, curving down from the apex to an impost.<br>     梁腋，拱腋拱门上任意一个从拱顶到拱墩间的部分<br>'),(4622,'impractical','','','','','a. 不实用的(不切实际的,不能实行的)',' The plan is feasible in reason but impractical.<br>     这个计划道理上行得通, 但不现实。<br>\n The ideals or principles of a utopian; idealistic and impractical social theory.<br>     乌托邦思想及理论空想社会主义者的理想或原则；理想但不切实际的社会主义学说<br>'),(4623,'imprecise','','','','','a. 不正确的',''),(4624,'impress','','','','','n. 印象,特徵,印记<br>\nv. 使...有印象,影响',' She impressed me as a scholar.<br>     她给我留下了学者的印象。<br>\n My father impressed me with the importance of hard work.<br>     我父亲使我明白了努力工作的重要性。<br>'),(4625,'impression','','','','impressions','n. 印象',' What were your first impressions of Beijing?<br>     你对北京的最初印象如何？<br>\n I am surprised you got an unfavorable impression of him.<br>     我很惊讶你对他印象不佳。<br>'),(4626,'impressive','','','','','a. 给人深刻印象的',' His collection of paintings is the most impressive.<br>     他的绘画收藏令人