rities','n. 不纯,杂质',' There are some impurities in food.<br>     食物中有一些杂质。<br>\n Workers are removing impurities from silver.<br>     工人们正去除银中的杂质。<br>'),(4636,'in','','','','ins','prep. 在,在...之内',' I\'m afraid we\'re in for a storm.<br>     恐怕我们要遇上暴风雨了。<br>\n The telephone was in the little study on the ground floor.<br>     电话在底楼的小书房里。<br>'),(4637,'inability','','','','','n. 无能,无力',' His inability to speak French puts him at a disadvantage.<br>     他不会说法语, 这使他很吃亏.<br>\n The persistent inability to conceive a child.<br>     不孕持续的不能怀孕的能力<br>'),(4638,'inaccessible','','','','','a. 难接近的,难达到的,难达成的',' The scientist discovered the plant in the most inaccessible reaches of the jungle.<br>     这位科学家在丛林深处最难进入的区域发现了这种植物。<br>\n His busy schedule made him completely inaccessible to his students.<br>     他的时间排得很满，学生根本无法和他接触。<br>'),(4639,'inaccuracy','','','','inaccuracies','不准确度,错误',' She is a proverb for inaccuracy.<br>     她做事马虎是出了名的。<br>\n I must ask the readers\' kind indulgence for any inaccuracies and omissions that may possibly occur.<br>     我必须请求读者原谅可能出现的错误和疏漏。<br>'),(4640,'inaccurate','','','','','a. 不准确的',' Your information is inaccurate and your conclusion is therefore wrong.<br>     你的信息不准确，所以你的结论是错误的。<br>'),(4641,'inactivate','inactivated','inactivated','inactivating','','vt. 使不活动',''),(4642,'inactive','','','','','a. 不活动的,停止的,怠惰的<br>\n[计算机] 不活动的',' These are inactive elements.<br>     这些是惰性元素。<br>\n I don\'t want to lead an inactive life.<br>     我不想过沉闷的生活。<br>'),(4643,'inadequate','','','','','a. 不充分的,不适当的',' His explanation is inadequate.<br>     他的解释不充分。<br>\n The plan, brilliant in its conception, failed because of inadequate preparation.<br>     那计划的构想倒是十分宏伟, 但终因准备不足而告吹.<br>'),(4644,'inapt','','','','','a. 不适当的,不合适的',''),(4645,'inasmuch','','','','','ad. 因...之故,因为',' He is a Dane inasmuch as he was born in Denmark.<br>     他按出生在丹麦来说是丹麦人。<br>\n Inasmuch as; since.<br>     因为；由于<br>'),(4646,'inaudible','','','','','a. 听不见的',''),(4647,'inaugural','','','','','a. 开幕的',' The inaugural session closed at17:10 local.<br>     开幕式在当地时间下午5点10分结束。<br>'),(4648,'inaugurate','inaugurated','inaugurated','inaugurating','','v. 开创,举行...开幕典礼',' The city library was inaugurated by the mayor.<br>     市长主持了市图书馆的落成仪式。<br>\n Mr. Clinton was inaugurated as the President of the U.S.A.<br>     克林顿就职美国总统。<br>'),(4649,'inauguration','','','','inaugurations','n. 开始(开幕仪式,落成典礼,通车仪式)',''),(4650,'inbound','','','','','a. 回内地的,归本国的<br>\n[计算机] 入站',''),(4651,'incalculable','','','','','a. 不可数的,无数的',' He is a person of incalculable moods.<br>     他是个喜怒无常的人。<br>\n He did incalculable harm to her reputation.<br>     他严重损害了她的声誉。<br>'),(4652,'incapable','','','','','a. 无能力的,不能的',' The children seem to be totally incapable of working quietly by themselves.<br>     这些孩子似乎完全不能安静地自己做功课。<br>\n That child seems incapable of keeping out of (ie not getting into) mischief.<br>     那个孩子不调皮捣蛋简直就受不了.<br>'),(4653,'incense','','','','','vt. 使...发怒(点香)<br>\nn. 香',' I was incensed at his rudeness.<br>     我对他的粗鲁感到愤怒。<br>\n The monk burned a stick of incense in the incense burner.<br>     和尚在香炉里焚上一柱香。<br>'),(4654,'incentive','','','','incentives','a. 刺激的,鼓励的<br>\nn. 刺激,鼓励,动机',' He hasn\'t much incentive to work hard.<br>     他没有努力工作的动力。<br>\n They don\'t try very hard if there is no incentive.<br>     没有奖励，他们工作就不太努力。<br>'),(4655,'inch','inched','inched','inching','inches','n. 英寸<br>\nv. 慢慢前进,慢慢移动',' Prices are inching down.<br>     物价在慢慢下降。<br>\n How many inches of rain fell last year?<br>     去年的雨量是多少英寸？<br>'),(4656,'incidence','','','','','n. 发生(率)',' The rate of incidence of a disease.<br>     发病率发生疾病的概率<br>'),(4657,'incident','','','','incidents','n. 事件<br>\nn. 插曲，事变<br>\nadj. 难免的，附带的<br>\nadj. (物理)入射的',' The serious incident along the border increased our fears of the war.<br>     边境上的紧张局势加重了我们对战争的忧虑。<br>\n The police are connecting this incident with last week\'s terrorist bombing.<br>     警方认为这次事件和上周的恐怖分子爆炸事件有关。<br>'),(4658,'incidentally','','','','','ad. 附随地,偶然,顺便',' Incidentally, if you want that book, I\'ll bring it next time.<br>     顺便说一句，如果你要那本书，我下次带给你。<br>\n And, incidentally, it is a chronic complaint of wives that their husbands do not notice new dresses, new hats, and changes in household arrangements.<br>     而且，顺便说一句，妻子们经常抱怨，他们的丈夫不注意新衣服、新帽子和家庭摆设的变化。<br>'),(4659,'incipient','','','','','a. 起初的,发端的,初期的',' Detecting incipient tumors; an incipient personnel problem.<br>     发现早期肿瘤；刚出现的个人问题<br>'),(4660,'incite','incited','incited','inciting','','v. 刺激,激励,引诱',' They incited the workers to violence.<br>     他们煽动工人暴动。<br>\n The captain was accused of inciting other officers to mutiny.<br>     该上尉被控煽动军官叛变。<br>'),(4661,'inclination','','','','inclinations','n. 倾向,意愿,倾斜度',' You always follow your own inclination instead of thinking of our feelings.<br>     你总是随心所欲而不考虑我们的情感。<br>\n She is not free to follow her own inclination in the matter ofmarriage.<br>     她的婚姻不能自主.<br>'),(4662,'incline','','','','','n. 倾斜,斜坡,斜面<br>\nv. 使...倾向,爱好,易于',' I\'m inclined to believe him innocent.<br>     我倾向于相信他的无辜。<br>\n I\'m inclined to tiredness in winter.<br>     我在冬天易于疲劳。<br>'),(4663,'inclined','','','','','a. 倾向于...的',' I\'m inclined to believe he\'s innocent.<br>     我颇以为他是无辜的.<br>\n We can go for a walk, if you feel so inclined.<br>     你要是愿意的话, 咱们去散散步吧.<br>'),(4664,'include','included','included','including','','v. 包括,包含,连...在内<br>\n[计算机] 包括',' Is service included in the bill?<br>     帐单中包含服务费吗？<br>\n Please include me in the list.<br>     请把我列入名单中。<br>'),(4665,'inclusion','','','','','n. 包含',' Inclusion in an insurance policy or protective plan.<br>     保险项目某一保险单或担保方案所包含的内容<br>'),(4666,'inclusive','','','','','a. 包含...在内的<br>\n[计算机] 包括的',' Reserve double room June fourth to tenth inclusive.<br>     预订双人房间，六月四日至十日，共六晚，望订妥复电。<br>\n The monthly rent is$20 inclusive of everything.<br>     ＂月房租总共二十美元，包括一切费用在内。＂<br>'),(4667,'incoherence','','','','','非相关性',''),(4668,'income','','','','incomes','n. 收入,所得',' My monthly income was just over 200 pounds.<br>     我每月的收入是200多磅。<br>\n The senate was censured for income tax evasion.<br>     这名参议员因逃避缴纳所得税而受到指责。<br>'),(4669,'incoming','','','','','a. 引入的(入射的,增殖的)<br>\nn. 进来(来到,收入)',' The process of combining incoming messages into a single message.<br>     将输入的多个报文合并成一条报文的过程。参阅concentrator。<br>\n Point through which the incoming traffic flow enters a switching stage.<br>     输入通信量流进入交换站（台）所通过的地方。<br>'),(4670,'incompatibility','','','','','n. 不两立,不相容',''),(4671,'incompatible','','','','incompatibles','a. 不相容的,不能并存的,矛盾的',' The state or quality of being incompatible.<br>     不相容性不相容的状态或性质<br>\n The incompatible offices of prosecutor and judge.<br>     检察官和法官的职位不能由一个人兼任<br>'),(4672,'incomplete','','','','','a. 不完全的,不完整的',' They only got an incomplete set of results from the experiment.<br>     他们从这次实验中只得到了一组不完整的答案。<br>\n Her handbooks are incomplete.<br>     她的手册不完整。<br>'),(4673,'incongruous','','','','','a. 不协调的,不一致的,前后不一的',' Completely different; incongruous.<br>     异类的完全不同的；不一致的<br>\n The state or quality of being incongruous.<br>     不相称自相矛盾的情况或性质<br>'),(4674,'inconsistency','','','','inconsistencies','n. 不一致,不调和,矛盾',' She noticed several minor inconsistencies in his argument.<br>     她觉察到他的论点有几处略微有些自相矛盾.<br>'),(4675,'inconsistent','','','','','a. 不一致的',' His accounts of the event were inconsistent.<br>     他对那件事情的说法前后不一致。<br>\n Such behavior is inconsistent with her high-minded principles.<br>     这样的行为与她情操高尚的原则是矛盾的。<br>'),(4676,'inconvenience','inconvenienced','inconvenienced','inconveniencing','inconveniences','n. 不便,困难<br>\nv. 使...感不便,使...感困难',' I suffered great inconvenience.<br>     我感到极不方便。<br>\n Please accept our apologies for any inconvenience we have caused.<br>     若有不便，敬请原谅。<br>'),(4677,'inconvenient','','','','','a. 不方便的',' Living such a long way from the shops can be very inconvenient.<br>     住得离商店这么远会很不方便。<br>\n They arrived at an inconvenient time ---we had just started the meal.<br>     他们来得很不是时候，我们刚开始吃饭。<br>'),(4678,'incorporate','incorporated','incorporated','incorporating','','a. 合并的,公司组织的,具体化的<br>\nv. 合并,组成公司,具体表现',' The new car design incorporates all the latest safety features.<br>     新的汽车设计具备最新安全措施的一切特点。<br>\n We had to incorporate for a company for tax reasons.<br>     鉴于税务原因，我们得组成公司。<br>'),(4679,'incorporated','','','','','组成公司的,合成一体的',' A borough of north-central England northeast of Manchester. Incorporated in1626, it is a major commercial, transportation, communications, and industrial center. Population, 718,100.<br>     利兹英国英格兰中北部城市，在曼彻斯特的东北部。1626年被合并，它是一个主要商业、运输、通讯及工业中心。人口718，100<br>\n A principality of the United Kingdom on the western peninsula of the island of Great Britain. Incorporated with England since the Act of Union(1536), Wales has maintained its own distinct culture and a strong nationalist sentiment. Cardiff is the capital and the largest city. Population, 2,790,462.<br>     威尔士英国大不列颠岛西部半岛之一地区。自联盟令（1536年）后与英'),(4680,'incorporation','','','','','n. 结合,编入,团体组织',''),(4681,'incorrect','','','','','a. 不正确的,错误的',' He gave an incorrect answer.<br>     他的答案是错误的。<br>\n Not consistent with established truth, fact, or rule; incorrect.<br>     错误的，不正确的与既定真相、事实或原则不一致的；错误的<br>'),(4682,'increase','','','','increases','n. 增加,增强,提高<br>\nv. 增加,提高',' They have increased the price of petrol again.<br>     他们又提高了汽油的价格。<br>\n There was a steady increase in population.<br>     人口在不断增长中。<br>'),(4683,'increasing','','','','','vbl. 增加',' The increasing unemployment caused social unrest.<br>     不断增加的失业引起了社会骚乱。<br>\n She came up with a new idea for increasing sales.<br>     她想出了增加销售量的新主意.<br>'),(4684,'increasingly','','','','','ad. 逐渐地,渐增地',' Increasingly, farm land is yielding to property development.<br>     地产的发展逐渐占据了农田.<br>\n Nowadays we rely increasingly on computers for help/to help us.<br>     现今人们越来越依赖计算机协助工作.<br>'),(4685,'incredible','','','','','a. 难以置信的',' He has an incredible house!<br>     他有一所极美的房子！<br>\n That\'s the most incredible coincidence I\'ve ever heard of!<br>     那是我听说过的最难以置信的巧合！<br>'),(4686,'incredulous','','','','','a. 怀疑的,不轻信的',' He looked at me with an incredulous expression.<br>     他怀疑地看着我。<br>\n She looked incredulous.<br>     她显出怀疑的样子。<br>'),(4687,'increment','','','','','n. 增加(增加物,增量,余差)',' Your salary will be 12000 a year, withannual increments of 500.<br>     你的年薪为12000英镑, 每年增加500英镑.<br>\n A finite increment in a variable.<br>     变量增量变量的有限增量<br>'),(4688,'incremental','','','','','增量的,增加的',' A decrease, especially a small or incremental one.<br>     减少尤指小规模或逐步增加者的减少<br>'),(4689,'incubation','','','','','n. 抱蛋,孵化,熟虑',''),(4690,'incur','incurred','incurred','incurring','','v. 招致,蒙受,遭遇',' The hunter incurred great danger in killing the wolf.<br>     猎人打狼时承受着巨大的危险。<br>\n Incurred substantial losses during the stock market crash.<br>     在股票市场剧跌时蒙受了巨大的物质损失<br>'),(4691,'incurable','','','','incurables','a. 不能医治的,不能矫正的,无救的<br>\nn. 不治的病人,无救的人',' He was found in incurable disease.<br>     他被查出得了不治之症。<br>\n The child has an incurable habit.<br>     那孩子有个无法矫正的习惯。<br>'),(4692,'indebted','','','','','a. 负债的(受惠的)',' He was indebted to her for nursing him through pneumonia.<br>     他感激她护理好了他的肺炎。<br>\n Owing something, such as gratitude, to another; indebted.<br>     受惠的欠别人东西，如人情；感激的<br>'),(4693,'indebtedness','','','','','n. 感激<br>\nn. 受恩惠, 亏欠,债务',' Enclosed is a sight draft for￡26.10.5 on Messrs. Robert& Sons, which clears off our indebtedness to you.<br>     兹同函奉上以Robert父子公司为付款人，面额26。15英镑的即期汇票一张，用以清偿所欠贵方债务。<br>'),(4694,'indeed','','','','','ad. 的确,真正地',' A friend in need is a friend indeed.<br>     患难之交才是真朋友。<br>\n The future of this firm will be very bleak indeed if we keep losing money.<br>     要是我们继续亏本的话，这家公司的前途会非常黯淡。<br>'),(4695,'indefinite','','','','','a. 模糊的,不确定的,无限的',' He has rather indefinite views on the question.<br>     他对该问题的看法颇暧昧。<br>\n She\'ll be away for an indefinite period.<br>     她将离开一段时间，何时回来未定。<br>'),(4696,'indefinitely','','','','','ad. 无限地(在长时期内,无穷地)',' Pressure was put on them to delay the games indefinitely.<br>     他们受到压力，让他们把运动会无限期推迟下去。<br>\n Continuing or lasting for an indefinitely long time.<br>     长期的，长久的继续或保持无限长的时间的<br>'),(4697,'indelible','','','','','a. 不能消除的,不能拭除的,难忘的',' His concern for the masses made an indelible impression on us.<br>     他对群众的关怀给我们留下不可磨灭的印象。<br>\n Act promptly to remove spots from these fabrics. The longer you delay, the more indelible will the mark become.<br>     赶快动手把这些污点从这些织物上擦掉。拖延时间越长，就越难擦掉。<br>'),(4698,'indemnify','indemnified','indemnified','indemnifying','','v. 赔偿,补偿,保护',' I will indemnify you for any expenses you may incur on my behalf.<br>     我会偿付你为了我而负担的任何花费。<br>\n Everyone should learn to indemnify oneself against harm.<br>     每个人都应当，学会使自己不受伤害。<br>'),(4699,'indemnity','','','','indemnities','n. 保证(赔偿,免罚)',' The victorious nations are demanding huge indemnities from their former enemies.<br>     战胜国要求战败国交付巨额赔款.<br>'),(4700,'indent','','','','','n. 契约,订货单<br>\nv. 切割成锯齿状,缩排,定货<br>\n[计算机] 缩排,缩进',' There are long indented coastlines in the South Sea.<br>     在南海有犬牙交错的海岸线。<br>\n Please indent the first line of each paragraph.<br>     请于每段第一行缩格书写。<br>'),(4701,'indentation','','','','','n. 刻痕(印压,缩进,曲折岸)',' Having indentations that extend about halfway to the center, as in certain leaves.<br>     半裂的有锯齿状边缘的，延伸到距中心一半的距离，例如某些叶片<br>'),(4702,'indention','','','','','缩排,定货',''),(4703,'independence','','','','','n. 独立,自主,自立',' When a boy leaves college and begins to earn money he can live a life of independence.<br>     男孩子大学毕业后开始赚钱时，便可独立生活了。<br>\n The condition or quality of being autonomous; independence.<br>     自主处于自主的状态或性质；独立<br>'),(4704,'independent','','','','independents','a. 独立的,自主的<br>\nn. 独立派人士,无党派者',' She is so independent that she refused all pecuniary aid.<br>     她很独立，所以拒绝一切金钱上的资助。<br>\n They are a proud and independent people.<br>     他们是独立自主的民族.<br>'),(4705,'independently','','','','','ad. 独立地,自立地',' Charles Darwin and Alfred Russell Wallace discovered evolution independently.<br>     查尔斯·达尔文和阿尔弗雷德· 罗素·华莱士各自独立地发现了进化论。<br>\n The belief that nations will benefit from acting independently rather than collectively, emphasizing national rather than international goals.<br>     国家主义国家将从独立发展中受益而不是和其他国家共同发展中受益的信仰，强调国家内部的自标而不是国家间的<br>'),(4706,'index','indexed','indexed','indexing','indices','n. 索引,指针,指数<br>\nv. 编入索引中,指出',' The book will be indexed in the next edition so as to make it more useful.<br>     为了使它更实用，这本书在下一版本中将编有索引。<br>\n Do you know the price index in the city?<br>     你知道这个城市的物价指数吗？<br>'),(4707,'india','','','','','n. 印度',' India is to the south of China.<br>     印度在中国的南边。<br>\n India used to be a dependency of Britain.<br>     印度过去是英国的附属地。<br>'),(4708,'indian','','','','','a. 印度的<br>\nn. 印第安人,印度人',' Some Indians are friendly to us.<br>     有些印第安人对我们很友好。<br>\n These Indian guest are familiar with this book.<br>     这些印度客人对这本书很熟悉。<br>'),(4709,'indicate','indicated','indicated','indicating','','v. 显示,象征,指示<br>\nv.指明,表明',' Don\'t forget to indicate before turning.<br>     拐弯之前别忘记指示车行方向。<br>\n Research indicates that men find it easier to give up smoking than women.<br>     研究表明，男人比女人更容易戒烟。<br>'),(4710,'indication','','','','indications','n. 象征,迹象,指示,表示',' There are some indications that the prices will rise.<br>     有迹象表明物价将上涨。<br>\n Did he give you any indication of his feelings?<br>     他向你表示过他的感情吗？<br>'),(4711,'indicative','','','','indicatives','a. 指示的,象徵的,表示...的',' Is a large head indicative of high intelligence?<br>     头大是不是表示智慧高？<br>\n Their failure to act is indicative of their lack of interest in the problem.<br>     他们没有采取行动，表明他们对这个问题不感兴趣。<br>'),(4712,'indicator','','','','indicators','n. 指示器,指示剂<br>\n[计算机] 指示符',' An indicator or a sighting apparatus on a plane table, used in angular measurement.<br>     旋标装置飞机控制板上的指示器或观测仪，用来测量角度<br>\n A hand-held, button-activated input device that when rolled along a flat surface directs an indicator to move correspondingly about a computer screen, allowing the operator to move the indicator freely, as to select operations or manipulate text or graphics.<br>     鼠标一种手用的、用按扭控制的输入设备，当在平台上滑动时可以相应地移动计算机屏幕上的指示箭头，使得操作者可以随意控制指示箭头，由此来选择项目、控制内容或作图<br>'),(4713,'indifference','','','','','n. 不重视,无兴趣,漠不关心',' The spread of disease among the refuges at last aroused the people from their indifference towards these unhappy people.<br>     难民群中疾病的流传，终于将人民从对这些不幸者的漠不关心的状态中唤醒。<br>\n A callous indifference to the suffering of others.<br>     对他人之痛苦漠不关心的铁石心肠的人<br>'),(4714,'indifferent','','','','','a. 漠不关心的,无重要性的,中立的',' I was so excited to see snow that I was indifferent to the cold.<br>     我看到雪激动得连寒冷都不在乎了。<br>\n She seems indifferent, but deep down she\'s very pleased.<br>     她貌似无动於衷, 其实心里非常高兴.<br>'),(4715,'indigenous','','','','','a. 该土地所固有的,土著的,国产的',' The indigenous population was soon displaced by the settlers.<br>     没过多久，外来移民就把当地人赶出了家园。<br>\n Indians were the indigenous inhabitants of America.<br>     印第安人是美洲的土著居民。<br>'),(4716,'indigestion','','','','indigestions','n. 消化不良',' He suffers from indigestion.<br>     他消化不良。<br>\n She had an attack of indigestion yesterday.<br>     她昨天消化不良。<br>'),(4717,'indignant','','','','','a. 愤慨的,愤愤不平的',' He is indignant at the false accusation.<br>     他对被诬告愤愤不平。<br>\n People are indignant by their shooting of innocent civilians.<br>     对于他们枪杀无辜平民，人们感到义愤填膺。<br>'),(4718,'indignation','','','','','n. 愤怒,愤慨,义愤',' I expressed my indignation at being unfairly dismissed.<br>     我对不公平地被解雇表示愤慨。<br>\n They felt strong indignation against their teacher.<br>     他们对他们的老师感到强烈愤慨。<br>'),(4719,'indirect','','','','','a. 间接的,迂回的',' The accident was the indirect result of the train being late.<br>     引发事故的间接原因是火车晚点。<br>\n His indirect way of telling me to leave annoyed me.<br>     他那种不直截了当地让我离开的方式激怒了我。<br>'),(4720,'indirection','','','','','间接',''),(4721,'indirectly','','','','','ad. 间接地',' In a furtive or circumspect manner; indirectly.<br>     行为鬼祟的或谨慎的；谨慎的<br>\n I know Linda was only indirectly concerned in what took place.<br>     我知道所发生的事情间接涉及到琳达。<br>'),(4722,'indiscriminate','','','','','a. 无差别的,不分皂白的,杂陈的',' He was indiscriminate in his choice of friends.<br>     他择友不慎重。<br>\n Savage, indiscriminate killing; a massacre.<br>     血洗野蛮的、不加区别的杀戳；大屠杀<br>'),(4723,'indispensable','','','','indispensables','a. 不可缺少的',' Air, food and water are indispensable to life.<br>     空气，食物，水皆为生命不可缺者。<br>\n A good dictionary is indispensable for learning a foreign language.<br>     学习外语离不开好的词典。<br>'),(4724,'indistinct','','','','','a. 不清楚的',' His indistinct speech made it impossible to understand him.<br>     他口齿不清, 无法听懂他的意思.<br>\n A low grumble or indistinct utterance.<br>     咕哝低声地嘟哝或者不清楚地说话<br>'),(4725,'individual','','','','individuals','a. 个别的<br>\nn. 个人,个体',' She has her own individual way of walking.<br>     她有自己独特的走路姿势。<br>\n A teacher can\'t give individual attention to each pupil if his class is large.<br>     如果班上的人数多，老师就不能给予个别辅导了。<br>'),(4726,'individually','','','','','ad. 个别地',' Individually the children are delightful; en masse they can be unbearable.<br>     孩子们单独时还讨人喜欢, 一多了就受不了了.<br>\n Individually, the children are quite nice, but in a group they badly behave.<br>     这些孩子单独呆著时都挺不错，可是聚在一起就没规没矩了。<br>'),(4727,'indoor','','','','','a. 户内的,室内的',' All roams are equipped with electric heaters to keep indoor temperatures constant at15-2.0.<br>     所有的房间都装备有电炉以保持室内撮氏15－20度的常温。<br>\n You stay indoors too much.<br>     你呆在室内的时间太多了。<br>'),(4728,'indoors','','','','','ad. 在户内',' You stay indoors too much.<br>     你呆在室内的时间太多了。<br>\n The heavy rain compelled us to stay indoors.<br>     大雨迫使我们呆在户内。<br>'),(4729,'induce','induced','induced','inducing','','v. 引诱,招致,感应',' Too much food induces sleepiness.<br>     吃得太饱会引起睡意。<br>\n We couldn\'t induce the old lady to travel by air.<br>     我们无法劝服那老太太乘飞机旅行。<br>'),(4730,'inducement','','','','inducements','n. 诱因,动机,刺激物',' He hasn\'t much inducement to study English.<br>     他没有学习英语的兴趣。<br>\n They have little inducement to work harder.<br>     没有什么可以使他们更加努力工作。<br>'),(4731,'induction','','','','inductions','n. 感应,感应现象<br>\n归纳法',' The centimeter-gram-second unit of magnetic induction, equal to one maxwell per square centimeter.<br>     高斯电磁感应的厘米－克－秒单位，等于每平方厘米的麦克斯韦尔<br>'),(4732,'indulge','indulged','indulged','indulging','','v. 纵情于,放任,迁就',' It pleased me to indulge her wishes.<br>     放手满足她的欲望，使我感到高兴。<br>\n He no longer indulged himself in smoking.<br>     他不再过度吸烟了。<br>'),(4733,'indulgence','','','','indulgences','n. 耽溺,放纵,嗜好',' Sweets are my only indulgence.<br>     甜食是我唯一的嗜好。<br>\n I must ask the readers\' kind indulgence for any inaccuracies and omissions that may possibly occur.<br>     我必须请求读者原谅可能出现的错误和疏漏。<br>'),(4734,'industrial','','','','industrials','a. 工业的,产业的',' England is an advanced industrial country.<br>     英国是一个发达的工业国家。<br>\n The industrial revolution had taken place in England first.<br>     工业革命首先在英国发生。<br>'),(4735,'industrialist','','','','industrialists','n. 工业家,实业家',' Nobel\'s greatness lay in the outstanding ability to combine the quality of an original scientists with those of a forward-looking industrialist.<br>     诺贝尔的伟大在于他具有把独创性科学家的品质与卓有远见的企业家的品质相互结合起来的杰出能力。<br>\n Scottish-born American industrialist and philanthropist who amassed a fortune in the steel industry and donated millions of dollars for the benefit of the public.<br>     卡内基，戴尔1888－1955美国教育家，因著有一本自我修养的书如何赢得朋友及影响人民（1936年）而闻名<br>'),(4736,'industrialization','','','','','n. 工业化',''),(4737,'industrialize','industrialized','industrialized','industrializing','','v. 使...业化,工业化',' Many townships in the coastal area have begin to industrialize.<br>     沿海地区的许多乡镇已开始工业化。<br>'),(4738,'industrialized','','','','','a. 工业化的',' The energy shortage of the world results partly from wasteful use by the industrialized countries.<br>     世界能源的短缺，部分是由于工业化国家挥霍能源而引起的。<br>'),(4739,'industrious','','','','','a. 勤劳的,勤奋的',' The Chinese are industrious people.<br>     中国人民是一个勤劳的民族。<br>\n He is an industrious worker.<br>     他是一个勤劳的工人。<br>'),(4740,'industry','','','','industries','n. 工业,产业,勤勉,刻苦',' The tourist trade has become a real industry.<br>     旅游业已经成为真正的产业。<br>\n Success comes with industry.<br>     成功来自勤奋。<br>'),(4741,'ineffective','','','','','a. 无效的',' One that is disappointingly ineffective or unsuccessful.<br>     无用的人或物的令人失望的无用的或不成功的人或物<br>'),(4742,'ineffectiveness','','','','','n. 低效率',''),(4743,'inefficiency','','','','inefficiencies','n. 无效率,无能',' The inefficiency of one department can bring a whole industry into disrepute.<br>     只要有一个部门的效率不高，就会使整个行业的名声受到影响。<br>\n In his speech he kept pounding away at his opponent\'s inefficiency.<br>     他在演说中不断攻击他的对手不称职。<br>'),(4744,'inefficient','','','','','a. 无效率的,无能的',' The quality, condition, or fact of being inefficient.<br>     无效率具有效率低的性质，处于无效率的状态或无效率的事实<br>\n He\'s hopelessly inefficient, but I suppose he means well.<br>     他低能得无以复加，然而却是出於好心。<br>'),(4745,'inept','','','','','a. 不适当的,无能的,笨拙的',' His inept handling of a minor problem turned it into a major crisis.<br>     他处理不善使小事变大了.<br>\n I\'ve never heard anyone so inept at making speeches.<br>     我从未听说过有这样不会讲话的人.<br>'),(4746,'inert','','','','','a. 惰性的,迟钝的',' She lay there inert, I thought she must be dead.<br>     她躺在那儿一动不动，我想她一定是死了。<br>\n There is an inert management team in our company.<br>     我们公司的管理阶层死气沉沉。<br>'),(4747,'inertia','','','','','n. 惯性,惰性',' The inertia of an entrenched bureaucracy.<br>     平稳的官僚机构内存在的惰性<br>\n Because of the sheer inertia of the system many badly needed reform is never introduced.<br>     纯粹是由於制度本身有惰性，很多事急需改革却从未实行。<br>'),(4748,'inevitable','','','','','a. 不可避免的,必然(发生)的',' An argument was inevitable because they disliked each other so much.<br>     争论是不可避免的，因为他们彼此非常厌恶。<br>\n Positions surrendered to our troops earlier in the day had now to be prepared against the inevitable counter-attack.<br>     那天早些时候迫使敌人放弃给我军的阵地现在需要布置起来，对付那必然的反攻。<br>'),(4749,'inevitably','','','','','ad. 不可避免地',' Of necessity; inevitably.<br>     必然必需地，不可避免地<br>\n Inevitably, a quarrel followed between the two sides.<br>     双方随後不可避免地争吵起来。<br>'),(4750,'inexact','','','','','a. 不正确的,不确实的,不精密的',' Weather forecasting is an inexact science.<br>     天气预报是一门模糊的科学.<br>\n An inexact result adequate for a given purpose.<br>     近似值适用于给定目标的不精确结论<br>'),(4751,'inexpensive','','','','','a. 不贵的',' This piece of furniture is really inexpensive with a price of less than forty dollars.<br>     这件家具还不到四十美元，实在不贵。<br>\n An alloy of copper with zinc and sometimes other metals, used in making inexpensive jewelry.<br>     顿巴黄铜铜与锌，有时还有其它金属的合金，用来制造廉价珠宝<br>'),(4752,'inexperienced','','','','','a. 无经验的,不熟练的',' He is inexperienced in business.<br>     他在经商方面没有经验。<br>\n We don\'t want to hire inexperienced worker.<br>     我们不想聘用没有经验的工人。<br>'),(4753,'infancy','','','','','n. 幼年,初期,幼儿期',' Our new plan is still only in its infancy.<br>     我们的新计划仍处于摇篮阶段。<br>\n Tadpoles are the infancy form of frogs.<br>     蝌蚪是青蛙的幼年形态。<br>'),(4754,'infant','','','','infants','a. 婴儿的,幼稚的,初期的<br>\nn. 婴儿,幼儿',' My sister\'s infant is very lovely.<br>     我姐姐的小婴儿非常可爱。<br>\n The information industry is an infant industry in our country.<br>     信息产业在我国是新兴产业。<br>'),(4755,'infanticide','','','','','n. 杀婴',''),(4756,'infantile','','','','','a. 婴儿的,幼稚的,初期的',' Her unconscious looks wander to her husband with infantile dependency.<br>     带著像婴儿般的依赖她不由自主地把目光投向了她的丈夫。<br>\n An adult or a young person who behaves in an infantile way.<br>     孩子气的人行为表现出孩子气的成年人或年轻人<br>'),(4757,'infantry','','','','','n. 步兵(部队)',' The infantry are defending well.<br>     步兵防守甚佳。<br>\n We have less infantry than the enemy.<br>     我们的步兵比敌军少。<br>'),(4758,'infect','infected','infected','infecting','','v. 传染,感染',' The young teacher infected the whole class with her enthusiasm.<br>     这位年轻的老师以她的热诚感染了全班。<br>\n The open wound soon became infected.<br>     裸露的伤口很快就受到了感染。<br>'),(4759,'infected','','','','','被感染的',' We should not be infected by erroneous ideas.<br>     我们不应该受错误观念的影响。<br>\n He was infected with a latent infection.<br>     他被感染了一种潜伏性的传染病。<br>'),(4760,'infection','','','','infections','n. 传染,影响,传染病',' We should pay more attention to the infection of young people with dangerous ideologies.<br>     我们应该多注意危险的思想意识对年轻人的影响。<br>\n People catch all kinds of infections in the winter.<br>     冬天人们易患多种传染病。<br>'),(4761,'infectious','','','','','a. 传染的',' He expressed infectious enthusiasm to his voters.<br>     他对他的选民表现出很有感染力的热情。<br>\n When you have this anthema, you are still infectious.<br>     身上还有这种疹子就仍然有传染性。<br>'),(4762,'infective','','','','','a. 易传染的,传染性的',''),(4763,'infer','inferred','inferred','inferring','','v. 推论,推断',' It is possible to infer two completely opposite conclusions from this set of facts.<br>     从这些事实中可能推断出两种截然相反的结论。<br>\n Can I infer that you think I\'m not telling the truth?<br>     看来你认为我没说实话？<br>'),(4764,'inference','','','','inferences','n. 推论',' If he is guilty, then by inference so is she.<br>     如果他有罪，可以推断出她也有罪。<br>\n She\'d begun spending a lot of money, and the obvious inference was that she\'d stolen it.<br>     她花起钱来大手大脚了，事情很明显，钱是偷来的。<br>'),(4765,'inferior','','','','inferiors','a. 次等的,较低的,不如的',' He\'s so clever, he makes me feel inferior.<br>     他那么聪明，让我自愧不如。<br>\n These people occupy an inferior position in local society.<br>     这些人在当地社会居于下等地位。<br>'),(4766,'inferiority','','','','','n. 自卑,次等',' Some of them developed a great inferiority complex.<br>     他们有些人养成了严重的自卑感。<br>\n Most people enjoy the inferiority of their best friend.<br>     大多数人都以他们最好的朋友的自卑感为乐。<br>'),(4767,'inferiors','','','','','下级的,差的',' Most inferior, as in quality, condition, or effect.<br>     最差的在质量、条件或效果方面最差的<br>\n He is gracious to his inferiors.<br>     他待下级和蔼可亲。<br>'),(4768,'infest','infested','infested','infesting','','v. 骚扰,群居于,大批出没',' It\'s a garden infested with weeds.<br>     这是杂草丛生的花园。<br>\n There is a warehouse infested by rats.<br>     那有一个大批老鼠出没的仓库。<br>'),(4769,'infiltration','','','','','n. 浸润',''),(4770,'infinite','','','','','a. 无限的,无穷的<br>\nn. 无限',' Teaching little children takes infinite patience.<br>     教幼儿需有极大的耐心。<br>\n The number of positive numbers is infinite.<br>     正数的数目是无穷的。<br>'),(4771,'infinitely','','','','','ad. 无限地,无穷地',' The particles in an atom are infinitely small.<br>     原子里的粒子极小.<br>\n That was infinitely better than his last film.<br>     这比他上一部电影不知胜过多少倍。<br>'),(4772,'infinitive','','','','infinitives','n. 不定词<br>\na. 不定词的',''),(4773,'infinity','','','','infinities','n. 无限大,无限',' Multiply y by infinity.<br>     以无穷数乘y.<br>\n Can you represent infinity to yourself?<br>     你能在心想像无限吗？<br>'),(4774,'infirmary','','','','infirmaries','n. 虚弱,弱点<br>\n   治疗室',''),(4775,'infix','','','','','插入',''),(4776,'inflame','inflamed','inflamed','inflaming','','v. 激怒,点火,使...发炎',' He was inflamed with anger.<br>     他满腔怒火。<br>\n The setting sun inflames the sky.<br>     落日映红天空。<br>'),(4777,'inflammable','','','','inflammables','a. 易燃的,易怒的',' Petrol is highly inflammable.<br>     汽油是高度易燃的。<br>'),(4778,'inflammation','','','','inflammations','n. 发炎,红肿,炎症',' He has an inflammation of the lungs.<br>     他得了肺炎。<br>\n The discharge that is characteristic of this inflammation.<br>     粘膜液体排出物具有这种炎症特征的排出物<br>'),(4779,'inflate','inflated','inflated','inflating','','v. 使膨胀,使得意,使通货膨胀<br>\n[计算机] 使膨胀',' With a supply of compressed air the large balloon inflated in a matter of seconds.<br>     大气球注入压缩空气後, 几秒钟就充足了气.<br>'),(4780,'inflation','','','','inflations','n. 通货膨胀',' The government is determined to bring down inflation.<br>     政府决心把通货膨胀率降低。<br>\n There appears to be a growing discontent about inflation.<br>     对通货膨胀似乎有一种日渐增长的不满情绪。<br>'),(4781,'inflexible','','','','','a. 不屈曲的,不屈挠的,顽固的',' Stubbornly prejudiced, narrow-minded, or inflexible.<br>     思想偏狭顽固的、迂腐的或守旧的<br>\n Not bending; inflexible.<br>     坚挺的不能弯曲的；坚挺的<br>'),(4782,'inflict','inflicted','inflicted','inflicting','','v. 施以,加害,科以',' Don\'t inflict your belief on me.<br>     不要把你的想法强加于我。<br>\n We should inflict severe chastisement on criminals.<br>     我们应该对罪犯施加严厉的惩罚。<br>'),(4783,'influence','influenced','influenced','influencing','influences','v. 影响,感化<br>\nn. 影响力,感化力,势力,权势',' He is a man of some influence in the government circles.<br>     他是个在政府内有一定势力的人。<br>\n Listening to the music has a calming influence on her.<br>     听音乐对她起了一种镇静的作用。<br>'),(4784,'influential','','','','','a. 有权势的,有影响的',' Our newspaper is an influential newspaper in this city.<br>     我们的报纸在本市有很大影响力。<br>\n He used his influential friends to help him get into the civil service by the back door.<br>     他利用那些有权有势的朋友帮助他走後门, 到政府行政部门任职.<br>'),(4785,'influenza','','','','','n. 流行性感冒',' We all had influenza last night.<br>     我们昨晚都患了流感。<br>\n I have an influenza epidemic.<br>     我得了流行性感冒。<br>'),(4786,'influx','','','','influxes','n. 流入,河口,辐辏<br>\n涌进;汇集[C][S1]<br>\nan influx of customers<br>\n顾客的蜂拥而来',' Textile workers favoured protection because they feared an influx of cheap cloth.<br>     纺织工人拥护贸易保护措施, 因为他们担心涌入廉价纺织品.<br>'),(4787,'info','','','','','信息,情报',' Please turn the article info English.<br>     请把这篇文章译成英语。<br>'),(4788,'inform','informed','informed','informing','','v. 告诉,通知<br>\nvi. 检举,告发<br>\nvt. 通知,告诉,向...报告',' I wasn\'t informed of the decision until too late.<br>     等到我得知这项决定时，已经太迟了。<br>\n Our only resort is to inform the police.<br>     我们唯一的办法就是向警方报案.<br>'),(4789,'informal','','','','','a. 非正式的',' We had an informal meeting.<br>     我们做了非正式的会晤。<br>\n These words are informal.<br>     这些词是非正式用语。<br>'),(4790,'information','','','','','n. 信息',' The police haven\'t got enough information to catch the criminal.<br>     警方还未得到可捉拿这个罪犯的足够情报。<br>\n Can you give me any information on this matter?<br>     关于此事，你能给我提供什么消息吗？<br>'),(4791,'informative','','','','','a. 情报的,使知道消息的,见闻广博的',' It will be most interesting and informative to hear Mr. Smith.<br>     届时能聆听到史密斯先生演讲，定会是极为有趣和增长见识的。<br>\n Sam placed his new book on one side for a year while he wrote some magazine articles and informative material.<br>     萨姆把写新书的工作搁置了一年时间，在这段时间里他写了一些杂志文章和报道材料。<br>'),(4792,'infrared','','','','','a. 红外线的<br>\nn. 红外线(的)',' Any of several devices that convert incident electromagnetic radiation of mixed frequencies to one or more discrete frequencies of highly amplified and coherent ultraviolet, visible, or infrared radiation.<br>     激光器使偶然的混杂频率的电磁辐射，变为一个或更多的高度强化和连续的紫外线、可见光或红外线辐射的分离频率仪器中的一种<br>'),(4793,'infrastructure','','','','','n. 下部构造,下部组织,基础结构，基础设施',' Our city offer overseas in vesture fair service for production aside from infrastructure.<br>     我市除了向外国投资者提供基础设施外，还提供良好的生产服务设施。<br>'),(4794,'infrequent','','','','','a. 稀少的,珍贵的,罕见的',' Explosions, though infrequent, are an occupational hazard for coal-miners.<br>     矿井爆炸虽然不常发生, 但却是煤矿工人职业中的危险.<br>\n Difficult, incomplete, or infrequent evacuation of dry, hardened feces from the bowels.<br>     便秘有困难的、不完全的或不经常从肠道排泄干燥且硬的大便<br>'),(4795,'infringe','infringed','infringed','infringing','','v. 破坏,犯,违反',' The publishing house infringed his copyright.<br>     出版社侵犯了他的版权。<br>\n They infringed on her rights.<br>     他们侵犯了她的权力。<br>'),(4796,'infringement','infringed','infringed','infringed','','n. 违反(侵犯)',' That law is an out-and-out infringement of our civil rights.<br>     （那项法令完全侵犯了我们的公民权。）<br>'),(4797,'ingenious','','','','','a. 机灵的,精制的,有独创性的',' This book shows that he is an ingenious author.<br>     这本书表明他是一个有创造力的作家。<br>\n I have an ingenious contrivance to get her to sign the document without reading it.<br>     我有一条不经她过目就签署文件的妙计。<br>'),(4798,'ingenuity','','','','ingenuities','n. 智巧,创造力,精巧的设计',' It took some ingenuity to squeeze all the furniture into the little room.<br>     把全部家具都塞进那个小房间是很费了一番心思的。<br>\n Something, such as a toy or game, that tests one\'s ingenuity.<br>     测智力游戏检验一个人的智力的东西，例如玩具或游戏<br>'),(4799,'ingest','ingested','ingested','ingesting','','v. 摄取',' Material, usually of plant or animal origin, that contains or consists of essential body nutrients, such as carbohydrates, fats, proteins, vitamins, or minerals, and is ingested and assimilated by an organism to produce energy, stimulate growth, and maintain life.<br>     食物，粮食通常是源于植物和动物的物质，包含有人体营养物的必不可少物质或由其组成如：糖类、脂肪、蛋白质、维他命和矿物质等，由产生能量、促进发育和维持生命的组织消化和吸收<br>\n A small stone found in the stomach of some reptiles, fish, and birds that aids in digestion by helping grind ingested food material.<br>     胃石一种小石头，常发现于某些爬虫、鱼和鸟的胃中，通过帮助碾磨食物来帮助消化<br>'),(4800,'ingestion','','','','','n. 吸收,咽下',''),(4801,'ingredient','','','','ingredients','n. 成分,因素',' There is a list of ingredients on the side of the packet.<br>     包装袋的边上印有所含配料表。<br>\n A source of nourishment, especially a nourishing ingredient in a food.<br>     营养品，滋养物营养的来源，尤指食物中的营养成分<br>'),(4802,'inhabit','inhabited','inhabited','inhabiting','','v. 居住于,占据,栖息',' Only a few people inhabited the island.<br>     只有少数人在这个岛上居住。<br>\n Fish inhabit the sea.<br>     鱼栖息于海中。<br>'),(4803,'inhabitant','','','','inhabitants','n. 居民',' He lives in a city with 100000 inhabitants.<br>     他住在一个有十万居民的城市。<br>\n A native or inhabitant of Elam.<br>     埃兰人埃兰本地人或居民<br>'),(4804,'inhalation','','','','inhalations','n. 吸入,吸入药剂',' One that vaporizes, especially a device used to vaporize medicine for inhalation.<br>     蒸发器蒸发的器具，尤其是用于蒸发吸入药剂的装置<br>\n A chronic, progressive lung disease caused by prolonged inhalation of asbestos particles.<br>     石棉沉着病由长期吸收石棉微粒而引起的慢性，日趋严重的肺病<br>'),(4805,'inhale','inhaled','inhaled','inhaling','','v. 吸入',' He inhaled deeply.<br>     他深深地吸了口气。<br>\n Follow me please, inhale! exhale!<br>     跟我做，吸气!呼气!<br>'),(4806,'inherent','','','','','a. 内在的,固有的',' There is an inherent weakness in the design.<br>     这设计本身存在弱点。<br>\n Inherent quality of character and temperament.<br>     内在的气质性格、脾气的内在气质<br>'),(4807,'inherit','inherited','inherited','inheriting','','v. 继承',' She inherited all her mother\'s beauty.<br>     她秉承了她母亲的全部美貌。<br>\n The oldest son will inherit the title.<br>     长子将继承爵位。<br>'),(4808,'inheritance','','','','inheritances','n. 遗传,遗产',' On the maternal side his inheritance was a happy one.<br>     他从母方接受的遗传是良好的。<br>\n He was cheated (out) of his rightful inheritance.<br>     他依法应得的遗产被人骗走了.<br>'),(4809,'inhibit','inhibited','inhibited','inhibiting','','v. 禁止,抑制<br>\n[计算机] 禁止',' The act of inhibiting or the state of being inhibited.<br>     禁止禁止的动作或被禁止的状态<br>\n A chemical substance used to destroy or inhibit the growth of plants, especially weeds.<br>     灭草剂用来摧毁或抑制植物，尤指杂草的生长的化学物质<br>'),(4810,'inhibited','','','','','a. 羞怯的, 内向的',' Shyness inhibited him from speaking.<br>     他因害羞而说不出话来.<br>\n A symbiotic relationship between organisms in which one species is harmed or inhibited and the other species is unaffected.<br>     片害共栖有机体之间共生的作用关系，一个物种受另一个物种侵害或抑制，而后者不受前者的影响<br>'),(4811,'inhibition','','','','','n. 禁止,禁制,压抑',' Inhibition of natural impulses may cause psychological problems.<br>     压抑自然的冲动可能会引起心理上的问题。<br>\n The inhibition of growth in one species of plants by chemicals produced by another species.<br>     植物毒素抑制，植物相克一种植物的生长因另一种植物所产生的化学物质而被抑制<br>'),(4812,'initial','initialed','initialed','initialing','initials','n. 词首大写字母<br>\na. 开始的,最初的,字首的<br>\nv. 签姓名的首字母',' Please write down your initials on each page of the paper.<br>     请在每页考卷上写下名字的首字母。<br>\n The word `hour\' is pronounced without an initial aspirate.<br>     hour一字的开头字母h不发送气音.<br>'),(4813,'initialization','','','','','n. 初始化,赋初值',' The initialization of a data medium such that a particular computer system can store data in and subsequently retrieve data from the medium.<br>     数据媒体的初始化，使某一特定计算机系统能将数据存在媒体中，随后又可从该媒体中检索出来。<br>'),(4814,'initialize','','','','','v. 初始化',''),(4815,'initially','','','','','ad. 最初,开头',' Initially, I disagree with his proposal, but later I changed my mind.<br>     起初我不同意他的提议，不过后来我改了主意。<br>\n She came initially to spend a few days, but in the end she stayed for a whole month.<br>     起先她只打算来待几天，但後来却住了整整一个月。<br>'),(4816,'initiate','','','','','n. 入会,开始<br>\na. 新加入的<br>\nvt. 开始,创始,启蒙',''),(4817,'initiative','','','','initiatives','a. 创始的,初步的,自发的<br>\nn. 第一步,首创精神',' It\'s only the initiative of the investigation.<br>     这仅仅是调查的开始。<br>\n The child displayed great initiative in going to fetch the police.<br>     那孩子极为主动地把警察找来。<br>'),(4818,'initiator','','','','','n. 创始者,首倡者,发起人',''),(4819,'inject','injected','injected','injecting','','v. 注射',' His medicine is a drug that can be injected or taken by mouth.<br>     他的药可以注射或口服。<br>\n The nurse injected penicillin into her arm.<br>     护士给她的胳膊注射了青霉素。<br>'),(4820,'injection','','','','injections','n. 注射',' The doctor gave her an injection to alleviate the pain.<br>     医生给她注射以减轻疼痛.<br>\n I had a bad reaction after my typhoid injection.<br>     我注射伤寒针剂後产生了不良反应。<br>'),(4821,'injure','injured','injured','injuring','','v. 伤害,使...受冤屈',' She was injured badly in the accident.<br>     她在事故中受重伤。<br>\n He injured his left hand in a fire.<br>     他在火灾中伤了左手。<br>'),(4822,'injury','','','','injuries','n. 受伤处,损害,伤害',' He suffered serious injuries to the arms and legs.<br>     他的双臂和双腿严重受伤。<br>\n The injury to their key player could be a decisive factor in the game.<br>     他们主力队员受伤可能是这场比赛胜负的决定性因素。<br>'),(4823,'injustice','','','','injustices','n. 不公正',' Justice will triumph over injustice.<br>     正义必将战胜非正义。<br>\n Wherever there is injustice, we try to help.<br>     凡有不公正的地方, 我们都竭力相助匡正.<br>'),(4824,'ink','inked','inked','inking','','n. 墨水',' The printing ink has been used up.<br>     印刷油墨用光了。<br>\n The little boy stained his fingers with ink.<br>     小男孩的手指让墨水给染脏了。<br>'),(4825,'inland','','','','','a. 内陆的,国内的',' Beijing is an inland city.<br>     北京是一个内陆城市。<br>\n Situated away from the sea; inland.<br>     内河的远离海的；内陆的<br>'),(4826,'inlet','','','','','n. 插入物',' Here is just the fuel inlet.<br>     这儿正是燃料入口。<br>\n The capital of New Zealand, on an inlet of Cook Strait in extreme southern North Island. It was founded in1840 and supplanted Auckland as capital in1865. Population, 133,200.<br>     威灵顿新西兰的首都，位于新西兰北岛最南端的库克海峡的小港内。建于1840年，在1865年它代替奥克兰成为首都。人口133，200<br>'),(4827,'inline','','','','','在线的,联机的',''),(4828,'inn','','','','inns','n. 客栈,小旅店',' It was raining; they had to stay in the inn the whole day.<br>     下雨了，他们不得不在旅馆里待了一整天。<br>\n They put up at an inn for the night.<br>     他们在一家小客栈里过夜.<br>'),(4829,'inner','','','','','a. 内部的,里面的,内心的<br>\nn. 里面,内部',' She went into the inner room to change her dress.<br>     她走进内室去换衣服。<br>\n Her artificial gaiety disguised an inner sadness.<br>     她以矫揉造作的快乐掩饰著内心的悲痛.<br>'),(4830,'innocence','','','','innocences','n. 无罪,无知,天真无邪',' Her innocence is only an imitation.<br>     她的天真只是一种伪装。<br>\n The accused man proved his innocence of crime.<br>     被告人经证实无罪。<br>'),(4831,'innocent','','','','','a. 无罪的,不懂事的,无知的,无辜的',' He was charged with murder but found innocent later.<br>     他被控杀人，但后来发现他是无罪的。<br>\n She asserted that he was innocent.<br>     她断言，他是无罪的。<br>'),(4832,'innovate','innovated','innovated','innovating','','v. 改革,创新',''),(4833,'innovation','','','','innovations','n. 创新,革新',' It was a period of innovation.<br>     这是革新时期。<br>\n After being led by him, one innovation after another are showing.<br>     从他领导后，一个又一个革新项目出现了。<br>'),(4834,'innumerable','','','','','a. 无数的,数不清的',' The stars in the night sky are innumerable.<br>     夜空中的星星数不清。<br>\n Any of innumerable small bodies thought to have orbited the sun during the formation of the planets.<br>     星子任何数不清的小固体块，被认为曾在行星形成阶段中在围绕太阳的轨道上运行<br>'),(4835,'inoculation','','','','','n. 接插芽,接木,接种',' Inoculation with a vaccine made from microorganisms obtained from the recipient\'s own body.<br>     自体接种利用从受体自身获得的微生物制备的疫苗作接种<br>\n The material used in an inoculation.<br>     接种体，种菌在接种中用的材料<br>'),(4836,'inorganic','','','','','a. 无机的',' Synthesis of carbohydrate from carbon dioxide and water using energy obtained from the chemical oxidation of simple inorganic compounds. This form of synthesis is limited to certain bacteria and fungi.<br>     化学合成用简单无机化合物的化学氧化所产生的能量将二氧化碳和水合成碳水化合物。这种化学合成形式只限于某些细菌和真菌<br>\n Farmers enrich the soil with organic and inorganic manures.<br>     农民用有机肥料和无机肥料来提高土壤的肥力。<br>'),(4837,'input','input','input','inputting','','n. 输入',' Two input keys don\'t work.<br>     有两个输入键有毛病。<br>\n I have inputted the data into a computer.<br>     我已经把数据输入到计算机中了。<br>'),(4838,'inquire','inquired','inquired','inquiring','','v. 询问,问明,查究',' I inquired of him about their work.<br>     我向他了解他们的工作情况。<br>\n We inquired the way of a boy.<br>     我们向一个男孩问路。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (4839,'inquiry','','','','inquiries','n. 打听,询问,调查,查问',' The police are making inquiries about the crime.<br>     警方正在询问罪案的情况。<br>\n The inquiry was critical of her work.<br>     该项调查对她的工作提出了批评。<br>'),(4840,'Ins','','','','','insert 插入键',' I know all the ins and outs of our school building.<br>     我知道我们教学大楼的一切情况。<br>\n The room is 15 feet in length and 10 feet in breadth.<br>     这房间长15英尺，宽10英尺。<br>'),(4841,'insane','','','','','a. 疯狂的,精神错乱的',' I have an insane desire to finish that thing.<br>     我疯狂地渴望去完成那件事。<br>\n That person is insane.<br>     那人精神错乱。<br>'),(4842,'inscribing','','','','','n. 登记,买或卖股票,注册',' At length she bethought herself of writing, and inscribed her name-it was a short one-with her hoof on the sand.<br>     最后她终于想到了写字，用一只蹄子把她的名字－－很短的一个名字－－划在沙地上。<br>\n She inscribed his name on the book.<br>     她将他的名字题写于书上。<br>'),(4843,'inscription','','','','inscriptions','n. 题字,碑铭',' I can\'t read the inscription on this stone because it\'s getting dark.<br>     天黑了，我看不见这块石头上的碑文。<br>\n Time and weather had long ago effaced the inscription on the monument.<br>     岁月和风雨早已磨掉纪念碑上的铭文。<br>'),(4844,'insect','','','','insects','n. 昆虫',' A locust is a kind of destructive insect.<br>     蝗虫是一种害虫。<br>\n Most of us would draw the line somewhere, like the man who said he\'d try anything once except insect and folk dancing.<br>     就像那个说他除了昆虫和民间舞蹈啥都想试试的人一样，我们大多数人心里都有个人界线，知道该在哪儿收手。<br>'),(4845,'insert','','','','','n. 插入物<br>\nv. 插入',' She inserted the key into the lock.<br>     她把钥匙插入锁中。<br>\n A triangular insert, as in the seam of a garment, for added strength or expansion.<br>     衬料一种三角形的插入物，在衣服的缝合处，为加固或加大衣服而用<br>'),(4846,'insertion','','','','insertions','n. 插入,刊载,插入物',' There are many insertions of advertisement in the newspapers.<br>     报纸上有很多插入的广告。<br>\n He put a coin into the insertion slot.<br>     他往投币孔投入一枚硬币。<br>'),(4847,'inside','','','','insides','a. 里面的<br>\nad. 在里面<br>\nn. 内部<br>\nprep. 在...里面',' This lock can only be opened from the inside.<br>     这把锁只能从里面打开。<br>\n We have to play inside because it is raining.<br>     因为天下雨，我们不得不在屋里玩。<br>'),(4848,'insider','','','','','n. 内部的人,会员,知道内情的人',''),(4849,'insight','','','','insights','n. 洞察力',' I\'ve got an insight into the problem.<br>     我对问题豁然开朗。<br>\n The book is filled with remarkable insights.<br>     这本书很有真知卓见。<br>'),(4850,'insignificant','','','','','a. 无关紧要的,可忽略的',' His hometown is an insignificant city on the map.<br>     他的家乡只是地图上一个不起眼的小城。<br>\n It is a waste of time to listen to his insignificant talk.<br>     听他那些废话纯属浪费时间。<br>'),(4851,'insipid','','','','','a. 乏味的,枯燥的',' Sickening or insipid in taste.<br>     （味道上）令人作呕的，淡而无味的<br>\n Insipid; weak; wishy-washy.<br>     无味的；缺乏生气的；软弱无力的<br>'),(4852,'insist','insisted','insisted','insisting','','v. 坚持,强调',' He insisted on paying for the meal.<br>     他坚持要付饭钱。<br>\n Since you insist, I must amend the letter of credit.<br>     既然你坚持，我就只好修改信用证。<br>'),(4853,'insistent','','','','','a. 坚持的,迫切的',' She\'s a most insistent person; she won\'t take `no\' for an answer.<br>     她是个说一不二的人, 决不容别人反对.<br>\n You mustn\'t be late; he was most insistent about that.<br>     你万不可迟到, 他对这一点最严格.<br>'),(4854,'insofar','','','','','ad. 在...范围内',' I\'ll help you insofar as I can.<br>     我将尽力帮助你。<br>\n \"Insofar as I can see, the representatives are all satisfied with the arrangement.\"<br>     ＂据我了解，代表们对这一安排都感到满意。＂<br>'),(4855,'insolent','','','','','a. 粗野的,无礼的',' His staff is insolent to our manager.<br>     他的员工对我们的经理很无礼。<br>\n You insolent young puppy!<br>     你这个目中无人的小子!<br>'),(4856,'insolvent','','','','','a. 无力偿还的,破产的<br>\nn. 无力还偿者,破产者',' A debtor that, upon voluntary petition or one invoked by the debtor\'s creditors, is judged legally insolvent. The debtor\'s remaining property is then administered for the creditors or is distributed among them.<br>     破产者经自愿请求或被债务人的债权人所请求，在法律上被判定为无偿债能力的债务人。该债务人的剩余财产交由债权人管理或在债权人之间分配<br>\n A priority of payment given to one or more creditors by an insolvent debtor.<br>     优先偿付由破产负债人给予一个或多个债权人的优先偿付<br>'),(4857,'inspect','inspected','inspected','inspecting','','v. 检查,调查,监查,检阅',' It was strange that nobody inspected my ticket before I got on the train.<br>     很奇怪，我上火车前，竟然没有人查看我的车票。<br>\n Police were called out to keep at the airport, and inspect the arriving planes.<br>     警察们被紧急召集起来去守卫机场，并对到达的飞机进行检查。<br>'),(4858,'inspection','','','','inspections','n. 检查,视察',' The soldiers lined up for their daily inspection by their officers.<br>     士兵们列队接受长官的日常检阅。<br>\n I gave the radio a thorough inspection before buying it.<br>     我把收音机彻底检查了一遍才买了下来。<br>'),(4859,'inspector','','','','inspectors','n. 检查员,巡视员',' A ticket inspector got on the train.<br>     查票员上了火车。<br>\n We had sundry visitations from the Tax Inspector.<br>     税务检查员常来我们这里, 不胜其烦.<br>'),(4860,'inspiration','','','','inspirations','n. 灵感',' His wife was a constant inspiration to him.<br>     他的妻子经常鼓励他。<br>\n Many poets and artists have drawn their inspiration from nature.<br>     许多诗人和艺术家从大自然中获得他们的灵感。<br>'),(4861,'inspire','inspired','inspired','inspiring','','v. 使...感动,激发,启示',' His best music was inspired by the memory of his mother.<br>     他最好的乐曲创作灵感来自怀念他的母亲。<br>\n The sight inspired him with nostalgia.<br>     这景象激起了他的怀旧之情。<br>'),(4862,'inspired','','','','','a. 有创见的,有灵感的',' His best music was inspired by the memory of his mother.<br>     他最好的乐曲创作灵感来自怀念他的母亲。<br>\n Never before have they been so inspired and so daring as at present.<br>     从来没有看见他们像现在这样精神振奋，意气风发。<br>'),(4863,'inspiring','','','','','a. 令人振奋的',' He possesses the quality of inspiring confidence.<br>     他有本事能让别人信任他.<br>\n The inspiring music acted on the emotions of the students.<br>     那激昂的音乐使学生们情绪激昂。<br>'),(4864,'instability','','','','','n. 不安定,不稳定,基础薄弱',' Insecurity or instability.<br>     不安全或不稳定<br>\n The riot can be considered a symptom of political instability.<br>     这次暴动可看作是政治上不稳定的征兆。<br>'),(4865,'instal','','','','','v. 安装,设置',' The salesman said it would make all the difference to our heating bills if we installed double glazing.<br>     那推销员说，如果我们安装双层玻璃窗的话，我们的暖气帐单就会完全不一样了。<br>\n A tub for bathing, especially one installed in a bathroom.<br>     浴缸澡盆，尤指固定设置在浴室内<br>'),(4866,'install','installed','installed','installing','','v. 安装,安置,使...就职<br>\nn.[计算机] 安装,DOS命令 : 装入结束且驻留软件',' The workers are installing a heating system.<br>     工人们正在安装供暖系统。<br>\n She installed her air-conditioner without help.<br>     没请别人帮助，她自己安装了空调。<br>'),(4867,'installation','','','','installations','n. 安装,装置',' It do provide information of the installation of pop specific software on system other than ad3.<br>     它的确提供除AD3以外系统上POP指定的软件的安装信息。<br>\n The price of these product will just compensate the cost of equipment and installation of the line.<br>     你方生产的产品价格将正好补偿我方提供的设备及安装生产线的费用。<br>'),(4868,'installment','','','','','n. 分期付款(安装,一期)',' We will pay for houses by monthly installments.<br>     我们将按月分期付款买房。<br>\n When will you pay the last installment of the loan?<br>     你什么时候付清最后一期分期贷款？<br>'),(4869,'instalment','','','','','n. 就职,装设,分期付款',' We will pay for houses by monthly instalments.<br>     我们将按月分期付款买房。<br>\n When will you pay the last instalment of the loan?<br>     你什么时候付清最后一期分期贷款？<br>'),(4870,'instance','instanced','instanced','instancing','instances','n. 例子<br>\nv. 举...为例,举例说明',' This is only one instance out of many.<br>     这不过是许多例子中的一个。<br>\n He came at our instance.<br>     他应我们的请求而来。<br>'),(4871,'instant','','','','instants','n. 立即,瞬间<br>\na. 立即的,即时的',' I\'ll be back in an instant.<br>     我马上就回来。<br>\n I took an instant dislike to him.<br>     我一见他就不喜欢。<br>'),(4872,'instantaneous','','','','','a. 瞬间的,即刻的<br>\nad. 瞬间,霎时',' Relief was instantaneous.<br>     痛苦的消除是瞬间的事<br>\n Death is instantaneous in a fatal accident.<br>     在致命的事故中，死亡是即刻发生的。<br>'),(4873,'instantiate','','','','','实例化,例示',''),(4874,'instantly','','','','','ad. 立即地,即刻地',' Please tell me instantly he arrives.<br>     他一到就请告诉我。<br>\n It\'s an instantly recognizable face.<br>     那是我一眼就能认得出的面孔。<br>'),(4875,'instead','','','','','ad. 代替,顶替',' I gave him advice instead of money.<br>     我给了他忠告，而不是钱。<br>\n I made this cake specially, with brown sugar instead of white.<br>     我特别地以红糖代替白糖做了这个蛋糕。<br>'),(4876,'instinct','','','','','a. 充满的<br>\nn. 本能,天性,直觉',' Birds learn to fly by instinct.<br>     鸟类学习飞翔是出于本能。<br>\n Instinct is not always a good guide.<br>     凭本能行事不一定都对.<br>'),(4877,'instinctive','','','','','a. 本能的,天性的',' Running away is our instinctive reaction when we meet danger.<br>     遇到危险时，我们的本能反应就是跑开。<br>\n Set aside for a moment your instinctive dislike of the man.<br>     暂且不要考虑你从直觉上憎恶他这一因素.<br>'),(4878,'institute','instituted','instituted','instituting','institutes','n. 学会,学院,协会<br>\nv. 创立,开始,制定',' He graduated from a famous foreign language institute.<br>     他毕业于一所知名的外语学院。<br>\n The police instituted an inquiry into the cause of the accident.<br>     警方开始调查事故的原因。<br>'),(4879,'institution','','','','institutions','n. 机构,惯例,创立',' Marriage is an institution in most societies.<br>     婚姻是大多数社会早已确立的制度。<br>\n A trustee is a member of managing business affairs of an institution.<br>     理事是机构管理班子中的成员。<br>'),(4880,'instruct','instructed','instructed','instructing','','v. 教,命令,指导<br>\n[计算机] 指示',' His uncle instructed him in French.<br>     他的叔叔教他法语。<br>\n I have been instructed by my agent that you still owe me 100 pounds.<br>     我的代理人通知我，你还欠我100磅。<br>'),(4881,'instruction','','','','instructions','n. 说明,须知,指令,教学',' The teacher gave them instructions to arrive early tomorrow morning.<br>     老师命令他们明天早晨要早到。<br>\n The catechism is used for religious instruction.<br>     教义问答法常用于宗教教学。<br>'),(4882,'instructive','','','','','a. 有益的,教育性的',' This is an instructive book.<br>     这是本有教育意义的书。<br>\n The minister\'s visit to the prison was not instructive.<br>     牧师这次探监没有意义。<br>'),(4883,'instructor','','','','instructors','n. 教师,讲师,指导书',' Our driving instructor is very kind.<br>     我们的驾驶教练非常和善。<br>\n Our instructor told us to keep the room locked.<br>     我们的教导员告诉我们把那间房锁上。<br>'),(4884,'instrument','','','','instruments','n. 乐器,工具,仪器,器械',' The hospital imported some surgical instruments.<br>     医院进口了一些外科器械。<br>\n The organization he had built up eventually became the instrument of his downfall.<br>     他创建起来的组织到头来却成为促使他倒台的根本原因了。<br>'),(4885,'instrumental','','','','instrumentals','a. 仪器的,器具的,可做为手段的',' I was instrumental in catching the criminal.<br>     我曾经协助捉拿这罪犯。<br>\n Our artistic director was instrumental in persuading the orchestra to come.<br>     我们的艺术指导帮助请来管弦乐队。<br>'),(4886,'instrumentation','','','','','仪表化,使用仪器',' The instrumentation is particularly fine.<br>     这首器乐曲编得特别细致.<br>'),(4887,'insufficient','','','','','a. 不足的',' A bank check drawn on insufficient funds to take advantage of the time interval required for collection.<br>     通融票据利用筹款需要的时间间隔开出不足的资金的银行支票<br>\n His children were dwarfed by insufficient food.<br>     他的儿女因营养不良而发育不全。<br>'),(4888,'insulate','insulated','insulated','insulating','','v. 使...绝缘,隔离<br>\n[计算机] 绝缘',' It is important to insulate the furnace from any neighbouring woodwork with brick and asbestos.<br>     用砖和石棉把炉子与周围所有的木制品隔开，这很重要。<br>'),(4889,'insulation','','','','','n. 隔离,孤立,绝缘',' Loss of electric current as a result of faulty insulation.<br>     漏电由于绝缘不好而导致的电流流失<br>\n Cork is often used for insulation.<br>     栓皮经常用作绝缘材料.<br>'),(4890,'insulator','','','','','n. 绝缘体,绝热器',' Conductors let electricity through, but insulators don\'t let through.<br>     导体让电流通过，而绝缘体则不让通过。<br>'),(4891,'insulin','','','','','n. 胰岛素',' Canadian physiologist. He shared a1923 Nobel Prize for the discovery of insulin.<br>     班廷，弗雷德里克·格朗1891－1941加拿大生理学家。因发现了胰岛素而获1923年诺贝尔奖<br>\n American-born Canadian physiologist noted for his work on the discovery and application of insulin.<br>     贝斯特，查尔斯·赫伯特1899－1978美裔加拿大生理学家，因其对胰岛素的发现与应用方面的工作而著名<br>'),(4892,'insult','','','','','侮辱',' He shouted insults at the boy who had kicked him.<br>     他大声辱骂那个踢了他的男孩。<br>\n He felt deeply insulted.<br>     他觉得受了大辱。<br>'),(4893,'insurance','','','','insurances','n. 保险',' He pays out 100 dollars in insurance premiums every year.<br>     他每年付保险费一百美元。<br>\n The accident prompted her to renew her insurance.<br>     这一事故促使她为投保续期.<br>'),(4894,'insure','insured','insured','insuring','','v. 保险,确保,投保...险',' My house is insured against fire.<br>     我的房子保了火险。<br>\n I am insured for all risks.<br>     我给自己保了综合险。<br>'),(4895,'intact','','','','','a. 尚未被人碰过的,原封不动的,完整的',' Few buildings survived the bombing raids intact.<br>     空袭过後幸存的建筑物绝无仅有。<br>\n His honor remained intact.<br>     他的名誉完整无损。<br>'),(4896,'intake','','','','','n. 引入口,入口,通风口',' Our school is gearing up for an increased intake of pupils.<br>     我们学校正在作好准备以接受更多的学生。<br>\n An opening providing a means of entrance or intake.<br>     入口公开地提供入场的方式或入口<br>'),(4897,'intangible','','','','','a. 难以明了的,无形的',' Sound and light are intangible.<br>     声和光是触摸不到的。<br>\n It is an intangible asset, and so be not show as an asset in a company\'s account, unless it figured as part of the purchase price paid when acquiring another company.<br>     商誉是一种无形资产，因为它不作为资产显示在公司的帐目中，除非收购另一公司时将它作为所付购买价格的一部分用数字来表示。<br>'),(4898,'integer','','','','','n. 完整的事物,整体,整数<br>\n[计算机] 整数',' Designating an integer not divisible by two, such as1, 3, and5.<br>     奇数的不能被2整除的整数，如1，3和5<br>'),(4899,'integral','','','','integrals','a. 构成整体所必需的,完整的<br>\nn. [数学] 积分, 完整, 部分',' The kitchen is an integral part of a house.<br>     厨房是房子不可缺的部分<br>\n In a duplicator, a tank that may or may not be an integral part of the machine, providing a reservoir of fluid for the damping system.<br>     复印机中的一个箱体，它可以是也可以不是复印机整体的组成部分，作为减震系统的液体容器。<br>'),(4900,'integrate','integrated','integrated','integrating','','v. 整合,使...成整体<br>\na. 真诚的',''),(4901,'integrated','','','','','a. 整合的<br>\nv. 整合<br>\nvbl. 整合',' I integrated your suggestion with my plan.<br>     你的建议使我的计划完整了。<br>\n I integrated your suggestions into my plans and this has improved them.<br>     我把你的建议采纳到我的计划中，由此改进了我的计划。<br>'),(4902,'integration','','','','','n. 整合,集成',' The policy of making only a perfunctory effort or symbolic gesture toward the accomplishment of a goal, such as racial integration.<br>     表面文章一种只对一个要完成的目标、如种族融合而作一些随意的努力或象征性的姿态的策略<br>\n A plan for the solution of a problem; consists of planning and coding, numerical analysis, systems analysis, specification of printing formats, and any other functions necessary to the integration of a computer in a system.<br>     为解决某一问题而作出的计划，包括规划和编码、数值分析、系统分析、打印格式规定以及把计算机结合进一个系统所必需的其它功能。<br>'),(4903,'integrator','','','','','积分器',''),(4904,'integrity','','','','','n. 诚实,正直,完整,完善',' You can trust him; he is a man of complete integrity.<br>     你可以相信他，他是一个刚正不阿的人。<br>\n Our integrity as a nation is threatened by these separatist forces.<br>     我们国家的完整受到了这些分裂主义势力的威胁。<br>'),(4905,'intellect','','','','intellects','n. 智力，思维逻辑领悟力，理解力/nn. 知识份子，智力高的人，才智超群的人',' Intellect distinguishes humans from other animals.<br>     人类与禽兽之别就在于具有思维能力。<br>\n He is a child of great intellect.<br>     他是个极具聪明才智的男孩。<br>'),(4906,'intellectual','','','','intellectuals','n. 有知识者,知识份子,凭理智做事者<br>\na. 智力的,知性的,聪明的',' The argument was too intellectual for me; I couldn\'t follow a word of it.<br>     这场争论对我来说太深奥了，我一点都搞不明白。<br>\n These views were common among intellectuals.<br>     这些观点在知识分子中很普遍。<br>'),(4907,'intelligence','','','','','n. 理解力,智力<br>\nn. 情报,情报工作,情报机关',' His intelligence quotient is very high.<br>     他的智商很高。<br>\n You should use your intelligence.<br>     你应该发挥你的聪明才智。<br>'),(4908,'intelligent','','','','','a. 聪明的,智能的',' The student gave an intelligent answer.<br>     这个学生给出了一个聪明的回答。<br>\n Someone as intelligent as you should go far.<br>     像你这样聪明的人一定很有作为。<br>'),(4909,'intelligible','','','','','a. 可理解的,易理解的,明了的',' His theory is not intelligible to us.<br>     他的理论我们无法理解。<br>\n Readily comprehended or understood; intelligible.<br>     易懂的易于理解或明白的；易懂的<br>'),(4910,'intend','intended','intended','intending','','v. 打算<br>\nvt. 想要,打算,计划',' I intended to catch the early train, but I didn\'t get up i