,'makeups','化妆品<br>\nn. 组成(接通,补给,修理)',' For the beautiful girl to use makeup would be to gild the lily.<br>     漂亮的姑娘加上化装，是锦上添花。<br>\n I can not tell who\'s who when the women take off their makeup.<br>     女士们卸了妆，我就分辨不出谁是谁。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (5845,'making','','','','','n. 制成',' When it comes to making friends, you cannot be too careful.<br>     一谈到交朋友，你再怎么小心也不为过。<br>\n A large sheet of paper folded once in the middle, making two leaves or four pages of a book or manuscript.<br>     对折纸在中间对折的一张大纸，制成书或手稿中的两张或四页<br>'),(5846,'maladjusted','','','','','a. 调节不良的,不能适应环境的',''),(5847,'maladjustment','','','','','n. 不适应环境,失调',''),(5848,'maladroit','','','','','a. 笨拙的',' His handling of the negotiations was maladroit.<br>     他的谈判技巧十分拙劣.<br>'),(5849,'malady','','','','maladies','n. 病,疾病,弊病',' Violent crime is only one of the maladies afflicting modern society.<br>     暴力犯罪仅仅是危害社会的弊病之一。<br>\n A bodily disorder or disease; a malady or an ailment.<br>     疾病身体的失调或疾病；疾病或小毛病<br>'),(5850,'Malaise','','','','','n. 不舒服',' You can see signs of (a creeping) malaise in our office.<br>     在我们办公室里可以看到有某种（令人不寒而栗的）不安迹象.<br>'),(5851,'malapropism','','','','','词语荒唐误用（指误用发音近似而意义不通的词语）',''),(5852,'malaria','','','','','n. 疟疾',' The boy had a bad attack of malaria.<br>     那个男孩得了严重的疟疾。<br>\n There are many malaria sufferers in hospital.<br>     医院里有很多疟疾病人。<br>'),(5853,'Malay','','','','','a. 马来亚的<br>\nn. 马来人',' A dialect of Malay that is the official language of Indonesia.<br>     印尼语马来语的一种方言，被指定为印度尼西亚的官方语言<br>\n The capital and largest city of Malaysia, on the southwest Malay Peninsula northwest of Singapore. Founded by tin miners in1857, it is the commercial and industrial hub of the country. Population, 937,817.<br>     吉隆坡马来西亚的首都和最大城市，位于马来半岛的西南部、新加坡西北。于1857年由锡矿工人建立，现为该国的商业和工业中心。人口937，817<br>'),(5854,'Malaysia','','','','','n. 马来西亚',' We imported raw rubber from Malaysia.<br>     我们从马来西亚进口生胶。<br>\n There are 13 states in Malaysia.<br>     马来西亚有十三个州.<br>'),(5855,'Malaysian','','','','','a. 马来西亚的,马亚群岛的<br>\nn. 马来西亚人',''),(5856,'malcontent','','','','','a. 抱不平的,不满的,不服的<br>\nn. 不满现状的人',' All the trouble is being caused by a handful of malcontents.<br>     这些是非都是由一小撮不满分子搬弄的.<br>'),(5857,'malcontented','','','','','a. 不满的',' All the trouble is being caused by a handful of malcontents.<br>     这些是非都是由一小撮不满分子搬弄的.<br>'),(5858,'male','','','','males','a. 男性的,雄性的<br>\nn. 男子,雄性动物',' The male is physically stronger than the female.<br>     男性在身体上要比女性强壮。<br>\n This flower is a male flower.<br>     这朵花是雄花。<br>'),(5859,'malediction','','','','','n. 诅咒',''),(5860,'malefactor','','','','','n. 罪人,犯人,坏人',' Malefactors will be pursued and punished.<br>     作恶的人要予以究治.<br>'),(5861,'malevolent','','','','','a. 有恶意的,恶毒的',' Having or showing malice or ill will; malevolent.<br>     恶意的具有或表现出恶意或不良愿望的；含有恶意的<br>\n The quality or state of being malevolent.<br>     恶毒处于邪恶的状态或具有恶毒的特征<br>'),(5862,'malfunction','malfunctioned','malfunctioned','malfunctioning','','n. 故障<br>\nv. 发生故障,不起作用',' Pertaining to the detection and isolation of a malfunction or mistake.<br>     用于修饰或说明与故障或错误的检测和隔离有关的特性。<br>\n A procedure to terminate execution of a program when an unrecoverable error or malfunction occurs.<br>     异常结束当一种无法补救的错误或故障发生时中止计算机程序的运行<br>'),(5863,'Mali','','','','','n. 马里',''),(5864,'malice','','','','','n. 恶意,怨恨',' She certainly bears you no malice.<br>     她对你的确并无恶意。<br>\n It seems so absurd to bear malice after all that.<br>     经过这一切之后还抱有怨恨情绪是很荒谬的。<br>'),(5865,'malicious','','','','','a. 怀恶意的,恶毒的',' He cares nothing about the malicious attack on his reputation.<br>     他对别人对他名声的恶毒攻击置之不理。<br>\n To do her justice, she was never malicious.<br>     说句公道话, 她从来没有恶意。<br>'),(5866,'malign','maligned','maligned','maligning','','a. 有害的,恶性的,有恶意的<br>\nv. 诽谤,说坏话',' A malign tumour was found in his stomach.<br>     在他的胃部发现了一个恶性肿瘤。　<br>\n She likes to malign innocent persons.<br>     她爱诋毁那些清白的人。<br>'),(5867,'malignancy','','','','malignancies','n. 恶性',''),(5868,'malignant','','','','malignants','a. 有恶意的,恶性的,有害的<br>\nn. 怀恶意的人,保王党员',' The tumour is not malignant.<br>     这个瘤不是恶性的。<br>\n It\'s a malignant slander to me.<br>     这对我是恶意的诽谤。<br>'),(5869,'malignity','','','','malignities','n. 邪恶,恶毒',''),(5870,'malinge