 大都市的,大主教区的,母国的',' She left the small island and became famous in metropolitan France.<br>     她离开小岛而在法国的大都市中成名。<br>\n Metropolitan new york cover200 square mile.<br>     纽约大都市覆盖面积达200平方英里。<br>'),(6276,'Mexican','','','','','n. 墨西哥人,墨西哥语<br>\na. 墨西哥的',' In the Alamo battle, less than two hundred defenders repulse the attack by thousands of Mexican in twelve days.<br>     在阿拉摩战役中，不满二百人的守军在十二天内击退了几千墨西哥人一次又一次的进攻。<br>\n Filming a Western on location in the Mexican desert.<br>     在墨西哥沙漠外景地拍摄一部西部片<br>'),(6277,'Mexico','','','','','n. 墨西哥',' Mexico has a large surplus of oil.<br>     墨西哥有大量过剩的石油。<br>\n A Pueblo people located north-northeast of Santa Fe, New Mexico.<br>     陶斯人一支居住于美国新墨西哥州圣大菲城东北偏北的普埃布洛印地安人中的成员<br>'),(6278,'microbe','','','','microbes','n. 微生物',''),(6279,'microcircuit','','','','','微电路',''),(6280,'microcode','','','','','微代码,微指令',' A program or other coding sequence that produces a result of specified type and format(\"a macro generator\";\"a microcode generator\").<br>     产生某种指定类型和格式的结果的程序或另一种编码序列（如“宏生成程序”、“微代码生成程序”）。<br>\n A procedure in which an instruction is broken down into the microcode operations necessary for its execution by a control unit.<br>     一种处理过程，其间由控制器将一条指令分解成为它的执行所必须的微码操作。<br>'),(6281,'microcomputer','','','','','n. 微电脑<br>\n[计算机] 微机计算机',' The system on the small-scale is called a microcomputer or minicomputer.<br>     小规模的系统叫做微型计算机或小型计算机。<br>\n In appearance, a microcomputer has three simple and apparent parts: the main frame, the keyboard and the monitor.<br>     从外表上看，微型计算机有简单而鲜明的三部分：主机、键盘和监视器。<br>'),(6282,'microcosm','','','','','n. 小宇宙,小世界,人类',' Man is a microcosm of the whole of mankind.<br>     人是全人类的缩影.<br>\n This small island contains the whole of nature in microcosm.<br>     这个小岛包含著小而完整的自然界.<br>'),(6283,'microeconomics','','','','','n. 微观经济学',''),(6284,'microfiche','','','','microfiches','微缩胶片',''),(6285,'microfilm','microfilmed','microfilmed','microfilming','','n. 缩影胶片',' Send the1990 correspondence to be microfilm or for microfilm.<br>     把1990年的信函送去摄制成缩微胶卷。<br>\n A card or sheet of microfilm capable of accommodating and preserving a considerable number of pages, as of printed text, in reduced form.<br>     缩微平片一个缩微胶卷片，能够以缩微形式容纳并储存相当多数量的页数，如一印刷文本的<br>'),(6286,'microinstruction','','','','','微指令',''),(6287,'microorganism','','','','','n. 微生物',' A minute life form; a microorganism, especially a bacterium that causes disease. Not in technical use.<br>     微生物；细菌一种极小的生命形式，一种微生物，尤指引起疾病的细菌，不用于技术用语<br>\n An organism, such as a mosquito or tick, that carries disease-causing microorganisms from one host to another.<br>     传病媒介把致病微生物从一个宿主传到另一宿主的生物，如蚊子或虱蝇等<br>'),(6288,'microphone','','','','microphones','n. 麦克风,扩音器',' The lecturer speaks through a microphone.<br>     演讲者通过麦克风说话。<br>\n He used a microphone so that everyone could hear him.<br>     他使用扩音器，使人人能听见他的讲话。<br>'),(6289,'microprocessor','','','','','n.微处理器<br>\n[计算机] 微处理器',' A term indicating machines, microprocessor, programs, or procedures that are designed or set apart for special or continued use.<br>     用于描述为专门的或连续的使用而设计或设置的机器、微处理器、程序或过程。<br>'),(6290,'microprogram','','','','','微程序',''),(6291,'microprogramming','','','','','微程序设计',''),(6292,'microscope','','','','microscopes','n. 显微镜',' He stained some slides and looked at them under the microscope.<br>     他给几张载玻片上染了色，然后放到显微镜下观察。<br>\n The biologist stained the specimen before looking at it through the microscope.<br>     那位生物学家先把标本染色, 然後再通过显微镜进行观察.<br>'),(6293,'microscopic','','','','','a. 显微镜的',' We can\'t see microscopic creature with naked eyes.<br>     我们不能用肉眼看到微生物。<br>\n The doctor had a microscopic examination of traces of blood.<br>     医生用显微镜作了血迹检查。<br>'),(6294,'microsecond','','','','','微秒',''),(6295,'Microsoft','','','','','微软(财富500强公司之一，总部所在地美国,主要经营软件数据服务)',' \"We\'re chipping away at a very dominant competitor where market share means a lot, \" said Peter Higgins, a Microsoft product manager in charge of Excel.<br>     微软公司（Microsoft）一位主管Excel的产品经理希金斯说：\"我们正逐渐地削弱一个首要的竞争者。在这一行业里市场占有率颇为重要。\"<br>\n Provide information to help you set up and run microsoft exchange.<br>     提供信息帮助你建立并运行MicrosoftExchange。<br>'),(6296,'microsurgery','','','','','n. 显微手术,显微外科',' They were pioneers in the field of microsurgery.<br>     他们是显微外科学领域的创始人.<br>'),(6297,'microwave','','','','','n. 微波',' The pie is not very hot. Can you microwave it a bit more?<br>     这个饼不是很热的，你再用微波炉加热一会好吗？<br>\n In microwave system the separate input from various sources must be brought together to give a composite input which is then transmitted and received by radio.<br>     在微波系统中，来自各处的分散的输入必须被汇集在一起，以形成一个综合的输入，然后由无线电发送和接收。<br>'),(6298,'mid','','','','','a. 中间的',' Two planes collided in mid air.<br>     两架飞机在半空中相撞。<br>'),(6299,'midday','','','','','n. 正午,中午<br>\na. 正午的',' It\'s very hot in summer\'s midday.<br>     夏天的中午非常热。<br>\n The house is shaded from the midday heat by those tall trees.<br>     高高的树木使这所房子避开了正午的炎热。<br>'),(6300,'middle','middled','middled','middling','middles','a. 中等的,中间的<br>\nn. 中间',' The man has reached middle age.<br>     这人已到了中年。<br>\n He planted roses in the middle of the garden.<br>     他在花园中间种上玫瑰。<br>'),(6301,'middleman','','','','middlemen','n. 中间人',' She wants to buy direct from the manufacturer and cut out the middleman.<br>     她想避开分销商直接自厂家买进货物.<br>\n He acted as a middleman in discussions between the two companies.<br>     他在两公司的谈判中作中间人.<br>'),(6302,'middling','','','','','a. 中等的,第二流的',' Fair to middling, thanks.<br>     还可以，谢谢。<br>\n How am I feeling today? Oh, fair to middling.<br>     我今天感觉如何？哦，马马虎虎。<br>'),(6303,'MIDI','','','','','音乐设备数字接口',' Musical Instrument Digital Interface, or MIDI, is a communication interface provided on virtually every synthesizer made today.<br>     音乐设备数字接口，或称MIDI，实际上是为目前制造的各种合成器提供的一种通信接口。<br>'),(6304,'midnight','','','','','n. 午夜',' That shop closed at midnight.<br>     那家商店营业到午夜十二点。<br>\n At midnight you\'ll hear the clock strike twelve.<br>     午夜时你会听到钟打12点。<br>'),(6305,'midst','','','','','n. 中间,当中<br>\nprep. (=amidst)在...当中',' He was but recently in our midst.<br>     他只是最近才到我们中间。<br>\n The girls had got on well together until the apple of discord in the person of a handsome young man arrived in their midst.<br>     姑娘们一直相处很好，后来一个英俊的小伙子来到她们中间，引起了她们之间的不和。<br>'),(6306,'might','','','','','aux. 可能,也许<br>\nn. 力量,威力<br>\nv. 或许,可以',' I thought it might be true.<br>     我曾认为这可能是真的。<br>\n The promise of a reward might stiffen their resolve.<br>     答应给他们奖励可以坚定他们的决心。<br>'),(6307,'mighty','','','','','a. 强有力的<br>\nad. [口]很',' The United Kingdom was a mighty empire before World War I.<br>     英联邦在第一次世界大战前曾是一个强大的帝国。<br>\n There\'s no need to be/get so high and mighty with me!<br>     用不著对我摆架子!<br>'),(6308,'migrant','','','','','n. 移居者',' Migrant workers move from city to city in search of work.<br>     流动工人为了寻找工作从一个城市移居到另一个城市。<br>'),(6309,'migrate','migrated','migrated','migrating','','v. 移动,移往,随季节而移居<br>\n[计算机] 迁移',' Some tribes migrate with their cattle in search of fresh grass.<br>     有些部落为了寻找新鲜的牧草而带着他们的牲畜迁移。<br>\n To all appearance, Mr. Li is going to migrate.<br>     李先生显然是要移民了。<br>'),(6310,'migration','','','','migrations','n. 移民,移往,移动',' Seabirds will fly from here to another place for migration every year.<br>     海鸟每年都要从一个地方迁徙到另一个地方。<br>\n There was a huge migration of people into Europe because of the war.<br>     因为战争，大量的移民涌入欧洲。<br>'),(6311,'mild','','','','','a. (烟、酒)味淡的,轻微的,温柔的,文雅的',' This cheese is very mild.<br>     这种奶酪味道清淡。<br>\n He has a mild nature.<br>     他的性格温和。<br>'),(6312,'mildew','mildewed','mildewed','mildewing','','n. 霉,面粉病菌,露菌病菌<br>\nv. 发霉,生霉',' Those roses have been ruined by mildew.<br>     那些玫瑰已经霉烂。<br>\n Cog liable to mildew damage effect ins acidly.<br>     货物可能会发霉，请予以投保。<br>'),(6313,'mildly','','','','','ad. 柔和地,和善地,谨慎地',' The chairman didn\'t act very sensibly, to put is mildly.<br>     说得婉转些，主席的行为没有理智。<br>\n She complained loudly to the shopkeeper, who answered her mildly.<br>     她大声对店主抱怨，店主却温和地回答她。<br>'),(6314,'mile','','','','miles','n. 英里