micked his uncle\'s voice and gestures perfectly.<br>     他把叔叔的声音和姿态模仿得惟妙惟肖。<br>'),(6335,'mince','minced','minced','mincing','','n. 切碎物<br>\nv. 切碎,矫揉做作地说',' I minced the lean meat finely before making dumplings.<br>     包饺子前，我把瘦肉细细剁碎。<br>\n I won\'t mince words (with you): I think your plan is stupid.<br>     我不（跟你）兜圈子, 我认为你的计画是胡闹.<br>'),(6336,'mind','minded','minded','minding','minds','n. 思想,主意,心意<br>\nv. 介意,照顾,留心',' Would you mind if I smoke here?<br>     我在这吸烟，你介意吗？<br>\n Mind your head!<br>     小心别碰了头!<br>'),(6337,'minded','','','','','a. 有意的,有心的,具有意志的',' He could do it if he were so minded.<br>     假如他想做，他就能做。<br>\n She has become very food-minded since her holiday in France.<br>     她自法国度假回来, 对食物就很讲究了.<br>'),(6338,'mindful','','','','','a. 深切注意的,留神的,留心的',' Mindful of the need to maintain efficient communication, the board of directors decided to construct a new communication network.<br>     董事会注意到维持有效通讯的需要，因此决定建立一个新的通信网。<br>\n Be mindful to follow my advice.<br>     你要注意照我的忠告去做。<br>'),(6339,'mindfulness','','','','','n. 留神,警觉,注意',''),(6340,'mindless','','','','','a. 不小心的,不留神的,不顾虑的',''),(6341,'mindset','','','','','n. 意向,精神状态<br>\n心态',''),(6342,'mine','','','','','n. 地雷,矿,矿山<br>\npron. 我的<br>\nv. 采掘,开矿',' That book is mine.<br>     那本书是我的。<br>\n The cruiser was mined, and sank in five minutes.<br>     这艘巡洋舰触雷，五分钟后沉没了。<br>'),(6343,'minefield','','','','','n. 雷区',' International law is a minefield for anyone not familiar with its complexity.<br>     国际法这一领域, 不熟悉其复杂性则寸步难行.<br>'),(6344,'minelayer','','','','','n. 布雷舰艇',''),(6345,'miner','','','','miners','n. 矿工',' I think it is dangerous to be a miner.<br>     我认为当矿工是很危险的。<br>\n The boarding-house keeper drew his pistol upon the miner who owed him, and said,\"Down with the dust! \"<br>     寄宿公寓的管理员拔出手枪对欠他房租的矿工说，“把钱交出来！”<br>'),(6346,'mineral','','','','minerals','a. 矿物的<br>\nn. 矿物,矿石',' Coal is a mineral.<br>     煤是一种矿物。<br>\n This shop sells minerals.<br>     这家商店卖矿泉水。<br>'),(6347,'mineral water','','','','','矿泉水',' They have sold up ten crates of mineral water in the afternoon.<br>     他们这个下午卖掉了十箱矿泉水。<br>\n Can I have a carafe of water, please? Mineral water, sir? No, ordinary tap water will do.<br>     请给我拿瓶水来，好吗？是矿泉水吗，先生？不，普通自来水就行。<br>'),(6348,'mineralogy','','','','','矿物学',''),(6349,'Ming','','','','','明朝',' A Chinese dynasty(1271-1368) established by the Mongolian ruler Kublai Khan at Peking(Beijing). It was superseded by the Ming dynasty.<br>     元朝由蒙古统治者忽必烈汗在北京建立的一个中国王朝（1271-1368年），它被明朝取代<br>\n The pagoda built in the Ming Dynasty is still in good repair.<br>     建于明代的那座塔现在还完好无损。<br>'),(6350,'mingle','mingled','mingled','mingling','','v. 混合,联合,交际',' She accepted the money with mingled feelings.<br>     她悲喜交集地收下了这笔钱。<br>\n He mingled in the crowd and lost in sight.<br>     他混入人群，看不见了。<br>'),(6351,'mingy','','','','','a. 吝啬的,小气的',' This restaurant serves very mingy portions.<br>     这家餐厅的饮食分量很少.<br>\n He\'s so mingy with his money.<br>     他对钱十分吝啬.<br>'),(6352,'mini','','','','minis','n. 缩型(缩影,小型计算机)',' The basic design of the Mini has held good for more than twenty-five years.<br>     微型汽车的基本设计已经适用了25年以上。<br>'),(6353,'mini-','','','','','表示“小型,迷你”之义',''),(6354,'miniature','miniatured','miniatured','miniaturing','miniatures','n. 缩图,小画像<br>\na. 小规模的,纤小的',' He showed me the miniature of the mansion.<br>     他给我显示了大厦的模型。<br>\n She is just like her mother in miniature.<br>     她简直是她母亲的缩影。<br>'),(6355,'miniaturize','miniaturized','miniaturized','miniaturizing','','vt. 使微型化',''),(6356,'minibar','','','','','小型条信号(发生器)',''),(6357,'minibus','','','','','n. 小型公共汽车',' The two-year-old boy liked a lot the boy minibus while her mother bought him for the first time. He always slept with it.<br>     这两岁的小男孩子非常喜爱他母亲第一次给他买的微型玩具车，他睡觉时也总是拿着睡。<br>\n I am told this minibus can go jar on very little petrol.<br>     我听说这种小客车能靠很少汽油开很多路。<br>'),(6358,'minicab','','','','','n. 微型出租汽车',''),(6359,'minicomputer','','','','','n. 微型计算机',' The system on the small-scale is called a microcomputer or minicomputer.<br>     小规模的系统叫做微型计算机或小型计算机。<br>\n A computer larger than a minicomputer that can handle more users and large programs.<br>     一种比小型计算机大，能容纳更多用户和处理较大程序的计算机。<br>'),(6360,'minimal','','','','','a. 最低限度的,最小的',' We stayed with friends, so our expenses were minimal.<br>     我们住在朋友家, 所以我们的花费很小.<br>\n Singapore, the world the minimal and one of the most advanced nation, celebrated the nation independent of30 anniversaries in last week.<br>     新加坡，这个世界上最小也是最发达的国家之一，上周庆祝国家独立三十周年。<br>'),(6361,'minimalist','','','','','n. 最低限要求者',''),(6362,'minimize','minimized','minimized','minimizing','','v. 将...减到最少<br>\n[计算机] 最小化',' To minimize the risk of burglary, install a good alarm system.<br>     安装可靠的报警设备以减低被盗的风险.<br>\n He minimized the value of her contribution to his research so that he got all the praise.<br>     他极力贬低她在那项研究中的贡献, 从而独获全部奖励.<br>'),(6363,'minimum','','','','minima','a. 最低的,最小的<br>\nn. 最小量,最低限度',' Repairing your car will cost a minimum of 100 dollars.<br>     修理你的汽车最低限度要100美元。<br>\n The class needs a minimum of 6 pupils to continue.<br>     这个班最低限度要六个学生才可以继续办下去。<br>'),(6364,'minimum wage','','','','','最低工资',''),(6365,'mining','','','','','n. 采矿,矿业',' This area depends on the mining industry.<br>     这个地区以采矿业为经济基础.<br>\n He went heels over head into buying mining stock.<br>     他购买了矿业股票，做事真鲁莽。<br>'),(6366,'minion','','','','minions','n. 奴才, 宠臣',' They are the dictator and his minions.<br>     他们就是那个独裁者和他的奴仆。<br>\n Can you send one of your minions to collect this file?<br>     你能不能派个助手来取这份档案？<br>'),(6367,'miniskirt','','','','miniskirts','n. 迷你短裙',' It\'s an era of the miniskirt in the seventies.<br>     七十年代是超短裙时代。<br>\n Miniskirts are starting to come back.<br>     超短裙又开始流行了。<br>'),(6368,'minister','ministered','ministered','ministering','ministers','n. 部长,大臣<br>\nv. 伺候<br>\nvi. 照顾,给予帮助',' He was elected Minister of Education.<br>     他被选为教育部长。<br>\n The Chancellor of the Exchequer is the minister in charge of finance in Britain.<br>     英国财政大臣是负责财政的大臣。<br>'),(6369,'ministerial','','','','','a. 部长的,内阁的,执政的',' They carried the ministerial veto.<br>     他们行使了内阁否决权。<br>'),(6370,'ministry','','','','ministries','n. (政府的)部',' The army, navy and airforce are all controlled by the Ministry of Defense.<br>     陆海空军皆由国防部控制。<br>\n She\'s on attachment to the Ministry of Defense.<br>     她现在隶属于国防部。<br>'),(6371,'mink','','','','mink','n. 貂,貂皮衣',' Picked up a mink coat on sale.<br>     拍卖时随手买了一件貂皮大衣<br>\n She wheedled him into buying her a mink coat.<br>     她用甜言蜜语诱他买貂皮大衣给她。<br>'),(6372,'Minnesota','','','','','n. 明尼苏达州',''),(6373,'minnow','','','','minnows','n. 鲦鱼,小淡水鱼',' These criminals arrested by the police are only minnows, their leader has escaped.<br>     这些被警察抓住的犯罪分子只是些小鱼，他们的头子却跑掉了。<br>'),(6374,'minor','minored','minored','minoring','minors','n. 未成年人,副修科目<br>\na. 次要的,较小的,二流的,未成年的<br>\nv. 辅修<br>\n[音乐] 小调',' She acted as a minor role in the play.<br>     她在剧中扮演了一个次要的角色。<br>\n I made minor alterations to the article.<br>     我对这篇文章作了小规模的修改。<br>'),(6375,'minority','','','','minorities','n. 少数,少数民族',' A small minority voted against the motion.<br>     投票反对该提议的人占少数。<br>\n There are 55 minorities in our country.<br>     我国有55个少数民族。<br>'),(6376,'minstrel','','','','minstrels','n. 吟游诗人(或歌手)',' The minstrel travelled about the country singing songs and poems written by him.<br>     这名吟游诗人在全国游历，吟唱他自己写的诗歌。<br>\n The minstrel has been to many places before he came here.<br>     在来到这里之前，这个吟游诗人已经去过很多地方。<br>'),(6377,'mint','','','','','n. 薄荷,造币厂,巨额<br>\nv. 铸造,铸币,伪造',' The poet minted several words that cannot be found in any dictionary.<br>     诗人造了几个词典里找不到的词。<br>\n Many people like to chew mint gum in the summer.<br>     许多人喜欢在夏天嚼薄荷口香糖。<br>'),(6378,'minuend','','','','','被减数',''),(6379,'minuet','','','','','n. 小步舞',' A French peasant dance resembling the minuet.<br>     加伏特舞一种法国农民的舞蹈，类似于小步舞<br>\n The music for or in the rhythm of the minuet.<br>     米奴哀舞曲为米奴哀舞而写的舞曲或米奴哀舞节奏的舞蹈<br>'),(6380,'minus','','','','minuses','a. 负的,减去的<br>\nn. 减号,负号<br>\nprep. 减去',' I got B minus in the test.<br>     我在考试中得了个B-。<br>\n Seven minus three equals four.<br>     七减三等于四。<br>'),(6381,'minus sign','','','','','减号',''),(6382,'minuscule','','','','','n. 草写小字,小写字<br>\na. 草写小字的,小写字的',''),(6383,'minute','','','','','a. 微小的<br>\nn. 分钟',' I had remembered in minute detail everything that had happened.<br>     我对发生的每件事的细枝末节都记得清清楚楚。<br>\n The park is only five minutes from downtown.<br>     这个花园离市中心只有五分钟的路程。<br>'),(6384,'minutes','','','','','n. 会议记录,分钟',' The minutes of the last meeting were approved.<br>     上次会议记录已获得通过.<br>\n Boil the vegetables for 20 minutes and then drain off the water.<br>     把蔬菜煮上20分钟，然后把水沥掉。<br>'),(6385,'minutia','','','','minutiae','n. 微枝末节,细节',''),(6386,'miracle','','','','miracles','n. 奇迹',' Her life was saved by a miracle.<br>     她的生命是靠奇迹救活的。<br>\n This cathedral was regarded as a miracle in architectural history.<br>     这座大教堂被认为是建筑史上的奇迹。<br>'),(6387,'miraculous','','','','','a. 奇迹的,不可思议的',' It\'s miraculous how much weight you\'ve lost!<br>     你体重减轻了这么多，真了不起！<br>\n The relics are credited with miraculous powers.<br>     这些早期遗物被认为具有神奇的力量.<br>'),(6388,'miraculously','','','','','ad. 奇迹般地',''),(6389,'mirage','','','','','n. 海市蜃楼,幻想',' A mirage is an optical illusion.<br>     海市蜃楼是一种视错觉.<br>\n The heat reflected from the white sand formed a mirage.<br>     热气经白色的沙面反射形成了蜃景.<br>'),(6390,'mire','mired','mired','miring','','n. 泥沼,泥泞<br>\nv. 使...陷于泥泞,使...陷入困境',' The most brilliant person may be mired in detail and confusion.<br>     即使是最聪明的人也会陷入琐事与混乱之中。<br>\n My car was mired.<br>     我的车上溅满污泥。<br>'),(6391,'mirror','mirrored','mirrored','mirroring','mirrors','n. 镜子<br>\nv. 反映,反射',' She stared at herself in the mirror.<br>     她凝视着镜中的自己。<br>\n The clear water mirrored the blue sky.<br>     清澈的水中映出蔚蓝的天空。<br>'),(6392,'mirroring','','','','','镜象的',' His figure looks very funny in the concave mirror.<br>     他的样子在凹镜里显得非常可笑。<br>\n The mirror is oval.<br>     镜子是椭圆的。<br>'),(6393,'mirth','','','','','n. 欢乐,