n. 不幸,灾难',' I lost your file by pure mischance.<br>     我把你的文件丢了，纯粹是碰上倒霉事了。<br>\n A series of mischance happened.<br>     一连串不幸的事发生了。<br>'),(6407,'mischief','','','','mischiefs','n. 伤害,灾祸,恶作剧',' The wind played mischief with my papers.<br>     风把我的文章吹得乱七八糟。<br>\n I try to keep the boy out of mischief.<br>     我尽量不让这个男孩胡闹。<br>'),(6408,'mischievous','','','','','a. 调皮的,恶作剧的',' One expects active children to be mischievous at times.<br>     活泼的孩子有时是会淘气的。<br>\n Mischievous, teasing, or annoying.<br>     有害的、调皮的或打搅<br>'),(6409,'mischievousness','','','','','n. 恶作剧',''),(6410,'miscommunication','','','','','n. 错误传达',''),(6411,'misconceive','misconceived','misconceived','misconceiving','','v. 误解',' The housing needs of our inner cities have been misconceived from the start.<br>     我们旧城区的住房需求一开始就受到误解.<br>'),(6412,'misconception','','','','','n. 误解,错误想法',' That a doctor shall be able to physic any disease is a misconception.<br>     认为医生应该能医治任何疾病的观念是错误的。<br>'),(6413,'misconduct','misconducted','misconducted','misconducting','','n. 处理不当(胡作非为)<br>\nvt 处理不当(胡作非为)',' That doctor has been accused of professional misconduct.<br>     那位医生被指控违反医德。<br>\n The company only dismisses its employees in cases of gross misconduct.<br>     公司仅在雇员严重失职的情形下才予以解雇.<br>'),(6414,'misconstrue','misconstrued','misconstrued','misconstruing','','v. 误解,曲解',' You have completely misconstrued me/my words/what I said.<br>     你完全误解了我[我的话/我的意思]了.<br>'),(6415,'miscreant','','','','','a. 极恶的,协道的,异端的<br>\nn. 罪大恶极的人,恶棍,异端',''),(6416,'misdeed','','','','','n. 不端行为',''),(6417,'misdemeanor','','','','','n. 坏事',''),(6418,'misdemeanour','','','','','n. 坏事',''),(6419,'miser','','','','misers','n. 守财奴,吝啬鬼',' The miser was despised by everyone in the city.<br>     这个守财奴受到城市里每个人的鄙视。<br>\n `A generous miser\' is a contradiction in terms.<br>     ｀慷慨的吝啬鬼＇在用词上自相矛盾.<br>'),(6420,'miserable','','','','','a. 悲惨的,痛苦的',' The play was a miserable failure.<br>     这出戏演砸了。<br>\n There are still many people whose living conditions 