without mishap.<br>     告诉你母亲你已经平平安安到达这里。<br>\n He hurt his knee during the football match, but this mishap didn\'t stop him from playing.<br>     足球比赛时他伤了膝盖，可他并没有因此中途退出。<br>'),(6434,'misinform','misinformed','misinformed','misinforming','','vt. 告诉...错误的消息',' I regret to say you have been misinformed (about that).<br>     很遗憾, （关於那事）你听到的情况不确.<br>'),(6435,'misinterpret','misinterpreted','misinterpreted','misinterpreting','','v. 误解',' I feel I must qualify my earlier remarks in case they are misinterpret.<br>     我觉得我得把我说的话改得具体些，以免产生误解。<br>\n The rioter misinterpret the instructions of the police.<br>     暴徒们错误地解释了警察的指示。<br>'),(6436,'misjudge','misjudged','misjuded','misjudging','','vt. 判断错误',' I\'m sorry I misjudged you/your motives.<br>     对不起, 我误会你[你的动机]了.<br>\n I misjudged how wide the stream was and fell in.<br>     我对小河的宽度估计错误, 结果掉进河里了.<br>'),(6437,'misjudgment','','','','','n. 估计错误,判断不公',''),(6438,'mislay','mislaid','mislaid','mislaying','','v. 遗失...,把...放错地方<br>\nvt. 放错位置,遗失',' I seem to have mislaid my passport have you seen it?<br>     我好像把护照放在什麽地方找不到了--你看见了吗?<br>\n I have mislaid my key to the door.<br>     我不知道把门钥匙放到哪里了。<br>'),(6439,'mislead','misled','misled','misleading','','vt. 带错',' He misled me into thinking he was rich.<br>     他使我误以为他很有钱。<br>\n We were misled by the guide.<br>     向导给我们引错了路。<br>'),(6440,'misleading','','','','','a. 使入误解的',' The misleading sign led me astray.<br>     那个标志误人，它使我迷了路。<br>\n Don\'t judge by appearances appearances can be misleading.<br>     勿以外貌取人--外貌不可靠.<br>'),(6441,'mismanage','mismanaged','mismanaged','mismanaging','','v. 处置失当,办错',''),(6442,'mismanagement','','','','','n. 管理不善,处理不当',' And who brought us to such a pass? You did, by sheer mismanagement.<br>     谁使我们陷入这样的困境？就是你，纯粹由于你管理不善。<br>\n By sheer mismanagement you brought us to such a pass.<br>     完全是你处理不当，才把事情弄得这样糟。<br>'),(6443,'mismatch','mismatched','mismatched','mismatching','','配错,不匹配',' Their marriage was a mismatch they had little in common.<br>     他们的婚姻不般配--两人几无共同之处.<br>'),(6444,'misnomer','','','','','n. 误称',' `First-class hotel\' was a complete misnomer for the tumbledown farmhouse we stayed in.<br>     把我们住的那个摇摇欲坠的村舍称作｀一流旅馆＇, 纯粹是乱用词语.<br>'),(6445,'misogamy','','','','','n. 厌恶结婚',''),(6446,'misogynist','','','','','n. 厌恶女人的人',''),(6447,'misplace','misplaced','misplaced','misplacing','','vt. 错放(误给)',' I\'ve misplaced my glasses they\'re not in my bag.<br>     我把眼镜放错地方了--没在我的包里.<br>\n If you think deafness is funny, you\'ve got a very misplaced sense of humour.<br>     假若认为耳聋有趣, 这种幽默感十分不当.<br>'),(6448,'misrepresent','misrepresented','misrepresented','misrepresenting','','vt. 误称(把...颠倒黑白,错误表现)',' The charge is that the producers of the programme either deliberately misrepresented its nature, or foolishly slid into changing its purpose during production--or both. Of course, it is a matter of judgement whether the charge is made to stick.<br>     指控说这个节目的制作者们要么有意地歪曲了节目的性质，要么就是在制作过程中愚蠢地改变了节目的目的——或者两种情况都有。当然，指控是否成立，还要看法官的裁决。<br>'),(6449,'miss','','','','','n. 小姐<br>\nvt. 想念<br>\nvt. 漏掉,错过',' That was a lucky miss.<br>     幸免于难。<br>\n May I help you, miss?<br>     要我帮忙吗，小姐？<br>'),(6450,'misshapen','','','','','a. 造型不佳的,残缺的,畸形的',' Distorted in form; misshapen.<br>     变形的形状上被扭曲的；畸形的<br>'),(6451,'missile','','','','missiles','n. 导弹',' The huge ship was sunk by a homing missile.<br>     这只巨大的军舰被一枚自动寻的导弹击中。<br>\n Demonstrators attacked the police, using sticks and assorted missiles.<br>     示威者用棍棒和各种投掷物攻击警察。<br>'),(6452,'missing','','','','','a. 缺掉的,失踪的',' The child had been missing for a week.<br>     那个孩子已经下落不明一个星期了。<br>\n The book had two pages missing.<br>     那本书缺两页。<br>'),(6453,'mission','missioned','missioned','missioning','missions','n. 任务,代表团,使命<br>\n[计算机] 使命',' He has been on confidential missions to Berlin.<br>     他前往柏林执行秘密任务。<br>\n The doctor works at the mission.<br>     那医生在贫民教区工作。<br>'),(6454,'missionary','','','','missionaries','n. 传教士,负有任务者,工作人员<br>\na. 传教的,负有使命的',' The missionary was sent to India last year.<br>     这名传教士去年被派到印度。<br>\n The scene the horror film where the cannibals dismembered the missionary left me with my hair standing on end.<br>     在那部恐怖电影中，食人者肢解那传教士的镜头使我毛骨悚然。<br>'),(6455,'Mississippi','','','','','n. 密西西比(河)[美国]',' He has a large farm in the Mississippi Valley.<br>     他在密西西比河流域拥有一个大农场。<br>\n The region of the United States west of the Mississippi River.<br>     西部地区美国密西西比河以西的地区<br>'),(6456,'Mississippi River','','','','','n. 密西西比河',' Mark used to be a pilot on the Mississippi River.<br>     马克曾在密西西比河上当过领航员。<br>\n The region of the United States west of the Mississippi River.<br>     西部地区美国密西西比河以西的地区<br>'),(6457,'missive','','','','','n. 公文,书信<br>\na. 送出的',''),(6458,'Missouri','','','','','n. 密苏里(美国州名)',' Carver, who was black, was born in Missouri in1864.<br>     卡佛是个黑人，1864年出生在密苏里州。<br>\n Don\'t try to fool me. I\'m from Missouri.<br>     别想骗我，我不会相信你的话。<br>'),(6459,'misspell','misspelled','misspelled','misspelling','','vt. 拼错',''),(6460,'misspend','misspent','misspent','misspending','','v. 浪费(时间、金钱等)',''),(6461,'misstep','','','','','n. 失足,过失',''),(6462,'missus','','','','','n. (已婚的)...夫人',' How\'s the missus (ie your wife)?<br>     你老婆好吗?<br>\n My missis hates me smoking indoors.<br>     我老婆讨厌我在屋里抽烟.<br>'),(6463,'mist','','','','','n. 雾,迷蒙,朦胧不清<br>\nv. 使...模糊,下雾',' She could hardly recognize her son through the mist of tears that filled her eyes.<br>     她泪眼蒙蒙，几乎不能认出自己的儿子。<br>\n Our breath is misting up the car windows.<br>     我们呼出的气渐渐给汽车的窗户上蒙上一层水蒸气。<br>'),(6464,'mistake','mistook','mistaken','mistaking','mistakes','n. 错误,误会<br>\nv. 犯错,误认',' You mistook my meaning entirely.<br>     你完全误解了我的意思。<br>\n You\'ve made several grammatical mistakes in the composition.<br>     你的作文中犯了几处语法错误。<br>'),(6465,'mistaken','','','','','a. 犯错的,错误的<br>\nvbl. 误认,弄错',' If I\'m not mistaken, that\'s the man we saw on the bus.<br>     要是我没认错人的话，我们在公共汽车上看见的就是那个男子。<br>\n You must have mistaken her for her sister.<br>     你一定是把她误认为是她的姊妹了。<br>'),(6466,'mistakenly','','','','','ad. 错误地, 曲解地',' A king of Thebes who was mistakenly killed by his own son, Oedipus.<br>     拉伊俄斯底比斯国王，被他自己的儿子俄底浦斯误杀<br>'),(6467,'mister','mistered','mistered','mistering','misters','n. 先生',' A little boy stopped me in the street and asked me, \"What\'s the time, mister?\"<br>     一个小男孩在街上拦住了我，问道；“先生，现在几点了？”<br>\n Don\'t mister me.<br>     不要叫我先生。<br>'),(6468,'mistletoe','','','','','n. 槲寄生(一种常用作圣诞节室内悬挂的植物)',' The mistletoe plant is a parasite on trees.<br>     槲寄生是寄生在树上的植物。<br>'),(6469,'mistral','','','','','n. 冷而干燥的强风',''),(6470,'mistreat','mistreated','mistreated','mistreating','','vt.虐待',''),(6471,'mistress','','','','mistresses','n. 主妇,女主人,情妇',' The dog ran alongside his mistress.<br>     狗在女主人的身边奔跑。<br>\n The poet addressed many poems to his mistress, praising her beauty.<br>     这位诗人为他心爱的女子写了许多诗，歌颂她的美丽。<br>'),(6472,'mistrust','mistrusted','mistrusted','mistrusting','','n. 不信任,疑惑<br>\nv. 不信任,疑惑',' He keeps his money at home because he has a great mistrust of banks.<br>     他把自己的钱放在家里，因为他很不信任银行。<br>\n Everything you say seems to be pervaded with a mistrust of the human race.<br>     你说的一切似乎都渗透了对人类的不信任。<br>'),(6473,'mistrustful','','','','','a. 不信任的,深疑的',' He is mistrustful of my ability.<br>     他不信任我的才干。<br>'),(6474,'mists','','','','','n. 史前时代',' The mists was fleeing before the rising sun.<br>     太阳慢慢升起，薄雾渐渐消失。<br>\n We watched the mists ascending from the valley below.<br>     我们看著薄雾从下面的山谷中升起.<br>'),(6475,'misty','','','','','a. 有雾的,模糊的,含糊的',' It was a misty morning, but not very cold.<br>     这是一个多雾的清晨，但不太冷。<br>\n A misty rain; a misty night.<br>     似雾的雨，雾朦朦的夜晚<br>'),(6476,'misunderstand','misunderstood','misunderstood','misunderstanding','','v. 误解,误会',' They pretend to misunderstand my complaint.<br>     他们假装误解了我的投诉。<br>\n He wrote her a letter for fear she misunderstand him.<br>     他给她写了封信，免得她误会。<br>'),(6477,'misunderstanding','','','','','n. 误会,误解',' I must weigh my words to avoid any misunderstanding.<br>     我须字斟句酌免生误解.<br>\n It\'s no more than a misunderstanding.<br>     这只是个误会。<br>'),(6478,'misuse','','','','','vt.&n. 误用,滥用',' Because of misuse of power, he was dismissed.<br>     因为滥用权力，他被开除了。<br>\n The manufacturers disclaim all responsibility for the damage caused by misuse.<br>     因使用不当造成的损坏，生产厂家不负任何责任。<br>'),(6479,'mite','','','','','n. 极小量,小虫',' I offer a mite of comfort to him.<br>     我给了他一点安慰。<br>\n Poor little mite!<br>     可怜的小家伙！<br>'),(6480,'mitigate','mitigated','mitigated','mitigating','','v. 镇静,缓和,减轻<br>\nv. 缓和',' The government is trying to mitigate the effects of inflation.<br>     政府正试图缓和通货膨胀的影响。<br>\n Her words mitigated my suffering.<br>     她的话减轻了我的痛苦。<br>'),(6481,'mitt','','','','mitts','n. 手套',' Take your mitts off me!<br>     别碰我!<br>\n I gave him a baseball mitt for his birthday.<br>     为祝贺他的生日，我送给他一只棒球手套。<br>'),(6482,'mitten','','','','mittens','n. 连指手套,露指手套',' In winter she wears mittens.<br>     冬天时她戴连指手套。<br>\n The part of a glove or mitten that covers the palm of the hand.<br>     （手套的）掌份覆盖手掌的物体或手套的一部分<br>'),(6483,'mix','mixed','mixed','mixing','mixes','n. 混合物,混乱<br>\nv. 混合,弄混,与<br>\n[计算机] 混合',' She put the sugar into the coffee and mixed them up with a spoon.<br>     她把糖放进咖啡里，用勺子把它们混合起来。<br>\n You can\'t mix oil with water.<br>     你不能把油和水混合。<br>'),(6484,'mixed','','','','','a. 混合的,形形色色的,弄糊涂的<br>\nv. 使...混合,交际<br>\nvbl. 混合,弄混',' The workers mixed the asphalt with sand and gravel together.<br>     工人们把沥青和沙子、石块混合在一起。<br>\n She put the sugar into the coffee and mixed them up with a spoon.<br>     她把糖放进咖啡里，用勺子把它们混合起来。<br>'),(6485,'mixed-up','','','','','a. 头脑不清楚的,迷惑不解',' She feels very mixed-up about life since her divorce.<br>     自离婚后，她对人生感到很迷茫。<br>'),(6486,'mixer','','','','','n. 混合器(混铁炉,混频器,混和者)',' She\'s outgoing and a good mixer.<br>     她是一个杰出的爱交际的人<br>'),(6487,'mixture','','','','mixtures','n. 混合,混合物',' Air is a mixture of gases.<br>     空气是气体的混合物。<br>\n The ball is filled with gaseous mixture.<br>     那个球被充满了气体混合物。<br>'),(6488,'mm','','','','','n. 毫米',' Mm! You