仿<br>\na. 假的,伪造的<br>\nv. 嘲弄,模仿,轻视',' The army training exercises ended with a mock battle.<br>     军事训练演习以一场模拟战结束。<br>\n We should not mock at other people\'s religious beliefs.<br>     我们不应该嘲笑别人的宗教信仰。<br>'),(6500,'mockery','','','','mockeries','n. 嘲弄,笑柄,蔑视',' That examination was a mockery, they all copied from the books.<br>     那次考试完全是骗人的鬼把戏，他们都抄书。<br>\n He continued with his plan to build a flying machine, in spite of the mockery of his friends.<br>     他不顾朋友们的反对，继续他建造飞行器的计划。<br>'),(6501,'modal','','','','','模态的',''),(6502,'mode','','','','modes','n. 方式,样式,时尚，时兴',' The country girl was not used to their lavish mode of living.<br>     这个乡下姑娘不习惯他们奢侈的生活方式。<br>\n The spacecraft was in its recovery mode.<br>     这艘飞船处于返回状态。<br>'),(6503,'model','modeled','modeled','modeling','models','n. 模型,模范,模特儿<br>\na. 模范的,作模型用的<br>\nv. 做模型,塑造,模仿',' This washing machine is the latest model.<br>     这种洗衣机是最新型产品。<br>\n That beautiful girl is a fashion model.<br>     那位漂亮的女孩是一位时装模特儿。<br>'),(6504,'modem','','','','','调制解调器',' Does your computer have a modem?<br>     你的电脑有调制解调器吗？<br>\n He is out of step with modem life/ideas.<br>     他与现代生活思想格格不入。<br>'),(6505,'moderate','','','','','a. 适度的,稳健的,温和的,中等的<br>\nv. 节制,使...稳定,使...缓和',' He usually drives at a moderate speed.<br>     他通常中速驾驶。<br>\n The wind was strong all day, but it moderated after sunset.<br>     风猛烈地刮了一整天后，日落后变小了。<br>'),(6506,'moderately','','','','','ad. 适当地,适度地,中庸地',' Just because Joe is moderately good-looking, he thinks he is the God\'s gift to women!<br>     乔正因为自已长得还帅，便自己认为对女人很有吸引力！<br>\n After subtracting food and energy costs, which can vary widely each month, the Producer Price Index for Finished Goods still rose at a moderately fast clip of four-tenths of1 percent, compared with a two-tenth rises in April.<br>     减去食物与能源的费用以后——这两项每月可能大幅变动——成品制造价格指数仍以略快的速度攀升百分零点四，相形之下，四月份仅上升零点二。<br>'),(6507,'moderation','','','','','n. 缓和,适度,温和',' Some people say that drinking in moderation isn\'t harmful to health.<br>     有些人说，有节制地饮酒对健康无害。<br>\n He showed great moderation in not responding angrily to the attacks on his character.<br>     他忍受对自己人品的攻击而不发火，表现出巨大的自我控制能力。<br>'),(6508,'moderato','','','','','ad.&a. 中板的（地）',''),(6509,'moderator','','','','','n. 调解人,仲裁人<br>\nn. 减速剂 (降低自由中子在核反应堆中速度的物质,让中子更可能使铀235原子裂变,而较少被铀238原子吸收)',''),(6510,'modern','','','','moderns','a. 现代的<br>\nn. 现代人',' It\'s more useful to learn modern languages, such as English and German, than Latin.<br>     学习英语和德语等现代语言比学习拉丁语更为有用。<br>\n What do you think of modern art?<br>     你对现代艺术有何看法？<br>'),(6511,'Modern English','','','','','近代英语(指1500年以后的英语)',' I\'m writing a grammar of modern English.<br>     我在写现代英语的语法书.<br>\n The fifth letter of the modern English alphabet.<br>     E字母现代英语字母表中第五个字母<br>'),(6512,'modernism','','','','','n. 现代主义,现代派',''),(6513,'modernization','','','','modernizations','n. 现代化',' International competition was a spur to modernization.<br>     国际竞争是实现现代化的动力。<br>\n The modernization of the industry was phased over a 20-year period.<br>     工业现代化分20年逐步实现.<br>'),(6514,'modernize','modernized','modernized','modernizing','','v. 现代化,近代化',' If the industry doesn\'t modernize it will not survive.<br>     该制造业若不现代化就不能继续存在.<br>\n Pay-cable channels are still free from regulation, and the rules could prod cable companies to modernize so that nearly all programs are sold a la carte, giving consumers more choice.<br>     有线电视仍未受管制，新规定将促使有线电视公司采用新办法，尽量个别提供所有节目，予消费者较多选择。<br>'),(6515,'modest','','','','','a. 谦虚的；适度的；端庄的',' Young girls must be modest in speech, dress and behavior.<br>     年轻姑娘必须言词谨慎，衣着得体，行为端庄。<br>\n I bought the house at a modest price.<br>     我以适中的价格买下了这所房子。<br>'),(6516,'modestly','','','','','ad. 谨慎地, 适当地',' Be youngster, we sit modestly at the back, never daring to speak.<br>     我们是些年轻人，都谦恭地坐在後面，始终不敢发言。<br>'),(6517,'modesty','','','','','n. 谦逊',' His modesty [air of joviality] was all put on.<br>     他的谦逊[愉快的样子]都是装出来的。<br>\n Modesty is not his long suit.<br>     谦虚可不是他的长处.<br>'),(6518,'modicum','','','','modica','n. 少量',' \"If he had a modicum of sense, he wouldn\'t do such a foolish thing.\"<br>     ＂要是他稍有一点理智，他决不会做出如此愚蠢的事来。＂<br>'),(6519,'modification','','','','modifications','n. 修正,修饰,修改',' Persistent modification of behavior resulting from an animal\'s experience.<br>     行为的修正由动物过去的经历导致的保持终生的行为修正<br>\n Automatic modification of the index register.<br>     自动修改变址寄存器内容。<br>'),(6520,'modified','','','','','v. 修改(重建)<br>\na. 修改的(重建的)',' The policy was agreed by the committee, but only in a modified form.<br>     那项政策经修改后才获得委员会同意。<br>\n Easily altered or modified to fit conditions; adaptable.<br>     能适应的容易改动或修改来适应情况的；能适应的<br>'),(6521,'modifier','','','','','n. 修正的人,修饰字或片语',''),(6522,'modify','modified','modified','modifying','','v. 修改,更正,修饰',' The union has been forced to slightly modify its position.<br>     工会被迫稍稍改变立场。<br>\n The policy was agreed by the committee, but only in a modified form.<br>     那项政策经修改后才获得委员会同意。<br>'),(6523,'modish','','','','','a. 流行的,时髦的',''),(6524,'modular','','','','','模块化的',' In structured analysis, the study of shapes and forms, herein with respect to the structure of modular hierarchies and organizations.<br>     在结构分析中，研究形状和格式的科学。此处指对模块层次和组织的结构的研究。<br>'),(6525,'modularization','','','','','模块化,积木化',''),(6526,'modulate','modulated','modulated','modulating','','v. 调整,转调',' A device used to modulate an electromagnetic wave.<br>     调制器用以调制电磁波的装置<br>\n Music students learn how to add other parts to add other parts to a given tune, and how to modulate to a related key.<br>     音乐学生学习给一个现有的调子配上其他音部，还要学习怎样转成和声调。<br>'),(6527,'modulation','','','','','n. 调音,调节,抑扬',''),(6528,'modulator','','','','','调制器',''),(6529,'module','','','','','[计算机] 模块<br>\nn. 组件',' In software engineering, an individual unit or module that is utilized by higher-level programs or modules.<br>     在软件工程中，指较高一级程序或模块使用的一个单元或模块。<br>\n The definition of a global symbol that is not explicitly available for reference by modules linked with the module in which the definition occurs.<br>     一种全局符号定义，它不能被与定义该全局符号的模块相链接的其它模块直接引用。<br>'),(6530,'modus operandi','','','','','(拉丁文)做法',''),(6531,'mogul','','','','','n. 显要人物,权势之人',' A region of western India bordering on the Arabian Sea. An independent kingdom after1401, it was annexed by the Mogul Empire in1572.<br>     古吉拉特印度西部一地区，与阿拉伯海相邻。1401年后成为一独立的王国，1572年被强行并入莫卧帝国<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (6532,'moiety','','','','moieties','n. 一半,一部份,应得之份',''),(6533,'moist','','','','','a. 潮湿的,湿润的<br>\n(果物)多汁的<br>\n【医】有分泌物的, 湿性的<br>\nn.潮湿',' The moist season has set in.<br>     雨季已来临。<br>\n The clothes are still moist. Dry them in the sun.<br>     这些衣服还是湿的，把他们在太阳下晾干。<br>'),(6534,'moisten','moistened','moistened','moistening','','v. 弄湿',' She moistened a tissue and gently wiped the dust off the necklace.<br>     她沾湿了一块纸巾，轻轻擦去项链上的灰尘。<br>\n Her eyes moistened slightly.<br>     她的眼睛湿润了。<br>'),(6535,'moisture','','','','','n. 潮湿,湿气',' The kitchen\'s stone floor was shining with moisture.<br>     厨房的石板地受了潮闪闪发亮。<br>\n The plants drink in moisture from the atmosphere.<br>     植物从大气中吸取水分。<br>'),(6536,'moisturize','moisturized','moisturized','moisturizing','','vt. 给...增加水分,给...提供水分',''),(6537,'moisturizer','','','','','n. 润肤霜',''),(6538,'molar','','','','','a. 磨碎的,臼齿的,质量的<br>\nn. 臼齿',' The elephant grinds its food with/between its powerful molars.<br>     象用其强有力的臼齿嚼碎食物.<br>'),(6539,'molasses','','','','','n. 糖浆,糖蜜',' You may put some molasses on the bread.<br>     你可以放些糖浆在面包上。<br>\n A flat, brittle cookie spiced with ginger and sweetened with molasses.<br>     姜饼一种薄而脆的饼干，用姜汁调味并加糖蜜使之甜<br>'),(6540,'mold','','','','','n. 模子,雏型,霉<br>\nv. 形成,塑造,发霉',' A trowel-shaped tool for smoothing the surface of clay, sand, or plaster in a mold.<br>     （瓦工的）镘用以刮光模子中泥土、沙粒或灰泥的表面的铲型工具<br>\n The making of such a mold or cast, as with plaster of Paris.<br>     制印模用石膏对这种模型或模子的制作，如用巴黎的石膏<br>'),(6541,'moldboard','','','','','n. 犁板',''),(6542,'molding','','','','','(C)[常~s][建筑](装饰墙壁等凸出部用)嵌线',' A narrow border, molding, or fillet.<br>     扁带饰窄条，装饰用嵌线或窄带<br>\n The sharp edge or ridge formed by two surfaces meeting at an angle, as in a molding.<br>     尖脊两个平面以某种角度相接所形成的尖突的边或脊形，如铸模中的<br>'),(6543,'moldy','','','','','a. 发霉的',' Let\'s get rid of this moldy old furniture.<br>     咱们把这件老掉牙的旧家具扔掉吧。<br>\n They\'ve given us a pretty moldy pay increase this year.<br>     我们今年的加薪少的可怜。<br>'),(6544,'mole','','','','','n. 痣,钱鼠',' They have found out the mole in the cabinet.<br>     他们已经发现了内阁中的间谍。<br>\n She has a tiny mole on her cheek.<br>     她面颊上有一颗小痣。<br>'),(6545,'molecular','','','','','a. 分子的',' Any of numerous natural and synthetic compounds of usually high molecular weight consisting of up to millions of repeated linked units, each a relatively light and simple molecule.<br>     聚合物许多天然和人工合成的化合物中的任一种，通常具高分子的重量，包含最多可达上百万个的彼此重复且相连的单位，每一个单位都是一个相对较轻和较简单的分子<br>\n Having an open-chain molecular structure rather than a ring-shaped structure.<br>     无环的具有开链分子结构的，而非环状结构的<br>'),(6546,'molecule','','','','molecules','n. 分子',' We can see many molecules flying in the air when a sunbeam penetrated the dark room.<br>     当一束光线穿进暗淡的房间时，我们可以看到空气中有许多小颗粒在飞舞。<br>\n Two atoms of hydrogen combine with one atom of oxygen to form a molecule of water.<br>     两个氢原子和一个氧原子结合而成一个水分子。<br>'),(6547,'molehill','','','','','n. 鼹鼠丘,琐事',' Never make a mountain of a molehill.<br>     【谚】切勿小题大做。<br>'),(6548,'molest','molested','molested','molesting','','v. 折磨,干扰,调戏',' The dog that molested the sheep was killed.<br>     那只骚扰绵羊的狗被杀死了。<br>\n Cares do still their thoughts molest, and still the unhappy poet\'s breast.<br>     烦忧仍然困扰诗人的思绪，诗人郁闷的胸膛。<br>'),(6549,'mollify','mollified','mollified','mollifying','','v. 安慰,安抚<br>\nvt. 使平息',' He tried to find ways of mollifying her.<br>     他想方设法安慰她.<br>'),(6550,'mollusk','','','','','n. 软体动物',' An animal, such as an insect or a mollusk, that lacks a backbone or spinal column.<br>     无脊椎动物缺少脊骨或脊柱的动物，例如昆虫或软体动物<br>\n The pearly internal layer of certain mollusk shells, used to make decorative objects.<br>     珠母层某些软体动物壳内似珍珠的层，用来做装饰物<br>'),(6551,'Molly','','','','','n. 莫利（女子名）',' As the sun grew warmer, Molly cast off her heavy winter clothes.<br>     太阳愈来愈暖和，于是莫利把冬衣搁在一边了。<br>'),(6552,'mollycoddle','mollycoddled','mollycoddled','mollycoddling','','n. 女性化的男人,娇生惯养的男人,没骨气<br>\nv. 溺爱,娇养',' He doesn\'t believe that children should be mollycoddled.<br>     他认为不应溺爱儿童.<br>'),(6553,'molt','molted','molted','molting','','n. 换毛,脱皮,换毛期<br>\nv. 脱毛,换毛',''),(6554,'molten','','','','','a. 熔化的,炽热的,铸造的<br>\nvbl. 融化,溶解,变软',' The study of the interaction of magnetic fields and electrically conducting liquids or gases, such as molten metal or plasma.<br>     磁流体动力学对磁场和导电的液体或气体，诸如熔化的金属或者等离子区之间的相互作用的研究<br>\n The rock formed by the cooling and solidifying of molten rock.<br>     熔岩融化的岩石冷却凝固后形成的岩石<br>'),(6555,'mom','','','','moms','n. 妈妈',' My only regret is that Todd and I didn\'t meet ten years ago so Mom could\'ve seen her dream come true.<br>     我唯一的遗憾是，和我没能在十年前就相遇，以致于妈妈没能看到她的愿望成为事实。<br>\n Mom, Dad\'s birthday is coming up. I don\'t know what to give him. Do you have any ideas for a gift?<br>     妈妈，爸爸的生日快到了。我不知道送给他点什么好。你有什么建议？<br>'),(6556,'Mombasa','','','','','蒙巴萨',''),(6557,'moment','','','','moments','n. 片刻,瞬间；力矩',' I\'d like to speak to you for a moment.<br>     我想和你谈一会儿。<br>\n My job is not a very glamorous one but it does have its moments.<br>     我的工作虽不算十分吸引人，但也自有其乐趣所在。<br>'),(6558,'momentarily','','','','','ad. 暂时地,立刻,随时地',' The charging of an isolated conducting object by momentarily grounding it while a charged body is nearby.<br>     感应通过短暂地磨擦，使一个充电导体附近的独立导体产生电流<br>\n The dark room was momentarily lit up by a vivid flash of lightning.<br>     那黑洞洞的房间顿时被强烈的闪电照亮了。<br>'),(6559,'momentary','','','','','a. 瞬间的,刹那间的',' She hesitated in momentary confusion.<br>     她一时思想紊乱，犹豫不定。<br>\n Giving a momentary or superficial impression of brilliance.<br>     闪烁的，炫耀的给人以短暂或表面印象的光彩或才华的<br>'),(6560,'momentous','','','','','a. 重要的,重大的',' History bears evidence that each momentous political change is usually followed by an economic revival.<br>     历史证明，在每次重大的政治变革之后随之而来的往往是经济上的复兴。<br>'),(6561,'momentum','','','','','n. 动力,要素<br>\nn. （物理）动量',' As the rock rolled down the mountainside, it gathered momentum.<br>     石头滚下山时，它的动量增加。<br>\n The struggle for independence is gaining momentum every day.<br>     为独立而斗争的势头日益增长。<br>'),(6562,'mommy','','','','mommies','n. 妈咪',''),(6563,'Mon','','','','','n. 监听装置(监听)',''),(6564,'monarch','','','','monarches','n. 帝王,统治者,元首/nn. 君王斑点蝶',' They attempted to overthrow the monarch.<br>     他们企图推翻国王。<br>\n The monarch as head of state.<br>     国王作为国家元首的君主<br>'),(6565,'monarch butterfly','','','','','黑脉金斑蝶',''),(6566,'monarchy','','','','monarchies','n. 君主政体,君主国,君主政治',' Britain is a constitutional monarchy.<br>     英国是君主立宪制国家。<br>\n The monarchy is seen by some as an anachronism in present-day society.<br>     君主政体在当今社会中被一些人视为是过时的制度.<br>'),(6567,'monastery','','','','monasteries','n. 修道院,僧侣',' The monks live in a large monastery.<br>     这些修道士居住在一个大修道院里。<br>\n The only regular visitors to the monastery in winter are parties of skiers who go there at Christmas and Easter.<br>     冬季到修道院来的常客只是几批滑雪者，他们通常在圣旦节和复活节去那里。<br>'),(6568,'monasticism','','','','','n. 修道生活,禁欲主义',''),(6569,'Monday','','','','','n. 星期一',' He\'ll arrive on Monday.<br>     他将于星期一到达。<br>\n Next Monday will be my 21st birthday.<br>     下星期一是我二十一岁的生日。<br>'),(6570,'monetarily','','','','','ad. 在货币问题上<br>\n从金钱角度<br>\n财政上',''),(6571,'monetary','','','','','a. 货币的,金融的',' The monetary system of some countries used to be based on gold.<br>     过去有些国家的货币制度是金本位制的。<br>\n A former monetary unit of East Germany worth100 pfennigs.<br>     东德马克德意志民主共和国使用的货币单位，等于100芬尼<br>'),(6572,'money','','','','moneys','n. 钱',' Money doesn\'t always bring happiness.<br>     财富并不一定带来快乐。<br>\n I\'m not made of money, you know!<br>     你知道我又不是财神爷！<br>'),(6573,'Money isn\'t everything','','','','','金钱不是一切',''),(6574,'money order','','','','','n. 汇兑',' I have enclosed a post office money order for$40, 000 which include the express charges.<br>     同函奉上面额40，000元的邮局汇票一纸包括快递费在内。<br>\n Enclosed please find a money order.<br>     兹附上一张汇票，请查收。<br>'),(6575,'moneylender','','','','','n. 放债者',' A banker or moneylender.<br>     银行家或放债人<br>'),(6576,'moneymaking','','','','','a. 孜孜求利的, 热心赚钱的',' He\'s intent on moneymaking.<br>     他一心一意地赚钱。<br>'),(6577,'Mongol','','','','','n. 蒙古人,蒙古语',' A medieval ruler of a Mongol, Tartar, or Turkish tribe.<br>     可汗蒙古族、鞑靼人或土耳其人在中世纪时的统治者<br>\n Mongol ruler who succeeded his father, Genghis Khan.<br>     窝阔台蒙古统治者，他继承了父亲成吉思汗的王位<br>'),(6578,'Mongolia','','','','','n. 蒙古',' A unit of currency in Mongolia.<br>     蒙戈蒙古人民共和国一货币单位<br>\n For all I know she may have emigrated to Outer Mongolia.<br>     我不太清楚，她也许移民去了外蒙古。<br>'),(6579,'Mongolian','','','','','n. 属于蒙古人种的人,蒙古语,蒙古症患者<br>\na. 蒙古人的,蒙古语的,蒙古病症的',' A Mongol or Mongolian.<br>     一个蒙古人或蒙古语<br>\n Looking over my notes.I can find only a few Han names, the rest are all Mongolian.<br>     翻翻我的笔记本，我只看到几个汉族名字，其他都是蒙族。<br>'),(6580,'mongrel','','','','mongrels','n. 杂种动物,混血儿',' A dog considered to be inferior or undesirable; a mongrel.<br>     劣等狗一种被视为低劣的或不受欢迎的狗；杂种狗<br>'),(6581,'monitor','monitored','monitored','monitoring','monitors','n. 监督器,级长,监听员<br>\nv. 监视,监听,监督<br>\n[计算机] 显示器,监视',' The monitor collected the exercise books after the class was over.<br>     下课后，班长把练习册收了起来。<br>\n This instrument monitors the patient\'s heartbeats.<br>     这台仪器监听病人的心跳。<br>'),(6582,'monk','','','','monks','n. 僧侣,修道士',' It is reported that some modern monks are using computers.<br>     有报道说有些现代和尚在使用计算机。<br>\n The hood or hooded robe worn especially by a monk.<br>     头巾，长袍尤指僧侣穿戴的头巾或带头巾的长袍<br>'),(6583,'monkey','monkeyed','monkeyed','monkeying','monkeys','n. 猴子<br>\nv. 胡闹,乱弄',' When the tree falls, the monkeys scatter.<br>     树倒猢狲散。<br>\n The little boy is as mischievous as a monkey.<br>     这个小男孩像猴子一样调皮。<br>'),(6584,'mono','','','','','a. (唱片等)单声道的<br>\nn. 单声道唱片',''),(6585,'mono-','','','','','[词头]单,单一的',''),(6586,'monochromatic','','','','','a. 单色的,一色的',''),(6587,'monochrome','','','','','n. 单色画,单色画法<br>\na. 单色的,黑白的<br>\n[计算机] 单色的',' Monitors, also known as video display terminals(VDTs), resemble television screens, and may be either monochrome or color.<br>     显示器类似于电视屏幕，也被称为视频显示终端（VDTs），有单色显示器和彩色显示器。<br>'),(6588,'monogamous','','','','','n. 一夫一妻的',''),(6589,'monogamy','','','','','n. 一夫一妻制',''),(6590,'monogram','monogrammed','monogrammed','monogramming','monograms','n. 由姓与名的第一个字母编制而成的图案',' The set of bath towels you personally monogrammed for us is beautiful.<br>     那套有你亲手绣着我们名字的浴巾美极了。<br>\n Stationery monogrammed with her initials.<br>     印有她姓名首字母的信笺<br>'),(6591,'monograph','','','','','n. 专题论文',''),(6592,'monolithic','','','','','a. 独石的,完全统一的,整体的',' A tall, four-sided shaft of stone, usually tapered and monolithic, that rises to a point.<br>     方尖石碑升到一点的四面体高塔或碑石，常为尖顶和由整块石料的<br>\n A monolithic sculpture.<br>     独块巨石雕塑<br>'),(6593,'monologue','','','','','n. 独白',' He writes dialogue by cut monologue in two.<br>     他把独白切成两截来写对白。<br>'),(6594,'monomer','','','','','n. 单体',' A polymer of two or more different monomers.<br>     共聚物一种由两种或多种不同单体构成的聚合物<br>'),(6595,'monophonic','','','','','单声道的',''),(6596,'monopolize','monopolized','monopolized','monopolizing','','v. 独占,垄断',''),(6597,'monopoly','','','','monopolies','n. 垄断,专利',' He seems to think he has a monopoly of brains.<br>     他似乎认为只有他才聪明。<br>\n The telecommunication service is a government monopoly.<br>     电信为政府专营。<br>'),(6598,'monostable','','','','','单稳态的',''),(6599,'monotone','','','','','a. 单调的<br>\nn. (说话或唱歌)单调,单调音',' A monotone recitation of names.<br>     名字的单调的朗诵<br>'),(6600,'monotonous','','','','','a. 单调的',' I only heard a monotonous voice of the singer.<br>     我只听到那个歌唱家单调的声音。<br>\n The explorer live on a monotonous diet of bean and rice.<br>     探险者靠吃豆子和米饭这些单调的食物为生。<br>'),(6601,'monotony','','','','','n. 单调,干燥,无味',' I work with monotony.<br>     我工作很单调。<br>\n The radio relieves the monotony of everyday life.<br>     收音机缓解了我们日常生活的单调状况。<br>'),(6602,'monotype','','','','','n. 自动铸字机,单型<br>\nv. 用自动铸字机拼',''),(6603,'monoxide','','','','','n. 一氧化物',' As motor vehicles burn fuel, they give off carbon monoxide as a waste.<br>     在汽车燃烧燃料时，产生废气—一氧化碳。<br>\n As the coke burns, some of it combine with the oxygen in the air to form carbon monoxide.<br>     焦碳燃烧时