ined its own distinct culture and a strong nationalist sentiment. Cardiff is the capital and the largest city. Population, 2,790,462.<br>     威尔士英国大不列颠岛西部半岛之一地区。自联盟令（1536年）后与英格兰合并，它同时保持了自己的独特文化风格和强烈的民族主义情感。卡迪夫为其首府及最大城市。人口2，790，462<br>\n The nationalists have put themselves out of court as desirable rulers of their communities.<br>     那些民族主义者做出的令人不齿之事证明他们不够资格做他们的社区的统治者。<br>'),(6929,'nationality','','','','nationalities','n. 国籍,民族',' There were diplomats of all nationalities in Geneva.<br>     日内瓦有世界各国的外交官。<br>\n There are two main nationalities in our village.<br>     我们村子有两大民族。<br>'),(6930,'nationalize','nationalized','nationalized','nationalizing','','v. 国有化',' Nationalize the steel industry.<br>     使钢铁工业国有化<br>\n Our government will not nationalize or requisition investment any property of investor.<br>     我国政府不会把投资者的资金和财产收归国有或征用。<br>'),(6931,'nationally','','','','','ad. 以国民立场,举国一致,全国性',''),(6932,'nationwide','','','','','a. 全国性的<br>\nad. 在全国范围内',' The chairman\'s speech will be broadcast nationwide.<br>     主席的讲话将向全国广播。<br>\n A speech that was broadcast nationwide; nationwide opposition to the tax hike.<br>     全国性的播出的演说；全国性的反对税收增多<br>'),(6933,'native','','','','natives','a. 本国的,本土的<br>\nn. 本地人',' He is a Beijing native.<br>     他是土生土长的北京人。<br>\n This house was built of native stones.<br>     这间屋子是用当地的石头建的。<br>'),(6934,'nativity','','','','nativities','n. 出生,诞生',' The baby\'s nativity brought them great pleasure.<br>     孩子的诞生给他们带来了巨大的欢乐。<br>'),(6935,'NATO','','','','','北大西洋公约组织',' Hasn\'t NATO slaked his lust for blood?<br>     难道北约还没有满足他的血腥的欲望吗？<br>\n Our Embassy was devastated by three bombs of NATO.<br>     我们的使馆被北约的三枚炸弹炸毁了。<br>'),(6936,'natty','','','','','a. 整洁的,漂亮的',''),(6937,'natural','','','','naturals','a. 自然的,正常的',' I prefer to see animals living in their natural state.<br>     我宁愿看处于野生状态的动物。<br>\n It\'s quite natural that you should succeed.<br>     你的成功是很自然的事情。<br>'),(6938,'natural gas','','','','','天然气',' They continued down until they came to some pockets of natural gas.<br>     他们继续往下钻, 终於找到了一些天然气的气阱.<br>\n Any of several highly volatile, flammable liquid mixtures of hydrocarbons distilled from petroleum, coal tar, and natural gas and used as fuel, as solvents, and in making various chemicals.<br>     石脑油一种高度挥发性的易燃液态碳氢化合物混合物，从石油、煤焦油和天然气中提炼出来，并用作石油、溶剂和制造各种化合物中<br>'),(6939,'natural law','','','','','自然法则',' We must follow the natural law.<br>     我们必须遵守自然法则。<br>\n In violation of a natural law.<br>     不自然的违反一条自然规律的<br>'),(6940,'natural resource','','','','','自然资源',' If I may refer back to the problem we discussed, I think we shall stress on the conservation of our natural resource.<br>     请允许我重提我们刚才讨论过的问题，我想我们应该强调保存我们的自然资源。<br>\n Immeasurable quantity of natural resource was lost forever through misuse.<br>     无法估量的自然资源因被滥用而永远丧失了。<br>'),(6941,'natural selection','','','','','n. [生]自然选择,物竞天择说',' A systematic long-term change of this kind suggests the action of natural selection and indicates that female skeletal characteristics confer greater fitness. But is this the whole story.<br>     这种长期的系统变化说明自然选择的作用，并表明女性骨骼的特性较大的适应性。但是，情况完全是这样的吗？<br>'),(6942,'naturalism','','','','','n. 自然(状态)',' One who believes in and follows the tenets of naturalism.<br>     自然主义者信仰和追随自然主义信条的人<br>'),(6943,'naturalist','','','','naturalists','n. 自然主义者,博物学者',' He is a naturalist who studies animals and plants.<br>     他是个研究动植物的博物学家。<br>\n The naturalist told us many stories about birds.<br>     博物学家给我们讲述了许多有关鸟儿的故事。<br>'),(6944,'naturalistic','','','','','a. 自然的,自然主义的,博物学的',''),(6945,'naturalize','naturalized','naturalized','naturalizing','','vt. 使(外国人)入籍,归化',' English sporting terms have been naturalized in many languages.<br>     英语的运动术语已被多种语言采用.<br>'),(6946,'naturally','','','','','ad. 自然地',' Try to act naturally, even if you\'re tense.<br>     即使紧张也不要做作.<br>\n Plants grow naturally in such a good climate.<br>     在这麽好的气候条件下, 植物可以自然生长.<br>'),(6947,'naturalness','','','','','n. 自然,当然,本然',''),(6948,'nature','','','','natures','n.自然,自然界,自然状态; 本性,天性,性质; 质; 性格; 性; 本质',' It\'s her nature to be generous.<br>     慷慨大方是她的天性。<br>\n Nature is at its best in spring.<br>     春天里万物欣欣向荣。<br>'),(6949,'naught','','','','','n. 无价值(零)',' All his work came to naught when the fire destroyed the house he was building.<br>     大火烧毁了他正在建的房子，他的一切成绩化为乌有。<br>\n His crime has gained him naught.<br>     他既犯了罪又一无所获.<br>'),(6950,'naughty','','','','','a. 顽皮的,淘气的',' You naughty boy! I\'ve told you not to play in the street.<br>     你这顽皮孩子！我说过，叫你别在马路上玩。<br>\n The naughty boy played a neat trick.<br>     这个淘气的小男孩玩了一个巧妙的花招。<br>'),(6951,'nausea','','','','','n. 反胃,晕船,极度的不快',' Experiencing nausea; nauseated.<br>     感到反胃的；恶心的<br>\n A feeling of unease or mild nausea caused especially by fearful anticipation.<br>     因害怕而发抖特别是由于可怕的预感而引起的不适感觉或轻度的恶心呕吐<br>'),(6952,'nauseate','nauseated','nauseated','nauseating','','v. 作呕,产生恶感,厌恶',' The idea of eating raw shellfish nauseates me.<br>     我一想到吃生贝就恶心.<br>'),(6953,'nauseous','','','','','a. 令人作呕的',' She felt/was nauseous during the sea crossing.<br>     她渡海时觉得恶心.<br>\n I feel a bit nauseous.<br>     我感到有点恶心。<br>'),(6954,'nautical','','','','','a. 海上的,航海的,船员的',''),(6955,'Navajo','','','','Navajo','n. 纳瓦霍人(美国最大的印第安部落)',' A usually earth-covered Navajo dwelling traditionally built with the entrance facing east.<br>     泥盖木屋那瓦和人居住的通常用泥土抹盖的房子，传统入口朝东<br>'),(6956,'naval','','','','','a. 海军的,军舰的',' The naval officer asked him to stay away from the base.<br>     那位海军军官让他离开基地。<br>\n \"In naval parlance, the left side of a ship is the port side.\"<br>     ＂用海军的用语来说，船的左边称为左舷。＂<br>'),(6957,'nave','','','','','n. 本堂,中央部,车轮的中心部',' People gathered in the nave of the house.<br>     人们聚拢在房子的中间。<br>\n If I made big money, you would nave a cut of the cake.<br>     我要是赚了大钱的话，少不了有你的一份。<br>'),(6958,'navel','','','','','n. 肚脐,中央,中心',' An encircling band for holding in a baby\'s protruding navel.<br>     脐带连于婴儿突出的肚脐上的环绕带<br>\n Having a central mark or depression resembling a navel.<br>     脐状的有象肚脐一样的中间的印记或凹陷