led','nibbling','nibbles','n. 轻咬,啃<br>\nv. 一点点地咬,慢慢啃<br>\nvt. 咬',' Food and rent nibbled away at the money they had saved.<br>     花在食物和房租上的钱把他们的积蓄一点一点耗掉了。<br>\n The mice have nibbled a hole in the cheese.<br>     老鼠在奶酪上啃出了一个洞。<br>'),(7091,'nice','','','','','a. 美好的,令人愉快的',' How nice of you to do that!<br>     你那样做真是太好了！<br>\n It\'s nice meeting you.<br>     很高兴认识你。<br>'),(7092,'nicely','','','','','ad. 漂亮地,爽快地,恰好地',' This sport jacket will match those pants nicely.<br>     这件运动衫和那条短裤很相配。<br>\n The beef is roasting nicely on the spit.<br>     这块牛肉在烤肉叉上烤得很好。<br>'),(7093,'nicety','','','','niceties','n. 精密,正确,纤细',' He judged the distance to a nicety.<br>     他判断距离很正确。<br>\n The manner in which she received him was calculated to a nicety to seem cool without being uncivil.<br>     她接待他时始终准确地把握好分寸，看似冷淡，却不失礼。<br>'),(7094,'niche','niched','niched','niching','niches','n. 壁龛(适当的位置)<br>\nvt 放在适当的位置',' He found the right niche for himself.<br>     他发现了一个适合他的职位。<br>\n Claude was probably a humbug, whose vanity, ambition, and intelligence led him to carve out a niche as the wickedest man in the world; there is always room for a sadist at the top.<br>     克劳德或许不过是个骗子，他的虚荣、野心和才智使他在世上恶人中争得魁首之名：有残忍癖，总能爬上顶端。<br>'),(7095,'nickel','nickeled','nickeled','nickeling','nickels','n. 镍,镍币,五分镍币<br>\nv. 镀镍于',' Can you give me a dime for two nickels?<br>     你能不能用两个五分镍币给我换一个一毛的镍币？<br>\n Rick found a sure-enough nickel.<br>     里克发现一个纯正的镍币。<br>'),(7096,'nickname','nicknamed','nicknamed','nicknaming','nicknames','n. 绰号,昵称<br>\nv. 给...取绰号,叫错名字',' Jess is just my nickname - my real name is Jessica.<br>     杰西只是我的昵称，我的真名是杰西卡。<br>\n They nicknamed him \"Lofty\" because he was so tall.<br>     他们给他起了个绰号叫“高个儿”， 因为他身材很高。<br>'),(7097,'nicotine','','','','','n. 尼古丁',' Smokers who inhale are likely to become addicted to nicotine.<br>     吸烟的人容易对尼古丁上瘾.<br>'),(7098,'niece','','','','nieces','n. 侄女,外甥女',' My niece always clings to me whenever she is at my home.<br>     我侄女只要一到我家里就缠着我不放。<br>\n You should take