北,来自东北',' The northeast wind was blowing hard at that time.<br>     那时候东北风刮得正紧。<br>\n His house is in the northeast of this city.<br>     他的家在这个城市的东北部。<br>'),(7175,'northern','','','','','a. 北部的,北方的',' In the northern hemisphere, spring is in March and April.<br>     在北半球，春季是三月和四月。<br>\n The Confederacy was defeated by the northern states.<br>     南部邦联被北方打败了。<br>'),(7176,'northward','','','','','n. 北方,北<br>\na. 向北的<br>\nad. 向北的',''),(7177,'northwards','','','','','a. 向北的<br>\nad. 向北',' The coast sweeps (away) northwards in a wide curve.<br>     海岸呈一大弧形向北伸展.<br>\n The escapee ran quickly northward and cut back to the original place.<br>     逃犯迅速向北跑去，然后又突然回到原地。<br>'),(7178,'northwest','','','','','n. 西北,西北方<br>\na. 西北的,在西北的,来自西北的<br>\nad. 向西北',' The city is located in the northwest part of Canada.<br>     这座城市位于加拿大的西北部。<br>\n The tourists drove northwest.<br>     游客们开车向西北而去。<br>'),(7179,'Norwegian','','','','','n. 挪威人,挪威语<br>\na. 挪威的,挪威人的,挪威语的',' The Norwegians live in a comparatively cold zone.<br>     挪威人生活在比较寒冷的地区。<br>\n Do you know Norwegian?<br>     你懂挪威语吗？<br>'),(7180,'nose','nosed','nosed','nosing','noses','n. 鼻子,突出部分,嗅觉<br>\nv. 嗅到',' Many dogs have a good nose.<br>     多数狗嗅觉都很灵。<br>\n The horse won by a nose.<br>     那匹马以微弱优势险胜。<br>'),(7181,'nostalgia','','','','','n. 乡愁,向往过去,怀旧之情',' Her work is pervaded by nostalgia for a past age.<br>     她的作品充满了怀旧之情。<br>\n The sight inspired him with nostalgia.<br>     这景象激起了他的怀旧之情。<br>'),(7182,'nostril','','','','nostrils','n. 鼻孔',' He dislikes his wide nostrils.<br>     他不喜欢自己的宽大的鼻孔。<br>'),(7183,'not','','','','','ad. 不<br>\n[计算机] \"非\"',' Not everyone likes this book.<br>     并不是每个人都喜欢这本书。<br>\n They will not agree.<br>     他们不会同意。<br>'),(7184,'Not at all','','','','','一点也不',' I\'m not at all satisfied.<br>     我一点也不满意。<br> Not at all.<br>     别客气<br>'),(7185,'notable','','','','notables','a. 显著的,著名的<br>\nn. 名人',' He is a notable artist.<br>     他是一位著名的艺术家。<br>\n The difference contrast is notable.<br>     差别对比是显著的。<br>'