英镑的钱.<br>\n The speaker had a sheaf of notes on the desk in front of him.<br>     演讲者在他面前的桌子上放着一叠笔记。<br>'),(7194,'noteworthy','','','','','a. 值得注意的',' A biographical essay presenting the subject\'s most noteworthy characteristics and achievements.<br>     人物概评表现主要人物最值得注意的特点和成就的传记性的文章<br>\n A noteworthy advance in cancer research.<br>     在癌症研究方面引人注意的进步<br>'),(7195,'nothing','','','','','ad. 毫不<br>\nn. 微不足道的人或事<br>\npron. 什么也没有',' Nothing ever happens in this town.<br>     这小镇上什么事也没发生过。<br>\n It has nothing to do with you.<br>     这与你无关。<br>'),(7196,'notice','noticed','noticed','noticing','notices','n. 注意,布告,通知<br>\nv. 注意,通知,留心',' Her appearance attracted my notice.<br>     她的外表引起了我的注意。<br>\n Did you notice anything peculiar?<br>     你注意到有什么异常的事吗？<br>'),(7197,'noticeable','','','','','a. 显而易见的',' There\'s been a noticeable improvement in her handwriting.<br>     她的书法有了明显的进步。<br>\n The scar on her forehead is hardly noticeable.<br>     她额头上的伤疤不太明显。<br>'),(7198,'notification','','','','','n. 通知,通告,告示<br>\n[计算机] 通知',' There have been no more notifications of cholera cases in the last week.<br>     上星期已没有霍乱病例的报告.<br>'),(7199,'notify','notified','notified','notifying','','v. 通知,通告,报告',' We\'ll notify her to draw up a contract.<br>     我们将通知她起草一份合同。<br>\n She notified us of the meeting.<br>     她通知我们开会。<br>'),(7200,'notion','','','','notions','n. 观念,想法,主张',' He didn\'t have a slightest notion of what I meant.<br>     他对我指的是什么没有一点儿概念。<br>\n We had a notion that he was telling a lie.<br>     我们当时的看法是他在说谎。<br>'),(7201,'notorious','','','','','a. 臭名昭著的',' Hitler is a notorious killer.<br>     希特勒是一个臭名昭著的刽子手。<br>\n The notorious thief will be put up for trial next week.<br>     那个臭名昭著的偷窃犯将于下周出庭受审。<br>'),(7202,'notwithstanding','','','','','ad. 虽然,尽管<br>\nprep. 纵使<br>\nconj. 虽然',' He tried to prevent the marriage but it still took place notwithstanding.<br>     虽然他竭力阻止这桩婚姻，但还是成了事实。<br>\n Notwithstanding her naughtiness, I love my little girl.<br>     尽管我的小姑娘很淘气，我还是很爱她。<br>'),(7203,'nought','','','','noughts','n. 没有,零,无',' Put two noughts after a seven to make seven hundred.<br>     在7后面加两个零成为700。<br>\n The Greeks did nought, but play the fools and lie.<br>     希腊人一事无成，仅仅在愚弄和欺骗。<br>'),(7204,'noun','','','','nouns','n. 名词',' There are many nouns in a dictionary.<br>     字典里有很多名词。<br>\n The function of an adjective is to describe or add to the meaning of a noun.<br>     形容词的作用是描述或增加名词的意思。<br>'),(7205,'nourish','nourished','nourished','nourishing','','v. 滋养,使...健壮,怀有',' Milk is all we need to nourish a small baby.<br>     我们供给婴儿营养只需喂奶就够了。<br>\n She have nourish the dream of becoming a movie star.<br>     她曾怀有成为电影明星的梦想。<br>'),(7206,'nourishment','','','','','n. 滋养品,养料,营养',' The patient took no nourishment all day until dinner.<br>     这个病人晚饭前什么东西都没吃。<br>\n A source of nourishment, especially a nourishing ingredient in a food.<br>     营养品，滋养物营养的来源，尤指食物中的营养成分<br>'),(7207,'novel','','','','','a. 新奇的<br>\nn. 小说',' We are supposed to dress up as movie characters for the party, what a novel idea!<br>     我们在晚会上要装扮得像电影中的角色，这是一个多么新奇的主意啊！<br>\n I like reading novels in my spare time.<br>     我喜欢闲暇时读小说。<br>'),(7208,'novelette','','','','','n. 中篇小说',''),(7209,'novelist','','','','novelists','n. 小说家',' I dreamed of becoming a novelist.<br>     我梦想成为一个小说家。<br>\n The novelist had issued many saga novels.<br>     那个小说家已经发表了很多长篇小说。<br>'),(7210,'novelty','','','','novelties','n. 新奇,新鲜,新奇的事物',' The novelty of his surroundings soon wore off.<br>     他对环境的新奇感不久就淡薄了。<br>\n The author seems to strain after novelty.<br>     作者似乎在力图标新立异。<br>'),(7211,'November','','','','','n. 十一月',' This office will open in November.<br>     这个事务所将在十一月开业。<br>\n He conked out in November with pleurisy.<br>     他患肋膜炎于十一月份死去。<br>'),(7212,'novice','','','','novices','n. 新手,初学者',' She\'s a complete novice as a reporter.<br>     她初任记者，完全是个生手。<br>\n A novice or learner, particularly in newspaper reporting.<br>     生手，新手新手或初学者，尤指报纸报导中的新手<br>'),(7213,'now','','','','','n. 现在,此刻<br>\nad. 现在,立刻<br>\nconj. 既然<br>\n=National Organization of Women 全国妇女组织',' He was at home just now.<br>     他刚才在家。<br>\n He is writing a letter now.<br>     他现在正在写信。<br>'),(7214,'nowadays','','','','','ad. 现今,现在<br>\nn. 现今,当今',' Nowadays, the poor student has become a rich man.<br>     如今，那个穷学生成了富人。<br>\n Phonograph is no longer used nowadays.<br>     留声机现在已不再使用了。<br>'),(7215,'nowhere','','','','','ad. 任何地方都不<br>\nn. 不知道的地方,无处',' That kind of talk will get you nowhere.<br>     说那种话对你没好处。<br>\n The book was nowhere to be found.<br>     这本书无处可寻。<br>'),(7216,'noxious','','','','','a. 有害的,有毒的',' Noxious chemical wastes.<br>     有毒化学废弃物<br>\n Chemicals that produce a noxious vapor when mixed.<br>     化学物质混合后会放出有毒气体<br>'),(7217,'ns','','','','','纳秒',''),(7218,'nuance','','','','','n. 配色,色调,细微差别',' A rich artistic performance, full of nuance.<br>     一场意味深长的艺术表演充满了微妙之处<br>'),(7219,'nuclear','','','','','a. 原子核的,原子能的',' They decided to establish a nuclear power station.<br>     他们决定修建一所核电站。<br>\n Russian-born American nuclear physicist known for his work on radioactivity and genetic information as well as his books popularizing theories of physics.<br>     伽莫夫，乔治1904－1968俄国裔的美国核物理学家，因在射线遗传信息方面的研究和有关普及物理理论的书籍而闻名于世<br>'),(7220,'nucleus','','','','nuclei','n. 核,核心,原子核',' These 1000 books will form the nucleus of the new school library.<br>     这一千本书将构成学校新图书馆藏书的基础。<br>\n The nutritive tissue that is derived from the nucleus and surrounds the embryo of the seed.<br>     外胚乳包在种子胚芽外，产生于细胞核的营养性组织<br>'),(7221,'nuisance','','','','nuisances','n. 讨厌的东西,讨厌的人',' You are a confounded nuisance; stop pestering me.<br>     你这个可恶的东西，别再缠着我了。<br>\n The noise was so loud that it was a nuisance to the neighbors.<br>     那声音大得让邻居讨厌。<br>'),(7222,'null','','','','','a. 无效力的,无效的,无价值的<br>\nn. 零<br>\n[计算机] 空',' The state or quality of being null.<br>     无效无效的状况或性质<br>\n The process of inserting meaningless characters, such as null characters, zeros, or spaces, into the unused portions of a field, record, or fixed- length block of data.<br>     一种插入一些无意义字符的处理方法。例如，在一个字段、记录或固定长度数据块的不用部分插入空字符、零或空格。<br>'),(7223,'nullify','nullified','nullified','nullifying','','v. 使无效,废弃,取消',' How can we nullify the enemy\'s propaganda?<br>     怎样才能抵销敌人的宣传?<br>\n The state of being nullified.<br>     取消被取消的状态<br>'),(7224,'numb','numbed','numbed','numbing','','a. 麻木的,失去知觉的<br>\nv. 使...麻木,使...昏迷,使...失去知觉',' The shock left me numb.<br>     我惊呆了。<br>\n His leg was numbed by the intense pain.<br>     他的腿因剧痛而麻木。<br>'),(7225,'number','numbered','numbered','numbering','numbers','n. 号码,数字<br>\nv. 编号,加号码,总计<br>\nvi. 总计<br>\nvt. 编号',' The students of our department numbered in the hundreds.<br>     我们系的学生总共有几百人。<br>\n The number of your finger is ten.<br>     你双手手指的总数是10。<br>'),(7226,'numbering','','','','','编号',' Alas, poor duke! the task he undertakes is numbering sands, and drinking oceans dry: Where one on his side fights, thousands will fly.<br>     唉！可怜的公爵！他担负的工作简直是数沙饮海；一个人站在他一边作战，就有1000人转身逃走。<br>\n The number of your finger is ten.<br>     你双手手指的总数是10。<br>'),(7227,'numeral','','','','numerals','n. 数字,数<br>\na. 数字的,表示数字的',' I asked a little boy, \"how many numerals can you count?\"<br>     我问一个小孩：“你能数多少个数字?”<br>\n The numerals he provided us are wrong.<br>     他提供给我们的数字是错的。<br>'),(7228,'numerate','numerated','numerated','numerating','','a. 数学基础好的',''),(7229,'numeration','','','','','记数,计算',''),(7230,'numeric','','','','','数字的',' A terminal containing less than a full alphanumeric keyboard; for example, one containing ten numeric keys plus control keys.<br>     一种终端，它的键盘不包括全套的字母数字字符键；例如，只包括十个数字键以及若干控制键。<br>\n A low-speed input device that converts graphic and pictorial data into binary, numeric inputs for a digital computer.<br>     一种低速输入设备，它将图形和图象数据转换成用于数字计算机的二进制数值输入。<br>'),(7231,'numerical','','','','','a. 数字的,用数字表示的',' A pictorial representation of numerical data or relationships, especially a graph, but having each value represented by a proportional number of pictures.<br>     统计图表，象形图用图画表现数字的信息或关系，尤指图表，但用有比例的一定数字的图画来代表每种价值<br>\n Put these invoice in numerical order.<br>     把这些发票按其号码顺序放好。<br>'),(7232,'numerous','','','','','a. 为数众多的,许多',' That kind of bird has become more numerous around here lately.<br>     近来在附近一带那种鸟越来越多了。<br>\n The Oxford has received numerous endowments.<br>     牛津获得了许多捐款。<br>'),(7233,'nun','','','','nuns','n. 尼姑,修女',' The nuns live in the convent.<br>     修女们住在修道院。<br>\n Any woman in the world, even a nun, would rather lose her virtue than her reputation.<br>     世间的女性，甚至尼姑，都情愿失掉贞操也不愿失掉声誉。<br>'),(7234,'nurse','nursed','nursed','nursing','nurses','n. 护士,褓姆,奶妈<br>\nv. 看护,照顾,栽培',' My daughter is a nurse.<br>     我女儿是一名护士。<br>\n She spends her spare time nursing her old mother.<br>     她的业余时间都花在照顾她年老的母亲上。<br>'),(7235,'nursery','','','','nurseries','n. 托儿所',' She sent her little son to a nursery when she was working.<br>     她工作的时候就把小儿子送到托儿所。<br>\n She\'s all for more nursery schools being built.<br>     她坚持主张多建托儿所.<br>'),(7236,'nurture','nurtured','nurtured','nurturing','','n. 养育,养成,教育<br>\nv. 养育,给与营养物,教养',' He wants to take the nurture of that delicate child.<br>     他想去照料那个纤弱的孩子。<br>\n The child got his nurture from his loving parents.<br>     这个孩子的教育来自他慈爱的双亲。<br>'),(7237,'nut','nutted','nutted','nutting','nuts','n. 坚果,螺母, 螺帽,难对付的人(事)<br>\nvi. 采坚果',' I am a Clark Gable nut: I have seen all his films.<br>     我是克拉克·盖博的影迷，我看过他演的所有影片。<br>\n Cashew nuts and walnuts are both nuts.<br>     腰果和核桃都是坚果。<br>'),(7238,'nutrient','','','','nutrients','a. 营养的,滋养的<br>\nn. 营养物,营养品',' Plants absorb minerals and other nutrients from the soil.<br>     植物从泥土中吸收矿物质和其他养料。<br>\n Maybe these nutrients are helpful to your health.<br>     或许这些营养品对你的健康有帮助。<br>'),(7239,'nutrition','','','','','n. 营养',' This food provides all the nutrition your dog needs.<br>     本食品含有狗所必须的一切营养。<br>\n Our bodies need adequate nutrition.<br>     我们的身体需要充足的营养。<br>'),(7240,'nylon','','','','nylons','n. 尼龙',' This coat is made of nylon.<br>     这件衣服是尼龙的。<br>\n Is this garment made of pure wool, or of wool mixed with nylon?<br>     这件衣服是纯羊毛的，还是羊毛与尼龙混纺的 ？<br>'),(7241,'oak','','','','oaks','n. 橡树,橡木<br>\na. 橡木制的',' The door is made of oak.<br>     这门是橡木做的。<br>\n There are many acorns on the oak tree.<br>     这棵橡树上有很多橡子。<br>'),(7242,'oar','oared','oared','oaring','oars','n. 桨,橹<br>\nv. 划(行)',' Many people tried to get their oars in.<br>     许多人都想插一手。<br>\n The blade of an oar or paddle.<br>     桨面桨或橹的叶片<br>'),(7243,'oasis','','','','oases','n. 绿洲',' The caravan stopped for the night at an oasis.<br>     旅行队在沙漠中的绿洲停下来过夜。<br>\n Her bedroom is an oasis of calm in the noisy house.<br>     她的卧室是这座嘈杂房屋中一个难得的安静之处。<br>'),(7244,'oath','','','','oaths','n. 誓言,誓约',' Repeat the oath after me.<br>     请跟着我宣誓。<br>\n The judge reminded the witness that she was under oath.<br>     法官提醒那个证人她已经宣过誓了。<br>'),(7245,'obedience','','','','','n. 服从,顺从',' Obedience to order is very important in an army.<br>     服从命令在军队中是很重要的。<br>\n The sergeant expects obedience from his men/that his men will obey him/his men to obey him.<br>     中士要士兵服从他的命令.<br>'),(7246,'obedient','','','','','a. 服从的,顺从的',' The dog is obedient to its master\'s orders.<br>     这只狗听从主人的命令。<br>\n My brother is an obedient boy.<br>     我弟弟是一个听话的男孩。<br>'),(7247,'obesity','','','','','n. 肥胖,肥大',' Obesity is a problem for many people in western countries.<br>     西方国家很多人都有过度肥胖的问题.<br>\n The branch of medicine that deals with the causes, prevention, and treatment of obesity.<br>     肥胖症学研究肥胖的原因、预防和治疗的医学的分支<br>'),(7248,'obey','obeyed','obeyed','obeying','','v. 服从,听从',' Soldiers are expected to obey their orders without question.<br>     军人应当绝对服从命令。<br>\n We should obey the law.<br>     我们应当遵守法律。<br>'),(7249,'object','','','','','n. 物,物体,目标,宾语<br>\nv. 反对',' Some people objected that the new tax law was unfair.<br>     一些人反对说，新税法不公平。<br>\n Various objects were on the table.<br>     桌子上摆着各种各样的物体。<br>'),(7250,'objection','','','','objections','n. 反对,异议',' There is no objection to your opening the window.<br>     你开窗没有什么不可以的。<br>\n The chief objection to this book is its great length.<br>     这本书的主要缺点是过于冗长。<br>'),(7251,'objective','','','','objectives','a. 客观的<br>\nn. 目标,目的',' Try to be more objective about it.<br>     尽量更客观地对待此事吧。<br>\n We have succeeded in our main objectives.<br>     我们已经成功地达到了主要目标。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (7252,'obligation','','','','obligations','n. 义务,责任',' The company has to fulfill the terms of its obligation.<br>     这个公司必须履行合同条款。<br>\n Damaging the goods puts you under an obligation to buy them.<br>     你损坏了这些商品，你就得都买下来。<br>'),(7253,'obligatory','','','','','a. 义不容辞的,义务的,必须的',' Be not a visit to Mr. George obligatory?<br>     是不是必须我拜访乔治先生？<br>\n It is obligatory upon us to protect the world from nuclear war.<br>     保护世界免於核子战争是我们的义务。<br>'),(7254,'oblige','obliged','obliged','obliging','','v. 强制,赐,施恩惠',' I\'m much obliged to you.<br>     我非常感谢你。<br>\n I felt obliged to leave after such an unpleasant quarrel.<br>     发生了这样不愉快的争吵之后，我觉得有必要离开。<br>'),(7255,'obligee','','','','','n. 权利人,债权人',''),(7256,'obliging','','','','','a. 乐于助人的',' Exhibiting a desire or willingness to please; cheerfully obliging.<br>     殷勤的表现出取悦别人意愿的；乐于顺从的<br>\n You are not obliged to answer these questions, but it would make our task easier.<br>     这些问题并非非答不可, 但答问对我们大有助益.<br>'),(7257,'obligor','','','','','n. 债务人,欠债者',''),(7258,'oblique','obliqued','obliqued','obliquing','obliques','a. 间接的,斜的<br>\nvi. 倾斜',' He drew an oblique line on paper.<br>     他在纸上划了一条斜线。<br>\n The tendency to grow at an oblique or horizontal angle. Used of roots, stems, or branches.<br>     斜向性向倾斜或与水平成角度的方向生长的倾向。用于植物的根、茎或枝<br>'),(7259,'obliterate','obliterated','obliterated','obliterating','','v. 涂去,擦去,删除',' The criminal obliterated all fingerprints.<br>     罪犯擦掉全部指印。<br>\n The view was obliterated by the fog.<br>     景色被浓雾遮住了。<br>'),(7260,'oblivious','','','','','a. 没注意到，或不知道',' I was oblivious of my surroundings.<br>     我没有注意到周围的事物。<br>\n The speaker ground on, oblivious of his listeners\' boredom.<br>     演说者唠唠叨叨, 没注意到听众的厌烦情绪.<br>'),(7261,'oblong','','','','oblongs','n. 长方形(椭圆形)<br>\na. 长方形的(椭圆形的)',''),(7262,'obnoxious','','','','','a. 可憎的,不愉快的,讨厌的',' I hate his obnoxious behavior.<br>     我恨他那讨厌的品行。<br>\n He is the most obnoxious man I know.<br>     他是我认识的最可憎的人。<br>'),(7263,'obscene','','','','','a. 淫秽的, 猥亵的',' She got an obscene phone call yesterday.<br>     她昨天接到一个下流的电话。<br>\n There are much obscene languages in this book.<br>     这本书中有很多淫秽的语言。<br>'),(7264,'obscure','obscured','obscured','obscuring','','a. 微暗的,难解的,不著名的<br>\nv. 使...阴暗,隐藏,使...含糊',' The path grew more obscure in the fading light.<br>     小径在渐渐消失的光线下变得更暗了。<br>\n The poem is obscure to those unlearned in the classics.<br>     这首诗在不懂古典诗作的人看来是费解的。<br>'),(7265,'observance','','','','observances','n. 遵守,仪式,惯例',' The worker was praised for his observance of the rules.<br>     这个工人因为严格遵守规则而受到了表扬。<br>\n An act of religious observance or prayer, especially when private.<br>     祈祷宗教仪式的活动或祷告的行为，尤指秘密的进行的<br>'),(7266,'observation','','','','observations','n. 观察<br>\nvb.了解',' The thief escaped observation.<br>     小偷未被人注意。<br>\n He was taken into hospital for observation.<br>     他被送进医院观察。<br>'),(7267,'observatory','','','','observatories','n. 天文台,气象台,了望台',''),(7268,'observe','observed','observed','observing','','v. 观察,遵守,注意到',' I observed him entering the bank with a gun.<br>     我看到他带着枪进了银行。<br>\n The police have been observing his movements.<br>     警方一直监视着他的一举一动。<br>'),(7269,'observer','','','','observers','n. 观察者',' They sent her there as an observer.<br>     他们派她去那做观察员。<br>\n The driver is a poor observer of speed restrictions.<br>     这个司机是个不遵守速度限制的人。<br>'),(7270,'obsess','obsessed','obsessed','obsessing','','vt. 缠住(不断地困扰)',' The fear of death obsessed her throughout her old age.<br>     她晚年一直受著死亡恐惧的困扰.<br>'),(7271,'obsession','','','','obsessions','n.[U]痴迷；困扰,成见<br>\n  [C]使人痴迷的的人（或物）',' Her commitment to a great cause degenerated from a crusade into an obsession.<br>     她致力於一伟大事业, 但其崇高的奋斗精神已变质成为偏执的狂热.<br>\n Caused or conditioned by compulsion or obsession.<br>     强迫的由强迫或压制所引起或制约的<br>'),(7272,'obsessive','','','','','a. 强迫性的, 分神的',' An abnormally obsessive preoccupation or attachment; a fixation.<br>     迷恋，迷信（物）不正常地萦绕于心头的事物或情感；固恋<br>\n An obsessive impulse to steal regardless of economic need, usually arising from an unconscious symbolic value associated with the stolen item.<br>     偷窃狂一种不考虑经济需要的持续的要去偷窃的神经冲动，通常由与被偷窃的物品相关的无意识的象征性价值引起<br>'),(7273,'obsidian','','','','','n. 黑曜石',''),(7274,'obsolescence','','','','','n. 荒废,退化',''),(7275,'obsolescent','','','','','a. 荒废的',''),(7276,'obsolete','obsoleted','obsoleted','obsoleting','','a. 已废弃的,过时的',' An obsolete locomotive.<br>     一个过时的火车机车<br>\n The army plans to phase out the equipment as it becomes obsolete.<br>     军队计划淘汰这些设备，因为它们已经报废了。<br>'),(7277,'obstacle','','','','obstacles','n. 障碍',' Lack of education is an obstacle of success.<br>     缺乏教育是成功的障碍。<br>\n Verification (eg Checking that weapons have been removed) could be an obstacle to an arms agreement.<br>     裁减军备协议难以达成, 症结在於如何证实（如检查武器确已销毁）.<br>'),(7278,'obstacle course','','','','','n. 超越障碍训练场',''),(7279,'obstetrician','','','','','n. 产科医生',' Her obstetrician could not be present at the birth.<br>     产科医生不能前来为她接生.<br>\n The obstetrician delivered the child.<br>     产科医生替这个孩子接生。<br>'),(7280,'obstetrics','','','','','n. 产科学,助产术',' The science of childbirth; midwifery or obstetrics.<br>     产科学分娩的科学；助产学或产科学<br>\n A physician who specializes in obstetrics.<br>     产科医生一个专攻产科医学的医生<br>'),(7281,'obstinacy','','','','obstinacies','n. (病痛等)难治,顽固',' Sheer obstinacy prevented her from apologizing.<br>     她固执得就是不道歉。<br>\n His obstinacy was irritating.<br>     他那顽固的劲真气人。<br>'),(7282,'obstinate','','','','','a. 固执的,倔强的',' This child is obstinate and rebellious.<br>     这个孩子倔强，难以管束。<br>\n Only a man full of the milk of human kindness could have continued to befriend the proud and obstinate young man.<br>     只有天性善良的人才会和这个性情高傲脾气倔强的年轻人继续交往。<br>'),(7283,'obstruct','obstructed','obstructed','obstructing','','v. 阻隔,妨碍,阻塞',' Tall trees obstructed his view of the road.<br>     有大树遮挡着，他看不见道路。<br>\n He was charged obstructing the highway.<br>     他因阻碍公路交通而受控告。<br>'),(7284,'obstruction','','','','obstructions','n. 障碍,妨碍,闭塞',' Your car is causing an obstruction.<br>     你的汽车挡道了。<br>\n He was found guilty of obstruction.<br>     他被判阻挡犯规。<br>'),(7285,'obtain','obtained','obtained','obtaining','','vt. 获得,得到<br>\nvi. 通用,流行,存在',' Further information can be obtained from our head office.<br>     详细的资料可从我们的总部得到。<br>\n These conditions no longer obtain.<br>     这些条件已不复存在了。<br>'),(7286,'obtainable','','','','','a. 能获得的(可得到的,能达到的)',' Are his records still obtainable?<br>     他的唱片还能买到吗?<br>\n The flowers are no longer obtainable.<br>     那花再也得不到了。<br>'),(7287,'obvious','','','','','a. 明显的,显而易见的',' The reformation of criminals has produced an obvious result.<br>     对罪犯的改造有了明显的效果。<br>\n The merits of the scheme are quite obvious.<br>     该计画的可取之处是相当明显的.<br>'),(7288,'obviously','','','','','ad. 显然地',' Obviously, she needs help.<br>     她显然需要帮助。<br>\n He was obviously drunk.<br>     他显然是醉了。<br>'),(7289,'occasion','occasioned','occasioned','occasioning','occasions','n. 场合,机会,理由<br>\nv. 致使,惹起,引起',' I only wear a tie on special occasions.<br>     我只在特殊场合才打领带。<br>\n There was no occasion to be so rude.<br>     没有理由这样粗鲁。<br>'),(7290,'occasional','','','','','a. 偶然的,不时的',' I only smoke an occasional cigar.<br>     我只是偶然抽一支雪茄。<br>\n He is only an occasional workman.<br>     他只是个临时雇工。<br>'),(7291,'occasionally','','','','','ad. 偶尔地',' You can\'t have a complete monopoly of the car, I need to use it occasionally.<br>     你不能一人独霸这辆汽车--我偶尔也要用.<br>\n Now and then; occasionally.<br>     不时地，时常地；偶尔地<br>'),(7292,'occident','','','','','n. 西方,欧美国家',''),(7293,'occidental','','','','','n. 西洋人,西方人<br>\na. 西洋的,西方的',' The characteristic traits or customs of Occidental peoples.<br>     西洋风味西方人习惯或品质性格特征<br>\n A native or inhabitant of an Occidental country; a westerner.<br>     西方人在西方国家居住的当地人或居住者<br>'),(7294,'occlude','occluded','occluded','occluding','','v. 使闭塞,封闭,关闭,逐出',''),(7295,'occupation','','','','occupations','a. 军事占领的,职业的<br>\nn. 职业',' He returned from Paris and found his office was under someone else\'s occupation.<br>     他从巴黎回来，发现他的办公室被别人占了。<br>\n Riding is her favorite occupation.<br>     骑马是她最喜欢的消遣。<br>'),(7296,'occupy','occupied','occupied','occupying','','v. 占领,占,住进',' Reading occupies most of my free time.<br>     阅读占去了我大部分的闲暇时间。<br>\n The enemy occupied the town.<br>     敌人占据了这个城镇。<br>'),(7297,'occur','occurred','occurred','occurring','','v. 发生<br>\nvi. 出现,存在,发生',' Didn\'t it occur to you that he was lying?<br>     你当时没想到他在撒谎吗？<br>\n That plane crash occurred only minutes after take-off.<br>     空难在起飞几分钟后就发生了。<br>'),(7298,'occurrence','','','','occurrences','n. 发生,事件,发现',' An unforeseen event that disrupts the normal course of things; an inopportune occurrence.<br>     意外扰乱事物正常进程的意外事件；不凑巧发生之事<br>\n It is more a made-up story than a real occurrence.<br>     那是杜撰的故事，而不是真实发生的事情。<br>'),(7299,'ocean','','','','oceans','n. 海洋',' This creature lives in the depth of the ocean.<br>     这种生物生活在海洋深处。<br>\n It\'s almost impossible to find him in the immense ocean.<br>     在无边无际的海洋中要找到他几乎是不可能的。<br>'),(7300,'Oceania','','','','','n. 大洋洲',' Is Australia part of Oceania?<br>     澳大利亚是在大洋洲吗？<br>\n A division of Oceania in the western Pacific Ocean comprising the islands east of the Philippines and north of the equator. It includes the Caroline, Marshall, Mariana, and Gilbert islands.<br>     密克罗尼西亚西太平洋上菲律宾群岛以东，赤道以北的岛群，是大洋洲的一部分，包括加罗林群岛，马绍尔群岛，马里亚纳群岛和吉尔伯特群岛<br>'),(7301,'oceanography','','','','','n. 海洋学',''),(7302,'o\'clock','','','','','=of the clock …点钟',' It\'s eleven o\'clock now.<br>     现在是十一点钟。<br>\n Hello. I\'d like to reserve a table for two for eight o\' clock, please.<br>     你好，我要订一张今晚八点两个人的餐桌。<br>'),(7303,'OCR','','','','','光字符阅读器,光字符识别',''),(7304,'octal','','','','','八进制的',''),(7305,'octet','','','','','八位位组',''),(7306,'October','','','','','n. 十月',' October first is the National Day of China.<br>     十月一日是中国的国庆节。<br>\n The hot weather extended into October.<br>     炎热天气一直持续到十月。<br>'),(7307,'odd','','','','','a. 奇数的,古怪的,剩余的<br>\n. 奇数',' He does odd jobs for me from time to time.<br>     他有时给我干点零活。<br>\n It\'s very odd that she didn\'t reply to our letter.<br>     她没有回我们的信是件很奇怪的事。<br>'),(7308,'odds','','','','','n. 不平等,机率,胜算',' The horse was running at odds of ten to one.<br>     那匹马参赛赔率是十比一。<br>\n He\'s moved most of his stuff; there are just a few odds and ends left.<br>     他把大部分东西都搬走了，只留下一些零星杂物。<br>'),(7309,'odometer','','','','','n. 里程表',''),(7310,'odor','','','','odors','n. 气味,名声',' My room is filled with the odor of roses.<br>     我的房间里充满了玫瑰花的香味。<br>\n What he had done put him in better odor.<br>     他的所作所为使他的名声得到改善。<br>'),(7311,'odour','','','','odours','n. 气味',' What he had done put him in better odour.<br>     他的所作所为使他的名声得到改善。<br>\n My room is filled with the odour of roses.<br>     我的房间里充满了玫瑰花的香味。<br>'),(7312,'odyssey','','','','odysseys','n.远行；奥德赛',' A drug mentioned in the Odyssey as a remedy for grief.<br>     忘忧药奥德赛中提到的一种药，作为一种医治忧愁的药剂<br>'),(7313,'OEM','','','','','初始设备制造厂家',''),(7314,'oersted','','','','','奥斯特(磁场强度单位)',''),(7315,'of','','','','','prep. …的,表示所属',' Many of the students came from other countries.<br>     学生中许多人来自其他国家。<br>\n I have heard of him.<br>     我听说过他。<br>'),(7316,'off','','','','','a. 远的,休假的,空闲的<br>\nad. 走开,出发,隔断<br>\nprep. 离开,脱落,在...之外',' Please turn the light off before leaving the room.<br>     离开房间前，请把灯关掉。<br>\n We went to the station to see her off.<br>     我们去车站为她送行。<br>'),(7317,'offence','','','','offences','n. 过错(攻击,令人讨厌的事物)',' One cannot hear such a remark without taking offence.<br>     听了这样的话，谁都会生气的。<br>\n They were arrested for drug offences.<br>     他们因吸毒罪而被逮捕。<br>'),(7318,'offend','offended','offended','offending','','v. 犯罪,冒犯,违反',' Some criminals are likely to offend again when they are released.<br>     有些罪犯被释放后有可能重新犯罪。<br>\n He was offended that we didn\'t agree with him.<br>     我们不同意他的观点，他生气了。<br>'),(7319,'offended','','','','','生气',' He was offended that we didn\'t agree with him.<br>     我们不同意他的观点，他生气了。<br>\n Your rudeness had offended many people.<br>     你的粗鲁已激怒了很多人。<br>'),(7320,'offender','','','','offenders','n. 罪犯,无礼的人,得罪人的人',' They don\'t usually imprison first offenders.<br>     他们通常不监禁初次犯罪的人。<br>\n He is always an offender on any occasions.<br>     不管什么场合，他总是得罪人。<br>'),(7321,'offense','','','','offenses','n. 犯罪,伤感情,攻击',' The best defense is offense.<br>     先下手为强/以攻为守。<br>\n A pecuniary offense.<br>     需处以罚金的犯罪行为<br>'),(7322,'offensive','','','','offensives','a. 令人不快的,侮辱的,攻击用的',' I found him extremely offensive.<br>     我发现他非常令人讨厌。<br>\n You will find it difficult to explain away your use of such offensive language.<br>     你使用这样无礼的语言是很难说得过去的.<br>'),(7323,'offer','offered','offered','offering','offers','n. 出价,提议<br>\nv. 提供,出价,企图',' He offered his seat to me.<br>     他把座位让给了我。<br>\n There is little work on offer.<br>     几乎没有什么工作可找。<br>'),(7324,'offerer','','','','','n. 发盘人,发价人',''),(7325,'offering','','','','offerings','n. 提供,奉献物,牲礼<br>\nvbl. 提供,出价,奉献',' The act or practice of offering, giving, or taking a bribe.<br>     行贿，受贿提供、给予或取得贿赂的行为或实践<br>\n I was about to raise my offer for the farm when a neighbour cut the ground from under my feet by offering a sum that I couldn\'t possibly match.<br>     我正准备出价买下那个农场，一个邻居出了一个我承受不起的价位，从而坏了我的事。<br>'),(7326,'office','','','','offices','n. 办公室',' On the wall of his office was a large map.<br>     在他办公室的墙上是一幅大地图。<br>\n There is a rose bush in front of the office.<br>     办公室前有一丛玫瑰。<br>'),(7327,'officer','officered','officered','officering','officers','n. 官员',' His father is a customs officer.<br>     他父亲是一位海关官员。<br>\n The immigration officer stamped my passport.<br>     移民官员在我的护照上盖了戳。<br>'),(7328,'official','','','','officials','a. 官方的,正式的<br>\nn. 官员',' An official of the local government called to see him.<br>     当地政府一位官员来看他。<br>\n She received several official letters this morning.<br>     她今天早晨收到了几封公函。<br>'),(7329,'officially','','','','','ad. 作为公务员,职务上,官方地，正式地',' This new library was officially opened last week.<br>     这家新图书馆上星期正式落成起用。<br>\n The new procedures have been officially christened, so to speak.<br>     新措施可以说已经正式实施了.<br>'),(7330,'offset','offset','offset','offsetting','offsets','n. 抵销,支派,平版印刷<br>\nv. 弥补,抵销,用平版印刷<br>\n[计算机] 偏移',' Higher mortgage rates are partly offset by increased tax allowances.<br>     抵押款提高了，其中一部分可由免税额增加而抵消。<br>\n He raised his prices to offset the increased cost of materials.<br>     他提高售价以补偿材料增加的成本。<br>'),(7331,'offshore','','','','','a. 海面的,吹向海面的<br>\nad. 向海面',' A ship that ran aground; a ship aground offshore.<br>     搁浅的轮船；在岸边搁浅的轮船<br>\n A small boat used to peddle provisions to ships anchored offshore.<br>     小卖艇向在岸边抛锚的船只兜售货物的小船<br>'),(7332,'offspring','','','','offsprings','n. 子孙,后代,产物',' How do parents pass genes on to their offspring?<br>     父母是怎样把基因遗传给自己的子女的？<br>\n The atom bomb is the offspring of the 20th century physics.<br>     原子弹是20世纪物理学的产物。<br>'),(7333,'often','','','','','ad. 经常',' How often do you go there?<br>     你多长时间去一次那里？<br>\n American girls are often very pretty.<br>     美国女孩多很漂亮。<br>'),(7334,'oh','','','','','int. 啊呀,哦',' Oh, what a lie!<br>     啊，真是弥天大谎！<br>\n Oh, how nice!<br>     哦，太好了!<br>'),(7335,'ohm','','','','','n. 欧姆',''),(7336,'oil','oiled','oiled','oiling','oils','n. 油,油画颜料<br>\nv. 涂油,溶化,加油',' The price of oil has gone up.<br>     石油的价格已经上涨了。<br>\n You should oil the sewing machine to stop the squeaking.<br>     你应该给缝纫机上点油，以免发出轧轧声。<br>'),(7337,'OK','','','','','a. 好,不错,可以<br>\nad. 好,不错,可以',' Is that OK?<br>     这样可以吗？<br>\n OK, thanks.<br>     还不错，谢谢。<br>'),(7338,'okay','okayed','okayed','okaying','okays','ad. <表示同意或允许>好的,可以,行',' Have they given you their OK?<br>     他们同意你了吗？<br>\n He made an okay decision.<br>     他做出同意的决定。<br>'),(7339,'old','','','','','a. 旧的,老的<br>\nn. 古时',' Don\'t play old tricks!<br>     别玩老一套的把戏了！<br>\n How old are you?<br>     你多大了？<br>'),(7340,'olive','','','','olives','n. 橄榄,橄榄树,橄榄色<br>\na. 黄绿色的,黄褐色的,橄榄色的',' The olive branch is the emblem of peace.<br>     橄榄枝是和平的象征。<br>\n She was sitting in the shade of a big olive tree.<br>     她正坐在一棵大橄榄树的树荫下。<br>'),(7341,'Olympics','','','','','n. 奥林匹克