r>\n They professed optimism about the outcome.<br>     他们对结果表示乐观.<br>'),(7407,'optimist','','','','','n. 乐观主义者',' The man who is a pessimist before forty-eight knows too much; the man who is an optimist after forty-eight knows too little.<br>     未逾四十八岁的悲观主义者，是知道得太多之人；而年逾四十八岁的乐观主义者，是知道得太少之人。<br>\n An incurable optimist; an incurable smoker.<br>     坚定不移的乐观主义者；不可救药的烟民<br>'),(7408,'optimistic','','','','','a. 乐观的,乐观主义的',' A person regarded as being foolishly or blindly optimistic.<br>     过分乐观者，盲目乐观者被视为愚蠢地或盲目地乐观的人<br>\n We are still optimistic, whatever the result (may be).<br>     我们仍然乐观，不论结果如何。<br>'),(7409,'optimization','','','','','优化<br>\nn. 最佳化',' It also incorporate new optimization specific to particular server and local database format.<br>     它也把新的优化细节合并到特殊服务器与本地数据库格式中。<br>\n An equation or inequality relating the variables in an optimization problem.<br>     在优化问题中，一种表示若干变量相互关系的方程（式）或不等式。<br>'),(7410,'optimize','optimized','optimized','optimizing','','v. 使...完美,乐观,使...完善<br>\nv.优化',''),(7411,'optimum','','','','optima','n. 最适宜<br>\na. 最适宜的',' Most favorable or desirable; optimum.<br>     最理想的最适宜的，最令人满意的，最优的<br>\n The market offer optimum condition for sale.<br>     市场为销售提供了最佳条件。<br>'),(7412,'option','','','','options','n. 选择',' Don\'t take the job now keep your options open until you leave university.<br>     先别接受这份工作－－暂时保留选择权，到离开这所大学再说。<br>\n The former option favours the married man.<br>     前一种选择对已婚男子有利.<br>'),(7413,'optional','','','','','a. 可以任选的,非强制的',' The insurance cover is optional.<br>     保险范围可以随意选择。<br>\n A4-speed automatic transmission is optional.<br>     四段自动变速器是可自由选择的。<br>'),(7414,'optionally','','','','','ad. 可选择地',''),(7415,'or','','','','','conj. 或者,还是<br>\nprep.&ad. 或者',' I don\'t care whether I get it or not.<br>     我不在乎我是否可以得到它。<br>\n Hurry up or else you\'ll be late.<br>     快，否则你就要来不及了。<br>'),(7416,'oral','','','','orals','a. 口头的<br>\nn. 口试',' He will take an oral examination.<br>     他将接受口试。<br>\n The old man told us a story pass