成一个矩形的竖行和横行进行排列的一张表格<br>'),(7425,'ordinal','','','','ordinals','n. 序数<br>\na. 顺序的<br>\n[计算机] 序号',' The ordinal number matching the number15 in a series.<br>     第十五在一系列中排在第十五的序数<br>\n The ordinal number matching the number14 in a series.<br>     第十四一序数词，一系列数中的第十四个<br>'),(7426,'ordinarily','','','','','ad. 通常,普通,大概',' Ordinarily, I find this job easy, but today I\'m having problems.<br>     平时我认为这工作很容易，岂知今日却有了问题。<br>\n Ordinarily home by six.<br>     通常一个家里有六口人<br>'),(7427,'ordinary','','','','ordinaries','a. 普通的',' Our ordinary workday is eight hours.<br>     我们正常的工作日是8小时。<br>\n She is likeable enough, but very ordinary.<br>     她还算可爱，但是并不标致。<br>'),(7428,'ore','','','','ores','n. 矿,矿石',' This is an area rich in ore.<br>     这里是个矿产丰富的地区。<br>\n After chemical assay, we have known the composition of the ore.<br>     经过化学分析，我们知道了矿石的构成。<br>'),(7429,'organ','','','','organs','n. 风琴,机构,器官',' The heart is a vital organ.<br>     心脏是维持生命必须的器官。<br>\n Parliament is an organ of government.<br>     议会是政府的一个机构。<br>'),(7430,'organic','','','','','a. 器官的,有机的,根本的,接近自然的',' I am not good at organic chemistry.<br>     我的有机化学学得不好。<br>\n The music is organic to the story.<br>     这首乐曲是这个故事必不可少的组成部分。<br>'),(7431,'organism','','','','organisms','n. 生物体,有机体',' Germs may invade the organism.<br>     细菌会侵入有机体。<br>\n The army is an extremely complex organism.<br>     军队是极其复杂的组织。<br>'),(7432,'organization','','','','organizations','n. 机构,组织',' The organization of such a large-scale party takes a lot of time and energy.<br>     组织这样大规模的聚会要花费许多时间和精力。<br>\n They have established a student organization.<br>     他们建立了一个学生组织。<br>'),(7433,'organizational','','','','','a. 组织的',''),(7434,'organize','organized','organized','organizing','','vi. 组织起来<br>\nvt. 组织',' The meeting was badly organized.<br>     会议组织得很糟。<br>\n \"Don\'t mourn for me. Organize! \" These were his last words.<br>     \"不要为我悲痛，组织起来！\"这就是他最后的遗言。<br>'),(7435,'orient','','','','','a. [诗]东方的<br>\nn. 东方,亚洲',' In the market, I breathed the smells of the Orient.<br>     在集市上，我闻到了东方的气息。<br>\n Ian is a dab hand at the orient art.<br>     伊恩是东方艺术的行家。<br>'),(7436,'oriental','','','','orientals','a. 东方人的',' This oriental legend is fascinating.<br>     这个东方传说很吸引人。<br>\n China is an oriental country with a long history.<br>     中国是一个有着悠久历史的东方国家。<br>'),(7437,'orientate','orientated','orientated','orientating','','vt. 定向(确定地址,使...向东,查明真相)',' The mountaineers found it difficult to orientate themselves in the fog.<br>     登山的人在浓雾中难以确定自己的方位.<br>\n Try to orientate your students towards the science subjects.<br>     把学生的兴趣尽力引导到理科方面.<br>'),(7438,'orientation','','','','orientations','n. 定位,适应,情况介绍<br>\n[计算机] 定向',' The unconscious perception of movement and spatial orientation arising from stimuli within the body itself.<br>     本体感受由身体本身的内部刺激引起的对于运动和空间定向的不自觉的感受<br>\n The orientation of a spacecraft relative to its direction of motion.<br>     飞行姿态宇宙飞船相对于其飞行方向所处的位置<br>'),(7439,'oriented','','','','','导向的,定向的',' In this way, the object is given both data properties and behaviors, and so object oriented programs can better reflect the real world they are trying to simulate.<br>     通过这种方式，对象被赋予数据特征和行为，因此，使用面向对象程序能够更好地反映程序欲模拟的现实世界。<br>\n In the market, I breathed the smells of the Orient.<br>     在集市上，我闻到了东方的气息。<br>'),(7440,'origin','','','','origins','n. 起源,出身,开端',' He is a Dane by origin.<br>     他原籍丹麦。<br>\n The illness is organic in origin.<br>     该病起初是器质性疾患.<br>'),(7441,'original','','','','originals','a. 最初的,原始的,有独创性的,原版的<br>\nn. 起源,原件,原稿',' The original owner of the house moved out.<br>     房子原先的主人搬出去了。<br>\n The original picture is in the British Museum.<br>     这幅画的原作在大英博物馆内。<br>'),(7442,'originality','','','','','n. 创意,新奇,原始',' The work lacks originality.<br>     那作品缺乏创造性。<br>\n Her designs have great originality.<br>     她的设计十分新颖。<br>'),(7443,'originally','','','','','ad. 本来,原来,最初<br>\n重要的',' The idea originally emanated from his brother.<br>     这个主意最初是他哥哥出的.<br>\n He originally need not buy such big house.<br>     他本来不必买这样一所大房子。<br>'),(7444,'originate','originated','originated','originating','','v. 开始,发明,发起<br>\n[计算机] 起始',' The quarrel originated in rivalry between the two families.<br>     这次争吵是两家不和引起的。<br>\n Who originated the concept of stereo sound?<br>     立体声是谁发明的？<br>'),(7445,'ornament','ornamented','ornamented','ornamenting','ornaments','n. 装饰(物)<br>\nv. 装饰',' We bought some ornaments for the Christmas tree.<br>     我们买了一些装饰品来点缀圣诞树。<br>\n I ornamented my room with flowers.<br>     我用鲜花装饰房间。<br>'),(7446,'ornamental','','','','ornamentals','a. 装饰的<br>\nn. 装饰品',' I\'ve just dropped one of your china ornamental.<br>     我刚才把你的一个瓷器装饰品弄掉了。<br>\n Ornamental copper pans hung on the wall.<br>     墙上挂着装饰性的铜盘。<br>'),(7447,'orphan','orphaned','orphaned','orphaning','orphans','n. 孤儿<br>\na. 无双亲的,孤儿的<br>\nv. 成孤儿',' She was orphaned at the age of ten.<br>     她在十岁时成为孤儿。<br>\n My cousin is an orphan; her parents died when she was young.<br>     我的表姐是孤儿，她的父母在她小时候就去世了。<br>'),(7448,'orthodox','','','','','a. 正(传)统的',' Orthodox Christian churches often have elaborate steeples.<br>     传统的基督教堂都有精致的尖塔。<br>\n Roman Catholics were the next largest group with46, 000, 000 members, There were5, 600, 000 Jews and700, 000 Eastern Orthodox Christians.<br>     罗马天主教是第二个最大的团体，有四千六百万教徒。犹太教徒有五百六十万，东正教徒有七十万。<br>'),(7449,'orthopedics','','','','','n. 矫形术',''),(7450,'OS','','','','','操作系统',''),(7451,'oscillate','oscillated','oscillated','oscillating','','v. 振动,彷徨,犹豫<br>\nv. 使振动,使动摇',' He oscillates between political extremes.<br>     他的政治观点在两个极端之间摇摆不定.<br>\n Manic depressives oscillate between depression and elation.<br>     躁狂抑郁症患者抑郁与躁狂交替发作.<br>'),(7452,'oscillation','','','','oscillations','n. 振动,动摇,变动彷徨',' Her oscillations in mood are maddening.<br>     她喜怒无常能把人气疯。<br>'),(7453,'oscilloscope','','','','','示波器',''),(7454,'osmosis','','','','','n. 渗透作用,渗透性',' Shrinkage or contraction of the protoplasm away from the wall of a living plant or bacterial cell, caused by loss of water through osmosis.<br>     胞质皱缩通过渗透作用由于缺水引起的活植细胞或细菌的细胞质的皱缩或收缩，并与细胞壁分离<br>\n Learned French by osmosis while residing in Paris for15 years.<br>     居住在巴黎的十五年中已经潜移默化地学习了法语<br>'),(7455,'ostensible','','','','','a. 表面的,假装的',' Seeming or professed; ostensible.<br>     假装的表面上的或自称的；貌似真实的<br>\n An ostensible or professed purpose; an excuse.<br>     借口，托词表面的目的；理由<br>'),(7456,'ostentation','','','','','n. 虚饰,虚有其表,卖弄',' Exhibiting no pretensions, boastfulness, or ostentation; modest.<br>     不装腔作势的不装腔作势的，不夸耀的；不铺张招摇的；谦逊<br>'),(7457,'other','','','','others','a. 别的,其他的<br>\npron. 另一个人(或事)',' She is more clever than the other girls in her class.<br>     她比班上其他任何女孩子都聪明。<br>\n The other students in my class are from Italy.<br>     我班其余同学都是意大利人。<br>'),(7458,'otherwise','','','','','ad. 否则,要不然,不同地,别的方式',' Some are wise, some are otherwise.<br>     有些人聪明，有些人则不然。<br>\n She is not very clever, but otherwise she\'s a nice girl.<br>     她并不聪明，但在其他方面，她倒是个好姑娘。<br>'),(7459,'ought','','','','','conj. 应该,大概',' You ought to be more careful, you know.<br>     你应该小心一点，知道吗？<br>\n He ought to/should be here in time he started early enough.<br>     他该[应]按时到这里--他出发得够早的.<br>'),(7460,'ounce','','','','ounces','n. 盎司',' He tried to open the door by using every ounce of his strength.<br>     他用尽全部力气想把门打开。<br>\n How many calories can an ounce of sugar supply?<br>     一盎司糖可以供给多少卡热量？<br>'),(7461,'our','','','','','pron. 我们的',' That\'s not our business.<br>     那事与我们不相干。<br>\n This could change our life.<br>     这可能会改变我们的生活。<br>'),(7462,'ours','','','','','pron. 我们的',' Your house is much bigger than ours.<br>     你们的房子比我们的大多了。<br>\n Their opinion jarred with ours.<br>     他们的意见与我们不一致。<br>'),(7463,'ourselves','','','','','pron. 我们自己',' We finished the job all by ourselves.<br>     我们全靠自己完成了这项工作。<br>\n We built ourselves a new surgery.<br>     我们给自己建了一间新的外科手术室。<br>'),(7464,'oust','ousted','ousted','ousting','','v. 逐出,夺取',' The umpire ousted the arguing player from the game.<br>     裁判员将那位不服判决的运动员罚下场。<br>\n Fox was ousted from office but he had nothing to say for himself.<br>     福克斯被赶下台，但是他没有什么可特别为自己辨护的。<br>'),(7465,'out','','','','outs','a. 外面的,下台的, 出局的<br>\nad. 在外,熄减,出现<br>\nprep. 出外,离去,向',' He took out a book from the case.<br>     他从箱子里拿出一本书。<br>\n The fire has gone out.<br>     火已熄灭。<br>'),(7466,'outage','','','','','停机,断电',''),(7467,'outbreak','','','','outbreaks','n. 爆发',' There has been an outbreak of typhoid.<br>     那儿正爆发伤寒。<br>\n The outbreak of riot caused many people to die.<br>     暴乱的发生使很多人丧生。<br>'),(7468,'outcast','','','','outcasts','a. 被逐出的,被遗弃的,无家可归的<br>\nn. 被驱逐的人,流浪人,无赖',' He was treated as an outcast.<br>     他遭到被人赶出似的对待。<br>\n The outcast boy was brought up by the government.<br>     这个被遗弃的孩子是由政府抚养大的。<br>'),(7469,'outcome','','','','','n. 结果',' What was the outcome of your meeting?<br>     你们会晤的结果如何?<br>\n The necessary outcome of a war is a fall in production.<br>     战争带来的必然结果就是生产力下降。<br>'),(7470,'outcry','','','','outcries','n. 尖叫,倒彩,强烈抗议',' There was a great outcry about the construction of the new airport.<br>     公众强烈反对修建该机场。<br>\n The government hushed the affair up to avoid a public outcry.<br>     当局对此事秘而不宣, 以免引起公众抗议.<br>'),(7471,'outdated','','','','','a. 旧式的,落伍的,过时的<br>\nv. 使时<br>\nvbl. 过时',' \"What Manchester thinks today the world will think tomorrow, \" is not an outdated belief. The old parochial outlook has become a world view.<br>     \"小范围的思想、言论很快就会变成大范围的思想、言论\"并非过时的信条。昔日的那个地方范围的观点已成了一种世界范围的观点。<br>\n The quality is all right, but the style is a bit outdated.<br>     质量无问题，只是式样有点过时。<br>'),(7472,'outdo','outdid','outdone','outdoing','','vt. 超过,胜过',' She outdid all her classmates.<br>     她超过她的所有同班同学。<br>\n He has outdone all his rivals in skill.<br>     他在技巧方面胜过所有的对手。<br>'),(7473,'outdoor','','','','','a. 户外的,屋外的',' Children like outdoor activities.<br>     孩子们喜欢户外活动。<br>\n I\'m very keen on outdoor sports.<br>     我非常喜欢室外运动。<br>'),(7474,'outdoors','','','','','a. 户外的,野外的<br>\nad. 在户外,在野外<br>\nn. (在)露天,户外',' Children of all ages should be outdoors several hours a day.<br>     各个年龄段的孩子每天都应户外活动几个小时。<br>\n She\'s outdoors gardening every afternoon.<br>     她每天下午都在户外搞园艺.<br>'),(7475,'outer','','','','','a. 外部的,外面的',' These creatures were believed to have come from outer space.<br>     据信这种生物来自外太空。<br>\n The outer walls of the building were painted blue.<br>     这座建筑的外墙被漆成了蓝色。<br>'),(7476,'outermost','','','','','a. 最外方的(最远的,最高头的)',''),(7477,'outfit','outfitted','outfitted','outfitting','outfits','n. 用具,配备,机构<br>\nv. 配备,供应',' The company will provide the sports outfits for all the players.<br>     这家公司将为所有运动员提供全套运动服装。<br>\n Such an outfit would be a useful addition to my wardrobe.<br>     在我的服装中添置这一套会有用的.<br>'),(7478,'outgoing','','','','','n. 外出,开支,流出<br>\na. 喜欢外出的<br>\n[计算机] 输出',' She\'s very outgoing.<br>     她非常爱好交际。<br>\n She\'s outgoing and a good mixer.<br>     她是一个杰出的爱交际的人<br>'),(7479,'outing','','','','outings','n. 郊游,远足<br>\na. 远足适用的',' Let\'s go for an outing.<br>     我们郊游去。<br>\n We had an outing to the seaside last summer.<br>     我们去年夏天去海边旅行。<br>'),(7480,'outland','','','','','n. 偏僻地区',''),(7481,'outlandish','','','','','a. 外国味的(奇异的)',' How Harry came into the possession of this outlandish stuff makes an interesting story which he is fond of relating.<br>     哈里如何得到这种稀奇古怪的东西，是一个他津津乐道的有趣的故事。<br>'),(7482,'outlaw','outlawed','outlawed','outlawing','outlaws','n. 被剥夺法律保护的人,罪犯<br>\nv. 使...失去法律保护,将...逐出社会,宣告非法',' Bands of outlaws lived in the desolate mountains after breaking the laws.<br>     成群的歹徒犯法后栖身于荒山中。<br>\n Bad man, the accidental, noble outlaw.<br>     有坏人啦，出人意料的逃。<br>'),(7483,'outlay','','','','','n. 费用,经费,支出<br>\nv. 花费',' The act or process of expending; outlay.<br>     支出支付的行为或过程；花费<br>\n Economy is one powerful motive for camping, since after the initial outlay upon equipment.<br>     想省钱是露营的一个主要动机。因为在开初支付了装备的费用后。<br>'),(7484,'outlet','','','','outlets','n. 出口,出路,通风口,批发商店',' They found some new outlets for their products.<br>     他们为自己的产品找到了一些新的市场。<br>\n Children need an outlet for their energy.<br>     儿童的精力需要发泄出来.<br>'),(7485,'outline','outlined','outlined','outlining','outlines','n. 大纲,轮廓,概要<br>\nv. 描画轮廓,描述要点',' He saw the outline of a building against the sky.<br>     他看到天边一幢建筑物的轮廓。<br>\n The flower was clearly outlined in the light of the lamp.<br>     花朵在阳光下清晰地显现出轮廓。<br>'),(7486,'outlines','','','','','n. 概述程序',' The first lecture introduces new students to the broad outlines of the subject.<br>     第一堂课是让新同学概括地了解这一科目.<br>\n Angular forms, outlines, or corners.<br>     角形角形，角的轮廓或棱角<br>'),(7487,'outlook','outlooked','outlooked','outlooking','outlooks','n. 观点,见解,展望,前景',' An American university president once commented that Einstein has created a new outlook, a new view of the universe.<br>     一位美国大学校长曾经评论说爱因斯坦创立了一种新的观点，即一种新的宇宙观。<br>\n Circumscribed and detached in outlook and experience; narrow or provincial.<br>     思想狭隘的眼界和经验受限制和孤立的；狭窄得或见解偏狭得<br>'),(7488,'outlying','','','','','a. 远离中心的,偏僻的',' They live on the outskirts (ie in an outlying district) of Paris.<br>     他们住在巴黎市郊.<br>'),(7489,'outmode','outmoded','outmoded','outmoding','','v. 使不流行',''),(7490,'outmoded','','','','','a. 过时的',''),(7491,'outnumber','outnumbered','outnumbered','outnumbering','','vt. 数量上超过',' We were completely outnumbered by the enemy.<br>     在数量上我们完全被敌人压倒。<br>\n Men outnumber women here in the ratio of three to one.<br>     此地男子数量以三比一超过女子。<br>'),(7492,'outperform','outperformed','outperformed','outperforming','','n. 成绩优于<br>\nv. 超额完成,过度执行',''),(7493,'output','outputted','outputted','outputting','outputs','n. 产量,输出,输出功率<br>\nvt. 输出(信息等)',' The average output of the factory is 20 cars a day.<br>     该工厂的平均产量是每天20辆汽车。<br>\n We must increase our output to meet demand.<br>     我们必须提高产量满足需求。<br>'),(7494,'outrage','outraged','outraged','outraging','outrages','n. 暴行,侮辱,愤怒<br>\nv. 凌辱,虐待,触犯',' We should never forget the outrage committed by the Japanese invaders.<br>     我们永远都不应该忘记日本侵略者犯下的暴行。<br>\n The Government has been dilatory in condemning the outrage.<br>     政府迟迟才谴责是次暴行.<br>'),(7495,'outrageous','','','','','a. 暴虐的,极无礼的,可恶的<br>\n 惊人的,肆无忌惮的,毫无节制的',' His treatment of his wife is outrageous.<br>     他对待妻子十分蛮横。<br>\n The price is outrageous.<br>     价钱高得吓人。<br>'),(7496,'outright','','','','','a. 率直的,完全的,总共的<br>\nad. 率直地,立刻地,一直向前',' I bought a house outright.<br>     我以一次付款方式买了一栋房子。<br>\n She was the outright winner.<br>     毫无疑问她是优胜者。<br>'),(7497,'outset','','','','','n. 开始,开端',' The start or initial stage; the outset.<br>     开始，开端开始或初始阶段<br>\n The teacher laid emphasis on the precision of the translation from the outset.<br>     老师从一开始就强调翻译准确性。<br>'),(7498,'outside','','','','','ad. 在外面<br>\nn.&a. 外部<br>\nprep. 在...外<br>\npron. 在...外边',' He has a rough outside, but a good heart.<br>     他外表粗鲁，心地善良。<br>\n The house was painted green outside.<br>     这房子外部漆成绿色。<br>'),(7499,'outsider','','','','outsiders','n. 外行(旁观者,没有关系的人)',' Although she\'s lived there for ten years, the villagers still treat her as an outsider.<br>     她虽然在那儿住了十年, 村里人仍视她如外人.<br>\n That horse is a complete outsider; I wouldn\'t waste your money on it.<br>     那匹马绝无获胜可能, 我要是你可不把钱压在它身上.<br>'),(7500,'outskirts','','','','','n. 郊区',' Presently she recognized that she was already in the outskirts of the city.<br>     不久她看出，她已经到达这座城市的郊区。<br>\n Fires swept through the outskirts, where the houses, being mostly of wood, were razed to the ground.<br>     大火席卷郊区，那里的房屋多数都是木造的，被烧成了一片废墟。<br>'),(7501,'outspoken','','','','','a. 直言无讳的,坦率的,坦白无隐的',' Hans got in bad with some of his friends because of his outspoken opposition to the war.<br>     汉斯因为坦率地反对这场战争，使得他的一些朋友不再喜欢他了。<br>'),(7502,'outstanding','','','','outstandings','a. 突出的,显著的',' Superior to or notable above all others; outstanding.<br>     突出的高于所有其他的或比所有人都显著的；杰出的<br>\n The firm recognized Tom\'s outstanding work by giving him an extra bonus.<br>     公司发给汤姆一笔额外奖金以表彰他工作出色.<br>'),(7503,'outstrip','outstripped','outstripped','outstripping','','v. 超过,跑过<br>\nvt. 胜过,超过',' Demand is outstripping current production.<br>     现在需求逐渐超过了生产能力.<br>\n We soon outstripped the slower runners.<br>     我们很快就超过那些跑得慢的人.<br>'),(7504,'outturn','','','','','n. 卸货情况',' On no account should we cut down the outturn.<br>     我们绝不可以把产量降低。<br>\n No doubt you\'ve received the outturn samples of the inferior quality goods.<br>     你们一定收到了质量低劣产品的到货抽样。<br>'),(7505,'outward','','','','outwards','a. 向外的,表面的,外服的<br>\nad. 向外,在外,表面',' The two things are the same in outward form but different in essence.<br>     那两样东西在外表上相同，但在本质上不同。<br>\n He was to all outward appearances dead.<br>     他显然已经死了.<br>'),(7506,'outwards','','','','','ad. 向外地',' The door opened outwards.<br>     这门是朝外开的。<br>\n Does the window open inwards or outwards?<br>     这窗户是朝里开的还是朝外开的?<br>'),(7507,'outweigh','outweighed','outweighed','outweighing','','v. 比...为重,比...重要,比...有价值',' The advantages far outweigh the disadvantages in this case.<br>     这件事上，利远大于弊。<br>\n This outweighs all other considerations.<br>     这一点是首要考虑的。<br>'),(7508,'oval','','','','ovals','n. 椭圆形<br>\na. 卵形的,椭圆形的',' The playing field is a large oval.<br>     球场很大，呈椭圆形。<br>\n The mirror is oval.<br>     镜子是椭圆的。<br>'),(7509,'ovation','','','','ovations','n. 热烈欢迎,大喝采,大受欢迎',' The singer got a ten-minute standing ovation.<br>     观众起立向那位歌手鼓掌达十分钟.<br>\n After a while Lenin came out on the stage. The ovation was unlike anything I have ever seen. Lenin let it continue for a few minutes, standing absolutely still, then with a single motion of his arms across his body stopped the uproar instantaneously and you could have heard a pin drop.<br>     不久列宁在台上出现了，那种热烈的欢呼是我从未见过的。列宁先静静地站了几分钟，让欢呼声继续着，然后用手在胸前横挥一下，喝彩声马上终止，于是连一根针落地的声音你都可以听得到。<br>'),(7510,'oven','','','','ovens','n. 烤炉,烤箱',' It is like an oven in here; please open the window.<br>     这里热得象火炉，请把窗户打开。<br>\n The bread is baking in the oven.<br>     烤箱里正在烤面包。<br>'),(7511,'over','','','','','a. 结束的<br>\nad. 结束<br>\nprep. 在...的上方<br>\nv. 越过',' The meeting is over.<br>     会议结束了。<br>\n You\'d better think it over carefully.<br>     你最好仔细考虑一下。<br>'),(7512,'overall','','','','overalls','a. 全部的,全体的,一切在内的<br>\nad. 总的来说,全部地',' There\'s been an overall improvement recently.<br>     近来各方面都有所改进。<br>\n The overall measurement of this room is 80 square meters.<br>     这个屋子的面积是80平方米。<br>'),(7513,'overcast','overcast','overcast','overcasting','','a. 阴天的,阴暗的,愁闷的',' It\'s a bit overcast; it might rain.<br>     天有点阴，可能下雨。<br>\n There is a gloomy, overcast expression on his face.<br>     他愁眉苦脸。<br>'),(7514,'overcharge','overcharged','overcharged','overcharging','','v. 讨价过高,装药过多,过度充电<br>\nn. 超载,装药过多,过度充电',' We were overcharged for the eggs.<br>     我们的鸡蛋买贵了.<br>\n That grocer never overcharges.<br>     那杂货商从不多要价.<br>'),(7515,'overcoat','','','','overcoats','n. 外套,大衣',' I took off my overcoat since it was warm.<br>     天气很暖和，我就把大衣脱了。<br>\n She didn\'t put on an overcoat though it was very cold outside.<br>     外头虽冷，她却没披件外套。<br>'),(7516,'overcome','overcame','overcome','overcoming','','a. 充满了的,占据了的<br>\nv. 战胜,克服',' Can you overcome your shortcomings?<br>     你可以克服你的缺点吗？<br>\n We need a spirit of enterprise if we are to overcome our difficulties.<br>     如果我们要克服困难，我们就要有进取精神。<br>'),(7517,'overdo','overdid','overdone','overdoing','','v. 做得过分,过度,夸张',' He\'s been overdoing things recently.<br>     近来他做事过分努力.<br>\n You must stop overdoing it you\'ll make yourself ill.<br>     不要过劳了--你要生病的.<br>'),(7518,'overdraft','','','','','v.&n. 透支',' He has a huge overdraft to pay off.<br>     他有一大笔透支要偿还.<br>\n The bank manager said that, in order to bring me down to earth and control my spending, I would have no overdraft facility and my cheque card would be withdrawn.<br>     银行经理说，为了使我从幻想中清醒过来并控制我的开支，将不给我有透支的便利，并还将收回我的支票卡。<br>'),(7519,'overdraw','overdrew','overdrawn','overdrawing','','v. 拉过度,夸大,夸张<br>\nv. 透支',' Overdraw a bow.<br>     把弓拉得过紧<br>'),(7520,'overdue','','','','','a. 过期的,未兑的,迟到的',' Please let us have your check for the$60 now past overdue.<br>     迟付的60美元，请速予寄下为荷。<br>\n Legislative reform is long overdue.<br>     立法方面的改革早该进行。<br>'),(7521,'overestimate','overestimated','overestimated','overestimating','','v. 评价过高,出价过高<br>\nn. 估计过高,评价过高,出价过高',' I overestimated his abilities he\'s finding the job very difficult.<br>     我过高估计了他的能力--现在他觉得工作非常困难.<br>\n I overestimated the amount of milk we\'d need for the weekend.<br>     我过高估计了我们周末的用奶量.<br>'),(7522,'overextend','overextended','overextended','overextending','','v. 使...承担过多的义务',' Any users of credit may overextend themselves.<br>     每个贷款使用者都有可能作出不自量力的事。<br>'),(7523,'overflow','','','','','n. 溢值,超值,泛滥<br>\nv. 泛滥,溢出,充溢<br>\n[计算机] 溢出',' Overflow patients lay on the floors and in the corridors.<br>     容纳不下的病人躺在地上和走廊里。<br>\n The crowd overflowed the auditorium.<br>     人群挤得礼堂无法容纳。<br>'),(7524,'overhaul','','','','','v. 分解检查,翻修,精细检查； 超车、赶上<br>\n<br>\nn. 分解检查,精细检查',' The engine is due for an overhaul.<br>     那台发动机该大修了.<br>\n The fast cruiser soon overhauled the old cargo boat.<br>     快速巡逻艇迅即赶上那艘旧货船.<br>'),(7525,'overhead','','','','overheads','n. 经常开支,普通用费<br>\na. 在头上的,高架的<br>\nad. 在头顶上,在空中,在高处<br>\n[计算机] 总开销',' Their office is in central Beijing, so their overhead is very high.<br>     他们的办事处设在北京市中心，所以他们的日常开支很大。<br>\n Seagulls were circling overhead.<br>     海鸥在头顶山盘旋。<br>'),(7526,'overhear','overheard','overheard','overhearing','','v. 无意中听到,偷听',' I overheard some cruel remarks about him.<br>     我无意中听到了一些议论他的粗鲁的话。<br>\n I overheard them saying they were unhappy.<br>     我偶然听到他们说，他们很不快乐。<br>'),(7527,'overheat','overheated','overheated','overheating','','v. 使过热,过热',' Fill your radiator with water, or your engine will overheat.<br>     给你的散热器充水，否则引擎会过热。<br>'),(7528,'overjoy','overjoyed','overjoyed','overjoying','','n. 使大喜',' She was overjoyed to hear about the arrival of the baby.<br>     她听说婴儿出生而欣喜若狂.<br>\n He\'ll be overjoyed at your news.<br>     他一定对你的消息大喜过望.<br>'),(7529,'overlap','','','','','n. 重叠,重复<br>\nv. 重叠,重复<br>\n[计算机] 重叠',' There is no question of overlap between the two courses.<br>     这两门课程之间不存在重叠的问题。<br>\n A stitch made by inserting the needle at the midpoint of a preceding stitch so that the stitches overlap by half lengths.<br>     回针缝在先前缝的一针中间加缝的一针，以便使针脚的交错重叠为原来长度的一半<br>'),(7530,'overlapping','','','','','a. 相互重叠的',' Having the edges overlapping in a regular arrangement, as roof tiles or the scales of a fish.<br>     鳞状叠覆的具有规则安排的叠盖边缘的，如瓦片或鱼鳞<br>\n Overlapping or crossing, as the wings of some insects when at rest.<br>     重叠的，交叉的某些昆虫休息时其翅膀重迭的或交叉的<br>'),(7531,'overlay','overlaid','overlaid','overlaying','','覆盖',' A polar projection of half or more of the celestial sphere on a chart equipped with an adjustable overlay to show the stars visible at a particular time and place.<br>     星座一览图天体球的一半或多半在平面图上的极投影图，这种图具有可调节的遮蔽物以显示在给定时刻和位置可见的恒星<br>\n An open framework made of strips of metal, wood, or similar material overlapped or overlaid in a regular, usually crisscross pattern.<br>     格构开放式格架，由金属片。木片或相类似原料搭叠成格状，通常用交叉方式构成<br>'),(7532,'overload','','','','','v. 超载,过载,超过负荷<br>\nn. 超载,负荷过多<br>\n[计算机] 过载',' The lights fused because the system was overloaded with electrical appliances.<br>     电灯灭了, 因线路上用电器超负荷把保险丝烧断了.<br>\n For analog inputs, any absolute voltage value above which the analog-to- digital converter cannot distinguish a change. The overload value can be different for plus and minus inputs.<br>     就模拟输入而言，使模数转换器不能区别其变化的超范围的绝对电压值。超载值对于正输入和负输入可能不同。<br>'),(7533,'overlook','overlooked','overlooked','overlooking','','v. 俯看,远眺,没注意到',' They overlooked the enormous risks involved.<br>     他们忽略了暗含的巨大危险。<br>\n My room overlooked the garden.<br>     我的房间俯瞰花园。<br>'),(7534,'overnight','','','','','n. 前晚<br>\na. 通宵的,晚上的,前夜的<br>\nad. 在前一夜,整夜,昨晚一晚上',' She became a celebrity overnight.<br>     她一下变成名人了。<br>\n I stayed overnight at a friend\'s house.<br>     我在朋友家过了一夜。<br>'),(7535,'overpass','overpassed','overpassed','overpassing','','n. 天桥,陆桥<br>\nv. 超越,胜过,忽略',' Is that why they\'re constructing so many underpasses, overpasses and highways?<br>     那就是他们建这么多天桥、地下通道和公路的原因吗？<br>'),(7536,'overproduction','','','','','n. 生产过