时间之外(超出时间地)',' He was cruel to make them work overtime.<br>     他要他们加班工作, 真是残酷。<br>\n This new order will mean (us) working overtime.<br>     这一新定单意味著（我们）得加班加点.<br>'),(7547,'overture','','','','overtures','n. 提议,提案,初步交涉,序曲',' The audience must be in their seats before the overture.<br>     观众必须于序曲演奏前入座。<br>'),(7548,'overturn','','','','','n. 倾覆,破减,革命<br>\nv. 推翻,颠倒',' The revolutionist planned to overturn this puppet regime.<br>     革命者计划推翻傀儡政府。<br>\n The boat overturned but didn\'t sank.<br>     小船翻了，但没有沉。<br>'),(7549,'overview','','','','','n. 概观<br>\n[计算机] 概貌',' The general manager gave us an overview of the company\'s marketing plans for the coming year.<br>     总经理扼要介绍了公司明年的销售计划。<br>\n The opening chapter gives a general overview of the subject.<br>     开篇第一章是对主题的概述.<br>'),(7550,'overweight','overweighted','overweighted','overweighting','','a. 超重的',' The baggage is two kilos overweight.<br>     那件行李超重两公斤。<br>\n Be my luggage overweight?<br>     我的行李超重了吗？<br>'),(7551,'overwhelm','overwhelmed','overwhelmed','overwhelming','','v. 淹没,受打击,压倒',' Your kindness quite overwhelmed me.<br>     你的好意使我感激难言。<br>\n The village was overwhelmed when the floods came.<br>     这个村庄在洪水泛滥时被淹没了。<br>'),(7552,'overwhelming','','','','','a. 势不可挡的,压倒的',' Our football team has won an overwhelming victory.<br>     我们的足球队取得了压倒性的胜利。<br>\n The scenic splendors of the Rocky Mountains are overwhelming.<br>     落基山脉的壮丽景色使人赞叹不已。<br>'),(7553,'overwork','','','','','n. 过度操劳,过度工作<br>\nv. 工作过度',' His illness grew out of his tendency to overwork.<br>     他的病是由于工作过度所致。<br>\n Self- make men are very apt to usurp the prerogative of the almighty and overwork themselves.<br>     全凭一己奋斗而成功的人，大有篡夺上帝的大权之势而过度工作。<br>'),(7554,'overwrite','overwrote','overwritten','overwriting','','重写',' Send or receiving a new snapshot overwrite the previous image.<br>     发送或接收一幅新的快照会覆盖前面的图象。<br>'),(7555,'overwrought','','','','','a. 过劳的(工作过累的,紧张过度的)',' She didn\'t mean to offend you; she was overwrought.<br>     她无意得罪你, 她是情绪不好.