','','','','paralyses','n. 瘫痪',' A person affected with paralysis.<br>     瘫痪病者，麻痹患者患麻痹症的人<br>\n The disease results in creeping paralysis.<br>     这种病可发展成脊髓痨.<br>'),(7635,'paralyze','paralyzed','paralyzed','paralyzing','','v. 使...瘫痪,使...麻痹',' The electricity failure paralyzed the water supply.<br>     停电使水供应陷于瘫痪。<br>\n The accident left her paralyzed in both legs.<br>     事故后她的腰部以下瘫痪了。<br>'),(7636,'parameter','','','','','n. 参数,参量',' We have to work within the parameters of time and budget.<br>     我们工作受时间和财力所限.<br>\n Spend by each department have to fall within certain parameter.<br>     每个部门的开支必须属于确定的系数之内。<br>'),(7637,'paramount','','','','paramounts','派拉蒙(美电影公司)<br>\n极为重要的',' The reduction of unemployment should be paramount.<br>     降低失业率应是头等大事。<br>\n This matter is of paramount importance.<br>     此事至关重要。<br>'),(7638,'paranoia','','','','','n. [心]妄想狂, 偏执狂',' Relating to, characteristic of, or affected with paranoia.<br>     类偏执狂的，有偏执狂特征的与偏执症有关的、有其特征的或有此症状的<br>\n Paranoia reigns supreme among the women, causing much marital conflict.<br>     偏执狂现象在妇女中很盛行，引起了许多婚姻纠纷。<br>'),(7639,'paraphernalia','','','','','n. 随身用具(附件)',' All my fishing paraphernalia is in the car.<br>     我的鱼具都在汽车里.<br>\n He has all the music paraphernalia you can buy.<br>     你能买到的音乐相关产品，他全都有。<br>'),(7640,'paraphrase','paraphrased','paraphrased','paraphrasing','paraphrases','n. 释义,解述,改写<br>\nv. 改写,解述',' Paraphrase the following passage into two paragraphs.<br>     把下面这一节文章意译成两段。<br>'),(7641,'parasite','','','','parasites','n. 寄生虫,食客',' The mistletoe plant is a parasite on trees.<br>     槲寄生是寄生在树上的植物。<br>\n Don\'t give money to him; he is a parasite.<br>     别给他钱，他是个好吃懒做的人。<br>'),(7642,'parcel','parceled','parceled','parceling','parcels','n. 包裹<br>\nv. 打包,捆扎<br>\nvt. 打包',' He parceled up the books.<br>     他把书打成了包。<br>\n She sent me the present by parcel post.<br>     她用邮包把礼物寄给了我。<br>'),(7643,'pardon','pardoned','pardoned','pardoning','pardons','n. 原谅,赦免<br>\nv. 宽恕,原谅',' I beg your pardon.<br>     对不起；请原谅。<br>\n If I have offended you, I ask your pardon.<br>     如有冒犯之处，请多多原谅。<br>'),(7644,'parent','','','','parents','n. 父母,父母亲,根源',' My parents have gone to Hangzhou for holiday.<br>     我父母已经去杭州度假了。<br>\n Being a parent can be hard work.<br>     当父母可是件辛苦的事。<br>'),(7645,'parentheses','','','','','圆括号',' In assembler programming, one or more operation represented by a combination of terms and paired parentheses.<br>     汇编程序设计中，用项和括号对的组合所代表的一个或多个操作。<br>\n A string of one or more characters used to separate or organize elements of computer programs or data; for example, parentheses, blank character, arithmetic operator, if,\"BEGIN\".<br>     用来分隔或组织计算机程序元素或数据元素的字符或字符串。例如括号、空格符、算术运算符、if（如果）、“BEGIN＂等。<br>'),(7646,'parenthesis','','','','parentheses','n. 括弧,插入语,附带',' The statistics were given in parenthesis.<br>     统计数字在括号里.<br>\n One have to dismount from an idea and get into saddle again at every parenthesis.<br>     每当遇上一个括号，就叫人不得不从一种想法下马，然后再次骑上马鞍。<br>'),(7647,'Paris','','','','','n. 巴黎',' Paris is the capital of France.<br>     巴黎是法国的首都。<br>\n First prize in the raffle is a holiday for two in Paris.<br>     抽奖销售的头奖是两个人到巴黎度假旅游。<br>'),(7648,'parish','','','','parishes','n. 教区',' Don\'t worry about the printing; that\'s my parish.<br>     别担心打印的事，那是我的工作范围。<br>\n They go to the parish church every week.<br>     他们每周都去教区的教堂。<br>'),(7649,'parity','','','','parities','n. 同等,同格,同位',' The two currencies have now reached parity.<br>     这两种货币现已达到同等价值。<br>\n A bit added to a binary code that indicates parity and is used to check the integrity of data.<br>     奇偶校验位加在二进制码上的一个标明奇偶数的位，用于检验数据的完整性<br>'),(7650,'park','parked','parked','parking','parks','n. 公园,停车处<br>\nv. 停车,置于,停车',' I often take my children to play in the park.<br>     我经常带我的孩子们去公园玩。<br>\n You are not allowed to park here.<br>     此处不准停车。<br>'),(7651,'parking','','','','','n. 停车<br>\na. 停车的<br>\nvbl. 停车',' We encouraged the Smiths before leaving the parking lot.<br>     在离开停车场之前, 我们鼓励了史密斯一家。<br>\n It\'s murder trying to find a parking place for the car.<br>     找个停车的地方比登天还难.<br>'),(7652,'parliament','','','','parliaments','n. 议会,国会',' The Conservative Party won 230 seats in Parliament.<br>     保守党在议会获得了230 个席位。<br>\n The President announced the dissolution of Parliament.<br>     总统宣布了议会解散。<br>'),(7653,'parlor','','','','parlors','n. 客厅,会客室,店',' My sister goes to a beauty parlor once a week.<br>     我妹妹每周去一次美容院。<br>\n Rock music blasted full from the parlor.<br>     摇滚乐声震屋宇，从客厅传来。<br>'),(7654,'parody','parodied','parodied','parodying','parodies','n. 打油诗文,诙谐的改编诗文,拙劣的模仿<br>\nv. 拙劣模仿,作模仿诗文',' The trial was a parody of justice.<br>     这次审判是对公正的一次拙劣的模拟<br>\n An exaggerated or grotesque imitation, such as a parody of a literary work.<br>     模仿一种夸张或怪诞的模仿，如对一个文学作品的滑稽模仿<br>'),(7655,'parrot','parroted','parroted','parroting','parrots','n. 鹦鹉<br>\nv. 学舌',' He talks like a parrot and just repeats what he heard.<br>     他只是鹦鹉学舌，拾人牙慧罢了。<br>\n This parrot is an amazing mimic.<br>     这只鹦鹉很会学舌。<br>'),(7656,'parse','parsed','parsed','parsing','','v.&n. 从语法上分析',''),(7657,'parser','','','','','语法分析器',''),(7658,'part','parted','parted','parting','parts','n. 部份,零件,角色<br>\nv. 分开,分离,分配<br>\nad. 部份地,有几分',' I hope we can part as friends.<br>     我希望我们和和气气地分手。<br>\n This piece of glass seems to be part of a lamp.<br>     这片玻璃似乎是一盏灯的一部分。<br>'),(7659,'partake','partook','partaken','partaking','','v. 分担,参与,有几分',' His manner partakes of insolence.<br>     他的态度带有几分傲慢。<br>\n Will you partake of a drink with us?<br>     和我们一同喝一杯好吗？<br>'),(7660,'partial','','','','','a. 部分的,偏袒的,偏爱的',' His partial attitude called forth a lot of criticism.<br>     他的偏袒态度招致了不少批评。<br>\n I\'m very partial to sweet foods.<br>     我非常偏爱甜食。<br>'),(7661,'partiality','','','','','n. 偏袒,偏心',' A partiality or disposition in favor of something; a preference.<br>     偏爱，偏袒偏爱或喜欢事物的性情；偏爱<br>\n Challenging the array is made either by reason of the partiality of the Sheriff or his under officer who arrayed the panel, or for some other c