as many patrons.<br>     这家商店有许多老顾客。<br>\n Modern artists have difficulty in finding patrons.<br>     现代艺术家们很难找到赞助人。<br>'),(7756,'patronage','','','','','n. 赞助,光顾,任免权',' We thank you for your patronage.<br>     我们谢谢您的惠顾。<br>\n The theatre is under the patronage of the Arts Council.<br>     那家剧院得到了艺术委员会的赞助。<br>'),(7757,'patronize','patronized','patronized','patronizing','','v. 保护,支援',' The restaurant is patronized by politicians and journalists.<br>     这家饭馆常有政治家和记者光顾.<br>\n He resented the way she patronized him.<br>     她待他那种屈尊纡贵的样子, 他十分愤恨.<br>'),(7758,'patter','','','','','n. 急速拍打声,轻快脚步声,行话<br>\nv. 急速地念,滴答地响,发出急速轻拍声',' The falling leaves pattered against the windowpanes.<br>     落叶嗒塔地打在玻璃窗上。<br>\n They will soon be hearing the patter of tiny feet.<br>     他们很快就会有个小宝宝了。<br>'),(7759,'pattern','patterned','patterned','patterning','patterns','n. 图案,式样,典范<br>\nv. 仿造,模仿',' This cloth has a pattern of blue and white squares.<br>     这种布有蓝白格子的图案。<br>\n He patterned himself upon a man he admired.<br>     他模仿一个他钦佩的人。<br>'),(7760,'patty','','','','patties','n. Mathilda,Matilda,Martha 的昵称',' I made some patties for them.<br>     我给他们做了一些小馅饼。<br>\n Patty dawdled away four years in college.<br>     帕蒂在大学里混了四年。<br>'),(7761,'paucity','','','','','n. 少数,少量,缺乏',''),(7762,'Paul','','','','','n. 保罗',' His Holiness Pope John Paul II was welcomed by the crowd.<br>     尊敬的保罗教皇陛下受到人群的欢迎。<br>\n Peter sat next to Paul on the sofa.<br>     彼得挨著保罗坐在沙发上。<br>'),(7763,'Paula','','','','','波拉(女名)',' Paula turned everything in the house upside-down when she was trying to find her missing necklace.<br>     波拉在寻找她丢失的项链时，把屋子里的所有东西翻得乱七八糟。<br>'),(7764,'paunch','','','','','n. 腹,胃,大肚子<br>\nv. 剖腹,取出内脏',''),(7765,'paunchy','','','','','a. 大肚子的',''),(7766,'pauper','','','','paupers','n. 贫民,被救济者,穷人',' An impoverished person; a pauper.<br>     穷人贫困的人；贫民<br>\n He was degraded in their eyes; he had lost caste and station before the very paupers.<br>     他在他们的眼光里是坍台了；他在贫民前面丢了体面和地位。<br>'),(7767,'pause','paused'