于冲击的,叩诊',''),(7944,'perdition','','','','','n. 地狱,灭亡',' He was damned to perdition.<br>     他万劫不复。<br>\n The man trembled whenever he thought of the perdition.<br>     这个人一想起死后的永久惩罚就颤抖不已。<br>'),(7945,'peregrination','','','','','n. 游历,旅行',''),(7946,'peremptory','','','','','a. 专横的,不容反抗的',' He made a peremptory order.<br>     他下达了一个必须服从的命令。<br>\n The teacher spoke in a peremptory tone.<br>     老师以命令的口吻说话<br>'),(7947,'perennial','','','','perennials','a. 四季不断的,继续多年的',' A perennial woody plant having a main trunk and usually a distinct crown.<br>     树一种多年生木质植物，生有一个主干且常有一个很明显的树冠<br>'),(7948,'perennially','','','','','永久地',' Permanently frozen subsoil, occurring throughout the Polar Regions and locally in perennially frigid areas.<br>     永冻土永久冰冻的下层土壤，出现在整个北极地区和部分长期寒冷的地区<br>\n Something that remains perennially fresh, interesting, or well liked.<br>     经久不衰的事物常新的、百看不厌的或永保美名的事物<br>'),(7949,'perestroika','','','','','n. (Rus.) 改革',' Any solution [to Soviet economic malaise], however, is hostage to the crisis of authority, creating a catch-22 stalemate between perestroika and glasnost, between economics and politics: any measure to shore up the economy only fans public anger and reduces the authority of the Government.<br>     不过，任何解决[苏联经济失调]办的法都受到权力危机的影响，在改革与开放，经济与政治之间产生一种自相矛盾僵持不下的情况：任何振兴经济的办法不过煽起民众的忿怒并损及政府威信而已。<br>'),(7950,'perfect','perfected','perfected','perfecting','','a. 完美的,全然的,理想的<br>\nv. 使...完美,使...完善,使...熟练',' The weather during our holiday was perfect.<br>     我们度假时的天气好极了。<br>\n The project is far from perfect.<br>     这项企划很不完美。<br>'),(7951,'perfection','','','','','n. 完美,完善',' She sings to perfection.<br>     她唱得好极了。<br>\n If a thing is not done to perfection, it is unacceptable.<br>     做得不完美的事是无法接受的。<br>'),(7952,'perfectionist','','','','','n. 十全十美主义者, [哲]至善论者',' The innkeeper is a notoriously hard driving, whip-cracking perfectionist.<br>     这个酒馆的老板出名地凶狠，不准手下人犯一点错误。<br>'),(7953,'perfectly','','','','','ad. 完全地,无瑕疵地,完整地',' You needn\'t labor a point that is perfectly plain.<br>     这点很明显，你用不着讲个没完。<br>\n Don\'t shout into my ears like that, I can hear you perfectly well.<br>     别那样对我大声嚷嚷，我能听清楚。<br>'),(7954,'perfervid','','','','','a. 非常热心的',''),(7955,'perfidious','','','','','a. 不忠的,背信弃义的',''),(7956,'perfidy','','','','perfidies','n. 不诚实,背信',''),(7957,'perforate','','','','','v. 穿孔于,刺穿',''),(7958,'perforation','','','','','n. 穿孔,贯穿,贯通',''),(7959,'perforce','','','','','a. 必然地,必需地',''),(7960,'perform','performed','performed','performing','','v. 执行,表演,做',' The surgeon has performed the operation.<br>     外科医生做了手术。<br>\n Their football team performed very well in the match yesterday.<br>     他们的足球队在昨天的比赛中表现突出。<br>'),(7961,'performability','','','','','可执行性',''),(7962,'performance','','','','performances','n. 表演,表现<br>\nn. 性能',' The car\'s performance on corners needs to be improved.<br>     这辆车在转弯时的性能还需要改进。<br>\n The novel is considered a brilliant performance.<br>     这部小说被认为是出色的佳作。<br>'),(7963,'performer','','','','performers','n. 表演者,执行者',' Let\'s have a good round of applause for the next performer.<br>     咱们为下一个表演者热烈鼓掌吧。<br>\n The performer received only pitying looks from his audience.<br>     从观众的表情看, 那表演者得到的只是同情和怜悯.<br>'),(7964,'perfume','','','','','n. 香水,香气<br>\nv. 洒香水于,薰香',' The roses perfumed the air.<br>     玫瑰花的芳香四溢。<br>\n Can you smell the perfume of the roses?<br>     你能闻到玫瑰花的香味吗？<br>'),(7965,'perfunctorily','','','','','ad. 敷衍地,潦草地,表面地',''),(7966,'perfunctory','','','','','a. 草率的,敷衍的',' The operator answered the phone with a perfunctory greeting.<br>     接线员接通电话，象征性的打了招呼<br>\n The policy of making only a perfunctory effort or symbolic gesture toward the accomplishment of a goal, such as racial integration.<br>     表面文章一种只对一个要完成的目标、如种族融合而作一些随意的努力或象征性的姿态的策略<br>'),(7967,'pergola','','','','pergolas','n. 棚架,凉棚',''),(7968,'perhaps','','','','perhapses','ad. 也许,可能',' Perhaps I am wrong, but I think she is near forty.<br>     也许我错了，但是我想她快四十岁了。<br>\n Such a mistake would perhaps lead to disastrous consequences.<br>     这样一种错误可能导致灾难性的后果。<br>'),(7969,'pericardium','','','','pericardia','n. 围心, [解]心包膜',''),(7970,'perigee','','','','','n. 近地点',''),(7971,'peril','periled','periled','periling','perils','n. 危险,冒险<br>\nv. 置...于险境,冒险',' The ship was in imminent peril of being wrecked.<br>     那条船马上就有失事的危险。<br>\n You had better not invest so much money at your peril.<br>     你最好不要冒险投资这么多。<br>'),(7972,'perilous','','','','','a. 危险的',' Their perilous journey across the ocean has attracted public attention.<br>     他们的越洋冒险旅行引起了公众的注意。<br>\n It is true during their explorations they often faced difficulties and dangers of the most perilous nature.<br>     确实在探险中，他们经常面临着各种最有危险性的艰难和险阻。<br>'),(7973,'perimeter','','','','','n. 周长,周界',' The plane stalled, flipped over onto its back and crashed near the perimeter.<br>     飞机失速了，翻了一个跟头，坠毁在机场环形围栏附近。<br>\n The barbed wire fence round the perimeter discouraged intruders.<br>     周围有铁丝网阻止了外人闯入.<br>'),(7974,'period','','','','periods','n. 学时,课时,一段时间,时期,周期,句点',' We have three periods of chemistry a week.<br>     我们一星期三节化学课。<br>\n Which period of history are you studying?<br>     你正在学哪一段历史？<br>'),(7975,'periodic','','','','','a. 周期的,定期的',' The doctor made periodic visit to the house to see if the baby was all right.<br>     医生定期到这家进行拜访，检查婴儿有没有问题。<br>\n The quality or state of being periodic; recurrence at regular intervals.<br>     周期性周期出现的性质或状态；以固定的间隔而发生<br>'),(7976,'periodic table','','','','','周期表',' A column in the periodic table of the elements.<br>     属，族元素周期表上的一栏<br>\n The periodic table now contains all the elements known to man arranged in their proper sequence.<br>     现在周期表包括人类已知的全部元素，这些元素按适当的顺序排列起来。<br>'),(7977,'periodical','','','','periodicals','n. 期刊<br>\na. 周期的,定期的',' The periodical is obtainable on the very first day of every month.<br>     这本杂志每月一号出版。<br>\n I should be glad if you could insert this article into your periodical.<br>     如果能把这篇文章登在你的期刊上我将很高兴。<br>'),(7978,'periodically','','','','','ad. 周期性地,定期地',' New strains of viruses appear periodically.<br>     新菌系的细菌周期性地产生<br>\n A device that periodically and automatically opens and closes an electric circuit, producing pulses.<br>     断续器一种阶段性的能自动打开及关闭电路并产生脉冲的仪器<br>'),(7979,'periodicity','','','','','n. 定期性,周期性,周期数',''),(7980,'peripatetic','','','','','a. 巡游的',' Peripatetic music teachers visit the school regularly.<br>     兼职音乐教师定期到校授课.<br>'),(7981,'peripheral','','','','','a. 不重要的,外围的',' An interface unit or circuitry that converts data to and from the representation used by a particular peripheral device or class of peripheral devices; for example, a device that converts between bit serial and bit parallel and resolves differences in transmission speeds.<br>     一种接口部件或电路，用来把数据转换成某种特殊的外围设备上的表示或某类外围设备上的表示或把此种表示转换成数据。例如，一台在串行位和并行位之间作转换且解决传输速度差别的设备。<br>\n The central processing unit of a computer exclusive of peripheral and remote devices.<br>     主机计算机除了外部和分离的装置以外的中心运作部件<br>'),(7982,'periphery','','','','peripheries','n. 周边(边缘,圆周,圆柱体表面)',' The idea is also expressed by minor poet on the periphery of the movement.<br>     该运动外围一些不大出名的诗人也表达了这些观点。<br>\n Carrying inward to a central organ or section, as nerves that conduct impulses from the periphery of the body to the brain or spinal cord.<br>     传入的传入到中央器官或部分的，如从身体的神经末梢周围传导神经冲至大脑或脊柱腱的神经<br>'),(7983,'periphrasis','','','','periphrases','n. 绕语,迂回的话',''),(7984,'periphrastic','','','','','a. 迂回的,冗赘的',''),(7985,'periscope','','','','','n. 潜望镜',''),(7986,'perish','perished','perished','perishing','','v. 毁减,死亡',' Almost a hundred people perished in the hotel fire last night.<br>     近百人在昨夜旅馆的大火中丧生。<br>\n The lumbermen were perished with cold.<br>     伐木工人冻僵了。<br>'),(7987,'perishable','','','','perishables','a. 易腐坏的,会枯萎的,会死的<br>\nn. 易腐坏的',' Perishable food should be stored in a refrigerator.<br>     易腐的食物应储存在冰箱里.<br>\n Keep perishable foods under refrigeration.<br>     把容易变质的食物冷藏起来.<br>'),(7988,'perishing','','','','','a. 严寒的',' I can\'t get in I\'ve lost the perishing key!<br>     我进不去－－我把该死的钥匙