itude.<br>     适应气候动物或植物在生理上对气候或环境的变化，比如光线，气温或高度变化的适应<br>'),(8200,'physiological psychology','','','','','生理心理学',''),(8201,'physiologically','','','','','ad. 生理上,在生理学上',''),(8202,'physiologist','','','','physiologists','n. 生理学家',' German physiologist. He won a1901 Nobel Prize for work on serum immunization against diphtheria and tetanus.<br>     贝林，埃米尔·冯1854－1917德国生理学家，因其在抗白喉与破伤风血清免疫方面的工作获1901年诺贝尔奖<br>\n Russian physiologist who is best known for discovering the conditioned response. He won a1904 Nobel Prize for research on the nature of digestion.<br>     巴甫洛夫，伊凡·彼得洛维奇1849－1936俄国生理学家，因发现条件反射而著名，他1904年因在研究消化作用的特征方面的贡献而获诺贝尔奖<br>'),(8203,'physiology','','','','physiologies','n. 生理学',' We had studied physiology in middle school.<br>     我在中学就已经学过生理学。<br>\n The application of the principles of the natural sciences, especially biology and physiology, to clinical medicine.<br>     临床生物医学应用于临床医学的自然科学原理，尤指生物学与生理学<br>'),(8204,'physiotherapy','','','','','n. 物理疗法',''),(8205,'physique','','','','','n. 体格',' Having a heavy, muscular physique.<br>     公牛般的有健壮的、肌肉发达的体格的<br>\n Practicing gongfu strengthens the physique.<br>     武术可以锻炼筋骨。<br>'),(8206,'phytoplankton','','','','','n. 浮游生物',''),(8207,'pianissimo','','','','pianissimos','ad.&a. 极弱的(地)',''),(8208,'pianist','','','','pianists','n. 钢琴家',' I hope his dream of becoming a pianist will come true.<br>     我希望他成为钢琴家的梦想可以成真。<br>\n The pianist forgot his music and had to improvise (the accompaniment).<br>     弹钢琴的人把乐谱忘了, 只好即兴伴奏.<br>'),(8209,'piano','','','','pianos','n. 钢琴',' She is learning to play the piano.<br>     她在学弹钢琴。<br>\n The singer was accompanied by her sister at the piano.<br>     这位歌唱家由她妹妹担任钢琴伴奏。<br>'),(8210,'piazza','','','','piazzas','n. 广场,走廊,市场',' A boy is flying a kite in the piazza.<br>     一个小男孩在阳台上放风筝。<br>'),(8211,'PIC','','','','','(Picture)图像压缩',''),(8212,'picador','','','','picadores','n. 斗牛士之助手',''),(8213,'picaresque','','','','','a. 以流氓为题材的',''),(8214,'picaro','','','','picaros','n. 坏蛋,流浪汉',''),(8215,'P