piddling amounts of money.<br>     花这麽一点钱也要去请示, 真烦人.<br>'),(8237,'pie','','','','','n.饼图 n.派,馅饼,杂乱,喜鹊,爱说话的人 vt.弄乱',' Would you like some more apple pies?<br>     再来点苹果馅饼好吗？<br>\n She had two generous helpings of pie.<br>     她吃了两客分量很足的馅饼。<br>'),(8238,'piebald','','','','','a. 花斑的<br>\nn. 花马',''),(8239,'piece','pieced','pieced','piecing','pieces','n. 块,片,篇<br>\nv. 修补,结合',' Would you please give me a piece of paper?<br>     能给我一张纸吗？<br>\n He went to pieces when they told him the tragic news.<br>     人们告诉他那悲惨的消息後，他已六神无主了。<br>'),(8240,'piecemeal','','','','','ad. 一件一件,一片一片<br>\na. 一片一片的,逐渐的<br>\nn. 断片',' I\'ve only had a piecemeal account of what happened.<br>     我对发生的事情只有支离破碎的了解.<br>\n The building was assembled piecemeal.<br>     那座建筑物是一块一块地组装起来的。<br>'),(8241,'pieces','','','','','支<br>\n毛束<br>\n匹头',' The huge waves battered the wrecked ship to pieces.<br>     巨浪将那艘失事的船只冲击得支离破碎.<br>\n The poster had been ripped to pieces.<br>     那张广告画已被撕得粉碎。<br>'),(8242,'piecework','','','','','n. 计件工作',''),(8243,'pied','','','','','a. 斑驳的,杂色的,花衣服的',' The Pied piper had all the children of Hamlin on his heels.<br>     穿彩衣的吹笛人使得汉姆林镇所有的孩子都跟着他走。<br>\n I am cooking apple pies with my newly bought frying pan.<br>     我正在用我新买的煎锅做苹果馅饼。<br>'),(8244,'pier','','','','piers','n. 码头',' The ship lies at the pier.<br>     船在码头停着。<br>\n A pier running out into the sea.<br>     突伸到海中的码头。<br>'),(8245,'pierce','pierced','pierced','piercing','','n. 皮尔斯<br>\nv. 刺穿,穿透,洞悉',' The regiment pierced through the enemy\'s lines.<br>     这个团突破了敌军防线。<br>\n The needle pierced her finger.<br>     针刺进了她的手指。<br>'),(8246,'piercing','','','','','a. 刺骨的,刺穿的,讽刺的',' The calling of a man\'s self to a strict account, is a medicine, sometime too piercing and corrosive.<br>     一个人的严厉自责是一种有时过于猛烈，蚀力过强的药品。<br>\n All of a sudden a piercing scream broke the silence.<br>     突然，刺耳的尖叫声打破了寂静。<br>'),(8247,'Pierre','','','','','皮埃尔(男子名, Peter 的异体)',' Sarah is going on an exchange to Paris to stay with Pierre, and he is coming to stay