INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (8382,'plastered','','','','','a. 醉醺醺的',' The cracks in the ceiling have to be plastered up before you can start painting.<br>     在油漆天花板之前，先得用灰泥把裂缝填塞起来。<br>\n The two decorators worked slowly to make mine that paint was plastered on the furniture evenly.<br>     两个装饰工人干得很慢，以确保家俱上的油漆被均匀地涂上。<br>'),(8383,'plastic','','','','plastics','a. 塑料的<br>\nn. 塑料,(外科)整形的',' Many items in daily use are made of plastic.<br>     很多日常生活用品是用塑料制成的。<br>\n Plastic is sometimes used instead of leather.<br>     塑胶有时可以替代皮革。<br>'),(8384,'plasticity','','','','','n. 可塑性,适应性,柔软性',' It is their plasticity at certain temperatures that gives plastics their main advantage over many other materials.<br>     正是在一定温度下塑料所具有的塑性使它比其他许多材料更优越。<br>'),(8385,'plastics','','','','','n. 整形外科, 外科修补术',' He is a plastic surgery specialist.<br>     他是个整形外科医生。<br>\n Plastics are often used today.<br>     塑料是现今常用的材料。<br>'),(8386,'plate','plated','plated','plating','plates','n. 碟,盘,金属板,板块<br>\nv. 镀金,电镀',' The doctor inserted a steel plate into his damaged leg.<br>     医生在他受伤的腿中植入了一块钢板。<br>\n His plate was piled high with rice.<br>     他的盘子里盛满了米饭。<br>'),(8387,'plate glass','','','','','平板玻璃',''),(8388,'plate tectonics','','','','','板块结构学',''),(8389,'plateau','','','','plateaus','n. 高原;平稳;稳定状态',' Sales have now reached a plateau.<br>     销售现已开始停滞不前。<br>\n After a period of rapid inflation, price have now reach a plateau.<br>     经急剧通货膨胀之後物价现已趋於平稳。<br>'),(8390,'platelet','','','','','n. 血小板',''),(8391,'platen','','','','','压纸卷筒,压盘,滚筒',''),(8392,'platform','platformed','platformed','platforming','platforms','n. 平台,月台,讲台,坛',' The party\'s platform is reducing taxes.<br>     那个政党的政治纲领是减税。<br>\n Please buy me a platform ticket.<br>     请给我买张站台票。<br>'),(8393,'platinum','','','','','n. 白金',' Platinum is used to make jewelry.<br>     白金常常用来做珠宝饰物。<br>\n Originally Edison used platinum alloys for the filament, in the belief that carbon was impracticable.<br>     爱迪生不相信碳可作灯丝用，所以一开始就用铂合金作灯丝。<br>'),(8394,'platitude','','','','','n. 陈词滥调',' A commonplace remark or notion; a platitude.<br>     陈词滥调陈腐庸俗的话或想法；陈词滥调<br>\n It\'s no more than a platitude.<br>     无非是老生常谈。<br>'),(8395,'Plato','','','','','柏拉图[古希腊哲学家]',' A legendary island in the Atlantic Ocean west of Gibraltar, said by Plato to have sunk beneath the sea during an earthquake.<br>     亚特兰蒂斯大西洋中一传说岛屿，位于直布罗陀西部，柏拉图声称在一场地震中沉入海底<br>\n The modern Plato has an unbounded contempt for politicians and statesmen and party leaders who are not university men.<br>     现代的“柏拉图”对那些不是大学毕业的政客、政治家和党派领导人轻蔑到无以复加的程度。<br>'),(8396,'platonic','','','','','a. 柏拉图哲学的, 柏拉图主义的, 理想的, 不切实际的',' I often go out with Cynthia but it\'s purely Platonic love between us.<br>     我经常和辛西娅外出，但那纯粹是精神上的相爱。<br>\n Existing as an archetype or pattern, especially as a Platonic idea or perception.<br>     观念的，理念的以原型或固定形式出现的，特指柏拉图哲学中的观点或概念<br>'),(8397,'platoon','','','','','n. 排,一组,团',' The sergeant bellowed orders at the platoon.<br>     士官向全排士兵大声地发出命令.<br>\n Platoon, halt!<br>     全排注意, 立定!<br>'),(8398,'platter','','','','platters','n. 大浅盘',' She put the grapes onto the platter.<br>     她把葡萄放到一个大盘子上。<br>\n Always got what they wanted on a platter.<br>     总是毫不费力地得到他们想要的东西<br>'),(8399,'platypus','','','','platypi','n. 鸭嘴兽',''),(8400,'plaudit','','','','plaudits','n. 赞美',' She won plaudits for the way she presented her case.<br>     她妙语陈情博得众口交赞.<br>\n A new play that opened to the plaudits of the critics.<br>     受到评论家们喝彩的一出新戏剧<br>'),(8401,'plausible','','','','','a. 似真实的,似合理的,说得蛮像回事的',' The plausible talk of a crafty salesperson.<br>     诡计多端的推销员的花言巧语<br>\n He trotted out a most plausible story, but most of us were inclined to doubt the truth of it.<br>     他提出了一个听起来很有道理的说法，但我们大多数人对此都持怀疑态度。<br>'),(8402,'play','played','played','playing','plays','n. 游戏,游玩,剧本,比赛<br>\nv. 玩,进行比赛,演奏,播放',' The boys were playing with balls.<br>     男孩子们正在玩球。<br>\n They played a joke on me.<br>     他们开我的玩笑。<br>'),(8403,'playback','','','','','回放,重放',' On dictation equipment, a device for accurate alignment of playback head, or combined head, to the track on the recording medium.<br>     录音设备上的一种装置，它能精确地把重放磁头或组合磁头调准到记录介质的磁道上。<br>\n A relatively narrow magnetic tape used to record sound for subsequent playback.<br>     录音磁带一种相对狭长的磁带，用于录下声音以便日后重放<br>'),(8404,'playboy','','','','playboys','n. 花花公子',' He has been given a label of \"playboy\" by his friends.<br>     他的朋友给他起了一个“花花公子”的绰号。<br>'),(8405,'player','','','','players','n. 比赛者,运动员',' There are eleven players in the game.<br>     这场比赛中有11名选手。<br>\n This tennis player ranked third in the world.<br>     这位网球运动员排名世界第三。<br>'),(8406,'playful','','','','','a. 爱打趣的,多趣的,嬉戏的',' He gave me a playful slap on the hand.<br>     他闹着玩地打了一下我的手。<br>\n She has a playful mood.<br>     她有着快活的心情。<br>'),(8407,'playground','','','','playgrounds','n.&a. 操场',' The students are playing on the playground.<br>     学生们正在操场上玩。<br>\n There are more than five hundred people on the playground.<br>     运动场上有五百多人。<br>'),(8408,'playhouse','','','','playhouses','n. 儿童游戏房',' Mike Jackson, the new pop singer, was certainly a hit with the audience at the Playhouse Theatre last night.<br>     迈克·杰克逊，一名新的流行歌星，昨晚在剧场当然地受到观众们的欢迎。<br>\n The children enjoyed making a playhouse out of cardboard.<br>     那些孩子们喜欢用卡纸板搭玩具小屋玩。<br>'),(8409,'playing card','','','','','n. 纸牌,扑克牌',' A playing card bearing the figure of a queen, ranking above the jack and below the king.<br>     王后画有王后人像的一张纸牌，比杰克大但比国王小<br>\n A playing card marked with nine pips.<br>     标有九点的一张扑克牌<br>'),(8410,'playmate','','','','playmates','n. 玩伴,游伴',' He was my playmate in childhood.<br>     他是我童年时的玩伴。<br>\n She has been the playmate of every boy on the football team.<br>     她曾经是足球队上每个人的性伴侣。<br>'),(8411,'playoff','','','','','n. （双方得分相等时的）最后决赛',' The team manager fell in for the major share of the blame when his team lost the playoffs.<br>     球队的经理在他的球队失去决赛权时，首当其冲受到许多谴责。<br>'),(8412,'plaything','','','','playthings','n. 玩具,被玩弄的人',' He treated the silly girl as a plaything.<br>     他把那个愚蠢的女孩当作一个玩物。<br>\n I used to get them new plaything to keep them quiet.<br>     我过去总是给他们买新玩具来使他们安静。<br>'),(8413,'playtime','','','','','n. 游戏时间,娱乐时间,开幕时刻',' The children are outside during playtime.<br>     在娱乐时间学生都在室外活动。<br>\n The children have three playtimes during the day.<br>     那些学生一天有三次游戏时间.<br>'),(8414,'playwright','','','','playwrights','n. 剧作家',' This playwright is very popular now.<br>     这位剧作家现在很受欢迎。<br>\n The legal right granted to an author, a composer, a playwright, a publisher, or a distributor to exclusive publication, production, sale, or distribution of a literary, musical, dramatic, or artistic work.<br>     版权授予文学、音乐、戏剧或艺术作品的作者、作曲者、剧作者、出版商或独家经营出版、生产或销售的批发商的合法权利<br>'),(8415,'plaza','','','','plazas','n. 广场,市场',' We\'ve booked you in at the Plaza for two nights.<br>     我们为你在普拉扎旅馆预订了两夜的房间.<br>'),(8416,'plea','','','','pleas','n. 请求,恳求<br>\nv. 借口,恳求,请求',' The accused entered a plea of \"not guilty\".<br>     被告作了“无罪”的抗辩。<br>\n She made an impassioned plea for justice.<br>     她激昂地抗辩，恳求获得公正。<br>'),(8417,'plead','pleaded','pleaded','pleading','','v. 辩护,恳求,托称',' The girl charged with murder was said to be mad and unfit to plead.<br>     据说那个被指控谋杀的女孩是疯子，不能为自己申辩。<br>\n Pleading ignorance of the law won\'t help you if you are caught.<br>     假若因犯法被抓住，藉口不知是犯法亦无济於事。<br>'),(8418,'pleading','','','','','n. 恳求',' Pleading ignorance of the law won\'t help you if you are caught.<br>     假若因犯法被抓住，藉口不知是犯法亦无济於事。<br>\n He apologized for not coming to the party, pleading pressure of work.<br>     他为不能到会而道歉, 推说是工作太忙.<br>'),(8419,'pleasant','','','','','a. 令人愉快的,舒适的<br>\nvi. 满意,喜欢<br>\nvt. 使高兴',' She seems a pleasant woman.<br>     她似乎是一个友善的女人。<br>\n We are living in pleasant surroundings.<br>     我们生活在舒适的环境中。<br>'),(8420,'pleasantly','','','','','ad. 友好地,亲切地,客气地',' The noise of the stream had a pleasantly somnolent effect.<br>     小河潺潺的流水声有宜人的催眠效果.<br>\n The day went pleasantly enough until I received your call.<br>     接到你的电话前，我过了愉快的一天<br>'),(8421,'please'