the trade negotiations.<br>     该部长获有全权进行贸易谈判.<br>\n A minister plenipotentiary assigned to a foreign embassy, ranking next below the ambassador.<br>     特命全权公使派驻国外使馆的特命全权使节，仅低于大使<br>'),(8432,'plenitude','','','','','n. 完全,大量',''),(8433,'plentiful','','','','','a. 多的,丰富的',' The camp has a plentiful supply of food.<br>     营地有充足的食品供应。<br>\n Marked by abundance; plentiful.<br>     表现为丰富的；大量的<br>'),(8434,'plenty','','','','','a. 充足的,相当多的<br>\nn. 充足,大量<br>\npron. 充分,够多',' In years of plenty everyone has plenty to eat.<br>     丰年时人人都吃得饱。<br>\n There\'s plenty of room for everyone inside.<br>     里面有的是地方，大家都可以进来。<br>'),(8435,'plesiosaur','','','','','n. 蛇,颈龙',''),(8436,'plethora','','','','','n. 过量,过剩',' The report contained a plethora of detail.<br>     报告中细节过多.<br>'),(8437,'plethoric','','','','','a. 充血的,多血的',''),(8438,'plexor','','','','','n. 叩诊锤',''),(8439,'pliable','','','','','a. 易曲折的,柔软的,圆滑的',' Pliable or impressionable.<br>     顺从的或易受影响的<br>\n Capable of being bent or flexed; pliable.<br>     柔软的可弯曲或扭曲的；柔韧的<br>'),(8440,'pliant','','','','','a. 易受影响的,易弯的',''),(8441,'pliers','','','','','n. 钳子',''),(8442,'plight','','','','','n. 境况,誓约,情形<br>\nv. 宣誓,保证,约定',' The poor girl was in a terrible plight.<br>     这个可怜的女孩处境极其恶劣。<br>\n She plighted herself to him.<br>     她和他订婚了。<br>'),(8443,'plinth','','','','','n. 柱脚,底座',''),(8444,'plod','plodded','plodded','plodding','','n. 沉重的步伐,辛勤工作<br>\nv. 沉重地走,辛勤工作,孜孜从事',' We plodded on through the rain for several hours.<br>     我们在雨中跋涉了几个小时。<br>\n Labourers plodded home through the muddy fields.<br>     工人们穿过泥泞的田地走回家去。<br>'),(8445,'plodding','','','','','a. 沉重缓慢的,单调乏味的',' How\'s the book?\' Oh, I\'m plodding along. \'<br>     ｀那本书怎麽样?＇｀哦, 我正在磨蹭呢.＇<br>\n We plodded on through the rain for several hours.<br>     我们在雨中跋涉了几个小时。<br>'),(8446,'plot','plotted','plotted','plotting','plots','n. 图,阴谋,情节<br>\nv. 绘图,密谋,计划',' I grow potatoes on my little plot of land.<br>     我在那一小块地上种土豆。<br>\n They are plotting how to murder him.<br>     他们在密谋如何杀害