t','','','','','a. 悲伤的,严厉的,尖锐的,剧烈的',''),(8498,'poikilothermic','','','','','a. [动]变温的,冷血的,冷血动物的',''),(8499,'point','pointed','pointed','pointing','points','n. 点,要点,尖端<br>\nv. 指出,指,描准',' I\'m in a hurry, so come to the point.<br>     我赶时间，直接了当说出来吧。<br>\n I don\'t see the point of her last remark.<br>     我不明白她最后那句话的意思。<br>'),(8500,'point of view','','','','','n. 观点(看法,见解)',' If one has an open mind, it is easy to appreciate another\'s point of view.<br>     如果一个人思想开放, 就不难接受他人的观点。<br>\n I have some sympathy with that point of view.<br>     我比较赞成这种看法.<br>'),(8501,'pointed','','','','','a. 尖的,锐利的,率直的<br>\nv. 指出,指,瞄准<br>\nvbl. 指出,指,瞄准',' He pointed at the diagram to illustrate his point.<br>     他指着图表来说明他的论点。<br>\n I pointed out the shortcomings of the scheme, but he countered that the plans were not yet finished.<br>     我指出那方案的缺点, 但他申辩说各项计划尚未完成.<br>'),(8502,'pointedly','','','','','ad. 尖锐地, 指向地',' She stared pointedly at me.<br>     她严厉地瞪著我.<br>\n After having pointedly warned Baghdad not to use poison gas or combat aircraft anywhere in Iraq, warnings that had encouraged the rebellion, Mr.Bush pulled up short when Iraq continued to fly combat helicopters against the insurgents.<br>     经过特别警告巴格达不得在伊拉克任何地方使用毒气和作战飞机（这些警告鼓励了少数民族叛变）以后，当伊拉克继续用作战直升机对付叛军时，布什却半途而废未加制止。<br>'),(8503,'pointer','','','','pointers','n. 指示的人,教鞭,暗示',' The pointer flickered.<br>     指示针来回摆动。<br>\n A graduated surface or face on which a measurement, such as speed, is indicated by a moving needle or pointer.<br>     标度盘有刻度的表面或面，在上面由活动的指针或指示器表示度量衡，比如温度<br>'),(8504,'pointing','','','','','指点,指示',' One of the penalties of fame is that people point at you on the street.<br>     当了名人的麻烦之一是在街上被人指指点点。<br>\n That\'s the man who did it,\' she said, pointing at me.<br>     ｀那事就是他干的,＇她指著我说.<br>'),(8505,'pointless','','','','','a. 不尖的,钝的,不得要领的',' We had fallen so far behind that it seemed pointless continuing.<br>     我们已经落在後面很远, 继续下去似乎没有什麽意义.<br>\n It\'s pointless trying to keep your friendship secret it\'s common knowledge already.<br>     你们无谓将友情保密--其实已尽人皆知了.<br>'),(8506,'points','','','','','磅',' Gained15 pounds; the market gained30 points.<br>     增加了15镑；股市增长了30个点<br>\n The Dow Jones industrials, ahead10 points early in tandem with further improvement in bond prices, ended off13.59 at1, 944.63.<br>     道·琼斯工业股早先随着公债价格提升而上涨10点，最后以1944。63收盘，下降13。59。<br>'),(8507,'poise','poised','poised','poising','','n. 平衡,姿势,镇静<br>\nv. 使...平衡,保持平衡,保持...姿势',' He poised the glass on the shelf.<br>     他把玻璃杯稳稳地放在架子上。<br>\n We admired the graceful poise of the dancer.<br>     我们很欣赏那位舞蹈演员的优美舞姿。<br>'),(8508,'poised','','','','','a. 摆好姿势不动的，稳重的，坦然自若的',' He poised the glass on the shelf.<br>     他把玻璃杯稳稳地放在架子上。<br>\n The eagle poised in mid-air ready to swoop on its prey.<br>     那鹰在半空中盘旋准备扑向猎物.<br>'),(8509,'poison','poisoned','poisoned','poisoning','poisons','n. 毒药,败坏道德之事,毒害<br>\nv. 毒害,摧毁,中毒',' Someone tried to poison our dog.<br>     有人想毒杀我们的狗。<br>\n Gases from cars are poisoning the air of our cities.<br>     汽车放出的废气在污染我们城市的空气。<br>'),(8510,'poisoning','','','','','n. 中毒',' Food poisoning can cause death.<br>     食物中毒可导致死亡.<br>\n The chemical companies are poisoning our rivers with effluent.<br>     这些化学公司排出废水污染著我们的河流。<br>'),(8511,'poisonous','','','','','a. 有毒的',' She gave him a poisonous look.<br>     她恶狠狠地瞪了他一眼。<br>\n Some plants have poisonous berries.<br>     有些植物的浆果有毒。<br>'),(8512,'poke','','','','','n. 刺,戳,袋<br>\nv. 拨开,刺,探索',' He is poking the fire with a poker.<br>     他正用通条捅火。<br>\n She poked her finger into the hole.<br>     她把手指插入孔中。<br>'),(8513,'poker','','','','','n. 扑克<br>\nvt. 烙制',' Bridge, poker and whist are card-games.<br>     桥牌、 扑克和惠斯特都是纸牌游戏.<br>\n The reserve pieces, cards, chips, or play money in some games, such as poker, from which the players may draw.<br>     发剩的牌在某些游戏如扑克牌游戏中保留的张、卡、片或纸钱，游戏者可以从中抽牌<br>'),(8514,'poky','','','','','a. (地方)狭小的,不舒适的',''),(8515,'Poland','','','','','n. 波兰',' He was born in Poland.<br>     他出生在波兰。<br>\n Wales were trounced 5-0 by Poland.<br>     威尔士队让波兰队以5比0打得一败涂地.<br>'),(8516,'polar','','','','','a. 两极的,南辕北辙的,极地的',' The two systems of government are polar opposites.<br>     这两种政体正好相反。<br>\n Are there any animals in the polar circles?<br>     南极圈和北极圈内有动物存在吗？<br>'),(8517,'polar bear','','','','','n. 北极熊',' In spite of vigilance a polar bear escape from the zoo.<br>     尽管警戒很严，北极熊还是逃出了动物园。<br>\n Although they can swim, the polar bears are terrestrial animals.<br>     北极熊虽然会游泳，但也是陆栖动物。<br>'),(8518,'Polaris','','','','','北极星',''),(8519,'polarity','','','','polarities','n. 有两极,磁性引力,极性<br>\nn. 两极分化,极端性',''),(8520,'polarization','','','','','n. 极化',' An instrument used to measure the rotation of the plane of polarization of polarized light passing through an optical structure or sample.<br>     偏振计；旋光计用来测量经过光学结构或样品的极化光的偏振平面旋转的一种仪器<br>'),(8521,'polarize','polarized','polarized','polarizing','','vt. 极化(使...偏振化,使...两极分化)',' Public opinion has polarized on this issue.<br>     在这个问题上公众的意见已两极分化.<br>'),(8522,'Polaroid','','','','','n. 人造偏光板,其商标名',''),(8523,'pole','','','','','n. 极(点)<br>\nv. 跳,支撑',' Our opinions on this subject are at opposite poles.<br>     我们对这一问题的看法截然相反。<br>\n The hut was made of poles covered with grass mats.<br>     茅屋用木杆搭成，上面以草席覆盖。<br>'),(8524,'pole vault','','','','','n. 撑杆跳<br>\nvt. 撑杆跳高',' Our school won first place for the pole vault.<br>     我们学校赢得了撑杆跳第一名。<br>'),(8525,'polemic','','','','','n. 争论,论战',' He launched into a fierce polemic against the government\'s policies.<br>     他猛烈地抨击政府的政策.<br>'),(8526,'polemical','','','','','a. 辩论法, 辩论术, 好辩的, 挑起争端的,引起论战的',''),(8527,'polemics','','','','','n. 争辩',' He launched into a fierce polemic against the government\'s policies.<br>     他猛烈地抨击政府的政策.<br>\n In place of the scholarly tome that many people expected of him, Mr White has produced a polemic, and not a very good one at that. As the woman said, we are not amused.<br>     怀特先生出版了一本并非人们所期待的博学的大部头，而是一本有争议的不是太好的小作品。正如这位妇女所说，我们对这很冷淡。<br>'),(8528,'polestar','','','','','n. 北极星,指导者,指导原理',''),(8529,'police','policed','policed','policing','','a. 警察的<br>\nn. 警察,警方<br>\nv. 管辖',' The police have caught the murderer.<br>     警察已经抓获杀人凶手。<br>\n Our neighbourhood police are very friendly.<br>     我们邻近的警察非常友善。<br>'),(8530,'police officer','','','','','n. 警官, 警员',' The investigation was carried out under the direction of a senior police officer.<br>     调查是在一位高级警官的指导下进行的。<br>\n I\'ll find the evidence I want, said the police officer, even if we have to tear the whole house apart.<br>     警官司说：“即使我们不得不把整个房子翻个一塌糊涂，我也愿找到我要的证据”。<br>'),(8531,'police station','','','','','n. 警察局',' Terrorists bombed the police station in revenge for the arrests.<br>     恐怖分子用炸弹袭击了警察局报复逮捕行动.<br>\n At the police station, he was formally charged with murder.<br>     在警察局他被正式控告犯谋杀罪。<br>'),(8532,'policeman','','','','policemen','n. 警察',' The policeman ordered him to stop the car.<br>     警察命令他停车。<br>\n The policeman was justified in shooting the criminal in self-defence.<br>     那个警察出于自卫枪击罪犯是正当防卫。<br>'),(8533,'policemen','','','','','n. 警察',' The sheriff ordered the policemen to gather.<br>     警察局长命令警察集合。<br>\n The Queen was flanked by a retinue of bodyguards and policemen.<br>     女王左右有保镖和警察护卫着。<br>'),(8534,'policewoman','','','','policewomen','n. 女警察',' The thief made a misguided attempt to rob a policewoman.<br>     那个贼不识好歹竟要抢劫一个女警察。<br>\n She was strongly committed to her job, a policewoman by eminence.<br>     她非常忠于职守，一位典型的（卓越的）女警察。<br>'),(8535,'policy','','','','policies','n. 政策,方针,保险单',' Honesty is the best policy.<br>     诚实是最明智的。<br>\n This latest incident may be the lever needed to change government policy.<br>     最近的事件或许可以作为迫使政府改变政策所需的手段。<br>'),(8536,'polio','','','','','n. ［医］脊髓灰质炎,小儿麻痹症',' She had polio as a child and spent the rest of her life in a wheelchair.<br>     她小时候得了小儿麻痹症, 终生没离开过轮椅.<br>\n He failed many times but he finally broke through to find a successful polio vaccine.<br>     他失败了许多次，但终于发现了有效的预防小儿麻痹症的疫苗。<br>'),(8537,'poliomyelitis','','','','','n. 脊髓灰质炎',''),(8538,'polis