br>\n Suddenly he had a presage about the near danger.<br>     他突然对即将到来的危险有了一种预感。<br>'),(8904,'Presbyterian','','','','','a. [宗]长老会(制)的',' There are some reports about the Presbyterian Church on the newspaper.<br>     报纸上有许多关于基督教长老会的报道。<br>\n The church has become a social as well as a religious force in the community, but community life is not broken up into Presbyterian, Methodist, Lutheran, Roman Catholic, and Jewish groups.<br>     在社会上，教会不仅是一种宗教力量，而且也是一种社会力量，但长老会、卫理公会、路德会、罗马天主教会和犹太教会等教派教徒在社会生活中并不各成体系。<br>'),(8905,'preschool','','','','','a. 未满学龄的,就学前的<br>\nn. 育幼院,幼稚园',''),(8906,'preschooler','','','','','n. （美）学龄前儿童',''),(8907,'prescience','','','','','n. 预知,先见',''),(8908,'prescient','','','','','a. 有先见之明的',''),(8909,'prescribe','prescribed','prescribed','prescribing','','v. 规定,命令,开药方',' Regulations prescribe that a lawyer draw up the paper.<br>     条文规定必须由律师拟定此公文。<br>\n What medicine did the doctor prescribe for your illness?<br>     医生开了什么药来治你的病？<br>'),(8910,'prescribed','','','','','a. 规定的',' Having no prescribed destination. Used of mail.<br>     无姓名和地址的没有规定的目的地。用于邮政<br>\n The act of adjusting, arranging, or shifting characters to the left or right to fit a prescribed pattern.<br>     为了适合规定的格式，将字符向左或向右进行调整、排列或移位的动作。<br>'),(8911,'prescript','','','','','n. 命令,规定',''),(8912,'prescription','','','','prescriptions','n. 药方',' The doctor is writing a prescription.<br>     医生正在开处方。<br>\n The prescription of drugs is a doctor\'s responsibility.<br>     开药方是医生的职责。<br>'),(8913,'presence','','','','','n. 出席,在场',' She was so quiet that her presence was hardly noticed.<br>     她那么安静，几乎没有人注意到她在这里。<br>\n Since she joined the team last season she has made her presence felt.<br>     自从上个赛季加入这个队以来，她就使人感到她是个举足轻重的队员。<br>'),(8914,'presence of mind','','','','','n. 镇定',' The child showed great presence of mind by grabbing the falling baby.<br>     那孩子毫不慌张一把抓住了摔下的婴儿.<br>'),(8915,'present','presented','','','','n. 礼物,现在<br>\na. 现在的,出席的,当面的<br>\nv. 赠送,提出,呈现',' We learn from the past, experience the present and hope for success in the future.<br>     我们从过去中学习，体验现在，展望未来的成功。<br>\n He presented her with a bunch of flowers.<br>     他献给她一束花。<br>'),(8916,'present perfect','','','','','n. [语]现在完成时',''),(8917,'presentation','','','','presentations','n. 陈述,介绍,赠与<br>\nn. [美]讲课,报告',' They are preparing for the presentation of a new musical.<br>     他们正准备上演新的歌舞喜剧。<br>\n We went to the premiere of their new presentation.<br>     我们去观看了他们的新剧目的首场演出。<br>'),(8918,'present-day','','','','','a. 当前的,当代的',''),(8919,'presenter','','','','','n. 赠送的,呈献者,提出者',''),(8920,'presentiment','','','','','n. 预感,预觉',' A feeling or an intuition of what is going to occur; a presentiment.<br>     预感，预知对将要发生的事的感觉或直觉；预感<br>\n A presentiment of the future; a foreboding.<br>     对未来的不祥预感；预兆<br>'),(8921,'presently','','','','','ad. 不久,一会儿,现在,目前',' The professor is presently writing a book.<br>     这位教授目前正在写一本书。<br>\n The doctor will be here presently.<br>     医生一会儿就到。<br>'),(8922,'preservation','','','','','n. 保存',' The aim of the policy is the preservation of peace.<br>     这一政策旨在维护和平。<br>\n The paintings were in an excellent state of preservation.<br>     这些画保存的非常好。<br>'),(8923,'preservative','','','','preservatives','a. 保存的,有保存力的,防腐的<br>\nn. 预防法,预防药,防腐剂',' For the first, the best preservative to keep the mind in health, is the faithful admonition of a friend.<br>     说到第一种，最能保人心神之健康的预防药就是朋友的忠言规谏。<br>\n Salt is a common food preservative.<br>     盐是一种常用的食物防腐剂。<br>'),(8924,'preserve','preserved','preserved','preserving','preserves','v. 保护,保持,维持,防腐,做蜜饯',' I think these interesting old customs should be preserved.<br>     我认为这些有趣的旧习俗应该保存下去。<br>\n It\'s the duty of the police to preserve the public order.<br>     维护公共秩序是警察的职责。<br>'),(8925,'preset','preset','preset','presetting','','v. 事先调整',' The menu will expand to show four preset positions and preset1 will automatically be highlighted.<br>     此菜单会展开显示四个预置位置，Preset1将自动变后。<br>\n Preset a microwave oven.<br>     预先调节好微波炉<br>'),(8926,'preside','presided','presided','presiding','','v.   任主席,统辖,当主人',' Some people believe that the Fates preside over man\'s destiny.<br>     有些人相信，命运之神支配人类的命运。<br>\n The hostess presided at table with tact and urbanity.<br>     女主人招待客人进餐时风雅而又得体。<br>'),(8927,'presidency','','','','presidencies','n. 总统职位,总裁职位,主席职位',' He was elected to a second presidency.<br>     他获选连任总统。<br>\n She hopes to win the presidency.<br>     她希望争取到总统职位。<br>'),(8928,'president','','','','presidents','n. (国家)总统,(公司)总裁,总经理,社长(日本)',' President Lincoln was born poor.<br>     林肯总统出身贫寒。<br>\n The president is strongly desirous that you should attend the meeting.<br>     董事长极希望你能参加会议。<br>'),(8929,'presidential','','','','','a. 总统的',' Next year is a presidential year.<br>     明年是总统选举年。<br>\n That politician won the presidential election campaign and became the President.<br>     那位政治家赢得了总统选举，成为了总统。<br>'),(8930,'press','pressed','pressed','pressing','presses','n. 新闻界,压力<br>\nv. 按,压',' Press this button to start the engine.<br>     按这个按钮开动引擎。<br>\n The child pressed her nose against the window.<br>     那小女孩把鼻子贴在窗户上。<br>'),(8931,'press conference','','','','','n. 记者招待会',' You will see him at the press conference.<br>     你会在记者招待会上见到他的。<br>\n The spokesman was bombarded with questions on the press conference.<br>     新闻发布会上那位发言人遭到了连珠炮般的发问。<br>'),(8932,'pressing','','','','pressings','a. 紧迫的,紧急的,切实的<br>\nvbl. 压迫',' Compelling immediate action or attention; pressing.<br>     紧迫的强求立即的行动和关注的；急迫的<br>\n Pressing business kept him in Leeds, so he sent his deputy on to represent him in Edinburgh.<br>     紧急的事务使他留在里兹，所以他派代理人代表他先赶到爱丁堡去。<br>'),(8933,'pressure','pressured','pressured','pressuring','pressures','n. 压力,压强,压迫',' It took a bit of pressure to make the lid close.<br>     要稍按一下才能把盖子盖紧。<br>\n It was done under the pressure of the necessity.<br>     这件事是在迫切需要的情况下而做的。<br>'),(8934,'pressurize','pressurized','pressurized','pressurizing','','vt. 增压(密封,使...压入)',' He felt that he was being pressurized to resign.<br>     他感到有压力逼他辞职.<br>\n She was pressurized into agreeing to a merger.<br>     她被迫同意将公司合并.<br>'),(8935,'prestidigitation','','','','','n. 变戏法,手法敏捷',''),(8936,'prestige','','','','','n. 威望,声望',' The War and Navy departments each accumulated growing prestige which fostered the spirit of the old school tie.<br>     陆军部和海军部各自积累了不断增长的威望，这种威望培育了小集团主义精神。<br>\n Is, as Mr. Nixon said, our prestige at an all time high?<br>     是否如尼克松先生所说，我们的声望正前所未有的高？<br>'),(8937,'prestigious','','','','','a. 享有声望的,声望很高的',''),(8938,'prestissimo','','','','','ad.&a. 最快的（地）',''),(8939,'presto','','','','','ad.&a. 急速的（地）<br>\nn. (音乐)快拍,急速',' I just turn the piece of wire in the lock and hey presto, the door open.<br>     我把金属丝伸到锁孔里一拧，嘿，那门就开了。<br>'),(8940,'Preston','','','','','普雷斯顿',' Oh, is not that preston Jack? So sorry.<br>     噢，不是普雷斯顿杰克吗？对不起。<br>'),(8941,'presumable','','','','','a. 可推测的,可能有的,似真的',' The presumable result is an election defeat.<br>     推测结果是竞选可能会失败。<br>'),(8942,'presumably','','','','','ad. 推测上,假定上,大概',' He will presumably resign in view of the complete failure of his policy.<br>     由於他所推行的政策彻底失败了, 他很可能辞职.<br>\n She is aware of the difficulties, presumably?<br>     她对这些困难大概了解吧?<br>'),(8943,'presume','presumed','presumed','presuming','','v. 假定,推测,占便宜',' A signed invoice presumes receipt of the shipment.<br>     经过签字的发票表示货物已经收到。<br>\n The law presumes innocence until guilt is proved.<br>     在罪状未证实前，法律假定被告无罪。<br>'),(8944,'presumption','','','','presumptions','n. 推测,可能性',' The article has too many false presumptions.<br>     这篇文章中凭空臆测的东西太多。<br>\n She was infuriated by his presumption in making the travel arrangements without first consulting her.<br>     他事先没有和她商量便作好旅行安排，她对他自作主张很生气。<br>'),(8945,'presumptuous','','','','','a. 放肆的,冒昧的,冒失的',' I dislike that presumptuous young man.<br>     我不喜欢那个自以为是的年轻人。<br>\n Having or showing excessive and arrogant self-confidence; presumptuous.<br>     冒昧的，放肆的拥有或显示过分的或傲慢的自信的；自行其事的<br>'),(8946,'presupposition','','','','','n. 预先假定,臆测',' Bail was refused on the presupposition of his guilt.<br>     已料到他罪名成立而不准保释.<br>\n You have made several unjustified presuppositions.<br>     你作了一些毫无根据的假设.<br>'),(8947,'pretence','','','','','n. 假装(自命,无事实根据的要求)',' You can\'t keep up the pretence any longer.<br>     你不能再假装下去了。<br>\n Don\'t listen to his pretences; he is lying.<br>     别听他的种种藉口，他在撒谎。<br>'),(8948,'pretend','pretended','pretended','pretending','','v. 假装,伪称',' She pretends that she likes them so that she can get their help.<br>     她假装很喜欢他们，借以获得他们的帮助。<br>\n The young actor pretended to be Hamlet.<br>     那个年轻演员扮演哈姆雷特。<br>'),(8949,'pretended','','','','','a. 假的,虚伪的',' He is nothing but a hypocrite, pretending that he knows nothing about it.<br>     他是一个虚伪的人，假装对那件事一无所知。<br>\n The young actor pretended to be Hamlet.<br>     那个年轻演员扮演哈姆雷特。<br>'),(8950,'pretender','','','','','n. 冒充者,假冒者',''),(8951,'pretense','','','','pretenses','n. 藉口,虚假,伪装',' It is merely a pretense.<br>     这只是托词而已。<br>\n The act of inventing such a creation or pretense.<br>     虚构，捏造虚构作品或捏造借口的行为<br>'),(8952,'pretension','','','','pretensions','n. 借口, 要求, 主张, 自负, 骄傲, 权力, 资格, 预紧,预伸,预拉',' He has no pretensions to being an expert on the subject.<br>     他并不以这方面专家自居。<br>\n His social pretensions make him appear ridiculous.<br>     他冒充上流社会人士而出尽洋相。<br>'),(8953,'pretentious','','','','','a. 自负的,自命不凡的',' One who is insincere or pretentious.<br>     伪君子虚伪或自负的人<br>\n Striving to be modern in appearance or style but lacking taste or refinement; pretentious.<br>     做作地追求现代的力求具有现代样式或外观但不雅观或缺少品味的；自命不凡的<br>'),(8954,'pretentiousness','','','','','n. 自命不凡',''),(8955,'preternatural','','','','','a. 异常的,超自然的',''),(8956,'pretext','','','','pretexts','n. 借口',' We\'ll have to find a pretext for not going to the party.<br>     我们得找个借口不去参加聚会。<br>\n He came to see me on the pretext of asking my advice.<br>     他以请我指教为借口来看我。<br>'),(8957,'prettily','','','','','ad. 可爱地',' She decorated the room very prettily.<br>     她把房间装饰得漂亮极了。<br>\n She smiled prettily as she accepted the flowers.<br>     她在接受鲜花时, 笑得真迷人.<br>'),(8958,'pretty','prettied','prettied','prettying','pretties','a. 漂亮的<br>\nad. 相当地',' The little girl is pretty.<br>     这个小女孩很漂亮。<br>\n What a pretty little garden!<br>     多么漂亮的小花园！<br>'),(8959,'prevail','prevailed','prevailed','prevailing','','v. 获胜,流行,盛行',' Misty weather prevails in this part of the country.<br>     该国的这一地区天气多雾。<br>\n Sadness prevailed in our mind.<br>     我们的心中充满悲痛，<br>'),(8960,'prevailing','','','','','a. 盛行很广的,一般的,最普通的<br>\nvbl. 获胜,盛行,流行',' Product buy- back is a prevailing payment term at present.<br>     产品回购是目前流行的一种付款方式。<br>\n Being in or conforming to the prevailing or current fashion; stylish.<br>     流行的符合流行的或现时的式样的；时髦的<br>'),(8961,'prevalence','','','','','n. 传播,流行,普及',' They are so surprised by the prevalence of anti-government sentiments.<br>     他们对普遍存在的反政府情绪感到很吃惊。<br>\n I\'m shocked at the prevalence of bribery among these officials.<br>     我对这些官员的普遍受贿感到震惊。<br>'),(8962,'prevalent','','','','','a. 流行的,普遍的',' Eye diseases are prevalent in some tropical countries.<br>     在一些热带国家，眼疾很流行。<br>\n The prevalent opinion is in favour of reform.<br>     一般舆论都支持改革.<br>'),(8963,'prevalently','','','','','ad. 流行地,普遍地',''),(8964,'prevaricate','prevaricated','prevaricated','prevaricating','','v. 支吾其辞,搪塞,推诿',' Tell us exactly what happened and don\'t prevaricate.<br>     有什麽就原原本本地告诉我们吧, 别躲躲闪闪的.<br>\n Instead of admit his guilt, he prevaricate.<br>     他不但不承认，反而支吾其词。<br>'),(8965,'prevent','','','','','v. 预防,防止',' What can we do to prevent the disease spreading?<br>     我们能做什么来防止这种疾病蔓延呢？<br>\n These regulations are intended to prevent accidents.<br>     这些规章制度旨在防止事故发生。<br>'),(8966,'prevention','','','','','n. 阻止,妨碍,预防',' Prevention is better than cure.<br>     预防胜于治疗（治病不如防病）。<br>\n They have begun to do the prevention of crime.<br>     他们已经开始防止犯罪行为。<br>'),(8967,'preventive','','','','preventives','a. 预防的<br>\nn. 预防法',' Please take some preventive medicine now.<br>     请吃些预防药吧。<br>\n We had to take preventive measures.<br>     我们不得不采取预防措施。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (8968,'preview','previewed','previewed','previewing','previews','n. 事先查看,查阅<br>\nv. 事先查看,查阅',' I showed the sales director a preview of the proposal to whet his appetite for the main advertising campaign.<br>     我给销售经理预先看所提的建议，以增加他对广告宣传运动的兴趣。<br>\n After a sneak preview of the film they decided to shelve it.<br>     该影片在试映后，他们决定把它搁置起来。<br>'),(8969,'previous','','','','','a. 在...之前,先,前,以前的',' Previous to the conference we had discussed the matter among ourselves.<br>     在会议之前，我们讨论了这个问题。<br>\n Have you had previous career experience?<br>     你过去有过工作经验吗？<br>'),(8970,'previous to','','','','','在...之前',' Previous to the conference we had discussed the matter among ourselves.<br>     在会议之前，我们讨论了这个问题。<br>'),(8971,'previously','','','','','ad. 以前(预先)',' Who previously held the record?<br>     这个纪录原先由谁保持？<br>\n The star of the film is a previously unknown actor.<br>     这部电影里的明星以前是个默默无闻的演员.<br>'),(8972,'prevision','','','','','n. 先见,预感',''),(8973,'prey','preyed','preyed','preying','','n. 被掠食者,牺牲者<br>\nv. 捕食,掠夺,使...苦恼',' Cares preyed upon her health.<br>     忧虑损害了她的健康。<br>\n The lion seized its prey and ate it.<br>     狮子抓住猎物，把它吃了。<br>'),(8974,'price','priced','priced','pricing','prices','n. 价格,代价,价值<br>\nv. 定...的价格,标价',' The dresses in the shop are priced high.<br>     这家商店的衣服定价很高。<br>\n What is the price of the suit?<br>     这套西装多少钱？<br>'),(8975,'priceless','','','','','a. 无价的',' In its spacious halls are displayed over8000 priceless relics.<br>     在它宽敞的大厅里，展出了8000多件珍贵文物。<br>\n A maniac had gouged several holes in the priceless painting.<br>     有个狂徒在那幅价值连城的画上乱凿了几个洞.<br>'),(8976,'pricey','','','','','a. 昂贵的,过分昂贵的',' This restaurant is a bit pricey for me.<br>     这家饭馆的价钱对我来说贵了些.<br>\n Houses are pricey in this area of the city.<br>     城里这个地区的住房价格很高。<br>'),(8977,'pricing','','','','','n. 定价',' The separate pricing of goods and services.<br>     分别处理商品和服务的价格<br>\n The new law allows firms a lot less latitude than before in fixing the price of their goods.<br>     新法律在允许各商行给产品定价的自由上比以前少得多了。<br>'),(8978,'prick','pricked','pricked','pricking','pricks','v. 刺,穿,受责备<br>\nn. 扎,逗点,锥',' She pricked herself on a needle.<br>     她被针扎了一下。<br>\n He felt a sharp prick when he stepped on a upturned nail.<br>     他一脚踩在一枚尖头朝上的钉子上，感到一阵剧痛。<br>'),(8979,'prickle','','','','','n. (动物或植物上的)刺,棘<br>\nv. 刺痛',' The woollen cloth prickles (my skin).<br>     穿毛料衣服（使我的皮肤）有被扎的感觉.<br>\n My scalp began to prickle as I realized the horrible truth.<br>     我了解到了那令人恐惧的事实, 顿时感到不寒而栗.<br>'),(8980,'prickly','','','','','a. 多刺的,易生气的',' Bearing or covered with spines or bristles; prickly.<br>     棘皮的具有或覆盖有针或刺的；多刺的<br>\n The child\'s rubber ball punctured when it fell on a prickly bush.<br>     那小孩的皮球落在带刺的树丛上时被戳破了。<br>'),(8981,'pride','prided','prided','priding','','n. 自傲,自豪,自尊<br>\nv. 以...自豪',' Pride was his downfall.<br>     骄傲是他垮台的原因。<br>\n I think you hurt his pride by laughing at the way he speaks English.<br>     我觉得你嘲笑他说英语的方式刺伤了他的自尊心。<br>'),(8982,'priest','priested','priested','priesting','priests','n. 教士,神父',' The priest persuaded him to give up his bad habit.<br>     牧师劝他放弃坏习惯。<br>\n The priest is a regular caller.<br>     这位神父经常来访。<br>'),(8983,'priestess','','','','','n. 尼,尼姑,女祭司',''),(8984,'prig','','','','','n. 自以为比别人更有道德的人',' Charles thinks he\'s better than the rest of us, the self-righteous prig!<br>     查尔斯认为他比我们大家都强，真是个自以为是的家伙！<br>'),(8985,'prim','primmed','primmed','primming','','a. 规规矩矩的,呆板的,拘谨的<br>\nv. 弄整齐,地把嘴闭紧',' You can\'t tell that joke to her she\'s much too prim and proper.<br>     可别给她讲那样的笑话--她这人过於古板和认真.<br>\n Prim and sedate.<br>     严肃沉闷的<br>'),(8986,'primal','','','','','a. 最初的,原始的',''),(8987,'primarily','','','','','ad. 首先,主要地',' This building was primarily intended to be a dinning hall.<br>     这座建筑原来是打算用作餐厅的。<br>\n Most linguists would say they were concerned primarily with the structure of languages.<br>     大多数语言学家都会说，他们主要研究各种语言的结构。<br>'),(8988,'primary','','','','primaries','n. 最主要者<br>\na. 主要的,初期的,根本的',' Love and hatred are primary emotions.<br>     爱和恨是基本的情感。<br>\n The disease is still in its primary stage.<br>     这疾病仍然在初发阶段。<br>'),(8989,'primary care','','','','','最初治疗,初级治疗',''),(8990,'primary school','','','','','小学',' The little boy left primary school at eleven.<br>     这个小男孩十一岁时小学毕业。<br>\n Sure. We are friends since primary school.<br>     当然，我们从小学就是朋友了。<br>'),(8991,'primate','','','','','n. 灵长目动物',' The office, rank, or province of primate.<br>     首席主教（或都主教，大主教）的职责，阶层或教区<br>\n The human being is a primate.<br>     人类是灵长类动物<br>'),(8992,'primavera','','','','','n. 白桃花心木(中美洲出产的一种树木或其木材)',''),(8993,'prime','primed','primed','priming','primes','a. 首要的,最好的<br>\nn. 青春,壮年,全盛时期',' He makes it his prime care.<br>     他极为重视这件事。<br>\n What was said was of prime importance.<br>     说过的那件事是很重要的。<br>'),(8994,'prime minister','','','','prime','n. 总理, 首相',' Mr. Heath is the former Prime Minister of Britain.<br>     希思先生是英国前任首相。<br>\n The Prime Minister was dethroned by the President.<br>     总理被总统废黜了。<br>'),(8995,'primer','','','','primers','n. 启蒙书,识字课本',' A coat of primer should be made over the bare surface before the main painting.<br>     在喷涂主漆前，应在物品的表面刷一层底漆。<br>\n Children learn knowledge from primers.<br>     孩子们从启蒙书上学习知识。<br>'),(8996,'primeval','','','','','a. 原始的,早期的,远古的',' The primeval chaos out of which it was believed that the earth and sky were formed.<br>     混沌，洪荒原始的混沌状态，据信地球和天空由此形成<br>\n Being first in time; original; primeval.<br>     最初的，原始的；远古的<br>'),(8997,'primitive','','','','primitives','a. 原始的<br>\nn. 原始人',' Primitive man made himself primitive tools from sharp stones and animal bones.<br>     原始人用尖石块和兽骨为自己制作原始的工具。<br>\n Small seashells were often used as a primitive kind of money.<br>     小贝壳常被用作简单的货币。<br>'),(8998,'primogeniture','','','','','n. 长子之身分',' He inherited his father by right of his primogeniture.<br>     他凭着长子继承权，继承了他父亲的财产。<br>'),(8999,'primordial','','','','','a. 原始的,自原始时代的,最初的',' Play a primordial role.<br>     担任主要角色<br>\n Life\'s primordial reality is spirit.<br>     生命的根本真实性是精神。<br>'),(9000,'primp','primped','primped','primping','','v. (妇女)刻意打扮',''),(9001,'primrose','','','','','n. 樱草类,樱草花,樱草色<br>\na. 樱草的,樱草色的,华美的',' They walked along the primrose bank chatting.<br>     他们沿着报春花盛开的河岸边走边聊。<br>\n Oil of evening primrose is used as a herbal medicine.<br>     月见草油可用作草药.<br>'),(9002,'prince','','','','princes','n. 王子,亲王',' Prince Charles will be the next king of England.<br>     查尔斯王子将是英国的下一位国王。<br>\n The prince lived in a large and beautiful castle.<br>     王子住在一个美丽的大城堡里。<br>'),(9003,'princely','','','','','a. 王子的,像君主的,壮丽的',' They paid me the princely sum of USD5000.<br>     他们慷慨地给我5000美元。<br>\n That\'s a princely state.<br>     那是一个国王统治的国家。<br>'),(9004,'princess','','','','princesses','n. 公主,王妃',' Princess Anne is the daughter of Queen Elizabeth.<br>     安妮公主是伊丽莎白女王的女儿。<br>\n She performs the duties of a princess with great aplomb.<br>     她泰然自若地履行王妃的职责.<br>'),(9005,'Princeton','','','','','n. 普林斯顿',' Professor Green, lately of Princeton, is now head of the department at California.<br>     格林教授不久前在普林斯顿任教，现在是加州大学的系主任。<br>'),(9006,'principal','','','','principals','a. 主要的<br>\nn. 负责人,校长,资本',' Our principal problem is lack of time.<br>     我们的主要问题就是缺少时间。<br>\n The agent spoke on behalf of his principal.<br>     代理人代表他的委托人说话。<br>'),(9007,'principality','','','','principalities','n. 封邑,公国',' I\'ve been to the Principality of Monaco.<br>     我曾去过摩纳哥公国。<br>\n A woman who is ruler of a principality.<br>     女王，女诸侯统治公国（或封邑）的妇女<br>'),(9008,'principally','','','','','ad. 主要地',' The dialect is spoken principally in the rural areas.<br>     这种方言主要在农村地区使用。<br>\n The money is invested principally in government stock.<br>     这笔钱主要投资于政府公债上。<br>'),(9009,'principle','','','','','n. 原则,原理,主义,信念',' We adhere to the principle that everyone should be treated fairly.<br>     我们必须坚持人人都应该被平等对待这一原则。<br>\n The system works on the principle that heat rises.<br>     该项装置是按照热力上升的原理运转的。<br>'),(9010,'print','printed','printed','printing','prints','n. 版,印刷物,印迹<br>\nv. 印刷,出版,打印',' This printer can print 40 pages in a minute.<br>     这台打印机一分钟能打印40页。<br>\n I can\'t read small print without my glasses.<br>     我不戴眼镜看不清小字体。<br>'),(9011,'print head','','','','','打印头',' A pin in the print head of a computer printer.<br>     撞针计算机打印机的印刷头上的撞针<br>'),(9012,'printable','','','','','可印刷的',' His comment when he heard the news was not printable! ie was too rude to be printed.<br>     他在得知这消息时所发的议论不宜见诸报端（语言粗俗难登大雅之堂）.<br>\n The article is too badly written to be printable.<br>     这篇文章写得很糟糕, 不宜发表.<br>'),(9013,'printed matter','','','','','印刷品',' Printed matter of passing interest.<br>     只具有极短吸引力的印刷品<br>\n Spaces or a space, as in printed matter.<br>     字距空隙或空白，如印刷品中<br>'),(9014,'printer','','','','printers','n. 打印机',' This error is made by printer.<br>     这个错误是由印刷工造成的。<br>\n Do you have enough money to buy a new printer?<br>     你有足够的钱买一台新的打印机吗？<br>'),(9015,'printing','','','','printings','n. 印刷,印刷术<br>\nvbl. 印刷',' The old printing press will have to be pensioned off.<br>     那个旧印刷机得报销了.<br>\n The firm specializes in printing advertisements.<br>     这家公司专印广告.<br>'),(9016,'printing ink','','','','','n. 印刷油墨',' The printing ink has been used up.<br>     印刷油墨用光了。<br>'),(9017,'printout','','','','','打印输出',' Get me a printout of the statistics.<br>     给我一份打印出的统计资料.<br>\n A printout of a program or data set.<br>     清单打印出的程序或数据组<br>'),(9018,'prior','','','','','a. 更重要的,较早的,在先的<br>\nad. 居先',' All the arrangements should have been completed prior to our departure.<br>     全部安排都应该在我们出发之前完成。<br>\n I was unable to attend the meeting because of a prior engagement.<br>     我因有约在先，所以未能参加这个会。<br>'),(9019,'prior to','','','','','在...之前',' All the arrangements should have been completed prior to our departure.<br>     全部安排都应该在我们出发之前完成。<br>\n The interest deducted prior to purchasing, selling, or lending a commercial paper; the discount rate.<br>     贴现率在购买、出售或贷款的商业票据前削减利息；贴现率<br>'),(9020,'priority','','','','priorities','n. 优先权,优先顺序,优先',' I have priority over you in my claim.<br>     我的请求比你的优先。<br>\n Rebuilding the area is a (top) priority.<br>     重建这一地区是当务之急.<br>'),(9021,'priory','','','','priories','n. 小修道院',''),(9022,'prism','','','','prisms','n. 棱镜',' The sunlight will break into different colors through a prism.<br>     阳光穿过棱镜时将分解成各种颜色。<br>\n A prism decomposes light.<br>     棱镜可以分解光线。<br>'),(9023,'prison','','','','prisons','n. 监狱',' Many people believe that prison isn\'t a cure for crime.<br>     许多人都相信监禁解决不了犯罪问题。<br>\n The thief was put into prison for one year.<br>     小偷被监禁一年。<br>'),(9024,'prisoner','','','','prisoners','n. 囚犯',' The prisoners are allowed an hour\'s exercise every day.<br>     犯人们每天有一小时放风的时间。<br>\n We are all prisoners of our past.<br>     我们都摆脱不了往事的羁绊。<br>'),(9025,'prissy','','','','','a. 谨小慎微的,神经质的,为小事挂虑的',''),(9026,'pristine','','','','','a. 原来的,古时的,原始的',' Pristine mountain snow.<br>     山上洁白的雪<br>'),(9027,'privacy','','','','privacies','n. 隐私,隐居,秘密',' Everyone has his own privacy.<br>     每个人都有自己的隐私。<br>\n In this place privacy is impossible.<br>     在这种地方保密是不可能的。<br>'),(9028,'private','','','','privates','a. 私人的<br>\nn. 士兵',' She is a very private person.<br>     她是个非常孤僻的人。<br>\n It\'s illegal to read people\'s private letters without permission.<br>     未经允许看别人的私人信件是不合法的。<br>'),(9029,'private enterprise','','','','','n. 私人企业, 民营企业',' He works in a private enterprise.<br>     他在一家私人企业工作。<br>\n Conservativegovernments in Britain favour private enterprise rather than nationalization.<br>     英国的保守党政府赞成私人经营而反对国有化.<br>'),(9030,'private school','','','','','n. 私立中小学',' If a child attends a private school, his parents pay the school for the child\'s education.<br>     如果孩子上了私立学校，他的父母就要为孩子的教育付学费。<br>\n Entered the children in private school; entered dahlias in a flower show.<br>     使孩子入私立学校；使大丽花参加一个花卉展览<br>'),(9031,'privately','','','','','ad. 私下(秘密地)',' Take a deep breath and ask if you can see her privately.<br>     平心静气地想一想你能否私下里去拜访她。<br>\n Rochester quiets the household\'s alarm but asks Jane privately to help nurse Mr. Mason who is bleeding and unconscious.<br>     庄园里的人惊慌失措，罗切斯特使他们镇静下来。但他私下里要求简·爱帮助照料正在流血、失去知觉的梅森先生。<br>'),(9032,'privation','','','','privations','n. 丧失,贫困',' It would be the greatest imaginable privation for her to have to leave London.<br>     对她来说, 不得不离开伦敦大概是能想像到的最大的损失.<br>\n She didn\'tfind the lack of a car any great privation.<br>     她觉得没有汽车并非重大缺憾.<br>'),(9033,'privilege','privileged','privileged','privileging','privileges','n. 特权,特别恩典,基本人权<br>\nv. 给与...特权',' It was a privilege to work with him.<br>     和他在一起工作是一项殊荣。<br>\n She had led a life of luxury and privilege.<br>     她过著养尊处优的生活。<br>'),(9034,'privileged','','','','','a. 有特权的',' Tax laws that favored the privileged at the expense of the disadvantaged.<br>     以处于劣势的人为代价而有利于拥有特权者的税法<br>\n On an occasion such as this (ie as important as this) we are privileged to welcome...<br>     在这样重要的场合, 我们有幸能欢迎...<br>'),(9035,'privy','','','','privies','a. 个人的<br>\nn. 厕所(有利害关系的人)',' I was not privy to the discussion, so I cannot tell you what was decided.<br>     我并不了解讨论的情况，所以无法告诉你做了什么决定。<br>\n A latrine; a privy.<br>     厕所旧式厕所；茅坑<br>'),(9036,'prize','','','','','n. 奖,奖品,战利品<br>\nv. 珍视,捕获',' First prize in the raffle is a holiday for two in Paris.<br>     抽奖销售的头奖是两个人到巴黎度假旅游。<br>\n The boy\'s bicycle was his most prized possession.<br>     这个男孩子把自行车看作是他最宝贵的财产。<br>'),(9037,'prizewinner','','','','','n. 获奖人',''),(9038,'pro','','','','','n. 能手(赞成)<br>\nad. 正面地',' This arrangement will have to do pro tem.<br>     暂时只好这样安排.<br>\n Much has been written on the subject pro and con.<br>     对那问题已有很多赞成和反对的文章。<br>'),(9039,'pro forma','','','','','a. 形式的',' Enclosed you will find a bill of lading for this wine, and an invoice, pro forma, as you are not limited as to the price.<br>     关于葡萄酒，我们同函寄上提单以及发票，请查收为荷。发票部分由于贵公司并未给予我公司限价，故改为估价。<br>\n It was merely a pro forma meeting; the real business had already been discussed.<br>     这只是形式上的会议，真正的议题早已讨论过了。<br>'),(9040,'pro