的位置。<br>'),(9148,'prominently','','','','','ad. 显著地',' He figured prominently in the discussion.<br>     他参与了这次讨论，并引起了人们的注意。<br>'),(9149,'promiscuity','','','','promiscuities','n. 混乱,杂乱,放荡',''),(9150,'promiscuous','','','','','a. 杂乱的,混杂的,混淆的<br>\nad. 偶然地,胡乱地',' A person regarded as promiscuous.<br>     淫棍被认为性关系混乱的人<br>\n A promiscuous man; a philanderer.<br>     好色者好色的男人；玩弄女性的男人<br>'),(9151,'promise','promised','promised','promising','promises','n. 诺言,约定,希望<br>\nv. 允诺,约定,预示',' John promises well as an actor.<br>     约翰有希望成为演员。<br>\n The new sales policy promises well.<br>     新的销售办法可望取得良好效果。<br>'),(9152,'Promised Land','','','','','上帝允许给亚伯拉罕的地方<br>\n乐土<br>\n福地<br>\n希望之乡',' Nobody can bring us swiftly, painlessly into the promised land.<br>     无人能够把我们迅速地、毫无痛苦地带进理想之园。<br>'),(9153,'promisee','','','','','n. 承诺人,受约人',''),(9154,'promises','','','','','n. 承诺<br>\nv. 允诺',' Their promises are not worth a damn.<br>     他们的承诺分文不值.<br>\n Many voters know that the promises of different parties before an election are all just pie in the sky.<br>     许多选民都知道各党派在选举前的承诺只不过是空头支票，不会兑现的。<br>'),(9155,'promising','','','','','a. 有希望的,有前途的',' The newspapers described her as a promising young singer.<br>     报纸上将她称为大有前途的青年歌手。<br>\n The coach is bringing on some promising youngsters in the reserve team.<br>     教练正在帮助後备队中有前途的年轻人提高技术.<br>'),(9156,'promissory','','','','','a. 约定的',' A promissory note.<br>     借据保证性的证据<br>'),(9157,'promissory note','','','','','本票<br>\n期票',' A promissory note.<br>     借据保证性的证据<br>'),(9158,'promontory','','','','promontories','n. 海角,岬',' A promontory of southeast Newfoundland, Canada, on the coast of the Avalon Peninsula.<br>     莱思角加拿大纽芬兰省东南部一海角，位于亚法隆半岛沿岸<br>'),(9159,'promote','promoted','promoted','promoting','','v. 促进,提升,升迁,促销',' After this win, Manchester United was promoted to the First Division.<br>     这次踢赢之后，曼彻斯特联队升入了甲级。<br>\n The young army officer was promoted to the rank of captain.<br>     这个年轻军官被提升为上尉。<br>'),(9160,'promoter','','','','promoters',