osed for your information.<br>     随信寄上一份暂定议事的日程安排供参考。<br>'),(9288,'provisions','','','','','n. 粮食,食品',' We set out with enough provisions.<br>     我们带上足够的食品出发了。<br>\n Both sides should act according to the provisions of the agreement.<br>     双方都应按协议条款办事。<br>'),(9289,'proviso','','','','provisos','n. 附文,条件',' Depending on a proviso; conditional.<br>     有附带条件的依赖于限制性条文的；条件性的<br>'),(9290,'provisory','','','','','a. 有附文的,有附带条件的,暂时的',''),(9291,'provocation','','','','provocations','n. 激怒,刺激,挑拨',' They attacked our border guards without the slightest provocation.<br>     在事先未发生任何挑衅的情况下，他们便袭击我们的边防哨兵。<br>\n A provocation to action; a stimulus.<br>     激励，刺激某种行动的刺激；激励<br>'),(9292,'provocative','','','','','a. 气人的,挑拨的,刺激的<br>\nn. 刺激物,挑拨物,兴奋剂',' Harry claims to be an anarchist but he\'s really only striking an attitude to be provocative.<br>     哈里自称是一名无政府主义者，但是他实际上只是在装腔作势以引起人们的议论。<br>'),(9293,'provoke','provoked','provoked','provoking','','v. 激怒,惹起,驱使',' He tried to provoke them into fighting.<br>     他企图挑拨他们打架。<br>\n Such a questionable assertion is sure to provoke criticism.<br>     这种有问题的主张肯定会招致非议。<br>'),(9294,'provoking','','','','','a. 激怒人的,刺激人的',' It is very provoking of her to be so late.<br>     她到得这麽晚真叫人生气。<br>\n The act of provoking or inciting.<br>     激怒挑衅或煽动的行动<br>'),(9295,'prow','','','','','n. (飞机)机头,船头',' He stands on the prow looking at the sea.<br>     他站在船首看着大海。<br>\n A carved figure on the prow of a ship.<br>     船头雕饰在船头的雕刻图象<br>'),(9296,'prowess','','','','','n. 英勇,勇敢,超凡技术',' The soldiers sang a song of victory, describing their prowess in battle.<br>     战士们唱起了歌颂他们英勇战斗的凯歌。<br>\n Simon\'s always talking big about his prowess on the golf course.<br>     西蒙总是吹嘘自己在高尔夫球场上的杰出才能。<br>'),(9297,'prowl','prowled','prowled','prowling','','n. 潜行,徘徊,悄悄踱步<br>\nv. 潜行以觅食,窥伺,逡巡于',' He saw a hungry wolf on the prowl with his telescope.<br>     他通过望远镜看到了一头四处觅食的饿狼。<br>\n I saw someone prowling around among the trees.<br>     我见有人在树林里鬼鬼祟祟地走动。<br>'),(9298,'proximate','','','