),(9441,'purification','','','','','n. 净化(提纯)',' Purification of water may be achieved by distillation.<br>     水的净化可由蒸馏获得。<br>\n Reading a good book may bring purification to souls.<br>     读一本好书可以带来心灵的净化。<br>'),(9442,'purify','purified','purified','purifying','','v. 纯净,净化,去除',' You can purify the water by distilling.<br>     你可以通过蒸馏来净化水。<br>\n The act or an instance of cleansing or purifying.<br>     净化洗涤或净化的行为或情况<br>'),(9443,'Puritan','','','','','n.&a. 清教徒(的)',' He is too much of a puritan to enjoy dancing.<br>     他在生活上过于奉行清教徒式的原则，所以不能领略跳舞的乐趣。<br>\n As a Puritan, he is strict in moral and religion.<br>     作为清教徒，他的道德和宗教观念都很严格。<br>'),(9444,'puritanical','','','','','a. 极端拘谨的',''),(9445,'purity','','','','','n. 纯净,纯正,纯粹',' We must ensure the purity of drinking water.<br>     我们必须确保饮用水的纯净。<br>\n It\'s a soprano of great compass and of great purity.<br>     这是一种音域宽广，高度纯正的女高音。<br>'),(9446,'purlieu','','','','','n. 森林边缘地,常去的地方,范围,界限',''),(9447,'purloin','purloined','purloined','purloining','','v. 偷窃',''),(9448,'purple','purpled','purpled','purpling','','a. 紫色的<br>\nn. 紫色',' That girl likes to wear purple dresses.<br>     那个女孩喜欢穿紫色的衣服。<br>\n He was born to the purple.<br>     他出身皇族。<br>'),(9449,'purport','purported','purported','purporting','','n. 意义,要旨,大要<br>\nv. 意味著,做为...要旨,要领是...',' The purport of the statement is that the firm is bankrupt.<br>     该项声明大意是说该商行已经破产。<br>\n The purport of what he said is that he is right.<br>     他说话的涵义是说他是对的。<br>'),(9450,'purpose','purposed','purposed','purposing','purposes','n. 目的,意图',' Did you come to London for the purpose of seeing your family, or for business purposes?<br>     你到伦敦来的目的是为了要看望家人还是为了公事？<br>\n She seems to do these things on purpose.<br>     她似乎是有意地做这些事。<br>'),(9451,'purposeful','','','','','a. 有目的的',' They dealt with the problem in a purposeful way.<br>     他们处理这问题很果断.<br>\n Purposeful or industrious activity; enterprise.<br>     企图，进取心有目的的、勤勉刻苦的行动；进取心<br>'),(9452,'purposefully','','','','','有目的地<br>\n自觉地',''),(9453,'purr','purred','purred','purring','','v. 姑噜姑噜叫,发出喉音<br>\nn. 姑噜姑噜声',' The cat purred loudly.<br>     那只猫大声地发出呼噜呼噜声。<br>\n I heard a car engine purring smoothly.<br>     我听到一辆汽车发动机发出平稳的轰隆声。<br>'),(9454,'purse','pursed','pursed','pursing','purses','n. 钱包, 资金,金钱,财富<br>\nv. 皱起，使缩拢',' Her purse was stolen when she was on the bus.<br>     她的手袋在公共汽车上被偷了。<br>\n The loss of her purse caused her much inconvenience.<br>     丢失钱包给她带来了诸多不便。<br>'),(9455,'purser','','','','pursers','会计员,出纳员',''),(9456,'pursuance','','','','','n. 追求,实行',''),(9457,'pursuant','','','','','adjective [after verb] FORMAL OR LEGAL<br>\naccording to 按照(根据,与...致,合乎,和-一致)',' A decision of the local authority pursuant to the power and duties impose upon it by the statutory code.<br>     地方政府根据成文法（典）所给予的权力和义务所作出的决定。<br>'),(9458,'pursue','pursued','pursued','pursuing','','v. 追捕,追求,继续从事',' The police are pursuing an escaped prisoner.<br>     警方正在追捕一名越狱的逃犯。<br>\n The government is pursuing a policy of non-intervention.<br>     政府正奉行不干预政策。<br>'),(9459,'pursuer','','','','pursuers','n. 从事者,追赶者,追求者',' He managed to avoid his pursuers.<br>     他设法甩掉了那些追捕者。<br>\n I know she has many pursuers.<br>     我知道她的追求者很多。<br>'),(9460,'pursuit','','','','pursuits','n. 追求,追赶,工作',' He exercises everyday in pursuit of health.<br>     他为了健康而每天锻炼。<br>\n What\'s your favorite pursuit?<br>     你的爱好是什么？<br>'),(9461,'purvey','purveyed','purveyed','purveying','','v. 供给,供应',''),(9462,'purveyance','','','','','n. 粮食的供给',''),(9463,'purveyor','','','','purveyors','n. 供应粮食者',' Mozart was, after all, not a mere purveyor of music but one of the supreme dramatic geniuses of all time.<br>     莫扎特毕竟不仅是作曲家，而且是空前的最大戏剧天才之一。<br>\n A purveyor of lies.<br>     谎言的传播者<br>'),(9464,'purview','','','','','n. 范围',' These are questions that lie outside/that do not come within the purview of our inquiry.<br>     这些问题不在我们的调查范围之内.<br>'),(9465,'pus','','','','','n. 脓',' The tip of an abscess, a boil, or a pimple, in which pus forms.<br>     脓头中间有脓液的脓疮、疖或丘疹的顶端<br>\n Discharge or waste, such as pus or feces, from a living organism.<br>     排出物从生命体排生物或废物，如脓、屎、尿等<br>'),(9466,'push','pushed','pushed','pushing','pushes','n. 推,奋力,决心<br>\nv. 推,挤,逼迫',' He pushed her into making a decision.<br>     他催促她做出决定。<br>\n You may stop the machine by pushing this button.<br>     你按下这个按钮就可以关机。<br>'),(9467,'push-button','','','','','按钮<br>\na. 用按钮操纵的',''),(9468,'pushcart','','','','','n. 手推车',' He has come up in the world since he peddled his own baked goods from a pushcart.<br>     他是靠用手推车兜售自己烤制的食品而得以发迹的。<br>'),(9469,'pusher','','','','','n. (毒品等的)非法销售者',' The neighbourhood pusher got Joe a fix.<br>     邻里的不法商贩给乔打了一针毒品。<br>'),(9470,'pushover','','','','','n. (俚)易于征服或控制的人',' The examination was a pushover; I knew all the answers.<br>     那次考试很容易，题目的答案我全都知道。<br>'),(9471,'pushup','','','','','n. 上推(垮砂,砂眼);俯卧撑',''),(9472,'pushy','','','','','a. 强求的',' He made himself unpopular by being so pushy.<br>     他特别喜欢出风头, 所以人缘不好.<br>'),(9473,'pusillanimous','','','','','a. 懦弱的,胆小的',''),(9474,'puss','','','','','n. (爱称)小猫儿,少女',' Here puss, puss!<br>     过来，猫咪！<br>\n She\'s a sly puss.<br>     她是个刁滑的姑娘.<br>'),(9475,'pussy','','','','','n. 小猫,少女,女性的阴部<br>\na. 多脓的',' The baby was playing with his pussy.<br>     孩子正和他的猫嬉戏。<br>'),(9476,'put','put','put','putting','','v. (put, put) 放,安置',' I want to know how to put this in French.<br>     我想知道如何用法语来表达这件事。<br>\n He put some more wood on the fire.<br>     他在火里加了一些柴。<br>'),(9477,'putative','','','','','a. 假定的',''),(9478,'Putonghua','','','','','n. 普通话',''),(9479,'putrefaction','','','','','n. 腐败,腐败物',''),(9480,'putrefy','putrefied','putrefied','putrefying','','v. 使腐烂',''),(9481,'putrid','','','','','a. 腐臭的',''),(9482,'putsch','','','','','n. 起义,叛乱',''),(9483,'putt','putted','putted','putting','','(高尔夫球)推杆',' John tried to help the putt fall by using body English.<br>     约翰尽量把身体扭向洞口方向以期高尔夫球能落进洞内。<br>\n I am merely putt forward toe opinion(that) we shall dine out to save time.<br>     我刚才只是主张应该外出就餐，以节省时间。<br>'),(9484,'puttee','','','','puttees','n. 绑腿,裹腿',''),(9485,'puzzle','puzzled','puzzled','puzzling','puzzles','n. 难题,迷惑<br>\nv. 使...困惑,为难',' The question puzzled me.<br>     这个问题把我难住了。<br>\n He stood there watching with puzzled despair.<br>     他束手无策地站在那儿看着。<br>'),(9486,'puzzled','','','','','v. 困惑<br>\nvbl. 困惑',' His deliverance from the prison puzzled us.<br>     他被从监狱释放使我们困惑不已。<br>\n She listened with a puzzled expression on her face.<br>     她脸上带著困惑的表情在倾听著。<br>'),(9487,'puzzlement','','','','','n. 迷惑',' He stared at the words in complete puzzlement.<br>     他注视著那些语句, 茫然不解.<br>\n Suggesting puzzlement; questioning.<br>     疑惑的表示困惑的；有疑问的<br>'),(9488,'puzzling','','','','','a. 令人迷惑的,茫然不知所措的,莫名其妙的',' She\'s been puzzling over his strange letter for weeks.<br>     她几个星期也琢磨不透他那封奇怪的来信.<br>\n The teacher\'s explanation clarify the puzzling problem.<br>     老师的说明澄清了困扰的问题。<br>'),(9489,'pygmy','','','','pygmies','n. 矮人,侏儒',''),(9490,'pyjama','','','','','n. [常用复数形式](宽大的)睡衣裤',' He had lost his case and had to borrow Tom\'s pyjamas.<br>     他丢失了手提箱，不得不向汤姆借睡衣。<br>\n Put on the electric fire and warm your pyjamas before putting them on.<br>     把电炉打开，在穿睡衣睡裤之前把它们先烤热。<br>'),(9491,'pyjamas','','','','','n. 睡衣',' No rational person would go to work in his pyjamas.<br>     任何神智正常的人都不会穿着睡衣去上班。<br>\n Pyjamas made from flammable material have been removed from most shop.<br>     大部分商店都不再出售用易燃材料做的睡衣了。<br>'),(9492,'pylon','','','','','n. 高压电线架,桥塔',' The helicopter lifted up the steel pylon, transported it to the site, and dropped it gently into place.<br>     直升飞机把高压电缆铁塔吊起，运至工地，然后轻轻放下使之就位。<br>'),(9493,'pyramid','pyramided','pyramided','pyramiding','pyramids','n. 金字塔',' Egypt is famous for its grand pyramids.<br>     埃及以巨大的金字塔闻名。<br>\n A pyramid of stones marked the spot.<br>     那地点用一堆堆成金字塔形状的石头作了标记。<br>'),(9494,'pyre','','','','','n. 火葬柴堆',''),(9495,'pyridine','','','','','n. 吡啶,氮苯',''),(9496,'pyromania','','','','','n. 纵火狂',''),(9497,'pyromaniac','','','','','n. 放火狂<br>\na. 放火狂的',''),(9498,'pyrrhic','','','','','a. 付出极大代价而获得的',' So it looks as it the politicians have won. My only point is that it has been a Pyrrhic victory. In no country in the world are politicians held in greater or more open division than they are here.<br>     因此，看起来政治家们取得了胜利。我惟一的想法是，他们为此付出了惨重的代价，未免得不偿失。世界上其他任何一个国家的政治家之间的分歧都没有这里的政治家之间的分歧那么大，那么公开。<br>'),(9499,'Pythagoras','','','','','n. 毕达哥拉斯',''),(9500,'python','','','','','n. 丹舌,大蟒,巨蟒',''),(9501,'Qingdao','','','','','青岛',' I can not make up my mind where to go for my holiday; I\'m divided Xian and Qingdao.<br>     我决定不下到底去哪儿度假，是去西安还是去青岛。<br>\n By that time they should have fetched up in Qingdao.<br>     到那时候他们应该已经抵达青岛了。<br>'),(9502,'quack','','','','','n. 庸医，(指鸭)呷呷地叫, 大声闲聊, 吹嘘<br>\nn. (鸭子)呷呷叫声, 庸医, 骗子<br>\nadj. 骗人',' He is a quack doctor.<br>     他是个庸医。<br>\n A quack cure.<br>     庸医般的治疗<br>'),(9503,'quad','','','','','n. 四边形(象限,四倍,四心线组,嵌块)<br>\nvt 用空铅填',''),(9504,'quadrangle','','','','','n. 四边形',''),(9505,'quadrant','','','','quadrants','象限',''),(9506,'quadrilateral','','','','','n. 四边形',''),(9507,'quadruped','','','','','n. 四足兽',' The part of the body of a human being or quadruped on either side of the backbone and between the ribs and hips.<br>     腰部人类或四足动物的身体部分，位于脊柱两侧，肋骨与臀部之间<br>\n A joint, as of a bird or quadruped, corresponding to the human elbow.<br>     关节，肘部鸟或四肢动物的关节，相当于人的肘<br>'),(9508,'quadruple','quadrupled','quadrupled','quadrupling','','ad.&a. 四倍的(地)<br>\nn. (使)乘四倍<br>\nv. (使)成四倍',' Their profits have quadrupled/They have quadrupled their profits in ten years.<br>     他们的利润十年中增长至四倍[他们使利润在十年中增长至四倍].<br>'),(9509,'quaff','quaffed','quaffed','quaffing','quaffs','v. 一口气喝干,大口地喝<br>\nn. 一饮而尽,痛饮',' We quaffed wine last night.<br>     我们昨晚畅饮了一次酒。<br>\n He is quaffing his beer by the pint.<br>     他论品脱地大喝啤酒。<br>'),(9510,'quagmire','','','','','n. 沼泽(绝境)',''),(9511,'quail','','','','','n. 鹌鹑',' I quailed with fear at the thought of telling her the bad news.<br>     想到要告诉她这个坏消息，我就害怕得发抖。<br>\n A group of animals or birds, especially larks or quail.<br>     一群动物，一群鸟一群动物或鸟，尤指云雀或鹌鹑<br>'),(9512,'quaint','','','','','a. 古雅的,离奇有趣的,奇怪的',' What a quaint little building!<br>     多么古雅的一座小房子啊！<br>\n Quaint dialect words.<br>     古怪的方言单词<br>'),(9513,'quaintly','','','','','ad. 古雅别致,离奇有趣地, 优雅地','');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (9514,'quake','quaked','quaked','quaking','quakes','n. 地震',' I stood there quaking with fear.<br>     我站在那里，害怕得直发抖。<br>\n The ground quaked under his feet.<br>     大地在他的脚下震动。<br>'),(9515,'Quaker','','','','','n. 教友派信徒',' Quakers strongly oppose violence and war.<br>     教友派信徒们强烈反对暴力和战争。<br>\n The twelve presidents who held office from1890 to1963 represented religious denominations as follows: two Methodists, two Presbyterians, two Baptists, one Unitarian, one Dutch Reformed, one Congregationalist, one Quaker, one Episcopalian, and one Roman Catholic.<br>     从1890年到1963年任职的十二位总统所属的教派如下：两位卫理公会教徒，两位长老会教徒，两位浸礼会教徒，一位唯一神派教徒，一位荷兰新教徒，一位公理会教徒，一位公谊会教徒，一位圣公会教徒，一位罗马天主教徒。<br>'),(9516,'qualification','','','','qualifications','n. 资格,条件,限制',' He\'s got all the right qualifications but is temperamentally unsuitable.<br>     他具备一切合格的条件，惟独性情不适合。<br>\n What sort of qualifications do you need for the job?<br>     做这项工作需要什么资格？<br>'),(9517,'qualifications','','','','','n. 资格,条件',' What sort of qualifications do you need for the job?<br>     做这项工作需要什么资格？<br>\n He\'s got all the right qualifications but is temperamentally unsuitable.<br>     他具备一切合格的条件，惟独性情不适合。<br>'),(9518,'qualified','','','','','a. 有资格的<br>\nvbl. 取得资格',' An English system of land tenure from Anglo-Saxon times to1926 that provided for the equal division of land among all qualified heirs.<br>     财产保有权一种英国的土地保有制度，始于盎格鲁－撒克逊时期，废于1926年，即把其土地平均分配给有资格的继承人<br>\n There is only one man qualified for the job.<br>     仅有一个人能胜任这个工作。<br>'),(9519,'qualifier','','','','','n. 给与资格的人,限定物,限定句',' The final brings together four qualifiers from each heat.<br>     有四名初赛获胜者进入决赛.<br>'),(9520,'qualify','qualified','qualified','qualifying','','v. 取得资格,有资格',' Eighteen-year-olds qualify to vote.<br>     年满十八岁者有选举权.<br>\n Your passport qualifies you to receive free medical treatment.<br>     你所持的护照可使你享有免费医疗.<br>'),(9521,'qualitative','','','','','a. 性质上的,质的,定性的',''),(9522,'quality','','','','qualities','n. 品质,特质,才能',' He shows quality of leadership.<br>     他显示出领导才能。<br>\n The quality of service in this restaurant has improved a lot.<br>     这个饭店的服务质量已经有了很大改善。<br>'),(9523,'quality control','','','','','n. 质量管理, 质量控制',' Production manager: Initiated quality control resulting in a reduction in working hours by20% while increasing productivity by25%.<br>     生产部经理：引入质量控制，使工作时数减少了20％，而生产力则提高了25％。<br>\n Imperfect articles are rejected by our quality control.<br>     我们进行质量检验时，有缺陷的产品均予剔除。<br>'),(9524,'qualm','','','','qualms','n. 疑惧,紧张不安',' He had/felt no serious qualms about concealing the information from the police.<br>     他向警方隐瞒实情而并未感到十分不妥.<br>\n Emma herself suffered from no such qualms, for she was certain that Mr. Elton was as much in love with Harriet as Harriet---through Emma\'s instigation---was with him.<br>     爱玛自己倒是心安理得，因为她确信埃尔顿先生对哈里特十分钟情，而哈里特——在她的鼓动之下——对他也有同样的爱慕之心。<br>'),(9525,'quandary','','','','quandaries','n. 困惑,迷惑,为难',' I am in a quandary, for this situation is totally unforeseen.<br>     我陷入困惑，因为这个局面完全没有被预料到。<br>\n I was put in a great quandary.<br>     我陷于进退两难的窘境。<br>'),(9526,'quantifiable','','','','','a. 可以计量的',' A school of psychology that confines itself to the study of observable and quantifiable aspects of behavior and excludes subjective phenomena, such as emotions or motives.<br>     行为科学主义心理学的一个流派，着重研究行为中可以观察到的、可以量化的方面，排除主观现象，如感情或动机<br>'),(9527,'quantify','quantified','quantified','quantifying','','v. 定量，表示份量，称量，量化',' The cost of the flood damage is impossible to quantify.<br>     这次水灾的损失是无可估量的.<br>'),(9528,'quantitative','','','','','a. 数量的,定量的',' The substitution of one metrical unit for another, especially the substitution of two short syllables for one long syllable in quantitative verse.<br>     长音节的拆分或替换一个韵律元素替代另一个，尤指在数量韵文中用两个短音节替代一个长音节<br>\n Having no fixed quantitative value.<br>     变量的没有固定数量值的<br>'),(9529,'quantity','','','','quantities','n. 量,数量,大量',' It was a bad year for films, in terms of both quantity and quality.<br>     今年的电影无论从数量上还是质量上都说不上好。<br>\n This company is more concerned with quality than with quantity.<br>     这家公司对质量比对产量更重视.<br>'),(9530,'quantization','','','','','量子化,数字化',''),(9531,'quantize','quantized','quantized','quantizing','','量化,数字转换',''),(9532,'quantum','','','','quanta','n. 分配量,额,量',' Liability was admitted by the defendant, but the case went to trial because they could not agree the quantum of damages.<br>     被告承认有责任，但案子还是拿到法庭审判，因为双方当事人不能就损害赔偿金金额达成协议。<br>\n This discovery marks a quantum leap forward in the fight against cancer.<br>     这一发现标志著治疗癌症的 一大突破.<br>'),(9533,'quarantine','quarantined','quarantined','quarantining','','n. 隔离,封锁交通,检疫期间<br>\nv. 检疫,停止交涉',' He had been kept in quarantine for a week.<br>     他接受了一星期的检疫隔离。<br>\n Quarantine restriction have been lifted on import animal from that country.<br>     对来自那个国家的进口动物的检疫限制已被解除。<br>'),(9534,'quark','','','','','夸克',''),(9535,'quarrel','','','','','n. 吵架,反目,怨言<br>\nv. 吵架,争论,挑剔',' I got involved in a quarrel about the price.<br>     我被卷入了一场有关价格的争吵。<br>\n I don\'t quarrel with what you say, but with how you say it.<br>     我并不在意你说了什么，而是不满意你说话的那种方式。<br>'),(9536,'quarrelsome','','','','','a. 喜欢争吵的',' He is a quarrelsome person.<br>     他是个爱争论的人。<br>\n The diary portrays his family as quarrelsome and malicious.<br>     日记中描述了他家反宅乱的事.<br>'),(9537,'quarry','','','','','n. 采石场,猎获物,出处<br>\nv. 挖出,苦心找出',' They are quarrying in old manuscripts.<br>     他们正在旧手稿中寻找资料。<br>\n Detectives kept the quarry under surveillance for weeks.<br>     侦探们监测那个目标已有好几个星期了。<br>'),(9538,'quart','','','','quarts','n. 夸脱',' He still takes his quarts.<br>     他现在还是照常喝大满杯的啤酒。<br>\n One fifth of a gallon or four fifths of a quart of liquor.<br>     五分之一加仑或一夸脱酒的五分之四<br>'),(9539,'quarter','quartered','quartered','quartering','quarters','a. 四分之一的<br>\nn. 四分之一,一刻钟<br>\nvt. 四等分',' It\'s a quarter past ten.<br>     现在是十点一刻。<br>\n The rent is due at the end of each quarter.<br>     缴纳租金以每季度末为期限。<br>'),(9540,'quarterback','quarterbacked','quarterbacked','quarterbacking','','vt. 操纵(对...发号施令)',' A new or substitute offensive play called by the quarterback or a defensive formation called by a linebacker at the line of scrimmage as an adjustment to the opposing side\'s formation.<br>     改变打法一种在橄榄球争球线上作为就对方阵势的调整，由四分卫发令的新的或替代进攻打法，或由后卫发令的防守阵势<br>\n The quarterback was mobbed by the defensive line.<br>     四分卫遭到防守线球员猛烈攻击<br>'),(9541,'quarterly','','','','quarterlies','a. 季度的<br>\nad. 每季一次<br>\nn. 季刊',' For future transaction we are pleased to grant you credit facilities, and shall submit a quarterly statement.<br>     为了将来处理方便起见，我们确认贵公司信用，并乐于给你方提供按季结算。<br>\n A monetary allowance, wage, or payment made or received quarterly.<br>     按季收付的款项按季度发放或收到的津贴、工资或付款<br>'),(9542,'quarters','','','','','n. 营房,住处',' Married quarters are houses where soldiers live with their families.<br>     已婚人员营房是军人与其眷属所住的宿舍。<br>\n The soldiers grappled with the enemy at close quarters.<br>     士兵短兵相接地同敌人格斗。<br>'),(9543,'quartet','','','','quartets','n. 四重奏',' This quartet represents a major new trend in modern music.<br>     这首四重奏的曲子反映了现代音乐中一种主要的新趋向.<br>\n The string quartet is a kind of delicate chamber music.<br>     弦乐四重奏是一种优雅的室内乐。<br>'),(9544,'quartz','','','','','n. 石英',' The prospectors have discovered such minerals as calcite, quartz and asbestos here.<br>     探矿人员在这里发现了方解石、石英、石棉等矿藏。<br>\n A mineral, especially a transparent form of quartz, having a crystalline structure, often characterized by external planar faces.<br>     水晶一种具有晶体结构的矿石，尤指石英的一种透明形态，通常其晶面在同一平面上<br>'),(9545,'quasar','','','','','n. 恒星状球体,半星球体,类星球体',' A lunar occultation of a quasar.<br>     类星体的月星掩测定<br>'),(9546,'quash','','','','','v. 压碎,镇定,镇压',' The applicant seek judicial review to quash the bind-over order.<br>     申请人请求司法检查以便废除责令某人守法的命令。<br>\n The appeal court quash the care order make by the juvenile court.<br>     上诉法院宣布少年法院发出的照看命令无效。<br>'),(9547,'quasi','','','','','a. 类似的,外表的',''),(9548,'quaver','quavered','quavered','quavering','quavers','n. 颤音<br>\nvi. 用颤声说(唱),震动,颤抖',' The children quavered out their little song.<br>     孩子们颤悠悠地唱出了一支歌.<br>\n You could hear the quaver in her voice.<br>     她的声音中能听出有些颤抖.<br>'),(9549,'quay','','','','quays','n. 码头',' We tied (the boat) up alongside the quay.<br>     我们把船停泊在码头处.<br>\n We moored alongside the quay.<br>     我们靠码头停泊.<br>'),(9550,'queasy','','','','','a. 催吐的,使人呕吐的,反胃的;不稳定的、不确定的.',' I feel sort of queasy.<br>     我有些恶心.<br>\n Dizzy or queasy.<br>     迷惑的或令人作呕的<br>'),(9551,'Quebec','','','','','n. 魁北克(加拿大港市省名)',' A town of southern Quebec, Canada, a suburb of Montreal. Population, 37,346.<br>     安茹加拿大魁北克南部的一个城镇，蒙特利尔的郊区，人口37，346<br>\n An inhabitant of French descent living in Canada, especially Quebec, or in Louisiana.<br>     法裔加人祖籍法国，现住加拿大的人，尤其是魁北克人或是在路易斯安那的人<br>'),(9552,'queen','queened','queened','queening','queens','n. 女王,王后',' Queen Marie Antoinette of France was the wife of Louis the 16th.<br>     法国玛丽安东妮皇后是路易十六的妻子。<br>\n Since her promotion she queens it over everyone else in the office.<br>     她获提升後对办事处所有的人都发号施令。<br>'),(9553,'queen-size','','','','','大号的',''),(9554,'Queensland','','','','','昆士兰州(澳大利亚)',''),(9555,'queer','queered','queered','queering','queers','n. 同性恋者<br>\na. 奇怪的,不舒服的,可疑的',' Her queer way of dressing attracted the attention of the passerby.<br>     她古怪的着装方式引起了过路人的注意。<br>\n There is something queer about him.<br>     他有些古怪。<br>'),(9556,'quell','quelled','quelled','quelling','','v. 压制,平息,镇定',' The government\'s reassurances have done nothing to quell the doubts of the public.<br>     政府的再次保证并没有消除公众的疑虑。<br>\n The police have been called in to quell a minor disturbance.<br>     警察奉命出动以平息一场小规模的骚乱。<br>'),(9557,'quench','quenched','quenched','quenching','','v. 熄减,结束,冷浸,解渴',' Hot steel is quenched to harden it.<br>     烧热的钢淬火使它坚硬。<br>\n Water will quench a fire.<br>     水可以灭火。<br>'),(9558,'querulous','','','','','a. 鸣不平的,发牢骚的,易怒的',''),(9559,'query','queried','queried','querying','queries','n. 疑问,疑问号,质问<br>\nv. 问',' The minister was queried about his plans for the industry.<br>     有人向部长提出了工业计划问题。<br>\n Your interesting report raises several important queries.<br>     你的精彩报告引出了几个重要问题。<br>'),(9560,'quest','quested','quested','questing','quests','n. 探索,寻求<br>\nv. 寻找,找,追寻猎物',' The quest for gold was difficult.<br>     寻找金矿是很困难的。<br>\n The lawyer was on a quest for further evidence.<br>     律师正在到处找寻更多的证据。<br>'),(9561,'question','questioned','questioned','questioning','questions','n. 问题,疑问,疑问句<br>\nv. 询问,审问,怀疑',' May I ask a question?<br>     我可以问一个问题吗？<br>\n I would never question his honesty.<br>     我对他的诚实绝不怀疑。<br>'),(9562,'questionable','','','','','a. 可疑的,可置疑的',' Such a questionable assertion is sure to provoke criticism.<br>     这种有问题的主张肯定会招致非议。<br>\n The man looks questionable.<br>     这个男人看上去很可疑。<br>'),(9563,'questioner','','','','','n. 质问者,发问者',''),(9564,'questioning','','','','','质问',' By clever questioning they trapped him into making a confession.<br>     他们用巧妙的提问诱使他招认了。<br>\n The police detained him for questioning.<br>     警方对他进行拘留审问.<br>'),(9565,'questionnaire','','','','questionnaires','n. 调查表',' Please complete and return the enclosed questionnaire.<br>     所附问卷请填妥交回。<br>\n We gave them some questionnaires for collecting data.<br>     为了收集数据我们发给他们一些调查表。<br>'),(9566,'queue','queued','queued','queuing','queues','n. 行列,长队<br>\nv. 排队<br>\nvi. 排长队',' We queued up for the bus.<br>     我们排队等公共汽车。<br>\n People are queuing to buy tickets.<br>     人们正排队买票。<br>'),(9567,'quibble','quibbled','quibbled','quibbling','','n. 遁辞,谬论,双关话<br>\nv. 推托,说模棱两可的话,说俏皮话',' A petty distinction or objection; a quibble.<br>     遁辞微不足道的区别或反对；遁辞<br>\n An equivocation; a quibble.<br>     遁辞模棱两可的话；遁辞<br>'),(9568,'quick','','','','','a. 快的,迅速的<br>\nad. 快,迅速地<br>\nn.皮下（尤指指甲下）细嫩或敏感的肉；活肉',' He is quick to understand.<br>     他理解能力强。<br>\n He gave a quick answer to the teacher\'s question.<br>     他对老师的提问作出了迅速的回答。<br>'),(9569,'quicken','quickened','quickened','quickening','','v. 加快,使...有生气,鼓舞',' Your heart beat will quicken when you run up the stairs.<br>     跑上楼梯时，心跳会加速。<br>\n We quickened our pace.<br>     我们加快了步速。<br>'),(9570,'quickie','','','','','n. 草草完成的劣品',' I\'ve just made some coffee have you time for a quickie?<br>     我刚煮好咖啡--你能抽空儿喝点儿吗?<br>\n My husband and I are so busy that we only have time for quickie.<br>     我丈夫和我都很忙，我们只有时间草草完事。<br>'),(9571,'quickly','','','','','ad. 快,迅速',' He adjusted himself very quickly to the heat of the country.<br>     他很快使自己适应了这个国家炎热的天气。<br>\n The news of her death circulated quickly.<br>     她死去的消息迅速传开。<br>'),(9572,'quicksand','','','','','n. 流沙',' A place filled with mud or quicksand that is a hazard to cattle.<br>     沼穴充满泥浆或流沙的地方，可对牛群构成威胁<br>'),(9573,'quick-witted','','','','','a. 反应灵敏的',''),(9574,'quid','','','','','n. 咀嚼物,烟草块<br>\nn.（英国口语）一英镑（单复同型）',' Something held in the mouth and chewed, such as a quid of tobacco.<br>     咀嚼物，口嚼烟块放在口中进行咀嚼的东西，如烟草块<br>\n Please accept the use of our cottage as a quid pro quo for lending us your car.<br>     请尽管使用我们的村舍, 以酬谢借给我们汽车之事.<br>'),(9575,'quiescent','','','','','a. 静止的,不活动的,寂静的',' It is unlikely that such an extremist organization will remain quiescent for long.<br>     这种过激的组织是不太可能长期沉默的.<br>\n Quiescent. Used especially of a disease.<br>     静止的静止的。尤指一种疾病<br>'),(9576,'quiet','quieted','quieted','quieting','','n. 安静,闲适,平静<br>\na. 安静的,静止的,宁静的<br>\nv. 静止,使...减少,使...安心',' When he quieted down, I began to tell him the truth.<br>     当他平静下来时，我开始告诉他实情。<br>\n Ask him to keep quiet.<br>     让汤姆保持安静。<br>'),(9577,'quieten','quietened','quietened','quietening','','v. (使)平静下来',' Quieten down and get on with your work.<br>     静下心来继续工作吧.<br>'),(9578,'quietly','','','','','a. 寂静地,静止地<br>\nad. 安静地,平静地',' She sang so quietly that I could hardly hear her.<br>     她唱的声音很小, 我几乎听不见.<br>\n The children seem to be totally incapable of working quietly by themselves.<br>     这些孩子似乎完全不能安静地自己做功课。<br>'),(9579,'quietness','','','','','n. 平静,安定,安静',' We enjoyed the quietness of the country.<br>     我们喜欢乡村的平静。<br>\n After the quietness of home and school, university has been almost frightening.<br>     过惯了家庭和中学的平静生活之後，大学简直有些可怕了。<br>'),(9580,'quietude','','','','','n. 安静,静止',' Quietude is the crown of life.<br>     人生何为先，宁静为桂冠。<br>'),(9581,'quill','quilled','quilled','quilling','quills','n. 羽茎,大翎毛,鹅毛笔',' The duke wrote a letter with a quill pen.<br>     公爵用一根羽毛笔写信。<br>'),(9582,'quilt','quilted','quilted','quilting','quilts','n. 被子',' He bought a heavy quilt for the winter.<br>     他买了一床厚被子过冬。<br>\n Quilt a skirt.<br>     缝制裙子<br>'),(9583,'quinine','','','','','n. 奎宁',' Quinine is used as medicine against malaria.<br>     奎宁是用来治疗疟疾的药物。<br>\n Quinine is a specific for malaria.<br>     奎宁是治疗疟疾的特效药.<br>'),(9584,'quintessence','','','','','n. 精粹,(物体)最纯粹的形体,典型',' He is the quintessence oftact and politeness.<br>     他处世谦恭得体.<br>\n Her book captures the quintessence of Renaissance humanism.<br>     她的书抓住了文艺复兴时期人文主义的精髓.<br>'),(9585,'quintet','','','','','五位字节',' The first item on the program is woodwind quintet.<br>     节目单上的第一个节目是木管五重奏。<br>'),(9586,'quintuplet','','','','quintuplets','n. 五胞胎之一',''),(9587,'quip','quipped','quipped','quipping','','n. 警句,名言,讽刺<br>\nv. 说讽刺的话,嘲弄,托辞',' `Who overslept this morning?\' She quipped.<br>     ｀今天早晨谁睡过头了?＇她风趣地问.<br>\n Quips and cranks.<br>     妙语和警句<br>'),(9588,'quirk','','','','','n. 怪癖',' He have a strange quirk of addressing his wife as Mrs Smith.<br>     他很怪，把自己的妻子称作史密斯夫人。<br>\n By a quirk of fate they have booked into the same hotel.<br>     由於命运的捉弄，他们住进同一家旅馆。<br>'),(9589,'quisling','','','','','n. 卖国贼,内奸',''),(9590,'quit','quit','quit','quitting','','v. 离开,辞职,停止',' I\'ve quit my job.<br>     我辞职了。<br>\n You cannot quit smoking too soon.<br>     你愈早戒烟愈好。<br>'),(9591,'quite','','','','','ad. 很,十分',' The boy has quite recovered.<br>     这男孩已彻底恢复健康。<br>\n He was quite young.<br>     他相当年轻。<br>'),(9592,'quitter','','','','','n. 轻易停止的人,懒人,无志气的人',' I\'ve asked you to do this for me because I know you\'re not a quitter.<br>     我要求你为我做这件事, 因为我知道你做事不虎头蛇尾.<br>'),(9593,'quiver','','','','','n. 震动,颤抖,箭袋<br>\nv. 颤