ive','','','','','a. 反动的,反应性的,反冲的',' Not readily reactive with other elements; forming few or no chemical compounds.<br>     惰性的与其它元素反应不活泼的；不能形成或很少能形成化合物的<br>'),(9793,'reactor','','','','','n. 反应堆',' A reactor is a container for chemical reaction.<br>     反应器是进行化学反应的容器。<br>\n An undamaged nuclear reactor; undamaged feelings.<br>     未毁坏的核反应堆；未受伤害的感情<br>'),(9794,'read','read','read','reading','','读,阅读,看懂,理解',' I can read French but I can\'t speak it.<br>     我能看懂法文但不会说。<br>\n The teacher read the poem to the class.<br>     老师给全班同学朗诵这首诗歌。<br>'),(9795,'readability','','','','','可读性',''),(9796,'readable','','','','','a. 值得一读的,易读的,读起来津津有味的',' It is the combination of wit and political analysis that makes his articles so readable.<br>     他的生花妙笔与政治分析相得益彰, 使他的文章脍炙人口.<br>\n A readable story.<br>     一个可读性强的故事<br>'),(9797,'reader','','','','readers','n. 读物,读本,读者',' Open your German readers at page 28.<br>     把德语课本翻到第28页。<br>\n We have received many letters on this subject from our readers.<br>     关于这个题目我们收到了很多读者的来信。<br>'),(9798,'readership','','','','','n. (某一报刊杂志等的)读者们',' The Daily Echo has a readership of over ten million.<br>     《每日回声报》拥有读者逾一千万人。<br>\n The paper has a wide readership.<br>     该报拥有广泛的读者。<br>'),(9799,'readily','','','','','ad. 不迟疑地,迅速地,轻易地',' He readily promised to help.<br>     他欣然答应帮忙。<br>\n They can readily be brought anywhere.<br>     它们易于携带。<br>'),(9800,'readiness','','','','','n. 预备,准备,敏捷',' The defences are kept in readiness for any enemy attack.<br>     防御工事已筑好，准备对付敌人进攻。<br>\n She shows great readiness to learn.<br>     她表现出强烈的学习愿望。<br>'),(9801,'reading','','','','readings','a. 阅读的<br>\nn. 阅读',' He is a man of wide reading.<br>     他是一个博览群书的人。<br>\n Reading occupies most of my free time.<br>     阅读占去了我大部分的闲暇时间。<br>'),(9802,'readjust','readjusted','readjusted','readjusting','','vi. 再调整',' It\'s hard to readjust (oneself) to life in Britain after working abroad.<br>     在国外工作之後, 很难重新适应英国的生活.<br>\n You need time to readjust (to living alone).<br>   