'','','','refractories','a. 不听话的,执拗的,难治疗的',' The state or quality of being stubborn or refractory.<br>     顽固，倔强顽固、固执或倔强的状态或性质<br>'),(10040,'refrain','','','','','n. 重复,叠句,副歌<br>\nv. 节制,避免,制止',' Let\'s hope they will refrain from hostile actions.<br>     希望他们不采取敌对行动。<br>\n I carefully refrained from looking at him.<br>     我留意着避免朝他看。<br>'),(10041,'refresh','refreshed','refreshed','refreshing','','v. 使...生气蓬勃,提起精神,恢复精神',' I refreshed myself with a cup of coffee.<br>     我喝了一杯咖啡给自己提提神。<br>\n Let me refresh your memory with some fact.<br>     我来提几件事帮你恢复记忆吧。<br>'),(10042,'refreshing','','','','','a. 使清爽的,有精神的,爽快的',' There is nothing as refreshing as lemon tea.<br>     什麽都不如柠檬茶那样提神.<br>\n After a refreshing nap, Mr Adams was again his own man.<br>     亚当斯先生睡了个好午觉，又恢复了精神。<br>'),(10043,'refreshment','','','','refreshments','n. 点心,提神之事物,精神爽快',' They came into the room for some refreshment.<br>     他们进屋吃点东西。<br>\n Refreshments will be available all day long so just help yourself when you\'re hungry.<br>     点心与饮料将全天供应，你们饿时只管随便享用。<br>'),(10044,'refrigerate','refrigerated','refrigerated','refrigerating','','v. 冷藏,使冷<br>\nvt. 冷冻,冷藏',''),(10045,'refrigerator','','','','refrigerators','n. 冰箱',' Mary put a lot of food in the refrigerator.<br>     玛利把许多吃的放在冰箱里了。<br>\n The boys made away with the contents of the refrigerator.<br>     男孩子们把冰箱中的食物吃得精光。<br>'),(10046,'refuel','refueled','refueled','refueling','','v. 补给燃料',''),(10047,'refuge','refuged','refuged','refuging','refuges','n. 避难(处),庇护(所)<br>\nv. 庇护,避难(所)',' A small cave was the only refuge from the cold.<br>     小洞穴是唯一的避寒处。<br>\n It is a classic sanctuary in which the rationalist fancy may take refuge.<br>     这是一所古雅的圣殿，理性主义者可以躲在其中。<br>'),(10048,'refugee','','','','refugees','n. 难民',' The government has set two refugee camps.<br>     政府已经建了两个难民营。<br>\n There are many refugees from that country.<br>     有许多来自那个国家的难民。<br>'),(10049,'refulgence','','','','','n. 辉煌,光亮',''),(10050,'refulgent','','','','','a. 辉煌的,灿烂的',''),(10051,'refund','','','','','n. 偿还<br>\nv. 付还,偿还借款,换回新公债',' I\'d like a refund.<br>     我想要退款。<br>\n She demand a refund.<br>     她要求退款。<br>'),(10052,'refurbish','refurbished','refurbished','refurbishing','','v. 再磨光,刷新',' The flat will be refurbished for the new tenants.<br>     这套房间将重新粉刷以接纳新房客.<br>'),(10053,'refusal','','','','refusals','n. 拒绝',' He made a refusal of her invitation.<br>     他拒绝了她的邀请。<br>\n We interpreted his silence as a refusal.<br>     我们认为他的沉默是拒绝的表示。<br>'),(10054,'refuse','','','','','n. 废物,垃圾<br>\nvi. 不愿,拒绝<br>\nvt. 拒绝',' He asked me to marry him but I refused.<br>     他向我求婚，但我拒绝了。<br>\n We were refused permission to enter.<br>     我们被拒之门外。<br>'),(10055,'refutation','','','','','n. 辩驳,反驳',' A person engaged in or inclined to controversy, argument, or refutation.<br>     辩论者；争辩者从事或喜欢争辩、辩论或驳斥的人<br>'),(10056,'refute','refuted','refuted','refuting','','v. 驳斥,反驳',' I was able to refute his argument.<br>     我能驳倒他的论点。<br>\n As for the Flat Earth theory, I believe I could refute it.<br>     至于地平学说，我相信我能驳斥它。<br>'),(10057,'regain','regained','regained','regaining','','v. 恢复,重回,复得',' He regained his health after the operation.<br>     手术后他恢复了健康。<br>\n When will the patient regain his consciousness?<br>     这个病人什么时候恢复知觉？<br>'),(10058,'regal','','','','','a. 帝王的,适于帝王的',' The regal lady had made a deep impression on him.<br>     那位雍容华贵的妇人给他留下了深刻的印象。<br>\n Royal or imperial; regal.<br>     贵族或皇室的；帝王的<br>'),(10059,'regale','regaled','regaled','regaling','','vt. 盛情招待<br>\nn. 款待',' She regaled us with an account of her school-days.<br>     她讲她上学时的往事把我们逗得不亦乐乎.<br>'),(10060,'regard','regarded','regarded','regarding','regards','n. 关心,注意,尊敬<br>\nv. 视为,注意,和...有关',' She is generally regarded as one of the best writers in the country.<br>     人们普遍认为她是该国最优秀的作家之一。<br>\n She regarded him thoughtfully.<br>     她若有所思地看着他。<br>'),(10061,'regarding','','','','','prep. 关于,至于',' I know nothing regarding the future.<br>     我对未来一无所知。<br>\n She said nothing regarding your request.<br>     她对你的要求只字不提。<br>'),(10062,'regardless','','','','','a. 不管,不注意,不顾',' All our proposals were rejected, regardless of their merits.<br>     我们所有的建议都遭到拒绝，不管这些建议的价值如何。<br>\n They decorated the house regardless of cost.<br>     他们不惜工本装修这栋房子。<br>'),(10063,'regardless of','','','','','不顾,不惜',' They decorated the house regardless of cost.<br>     他们不惜工本装修这栋房子。<br>\n She is determined to do regardless of all consequences.<br>     她不顾一切后果，决心这样做。<br>'),(10064,'regards','','','','','n. 问候,致意',' Should you happen to see him, please give him my regards.<br>     如果你碰巧见到他，请代我向他致意。<br>\n Should you see him, please give him my regards.<br>     如果你见到他，请代我向他致意。<br>'),(10065,'regatta','','','','regattas','n. 赛舟会',''),(10066,'regency','','','','regencies','n. 摄政统治,摄政期间',' Dave Barber, a bartender at Lexington\'s Hyatt Regency Hotel, said:\"I think she has definitely become one of the little people now. Just deserts. I don\'t know if the judge and the jury took that into account, but the man upstairs did.\"<br>     在莱克辛顿大道上的凯悦大酒店一位调酒师巴伯说，“我看她现在肯定成了一个小人物了。罪有应得。不知道法官和陪审员会不会把那句话考虑进去，可是上天有眼。”<br>'),(10067,'regenerate','regenerated','regenerated','regenerating','','vt. 再生(回收,革新)<br>\na. 再生的(更新的,革新的)',' The party soon regenerated under her leadership.<br>     该党在她的领导下很快焕然一新.<br>\n Their aim is to regenerate British industry.<br>     他们的目的是复兴英国的工业.<br>'),(10068,'regeneration','','','','','n. 再生,重建',''),(10069,'regenerative','','','','','a. 再生的,更生的,更新的',''),(10070,'regent','','','','regents','n. 摄政者,摄政,评议员<br>\na. 摄政的',' The regent carried out an advanced system in his country.<br>     摄政者在他的国家推行了一套先进的制度。<br>\n His address be248 regent street, right?<br>     他的住址是摄政街284号，对吗？<br>'),(10071,'reggae','','','','','n. 瑞格舞（西印度群岛的一种舞蹈及舞曲）',''),(10072,'regime','','','','regimes','n. 政体,制度<br>\nv. 严格抵制管辖',' Things will change under the new regime.<br>     在新政权下，事情将会发生变化。<br>\n The people have been kept down for years by a brutal regime.<br>     人民多年遭受野蛮制度压迫.<br>'),(10073,'regimen','','','','','n. 养生法,生活规则',''),(10074,'regiment','','','','','n. 团,多数,管理<br>\nv. 组织,编成团,统制',' Teenagers don\'t like being regimented.<br>     十几岁的青少年不喜欢被严格管教。<br>\n His son is a soldier in a cavalry regiment.<br>     他的儿子是骑兵团的一名战士。<br>'),(10075,'regimental','','','','','a. 团的',' The regimental mascot is a goat.<br>     这个团的吉祥物是山羊.<br>\n The regimental band triumphantly piped the soldiers in.<br>     团部的乐队用风笛奏起凯歌，迎入士兵。<br>'),(10076,'regimentation','','','','','n. 严格控制,纪律',''),(10077,'region','','','','regions','n. 地区,地域,地带',' Her motherland is in the tropical region.<br>     她的祖国位于热带地区。<br>\n The capital of Swaziland, in the northwest part of the country. It is a commercial center for an agricultural region. Population, 33,000.<br>     姆巴巴纳斯威士兰首都，位于该国的西北部。是农业区的商业中心。人口33，000<br>'),(10078,'regional','','','','','a. 地区的,局部的',' A regional dialect or language that becomes the standard language over a wider area, losing its most extreme local features.<br>     共通语一种地区方言或语言，它成为广大地区的通用语言而失去了最显著的地方特征<br>\n Close analysis of sales figures showed clear regional variations.<br>     对销售额的仔细分析显示出明显的地区差别。<br>'),(10079,'regionalize','regionalized','regionalized','regionalizing','','v. 使区域化',''),(10080,'register','registered','registered','registering','registers','v. 记录,登记,注册,挂号<br>\nn. 暂存器,记录,登记簿',' The car was registered in my name.<br>     汽车是用我的名字登记注册的。<br>\n Each class has a register of 50 students.<br>     每班有50名学员注册。<br>'),(10081,'registered','','','','','a. 注册的,登记过的,记名的<br>\nvbl. 注册',' The car was registered in my name.<br>     汽车是用我的名字登记注册的。<br>\n Now so many football clubs are registered with the football association.<br>     当今有那么多的足球俱乐部在足协登记注册。<br>'),(10082,'registered mail','','','','','挂号信[美国以外]',''),(10083,'registrar','','','','','n. 记录者,登记者,登记官员',' You can obtain the application from the registrar.<br>     你可以向注册人员索取申请书。<br>'),(10084,'registration','','','','registrations','n. 登记,注册',' What\'s your company\'s registration number in customs?<br>     你们公司的海关注册号码是多少？<br>\n The registration of students for an examination has been over.<br>     学生的考试登记已经结束了。<br>'),(10085,'registry','','','','registries','n. 记入,登记,登记名册',''),(10086,'regression','','','','','n. 复原,逆行,退步',''),(10087,'regressive','','','','','a. 退步的,退化的',' A type of schizophrenia, usually starting at puberty, characterized by foolish mannerisms, senseless laughter, delusions, hallucinations, and regressive behavior.<br>     青春期痴呆一种精神分裂症，通常始发于青春期，其特征为举止痴呆、傻笑、妄想、幻觉以及退化的举止<br>'),(10088,'regret','regretted','regretted','regretting','regrets','n. 遗憾,后悔,抱歉<br>\nv. 为...感到遗憾,后悔,惋惜',' We informed her with regret of our decision.<br>     我们遗憾地把我们的决定通知她。<br>\n She immediately regretted her decision.<br>     她做出决定后立即感到后悔。<br>'),(10089,'regretful','','','','','a. 惋惜的,遗憾的,哀惜的',' His decision is made us feeling regretful.<br>     他的决定令人感到遗憾。<br>'),(10090,'regretfully','','','','','ad. 遗憾地',' I very regretfully tell you, and your examination is failed.<br>     我很遗憾地告诉你，你考试不及格。<br>'),(10091,'regrettable','','','','','a. 可叹的,可惜的,抱歉的',' It is regrettable that few people shall walk today because of the development of traffic facilities.<br>     由于交通设施的发展，现在很少人愿意步行，这是很可惜的。<br>\n It\'s regrettable that you diddled away the whole afternoon.<br>     真可惜，你把整个下午浪费掉了。<br>'),(10092,'regular','','','','regulars','a. 有规律的,有规则的,整齐的,正规的',' A cube is a regular solid.<br>     立方体是正多面体。<br>\n He has very regular features.<br>     他五官端正。<br>'),(10093,'regularity','','','','regularities','n. 有规则,匀整,调和',' Regularity ought to be observed, as regularity is very conducive to health.<br>     生活应遵守规律，因为规律对健康有益。<br>\n They meet with great regularity.<br>     他们定期会面。<br>'),(10094,'regularly','','','','','ad. 定期地,有规律地',' I regularly get letters from people who have read my books.<br>     我经常收到读过我的书的读者的来信。<br>\n Take the medicine regularly three times a day.<br>     定时吃药，每天三次。<br>'),(10095,'regulate','regulated','regulated','regulating','','v. 有系统的管理,规定,调节',' Accidents sometimes happen even in the best regulated families.<br>     即便是在管理最好的家庭，事故有时也会发生的。<br>\n Your watch is always slow; it needs to be regulated.<br>     你的手表总是慢，需要校准一下。<br>'),(10096,'regulation','','','','regulations','n. 规则,规章',' She was fined for driving above the regulation speed.<br>     她因超速开车而被罚款。<br>\n The convocation held at four o\'clock had passed a regulation.<br>     四点举行的会议通过了一项规章制度。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (10097,'regulator','','','','','n. 调整者,取缔的人,调整器',' His defense, which seems credible on the evidence so far, is that the bank masked its skullduggery so completely that no regulator anywhere in the world could get a handle on it.<br>     他的辩词（根据目前证据似乎可信）是：银行把它的偷天换日的做法遮掩得天衣无逢，全世界任何地方的监管人员都无法掌握。<br>\n Despite all the fanfare by Federal regulators over recent bailouts of sick savings institutions, evidence is mounting that the deals are merely papering over the severe problems plaguing the industry.<br>     不论联邦监管人员最近如何大张旗鼓挽救一蹶不振的储蓄行业，越来越多的证据显示：政府所做仅仅在掩饰困扰该待业的严重问题。<br>'),(10098,'regulatory','','','','','a. 取缔的,统制的,调整的',' Complaint is referred to several regulatory body.<br>     投诉提交给好几个管理机构。<br>'),(10099,'regurgitate','regurgitated','regurgitated','regurgitating','','v. 使涌回,喷回,流回',' He\'s simply regurgitating stuff remembered from lectures.<br>     他只不过是照背讲义而已.<br>'),(10100,'rehabilitate','rehabilitated','rehabilitated','rehabilitating','','v. 恢复原状,使复权,使恢复<br>\n恢复名誉',' Punishment intended to rehabilitate or improve.<br>     处罚为复原或提高而进行的惩罚<br>'),(10101,'rehabilitation','','','','','n. 复原',' The study, theory, and practice of prison management and criminal rehabilitation.<br>     刑狱学一种对刑罚典狱和监狱管理的研究、实践和理论<br>'),(10102,'rehash','rehashed','rehashed','rehashing','','v. 重复谈论',' His answer is just a rehash version of my lecture.<br>     他的回答只不过是把我的讲义重复了一遍。<br>'),(10103,'rehearsal','','','','rehearsals','n. 排练,彩排<br>\nv. (使)排练,背诵',' The whole cast broke off for coffee in the middle of rehearsal.<br>     全体演员在排练休息时喝咖啡。<br>\n Carlin has been so out of it at rehearsal that week.<br>     卡琳那个星期彩排的时候一直醉得不省人事。<br>'),(10104,'rehearse','rehearsed','rehearsed','rehearsing','','v. 预演,排演,预先演习',' The actors were rehearsing the play.<br>     演员们一直在排练这出戏。<br>'),(10105,'reign','reigned','reigned','reigning','reigns','n. 执政,主权,王朝<br>\nv. 当政,统治,占优势',' He reigned over the country for forty years.<br>     他统治了这个国家四十年。<br>\n Silence reigned everywhere.<br>     万籁俱寂。<br>'),(10106,'reimburse','reimbursed','reimbursed','reimbursing','','v. 偿还',' All expenses will be reimbursed (to you).<br>     一切费用都能（给你）报销.<br>\n We will reimburse the customer for any loss or damage.<br>     我们愿赔偿顾客受到的一切损失和损害.<br>'),(10107,'reimbursement','','','','','n. 偿还(偿付,赔偿)',''),(10108,'rein','reined','reined','reining','reins','n. 缰绳,统驭,支配<br>\nv. 驾驭,以缰绳控制,统制',' This horse reins well.<br>     这匹马易于驾驭。<br>\n He pulled at the reins.<br>     他使劲拉住缰绳。<br>'),(10109,'reincarnate','','','','','v. 使化身,转生',''),(10110,'reincarnation','','','','','n. 再赋与肉体,化身,再生',''),(10111,'reindeer','','','','reindeer','n. 驯鹿',' Reindeer have branched antlers.<br>     驯鹿有带叉的角。<br>\n Any of several large reindeer native to northern North America.<br>     北美驯鹿原产于北美洲北部的一种巨大的驯鹿<br>'),(10112,'reinforce','reinforced','reinforced','reinforcing','','n. 加固物<br>\nv. 增援,加强<br>\nvt. 加强,增援',' Our defences must be reinforced against attack.<br>     我们必须加强防御设施以抵御进攻。<br>\n This evidence reinforces my view that he is a spy.<br>     这个证据证实了我认为他是间谍的这一看法。<br>'),(10113,'reinforcement','','','','reinforcements','n. 加强法(加强件)',' The soldiers held the fort desperately till reinforcement arrived.<br>     战士们拼死坚守阵地，直到援军到来。<br>\n An athletic supporter having a protective reinforcement of rigid plastic or metal.<br>     运动员护身一种运动员用的护身弹性织物，有用保护性的坚硬塑料或金属制成的加强层<br>'),(10114,'reinstate','reinstated','reinstated','reinstating','','v. 恢复(原职)<br>\nvt. 使恢复原有的职位',' His supporters failed in their attempt to reinstate the President in the White House.<br>     他的支持者试图使总统重新入主白宫的努力失败了。<br>'),(10115,'reintegrate','reintegrated','reintegrated','reintegrating','','v. 再使完整,恢复,重建',''),(10116,'reiterate','reiterated','reiterated','reiterating','','v. 反覆地说,反覆地做',' The captain reiterated the command to us.<br>     上尉对我们重申了那项命令。<br>\n The teacher reiterates that rule.<br>     老师重申了那条规则。<br>'),(10117,'reject','','','','','n. 被拒之人,不合格品,不及格者<br>\nv. 拒绝,驳回,丢弃',' The supermarket rejected all spotted apples.<br>     超级市场丢弃了所有的烂苹果。<br>\n The factory sells some of its better rejects cheaply, but it throws most of the rejects away.<br>     这家公司廉价出售略好一些的次品，但将大多数次品丢弃。<br>'),(10118,'rejection','rejected','rejected','','rejections','n. 拒绝,被弃,被抛弃的实例',' Her proposal met with continual rejections.<br>     她的建议一再遭到拒绝。<br>\n The rejection of their pay claim was given a less than rhapsodic reception by the miners.<br>     矿工要求提高工资遭到拒绝而甚为恼火.<br>'),(10119,'rejoice','rejoiced','rejoiced','rejoicing','','v. 使...欢喜,高兴',' We rejoiced at the good news.<br>     我们为这个好消息而高兴。<br>\n They all rejoiced to hear the happy news.<br>     他们都很乐于听到这个令人高兴的消息。<br>'),(10120,'rejoicing','','','','rejoicings','n. 欣喜,高兴,欢欣之事<br>\nvbl. 使...欢喜,高兴,庆祝',' \"Yes, \" I said, rejoicing with him.<br>     \"是的。\"我真替他高兴。<br>\n The good news rejoiced the cockles of my heart.<br>     这好消息使我从心坎里感到高兴。<br>'),(10121,'rejoin','','','','','vt. 使再结合, 再加入, 再回答<br>\nvi. 重新聚集, 回答, 答辩',' You\'re wrong!\' she rejoined.<br>     ｀你错了!＇她答道.<br>\n \"I\'ll have you both licked when I get out, that I will, \" rejoined the boy, beginning to snivel. \"Two can play at that game, mind you, \" said Tom.<br>     \"等我走出学校，我要叫人把你们俩狠狠揍一顿，我一定要，\"那孩子回答说，开始哭鼻子。\"你叫人，我们也会叫人，你不要忘记。\"汤姆说。<br>'),(10122,'rejoinder','','','','','n. 回答',' `No!\' was his curt rejoinder.<br>     他草率地回答了一声｀不!＇<br>'),(10123,'rejuvenate','rejuvenated','rejuvenated','rejuvenating','','v. 使...年轻,使...恢复精神',''),(10124,'rekindle','rekindled','rekindled','rekindling','','v. 重新点燃',' Nothing could rekindle her extinct passion.<br>     她激情已逝, 无从心回意转.<br>'),(10125,'relapse','relapsed','relapsed','relapsing','relapses','n. 复旧,故态复萌,再发<br>\nv. 故态复萌,再陷邪道,再度堕落',''),(10126,'relate','related','related','relating','','v. 讲,叙述,使联系,有关系',' Children need to learn to relate to other children.<br>     孩子们应该学会与其他孩子友好相处。<br>\n These two events were related to each other.<br>     这两个事件相互有联系。<br>'),(10127,'related','','','','','a. 有关系的,有关联的<br>\nv. 讲,有关系<br>\nvbl. 讲,有关系',' A variable so related to another that for each value assumed by one there is a value determined for the other.<br>     应变量，函数一个与他量有关联的变量，这一量中的任何一值都能在他量中找到对应的固定值<br>\n We are nearly related.<br>     我们是至亲。<br>'),(10128,'relation','','','','relations','n. 关系,家人,亲戚,叙述,陈述',' Their relationship has lasted many years.<br>     他们的感情已经有很多年了。<br>\n He is a near relation of mine.<br>     他是我的一个近亲。<br>'),(10129,'relational','','','','','关系的,相关的',''),(10130,'relations','','','','','n. 交往,事务',' Those two countries have broken off diplomatic relations again.<br>     那两个国家再次终止了交往。<br>\n His relations with his clients were also cut and dried, very little personal feeling could in the nature of things come into them.<br>     他与顾客的关系是事务性的，理所当然不可能跟他们之间有多少个人感情。<br>'),(10131,'relationship','','','','relationships','n. 关系,关联',' Their relationship has lasted many years.<br>     他们的感情已经有很多年了。<br>\n The relationship between them is being improved.<br>     他们之间的关系正在改善。<br>'),(10132,'relative','','','','relatives','a. 相对的,比较的<br>\nn. 亲戚,亲属',' The teacher asked me some questions relative to my paper.<br>     老师问了我一些和我的论文有关的问题。<br>\n They are now living in relative comfort.<br>     他们现在过着比较舒适的生活。<br>'),(10133,'relative to','','','','','a. 关于(相对于)',' The dynamics of bodies moving relative to gases, especially the interaction of moving objects with the atmosphere.<br>     空气动力学相对于气体的物体移动，特别是移动物体与大气相互作用的动力学<br>\n The orientation of a spacecraft relative to its direction of motion.<br>     飞行姿态宇宙飞船相对于其飞行方向所处的位置<br>'),(10134,'relatively','','','','','ad. 比较地,相对地',' Relatively speaking, it\'s not important.<br>     相对来说，那并不重要。<br>\n The exam was relatively easy.<br>     这次考试比较容易。<br>'),(10135,'relativity','','','','','n. 相对论',' Not everyone can understand Einstein\'s Theory of Relativity.<br>     不是每个人都能读懂爱因斯坦的相对论的。<br>\n Einstein\'s theory of relativity.<br>     爱因斯坦的相对论。<br>'),(10136,'relax','relaxed','relaxed','relaxing','','v. 放松,松懈,松弛',' His muscles relaxed.<br>     他的肌肉松弛了。<br>\n The music will help to relax you.<br>     音乐会使你感到轻松。<br>'),(10137,'relaxation','','','','relaxations','n. 松弛,放松,减轻',' Would you like to have some relaxation after swimming?<br>     游完泳后你愿意放松一下吗？<br>\n Fishing is his favorite relaxation.<br>     他最喜爱的消遣是钓鱼。<br>'),(10138,'relaxed','','','','','v. 放松(缓和,松懈)<br>\na. 松懈的',' An informal gathering of friends; a relaxed, informal manner.<br>     朋友们的非正式聚会；一种放松的、随便的方式<br>\n She\'s a bit too knowing for me to feel relaxed with her.<br>     她很有点世故, 和她相处我觉得不自在.<br>'),(10139,'relaxing','','','','','a. 令人感到轻松的',' I find stamp collecting relaxing and it takes my mind off my work.<br>     我觉得集邮是一种休息，因为它可以使我的注意力从工中移去。<br>\n His muscles relaxed.<br>     他的肌肉松弛了。<br>'),(10140,'relay','relayed','relayed','relaying','','vt. 中继(用继电器控制,接替)<br>\nn. 继电器(转播,备用品,替班人)',' Scientists have set up two kinds of relay stations. One kind is on the earth, the other is a satellite placed in space around the earth.<br>     科学家们已建立了两种中继站，一种在地球上，而另一种是放在地球周围太空中的卫星上。<br>\n The moving part of an electromagnetic device such as a relay, buzzer, or loudspeaker.<br>     电枢电磁装置的移动部分，如继电器，蜂音器或扬声器<br>'),(10141,'relay race','','','','','接力赛',' A relay race is a race in which each member of each team runs part of the distance.<br>     接力赛跑是各队的每个成员各跑部分路程的一种赛跑。<br>\n Six teams competed in yesterday\'s relay race.<br>     六个队参加了昨天的接力赛。<br>'),(10142,'release','released','released','releasing','releases','n. 释放,让渡,发行<br>\nv. 释放,让与,准予发表',' He was released from prison after serving his sentence.<br>     他刑满获释。<br>\n The new film will be released next month.<br>     这部新的电影下个月发行。<br>'),(10143,'relegate','relegated','relegated','relegating','','v. 命令撤离,降低地位,贬谪',' Will Spurs be relegated to the third division?<br>     斯珀尔斯队会降为丙级队吗?<br>\n Mr. Taylor relegate his project to his son after he have ret.<br>     泰勒先生退休后把他的事业移转给儿子。<br>'),(10144,'relent','relented','relented','relenting','','v. 变宽厚,变温和,动怜悯之心',' At first she threatened to dismiss us all, but later she relented.<br>     起初她威胁要解雇我们所有的人，但是后来她态度软化了。<br>\n The police will not relent in their fight against crime.<br>     警方在跟犯罪分子的斗争中决不手软。<br>'),(10145,'relentless','','','','','a. 无情的,冷酷的,残酷的',' He was relentless in demanding repayment of the debt.<br>     他冷酷无情地要求偿还那笔债。<br>'),(10146,'relentlessly','','','','','ad. 无情地, 残酷地',' He drives the team relentlessly.<br>     他无情地鞭策全队苦练。<br>\n The sun glared down relentlessly.<br>     太阳毫不留情地发出强烈的光。<br>'),(10147,'relevance','','','','','n. 中肯,适当,关联,相关性',' I really can\'t see what relevance is has, I\'m afraid.<br>     恐怕我确实看不出那有什么关系。<br>\n Having logical, precise relevance to the matter at hand.<br>     有关系的，相关的对即将到来的事情有合乎逻辑且明确的关联<br>'),(10148,'relevancy','','','','','n. 切题,中肯',''),(10149,'relevant','','','','','a. 相关的,切题的,中肯的',' His nationality isn\'t relevant to whether he\'s a good teacher.<br>     他的国籍与他是否是位好老师无关。<br>\n She gobbled up all the relevant information.<br>     她如饥似渴地收集一切有关的信息。<br>'),(10150,'reliability','','','','','n. 可靠性',' Performance is less important than reliability in a car.<br>     汽车的可靠性比其机械性能更重要.<br>\n An experiment was made to check up on the reliability of certain criteria.<br>     已经进行了一项实验以检查某些标准的可靠性。<br>'),(10151,'reliable','','','','','a. 可靠的',' I don\'t think he is a reliable man.<br>     我认为他不是一个可靠的人。<br>\n The news comes from a reliable source.<br>     这消息来自可靠的来源。<br>'),(10152,'reliance','','','','reliances','n. 信赖,依靠',' Don\'t place too much reliance on his advice.<br>     别太相信他的意见。<br>\n Reliance on something in the future; hope.<br>     期待，期望对某事未来的信赖；希望<br>'),(10153,'relic','','','','relics','n. 神圣的遗物,遗迹,纪念物',' This stone axe is a relic of ancient times.<br>     这把石斧是古代的遗物。<br>\n This ruined bridge is a relic of the Civil War.<br>     这座毁坏的桥是南北战争时的遗迹。<br>'),(10154,'relics','','','','','遗物，遗迹，遗产，遗体',' In its spacious halls are displayed over8000 priceless relics.<br>     在它宽敞的大厅里，展出了8000多件珍贵文物。<br>\n The museum has many immemorial cultural relics.<br>     该博物馆收藏了很多极其古老的文物。<br>'),(10155,'relict','','','','','a. 残存的',''),(10156,'relief','','','','','n. 减轻,解除 救济',' It was a great relief to find that my family was all safe.<br>     看到我的家人安然无恙，我感到极大的欣慰。<br>\n The coach was full so a relief was put on.<br>     长途汽车已满员，所以增开了一辆。<br>'),(10157,'relieve','relieved','relieved','relieving','','v. 减轻,救济,解除',' The general was relieved of his command.<br>     将军被解除了指挥权。<br>\n He was relieved of his watch.<br>     他的表被偷走了。<br>'),(10158,'relieved','','','','','放心的',' The general was relieved of his command.<br>     将军被解除了指挥权。<br>\n He was relieved of his watch.<br>     他的表被偷走了。<br>'),(10159,'religion','','','','religions','n. 宗教;宗教信仰',' Politics and religion are daily topics of conversation.<br>     政治和宗教是人们平常交谈的主要话题。<br>\n There are many religions in the world.<br>     世界上有许多种宗教信仰。<br>'),(10160,'religious','','','','religious','a. 宗教的',' She is very religious and goes to church three times a week.<br>     她非常虔诚，每周去教堂三次。<br>\n These two countries had three religious wars in twenty years.<br>     这两个国家在20年里发生过三次宗教上的冲突。<br>'),(10161,'relinquish','relinquished','relinquished','relinquishing','','v. 放弃,放手,让渡',' She relinquished possession of the house to her sister.<br>     她把房子的所有权让给了她妹妹。<br>\n I had relinquished all hope that she was alive.<br>     我已经放弃了她还活着的一切希望。<br>'),(10162,'relinquishment','','','','','n. 撤回,放弃,停止',''),(10163,'relish','relished','relished','relishing','relishes','n. 滋味,爱好,调味品<br>\nv. 品味,喜欢,有...味道',' His wife won\'t relish having to wash all those dishes.<br>     他的妻子不会喜欢洗这一大堆碟子的。<br>\n He drank up the wine with relish.<br>     他津津有味地把酒喝光了。<br>'),(10164,'relive','relived','relived','reliving','','vt. 再生(重温)',' I relive that fateful day over and over in my mind.<br>     我在思想上不断地重温著那决定不幸命运的日子。<br>\n I wish I could put the clock back and relive my schooldays; I regret not having tried harder and passed more exams.<br>     我希望时光能够倒退回去，我可以重新去过学生时代的生活。我后悔当初不够努力，没有通过更多的考试。<br>'),(10165,'reload','reloaded','reloaded','reloading','','再装入',''),(10166,'relocate','relocated','relocated','relocating','','v. 重新装置,再配置,放在新地方',' The management decided to relocate