的',' Your presence is requested at the meeting.<br>     请你务必出席会议。<br>\n It is requested that all members be present at the party.<br>     全体会员都被要求出席这次晚会。<br>'),(10335,'requiem','','','','','n. 安魂曲,安灵曲',' But to Mozart--- at that time sick, depressed, haunted by the thought of death--- the stranger seemed a messenger from the other world, bidding him write his own requiem.<br>     但是，对莫扎特来说——此时他身体不好，情绪低落，整天想着死——这个陌生人无异是从另一个世界派来的使者，来命令他写下他自己的安魂曲。<br>'),(10336,'require','required','required','requiring','','v. 需要,要求',' The floor requires washing.<br>     这地板该洗了。<br>\n All passengers are required to show their tickets.<br>     所有乘客都必须出示车票。<br>'),(10337,'required','','','','','必需的',' Being a substance that is required for normal functioning but does not need to be included in the diet because of the body\'s ability to synthesize it from other nutrients.<br>     （氨基酸）非必需的是正常的运转所需要的物质的，但因为机体有从其它营养成分合成它的能力，因此不需要被包括在日常的食物中的<br>\n The ships required the protection of naval and air power.<br>     船只本身需要海军和空军的保护。<br>'),(10338,'requirement','','','','requirements','n. 要求',' Candidates who fail to meet these requirements will not be admitted to the University.<br>     不符合这些要求的考生不能上这所大学。<br>\n The refugees\' main requirements are food and shelter.<br>     难民的主要必需品是食物和住所。<br>'),(10339,'requisite','','','','requisites','a. 必要的,需要的<br>\nn. 必需品',' I must buy some toilet requisites.<br>     我必须买些卫生间必需品。<br>\n She expect to achieve the requisite two-thirds majority for nomination.<br>     她期望得到获得提名所必需的三分之二多数。<br>'),(10340,'requisition','requisitioned','requisitioned','requisitioning','requisitions','n. 请求,强求,命令<br>\nv. 强制使用,徵用,命令徵用',' The town hall was requisitioned as army headquarters.<br>     市政厅徵用作了军队的指挥部。<br>\n The army requisition all the truck to carry supplies.<br>     军队征用了所有卡车，目的是为了运输车需品。<br>'),(10341,'requital','','','','','n. 报酬,还礼,报仇',' One\'s due, reward, or punishment; requital.<br>     报偿，报应一个人应得报酬、报答、惩罚；补偿，赔偿<br>\n A full requital of his striving pain.<br>     这是对他艰苦努力的