 what they paid.<br>     投机者多得很，他们买下土地，搁置一两个月后又以双倍的价格卖出去。<br>\n Speculators are thick on the ground-literally speaking. They buy up land, sit on it for a year of two and resell for several times what they paid.<br>     不夸张地说，投机商多得很，他们买下土地，然后放它个一两年，再以几倍于以前的价格卖出去。<br>'),(10354,'resemblance','','','','resemblances','n. 相像',' There is a degree of resemblance between the two boys.<br>     这两个男孩有某些相似之处。<br>\n Your story shows little resemblance to the facts.<br>     你说的与事实相去甚远。<br>'),(10355,'resemble','resembled','resembled','resembling','','v. 相似,类似,像',' The situation closely resembles that of Europe in 1940.<br>     这种形势与1940年的欧洲十分相似。<br>\n She resembles her sister in appearance but not in character.<br>     她和她姐姐外貌相似，但性格不同。<br>'),(10356,'resend','resent','resent','resending','','再发送',' I resent having to get his permission for everything I do.<br>     我讨厌做每件事都要得到他的许可。<br>\n I bitterly resent his attempts to interfere in my work.<br>     我非常讨厌他企图干涉我的工作。<br>'),(10357,'resent','resented','resented','resenting','','v. 愤恨,憎恶,怨恨',' I resent having to get his permission for everything I do.<br>     我讨厌做每件事都要得到他的许可。<br>\n I bitterly resent his attempts to interfere in my work.<br>     我非常讨厌他企图干涉我的工作。<br>'),(10358,'resentful','','','','','a. 不满(对...产生反感)',' Resentful and rebellious, especially against authority.<br>     不满的，造反的，尤反对政府当局<br>\n He is resentful at the way he has been treated.<br>     他对所受的待遇感到忿恨。<br>'),(10359,'resentment','','','','resentments','n. 怨恨,愤恨',' He has a deep-seated resentment at the way he has been treated.<br>     他因受到如此对待而深怀怨恨。<br>\n The resentment festered in his mind.<br>     他心中的愤恨有增无减。<br>'),(10360,'reservation','','','','reservations','n. 预定',' Some members of the committee expressed reservations about the proposal.<br>     委员会一些成员对这项提议持保留态度。<br>\n His family are living in an Indian reservation.<br>     他全家都住在一个印第安居留地里。<br>'),(10361,'reserve','reserved','reserved','reserving','reserves','n. 预备品,贮存,预备舍<br>\nvt. 保留,预订,延期',' He still reserved his opinion on some points.<br>     在一些问题上，他仍然保留自己的意见。<br>\n Please reserve a seat for me.<br>     请为我预定一个座位。<br>'),(10362,'reserved','','','','','v. 保留(预定,推迟)<br>\na. 保留的(预订的,冷淡的,缄默)',' He still reserved his opinion on some points.<br>     在一些问题上，他仍然保留自己的意见。<br>\n She is not usually so reserved.<br>     她通常不如此缄默。<br>'),(10363,'reservoir','reservoired','reservoired','reservoiring','reservoirs','n. 水库,蓄水池',' The show is a veritable reservoir of new talent.<br>     这个演出真是新秀集萃。<br>\n They open the sluice gates of reservoir.<br>     他们打开水库的闸门。<br>'),(10364,'reset','reset','reset','resetting','','n. 重新设定,重新组合<br>\nv. 重新设定,重新放置,重新组合',''),(10365,'reshape','','','','','v. 改造,使成新的形状,打开新局面',''),(10366,'reshuffle','reshuffled','reshuffled','reshuffling','','v. 再洗牌,改组<br>\nvt. 改组',' It\'s amusing to watch members jockeying for the Prime Minister\'s attention prior to Cabinet reshuffle.<br>     看到政府官员在内阁改组之前耍弄花招以讨得首相欢心是很有趣的。<br>\n Who let out the details of the reshuffle in the department?<br>     是谁泄漏了部门重组的细节?<br>'),(10367,'reside','resided','resided','residing','','v. 住,居留,属于',' Memory has been shown to reside in some metals.<br>     已经证实，记忆存在于某些金属中。<br>\n This family has resided in this city for 60 years.<br>     这个家族住在本城已有60 年了。<br>'),(10368,'residence','','','','residences','n. 住处,住宅',' He married an English woman and took up his residence in London.<br>     他与一名英国女子结婚并且定居在伦敦。<br>\n They have a summer residence in the countryside.<br>     他们在乡间有夏季住宅。<br>'),(10369,'residency','','','','residencies','n. (美)高级专科住院实习(期)',''),(10370,'resident','','','','residents','a. 居住的<br>\nn. 居民',' The residents of the town are proud of its new library.<br>     该镇的居民都为镇上新建的图书馆感到自豪。<br>\n I have been resident in this hotel for two weeks.<br>     我已经在这家旅馆里住了两个星期了。<br>'),(10371,'residential','','','','','a. 住宅的,与居住有关的',' Gradually the surrounding farmland turned residential.<br>     周围的农田渐渐变成了住宅区。<br>\n A town of northeast Massachusetts, a primarily residential suburb of Boston. Population, 22,539.<