e your idea about him.<br>     你应该修改对他的看法。<br>'),(10547,'revision','','','','revisions','n. 校订,修正,修订本<br>\nn. 复习,重温',' Our budget needs drastic revision.<br>     我们的预算需作重大修改。<br>\n The catalogue is under revision.<br>     目录正在修订之中。<br>'),(10548,'revisit','revisited','revisited','revisiting','','v. 再访,重游,重临',''),(10549,'revitalization','','','','','n. 新生(复活,恢复元气)',''),(10550,'revitalize','revitalized','revitalized','revitalizing','','v. 使复活,使重新充满活力<br>\nvt. 使复兴,使苏醒,使复活,使恢复',' I think we have to revitalize our society.<br>     我觉得我们的社会需要新生。<br>'),(10551,'revival','','','','revivals','n. 复兴,复活,恢复精神',' Our economy is undergoing a revival.<br>     我们的经济正处于复苏阶段。<br>\n The patient had a speedy revival after her operation.<br>     那个女病人在手术后迅速康复。<br>'),(10552,'revive','revived','revived','reviving','','v. 使...生醒,复生,恢复精神',' The flowers will revive in water.<br>     这些花在水中会再活。<br>\n Interest in classic music has revived recently.<br>     近来对古典音乐的兴趣又浓厚起来。<br>'),(10553,'revocable','','','','','a. 可废除的',''),(10554,'revocation','','','','','n. 废弃,取消',''),(10555,'revokable','','','','','可取消的',''),(10556,'revoke','revoked','revoked','revoking','revokes','vt. 撤回(回想)<br>\nn. 取消(回想)',' The unreasonable rules were revoked.<br>     不合理的规则被废除了。<br>\n His driving licence was revoked after the crash.<br>     他撞车后驾驶执照被吊销了。<br>'),(10557,'revolt','revolted','revolted','revolting','revolts','n. 叛乱,反抗,反感<br>\nv. 叛乱,起反感,使...恶心',' Human nature revolts at such a crime.<br>     人性厌恶这样的罪行。<br>\n The colonists revolted against their British ruler.<br>     殖民地人民反抗他们的英国统治者。<br>'),(10558,'revolting','','','','','a. 背叛的,叛乱的,讨厌的',' His feet smelt revolting.<br>     他双脚散发的气味让人恶心.<br>\n He was the prime mover in the revolt against the government.<br>     他是这场反政府叛乱的煽动者.<br>'),(10559,'revoltingly','','','','','ad. 令人作呕地,使人反感地',''),(10560,'revolution','','','','revolutions','n. 革命,旋转,转数',' Most countries have had revolutions aganist the government.<br>     大多数国家发生过反对政府的革命。<br>\n The act of turning or the condit