d','reworking','','重做,改写',''),(10573,'rewrite','rewrote','rewritten','rewriting','','n. 重写,改写<br>\nvt. 改写,重写',' I rewrote the article because it do not according with our policy.<br>     由于该文与我们的政策不符，我重新写了一遍。<br>'),(10574,'RFD','','','','','rural free delivery:邮件乡村地区免费递送',''),(10575,'rhapsodize','rhapsodized','rhapsodized','rhapsodizing','','v. 过份赞美',''),(10576,'rhapsody','','','','rhapsodies','n. 溢美之词,狂想曲',' The guests went into rhapsodies over the food.<br>     宾客对食物交口称赞.<br>'),(10577,'rhetoric','','','','','n. 修辞,华丽虚饰的语言,修辞学',' The sentence contains impassioned rhetoric.<br>     这个句子含有富有表现力的修辞。<br>\n I am tired of the empty rhetoric of politicians.<br>     我讨厌政客们的花言巧语。<br>'),(10578,'rhetorical','','','','','a. 修辞学的,符合修辞学的,修辞的',' An abrupt change within a sentence to a second construction inconsistent with the first, sometimes used for rhetorical effect; for example, I warned him that if he continues to drink, what will become of him?<br>     改变说法；错格句子中与第一个语法结构不一致的突然出现的第二个结构，有时用于修辞效果；例如，我警告过他，如果他继续喝酒的话将会有什么下场呢？<br>\n A statement or rhetorical discourse intended to give information about or an explanation of difficult material.<br>     讲解为了给…提供信息陈述或比喻性的说明，或对有难点的题材的解释<br>'),(10579,'rhetorical question','','','','','不必回答,只为加强语气及效果的反问',''),(10580,'rheumatism','','','','','n. 风湿症',' The patient is suffering from the rheumatism.<br>     这个病人受到风湿病的折磨。<br>\n She is afflicted with rheumatism.<br>     她为风湿症所苦。<br>'),(10581,'rheumy','','','','','a. 分泌粘液的',''),(10582,'Rhine','','','','','n. 莱因河[欧洲西部]',' A region and former duchy of central Germany north and east of the Main and Rhine rivers. The region became a duchy in1806 and was absorbed by Prussia in1866. Members of the original dynasty subsequently ruled Luxembourg and the Netherlands(as the house of Orange).<br>     拿骚一个地区，从前为中德的领地，位于美因河和莱茵河的北部和东部。该地区在1806年成为领地并于1866年被普鲁士接收。原先的王朝成员相继统治了卢森堡和荷兰（作为奥兰治的王室）<br>\n Where does this stream merge into the Rhine?<br>     这条小河在什么地方与莱茵河合流？<br>'),(10583,'rhinestone','','','','','n. 水晶之一种,人造钻石',' A small, glittering ornament, such as a rhinestone or a sequin, applied to fabric or a garment.<br>     亮片一种用于织物或服装上的闪闪发光的小饰物，比如像水晶或金属闪光片<br>'),(10584,'rhinitis','','','','','n. 鼻炎',''),(10585,'rhino','','','','rhino','n. 犀牛<br>\nn. <俚> 钱, 现金',''),(10586,'rhinoceros','','','','rhinoceros','n. 犀牛<br>\nn. (对受攻击、批评、侮辱等）麻木不仁',' The rhinoceros has one horn on its nose.<br>     犀牛鼻子上有一个角。<br>\n The game wardens tranquillized the rhinoceros with a drugged dart.<br>     猎物保护区管理员用麻醉射器让犀牛静了下来.<br>'),(10587,'Rhode Island','','','','','(美国州名)罗得岛',' A town of southeast Massachusetts near the Rhode Island border southwest of Boston. It was settled in1660. Population, 22,095.<br>     富兰克林美国曼彻斯特东南部一城镇，邻罗得岛边缘，位于波士顿西南部。1666年在此建立了殖民地。人口22，095<br>\n A town of north-central Rhode Island, a manufacturing suburb of Providence. Population, 24,907.<br>     约翰斯顿罗得岛州中北部城镇，位于普罗维登斯郊区，以制造业为主。人口24，907<br>'),(10588,'rhubarb','','','','rhubarbs','n. 大黄,大黄的叶柄,调味液之一种',' \"Won\'t you grow any fruit? \" \"No. only rhubarb, God\'s gift to Scotland and lazy gardeners.\"<br>     \"你们这里种水果吗？\"\"不种，只种大黄，这是上帝对对苏格兰人和懒人的恩宠。\"<br>'),(10589,'rhyme','rhymed','rhymed','rhyming','rhymes','n. 韵,押韵,韵文<br>\nv. 押韵',' The last two lines of this poem don\'t rhyme properly.<br>     这首诗的最后两行没有押好韵。<br>\n This nursery rhyme is very familiar to me.<br>     我对这首摇篮曲很熟悉。<br>'),(10590,'rhythm','','','','rhythms','n. 节奏,韵律',' He is trying to play the same tune in a different rhythm.<br>     他正试图用不同节奏演奏同一个曲子。<br>\n Stress and rhythm are important in speaking English.<br>     说英语时, 重音和节奏是很重要的.<br>'),(10591,'rhythmic','','','','','a. 间歇的(调和的)',' A foot of verse used in lyric poetry having two unstressed syllables flanked by the two rhythmic stresses marking the first and last syllables of the foot.<br>     扬抑抑扬格一种应用于抒情诗诗体中的音步，由两个轻音节夹在两个有节奏的重音之间构成，用于表示该音步的第一个和最后一个音节<br>\n The rhythmic stamping of the heels characteristic of Spanish flamenco dances.<br>     踢达舞西班牙弗拉曼柯舞中特有的有节奏地踏足<br>'),(10592,'rhythmical','','','','','a. 有节奏的,有韵律的',' A monotonous rhythmical drumbeat or similar sound.<br>     单调鼓声一种单调的有节奏的敲鼓声或类似的声音<br>\n The measured, rhythmical sound of verse; meter.<br>     韵律诗的节奏，韵律；音步<br>'),(10593,'rib','ribbed','ribbed','ribbing','ribs','n. 肋骨',' How many ribs does a man have?<br>     一个人有几条肋骨？<br>\n It is not true that woman is made from man\'s rib; she is really made from his funny bone.<br>     女人并非真的以男人的肋骨来造成的；其实，她是由男人的“笑骨”[尺骨]造成的。<br>'),(10594,'ribald','','','','','a. 说话猥亵的,下流的,卑贱的',' The chairman had to call the meeting to order after the ribald comments of one of the members caused uproar among the others.<br>     会议成员之一说的下流话在其他成员中引起了一阵骚动，主席只得叫大家遵守会议秩序。<br>\n A variety show characterized by broad ribald comedy, dancing, and striptease.<br>     粗俗的表演各种以下流粗俗的喜剧、舞蹈和脱衣舞为特征的表演<br>'),(10595,'ribbed','','','','','a. 呈肋状的,有罗纹的',' A soft, ribbed cloth of wool or a wool blend, usually used for dresses.<br>     罗纹织物一种羊毛的或羊毛混纺的柔软的、有罗纹的织物，一般用来制作女装<br>\n She was constantly ribbed about her accent.<br>     人家总拿她的口音开玩笑.<br>'),(10596,'ribbon','ribboned','ribboned','ribboning','ribbons','n. 缎带,色带,带状物<br>\nv. 用丝带装饰,撕碎',' Her hair was tied back with a black ribbon.<br>     她的头发用黑缎带扎在后面。<br>\n The old man wore an eyeglass attached to a piece of ribbon.<br>     那老人戴著单片眼镜，上面连结著一条丝带。<br>'),(10597,'rice','riced','riced','ricing','','n. 稻,饭,米',' He had some rice for supper.<br>     晚饭时他吃了一些米饭。<br>\n The peasants are harvesting rice in the field.<br>     农民们正在田野里收割稻子。<br>'),(10598,'rich','','','','','a. 富有的,浓厚的,贵重的',' He is a rich man.<br>     他是一个富有的人。<br>\n The country is rich in oil and coal.<br>     这个国家石油和煤的资源丰富。<br>'),(10599,'Richard','','','','','n. 理查',' Who\'s the girl standing behind Richard?<br>     站在理查德後面的那个姑娘是谁?<br>\n Late again, Richard? What\'s your alibi this time?<br>     理查德, 又迟到了? 这次你有什么藉口呢?<br>'),(10600,'riches','','','','','n. 房地产,丰富',' All his riches are of no good to him if he is so ill.<br>     如果他身体这么糟，那么他的所有财富对他毫无用处。<br>\n The more riches a fool hath, the greater fool he is.<br>     【谚】傻瓜越富越蠢。<br>'),(10601,'richly','','','','','ad. 富裕地,浓厚地',' He richly deserved the punishment he received.<br>     他受到的处罚是罪有应得。<br>\n Richly ornamented clothing; finery.<br>     华饰装饰华丽的衣物；华服<br>'),(10602,'Richmond','','','','','里士满(城市名)',''),(10603,'richness','','','','','n. 富裕,丰富,肥沃',' Thrift is the basement of richness.<br>     节约是富裕的基础。<br>\n The richness of the soil favored the growth of crops.<br>     土地的肥沃有利于运动员的生长。<br>'),(10604,'Rick','','','','','n. 干草堆<br>\nv. 堆成小屋形<br>\nn. 瑞克',' Rick often watched the boats returning to port in the late afternoon.<br>     瑞克常常看到小船在傍晚正回到港口。<br>\n Rick found a sure-enough nickel.<br>     里克发现一个纯正的镍币。<br>'),(10605,'rickets','','','','','n. 软骨病,英吉利病,驼背',''),(10606,'rickety','','','','','a. 患软骨病的,驼背的,摇摆的',' An old, rickety vehicle, especially a decrepit automobile or aircraft.<br>     破旧汽车，破旧飞机一种用久而破烂的交通工具，尤指破坏了的汽车或飞机<br>\n The ladder looks rather rickety; don\'t attempt to climb it unless you are sure you can do it with safety.<br>     这梯子看起来不怎么牢固，除非能确保安全，否则你就不要去爬。<br>'),(10607,'rickshaw','','','','','n. 人力车',''),(10608,'rid','rid','rid','ridding','','v. 免除,清除,使...获自由',' We will be glad to get rid of him.<br>     摆脱他，我们将很高兴。<br>\n The man rid himself of debt.<br>     他还清了债。<br>'),(10609,'ridden','','','','','ride 的过去分词',' Having ridden for some time, he put the horse about and headed for home.<br>     他骑了一段时间以后，掉转马头回家去了。<br>\n He is ridden by doubts.<br>     他为怀疑而苦恼。<br>'),(10610,'riddle','','','','','n. 谜,谜语<br>\nv. 解谜,出谜题',' The door was riddled with shots.<br>     门被子弹打得尽是窟窿。<br>\n He could not solve the riddle.<br>     他猜不出这个谜。<br>'),(10611,'ride','rode','ridden','riding','rides','n. 乘坐,乘车,搭便车<br>\nv. 骑,乘坐,克服',' Can you ride a bicycle?<br>     你会骑自行车吗？<br>\n The luxury model gives a smoother ride.<br>     坐这种豪华型汽车感觉很平稳。<br>'),(10612,'rider','','','','riders','n. 骑士,附件,扶手',' She is no rider.<br>     她不会骑马。<br>\n The rider forced his horse on through the storm.<br>     骑士迫使他的马在暴风雨中前进。<br>'),(10613,'ridge','ridged','ridged','ridging','ridges','n. 脊,山脊,山脉',' His forehead was ridged with anxiety.<br>     他的前额因焦虑而布满了皱纹。<br>\n The floor of the atlantic ridge in the middle from north to south.<br>     大西洋洋底在中部形成由北向南的海脊。<br>'),(10614,'ridicule','ridiculed','ridiculed','ridiculing','','n. 嘲笑,愚弄,笑柄<br>\nv. 嘲笑,嘲弄,愚弄',' To choose such a line of work is to invite ridicule.<br>     选择从事这个行业会惹人嘲笑。<br>\n Scornfully contemptuous ridicule; derision.<br>     嘲讽责备地鄙视可笑之事；嘲笑<br>'),(10615,'ridiculous','','','','','a. 荒谬的,可笑的',' What a ridiculous suggestion!<br>     多么荒唐的建议！<br>\n That fat woman looked ridiculous in her tight golden dress.<br>     那位胖妇人穿着金色的紧身礼服，显得滑稽可笑。<br>'),(10616,'ridiculousness','','','','','n. 荒谬(不合理)',''),(10617,'riding','','','','','n. 骑马',' Riding is her favorite occupation.<br>     骑马是她最喜欢的消遣。<br>\n Every Saturday Jean went riding on the village common.<br>     每周六琴在村里的公用草地上骑马。<br>'),(10618,'rife','','','','','a. 流行的,盛传的,非常多的',' Fraud, violence, war at home and abroad were rife.<br>     欺诈、暴力、对内对外的战争四处猖獗。<br>\n His thesis is rife with errors.<br>     他的学位论文错误连篇。<br>'),(10619,'rifle','','','','','n. 步枪<br>\nv. 洗劫,抢劫',' He was appointed captain of a company of rifles.<br>     他被任命为步枪连连长。<br>\n The soldier told us where the firing mechanism of a rifle is.<br>     那个士兵告诉我们哪儿是步枪的击发装置。<br>'),(10620,'rift','','','','','n. 裂口,隙缝,切口<br>\nv. 裂开,割开',' Healed the rift between us.<br>     弥补我们之间的裂痕<br>'),(10621,'rig','','','','','n. 装备,帆具,服装<br>\nv. 装配,装扮,垄断',' He looked rather out of place when he turned up in full ceremonial rig.<br>     当他穿着全套大礼服露面的时候，显得和整个场合很不协调。<br>\n They rigged the little boy out as a sailor.<br>     他们把小男孩打扮成水手模样。<br>'),(10622,'right','righted','righted','righting','rights','a. 对的,正确的<br>\nad. 对<br>\nint. 好<br>\nn. 权利,右<br>\nvt. 纠正<br>\nadv.恰恰,正好',' I have the right to ask for an explanation.<br>     我有权要求一个解释。<br>\n The Normans ruled England by right of conquest.<br>     诺曼人征服了英格兰成了统治者。<br>'),(10623,'right angle','','','','','直角',''),(10624,'right away','','','','','立刻,马上',' Did you get dressed right away?<br>     你马上就穿衣服了吗？<br>\n The storm will blow over right away.<br>     暴风雨很快就会平息。<br>'),(10625,'right off','','','','','立刻',' All that talk about abattoirs turned me right off!<br>     关於屠宰场的那些话让我十分恶心!<br>\n I go to bed at about eleven, and go right off to sleep.<br>     我大约在十一点上床，躺下就睡着了。<br>'),(10626,'righteous','','','','','a. 公正的,公义的,当然的',' He is a righteous young man.<br>     他是一个正直的年轻人。<br>\n The abode of righteous souls after death; heaven.<br>     善人灵魂安息的乐园正直的灵魂死后所住的地方；天堂<br>'),(10627,'righteousness','','','','','n. 正当,正义,正直',' We admire him for his righteousness.<br>     我们钦佩他的正直。<br>\n Some folks in this world spend their whole time hunting after righteousness and can not find any time to practice it.<br>     这世上有些人把整个时间花费于搜寻正义，却腾不出时间来付诸实践。<br>'),(10628,'rightful','','','','','a. 合法的,正直的,当然的',' What he said is a rightful claim.<br>     他所说的是正当的要求。<br>\n I am the rightful owner of this car.<br>     我是这辆新车的合法主人。<br>'),(10629,'right-hand','','','','','a. 右手的, 得力的',''),(10630,'right-handed','','','','','a. 用右手的, 向右旋地',''),(10631,'right-hander','','','','','n. 惯用右手的人',''),(10632,'rightly','','','','','ad. 端正地,正当地,正确地',' And if this something else is rightly chosen, if it is really attended by the illumination of another field of interest.<br>     假如你正确地选取了其他念头，假如这个念头的确受到别的领域的情趣的启迪。<br>\n Mr.Gorbachev and his reformist Kremlin allies are prepared to tolerate, even encourage, moderate nationalists who challenge central control and demand autonomy. But Moscow rightly feels that, in a polyglot country with102 different nationalities, ethnic violence is beyond the pale.<br>     戈尔巴乔夫和他克里姆林宫改革派盟友们，准备容忍，甚至鼓励温和的民族主义分子向中央控制挑战并要求独立。可是莫斯科自有理由觉得：在一个操多种语言，由102个民族组成的国家里，族裔之间的暴力则属过分。<br>'),(10633,'rightness','','','','','n. 廉正,正直,公正',''),(10634,'rights','','','','','权利',' People have the rights of assembly and expression.<br>     人们有集会和发表言论的权利。<br>\n Rights are inseparable from duties.<br>     权利和职责是分不开的.<br>'),(10635,'rigid','','','','','a. 僵硬的,刻板的,严格的',' She was rigid with fear.<br>     她害怕得全身僵住了。<br>\n The caste refers to social system based on rigid distinctions of birth, rank, wealth, etc.<br>     社会等级是指按照血统，阶级，财富等严格区分的社会制度。<br>'),(10636,'rigidity','','','','','n. 硬,劲直,硬度','');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (10637,'rigidly','','','','','ad. 不易弯地,坚硬地',' He maintains a rigidly right-wing political stance.<br>     他坚持僵硬的右派政治立场.<br>\n An automobile designed to look like a convertible but having a rigidly fixed, hard top.<br>     金属顶盖式汽车具有看似篷式汽车但却有固定的顶篷设计的汽车<br>'),(10638,'rigmarole','','','','','n. 冗长无聊的废话',' I\'ve never heard such a rigmarole.<br>     我从来没听过像这样的长篇废话.<br>'),(10639,'rigor','','','','rigors','n. 严格,酷烈,严密',' He deserves to be punished with the full rigor of the law.<br>     他应该受到法律最严厉的惩罚。<br>\n The expedition suffered all the rigors of a Canadian winter.<br>     这支探险队饱受了加拿大严冬的折磨。<br>'),(10640,'rigorous','','','','','a. 严厉的,严酷的,严格的',' Now her teachers corps, called Teach for American is off and running. After a rigorous competition,500 recent college graduates won places out of a field of2, 500 applicants, proving Ms.Kopp\'s theory that making the corps selective would enhance its appeal to college students.<br>     现在她的教师工作团——名为教师报国团——已迅速展开工作。经过一番激烈竞争之后，2500名申请人中，500名刚从大学毕业的被录取。证明了柯普女士的理论：工作团从严录取将可在大学生中增加号召力。<br>\n Rigorous or ceremonious adherence to established forms, rules, or customs.<br>     拘泥形式遵照或顺从已被确认的形式、规则或习俗<br>'),(10641,'rigorously','','','','','ad. 严格地',''),(10642,'rile','riled','riled','riling','','v. 搅浑浊,惹怒,使焦急',' It riles me that he won\'t agree.<br>     他就是不同意, 真气人.<br>\n Don\'t get riled.<br>     别生气.<br>'),(10643,'rill','rilled','rilled','rilling','rills','n. 小河<br>\nvi. 小河般地流',' The water in this rill is very clean.<br>     这条小溪里的水非常清澈。<br>'),(10644,'rim','rimmed','rimmed','rimming','rims','n. 边,轮缘,框<br>\nv. 镶边,为...之边',' She put a flower on the rim of the hat.<br>     她在帽子边上放了一朵花。<br>\n She opened the door, and the yellow light from inside rimmed about her.<br>     她打开门，里面射出的灯光在她的身影四周镶了一圈黄色的边。<br>'),(10645,'rime','','','','','n. 白霜',' The field was covered with rime in the early morning.<br>     清晨地里覆盖着一层白霜。<br>\n According as I have rime, I\'ll go shopping.<br>     如果我有时间，我就去买些东西。<br>'),(10646,'rind','rinded','rinded','rinding','rinds','n. 皮,壳,外表<br>\nv. 削皮,剥壳',' Those apple rinds are green.<br>     那些苹果的皮是绿的。<br>\n Please help me to cut off the rinds of lemons.<br>     请帮我去掉柠檬的皮。<br>'),(10647,'ring','ringed','ringed rang','ringing','','n. 环,戒指,铃声<br>\nv. 响,鸣,回响',' I wonder when mother will ring?<br>     我不知道母亲什么时候会打电话来？<br>\n The telephone is ringing.<br>     电话响了。<br>'),(10648,'ringed','','','','','a. 戴戒指的,带环的',' A high fence ringed the prison camp.<br>     有一道高高的铁丝网围著战俘营<br>\n The lake is ringed with willows.<br>     该湖四周柳树环绕。<br>'),(10649,'ringer','','','','','振铃器,信号器',' She\'s a dead ringer for a girl I used to know.<br>     她酷似以前我认识的一个女孩。<br>\n It is time for the ringers to change off.<br>     是敲钟人换班的时候了。<br>'),(10650,'ringlet','','','','ringlets','n. 卷发',' Her hair hung down in ringlets.<br>     她的头发呈许多小发卷下垂着。<br>\n The child\'s hair fell in ringlets.<br>     小孩的卷发自然下垂<br>'),(10651,'ringmaster','','','','','n. 马戏演出指挥',''),(10652,'rings','','','','','吊环',' That rings a bell.<br>     我总算想起来了。<br>\n The popular song rings far and near.<br>     这首流行歌曲到处流传。<br>'),(10653,'rink','','','','','n. 溜冰场',' The playing field in ice hockey; the rink.<br>     溜冰场冰球的场地；冰球场<br>'),(10654,'rinse','rinsed','rinsed','rinsing','rinses','n. 清洗,润丝,洗刷<br>\nv. 以清水冲洗,灌进',' You may use hot water to rinse the congealed fat off the dinner plates.<br>     你可以用热水把菜盘上凝结的油污冲洗掉。<br>\n Rinse the clothes.<br>     把衣服涮一涮。<br>'),(10655,'Rio de Janeiro','','','','','里约热内卢（巴西港市）',' Eleven hours out of Paris, the Air France plane let down into Rio de Janeiro.<br>     法国航空公司的飞机在飞离巴黎11个小时之后，在里约热内卢减速下降。<br>\n A native or inhabitant of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.<br>     巴西里约热内卢人或里约热内卢的居民<br>'),(10656,'riot','rioted','rioted','rioting','riots','v.&n. 骚乱,闹事<br>\nvi. 闹事,骚乱',' The football supporters ran riot through the town after the defeat of their team.<br>     足球队输球后球迷们在街上聚众闹事。<br>\n The police stopped several riots on election night.<br>     警方在竞选之夜制止了几处骚乱。<br>'),(10657,'riotous','','','','','a. 引起骚扰的,暴动的,放荡的',' We spent a riotous night at Christmas.<br>     圣诞节我们度过了一个狂欢之夜。<br>\n He was charged with riotous behaviour.<br>     他被控聚众闹事。<br>'),(10658,'rip','','','','','n. 裂痕,破绽,拉裂<br>\nv. 拉开,划开,裂开',' I ripped my stocking on a nail.<br>     一个钉子挂破了我的袜子。<br>\n The poster had been ripped to pieces.<br>     那张广告画已被撕得粉碎。<br>'),(10659,'riparian','','','','','a. 河岸的,生于河岸的<br>\nn. 河岸的土地所有人',' Fishing and other riparian rights belong to owners of riparian land.<br>     捕鱼和其他河岸权属于该河两岸土地的所有者。<br>'),(10660,'ripe','','','','','a. 成熟的',' The time was ripe for a challenge to the power of the government.<br>     时机已经成熟，可以向政府权力提出挑战了。<br>\n These apples are not ripe; they are sour.<br>     这些苹果不熟，是酸的。<br>'),(10661,'ripen','ripened','ripened','ripening','','成熟',' Time had ripened his life and mellowed its fruits.<br>     时间使他的生命成熟，结出硕果。<br>\n Fruit sweetens as it ripens.<br>     水果成熟後就好吃了.<br>'),(10662,'riposte','riposted','riposted','riposting','','n. .机敏的反驳或应答,剑术上的挡后回刺',''),(10663,'ripple','','','','','n. 涟波,涟漪,波纹<br>\nv. 使...起涟漪,起微波,起潺潺声',' The wheat rippled in the breeze.<br>     小麦在微风中起伏波动。<br>\n The breeze rippled the quiet water.<br>     微风吹皱了平静的水面。<br>'),(10664,'RISC','','','','','精简指令系统计算机',''),(10665,'rise','rose','risen','rising','rises','n. 上升,增加,小山<br>\nv. 升起,起身,上升,(日、月、星)升起',' I am reading a book about the rise and fall of the Roman Empire.<br>     我正在看一本关于罗马帝国兴衰的书。<br>\n The sun rises in the east.<br>     太阳从东方升起。<br>'),(10666,'risen','','','','','rise的过去分词',' Many people got rich by hoarding up gold until the price had risen more than ten times.<br>     许多人通过储存黄金待其涨价至10倍以上而发了财。<br>\n The river has risen (by) several metres.<br>     河水上涨了好几米.<br>'),(10667,'risible','','','','','a. 可笑的,引人发笑的',' The entire proposal is risible: it will never be accepted.<br>     这个建议完全是荒唐可笑的, 根本不可能采纳.<br>'),(10668,'rising','','','','','n. 上升,造反,叛乱<br>\na. 上升的,高涨的,晋升的<br>\nvbl. 升起,起身,上升',' The mercury is rising.<br>     温度正在上升。<br>\n The mists was fleeing before the rising sun.<br>     太阳慢慢升起，薄雾渐渐消失。<br>'),(10669,'risk','risked','risked','risking','risks','n. 风险,危险<br>\nv. 冒...的危险',' Anyone swimming in this lake does so at his own risk.<br>     任何人在此湖中冒险游泳，其后果自负。<br>\n He saved my life at the risk of his own.<br>     他冒着自己的生命危险救了我的命。<br>'),(10670,'risky','','','','','a. 危险的(冒险的,大胆的)',' He would not have succeeded in such a risky business if he had not been such a clever entrepreneur.<br>     假若他不是那麽精明强干的企业家, 就不会在这样冒险的事业中取得成功.<br>\n So risky as to require very deft handling.<br>     冒险的冒险的，需灵巧处理的<br>'),(10671,'risque','','','','','a. <法> (作品等)淫秽的, 败坏风俗的',''),(10672,'rite','','','','','n. 仪式,典礼',' Did you go to their marriage rites?<br>     你参加他们的婚礼了吗？<br>\n The sacrament or rite of ordination.<br>     神职仪式神职的任命或神职任命仪式<br>'),(10673,'ritual','','','','rituals','n. 仪式,典礼,宗教仪式,固定程序<br>\na. 仪式的,依仪式而行的，老规矩的，惯常的',' An ancient ritual in modern dress.<br>     以现代风貌包装的古代仪式<br>\n A person trained in Jewish law, ritual, and tradition and ordained for leadership of a Jewish congregation, especially one serving as chief religious official of a synagogue.<br>     犹太的法学博士在犹太法律、仪式及传统方面受过训练的人，并被任命主持犹太教集会，尤指在犹太教堂中作为主要神职的人员<br>'),(10674,'ritualistic','','','','','a. 仪式的',''),(10675,'ritualize','ritualized','ritualized','ritualizing','','v. 仪式化',''),(10676,'rival','rivaled','rivaled','rivaling','rivals','n. 对手,竞争者<br>\na. 竞争的<br>\nvt. 与…相匹敌,比得上',' Ships can\'t rival aircraft for speed.<br>     轮船在速度方面无法与飞机匹敌。<br>\n Tom and I were rivals for the job.<br>     汤姆和我是这次求职的竞争对手。<br>'),(10677,'rivalry','','','','rivalries','n. 敌对,竞争,对抗',' That country was paralysed by political rivalries.<br>     那个国家由于政治对抗而陷于瘫痪。<br>\n It\'s an usual rivalry between brother and sister.<br>     那是兄妹之间常见的钩心斗角。<br>'),(10678,'rive','rived','rived','riving','','v. 撕开,使沮丧',''),(10679,'river','','','','rivers','n. 江,河',' The Changjiang River is one of the longest rivers in the world.<br>     长江是世界上最长的河流之一。<br>\n The guide led us to the river.<br>     向导带领我们到河边。<br>'),(10680,'riverfront','','','','','n. (城镇的)河边地区,河边陆地',''),(10681,'riverside','','','','','n. 河岸,河畔',' Let\'s go for a picnic by the riverside.<br>     我们到河边野餐去吧。<br>\n My dog heeled me all the way to the riverside.<br>     我那条狗一路紧跟著我跑到河边。<br>'),(10682,'rivet','riveted','riveted','riveting','rivets','n. 铆钉<br>\nv. 用铆钉固定,敲进去,注目',' We stood riveted to the spot.<br>     我们寸步不移的站在那儿。<br>\n I was absolutely riveted by her story.<br>     她的故事完全把我吸引住了。<br>'),(10683,'riveting','','','','','n. 铆接法',' Only by riveting her attention on her word could she forget her worries.<br>     只有全身心投入到工作上她才能忘记烦恼。<br>\n Can I fasten these metal plates with rivets?<br>     我可以用铆钉把这些金属板固定在一起吗？<br>'),(10684,'rivulet','','','','rivulets','n. 小河',''),(10685,'RNA','','','','','核糖核酸',' Any of a group of red dyes used as a biological stain, especially to detect the presence of RNA.<br>     焦宁；二苯氧芑胶染料用作生物染色剂的一组红色染料中的任一种，尤指用来探测核糖核酸的存在<br>'),(10686,'roach','','','','','n. 蟑螂',''),(10687,'road','','','','roads','n. 路',' All roads lead to Rome.<br>     条条大道通罗马。<br>\n The road was blocked by a huge rock.<br>     道路被一块大石头堵住了。<br>'),(10688,'road map','','','','','道路图,街道图',''),(10689,'roadblock','','','','','n. 路障',''),(10690,'roadside','','','','','n. 路傍,路边',' We ate our meal at a roadside pub.<br>     我们是在路旁的一家小酒馆里吃的饭。<br>\n We ate our meal by the roadside.<br>     我们是在公路旁吃的饭。<br>'),(10691,'roadster','','','','roadsters','n. 双人座敞篷汽车',''),(10692,'roadway','','','','roadways','n. 车行道,路面',' A mound of earth or stone built to hold back water or to support a roadway.<br>     堤用以阻挡水或支持公路而建造的土堆或石堆<br>\n A raised roadway, as across water or marshland.<br>     堤道加高的行道，如穿过水洼或沼泽的道路<br>'),(10693,'roam','roamed','roamed','roaming','','v. 漫游,闲逛,徜徉',' He settled down after years of roaming.<br>     漂泊数年后，他定居了下来。<br>\n Bison used to roam through the American great plains, but most of them are slaughter by hunter.<br>     从前野牛在美国大平原上漫游，但是大多数都被猎人屠杀了。<br>'),(10694,'roaming','','','','','移动',' He settled down after years of roaming.<br>     漂泊数年后，他定居了下来。<br>\n He spent much of his spare time roaming about the streets.<br>     他把大部分的闲暇时间用来逛街。<br>'),(10695,'roan','','','','','a. 菊花青色的<br>\nn. 菊花青色的马,柔软的羊皮',' Jump in, there is roan for one more person in the car.<br>     快进来，汽车里还可以坐1个人。<br>'),(10696,'roar','roared','roared','roaring','roars','n. 吼,咆哮,轰鸣<br>\nv. 吼,大声说出,叫喊',' He roared with pain.<br>     他疼得大叫起来。<br>\n The football crowd roared.<br>     足球观众大喊起来。<br>'),(10697,'roaring','','','','','n. 吼声,咆哮,怒吼<br>\na. 风哮雨嚎的,喧哗的,兴胜的',' The place was a blazing, raging, roaring, etc inferno.<br>     那地方是一片熊熊的、 滚滚的、 咆哮的...火海.<br>\n The news was greeted with roaring cheers among the workers.<br>     工人们听到这消息时都欢声雷动。<br>'),(10698,'roast','roasted','roasted','roasting','roasts','n. 烤肉,烘烤<br>\na. 烘烤的,烤过的<br>\nv. 烤,烘焙',' Let\'s have a nice roast for Sunday dinner.<br>     我们星期天晚上好好吃一顿烤肉吧。<br>\n The beef is roasting nicely on the spit.<br>     这块牛肉在烤肉叉上烤得很好。<br>'),(10699,'roasted','','','','','a. 烤好的',' The critics roasted her new play.<br>     评论家狠狠挖苦她 的新剧.<br>\n The benefit party at$100 a ticket promises to be a real fine donkey roast.<br>     这个募捐晚会，票价定为100美元1张，保证开成一个盛会。<br>'),(10700,'rob','robbed','robbed','robbing','','v. 抢劫<br>\nvi. 抢劫,盗窃<br>\nvt. 非法剥夺,使丧失,抢劫',' They knocked him down and robbed him of his briefcase.<br>     他们把他打倒在地，抢走了他的公文包。<br>\n The silly ending robs the plot of any credibility.<br>     这愚蠢的结尾使得整个情节变得一点都不可信。<br>'),(10701,'robber','','','','robbers','n. 盗贼,强盗',' The robbers escaped before the police arrived.<br>     强盗们在警察到来之前逃走了。<br>\n They kept a wary eye on the robber.<br>     他们密切注意那个强盗。<br>'),(10702,'robbery','','','','robberies','n. 抢劫',' He had committed several robberies in the neighborhood.<br>     他已在附近犯下了好几起抢劫案。<br>\n The police have excluded robbery as a motive for the murder.<br>     警方已排除该谋杀案中有抢劫的动机.<br>'),(10703,'robe','robed','robed','robing','robes','n. 长袍<br>\nv. (使)穿上长袍等',' You should put a robe on if you go out in a cold day.<br>     冷天出门时要披上披肩。<br>\n He robes himself in moonlight.<br>     他沐浴在月光下。<br>'),(10704,'Robert','','','','','罗伯特(男名)',' The film co-starred Robert Redford (and Paul Newman).<br>     这部影片由罗伯特·雷德福（和保罗·纽曼）联合主演.<br>\n A slip of the tongue made me say Robert instead of Richard.<br>     我说走了嘴把理查德说成了罗伯特.<br>'),(10705,'Roberts','','','','','罗伯茨(姓氏)',' The Roberts were at table when I called.<br>     我造访时，罗伯特一家正在吃饭。<br>\n Roberts is a real cynic; he won\'t accept anything or anyone on face value.<br>     罗伯特实在是一个玩世不恭的人；他不会对任何事或任何人信以为真。<br>'),(10706,'robin','','','','robins','n. 知更鸟',' If you wish to catch that robin, try putting a pinch of salt on its tail.<br>     你要是想抓住那只知更鸟，设法撒一点盐在鸟尾巴上，这样就能逮住它。<br>\n The people in our neighborhood are sending a round robin to the Air Force to protest the nice the jet planes make flying over our house.<br>     我们这一带的居民在向空军部队递交一份有环形签名的抗议书，就喷气式飞机飞越我们住宅上空时产生的噪音问题提出抗议。<br>'),(10707,'Robin Hood','','','','','n. 罗宾汉',''),(10708,'Robinson Crusoe','','','','','鲁滨孙·克鲁索(《鲁滨孙漂流记》主人公)',''),(10709,'robot','','','','robots','n. 机器人',' Japanese industry is making increasing use of robots.<br>     日本工业越来越多地使用机器人。<br>\n The toy robot moved forward with quick jerky steps.<br>     玩具机器人一颠一颠地走得很快.<br>'),(10710,'robotics','','','','','机器人技术',''),(10711,'robust','','','','','a. 强壮的,强健的',' Being in robust and sturdy good health.<br>     强壮的，健康的强壮的和身体健康的<br>\n The old veteran could lay flat the most robust sportsman.<br>     这位沙场院老将能把最强壮的运动员拖得筋疲力尽。<br>'),(10712,'rock','','','','','n. 岩石,岩礁,巨石<br>\nv. 摇摆,摇动',' The ship struck on a rock and sank.<br>     船触礁沉没。<br>\n The news of the president\'s murder rocked the nation.<br>     总统被暗杀的消息震惊了全国。<br>'),(10713,'rock \'n\' roll','','','','','摇滚乐(摇滚乐曲歌词简单,常用作舞会音乐)',''),(10714,'Rockefeller','','','','','洛克菲勒(姓氏)',''),(10715,'rocker','','','','rockers','n. 摇轴(套钩,镰刀弯)',' You must be off your rocker!<br>     你简直疯了!<br>\n A punk rocker.<br>     庞克摇滚乐师<br>'),(10716,'rocket','','','','','n. 火箭,烟火<br>\nv. 发射火箭,猛涨',' The price of oil has suddenly rocketed up.<br>     石油价格突然飞涨。<br>\n They sent a distress rock