     他把橡皮筋啪的一声拉断了.<br>'),(10809,'rubbery','','','','','a. 强韧的',' A mild, white Italian cheese that has a rubbery texture and is often eaten melted, as on pizza.<br>     白干酪一种味淡的、白色的并有弹性的意大利奶酪，通常融化放在比萨饼上吃<br>'),(10810,'rubbish','','','','','a. 毫无价值的<br>\nn. 废话,垃圾,废物',' The dustman comes once a week to collect the rubbish.<br>     垃圾工每周来收一次垃圾。<br>\n That new TV show is absolutely rubbish.<br>     那个新的电视节目一点儿价值都没有。<br>'),(10811,'rubble','','','','','n. 粗石,破碎的砖,粗石堆',' Rubble covered the pavement.<br>     人行道上铺了碎石块.<br>\n The ceiling collapsed and rubble poured into the room.<br>     天花板坍塌了, 碎砖破瓦掉落到了屋里.<br>'),(10812,'rubicund','','','','','a. 红的,透红的',''),(10813,'ruby','rubied','rubied','rubying','rubies','a. 红宝石色<br>\nn. 红宝石',' Her ruby necklace brightened her face.<br>     红宝石项链照亮了她的脸庞。<br>\n The ruby sets off the diamond.<br>     红宝石把钻石衬托得更美丽。<br>'),(10814,'ruck','','','','','n. 皱褶,普通群众,大量',' Thesheets on my bed have rucked up.<br>     我床上的床单有褶子了.<br>\n He was eager to get out of the (common) ruck and distinguish himself in some way.<br>     他渴望出人头地, 在某方面与众不同.<br>'),(10815,'rucksack','','','','','n. 帆布背包',' She shouldered her rucksack and set off along the road.<br>     她背起帆布背包就上路了.<br>\n She swung the rucksack (up) onto her back.<br>     她把帆布背包转到身後.<br>'),(10816,'rudder','','','','rudders','n. 舵,方向舵',' The wood rudder of the ship was broken.<br>     船的木头舵坏了。<br>\n A part or surface, such as a wing, propeller blade, or rudder, whose shape and orientation control stability, direction, lift, thrust, or propulsion.<br>     翼剖面；机翼；翼面一个部件或平面，如机翼、螺旋桨叶、方向舵等，其形状或方位控制稳定性、方向、抬升、冲击或驱动<br>'),(10817,'ruddy','','','','','a. 红的,红润的',' He looked at the children\'s ruddy cheeks and smiled.<br>     他看着孩子们红润的脸颊，笑了。<br>\n The fire cast a ruddy glow over the city.<br>     这场火把城市上空映得一片通红。<br>'),(10818,'rude','','','','','a. 粗鲁的,无礼的',' Don\'t be so rude to your parents!<br>     别对你的父母这么没礼貌！<br>\n It\'s very rude of her to leave without telling us.<br>     她不向我们打声招呼就走了，这是非常不礼貌的。<br>'),(10819,'rudely','','','','','ad. 无礼地,粗鲁地,粗陋地',' The new student started off on the wrong foot with the teacher by answering back rudely.<br>     那个新来的学生粗鲁地跟老师顶嘴, 一开始就把关系搞僵了.<br>\n She was an odd fish, ignorant of common life, fond of rudely opposing established opinions.<br>     她是个怪人，不懂日常的社交生活，喜欢粗鲁地反对既定的见解。<br>'),(10820,'rudeness','','','','','n. 粗鲁,无礼',' His rudeness provoked me to strike him.<br>     他的粗鲁惹得我揍了他。<br>\n Your rudeness had offended many people.<br>     你的粗鲁已激怒了很多人。<br>'),(10821,'rudiment','','','','rudiments','n. 初步,初级',' I have mastered the rudiments of economics.<br>     我已精通经济学的基本原理。<br>'),(10822,'rudimentary','','','','','a. 基本的(初步的,起码的,根本的)',' I have only a rudimentary grasp of physics.<br>     我对物理学仅有初步的了解。<br>\n Sylvia\'s rudimentary knowledge of chess was more than enough to beat Peter, who had seldom played the game before; on the country of the blind….<br>     西尔维尔的象棋基础知识足以战胜彼得，因为彼得以前很少参加比赛，山中无老虎，猴子称王…。<br>'),(10823,'rudiments','','','','','n. 基础知识,入门',' I have mastered the rudiments of economics.<br>     我已精通经济学的基本原理。<br>'),(10824,'rue','','','','','n. 懊悔,芸香,后悔<br>\nv. 后悔,悲伤,懊悔',' He\'ll rue the day he married her.<br>     他将会因为和她结婚而抱恨终身。<br>\n I rue never having been to university.<br>     我后悔从未上过大学。<br>'),(10825,'rueful','','','','','a. 悲伤的,怜悯的,可怜的',' He thought of her with a rueful smile.<br>     他苦笑着回想她。<br>\n He was rueful for joining the army.<br>     他感到后悔去参军。<br>'),(10826,'ruffian','','','','ruffians','n. 恶棍,无赖<br>\na. 儿恶的,残忍的,残暴的',' A hired ruffian; a thug.<br>     打手一个被雇的恶棍；暴徒<br>\n He is one of the greatest ruffians who ever cheated the gallows.<br>     他是一个曾经逃过绞刑的最坏的恶棍。<br>'),(10827,'ruffle','','','','','n. 绉褶,波纹,生气<br>\nv. 弄绉,起绉,发脾气',' The bird ruffled up its feathers.<br>     鸟儿惊恐地竖起了羽毛。<br>\n A flag ruffled in the breeze.<br>     旗帜迎风飘扬。<br>'),(10828,'rug','','','','rugs','n. 毯子,地毯,旅行毯',' He is vacuuming a rug in the sitting room.<br>     他在起居室里用吸尘器打扫地毯。<br>\n She put a rug over the sleeping child.<br>     她给睡著的孩子盖上了毯子.<br>'),(10829,'rugby','','','','','n. 橄榄球',' I moved away from the North not long after, so most of my Rugby League since then has been viewed on the small screen.<br>     不久我便搬离了北方，自那以后，我的橄榄球竞赛联合会的多数成员都已在电视上亮相了。<br>\n The primarily defensive players in soccer, field hockey, and rugby.<br>     防守队员英式足球、曲棍球和橄榄球中主要的防守队员<br>'),(10830,'rugged','','','','','a. 高低不平的,崎岖的,粗糙的',' I don\'t like his rugged manner.<br>     我不喜欢他粗鲁的态度。<br>\n The path to glory is always rugged.<br>     通向光荣的道路常常是崎岖的。<br>'),(10831,'ruin','ruined','ruined','ruining','ruins','n. (pl.)废墟,毁灭<br>\nv. 毁坏,破坏<br>\nvi. (使)破产,毁灭<br>\nvt. 毁坏,毁灭',' The castle now lies in ruins.<br>     那城堡现在已成了一片废墟了。<br>\n The rain ruined my painting.<br>     这场雨把我的画给毁了。<br>'),(10832,'ruined','','','','','a. 毁坏的,破坏的',' This ruined bridge is a relic of the Civil War.<br>     这座毁坏的桥是南北战争时的遗迹。<br>\n The vessel was ruined by a submarine.<br>     那艘船是被潜水艇毁坏的。<br>'),(10833,'ruinous','','','','','a. 破坏性的,招致毁减的,零落的',' The prices in that restaurant are absolutely ruinous.<br>     那家餐馆的价格贵得能把人坑死。<br>\n They took a ruinous expenditure on the house.<br>     他们为了那所房子倾家荡产。<br>'),(10834,'rule','ruled','ruled','ruling','rules','n. 惯例,规则,统治<br>\nv. 裁定,统治,支配<br>\nvi. 裁决,统治<br>\nvt. 统治',' It\'s against the rule to pick up the ball.<br>     捡球是犯规的。<br>\n The rule is that someone must be on duty at all times.<br>     按照规定，任何时候均需有人值班。<br>'),(10835,'rule of thumb','','','','','n. 经验法则(靠经验估计)',' As a rule of thumb, you should cook a chicken for 20 minutes for each pound that it weighs.<br>     凭经验估计, 每磅鸡肉应烹调20分钟.<br>\n As a rule of thumb, a one-cent-a-gallon gasoline tax raises$1 billion. Oil producers in President-elect Bush\'s adopted state of Texas, however, would rather see a tax on imported crude oil.<br>     一般情形是，每加仑加汽油一分钱的税可以征收10亿元。可是，在布什第二家乡德克萨斯州的产油商宁愿看见在进口原油上征税。<br>'),(10836,'ruler','','','','rulers','n. 尺子<br>\nn. 统治者',' He reminded me not to forget to bring my ruler.<br>     他提醒我别忘了带尺子。<br>\n Sultan is sovereign ruler of certain Muslim countries.<br>     苏丹是某些穆斯林国家的最高统治者。<br>'),(10837,'ruling','','','','','n. 判决,裁定,统治<br>\na. 统治的,支配的,流行的<br>\nvbl. 规定,统治,管理',' The judge\'s ruling is final.<br>     法官的判决是不可改变的.<br>\n The new ruling gives effect to the recommendations of the special committee.<br>     这一新裁定使特别委员会的推荐生效.<br>'),(10838,'rum','','','','','n. 甜酒<br>\na. 古怪的,奇特的',' Rum is an alcoholic drink distilled from sugar-cane juice.<br>     郎姆酒是用甘蔗汁蒸馏制成的。<br>\n The rum is 30% below proof.<br>     朗姆酒低於标准度数30%.<br>'),(10839,'rumble','','','','','n. 隆隆声,辘辘声<br>\nv. 发隆隆声,辘辘响',' The heavy cart rumbled down the street.<br>     笨重的马车辘辘地在街上走过。<br>\n The thunder rumbled in the distance.<br>     远处雷声隆隆。<br>'),(10840,'ruminant','','','','','a. (动物)反刍的,沉思的',' Leather made from the hide of the African and Asian ruminant.<br>     羚皮革非洲、亚洲的羚羊皮做的皮革<br>'),(10841,'ruminate','ruminated','ruminated','ruminating','','v. 反刍,深思,沉思',' He is ruminating on recent events.<br>     他正在思考最近发生的事。<br>\n The cow began to ruminate after eating up grass.<br>     牛吃完草后开始反刍。<br>'),(10842,'rummage','rummaged','rummaged','rummaging','','v. 到处翻寻,搜出,检查<br>\nn. 翻箱倒柜的寻找,临检,碎屑',''),(10843,'rumor','rumored','rumored','rumoring','rumors','n. 谣言,传闻<br>\nv. 谣传',' He is rumored to have escaped to Dublin.<br>     据说他已逃往都柏林。<br>\n There is a rumor that there will be a General Election in the autumn.<br>     据传闻今秋将举行普选。<br>'),(10844,'rumour','rumoured','rumoured','rumouring','rumours','n. 谣言,传闻<br>\nv. 传闻,谣传',' There isn\'t an atom of truth in the rumour.<br>     谣言中没有丝毫的真实性.<br>\n There\'s a rumour going round that Sue and David are having an affair.<br>     有谣传称休和戴维关系暧昧.<br>'),(10845,'rump','','','','rumps','n. (鸟)尾部,(兽)臀部',' After the election the party was reduced to a rump.<br>     选举之后，该党的党员所剩无几了。<br>\n He ordered a juicy rump steak.<br>     他要了一份多汁的后腿肉牛排。<br>'),(10846,'rumple','rumpled','rumpled','rumpling','rumples','n. 皱纹,皱褶<br>\nv. 弄皱,弄乱',''),(10847,'rumpus','','','','','n. 吵闹,喧闹',' I was still there when I heard the rumpus. I came out into the hall and ran hell for leather to see what was the matter.<br>     当我听到那吵嚷声时，我还在那里，我立刻从房里来到过道里，飞快地跑出去看看是怎么回事。<br>'),(10848,'run','ran','run','running','runs','n. 奔跑,路程,趋向<br>\nv. 跑,运转,进行,运转,经营,褪色<br>\nvbl. 跑,进行,延续',' The little boy ran off to get his brother.<br>     这个小男孩跑去找他的哥哥。<br>\n The petrol is running out.<br>     汽油快要耗尽了。<br>'),(10849,'runaway','','','','runaways','n. 逃走的人,逃亡,亡命者<br>\na. 逃亡的,逃走的',' The runaway of the traffic accident is wanted by the police.<br>     警方正在通缉交通事故的逃逸者。<br>\n The runaway horse was cornered in a field.<br>     那匹跑掉的马在田地里被圈住了.<br>'),(10850,'rundown','','','','','n. 扼要报告,总结',' He will flatter a person to his face, and then rundown behind his back.<br>     他会当面吹捧一个人，背后又说他坏话。<br>\n I missed the meeting. Can you give me the rundown?<br>     我没能叁加会议，你能告诉我会议的概要吗？<br>'),(10851,'rung','','','','','n. 脚蹬横木,横档,车辐',' The director made his son start on the bottom rung of the ladder as an office boy.<br>     董事让他的儿子从最低级的职员做起。<br>\n A bell rung as a call to recite this prayer.<br>     天使经钟用来号召进行这种祈祷的钟声<br>'),(10852,'runner','','','','','n. 赛跑的人',' There are eight runners in the final race.<br>     最后的赛程中有八匹马参加。<br>\n The runner shot ahead (of the rest).<br>     那个赛跑的人向前飞奔而去（把其他人抛在後面）.<br>'),(10853,'runner-up','','','','runner-ups','n. 亚军, 亚军队',''),(10854,'running','','','','','n. 赛跑,流出,运转<br>\na. 流动的,跑著的,连续的<br>\nvbl. 跑,运转,经营',' Mike is rather timid with women, so Sue has to make all the running in their relationship.<br>     迈克在女子面前很　腆，所以苏珊只好对迈克主动一些。<br>\n The boy avoided punishment by running away.<br>     那个男孩逃跑来逃避惩罚。<br>'),(10855,'running track','','','','','n. 跑道',' The attendant smoothed away the slight irregularities in the running track.<br>     跑道上稍稍有些不平，勤务人员把它弄平整了。<br>\n All those men were jostling with each other on the running track, as if the result was so important.<br>     瞧那些人在跑道上你冲我撞的，似乎比赛的结果真的就是那样重要。<br>'),(10856,'runny','','','','','a. 流鼻涕的',' You\'ve got a runny nose!<br>     你流鼻涕了!<br>'),(10857,'runoff','','','','','n. 径流量(流出,流放口,出轨