ld her parents yet so keep it to yourself.<br>     我听说桑德拉怀孕了，但不知道她是否已告诉了她父母，所以不要告诉别人。<br>'),(11004,'sands','','','','','n. 沙漠',' The sands are running out: we must have the money by tomorrow.<br>     剩下的时间不多了: 我们明天得弄到这笔钱.<br>\n The wind blew from the desert and covered everything with sand.<br>     沙漠那边吹来的风把所有的东西都蒙上了一层沙子.<br>'),(11005,'sandstone','','','','','n. 沙岩',' Sandstone cuts easily.<br>     砂岩容易切割.<br>'),(11006,'sandstorm','','','','','n. 沙暴',' A sandstorm kicked up while we drove through the desert.<br>     我们在沙漠里行驶时，沙暴加强了<br>'),(11007,'sandwich','sandwiched','sandwiched','sandwiching','sandwiches','n. 三明治<br>\nv. 插入,夹入',' He made a ham sandwich.<br>     他做了一个火腿三明治。<br>\n He was sandwiched between two fat women.<br>     他被夹在两个胖女人中间。<br>'),(11008,'sandy','','','','','a. 沙的,沙地的,多沙的',' Most of the shore is rocky, but there is a sandy beach.<br>     沿海大部分为岩石，但也有一部分沙滩。<br>\n I prefer a sandy beach to a shingle one.<br>     我喜欢沙滩，不喜欢遍布小石子的海滩.<br>'),(11009,'sane','','','','','a. 神智健全的,理智的',' It\'s hard to stay sane under such awful pressure.<br>     处于这种可怕的压力之下，不疯才怪呢。<br>\n She have a sane attitude towards diving and never go too fast.<br>     她对於跳水的态度很明智，从不操之过急。<br>'),(11010,'sanely','','','','','ad. 神志清楚地',''),(11011,'sang','','','','','v. sing的过去式,唱,唱歌,鸣唱',' The soldiers sang a song of victory, describing their prowess in battle.<br>     战士们唱起了歌颂他们英勇战斗的凯歌。<br>\n She sang an incomparable song.<br>     她唱了一首无与伦比的歌。<br>'),(11012,'sangfroid','','','','','n. 冷静,泰然,沉著',''),(11013,'sanguinary','','','','','a. 流血的,血腥的,嗜血的',''),(11014,'sanguine','','','','','a. 乐天的,自信的<br>\nn. 血红色',' He is not very sanguine about our chances of success.<br>     他对我们成功的机会不太乐观。<br>\n We are sanguine that we shall be succeeding.<br>     我们自信会成功。<br>'),(11015,'sanitary','','','','sanitaries','a. 卫生的,清洁的',' Sanitary conditions had deteriorated to such an extent that there was widespread danger of disease.<br>     卫生条件恶化到了如此程度，到处都有发生疾病的危险。<br>\n Epidemic disease is often in connection with bad sanitary conditions.<br>     流行病通常是和不良的卫生条件有关的。<br>'),(11016,'sanitation','','','','','n. 环境卫生(卫生设备,下水道设备)',' The people lived in that city can keep sanitation clean.<br>     住在那个城市的人们能保持公共卫生的清洁。<br>'),(11017,'sanity','','','','','n. 神智健全,头脑清楚,健全',' His strange remarks planted doubts in our minds about his sanity.<br>     他那些怪话使我们心中生疑，不知他精神是否正常。<br>'),(11018,'sank','','','','','sink的过去式',' The ship sank 10 miles out of Stockholm.<br>     船在离斯德哥尔摩10英里处沉没了.<br>\n The ship sank beneath the waves.<br>     轮船沉没于波涛下面。<br>'),(11019,'Santa Claus','','','','','n. 圣诞老人',' She still believes in Santa Claus and it would be cruel to disillusion her.<br>     她仍然相信有圣诞老人, 要是使她这一幻想破灭就於心不忍了.<br>\n Bishop of Myra in Asia Minor who is often associated with Santa Claus and the custom of gift-giving at Christmas.<br>     尼古拉斯小亚细亚半岛上米拉的主教，他通常与圣诞老人和圣诞节赠送礼物的习俗联系在一起<br>'),(11020,'sap','','','','','n. 半穿甲的(烧结铝粉);the liquid within a plant that carries food to all parts of it;a foolish person;v.to gradually weaken(somebody\'s strength);',' Her long illness gradually sapped her strength.<br>     长期的患病使她的体力渐渐衰竭。<br>\n The sap flowed out when he broke the stem of the flower.<br>     他把花茎折断，汁液就流了出来。<br>'),(11021,'sapid','','','','','a. 有风味的',''),(11022,'sapience','','','','','n. 煞像有学识,装聪明,智慧',''),(11023,'sapient','','','','','a. 装聪明样的,聪明的,伶俐的',''),(11024,'sapless','','','','','a. 没有元气的',''),(11025,'sapling','','','','saplings','n. 树苗,小树',' It\'s our duty to protect the saplings.<br>     保护树苗是我们的责任。<br>\n She cut down the sapling with one chop.<br>     她一斧子就把树苗砍倒了.<br>'),(11026,'saponification','','','','','n. 皂化',''),(11027,'sapphire','','','','','n. 蓝宝石(青色)<br>\na. 蓝宝石色的(青色的)',' Her sapphire necklace attracted everyone\'s attention.<br>     她的蓝宝石项链吸引了每个人的注意。<br>\n She had the sapphire set in a gold ring.<br>     她把那枚蓝宝石镶在金戒指上了.<br>'),(11028,'Sapporo','','','','','札幌（日本北海道西部城市）',' At what time shall we arrive at sapporo if we take this plane.<br>     如果我们坐这架飞机，我们将在几点到达札幌。<br>'),(11029,'SAR','','','','','n. 特别行政区',''),(11030,'Sara','','','','','萨拉(女名)',' Judy goes to the movies as often as Sara does.<br>     朱迪像莎拉一样时常去看电影。<br>\n Sara was excited to see the rock band.<br>     莎拉看到摇滚乐团很兴奋。<br>'),(11031,'Saracen','','','','','n.&a. 撒拉逊人(的)',''),(11032,'sarcasm','','','','sarcasms','n. 挖苦,讽刺',' He was totally flattened by her sarcasm.<br>     她说的挖苦话使他无地自容.<br>\n \"It was a good idea to tell my mother you didn\'t like her dress\", she said with sarcasm.<br>     \"跟我母亲说你不喜欢她的衣服，那可真是个好主意，\"她讽刺地说。<br>'),(11033,'sarcastic','','','','','a. 讽刺的',' She talked with him with sarcastic tones.<br>     她用挖苦的语调和他说话。<br>\n He could feel their sarcastic tone about his poor work.<br>     他能感觉到他们对他拙劣作品的讽刺语调。<br>'),(11034,'sarcoma','','','','sarcomas','n. 肉瘤',''),(11035,'sarcophagus','','','','sarcophagi','n. (精美的)石棺',''),(11036,'sardine','','','','sardine','n. 沙丁鱼',' The ten of us were squashed together like sardines in the tin.<br>     我们十几个人像沙丁鱼罐头一样挤成一团。<br>\n The ten of us were squashed together like sardines in the lift.<br>     我们十个人在电梯里拥成一团.<br>'),(11037,'sardonic','','','','','a. 嘲笑的,冷笑的,讥讽的',''),(11038,'sargasso','','','','sargassos','n. 马尾藻',''),(11039,'Sargasso Sea','','','','','马尾藻海(在西印度群岛东北)',''),(11040,'sari','','','','saris','n. (印度妇女的)莎丽服',''),(11041,'sartorial','','','','','a. 裁缝匠的,缝工的,裁缝的',''),(11042,'sash','sashed','sashed','sashing','','n. 饰带,肩带,腰带<br>\nv. 装以窗框',' Our windows have double-pane sashes.<br>     我们的窗户有双层的玻璃窗框。<br>\n The officer wears sashes on his shoulders.<br>     这名军官的肩上佩戴着肩带。<br>'),(11043,'sat','','','','','v. sit的过去式,过去分词,坐<br>\nvbl. 坐',' She sat gazing out of the window.<br>     她坐着凝视着窗外。<br>\n We sat on the chairs chatting in his living room.<br>     我们坐在他起居室的椅子上聊天。<br>'),(11044,'Satan','','','','','n. 撒旦(魔鬼)',' Satan is still a servant of God.<br>     撒旦仍是上帝的奴仆。<br>\n The abode of condemned souls and devils in some religions; the place of eternal punishment for the wicked after death, presided over by Satan.<br>     地狱某些宗教中被判有罪的灵魂或魔鬼居住的地方；邪恶之人死后永远受惩罚的地方，由撒旦统治<br>'),(11045,'satanic','','','','','a. 恶魔的, 魔鬼的',' American writers closed ranks yesterday behind Satanic Verses\' author Salman Rushdie, with at least two demonstrations planned for tomorrow and called for President Bush to take action.<br>     美国作家昨天团结一致支持《撒旦诗篇》的作者拉什迪，计划明天至少举行两起示威，并要求布什总统采取行动。<br>'),(11046,'satchel','','','','satchels','n. (皮或帆布的)书包',''),(11047,'sate','','','','','v. 使心满意足,过份的给与,sit 的过去式',' She sated with sleep.<br>     她睡腻了。<br>\n Nothing could sate the careerist\'s greed for power.<br>     什么也满足不了这个野心家的权力欲。<br>'),(11048,'satellite','','','','satellites','n. 卫星',' They have launched a man-made satellite successfully.<br>     他们成功地发射了一颗人造卫星。<br>\n Television stations around the world are linked by satellite.<br>     全世界的电视台通过卫星联系一起。<br>'),(11049,'satiate','satiated','satiated','satiating','','v. 使饱足,生腻<br>\nvt. 使过饱',' She pushed her chair back from the table, satiated.<br>     她把椅子从餐桌向后挪了挪，再也吃不下了。<br>\n He was satiated with pleasure.<br>     他厌倦了享乐。<br>'),(11050,'satiety','','','','','n. 饱足,满足',''),(11051,'satin','','','','','a. 缎子做(的)<br>\nn. 缎子',' The little girl wore satin ribbons in her hair.<br>     小女孩在头发上戴了缎带。<br>\n The satin feels smooth.<br>     这缎子摸起来很滑溜。<br>'),(11052,'satiny','','','','','a. 光滑的,柔细的',''),(11053,'satire','','','','satires','n. 讽刺文,讽刺',' His new play is a satire on the fashion industry.<br>     他的新剧本是一部讽刺时装业的作品。<br>\n The party in power soon learns what it\'s like to be on the receiving end of political satire.<br>     执政党很快就尝到了遭受政治讽刺的滋味.<br>'),(11054,'satiric','','','','','a. 讽刺的,挖苦的',''),(11055,'satirical','','','','','a. 讽刺的,爱挖苦的',' A satirical imitation or burlesque of the heroic manner or style.<br>     嘲弄地模仿英雄风格的作品对英雄行为或风格的讽刺的模仿或戏谑<br>\n English poet and diplomat known for his epigrams and light satirical verse.<br>     普赖尔，马修1664－1721英国诗人和外交官，以其机智的短诗和略带讽刺的诗闻名<br>'),(11056,'satirist','','','','satirists','n. 讽刺诗作者,讽刺家,爱挖苦别人的人',' Roman satirist whose works denounced the corruption and extravagance of the privileged classes in Rome.<br>     尤维纳利斯古罗马讽刺作家，其作品谴责了古罗马特权阶级的腐化和奢侈<br>'),(11057,'satirize','satirized','satirized','satirizing','','v. 讽刺',' Politicians are often satirized on TV and radio.<br>     政客常遭到电视与无线电广播的讥讽.<br>'),(11058,'satisfaction','','','','satisfactions','n. 满意',' The store owner received satisfaction for the damage.<br>     店主收到了对损坏的赔偿。<br>\n She felt satisfaction at having her ability recognized.<br>     她因自己的才能得到赏识而满足。<br>'),(11059,'satisfactorily','','','','','ad. 满意地',' Some English phrases can\'t be done into Chinese satisfactorily.<br>     有些英语成语是无法满意地译成汉语。<br>\n The present system has worked satisfactorily, so why change it? My advice is to leave well alone.<br>     目前这个制度执行情况令人满意，为什么要改变呢？我侍建议是听其自然。<br>'),(11060,'satisfactory','','','','','a. 令人满意的',' The answer was not quite satisfactory to him.<br>     这项答复未能使他完全满意。<br>\n Everything was turning out most satisfactory.<br>     一切都非常趁心如意。<br>'),(11061,'satisfied','','','','','a. 感到满意的<br>\nvbl. 使...满意',' The quiet contentment of a well-fed child satisfied the tired mother.<br>     孩子喂饱后不哭不闹的满足状使疲惫的母亲很满意。<br>\n We are satisfied with the smoothness of the negotiation.<br>     我们对谈判的顺利进行很满意。<br>'),(11062,'satisfy','satisfied','satisfied','satisfying','','v. 使...满意,赔偿',' Just to satisfy my curiosity, how much did you pay for your car?<br>     我只是出于好奇，请问你买这辆车花了多少钱？<br>\n Some people are very hard to satisfy.<br>     有些人是很难使其满意的。<br>'),(11063,'satisfying','','','','','a. 满意的,充份的,足可相信的',' That is a satisfying book.<br>     那是一本令人满意的书。<br>\n Let me reassure you( that) your service is quite satisfying.<br>     让我向您保证，您的服务是很令人满意的。<br>'),(11064,'satrap','','','','','n. 暴吏,主管',''),(11065,'saturate','','','','','v. 使渗透,浸,使饱和<br>\na. 浸透的,饱度高的,深颜色的',' We lay on the beach, saturated in sunshine.<br>     我们躺在沙滩上, 沐浴在阳光里.<br>'),(11066,'saturated','','','','','a. 饱和的,渗透的,深颜色的',' We lay on the beach, saturated in sunshine.<br>     我们躺在沙滩上, 沐浴在阳光里.<br>\n The Water has been saturated with a special chemical