e saving club always pays out into time for Christmas.<br>     存款俱乐部总是在圣诞节时及时将钱支出。<br>'),(11092,'savings','','','','','储蓄',' The old man kept his savings in the bank.<br>     老人把他的储蓄存在银行里。<br>\n My savings amount to $2000.<br>     我的储蓄共达2000美元。<br>'),(11093,'savings account','','','','','n. 储蓄存款帐户',' My savings account is low.<br>     我的存款几乎用完了<br>\n My savings account draws5 per cent interest.<br>     我的储蓄存款有五厘利息。<br>'),(11094,'savior','','','','saviors','n. 救助者,救世主,救主',' To Christians, Jesus Christ is the Savior.<br>     对基督徒来说，主耶稣是他们的救世主。<br>\n Jesus Christ is styled the Savior.<br>     耶稣基督被称为救世主。<br>'),(11095,'saviour','','','','','n. 救助者(救星)',' To Christians, Jesus Christ is the Saviour.<br>     对基督徒来说，主耶稣是他们的救世主。<br>'),(11096,'savoir faire','','','','','n. 才干,急智,手腕',''),(11097,'savoir-faire','','','','','n. 机智',''),(11098,'savor','savored','savored','savoring','','n. 滋味, 气味, 食欲, 特定的味道或气味, 一种有特色的性质<br>\nvi. 有...的滋味, 有...气味<br>\nvt. 加调味品于, 使有风味, 尝到或闻到, 尽情享受',' He drank the wine slowly, savoring every drop.<br>     他慢慢地喝着酒，细细品尝着每滴酒的滋味。<br>\n Life seems to have lost most of its savor for him.<br>     对他来说，生活似乎已失去了一切乐趣。<br>'),(11099,'savory','','','','','a. 风味极佳的,可口的,味香的',' This place doesn\'t have a very savory reputation.<br>     这个地方的名声可不太好。<br>\n This restaurant is famous for its savory dishes.<br>     这家饭店以饭菜美味而出名。<br>'),(11100,'savour','','','','','n. 味道(滋味)<br>\nvt 具有...味道(具有...性质)',' Life seems to have lost most of its savour for him.<br>     对他来说，生活似乎已失去了一切乐趣。<br>\n He drank the wine slowly, savouring every drop.<br>     他慢慢地喝着酒，细细品尝着每滴酒的滋味。<br>'),(11101,'savoury','','','','','a. 芳香开胃的,美味可口的',' This restaurant is famous for its savoury dishes.<br>     这家饭店以饭菜美味而出名。<br>\n This place doesn\'t have a very savoury reputation.<br>     这个地方的名声可不太好。<br>'),(11102,'savvy','savvied','savvied','savvying','','v.&n. 理解能力,机智,悟性',' Where\'s your savvy?<br>     你的常识到哪里去了?<br>\n Keep your mouth shut! Savvy?<br>     闭上嘴! 懂吗?<br>'),(11103,'saw','sawed','sawed','sawing','','