r scabrous novels shocked the public.<br>     她的小说淫秽不堪, 公众十分震惊.<br>'),(11116,'scaffold','scaffolded','scaffolded','scaffolding','scaffolds','n. 鹰架,绞刑台,脚手架',' The worker fell down from the scaffold.<br>     那个工人从脚手架掉了下来。<br>\n The brick-layer at the top of the scaffold is calling for more mortar.<br>     脚手架顶上的砌砖工人喊着要人再送些灰浆上去。<br>'),(11117,'scalar','','','','','标量(的)',''),(11118,'scald','scalded','scalded','scalding','scalds','n. 烫(烫伤,用沸水烫,用蒸汽烫)<br>\nvt 烫(烫伤,用沸水烫,用蒸汽烫)',' She was scalded when the boiler exploded.<br>     锅炉爆炸时她被烫伤了。<br>\n This is an ointment for burns and scalds.<br>     这是治疗烧伤和烫伤的药膏。<br>'),(11119,'scalding','','','','','a. 滚烫的',' The coffee was scalding hot.<br>     这咖啡是滚烫的。<br>\n As if scalding her arm wasn\'t enough, she went and broke her ankle the next day.<br>     她烫伤了手臂还不算，竟然在第二天出去摔伤了踝节部。<br>'),(11120,'scale','scaled','scaled','scaling','','n. 鳞,刻度,衡量,数值范围<br>\nv. 依比例决定,攀登',' Scale the fish before cooking them.<br>     烧鱼之前先去掉鱼鳞。<br>\n We are seeing unemployment on an unprecedented scale.<br>     我们现在正经历规模空前的失业现象。<br>'),(11121,'scaling','','','','','缩放比例',' The act of scaling a fortified wall or rampart.<br>     攀登，爬云梯攀登设防的高墙或城垣的行为<br>\n The paint is scaling off.<br>     油漆正在脱落。<br>'),(11122,'scallion','','','','','n. 葱',''),(11123,'scallop','scalloped','scalloped','scalloping','scallops','n. 扇贝壳<br>\nv. 拾扇贝',' Some people like to eat scallop.<br>     有些人喜欢吃干贝。<br>\n She wears a dress with scallops around the neck.<br>     她穿着一件领口有扇形皱褶的衣裙。　<br>'),(11124,'scalp','scalped','scalped','scalping','scalps','n. 头皮(胜利品)<br>\nvt 刮光(拨顶)',' You\'ve just about scalped me!<br>     你把我的头发剃得太短了！<br>\n The Indians came back with their enemy\'s scalps.<br>     印地安人带着敌人的头皮回来了。<br>'),(11125,'scalpel','','','','','n. 外科手术刀,解剖刀',' The doctor finished the operation, but his success depended on the backroom boys who had invented the new laser scalpel.<br>     医生做完了手术，但他的成功有赖于那些发明了新型激光手术刀的研究人员。<br>'),(11126,'scaly','','','','','a. 鳞状的',' A congenital, often hereditary skin disease characterized by dry, thickened, scaly skin.<br>     鳞癣，干皮病一种先天的，经常是遗传性的皮肤病，表现为皮肤干燥、变厚并出现鳞状屑片<br>'),(11127,'scam','','','','','n. 诡计,故事',''),(11128,'scamper','scampered','scampered','scampering','scampers','n. 蹦跳<br>\nv. 奔跑,快跑<br>\nvi. 涉猎,浏览',' Giggling, the children scampered back into the house.<br>     孩子们咯咯笑着，蹦蹦跳跳地跑回屋里。<br>\n The children were scampering around the garden.<br>     孩子们在花园里嬉戏奔跑。<br>'),(11129,'scan','scanned','scanned','scanning','','n. 扫描,押韵,细查<br>\nv. 扫描,详细调查,分析韵律',' The radar scanned the sky for enemy planes.<br>     雷达密切监视天空，搜索敌机。<br>\n I scanned the newspaper when I was waiting for the bus.<br>     等公共汽车的时候，我匆匆浏览了一下报纸。<br>'),(11130,'scandal','','','','scandals','n. 丑闻',' The President is at the center of a recent scandal over revelation about his financial interests.<br>     总统因近来被揭露涉嫌金融权益问题而成为丑闻的主角。<br>\n The recent scandal has provided the government\'s opponents with plenty of ammunition.<br>     最近的丑闻给政府的反对派提供了大量的炮弹。<br>'),(11131,'scandalous','','','','','a. 不体面的,可耻的,可恶的',' We are surprised by his scandalous behaviour.<br>     我们很震惊他那令人反感的举止。<br>\n The book contains scandalous text.<br>     该书含有诽谤性的内容。<br>'),(11132,'Scandinavia','','','','','斯堪的纳维亚',' Scandinavia refers to Denmark, Norway, Sweden and Iceland.<br>     斯堪的那维亚是指丹麦、挪威、瑞典和冰岛。<br>\n The people of Scandinavia; the Scandinavians.<br>     斯堪的纳维亚民族；斯堪的纳维亚人<br>'),(11133,'Scandinavian','','','','','a. 斯堪的纳维亚的',' One of two words derived from the same historical source by different routes of transmission, such as skirt from Scandinavian and shirt from English.<br>     同源词词源相同但是传播途径不同的一对词中的一个，如skirt来自斯堪的纳维亚语和shirt来自英语<br>\n A supernatural creature of Scandinavian folklore, variously portrayed as a friendly or mischievous dwarf or as a giant, that lives in caves, in the hills, or under bridges.<br>     巨人，巨怪斯堪的那维亚民间传说中的超自然的生物，时而被描述成友好的或顽皮的侏儒，时而被描述成巨人，居住在山洞里、小山上或桥下<br>'),(11134,'scanner','','','','','n. 扫描机,扫描盘,光电子扫描装置',''),(11135,'scant','scanted','scanted','scanting','','a. 不充分的,不足的<br>\nv. 减缩,吝啬',' He paid scant attention to what was said.<br>     他没怎么听讲。<br>\n The movers gave me a scant hour\'s notice of their arrival.<br>     搬家的人只通知给我们短短的一小时，他们就来了。<br>'),(11136,'scanty','','','','','a. 缺乏的,仅有的,不够的',' He is scanty with words.<br>     他沉默寡言。<br>\n The beggar shivered in his scanty clothes.<br>     乞丐穿着单薄，冻得发抖。<br>'),(11137,'scapegoat','scapegoated','','scapegoating','','n. 替罪的羔羊,替人顶罪者,替身',' The accused was used as a scapegoat.<br>     被告成为别人的替罪羊。<br>\n The old curmudgeon found a new scapegoat and that let me out.<br>     那个老守财奴找到一个新的替罪羊，这样我就脱身了。<br>'),(11138,'scar','','','','','n. 疤痕,伤痕,断崖<br>\nv. 结疤,使...有伤痕,痊愈',' The wound gradually scarred over.<br>     伤口渐渐愈合。<br>\n He had a scar on his arm from an accident.<br>     他的手臂上因为事故留下了一个伤疤。<br>'),(11139,'scarce','','','','','a. 缺乏的,不足的,稀少的,罕见的',' Good fruit is scarce in winter and costs a lot.<br>     好的水果冬天难得见到，而且价格昂贵。<br>\n I could scarce believe my eyes.<br>     我几乎不敢相信自己的眼睛。<br>'),(11140,'scarcely','','','','','ad. 几乎不,简直没有,勉强',' Scarcely had he arrived when he had to leave again.<br>     他刚刚到达就不得不又离开。<br>\n He spoke scarcely a word of English.<br>     他几乎连一个英文单词都不会说。<br>'),(11141,'scarcity','','','','scarcities','n. 缺乏,不足,缺少',' The scarcity of food forced prices up.<br>     食物短缺促使物价上涨。<br>\n The factory is in frequent scarcity of raw materials.<br>     这个工厂经常原料不足。<br>'),(11142,'scare','scared','scared','scaring','scares','vt. 惊吓(惊恐,惊慌)<br>\nn. 惊吓(惊恐,惊慌)',' The child was scared of the fierce looking dog.<br>     这孩子害怕那条外表凶恶的狗。<br>\n You did give me a scare.<br>     你真吓了我一跳。<br>'),(11143,'scared','','','','','a. 害怕的',' The child was scared of the fierce looking dog.<br>     这孩子害怕那条外表凶恶的狗。<br>\n The dog scared the thief away.<br>     狗把小偷吓走了。<br>'),(11144,'scarf','','','','','n. 围巾',' She wore a woolen scarf around her neck.<br>     她脖子上戴了一条羊毛围巾。<br>\n She threw a scarf over her shoulders.<br>     她在肩上披上一块肩巾。<br>'),(11145,'scarify','scarified','scarified','scarifying','','v. 在(皮肤上)划痕',''),(11146,'scarlet','','','','','n. 深红色,斐红色,红衣<br>\na. 肥斐色的,深红色的',' Scarlet is much lighter than crimson.<br>     绯红色比深红色亮丽得多。<br>\n The girl planted some scarlet sage in her garden.<br>     女孩在她的花园里种了些一串红。<br>'),(11147,'scarlet fever','','','','','猩红热',' Scarlet fever is highly contagious.<br>     猩红热传染性很强。<br>\n James was quarantined for three weeks when he had scarlet fever.<br>     詹姆士患猩红热后被隔离了三个星期。<br>'),(11148,'scarp','scarped','scarped','scarping','','n. 悬崖,陡坡',''),(11149,'scars','','','','','冻结物',' The boat has scars from hitting the reefs.<br>     船只因撞在暗礁上而留下了疤痕。<br>\n The scars on his body lent colour to his claim that he had been tortured.<br>     他说他受过折磨拷打, 从他身上的伤疤看来倒也可信.<br>'),(11150,'scary','','','','','a. 容易受惊的,胆小的,提心吊胆',' That\'s scary! 　　<br>     真令人害怕！<br>'),(11151,'scathe','scathed','scathed','scathing','','n. 危害,损伤,损害<br>\nv. 损伤,伤害',''),(11152,'scathing','','','','','a. 严厉的,尖刻的',' The report is scathing about the lack of safety precaution.<br>     该报道对缺乏安全预防措施一事严加指责。<br>\n The scathing editorial simply boils down to an exercise in partisan politics.<br>     措词强烈的社论可以简单地归结为政党政治的纲领<br>'),(11153,'scatter','scattered','scattered','scattering','','n. 散播之物,散布<br>\nv. 散开,散布,散播',' The farmers were scattering seed on the fields.<br>     农夫把种子撒在田里。<br>\n The birds scattered at the sound of the gun.<br>     鸟群一听到枪声就四处飞散了。<br>'),(11154,'scatterbrain','','','','','n. 注意力不集中的人',''),(11155,'scattered','','','','','分散的',' Scattered showers are expected this afternoon.<br>     预料今天下午有零星阵雨。<br>\n Tartar hordes scattered on the plain.<br>     鞑靼人的游牧部落散布在这片平原上。<br>'),(11156,'scavenge','scavenged','scavenged','scavenging','','v. 打扫,排除废气,到处觅食',''),(11157,'scavenger','','','','','n. 清除剂(清道工,选池,基接受体)',' He is just fit for a job as scavenger.<br>     他正好当个清道夫之职。<br>\n A small fraction of the creatures that die are preserved in this way before decay sets in or, even more likely, before scavengers eat them.<br>     只有一小部分死掉的生物在开始腐烂前，或者更可能的情况是，在食腐动物吃掉它们之前如此地保存起来。<br>'),(11158,'scenario','','','','scenarios','n. 情节,剧本',' It looked ominously like we were about to repeat the earlier scenario.<br>     而且看上去很不妙，好象我们又得重复上次那一幕了。<br>\n For the rest of the day the port presented a scenario of furious productivity, guaranteed to warm the cockles of the dock boss\'s heart.<br>     那天其余的时间里，码头掀起了戏剧化的生产高潮，保证让船坞老板心满意足。<br>'),(11159,'scene','','','','scenes','n. 场,景,情景',' And now the scene shifts to the warehouse, where the murderer is lying in wait.<br>     现在场景转到仓库，行凶者正埋伏在那里伺机行动。<br>\n Our reporter was the first person on the scene.<br>     我们的记者是最先到达出事地点的。<br>'),(11160,'scenery','','','','','n. 风景',' We passed through some beautiful scenery on our journey through this district.<br>     我们在穿越这个地区的旅途中，看到了不少美丽的景色。<br>\n The scenery was beautiful beyond expression.<br>     那风景美丽得无法形容。<br>'),(11161,'scenic','','','','','a. 风景好的,戏剧性的',' The scenic splendors of the Rocky Mountains are overwhelming.<br>     落基山脉的壮丽景色使人赞叹不已。<br>\n There is a scenic route across the Alps.<br>     穿越阿尔卑斯山有一条风景优美的路径。<br>'),(11162,'scent','scented','scented','scenting','scents','n. 气味,香味,痕迹<br>\nv. 闻出,循著遗臭追踪,发觉',' The police are on the scent of the thieves.<br>     警察发现了小偷的线索。<br>\n There is a lavender scent and rosemary scent in the air.<br>     空气中有熏衣草和迷迭香花的味道。<br>'),(11163,'scepter','sceptered','sceptered','sceptering','scepters','n. 君主节杖v. 拥登王位,授与王权',''),(11164,'sceptic','','','','','n. 怀疑(论)者,多疑的人',' The government must still convince the sceptics that its policy will work.<br>     政府仍须使持怀疑态度的人相信其政策可行.<br>\n The government must still convince the sceptic that its policy will work.<br>     政府仍须使持怀疑态度的人相信其政策可行。<br>'),(11165,'sceptical','','','','','a. 怀疑的',' My assurances don\'t satisfy him: he\'s still sceptical.<br>     我说的确确实实他都不信，仍有疑虑。<br>\n Mary is sceptical about the solution.<br>     玛丽对这个解决办法表示怀疑。<br>'),(11166,'scepticism','','','','','n. 怀疑',''),(11167,'sceptre','sceptred','sceptred','sceptring','','n. 权杖,君权',' Sceptres are carried by kings as a sign of power.<br>     国王所持的权杖是权力的象征。<br>\n The sceptre is an attribute of kingly power.<br>     节杖是国王权力的象徵.<br>'),(11168,'schedule','scheduled','scheduled','scheduling','schedules','n. 时间表,一览表,计划<br>\nv. 安排,计划,预定,编制目录',' The project was completed ahead of the schedule.<br>     这项工程提前完工。<br>\n We\'ve already finished the work anterior to the schedule.<br>     我们已经提前完成了工作。<br>'),(11169,'scheduled','','','','','a. 预定的<br>\nv. 预定,编制目录<br>\nvbl. 预定,编制目录',' The train is due (in) (ie scheduled to arrive) in five minutes.<br>     火车预定在5分钟後到达.<br>\n The building is scheduled for completion in May.<br>     该大楼预定或计划于5月份完工。<br>'),(11170,'scheduler','','','','','调度程序',''),(11171,'schema','','','','schemata','图解,计划,模式',''),(11172,'schematic','','','','','a. 扼要的,图解的',''),(11173,'schematize','schematized','schematized','schematizing','','v. 扼要表示',''),(11174,'scheme','schemed','schemed','scheming','schemes','n. 方案,计划,阴谋<br>\nv. 计画,设计,体系，结构,图谋',' He examined the wiring scheme carefully.<br>     他仔细检查线路图。<br>\n She saw the possibilities of the scheme from the beginning.<br>     她从一开始就预见到这计画可能成功。<br>'),(11175,'scheming','','','','','a. 诡计多端,计划的',' A scheming person.<br>     诡计多端者<br>\n The committee decided to make a withdrawal of financial support for his scheme.<br>     委员会决定取消对他那项计划的资助。<br>'),(11176,'scherzo','','','','scherzoi','n. 谐谑曲',''),(11177,'schism','','','','','n. 分裂,分立,宗派分立罪',' A person claiming to be or elected pope in opposition to the one chosen by church law, as during a schism.<br>     伪教皇在教会分立中宣称教皇或被选为教皇的人，与教会律法选出的教皇对立<br>'),(11178,'schismatic','','','','','a. 分裂的',''),(11179,'schizophrenia','','','','','n. 精神分裂症',' A type of schizophrenia, usually starting at puberty, characterized by foolish mannerisms, senseless laughter, delusions, hallucinations, and regressive behavior.<br>     青春期痴呆一种精神分裂症，通常始发于青春期，其特征为举止痴呆、傻笑、妄想、幻觉以及退化的举止<br>'),(11180,'scholar','','','','scholars','n. 学者',' He ranks high as a scholar.<br>     他是第一流的学者。<br>\n We all listened to the venerable scholar with awe.<br>     我们都怀着敬畏之心倾听着这位德高望重的学者的讲话。<br>'),(11181,'scholarly','','','','','a. 学究气的(学者派头的)',' He could not fully understand these involved scholarly lectures.<br>     这些艰深的学术讲演他不能完全听懂。<br>\n A formal written composition intended to be published, presented, or read aloud; a scholarly essay or treatise.<br>     学术论文一篇写好的正式著作，为了出版、讲演或宣读；学术文章或论文<br>'),(11182,'scholarship','','','','scholarships','n. 奖学金,学问,学识',' He won a scholarship to Cambridge.<br>     他获得一份到剑桥大学读书的奖学金。<br>\n The teacher had both extensive knowledge and profound scholarship.<br>     先生的学问博大精深。<br>'),(11183,'scholastic','','','','','a. (formal)学术的,学习的',' A fixed amount of scholastic study used as a basis for calculating academic credits, usually measured in hours of classroom instruction or laboratory work.<br>     上课时量，计算学分的学习量学术研究的固定量，用作计算专科院校学分的基础，通常按教室教育或实验室工作的小时测量<br>\n He is unfitted for scholastic life.<br>     他不适於学者生涯。<br>'),(11184,'school','','','','','n. 学校',' She studies in a high school.<br>     她在一所中学学习。<br>\n He was schooled by life itself.<br>     他受了生活本身的熏陶。<br>'),(11185,'school board','','','','','(地方政府的)联合校董会,教育委员会',''),(11186,'school bus','','','','','n. 校车',''),(11187,'school day','','','','','n. 上课日',' May your future be as success flu as your school day had been.<br>     祝你将如同过去在学校一样事事成功。<br>\n He went to the badminton club at times during his school days.<br>     他上学时有时到羽毛球俱乐部去。<br>'),(11188,'school year','','','','','学年',' The coach checked the football uniforms at the end of the school year.<br>     教练在每个学年末都把足球运动服收回登记。<br>\n An examination given in the middle of a school year.<br>     学年中期考试一学年中期进行的考试<br>'),(11189,'schoolbook','','','','','n. 课本,教科书',''),(11190,'schoolboy','','','','schoolboys','n. 男学生',' These schoolboys decided to go outing.<br>     这些男学生决定去野游。<br>\n Even a schoolboy could manage (ie write) a better story than that.<br>     连小学生写的故事都比那个好.<br>'),(11191,'schoolfellow','','','','','n. 同学',''),(11192,'schoolgirl','','','','schoolgirls','n. 女生,女学生',' This schoolgirl likes to do some needlework.<br>     这个女学生喜欢做针线活。<br>\n The ratio of schoolboys to schoolgirls is 2 to 1.<br>     男学生和女学生的比例是2比1。<br>'),(11193,'schoolhouse','','','','schoolhouses','n. 校舍',' The roof of the schoolhouse is covered with snow.<br>     校舍的屋顶上覆盖着积雪。<br>'),(11194,'schooling','','','','','n. 学校教育',' He has little real schooling.<br>     他几没受过正式的学校教育。<br>\n Who\'s paying for her schooling?<br>     谁在供她读书?<br>'),(11195,'schoolmaster','','','','schoolmasters','n. 教师,男教员,校长',' What did the schoolmaster say?<br>     校长说了些什么？<br>\n A male teacher, schoolmaster, or tutor.<br>     男老师、校长或家庭教师<br>'),(11196,'schoolmate','','','','schoolmates','n. 同窗,同学',' Does she help her schoolmate to have known his mistake?<br>     她是否帮助她的同学认识了他的错误？<br>'),(11197,'schoolmistress','','','','','n. 女教师,女校长',''),(11198,'schoolroom','','','','schoolrooms','n. 教室',' How many schoolrooms are there in this college?<br>     这所大学里有多少教室？<br>'),(11199,'schoolteacher','','','','schoolteachers','n. 教师',''),(11200,'schoolwork','','','','','n. (包括课堂作业和家庭作业)作业',' Is her schoolwork up to scratch?<br>     她的功课行吗?<br>\n Activity, such as schoolwork or office work, meant to take up time but not necessarily yield productive results.<br>     无生产性工作，机关工作占用时间但不必要获得生产结果的活动，如学校工作或机关工作<br>'),(11201,'schoolyard','','','','','n. 校园,运动场',' I thought he was making fun of me and ran faster than ever reaching the schoolyard quite out of breath.<br>     我以为他在取笑我，就越发跑得快起来，到达学校时我都上气不接下气了。<br>'),(11202,'schooner','','','','schooners','n. 纵帆船',' He drank a schooner of beer and became drunken.<br>     他喝了一大酒杯啤酒后醉倒了。<br>'),(11203,'science','','','','sciences','n. 科学',' I like to read science fiction.<br>     我喜欢读科幻小说。<br>\n The college graduated 50 students from the science department last year.<br>     这所学院去年有50名理科毕业生.<br>'),(11204,'science fiction','','','','','n. 科幻小说',' I like to read science fiction.<br>     我喜欢读科幻小说。<br>\n The science fiction film had some marvellous special effects.<br>     这部科幻电影有些特殊效果美妙绝伦.<br>'),(11205,'scientific','','','','','a. 科学的',' We all support his scientific research.<br>     我们都支持他的科学研究。<br>\n She has a very scientific method of dealing with political problems.<br>     她处理政治问题的方法很科学。<br>'),(11206,'scientifically','','','','','ad. 合乎科学地,学问上,有系统地',''),(11207,'scientist','','','','scientists','n. 科学家',' Scientists haven\'t found the pathogeny of the disease.<br>     科学家们尚未发现这种病的病因。<br>\n A German scientist interrupted me and asked if I came from China.<br>     一位德国科学家打断了我，并问我是否来自中国。<br>'),(11208,'sci-fi','','','','','n. (science fiction的缩略)科幻小说',''),(11209,'scintilla','','','','scintillas','n. 火花,闪烁,些微的痕迹',''),(11210,'scintillate','scintillated','scintillated','scintillating','','vt. 闪烁(发火花)',''),(11211,'sciolism','','','','','n. 一知半解的学问',''),(11212,'scion','','','','','n. 后裔(接穗)',''),(11213,'scissor','scissored','scissored','scissoring','','n. 剪刀',''),(11214,'scissoring','','','','','剪切,删除',''),(11215,'scissors','','','','scissors','n. 剪刀',' There is a pair of scissors in the bottom drawer.<br>     最底下的抽屉里有把剪刀。<br>\n Blunt scissors don\'t cut cleanly.<br>     钝剪刀剪不齐.<br>'),(11216,'sclerosis','','','','scleroses','n. 硬化(症)',''),(11217,'scoff','','','','','n. 嘲笑,嘲弄,愚弄<br>\nv. 嘲笑,嘲弄,愚弄',' I told them my ideas but they scoffed at them.<br>     我把自己的想法告诉他们，但他们嗤之以鼻。<br>\n Who has scoffed all the pastries down?<br>     谁把点心全吃完了？<br>'),(11218,'scold','scolded','scolded','scolding','scolds','n. 老爱责骂的人<br>\nv. 责骂,训斥<br>\nvi. 责骂,申斥<br>\nvt. 责骂',' The child was scolded by his mother.<br>     这个孩子受到母亲的责骂。<br>\n Don\'t scold him too much; he is at best a child.<br>     不要太责骂他；他只不过是个孩子。<br>'),(11219,'scoop','scooped','scooped','scooping','scoops','n. 铲子,舀取,独家新闻<br>\nv. 汲取,舀取,抢先登出',' There are several scoops in my kitchen.<br>     我的厨房里有好几个勺子。<br>\n She scooped all the national newspapers to get the story.<br>     她抢在全国各报之前发表了这一消息。<br>'),(11220,'scooter','','','','scooters','n. 小轮摩托车，小孩滑板车',' For sale: small motor scooter. Enquire within.<br>     待售：小型摩托车，请进内询问。<br>'),(11221,'scope','','','','','n. 范围',' Your question is beyond the scope of this book.<br>     你所问的问题已超出了这本书的范围。<br>\n It is within my scope.<br>     那是在我的范围之内。<br>'),(11222,'scorch','scorched','scorched','scorching','scorches','n. 烧焦<br>\nv. 使烧焦,变焦,使枯萎',' The long drought scorched the grass.<br>     久旱使青草枯萎。<br>\n The meat will scorch if you don\'t lower the gas.<br>     如果你不把煤气调小一点，肉就要焦了。<br>'),(11223,'scorcher','','','','','n. 极热的东西(大热天,高速行驶的驾驶员)',' The bowler let go a couple of scorchers.<br>     投球手投出了几个快球.<br>\n Whew! It\'s a real scorcher today!<br>     哟! 今天可太热了!<br>'),(11224,'scorching','','','','','a. 灼热的',' He drew back from the scorching heat.<br>     他从灼人的热气中退了回来。<br>\n It\'s scorching hot.<br>     天气热得火烧似的。<br>'),(11225,'score','scored','scored','scoring','scores','n. 得分,刻痕,二十;背景音乐<br>\nv. 刻划,划线,得分',' The score was five-nil with five minute left in the game.<br>     比赛离终场还有五分钟时，双方比分为五比零。<br>\n Arsenal scored in the final minute of the game.<br>     阿森纳队在比赛的最后一分钟进了一球。<br>'),(11226,'scoreboard','','','','','n. 记分板',''),(11227,'scorer','','','','','n. (竞赛等的)记分员,记录员,得分者',' He\'s manchester\'s top scorer.<br>     他是曼联队的头号得分手。<br>'),(11228,'scoring','','','','','n. 得分',' Scoring ability or potential.<br>     得分率得分的能力或潜力<br>\n A hard rubber disk used in ice hockey as the playing and scoring medium.<br>     冰球冰球比赛中用于击打和得分的硬橡皮盘状物<br>'),(11229,'scorn','scorned','scorned','scorning','','n. 轻蔑,被叱责的人<br>\nv. 轻蔑,不屑做',' He poured scorn on my suggestion.<br>     他对我的建议表示轻蔑。<br>\n She scorned our offers of help.<br>     她不屑接受我们的帮助。<br>'),(11230,'scornful','','','','','a. 轻蔑的',' He gave a scornful laugh at my proposal.<br>     他对我的建议轻蔑地一笑。<br>\n We are scornful of the forces of convention.<br>     我们藐视习惯势力。<br>'),(11231,'scornfully','','','','','ad. 轻蔑地',' Scornfully contemptuous ridicule; derision.<br>     嘲讽责备地鄙视可笑之事；嘲笑<br>'),(11232,'scorpion','','','','scorpions','n. 蝎子,心黑的人,蝎子鞭',' A scorpion has a poisonous sting in its long jointed tail.<br>     蝎子的长尾巴上长着一个