INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (11234,'Scotch','','','','','n. 苏格兰人,苏格兰语,伤口,刻痕<br>\na. 苏格兰人的,苏格兰语的<br>\nvt. 弄伤,制止(车轮)转动,镇压,扑灭',' The doctor scotched her false story.<br>     医生戳穿了她的骗局。<br>\n Anyway, there never was any one more Scotch in this wide world.<br>     不管怎样，普天之下没有人比他更像一个苏格兰人了。<br>'),(11235,'Scotch whisky','','','','','苏格兰威士忌',''),(11236,'Scotland','','','','','n. 苏格兰',' These two tourists came from Scotland.<br>     这两名游客来自苏格兰。<br>\n Cold northerlies will bring rain to Scotland this week.<br>     寒冷的北风本星期将给苏格兰带来雨水。<br>'),(11237,'Scots','','','','','a. 苏格兰(人)的',' The Scots have distilled whisky for centuries.<br>     苏格兰人用蒸馏法制威士忌酒已有数百年历史.<br>\n Mary, Queen of Scots, was put to death in1587.<br>     苏格兰王后玛丽于1587年被处死。<br>'),(11238,'Scotsman','','','','','n. 苏格兰人',' What does a Scotsman wear underneath his kilt?<br>     苏格兰男子在短裙下面穿著什麽?<br>'),(11239,'Scott','','','','','n. 斯科特(m.)',' When Scott reached the South Pole he found Amundsen had anticipated him.<br>     当斯科特抵达南极的时候, 发现阿蒙森比他到得更早.<br>\n Paul has tracked down an early recording of Scott Joplin playing one of his rags.<br>     保罗已找到了斯科特·乔普林所演奏过的一个散拍乐曲的早期录音。<br>'),(11240,'Scottish','','','','','a. 苏格兰的<br>\nn. 苏格兰人',' This Scottish plant was a gift from my cousin.<br>     这棵苏格兰植物是我的一个表亲给我的礼物。<br>\n She is Scottish on her mother\'s side.<br>     根据母系的血缘，她是苏格兰的后裔。<br>'),(11241,'scoundrel','','','','scoundrels','n.&a. 无赖(的)',' The scoundrel was arrested and put into prison.<br>     这个恶棍被逮捕并被投进了监狱。<br>\n An unscrupulous, dishonest person; a scoundrel.<br>     流氓，无赖不守法，不诚实之人；恶棍<br>'),(11242,'scoundrelly','','','','','n. 恶棍(无赖,流氓)',''),(11243,'scour','','','','','vt. 擦洗(疏浚,腐蚀,搜索,飞快地跑过)<br>\nn. 摩擦(冲洗)',' The police scoured the area looking for the lost child.<br>     警方搜遍这个地区寻找这个走失的孩子。<br>\n He scoured off the dirt from the floor.<br>     他擦去地板上的污垢。<br>'),(11244,'scourge','scourged','scourged','scourging','scourges','n. 惩罚(灾难,祸患)<br>\nvt 折磨(使...痛苦,严惩)',' The old man is scourged by a guilty conscience.<br>     这个老人受到负