音,乱写<br>\nv. 搔痒,抓,抹掉',' The recording was spoiled by scratches.<br>     录音被沙沙声破坏了。<br>\n Somebody has scratched his name off the list.<br>     有人已经把他的名字从名单上划去了。<br>'),(11257,'scrawl','scrawled','scrawled','scrawling','scrawls','vt. 乱涂<br>\nn. 瞎画',' She scrawled a few words on the postcard.<br>     她在明信片上草草地写了几个字。<br>\n Her signature was an illegible scrawl.<br>     她的签字潦草难辩。<br>'),(11258,'scream','screamed','screamed','screaming','screams','n. 尖叫声<br>\nv. 尖叫,大笑',' The boy was screaming with pain.<br>     这男孩痛得尖叫起来。<br>\n She screamed herself hoarse.<br>     她把嗓子喊哑了。<br>'),(11259,'screamer','','','','','n. 尖声叫喊的人, <美俚>(报刊上的)惊人的标题',''),(11260,'screaming','','','','','a. 尖声的,发出尖叫声的',' The boy was screaming with pain.<br>     这男孩痛得尖叫起来。<br>\n Those cats have been screaming for hours.<br>     那些猫叫了半天了.<br>'),(11261,'scree','','','','','n. 山坡上的碎石堆',''),(11262,'screech','screeched','screeched','screeching','screeches','n. 尖声喊叫,尖叫声,急煞车时车子的煞车声<br>\nv. 尖著声音讲,发出尖锐的声音',' The gate screeched as it opened.<br>     大门打开时发出刺耳的声音。<br>\n He heard a screech of brakes and then fell down.<br>     他听到汽车刹车发出的尖锐的声音，然后就摔倒了。<br>'),(11263,'screed','','','','','n. 冗长的句子,泥水匠用的匀泥尺',''),(11264,'screen','screened','screened','screening','screens','n. 屏,幕,银幕,屏风<br>\nv. 选拔,掩蔽,遮蔽',' You can\'t screen your children from the real life forever.<br>     你不能永远护住自己的子女，不让他们接触现实生活。<br>\n His job at the bank was just a screen for his life as a spy.<br>     他在银行的工作仅仅是他当间谍的一种掩护。<br>'),(11265,'screen dump','','','','','屏幕转储',''),(11266,'screen memory','','','','','屏幕存储器',''),(11267,'screening','','','','','n. 遮蔽(屏蔽,筛,防波,筛屑)',' A screening against light or heat.<br>     遮蔽光或热的遮挡物<br>\n A revolving cylindrical sieve used for screening or sizing rock and ore.<br>     滚筒筛一种圆筒形的可旋转的筛，用于岩石和矿石的筛分或大小测量<br>'),(11268,'screenplay','','','','','n. 电影剧本,剧本',''),(11269,'screenwriter','','','','','n. 电影剧本作家,编剧家',''),(11270,'screw','screwed','screwed','screwing','screws','n. 螺丝钉,吝啬鬼,压迫<br>\nv. 扭紧,压榨',' The table legs are screwed