riat.<br>     以前在联合国秘书处服务过的史密斯先生。<br>\n After the congress, the secretariat moved from Shanghai to Beijing.<br>     代表大会召开之后，书记处由上海迁到了北京。<br>'),(11374,'secretary','','','','secretaries','n. 秘书,部长,大臣,书记',' She is a secretary in our company.<br>     她是我们公司的一位秘书。<br>\n The secretary said that the programme to phase down British air operations in Indo China is solidly based and progressing.<br>     部长说减少英军在印度支那的空中作战计划是有坚实基础的，并在进展中。<br>'),(11375,'secrete','secreted','secreted','secreting','','v. 隐秘,隐藏,隐匿<br>\nv. 分泌',' He found the money secreted in a drawer.<br>     他找到了藏在抽屉里的钱。<br>\n The kidneys secrete urine.<br>     肾脏是分泌尿液的器官。<br>'),(11376,'secretin','','','','','n. 分泌活素,分泌激素',''),(11377,'secretion','','','','secretions','n. 分泌,分泌物,分泌液',' The secretion of bile is useful for our bodies.<br>     胆汁的分泌对我们的身体很有用处。<br>\n Saliva is secretion of the salivary glands.<br>     唾液是唾液腺的分泌物。<br>'),(11378,'secretive','','','','','a. 密秘的,偷偷摸摸的',' I don\'t know why Fred is always secretive as regards his family.<br>     我不知道为什么凡涉及到他的家，弗雷德总是保密。<br>'),(11379,'secretly','','','','','ad. 秘密地,背地里',' Not in public; secretly or confidentially.<br>     秘密地非公开地；秘密地或在私下地<br>\n The boy slipped out of the room and headed for the swimming pool secretly.<br>     这孩子偷偷摸摸地溜出了屋子, 走向游泳池。<br>'),(11380,'sect','','','','sects','n. 分丐,宗派,教派',' The break-away sect was contemned by other religious groups.<br>     这个分裂出去的派别受到其他宗教团体的蔑视。<br>\n Each religious sect in the town have its own church.<br>     该城每一个宗教教派都有自己的教堂。<br>'),(11381,'sectarian','','','','','a. 宗派的,党派心强的,偏狭的<br>\nn. 属于宗派的人,宗派心强的人',''),(11382,'section','sectioned','sectioned','sectioning','sections','n. 部分,章节,部门,路段<br>\n断面,剖面,截面<br>\nv. 划分 [同]divide',' Signals control each section of the railway track.<br>     各种信号控制着铁路轨道的每个部分。<br>\n First the surgeon performed the section of the blood vessel.<br>     外科医生首先切开血管。<br>'),(11383,'sectional','','','','','a. 各部分组成的,各阶层或不同部分的',''),(11384,'sections','','','','','零件',' He had the support of large sections of the populace.<br>     他获得大多数民众的支持。<br>\n White lines divide the playing area into sections.<br>     这些白线把赛区分成各个部分.<br>'),(11385,'sector','sectored','sectored','sectoring','sectors','n. 扇形,扇区<br>\nn. 部门,区域',' The government made an investigation of the employment in the public and private sectors.<br>     政府对国营和私营部门的就业情况作了一次调查。<br>\n There are several sectors unusable in this disk.<br>     这张磁盘有几个扇区坏了。<br>'),(11386,'secular','','','','seculars','n. 牧师<br>\na. 世俗的,现世的,不朽的',' Secular music refers to music which is not religious.<br>     世俗音乐是指非宗教的音乐。<br>\n A secular law, rule, or code of law.<br>     世俗法规世俗的法律、制度或法典<br>'),(11387,'secure','secured','secured','securing','','a. 无虑的,安心的,安全的<br>\nv. 固定,获得,使...安全',' He secured the release of the hostages.<br>     他已经设法使人质获释。<br>\n The little boy felt secure near his parents.<br>     那小男孩在父母身边感到安心。<br>'),(11388,'securely','','','','','ad. 安心地, 安全地',' The prisoner\'s hands were securely tied.<br>     那犯人的双手给牢牢捆住了.<br>\n Beauty gilds her vices over, which more securely harm.<br>     她的罪恶有了美丽的外表，其恶更凶。<br>'),(11389,'securities','','','','','n. 股票,有价证券',' Failure to receive the proceeds of a transaction, as in the sale of stock or securities, by a specified date.<br>     交割失信在股票或抵押品售出后，未能在规定日期内办理交接手续<br>\n The area of an exchange where securities are traded.<br>     交易所交易所中进行证券交易的区域<br>'),(11390,'security','','','','securities','n. 安全<br>\nn. 保证金,抵押品,债券,证券',' What I need now is the security of a happy home.<br>     我现在需要的是一个幸福家庭所给予的安全感。<br>\n He uses his house as security to borrow the money.<br>     他用房子作借钱的抵押。<br>'),(11391,'sedan','','','','sedans','n. (美)轿车',' No problem. Right this way. Here we have a great red two-door to sedan.<br>     看这边。这儿有一辆很棒的红色双门轿车。<br>\n The black sedan suddenly drew out into the traffic.<br>     黑色轿车突然开动，驶进了车流。<br>'),(11392,'sedate','','','','','a. 安静的,镇静的',' Prim and sedate.<br>     严肃沉闷的<br>'),(11393,'sedative','','','','','a. 使安静的,使镇静的<br>\nn. 镇静剂,能使安静的东西',' The doctor gave him a sedative to help him sleep.<br>     医生给了他镇静剂帮助他入睡。<br>\n I\'ve given him a sedative; that should see him through the night.<br>     我给了他一片镇静剂，可使他熬过一个夜晚。<br>'),(11394,'sedentary','','','','','a. 久坐的,固定不动的',' He leads a sedentary life.<br>     他过着久坐不动的生活。<br>\n The scribe is a sedentary worker.<br>     作家工作时需要久坐。<br>'),(11395,'sediment','','','','sediments','n. 沉淀物',' You should not drink the wine with a gritty sediment.<br>     不要喝有沙粒状沉淀物的葡萄酒。<br>\n He emptied out the water barrel to clear it of sediment.<br>     他把水桶倒空以清掉桶底的沉淀物。<br>'),(11396,'sedimentary','','','','','a. 沉淀性的',''),(11397,'sedimentation','','','','','n. 沉淀,沉降',''),(11398,'sedition','','','','','n. 煽动骚乱,妨害治安,骚动',''),(11399,'seditious','','','','','a. 煽动性的',''),(11400,'seduce','seduced','seduced','seducing','','v. 怂恿,瞒骗,引诱',' He was seduced into leaving the company by the offer of higher pay elsewhere.<br>     其他地方更优厚的薪金待遇诱使他离开了公司。<br>\n The warm weather seduced me away from my studies.<br>     暖和的天气诱使我放下了学习。<br>'),(11401,'seduction','','','','','n. 勾引,引诱,诱惑,诱奸',' Seduction from morality, allegiance, or duty.<br>     道德败坏；不忠；玩忽职守<br>'),(11402,'seductive','','','','','a. 诱惑的,引人注意的,有魅力的',' I long to be seductive and tempting. What\'s Helen got that I haven\'t got?<br>     我真希望自己富有迷人的魅力。为什么海伦就比我强呢？<br>'),(11403,'sedulous','','','','','a. 勤勉的,勤苦工作的,聚精凝神的',''),(11404,'see','saw','seen','seeing','','v. 看见,看出,明白,知道',' I looked for her in the crowd but couldn\'t see her.<br>     我在人群中寻找她，但看不到。<br>\n Do you see what I mean?<br>     你明白我的意思吗？<br>'),(11405,'seed','seeded','seeded','seeding','seeds','n. 种子<br>\nvi. (植物)结实,播种<br>\nvt. 播种',' Part of every crop is saved for seed.<br>     每一种庄稼都留一部分作种子。<br>\n The farmers were scattering seed on the fields.<br>     农夫把种子撒在田里。<br>'),(11406,'seedling','','','','seedlings','n. 幼苗',' The seedling was frozen to death.<br>     幼苗被冻死了。<br>\n The seedling have shrivel up a bit in the hot sun.<br>     在炎热的太阳光下，幼苗已有一点乾枯。<br>'),(11407,'seedtime','','','','','n. 播种时期',''),(11408,'seedy','','','','','a. 褴褛的,破旧的,不体面的',' The grapes are delicious but very seedy.<br>     葡萄好吃是好吃, 就是子儿太多.<br>'),(11409,'seeing','','','','seeings','see的现在分词<br>\nn. 视觉',' Seeing is believing.<br>     眼见为实。<br>\n Seeing that she\'s legally old enough to get married, I don\'t see how you can stop her.<br>     鉴于她已经到了法定的结婚年龄，我想象不出你怎么可以阻止她。<br>'),(11410,'Seeing is believing','','','','','眼见为实',' Seeing is believing.<br>     眼见为实。<br> Words are but wind, but seeing is believing.<br>     【谚】耳听为虚，眼见为实。<br>'),(11411,'seek','sought','sought','seeking','','n. 找寻<br>\nv. 寻求,寻找,搜索',' You should seek advice from your lawyer on this matter.<br>     这件事情你应该请教你的律师。<br>\n We sought her out to tell her of her success.<br>     我们找到她，告诉她她成功了。<br>'),(11412,'seeker','','','','','n. 搜索者,探求者',' President James A. Garfield was shot by a disappointed office seeker on July2, 1881.<br>     1881年7月2日，詹姆斯·A·加菲尔德总统被一个失望的谋求官职者枪击<br>'),(11413,'seem','seemed','seemed','seeming','','v. 像是,似乎',' He seems an energetic person.<br>     他似乎是一个精力充沛的人。<br>\n He seems to know everything.<br>     他似乎什么都懂。<br>'),(11414,'seeming','','','','seemings','a. 表面上的<br>\nn. 外观',' Seeming or professed; ostensible.<br>     假装的表面上的或自称的；貌似真实的<br>\n Seeming to be coolly unconcerned or indifferent.<br>     漠不关心的，冷淡的看上去漠不关心的或冷淡的<br>'),(11415,'seemingly','','','','','ad. 表面上(看上去)',' I\'d prefer to too really back to normal, not seemingly so.<br>     我希望你的身体能真正恢复正常，而不只是表面上有好转。<br>\n She plays with seemingly effortless skill.<br>     她演奏得似乎毫不费力.<br>'),(11416,'seemly','','','','','a. 适当的,恰当的,合式的',' Chewing gum on a train is not seemly in a lady.<br>     淑女在火车上嚼囗香糖不太雅观。<br>'),(11417,'seen','','','','','vbl. 看到',' I haven\'t seen him recently.<br>     我最近没有看到他。<br>\n The smoke of the burning house could be seen many blocks away.<br>     着火的房子的冒出的烟在几个街区外都能看到。<br>'),(11418,'seep','seeped','seeped','seeping','','v. 渗出,渗流,漏<br>\nn. 水陆两用的吉普车',' The teacher stopped speaking to allow time for the meaning of his words to seep through.<br>     那位老师停止