 The tory party is very strong in the shire.<br>     保守党在农村各郡势力很强。<br>\n I can wear a red tie with a pink shire if I want to. What of it?<br>     我愿意的话，我可以扎红色领带，穿粉红色衬衫，那又有什么不行呢？<br>'),(11775,'shirk','shirked','shirked','shirking','','v. 逃避,规避',' You\'re supposed to tidy up, so stop shirking and do it!<br>     要你来整理就别躲著了, 干吧!<br>\n She is shirking going to the dentist.<br>     她躲著不愿意去治牙.<br>'),(11776,'Shirley','','','','','n. 雪莉（女子名）',' Shirley will try out for the lead in the play.<br>     雪莉将参加该剧主角的选拔演出。<br>\n Shirley had to make over her dress because it was too big.<br>     那件衣服太大了，雪莉只好把它改一下。<br>'),(11777,'shirt','','','','shirts','n. 衬衫',' My husband has several shirts of different colors.<br>     我丈夫有好几件颜色不同的衬衫。<br>\n Would you sew this button onto my shirt?<br>     请你把这颗纽扣缝到我的衬衫上好吗？<br>'),(11778,'shirttail','','','','','n. 衬衣下摆',''),(11779,'shit','shit','shit','shitting','shits','v. 拉屎<br>\nn. 粪,屎<br>\nint. 狗屁!',' That little shit stole my money.<br>     那个小混蛋把我的钱偷走了.<br>\n He doesn\'t give a shit about anybody else.<br>     他对别人漠不关心.<br>'),(11780,'shiver','','','','','vt. 颤动(碎裂)<br>\nn. 冷颤(碎块)',' The child shivered from the cold.<br>     这孩子冷得发抖。<br>\n I could not repress a shiver whenever I thought of him.<br>     我一想到他就忍不住颤抖。<br>'),(11781,'shivery','','','','','a. 寒冷的',' I feel shivery and I have gotten a sore throat.<br>     我觉得怕冷发抖，而且喉咙疼痛。<br>'),(11782,'shoal','','','','','a. 浅的<br>\nn. 鱼群<br>\nv. 浅滩',' Shoals of tourists come here in the summer.<br>     这里夏季常有大批游客。<br>\n The boat struck a shoal and fetched up all standing.<br>     那艘船撞上浅滩突然停了下来。<br>'),(11783,'shock','','','','','n. 震动,冲突,震惊<br>\nv. 震动,冲突,使...受电击',' Anyone touching that wire could get badly shocked.<br>     任何人碰到那根电线都会遭到严重的电击。<br>\n His death was a great shock to us all.<br>     他的死使我们大家都大为震惊。<br>'),(11784,'shocked','','','','','a. 震惊的,震撼的',' His behavior was, in a word, shocking.<br>     总之，他的行为是令人震惊的。<br>\n Anyone touching that wire could get badly shocked.<br>     任何人碰到那根电线都会遭到严重的电击。<br>'),(11785,'shocking','','','','','a. 可怕的,过份的',' Causing shock or horror; gruesome.<br>     可怕的导致惊吓或恐惧的；可憎的<br>\n What a shocking state of affairs!<br>     局势真惊人哪!<br>'),(11786,'shoddy','','','','shoddies','n. 次品<br>\na. 劣质的',' Our new washing-machine keeps breaking down it\'s entirely due to shoddy workmanship.<br>     我们的新洗衣机老出毛病－－完全是因为做的质量太差。<br>\n That salesman really took us for a ride, these goods are very shoddy.<br>     那个推销员真的欺骗了我们，这些都是劣质商品。<br>'),(11787,'shoe','shod','shod','shoeing','shoes','n. 鞋',' The shoes are a perfect fit.<br>     这双鞋子穿着非常合脚。<br>\n I wouldn\'t like to be in your shoes if they find out what you\'re doing.<br>     要是人家发现你现在干的这件事，我可不愿设想你得有多倒霉。<br>'),(11788,'shoelace','','','','','n. 鞋带',''),(11789,'shoemaker','','','','shoemakers','n. 鞋匠',' Adam Smith is a famous shoemaker in town.<br>     亚当·史密斯是镇上有名的鞋匠。<br>'),(11790,'shoes','','','','','n. 鞋子',' The shoes are a perfect fit.<br>     这双鞋子穿着非常合脚。<br>\n Her shoes chafed the skin on her feet.<br>     鞋子擦破了她脚上的皮肤。<br>'),(11791,'shoestring','','','','shoestrings','a. 小本经营的<br>\nn. 零星资本,小额资本',' He started his business on a shoestring. It took a lot of hard work and clever planning to build up it up to where it is today.<br>     他的公司是小本经营开办起来的，经过不少的艰苦劳动和苦心规划，才发展到今天这个样子。<br>\n He missed an attempt for a shoestring catch and the ball rolled to the bullpen.<br>     他错过了球快落地时抢接的机会，球滚到场外替补队热身区去了。<br>'),(11792,'shone','','','','','shine 的过去式(分词)',' The moonlight shone on the calm sea.<br>     月光映在平静的海面上。<br>\n The curtain was suddenly drawn and a bright light shone in.<br>     突然窗帘拉了开来，一道强光照了进来。<br>'),(11793,'shook','','','','','shake的过去式',' He shook his head in disapproval.<br>     他摇了摇头表示反对。<br>\n They shook hands with each other and then sat down.<br>     他们握了握手, 然后坐了下来。<br>'),(11794,'shoot','shot','shot','shooting','shoots','n. 射击,芽,发射<br>\nv. 射击,发出,发芽',' He invited us to his country estate for a weekend shoot.<br>     他邀请我们到他乡下的庄园去过一次打猎的周末。<br>\n The film was shot in black and white.<br>     这部电影拍成了黑白片。<br>'),(11795,'shooter','','','','','n. 射手,狩猎者,枪炮',' A large playing marble, often used as the shooter.<br>     大弹子经常用来击打其它弹子的大理石弹子<br>'),(11796,'shooting','','','','','n. 发射,猎场',' This is just a toy gun: it doesn\'t shoot.<br>     这只是玩具枪, 不能发射子弹.<br>\n People are indignant by their shooting of innocent civilians.<br>     对于他们枪杀无辜平民，人们感到义愤填膺。<br>'),(11797,'shooting gallery','','','','','打靶场',''),(11798,'shooting star','','','','','流星',' Do you wish when you see a shooting star?<br>     你看见流星时提出愿望吗？<br>'),(11799,'shoots','','','','','n. 嫩枝',' New buildings sprang up like bamboo shoots after a spring rain.<br>     新的建筑物如雨后春笋般大批出现。<br>\n The trees send out new shoots in spring.<br>     春天绿树发新芽。<br>'),(11800,'shop','shopped','shopped','shopping','shops','n. 商店<br>\nv. 购物',' The local dress shop is having a sale.<br>     附近的时装店正在大拍卖。<br>\n I usually go shopping on Sundays.<br>     我通常星期天购物。<br>'),(11801,'shopkeeper','','','','shopkeepers','n. 店主',' For the old lady buying the daily newspaper soon became an end in itself, since she really just wanted to chat with the shopkeeper.<br>     那老太太每天去买报纸, 不多时便觉乐在其中, 因为她主要是想和店主聊天.<br>\n The shopkeeper knocked10% off the bill.<br>     主人从帐单中减去10％。<br>'),(11802,'shoplift','shoplifted','shoplifted','shoplifting','','vt, vi. 从商店中偷商品',' I accept that he was caught shoplifting but there\'s no need to keep rubbing his nose in it.<br>     我承认他在冒充顾客进商店行窃时被抓住过，但也没必要老是提起他的过失行为。<br>'),(11803,'shoplifter','','','','shoplifters','n. 在商店中行窃的小偷',''),(11804,'shopper','','','','','n. 购物者,顾客',' An indiscriminate shopper; indiscriminate taste in music.<br>     无选择的购物者；在音乐上无特殊品味的<br>\n The shopper is showered with broken glass from the explosion.<br>     炸碎的玻璃劈头盖脸地落到购物顾客的身上。<br>'),(11805,'shopping','','','','','n. 购物',' I went out on a shopping spree.<br>     我出去疯狂地购物。<br>\n You may go grass skiing, bicycle riding, or shopping on the weekend.<br>     周末你可以去滑草，骑脚踏车，或购物。<br>'),(11806,'shopping center','','','','','n. 购物中心, 商店区',' The land is destined for a new shopping center.<br>     这块地已被划作为营建一个新购物中心之用。<br>\n It\'s sad to see the old museum being taken down to make way for a new shopping center.<br>     看着将老博物馆拆除来建新购物中心，真令人伤心。<br>'),(11807,'shopping mall','','','','','n. 大型购物中心',''),(11808,'shopworn','','','','','a. 陈旧的',''),(11809,'shore','','','','','n. 岸,滨<br>\nvt. (up)支撑,支持',' We found many beautiful shells on the shore.<br>     我们在岸边找到了好多美丽的贝壳。<br>\n The villagers shored up sagging huts.<br>     村民们撑起摇摇欲坠的茅棚。<br>'),(11810,'shorn','','','','','shear的过去分词',' The room looked bare, shorn of its rich furnishings.<br>     这个房间除去了豪华的家具以後, 看上去光秃秃的.<br>\n He was shorn of his privileges.<br>     他的特权被剥夺了。<br>'),(11811,'short','','','','shorts','a. 短的,矮的<br>\nn. 短裤<br>\nadv. 短暂地；突然地,急地',' The driver stopped short when the children ran into the street.<br>     小孩跑进街道时，司机猛然煞车。<br>\n He seems much shorter without his shoes on.<br>     他没穿鞋，看上去矮多了。<br>'),(11812,'short circuit','','','','','n. 短路,漏电',' The lights short-circuited when I joined up the wires.<br>     我一接上电线，电灯就短路了。<br>\n You\'ve short-circuited the washing-machine.<br>     你把洗衣机弄短路了.<br>'),(11813,'short story','','','','','短篇小说',' This is a short story whose easy style I love very much.<br>     这是一则短篇小说，我很喜欢它那简单的笔调。<br>\n He brightened up at the mention of his son\'s success as a short story writer.<br>     提到他儿子作为一个短篇小说作家是成功的，他就喜形于色。<br>'),(11814,'shortage','','','','shortages','n. 不足,缺少',' The war was lost because of a shortage of munitions.<br>     战争因军火不足而失败。<br>\n The company\'s main problem is the shortage of skilled personnel.<br>     这家公司的主要问题是缺少有技术的人员。<br>'),(11815,'short-circuit','','','short-circuiting','','v. 使...不工作<br>\nvt. 使简短',''),(11816,'shortcoming','','','','shortcomings','n. 短处,缺点',' No matter who point out our shortcoming, we will correct them.<br>     不管谁指出我们的缺点，我们都改正。<br>\n Donna is sensible of his shortcoming.<br>     唐纳知道他自己的缺点。<br>'),(11817,'shortcut','','','','','n. 捷径',''),(11818,'shorten','shortened','shortened','shortening','','v. 弄短,变短',' She shortened the shirt by an inch.<br>     她把衬衫截短了一英寸。<br>\n My teacher asked me to shorten the report to one page.<br>     老师让我把报告缩短为一页。<br>'),(11819,'shortening','','','','','n. 缩短',' An abnormal, often permanent shortening, as of muscle or scar tissue, that results in distortion or deformity, especially of a joint of the body.<br>     挛缩一种异常且常为永久性的缩短，如肌肉或瘢痕组织，会导致扭曲或变形，特别是身体关节处<br>\n Surgical shortening or reshaping of the nose.<br>     鼻部整形术外科手术中鼻子的整形或截短<br>'),(11820,'shortfall','','','','','n. 不足之量,差额',''),(11821,'shorthand','','','','','n. 速记',' You know how I loathe typing and shorthand.<br>     你知道我多么讨厌打字和速记。<br>\n His farewell speech was transcribed from shorthand notes.<br>     他的告别演说是由速记转译而成的。<br>'),(11822,'short-lived','','','','','a. 短命的, 短暂的, 短期的, 无常的',''),(11823,'shortly','','','','','ad. 立刻,马上',' The movie was over shortly before six.<br>     电影在六点钟不到就结束了。<br>\n She died in an accident shortly afterwards.<br>     不久以后，她就在一次事故中丧生。<br>'),(11824,'shortness','','','','','n. 短小,简略,不足',''),(11825,'short-range','','','','','a. 短程的,短期间的',''),(11826,'shorts','','','','shorts','n. 短裤',' This pair of pant was converted into shorts.<br>     这条裤子被改成了短裤。<br>\n Pants, such as blue jeans, made into shorts by cutting off part of the legs.<br>     毛边短裤长裤，如蓝布牛仔裤，通过截去裤腿的一部分而制成的短裤<br>'),(11827,'shortsighted','','','','','a. 近视的',' He was too shortsighted to focus on the object.<br>     他由於近视过深而无法把视力焦点对准在该物体上。<br>\n He is shortsighted.<br>     他是近视眼。<br>'),(11828,'short-term','','','','','a. 短期的',''),(11829,'shot','','','','','n. 炮弹,射击,射手<br>\nv. 射击,发出,发芽<br>\nvbl. 射击,发出,发芽',' I heard a shot in his room.<br>     我听到他的房间内一声枪响。<br>\n He won the golf match by two shots.<br>     他以两杆的成绩赢得了这场高尔夫球赛。<br>'),(11830,'shot put','','','','','n. [体]推铅球, 铅球的一次投射',''),(11831,'shotgun','shotguned','shotguned','shotguning','shotguns','n. 猎枪',' A shotgun leans against the table.<br>     桌子跟前靠着一支猎枪。<br>\n Willie accidentally lets off his father\'s shotgun and made a hole in the wall.<br>     威利玩他父亲的手枪时不小心走火了, 把墙壁打出一个洞。<br>'),(11832,'should','','','','','conj. 应该,将要',' I knew if I kept at it I should succeed.<br>     我知道如果我坚持下去就会成功。<br>\n You really ought to/should do something about that cough!<br>     你咳嗽那麽厉害, 真得治一治了!<br>'),(11833,'shoulder','shouldered','shouldered','shouldering','shoulders','n. 肩膀<br>\nv. 肩负,承担<br>\nvt. 承担,肩负',' The soldiers shouldered their kit and moved on.<br>     士兵们背起行装，继续前进。<br>\n The boy had a parrot on his right shoulder.<br>     男孩把一只鹦鹉放在右肩上。<br>'),(11834,'shoulders','','','','','割面肩',' Her wavy hair fell in loose wisps and loops upon her shoulders.<br>     她那一头波浪般的长发一簇簇一圈圈地散垂在肩上。<br>\n The officer wears sashes on his shoulders.<br>     这名军官的肩上佩戴着肩带。<br>'),(11835,'shouldn\'t','','','','','(=should not) 不应...',''),(11836,'shout','shouted','shouted','shouting','shouts','n. 呼喊,突发的大笑<br>\nv. 呼喊,高声谈笑,玩乐',' His news was greeted with shouts of joy.<br>     大家都对他的消息报以欢呼。<br>\n The children on the sand were shouting with excitement.<br>     沙滩上的孩子们兴奋得大喊大叫。<br>'),(11837,'shove','shoved','shoved','shoving','','n. 推,挤<br>\nv. 推挤,放置,撞',' He started shoving clothes into drawers.<br>     他开始把衣服乱塞在抽屉里。<br>\n Don\'t try to shove all the work onto me!<br>     别把工作都推给我！<br>'),(11838,'shovel','shoveled','shoveled','shoveling','shovels','n. 铲(挖斗机,一铲的量)<br>\nvt 铲(挖,舀)',' He put a shovel of coal on to the fire.<br>     他往火炉里加了一铲煤。<br>\n They were shoveling food into their mouths.<br>     他们正大口大口地往嘴里塞食物。<br>'),(11839,'shovelful','','','','shovelfuls','n. 满铲(一铲的量,一锹的量)',' He put a shovelful of snow in Kate\'s bed as a practical joke.<br>     他把一铲雪放在凯特的床上，以此来开玩笑。<br>'),(11840,'show','showed','shown','showing','shows','n. 显示,表现,表演<br>\nv. 表示,显现,展现',' One evening the school showed a cowboy film.<br>     有天晚上学校放映了一部西部片。<br>\n The leader rarely shows herself in public.<br>     这位领导她很少在公众场合露面。<br>'),(11841,'show business','','','','','娱乐业,演艺生意',' For this old trouper there is still no business like show business.<br>     对这位老剧团演员来说仍然是娱乐性行业最好。<br>'),(11842,'showcase','showcased','showcased','showcasing','showcases','n. (玻璃)陈列柜,陈列橱',''),(11843,'showdown','','','','showdowns','n. 摊牌','');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (11844,'shower','showered','showered','showering','showers','n. 阵雨,淋浴<br>\nv. 淋浴,淋湿,下骤雨',' Dates showered down when we shook the tree.<br>     我们摇树时，枣子纷纷落下。<br>\n The dancer was showered with praise.<br>     那个跳舞的人备受称赞。<br>'),(11845,'showing','','','','','显示,放映',' Possessing or showing knowledge or intelligence; perceptive and well-informed.<br>     有见识的，知识渊博的掌握或显示出知识或智力的；有洞察力的而且见识广的<br>\n Stop showing off in front of everybody.<br>     别再在大伙跟前卖弄了。<br>'),(11846,'showman','','','','showmen','n. 马戏团的老板,玩杂耍的',''),(11847,'shown','','','','','show的过去分词',' In his youth, he had shown great promise.<br>     他在青少年时代就显得很有出息。<br>\n The girls screamed when the grisly remains of the half-eaten corpses on the screen were shown.<br>     当屏幕上显示出尸体被吃掉一半的恐怖残骸时，女孩子们尖叫起来。<br>'),(11848,'showpiece','','','','','n. 展览品(供展览的样品)',''),(11849,'showroom','','','','','n. 陈列室',' Police restored the stolen jewels to the showroom.<br>     警方将被盗的珠宝交还给了陈列室.<br>\n Our entire range of cars is now on view at your local showroom.<br>     我们各种型号的汽车现正在贵区陈列室里展出。<br>'),(11850,'showy','','','','','a. 鲜艳的,显眼的',' A bauble is a showy ornament of little value.<br>     廉价珠宝是华而不实的装饰品。<br>\n A showy manner or display.<br>     炫耀炫耀的态度或展示<br>'),(11851,'shrank','','','','','shrink的过去式',' As he moved threateningly forward she shrank (back) from him.<br>     他步步逼近, 把她吓得直（向後）退缩.<br>\n The dough shrank slowly in the cold air.<br>     面团在冷空气中慢慢收缩了.<br>'),(11852,'shred','shredded','shredded','shredding','shreds','n. 碎布条,细片,些少<br>\nv. 撕成碎片,变成碎片',' I was shredding top-secret documents at that time.<br>     我当时正把机密文件切碎。<br>\n The jacket was torn to shreds by the barbed wire.<br>     那件夹克让铁丝网给戳破了。<br>'),(11853,'shredder','','','','shredders','碎纸机',''),(11854,'shrew','','','','shrews','n. 悍妇,泼妇',' People called her shrew.<br>     人们叫她泼妇。<br>'),(11855,'shrewd','','','','','a. 精明的',' He is a shrewd and sometimes ruthless adversary.<br>     他是个精明的、有时候冷酷无情的对手。<br>\n It was a shrewd assessment and probably pretty close to the truth.<br>     这个评估很有道理，可能相当正确。<br>'),(11856,'shriek','shrieked','shrieked','shrieking','shrieks','n. 尖叫,叫喊<br>\nv. 尖叫',' My sister gave a shriek of delight.<br>     我妹妹高兴地尖叫起来。<br>\n She shrieked in alarm.<br>     她惊恐地尖叫起来。<br>'),(11857,'shrill','shrilled','shrilled','shrilling','shrills','n. 尖锐的声音<br>\na. 尖锐的,刺耳的<br>\nv. 用尖锐的声音说,发出刺耳声',' Shrill protests about the new taxes filled the air.<br>     广播中充斥着对新税法的尖锐抗议。<br>\n The boys broke into shrill, excited cheering.<br>     男孩子们突然迸发出刺耳的兴奋的欢呼声。<br>'),(11858,'shrilly','','','','','ad. 尖声地',' The monkeys cry (out) shrilly when they see danger.<br>     猴子遇到危险时尖声大叫.<br>'),(11859,'shrimp','shrimped','shrimped','shrimping','shrimp','n. 虾',' Jumbo shrimp; a jumbo jet.<br>     大虾；巨型喷气式飞机<br>\n Fruit cocktail; shrimp cocktail.<br>     水果鸡尾酒；河虾鸡尾酒<br>'),(11860,'shrine','shrined','shrined','shrining','shrines','n. 圣地,神龛,庙<br>\nv. 将...置于神龛内',' Florence is the shrine of the Renaissance.<br>     佛罗伦萨是文艺复兴的圣地。<br>\n A religious building of the Far East, especially a many-storied Buddhist tower, erected as a memorial or shrine.<br>     塔，宝塔一种远东的宗教建筑，尤指一种多层的佛塔，作为纪念塔或神龛而建立<br>'),(11861,'shrink','shrank','shrunk','shrinking','shrinks','n. 收缩,萎缩<br>\nv. 收缩,退缩,萎缩',' He had a tendency to shrink up whenever attention was focused on him.<br>     当别人注意他时，他就会退缩一旁。<br>\n The economy is shrinking instead of growing.<br>     经济正在萎缩而不是在增长中。<br>'),(11862,'shrinkage','','','','','n. 收缩,缩小,减低',' Shrinkage or contraction of the protoplasm away from the wall of a living plant or bacterial cell, caused by loss of water through osmosis.<br>     胞质皱缩通过渗透作用由于缺水引起的活植细胞或细菌的细胞质的皱缩或收缩，并与细胞壁分离<br>\n As a result of shrinkage, the shirt is now too small to wear.<br>     由于洗后缩小，那件衬衫现在小得不能穿了。<br>'),(11863,'shrinking','','','','','a. 畏缩的,犹豫不决的',' The economy is shrinking instead of growing.<br>     经济正在萎缩而不是在增长中。<br>\n She\'s no shrinking violet always ready to speak up for herself.<br>     她可不胆小--任何场合都能为自己说话.<br>'),(11864,'shrivel','shriveled','shriveled','shriveling','','v. 枯萎,皱缩<br>\nvi. 枯萎,干枯',' The leaves shriveled up in the sun.<br>     叶子在阳光下都蔫了。<br>\n The dry air shrivels the leather.<br>     因空气干燥皮子都皱了。<br>'),(11865,'shroud','shrouded','shrouded','shrouding','shrouds','n. 寿衣,覆盖物,船之横桅索<br>\nv. 包以尸衣,遮蔽,隐藏',' The doctor wanted us to use the sheet for a shroud.<br>     医生想让我们用床单当裹尸布。<br>\n The whole jail was shrouded in darkness.<br>     整座监狱笼罩在黑暗之中。<br>'),(11866,'shrub','','','','shrubs','n. 灌木',' The naughty boy hid the books in the shrub.<br>     这个淘气的孩子把书藏在了灌木丛里。<br>\n Resembling a shrub, especially in having woody stems and branches.<br>     灌木状的类似灌木的，尤指有木质树干或树枝<br>'),(11867,'shrubbery','','','','shrubberies','n. 灌木,灌木林',' A secluded mansion, islanded by shrubbery and fences.<br>     用灌木丛和篱笆隔开的一座幽独的大宅<br>'),(11868,'shrug','shrugged','shrugged','shrugging','shrugs','n. 耸肩<br>\nv. 耸肩',' She gave a shrug and walked away.<br>     她耸了耸肩就离开了。<br>\n I really admire the way she is able to shrug off unfair criticism.<br>     我很佩服她能对错误的批评意见不予理会。<br>'),(11869,'shrunken','','','','','v. 使...收缩<br>\na. 缩拢的',''),(11870,'shuck','shucked','shucked','shucking','','n. (植物的)壳,夹,无用之物',' He must shuck off the bad habits.<br>     他应该改掉过去的坏习惯。<br>\n It\'s not worth shucks.<br>     那种东西一文不值。<br>'),(11871,'shudder','shuddered','shuddered','shuddering','shudders','n. 战悚,发抖<br>\nv. 战悚,发抖',' She shuddered at the sight of the dead body.<br>     她一看到死尸就战栗起来。<br>\n He shuddered with cold.<br>     他冷得发抖。<br>'),(11872,'shuffle','shuffled','shuffled','shuffling','shuffles','n. 拖著脚走,洗纸牌<br>\nv. 拖曳,慢吞吞地走',' Who is going to shuffle?<br>     该谁洗牌了？<br>\n Don\'t shuffle, give me a clear answer.<br>     别支支吾吾，给我一个明确的答复。<br>'),(11873,'shun','shunned','shunned','shunning','','v. 避开,规避,避免',' This recluse shunned all company.<br>     这位隐士不与任何人来往。<br>\n His friends shunned him.<br>     他的朋友都避开他。<br>'),(11874,'shunt','shunted','shunted','shunting','','vt. 分路(调车,推给别人,拖延)<br>\nn. 分路(转辙器,调轨)',' She tried to shunt the blame onto Miss Williams.<br>     她试图把责任推至威廉姆斯小姐身上。<br>\n Can we shunt the talks onto a new topic?<br>     我们谈话换个新话题好吧？<br>'),(11875,'shut','shut','shut','shutting','shuts','a. 关闭的,合拢的,围绕的<br>\nv. 关上,闭起,幽禁<br>\nvbl. 关上,闭起,幽禁',' He shut himself away for a month to catch up on his academic work.<br>     他与世隔绝一个月，力图把功课赶上去。<br>\n He shut his eyes to her faults.<br>     他对她的缺点视而不见。<br>'),(11876,'Shut up!','','','','','住嘴!',''),(11877,'shutdown','','','','','关机',''),(11878,'Shute','','','','','n. 舒特(姓)',''),(11879,'shutter','shuttered','shuttered','shuttering','shutters','n. 百叶窗,遮门,快门<br>\nv. 装以遮门,以百叶窗遮闭',' He adjusted the shutter before taking a photo.<br>     在照相前，他调整了快门。<br>\n The shop-front is fitted with rolling shutters.<br>     那商店的店面装有卷动门帘.<br>'),(11880,'shuttle','shuttled','shuttled','shuttling','shuttles','n. 穿梭,往返移动之物<br>\nv. 使...穿梭移动',' We shuttled the passengers to the city center by helicopter.<br>     我们来来回回地用直升机把旅客运送到市中心。<br>\n There is a shuttle service between the city center and the air station.<br>     在市中心和飞机场之间有往返的穿梭运行班车。<br>'),(11881,'shuttlecock','shuttlecocked','shuttlecocked','shuttlecocking','','n. 羽毛球,玩毽子,打羽毛球<br>\nv. 互相授受,这儿那儿移动',''),(11882,'shy','','','','','a. 害羞的<br>\nvi. 惊退,畏缩',' He was too shy to talk to anyone at the party.<br>     在晚会上他很腼腆，没有和任何人讲话。<br>\n We are still a little shy of our quota.<br>     我们离完成定额还差一点点。<br>'),(11883,'Shylock','','','','','夏洛克, 狠毒无情的放高利贷者(原为莎士比亚剧作《威尼斯商人》中的犹太放高利贷者)',' Jacob was at his best in the role of Shylock; he did not merely act; he lived the part.<br>     雅各布最擅长扮演夏洛克这个角色，他不仅是在演戏，而是把角色演活了。<br>\n Shylock has an itch for money.<br>     夏洛克渴望发财。<br>'),(11884,'shyly','','','','','ad. 畏缩地,羞怯地',' She glanced shyly at him and then lowered her eyes.<br>     她羞怯地偷看了他一下, 随即垂下眼帘.<br>\n She cast her eyes down shyly.<br>     她羞怯地垂下目光。<br>'),(11885,'shyness','','','','','n. 羞怯,胆怯',' She can\'t get over her shyness.<br>     她克服不掉羞怯感.<br>\n Shyness inhibited him from speaking.<br>     他因害羞而说不出话来.<br>'),(11886,'shyster','','','','','n. 奸诈的人,讼棍',''),(11887,'Siam','','','','','n. 暹罗',''),(11888,'siamang','','','','','n. [动]合趾猴( 产于马来半岛及苏门答腊)',''),(11889,'Siamese','','','','Siamese','a. 暹罗的',' The natural or surgical union of anatomical parts of two organisms, usually involving exchange of blood, as in the development of Siamese twins or in certain transplant operations.<br>     联体，并体天生的或手术施行的通常进行血液交换的两器官的联合，比如在连体婴的发育或某种嫁接手术中<br>\n Siamese cats are rather like dogs in some ways.<br>     泰国猫在某些方面相当象狗。<br>'),(11890,'Siberia','','','','','西伯利亚',' Cold, dry winds from Siberia prevail over the mainland from December to February.<br>     从12月到2月，西伯利亚来的干燥冷风控制大陆。<br>\n The cold air masses are moving from Siberia towards Inner Mongolia.<br>     冷空气团正由西伯利亚向内蒙古移动。<br>'),(11891,'Siberian','','','','','a. 西伯利亚的',' For long stretch of the try- siberian railway, all you see are trees.<br>     横跨西伯利亚的铁路沿线的景色是一望无际的树林。<br>'),(11892,'sibilant','','','','','a. 发咝咝声的',''),(11893,'sibling','','','','','n. 兄弟姐妹',' I have two brothers and a sister: three siblings in all.<br>     我有两个哥哥和一个妹妹: 共有三个兄妹.<br>\n Inferior craft; felt inferior to his older sibling.<br>     低等的手工艺品；感到比他的兄妹们低一等<br>'),(11894,'sibyl','','','','','n. 女预言家,女先知',''),(11895,'sibylline','','','','','a. sibyl 的,sibyl 性的,预言性的',''),(11896,'Sicily','','','','','n. 西西里(岛)[意大利]',' A peninsula of northeast Tunisia extending into the Mediterranean Sea across from Sicily.<br>     波恩角突尼斯东北部延伸入地中海的一个半岛，在西西里岛对面<br>'),(11897,'sick','','','','','a. 恶心的,有病的,腻烦的<br>\nn. 病人<br>\nvt. 呕吐',' Your uncle is very sick.<br>     你的叔叔病得很厉害。<br>\n I\'m sick of waiting around like this.<br>     我腻烦像这样在一旁等著。<br>'),(11898,'sick leave','','','','','病假',' He has been on sick leave for some weeks, and so he has to work hard to catch us all up.<br>     他因为请了几个星期的病假，因此不得不加紧工作来赶上我们大家。<br>'),(11899,'sickbed','','','','','n. 病床',''),(11900,'sicken','sickened','sickened','sickening','','v. 患病,使...厌倦,生病',' The dog began to sicken and soon died.<br>     这只狗开始生病并且很快就死了。<br>\n Cruelty sickens most of us.<br>     我们大多数人都对残暴行为十分愤慨.<br>'),(11901,'sickening','','','','','a. 引起疾病的',' The car hit the child with a sickening thud.<br>     汽车把那个孩子撞了, 发出一声可怕的闷响.<br>\n Sickening or insipid in taste.<br>     （味道上）令人作呕的，淡而无味的<br>'),(11902,'sickle','','','','sickles','n. 镰刀',' There is a picture of the sickle on the flag.<br>     旗帜上有镰刀的图案。<br>'),(11903,'sickly','sicklied','sicklied','sicklying','','a. 病弱的,阴沉的,无精打采的<br>\nv. 成苍白色',' His face was a sickly yellow.<br>     他的脸色是一种病态的黄。<br>\n Her cheeks have a sickly pallor.<br>     她面色苍白带有病容.<br>'),(11904,'sickness','','','','sicknesses','n. 疾病',' Chicken pox is a common childhood sickness.<br>     水痘是一种常见的儿童期疾病。<br>\n Some people develop altitude sickness when climbing high mountains.<br>     有些人在爬高山时会发生高山反应。<br>'),(11905,'side','sided','sided','siding','sides','n. 旁边,侧,方面<br>\na. 旁的,侧的<br>\nv. 偏袒',' A square has four sides but a circle has no sides.<br>     正方形有四条边，而圆形没有边。<br>\n The thief slipped away down a side street.<br>     小偷悄悄从一条小马路溜走了。<br>'),(11906,'side effect','','','','','副作用',' Physical and chemical tests verify that this Recovery Device has neither radioactive pollution nor toxic side effects.<br>     经理化检验证实：使用该器无放射性污染，对人体绝对无毒无副作用。<br>\n Medicines sometimes have unpleasant side effects.<br>     药物有时具有令人不快的副作用。<br>'),(11907,'sideboard','','','','sideboards','n. 餐具柜',' She put some plates in the sideboard.<br>     她往餐具柜里放了些盘子。<br>\n We keep the silver in this sideboard.<br>     我们把金属餐具放在这个餐具柜里.<br>'),(11908,'sideline','','','','sidelines','n. (球场)边线',' I was on the sidelines during the political crisis.<br>     在这一政治危机时期我是目睹一切的局外人。<br>\n Actually I\'m a teacher, my writing is just a sideline.<br>     我其实是个教师，写作只是我的兼职。<br>'),(11909,'sidereal','','','','','a. 恒星的',''),(11910,'sides','','','','','侧',' A box has a top, a bottom and four sides.<br>     盒子有顶面、 底面和四个侧面.<br>\n The railways carriages containing terrorists and hostages were two hundred yards away across an open field. Both sides prepared for a long drawn-out battle of 