ve tube','','','','','筛管',''),(11923,'sift','sifted','sifted','sifting','','v. 筛撒,纷落,详察',' Sift the flour before making the cake.<br>     做蛋糕前先把面粉筛一下。<br>\n Snow sifted through the crack in the roof into the room.<br>     雪从屋顶上的裂缝飘进屋里。<br>'),(11924,'sifter','','','','','n. 筛子',''),(11925,'sigh','sighed','sighed','sighing','sighs','n. 叹息<br>\nv. 叹息之声,渴望',' She looked out of the window, sighing for her lost youth.<br>     她看着窗外，为她失去的青春而惋惜。<br>\n We all heaved a sigh of relief when we heard that they were safe.<br>     当我们听说他们平安无事时，都松了一口气。<br>'),(11926,'sighs','','','','','叹息',' She sighs deeply for no conspicuous reason, yearns, suffers and looks in the air extremely sadly. This is soul.<br>     她没有明显的理由而却深深叹息、渴望、烦闷、极端悲伤地望着天空。这就是灵魂。<br>\n She sighs deeply for no conspicuous reason, yearn, suffer and looks in the air extremely sadly. This is soul.<br>     他没有明显的理由而却深深叹息、渴望、烦闷、极端悲伤地望着天空。这就是灵魂。<br>'),(11927,'sight','sighted','sighted','sighting','sights','n. 景观,视力,眼界<br>\nv. 看见,瞄准,观看',' The train is still in sight.<br>     火车仍在视线内。<br>\n We laughed at the sight of his strange clothes.<br>     一看到他古怪的穿着，我们就笑了。<br>'),(11928,'sight draft','','','','','即期票据',' Enclosed is a sight draft for￡26.10.5 on Messrs. Robert& Sons, which clears off our indebtedness to you.<br>     兹同函奉上以Robert父子公司为付款人，面额26。15英镑的即期汇票一张，用以清偿所欠贵方债务。<br>\n Payment will be made by paying your sight draft under our irrevocable letter of credit.<br>     我们的付款方式，是以不可撤消信用状见票即付汇票支付。<br>'),(11929,'sighting','','','','','n. 目击物,目击场所',' They reported sighting the plane.<br>     他们宣称看见了那架飞机.<br>\n He drove straight by sighting along the center line.<br>     他注视着中央线，驾车径直向前驶去。<br>'),(11930,'sights','','','','','n. 风景,名胜',' Come and see the sights of London.<br>     来看看伦敦的名胜.<br>\n The sights of the city never fail to impress foreign tourists.<br>     外国游客无一不对该市留有深刻印象.<br>'),(11931,'sightsee','sightseed','sightseed','sightseeing','','vi. 观光,游览',''),(11932,'sightseeing','','','','','n. 观光,游览',' They embarked on an orgy of sightseeing.<br>     他们开始尽情地观光游览。<br>\n Good morning, Mr.Smith. Sightseeing is our agenda today.<br>     早上好，史密斯先生。我们今天的日程安排是游览。<br>'),(11933,'sign','signed','signed','signing','signs','n. 符号,正负号,手势,迹象,招牌<br>\nv. 签，做手势，做标记',' Dark clouds are a sign of rain or snow.<br>     乌云是雨或雪将至的预兆。<br>\n The football team has signed two new players.<br>     该足球队已签约聘用了两名新队员。<br>'),(11934,'sign language','','','','','符号语言',' The speech was interpreted in sign language for the hearing-impaired.<br>     这次讲话因那些听力受损者而译成了手语<br>'),(11935,'signal','signaled','signaled','signaling','signals','n. 信号,导火线,动机<br>\nv. 向...作信号',' A red lamp is often a danger signal.<br>     红灯常常是危险的信号。<br>\n The police signalled the traffic to move forward slowly.<br>     警察向来往车辆打信号，示意缓慢前行。<br>'),(11936,'signatory','','','','signatories','n. 签署者,签约国',''),(11937,'signature','','','','signatures','1. 签名,签署;画押',' They forged their manager\'s signature on the cheque.<br>     他们在支票上伪造了经理的签名。<br>\n This document bore his signature.<br>     这份文件上有他的签名。<br>'),(11938,'signed','','','','','带正负号的',' At thirty, he signed on as first mate with a cargo ship.<br>     他30岁时受雇于一艘货船当了大副。<br>\n They signed a petition in support of the workers\' demands.<br>     他们在请愿书上签名，支持工人的请求。<br>'),(11939,'signer','','','','','签名人<br>\n(用手势) 示意者<br>\n[Signer ]美国独立宣言署名人',''),(11940,'significance','','','','','n. 意义,重要性',' Could you explain to me the significance of this part of the contract?<br>     你能给我解释一下合同这一部分的含义吗？<br>\n This new discovery of oil is of great significance to this area\'s economy.<br>     这次新发现的石油对这个地区的经济有着重大的意义。<br>'),(11941,'significant','','','','significants','a. 有意义的,相当数量的,意味深长的,重要的,重大的',' Their change of plan is strange but I don\'t think it\'s significant.<br>     很奇怪他们改变了计划，但我觉得没有什么用处。<br>\n Few people realized the discovery was significant.<br>     很少有人认识到这一发现的重要性。<br>'),(11942,'significantly','','','','','ad. 较大地(重要地)',' The police released him but, significantly, they didn\'t give him back his passport.<br>     警方释放了他，但是没有把护照还给他，这是有特殊用意的。<br>\n Significantly New York is left out of this list.<br>     意味深长的是纽约这个城市的名字从名单中划掉了。<br>'),(11943,'signify','signified','signified','signifying','','v. 象徵,预示',' It doesn\'t signify, so you needn\'t worry about it.<br>     这无所谓, 你不必担心.<br>\n What do these marks signify?<br>     这些符号表示什麽意思?<br>'),(11944,'signing','','','','','n. 签署,签字',' Make sure you read all the small print before signing.<br>     一定要先看清小号字体印刷部分再签字.<br>\n The workers were railroaded into signing the agreement.<br>     工人们被逼着匆忙地签订了这个协议。<br>'),(11945,'signor','','','','signori','n. (意大利语)先生',' Shylock [To Antonio] Rest you fair, good signor; Your worship was the last man in our mouths.<br>     夏洛克：［向安冬尼奥］您好，好先生：是哪一阵好风把尊驾吹了来啦？<br>'),(11946,'signpost','','','','','n. 招牌柱,广告柱,路标',' Is the road well signposted?<br>     这条路的路标清楚吗？<br>\n The signpost indicates the right way to go.<br>     路标标示正确的前进路线。<br>'),(11947,'silence','silenced','silenced','silencing','silences','n. 沉默,寂静<br>\nv. 使沉默,使安静<br>\nvt. 使安静,使沉默',' The enemy\'s guns were silenced by repeated bombings.<br>     敌人的炮火因遭到轮番轰炸而沉寂了。<br>\n There was nothing but silence in the room.<br>     这间屋内声息全无，一片寂静。<br>'),(11948,'silent','','','','silents','a. 安静的,不吵闹的,沉默的,无言的',' If you are arrested you have the right to remain silent.<br>     如果你被捕，你有权保持沉默。<br>\n The old house was quite silent.<br>     这所旧房子非常寂静。<br>'),(11949,'silently','','','','','ad. 沉默地,寂静地',' Silently we approached the enemy\'s camp.<br>     我们静悄悄地逼近敌人的营地。<br>\n The cat was creeping silently towards the mouse.<br>     猫悄悄地朝着老鼠爬过去。<br>'),(11950,'silhouette','silhouetted','silhouetted','silhouetting','silhouettes','n. 黑色半身侧面影,影子,轮廓<br>\nv. 描绘成侧面影,照出影子来,仅仅显出轮廓',' The outline, form, or silhouette of a thing.<br>     外形，轮廓某物的外廓、外形或轮廓<br>\n He saw the building in silhouette.<br>     他看到了那幢建筑的轮廓。<br>'),(11951,'silica','','','','','矽土',''),(11952,'silicate','','','','','n. 硅酸盐',''),(11953,'siliceous','','','','','a. 硅酸的,硅土的',''),(11954,'silicon','','','','','n. 硅'