s.<br>     我知道西蒙只是在猜测，他说公司可能陷入经济困难，而这一点他却说得令人吃惊地近乎正确。<br>'),(11974,'simper','simpered','simpered','simpering','','v. 傻笑,假笑',''),(11975,'simpering','','','','','a. 傻笑的',''),(11976,'simple','','','','simples','a. 简单的,简朴的,单纯的',' I like my clothes to be simple but elegant.<br>     我喜欢朴素但漂亮雅致的衣服。<br>\n She doesn\'t understand you. She\'s a bit simple.<br>     她不明白你的意思。她有点笨。<br>'),(11977,'simple-minded','','','','','a. 愚蠢的，头脑简单的',''),(11978,'simpleton','','','','','n. 笨蛋,傻子',''),(11979,'simplex','','','','simplices','单工的,单一的',''),(11980,'simplicity','','','','simplicities','n. 单纯,简朴',' The simplicity of the book makes it suitable for children.<br>     这本书简单易懂，适合儿童。<br>\n Simplicity is the essence of good taste.<br>     纯朴是情趣高尚的主要因素。<br>'),(11981,'simplification','','','','','n. 简化,精简',' What she said was a useful simplification of the theory.<br>     她把这一理论讲得深入浅出.<br>'),(11982,'simplified','','','','','a. 精简了的,简化了的',' She simplified the instructions so that the children could understand them.<br>     她简化了指令以便于儿童理解。<br>\n That will simplify my task.<br>     那可简化了我的工作。<br>'),(11983,'simplifier','','','','','n. 简化物',''),(11984,'simplify','simplified','simplified','simplifying','','v. 简化,使单纯<br>\nvt. 简化',' She simplified the instructions so that the children could understand them.<br>     她简化了指令以便于儿童理解。<br>\n That will simplify my task.<br>     那可简化了我的工作。<br>'),(11985,'simplistic','','','','','a. 过分简单化的',''),(11986,'simply','','','','','ad.&a. 简单地,仅仅',' I bought the house simply because it was large.<br>     我购买了这房子，只是因为它面积大。<br>\n You may open the tin simply by pulling the puller.<br>     你只要拉这个拉出器，就可以很容易地把罐头打开。<br>'),(11987,'simulate','simulated','simulated','simulating','','v. 假装,冒充,模仿,模拟',' An apparatus in which human beings or animals are enclosed and which is revolved to simulate the effects of acceleration in a spacecraft.<br>     航天试验离心机人和动物在其里面并旋转以模仿宇宙飞行器的加速作用的一种仪器<br>\n Some moths simulate dead leaves.<br>     有些蛾拟态为枯叶。<br>'),(11988,'simulated','','','','','a. 伪装的,模仿的',' In such a simulated environment, one would have an immersed sense.<br>     人在这个仿真的环境中，有一种“身临其境”的感觉。<br>\n A large-scale tactical exercise carried out under simulated conditions of war.<br>     对抗演习在模拟战争状态下所进行大型战术训练<br>'),(11989,'simulation','','','','','模拟,仿真',' Computer simulation of an in-flight emergency.<br>     计算机模拟飞行途中的紧急情况<br>\n In fact, virtual reality is exploiting software and hardware of　the computer to generate a simulation of an environment, such as an easeful classroom, a breathtaking action and so on.<br>     实际上，虚拟现实就是利用计算机的软件和硬件去产生一种境界的仿真，如仿真一个学习场所，一次惊险的行为等等。<br>'),(11990,'simulative','','','','','a. 假装的,模仿的',''),(11991,'simulator','','','','','模拟程序',''),(11992,'simultaneity','','','','','同时性',''),(11993,'simultaneous','','','','','a. 同时发生的',' The simultaneous demonstrations are held in London and New York.<br>     在伦敦和纽约同时举行示威游行。<br>\n The explosion was timed to be simultaneous with the plane\'s take-off.<br>     爆炸的时间定在飞机起飞的时刻。<br>'),(11994,'simultaneously','','','','','ad. 同时地(联立地)',' Gordon played ten people simultaneously at the chess club last week and really showed his pace-he lost only one game.<br>     上星期戈登在国际象棋俱乐部同时和１０个人对奕，那次他真正显示了自己的才华——他只输了一盘。<br>\n That cannot be simultaneously true; mutually exclusive.<br>     互相矛盾的不能同时成立的；互斥的<br>'),(11995,'sin','sinned','sinned','sinning','sins','n. 罪,罪孽<br>\nv. 犯罪',' We\'ve sinned against you, and against our fellow men.<br>     我们得罪了你，也得罪了我们的邻人。<br>\n I guess ignorance must be a sin.<br>     我认为无知是一种罪。<br>'),(11996,'since','','','','','ad. 后来<br>\nconj. 既然,因为<br>\nprep. 自从',' Since you can\'t answer the question, perhaps we\'d better ask someone else.<br>     既然你无法回答这个问题，我们最好再问问别人。<br>\n We\'ve been friends ever since we met at school.<br>     自从我们在学校认识之后，我们就一直是好朋友。<br>'),(11997,'sincere','','','','','a. 真诚的,诚挚的',' Please give my sincere regards to all the members of your family.<br>     请向你全家转达我真挚的问候。<br>\n Sincere congratulations on your son wedding please convey our best wish.<br>     令郎喜