elly, no point of argue with him.<br>     冷静些凯利，没有必要同他争论。<br>'),(12021,'sinuous','','','','','a. 弯弯曲曲的,迂回的,乖僻的',' A sinuous path, line, or marking.<br>     弯弯曲曲的道路、线条或记号<br>\n Marked by or moving in a wavelike form or motion; sinuous.<br>     波状的或以波浪式运动的；起伏不平的<br>'),(12022,'sip','sipped','sipped','sipping','sips','n. 啜饮<br>\nv. 啜饮,啜',' Bees sip honey from flowers and hum their thanks when they leave.<br>     蜜蜂从花中啜蜜，离开时营营地道谢。<br>\n I sipped at the coffee.<br>     我啜饮咖啡。<br>'),(12023,'siphon','siphoned','siphoned','siphoning','siphons','n. 虹吸管<br>\nvt. 用虹吸管吸出或排出',' She siphoned off profits from the business into her account.<br>     她把企业的赢利转到了自己的帐户上。<br>\n If you\'re short of petrol you can siphon off a gallon from my tank.<br>     如果汽油不够，你可以从我的油箱中用虹吸管吸一加仑去。<br>'),(12024,'sir','','','','sirs','n. 先生',' Thank you, sir.<br>     谢谢您，先生。<br>\n I\'m sorry, sir, the telephone line is busy.<br>     对不起，先生，电话占线。<br>'),(12025,'sire','sired','sired','siring','sires','n. (古用法)陛下<br>\nvt. 产生,创作',' A sire should be respected.<br>     父辈应当被尊重。<br>\n The old man has sire a boy child at the age of seventy.<br>     那位老人在七十岁时得子做了父亲。<br>'),(12026,'siren','','','','sirens','n. 汽笛,警报器',' An ambulance was racing along with its sirens wailing.<br>     救护车响着警报急驰而过。<br>\n We all heard the air-raid siren.<br>     我们都听到了空袭警报器的声音。<br>'),(12027,'sirloin','','','','','n. 牛里脊肉',''),(12028,'sirocco','','','','siroccos','n. 热风(从非洲向南欧)',''),(12029,'sirup','','','','','n. 糖浆',''),(12030,'sister','','','','sisters','n. 姐妹',' Joan and Lily are sisters.<br>     琼和丽丽是姐妹。<br>\n You should take care of your niece for the sake of your sister.<br>     看在姐妹的份上, 你应该照顾你的侄女。<br>'),(12031,'sister-in-law','','','','sisters-in-law','n. 夫或妻的姊妹',''),(12032,'sit','sat','sat','sitting','','v. 坐,坐',' He sat at his desk working.<br>     他坐在桌子旁边工作。<br>\n The farm sits on the side of the hill.<br>     农场位于山坡上。<br>'),(12033,'sitcom','','','','','n. 情景喜剧',' This sitcom is produced in cooperation with Hong Kong TV.<br>     这部连