xteens','num. 十六<br>\npron.&a. 十六(个,只...)',' She\'s sixteen, going on seventeen.<br>     她十六岁，快十七岁了。<br>\n Although she was only sixteen years old, she could hold her own against players twice her age.<br>     虽然她只有16岁，但是她能战胜比她年纪大两位的选手。<br>'),(12047,'sixteenth','','','','sixteenths','num.&a. 第十六',' My new house is on the sixteenth floor.<br>     我的新家在第十六层。<br>\n Tom is one of the seers in the sixteenth century.<br>     汤姆是十六世纪的先知。<br>'),(12048,'sixth','','','','sixths','n. 六分之一<br>\nnum.&a. 第六',' My new house is on the sixth floor.<br>     我的新房子在六楼。<br>\n The youngest children are in the first form, the oldest in the sixth form.<br>     最小的儿童上一年级, 最大的上六年级.<br>'),(12049,'sixtieth','','','','','num. 第六十',''),(12050,'sixty','','','','sixties','六十',' My father is sixty years old.<br>     我父亲六十岁了。<br>\n This fire hose is about sixty feet long.<br>     这段消防水管大约有60 英尺长。<br>'),(12051,'sizable','','','','','a. 相当大的',' Jack was hanging on to those shares-- he thought they\'d show a sizable gain shortly.<br>     杰克留着那些股票不脱售，他认为那些不久就会给他带来相当大的赚头。<br>\n Market booming sizable quantity report exchange hand at vary price15.5to16.25 corresponding7% to12% rise<br>     市场旺盛，据报道成交量很大：价格约涨7％到12％，在15。50到16。25之间。<br>'),(12052,'size','','','','','n. 尺寸,大小<br>\nv. 按大小排列或分类<br>\nvt. 按大小排列(或分类)',' The company doubled its size in nine years.<br>     9年来这家公司的规模扩大了一倍。<br>\n Would you like to try this jacket on for size, sir?<br>     先生，你要不要试穿一下这件夹克衫，看看尺寸是否合适？<br>'),(12053,'sizeable','','','','','a. 相当大的',''),(12054,'sizzle','sizzled','sizzled','sizzling','','vi. (油煎食物时)发出咝咝声',''),(12055,'sizzler','','','','','n. 炎热天气,大热天',' Whew! What a sizzler!<br>     唷! 多热的天哪!<br>'),(12056,'skate','','','','','n. 冰鞋<br>\nv. 滑冰<br>\nvi. 溜冰,滑冰',' My brother skates well.<br>     我弟弟滑冰滑得好。<br>\n I can move very fast across the ice on skates.<br>     我穿着冰鞋在冰上滑得很快。<br>'),(12057,'skateboard','skateboarded','skateboarded','skateboarding','','n. 溜冰板(一种装有滑轮的椭圆形滑板)',' Skateboards are the latest craze.<br>     滑板运动是目前最时兴的玩意儿.<br>'),(12058,'skater','','','','skaters','n. 滑雪的人',' The figure skater glided gracefully over the ice.<br>     花样滑冰者在冰上优雅地滑行。<br>\n The skater executed a perfect set of figures.<br>     那个滑冰的人做出了一套完美的花样动作。<br>'),(12059,'skates','','','','','pl.冰鞋',' I can move very fast across the ice on skates.<br>     我穿着冰鞋在冰上滑得很快。<br>\n May I borrow your roller skates?<br>     我可以借你的滚轴溜冰鞋吗？<br>'),(12060,'skating','','','','','n. 溜冰',' The boy is crazy about skating.<br>     那孩子溜冰着了迷。<br>\n The girls are skating and the boys (are) watching.<br>     这些女孩在溜冰，而这些男孩在观看。<br>'),(12061,'skein','','','','skeins','n. 一束(线或纱)',' She passed me a skein of wool.<br>     她递给我一绞毛线。<br>'),(12062,'skeletal','','','','','a. 骨骼的,骸骨的',' A systematic long-term change of this kind suggests the action of natural selection and indicates that female skeletal characteristics confer greater fitness. But is this the whole story.<br>     这种长期的系统变化说明自然选择的作用，并表明女性骨骼的特性较大的适应性。但是，情况完全是这样的吗？<br>\n The point or mode of attachment of a skeletal muscle to the bone or other body part that it moves.<br>     附着处骨骼肌肉与骨或它所带动的身体其他部分的连接点或连接方式<br>'),(12063,'skeleton','','','','skeletons','n. (建筑物、计划的)骨架,纲要,骨骼',' I\'ve written the skeleton of my report, but I have to fill in the details.<br>     我已写出报告的梗概，但我必须补充细节。<br>\n People cheered when the57, 000-ton steel skeleton was topped out in33 weeks-12 days ahead of schedule.<br>     当这座建筑物的５７，０００吨重的钢骨在３３周内——比原计划提前１２天——完成时，人们欢欣鼓舞。<br>'),(12064,'skeptic','','','','','n. 怀疑者,怀疑论者,无神论者',''),(12065,'skeptical','','','','','a. 怀疑的',' The leader had the gift of being able to infuse enthusiasm into the most skeptical member of the group.<br>     那位领导人很有天赋，能使团体中最持怀疑态度的人都充满热情。<br>'),(12066,'skepticism','','','','','n. 怀疑论,怀疑态度,怀疑主义',' A habitual attitude of skepticism or resistance to the suggestions, orders, or instructions of others.<br>     否定态度，怀疑主义对别人的建议，命令或指导持习惯性的怀疑态度或反对意见<br>\n If a man really have strong faith he can indulge in the luxury of skepticism.<br>     假如一个人果真有强烈的信仰，就可以纵情享受（宗教上的）怀疑主义了。<br>'),(12067,'sketch','','','','','n. 素描,草图<br>\nv. 描绘略图,写生',' Sketch out what you intend to do.<br>     把你要做的事概括地叙述一下。<br>\n In his most recent satirical sketch Heywood sent up fashionable young women who worked for charitable causes.<br>     海伍德在最近的一篇讽刺小品里讽刺了那些为慈善事业工作的时髦女郎。<br>'),(12068,'sketchpad','','','','','略图,草图',''),(12069,'sketchy','','','','','a. 写生的,写生风格的,概略的',' Your essay gives a rather sketchy treatment of the problem.<br>     你的文章只粗略地涉及到这个问题.<br>\n Information about the crisis was sketchy and hard to get.<br>     关於这次危机的消息所知甚少并且很难获得.<br>'),(12070,'skew','skewed','skewed','skewing','skews','a. 斜交的(不对称的,误解的)<br>\nn. 斜交(歪斜,歪轮,斜砌石)',' The picture is a bit skew.<br>     这幅画有点歪.<br>'),(12071,'skewer','skewered','skewered','skewering','','n. (烤肉用的)串肉杆<br>\nv. 用杆串好',' He skewered his foot on a nail.<br>     他的脚踩在钉子上了.<br>'),(12072,'ski','skied','skied','skiing','ski','a. 滑雪（用）的<br>\nn. 雪橇<br>\nv. 滑雪',' They often go skiing in December.<br>     他们经常在十二月份去滑雪。<br>\n The girl asked her father to buy a pair of skis for her.<br>     那个女孩请求她的父亲给她买一副滑雪板。<br>'),(12073,'ski lift','','','','','n. (运送滑雪者等的)上山吊椅',''),(12074,'skid','skidded','skidded','skidding','skids','n. 滑动(滑道,刹车,制件缺陷,走下坡路)<br>\nvt 打滑刹车(制件缺陷,走下坡路)',' Even as he shouted the warning the car skidded.<br>     就在他高喊注意的时候，汽车滑动了。<br>\n The brakes locked, causing the car to skid.<br>     汽车因车轮刹住而打滑。<br>'),(12075,'skiff','','','','','n. 轻舟,小船',''),(12076,'skiing','','','','','n. 滑雪,滑雪术',' They often go skiing in December.<br>     他们经常在十二月份去滑雪。<br>\n I like skiing and in the meantime, I know it is very dangerous.<br>     我喜欢滑雪, 同时也知道这非常危险。<br>'),(12077,'skilful','','','','','a. 巧妙的, 技术好的',' A skilful ball from Snow put out the opposing team\'s prize hope in the first five minutes.<br>     斯诺队的一个巧妙的球使对方队在前五分钟就失去了夺魁的希望。<br>\n The new method caught on and many peasants became very skilful at it.<br>     这个新方法很受欢迎，很多农民都掌握得很好了。<br>'),(12078,'skill','','','','skills','n. 技能,技巧',' It takes skill to tune a piano.<br>     为钢琴调音需要专门技能。<br>\n The point is there is a difference between an interest and a skill.<br>     这就是兴趣与技能是有区别的。<br>'),(12079,'skilled','','','','','a. 有技能的,熟练的',' I am skilled in operating a computer.<br>     我能够熟练操作计算机。<br>\n Skilled mechanics can quickly be brought to the assistance of motorists.<br>     熟练的机械师可迅速地被派去救援汽车驾驶人。<br>'),(12080,'skillet','','','','skillets','n. 煎锅',' Rub up the skillet please.<br>     请把长柄锅擦亮。<br>'),(12081,'skillful','','','','','a. 熟练的',' He is a skillful teacher.<br>     他擅长教学。<br>\n Skillful in the use of the hands.<br>     灵巧的手的使用熟练的<br>'),(12082,'skillfully','','','','','ad. 巧妙地, 技术好地',' John weaving his way skillfully through the crowds, was one of the few who managed to get a good view of the President.<br>     约翰巧妙地七弯八拐地穿过人群，是为数不多的几位能清楚地看见总统的人之一。<br>\n He steered the car skillfully through the narrow streets.<br>     他熟练地驾驶着汽车穿过狭窄的街道。<br>'),(12083,'skillfulness','','','','','a. 有技巧(制作精巧)',''),(12084,'skim','skimmed','skimmed','skimming','','v. 略读, 掠过, 滑过',' It took me an hour to skim the book.<br>     我花了一小时把这本书浏览了一遍。<br>\n The hovercraft is able to skim over the water.<br>     气垫船能掠过水面飞速行驶。<br>'),(12085,'skimmer','','','','','n. 撇取浮皮的器具,大略阅读的人,网杓',''),(12086,'skimming','','','','skimmings','早期获利',' It took me an hour to skim the book.<br>     我花了一小时把这本书浏览了一遍。<br>\n A seagull skims the water.<br>     海鸥掠过水面。<br>'),(12087,'skimp','skimped','skimped','skimping','','vt. 少给(淘汰选矿,马马虎虎的做)<br>\na. 少的(不足的)',' They have to skimp on fuel in winter.<br>     冬天他们得节省燃料.<br>\n Use plenty of oil. Don\'t skimp!<br>     多用些油. 别省著!<br>'),(12088,'skimpy','','','','','a. 缺乏的(马虎的)',''),(12089,'skin','skinned','skinned','skinning','skins','n. 皮肤,外皮<br>\nv. 剥皮,长皮',' He skinned his knee when he fell.<br>     他摔跤时把膝盖擦破了。<br>\n He had brown skin.<br>     他的皮肤是棕色的<br>'),(12090,'skin-deep','','','','','a. 肤浅的,外表上的',' His political commitment is only skin-deep.<br>     他政治上的承诺只是表面文章。<br>'),(12091,'skinflint','','','','','n. 吝啬鬼',''),(12092,'skinhead','','','','','n. (尤指英国)短发,行为暴戾的青少年',''),(12093,'skinny','','','','','a. 皮状的(体积小的)，皮包骨头的',' You\'re skinny enough without going on a diet!<br>     你不必节食就已经够瘦的了!<br>\n He looks much too skinny/scrawny to be a weight-lifter.<br>     他瘦骨嶙峋的, 当不了举重运动员.<br>'),(12094,'skip','','','','','n. 跳跃,跳读<br>\nv. 跳越,蹦跳,略过,跳过',' Children are fond of skipping.<br>     孩子们喜欢跳绳。<br>\n Lambs skipped in the field.<br>     小羊在田野里跳跃。<br>'),(12095,'skipper','','','','','n. 船长,主将,正驾驶',' The skipper knows where every storm is.<br>     船长知道每一个风暴在什么地方。<br>'),(12096,'skipping','','','','','暂时把货物腾空(以便称量皮重)',' Children are fond of skipping.<br>     孩子们喜欢跳绳。<br>\n I read the whole book without skipping (a page).<br>     我一页不漏地读完了全书.<br>'),(12097,'skirmish','skirmished','skirmished','skirmishing','skirmishes','n. 前哨战,小争斗,小冲突<br>\nv. 从事小争斗',' This area is peaceful except for a few skirmishes in the distance.<br>     除了远处的零星的小冲突之外，这个地区是和平的。<br>\n The skirmish grew into a major battle.<br>     小冲突扩大形成大战斗。<br>'),(12098,'skirt','skirted','skirted','skirting','skirts','n. 裙子<br>\nv. 位于...边缘,装边于,回避<br>\nvt. 绕开,位于...的边缘',' How many skirts do you have?<br>     你有多少条裙子？<br>\n We decided to skirt round the town center.<br>     我们决心绕过市中心。<br>'),(12099,'skit','','','','','n. 滑稽短剧',' A short, comic vaudeville skit that ends with lights off.<br>     熄灯结束以灯光熄灭而结束的一场滑稽杂耍短剧<br>\n A traditional British Christmas entertainment for children, usually based on nursery tales and featuring stock characters in costume who sing, dance, and perform skits.<br>     童话剧为儿童演的一种传统的英国圣诞节娱乐剧，常以幼儿园故事为基础，演员装扮成牲畜进行唱歌、跳舞和表演滑稽剧<br>'),(12100,'skittish','','','','','a. 易激动的, 轻佻的',' She gets very skittish when her boy-friend is around.<br>     她男朋友在场时, 她就显得格外轻佻.<br>'),(12101,'skive','skived','skived','skiving','','v. 躲避工作',' She always skives off early.<br>     她总是在干活儿时早早溜走.<br>\n He\'s usually skiving down at the pub when there\'s gardening to be done.<br>     他常在需要整理花园时就躲进酒馆去了.<br>'),(12102,'skulduggery','','','','skulduggeries','n. 舞弊,作假',''),(12103,'skulk','skulked','skulked','skulking','skulks','v. 躲躲闪闪,潜行<br>\nvi. 潜伏,躲躲闪闪',' I don\'t want reporters skulking around my house.<br>     我不愿看到记者在我家周围偷偷摸摸地走动。<br>\n The burglar skulk behind the door when he hear someone talking.<br>     当窃贼听到有人谈话时即躲在门后。<br>'),(12104,'skull','','','','skulls','n. 头骨',' The victim\'s skull had been stove in by a heavy instrument.<br>     遇害者的头颅是用重物击穿的.<br>\n The farmer turned up a human skull while ploughing the field.<br>     那农民　地时挖出一个人类的头颅骨.<br>'),(12105,'skunk','skunked','skunked','skunking','skunk','n. 臭鼬鼠,其皮毛,讨厌鬼<br>\nv. 使惨败,给对方吃零鸭蛋',' Did she also take the skunk to her bosom?<br>     她把臭鼬也抱在怀里吗？<br>\n Exclusiveness is a characteristic of recent riches, high society, and the skunk.<br>     排他主义，是为了近来的有钱人家、上流阶级以及臭鼬等的特色。<br>'),(12106,'sky','skied','skied','skying','skies','n. 天空',' The sky turned dark as the storm came near.<br>     暴风雨来临时，天空转暗。<br>\n The sky slowly changed from blue to red.<br>     天空慢慢由蓝色变为红色。<br>'),(12107,'skylark','skylarked','skylarked','skylarking','skylarks','云雀',''),(12108,'skylight','skylighted','skylighted','skylighting','skylights','n. 天窗',''),(12109,'skyline','','','','skylines','n. 天涯,地平线,以天空为背景的轮廓',' The Empire State Building is a famous landmark on the New York skyline.<br>     帝国大厦是纽约高楼大厦中著名的地面标志物.<br>\n The prince vituperated against the developers for ruining London\'s skyline.<br>     王子斥责土地开发商破坏了伦敦市建筑物映在空中的轮廓线之美.<br>'),(12110,'skyrocket','skyrocketed','skyrocketed','skyrocketing','','n. 烟火(高空探测火箭)<br>\nvt 使...上升',' Prices skyrocketed.<br>     物价飞涨。<br>'),(12111,'skyscraper','','','','skyscrapers','n. 摩天大楼',' The skyscraper was wrapped in fog.<br>     摩天大楼笼罩在云雾之中。<br>\n A new skyscraper has been put up downtown.<br>     市中心又建起了一座摩天大厦。<br>'),(12112,'slab','','','','','n. 平板,厚的切片<br>\nv. 切成厚板,以平板盖上',' The top of the table was formed by a stone slab.<br>     桌面是一块石板。<br>\n A slab of stone laid flat over a grave.<br>     平放在墓上的纪念碑石<br>'),(12113,'slack','','','','','n. 松弛,家常裤<br>\na. 松弛的,不流畅的<br>\nv. 使松弛,松弛',' Winter is the slack season at most hotels.<br>     冬天是大多数旅馆的淡季。<br>\n Business is slack just now.<br>     目前生意萧条不振。<br>'),(12114,'slacken','slackened','slackened','slackening','','v. 使松弛,变弱',' Please slacken the tent rope before it rains.<br>     下雨前，请将帐篷的绳索放松。<br>\n The train slackened speed as we approached the station.<br>     当我们快到车站时，火车减慢了速度。<br>'),(12115,'slacker','','','','','n. 逃避工作的人,懒虫',' He\'s a slacker, he actually skipped off and left us to do the clearing away.<br>     他是个懒鬼，他居然悄悄地溜走而把清除工作留给我们来做。<br>'),(12116,'slag','slagged','slagged','slagging','','n. 熔渣,铁屑,矿渣<br>\nv. 使变成熔渣,变熔渣',' Some come off in the form of gases, others collect as slag.<br>     有的化成气体跑掉了，有的结成了熔渣。<br>\n The limestone absorb impurity from the ore and form a fluid slag which floats on the surface of the heavier molten iron.<br>     石灰石吸咐了铁矿石中的杂质，形成浮在较重的铁水表面上的流动渣。<br>'),(12117,'slain','','','','','slay 的过去分词',' Two visitors were brutally slain yesterday.<br>     昨天有两名游客惨遭杀害。<br>\n A living creature slain and offered as a sacrifice during a religious rite.<br>     祭品在宗教仪式中的屠杀并奉为牺牲品的活的动物<br>'),(12118,'slake','slaked','slaked','slaking','','vt. 消除(沸化)',' Hasn\'t NATO slaked his lust for blood?<br>     难道北约还没有满足他的血腥的欲望吗？<br>\n We had to slake ourselves with rainwater in the desert.<br>     在沙漠中我们不得不用雨水解渴。<br>'),(12119,'slalom','slalomed','slalomed','slaloming','','n. 障碍滑雪比赛',''),(12120,'slam','','','','','n. 砰然声,猛然<br>\nv. 猛然关上,砰地关上',' He slammed the papers down on my desk and angrily walked out.<br>     他把文件使劲扔在我的桌子上便怒气冲冲地走了出去。<br>\n He closed the door with a slam.<br>     他砰的一声关上门。<br>'),(12121,'slander','slandered','slandered','slandering','','n. 中伤,毁谤<br>\nv. 中伤,毁谤',' Her company is suing her for slander because of her remarks about their safety record.<br>     由于她发表了关于公司安全记录的言论，该公司正以诽谤罪起诉她。<br>\n He claims he was slandered at the meeting.<br>     他声称在会上受人诋毁。<br>'),(12122,'slanderous','','','','','a. 诽谤的,中伤的',' A plaintiff\'s interpretation in a libel suit of allegedly libelous or slanderous material.<br>     对被告诽谤言辞的解释在诽谤案件中，原告对所称的诽谤的或谣言的材料的解释<br>\n Containing or implying calumny; slanderous or defamatory.<br>     栽赃的含有或隐含有明知故犯嫌疑的；诽谤或中伤的<br>'),(12123,'slang','slanged','slanged','slanging','','a. 俚语(的)<br>\nn. 俚语<br>\nvt. 辱骂,漫骂',' \"Grass\" is a criminal slang for \"informer\".<br>     grass 是罪犯用的俚语，意思是“告密的人”。<br>\n Slang insinuates itself into the language.<br>     俚语慢慢地渗入语言中。<br>'),(12124,'slant','slanted','slanted','slanting','slants','n. 倾斜,斜面<br>\na. 倾斜的<br>\nv. 使倾斜,倾斜',' Most handwriting slants to the right.<br>     大多数手写体都向右斜。<br>\n We slanted across the river.<br>     我们斜渡过河。<br>'),(12125,'slap','slapped','slapped','slapping','slaps','n. 掴,侮辱,拍击声<br>\nv. 拍击,侮辱,申斥<br>\nad. 正面地,直接地,突然地',' He slapped me on the back on my way home.<br>     在我回家的路上，他在我背上拍了一下。<br>\n His decision was a slap in the face to those who had tried to change his mind.<br>     他的决定对于那些试图要说服他的人不啻是一记耳光。<br>'),(12126,'slapdash','','','','','a. 草率的,马虎的',''),(12127,'slapstick','','','','','n. 打闹剧(演员用击板相互追打发出声响得名)',' A light dramatic work in which highly improbable plot situations, exaggerated characters, and often slapstick elements are used for humorous effect.<br>     轻喜剧一种轻松的戏剧形式，其中极为荒谬可笑的情节背景，夸张的角色和一些闹剧的成分以表现幽默的效果<br>\n I prefer the dry humour of situation comedy to the slapstick of circus clowns.<br>     我喜欢滑稽戏不动声色的幽默。不喜欢马戏小丑的低级滑稽。<br>'),(12128,'slash','','','','','vt. 深砍(螺纹滚,削减,湿地)<br>\nn. 深砍(螺纹滚,削减,湿地)，斜线\"/\"',' He is slashing wildly at his opponent with a sword.<br>     他正用剑疯狂地朝对手乱砍。<br>\n The government promises to slash taxes.<br>     政府许诺大幅减税。<br>'),(12129,'slat','','','','','n. (木,金属等的)板条',' The oil paintings are backed up with slats.<br>     这些油画是用细木条做背衬的。<br>\n Gales uprooted trees and whipped the slats off roofs.<br>     大风把树木连根拔起，并掀掉了屋顶的石板瓦。<br>'),(12130,'slate','','','','','n.板岩, 石板, 石片, 蓝色<br>\nadj. 暗蓝灰色的, 含板岩的<br>\nv. 铺石板',' I\'ve no change, could you put these eggs on the slate?<br>     我没零钱，能把这些蛋钱记在帐上吗？<br>\n The falling slate sliced into his arm.<br>     落下来的一块石片划破了他的手臂.<br>'),(12131,'slattern','','','','','n. 邋遢的女人',''),(12132,'slaughter','slaughtered','slaughtered','slaughtering','','n. 残杀,屠杀,大量杀戮<br>\nv. 残杀,屠杀',' Millions of cattle are slaughtered every day.<br>     每天有数百万头牛被屠杀。<br>\n Bison used to roam through the American great plains, but most of them are slaughter by hunter.<br>     从前野牛在美国大平原上漫游，但是大多数都被猎人屠杀了。<br>'),(12133,'slave','slaved','slaved','slaving','slaves','n. 奴隶,附件,卑鄙的人<br>\nv. 拼命工作',' He treats his wife like a slave.<br>     他把妻子当作奴隶看待。<br>\n The slave has never experienced the sweetness of freedom.<br>     这个奴隶从未体验过自由的快乐。<br>'),(12134,'slave trade','','','','','奴隶买卖/交易',' The book only touches on the causes of the war and does not do justice to the influence of the slave trade.<br>     这本书只稍稍涉及了一下战争的原因，并没有公正评价奴隶贸易的影响。<br>'),(12135,'slaver','slavered','slavered','slavering','','n. 奴隶商人,奴隶贩卖船,口水<br>\nv. 垂涎,淌口水,淌口水弄脏',' The dealer was slavering over some precious stones.<br>     那商人对一些宝石垂涎欲滴.<br>\n Stop slavering over thatbaby!<br>     别总看著人家的孩子了!<br>'),(12136,'slavery','','','','','n. 奴隶制,奴役',' Abraham Lincoln abolished slavery in the United States.<br>     亚伯拉罕·林肯在美国废除了奴隶制。<br>\n The abolition of slavery had been exercised in many countries.<br>     奴隶制在许多国家已经被废除。<br>'),(12137,'slay','slew','slain','slaying','','v. 杀,杀害,残杀',' Your jokes slay me.<br>     你的笑话笑死我了。<br>\n Two visitors were brutally slain yesterday.<br>     昨天有两名游客惨遭杀害。<br>'),(12138,'sleazy','','','','','a. 质地薄的,没有内容的,廉价的',''),(12139,'sled','sledded','sledded','sledding','sleds','n. 雪撬,小雪撬<br>\nv. 用撬搬运,座撬前往,乘撬',' The man attached a strong rope to his sled.<br>     那人将一条结实的绳子系在他的雪撬上。<br>\n Jack dug his sled out of the cellar.<br>     杰克在地窑里找到了他的雪橇。<br>'),(12140,'sledding','','','','','n. 雪撬的使用,适于使用雪撬的状态,进行状况',' Kathy had hard sledding in her math course because she was poorly prepared.<br>     凯西的数学很难进步，因为她的基础太差。<br>'),(12141,'sledge','','','','','n. 雪橇,大锤<br>\nv. 用雪橇搬运,坐雪橇往',' The sledge gained momentum as it ran down the hill.<br>     雪橇从山上下冲时动量越来越大.<br>\n A frame or sledge on which condemned persons were dragged to execution.<br>     囚笼，囚车一种架子或雪橇，遭指控者被拖到其上施刑<br>'),(12142,'sledgehammer','sledgehammered','sledgehammered','sledgehammering','','n. 长柄大锤',' Printing business cards on a thirty-inch press is using a sledgehammer to crack a nut.<br>     在30英寸印刷机上印刷名片简直是大材小用，得不偿失。<br>'),(12143,'sleek','sleeked','sleeked','sleeking','','a. 光滑的,井然有序的<br>\nv. 使光滑,梳拢',' The lion\'s fur is sleek.<br>     狮子的毛皮整洁而光亮。<br>\n He sleeked back his hair with water before going in to meet her.<br>     他进去见她之前，用水将头发梳理得很光亮。<br>'),(12144,'sleep','slept','slept','sleeping','sleeps','n. 睡眠,静止,睡意<br>\nv. 睡觉,睡眠,静止',' I didn\'t sleep well last night.<br>     昨晚我睡不安稳。<br>\n I haven\'t had enough sleep lately.<br>     最近我睡眠不够。<br>'),(12145,'sleeper','','','','sleepers','n. 枕木(卧车)',' I am a bad sleeper.<br>     我总睡不好。<br>\n That movie is the sleeper of the year: suddenly everyone has to see it.<br>     那部电影爆出冷门，成了今年的最佳影片。突然间，每一个人都不得不一睹为快<br>'),(12146,'sleepily','','','','','ad. 懒散地,瞌睡地',''),(12147,'sleeping','','','','','n.&a. 睡[眠]着(的)',' The baby was sleeping quietly in his crib.<br>     婴儿在他的小床里静静地睡着。<br>\n Occasionally she had to take sleeping pills.<br>     她偶尔不得不吃安眠药。<br>'),(12148,'sleeping bag','','','','','睡袋',' A good sleeping bag is an essential part of every campers equipment.<br>     一个完好的睡袋是每个露宿者必不可少的装备。<br>\n She had psyched herself up so much for the camping trip that she forgot her sleeping bag.<br>     因为要出去野营，她特别地激动，以至于忘了带睡袋<br>'),(12149,'sleeping pill','','','','','n. 安眠药片',' I need some sleeping pill.<br>     我需要一些安眠药片。<br>\n The sleeping pills soon put her off to sleep.<br>     安眠药片不久就使她睡着了。<br>'),(12150,'sleepless','','','','','a. 不睡眠的,睡不著的,不休息的',' Her irresponsible behaviour cost her father many sleepless nights.<br>     她那不负责任的行为使她父亲许多夜不得安眠。<br>\n She looked pale and drawn after weeks of sleepless nights.<br>     她经历了数周不眠之夜, 看上去脸色苍白, 形容憔悴.<br>'),(12151,'sleeplessness','','','','','n. 失眠',''),(12152,'sleepwalk','sleepwalked','sleepwalked','sleepwalking','','vi.&n. 梦游,梦行',''),(12153,'sleepwalking','','','','','n. 梦游(症)',''),(12154,'sleepy','','','','','a. 欲睡的',' I\'m too sleepy to watch the end of the show.<br>     我太困倦了，不能把戏看完。<br>\n The softness of the breeze made him feel sleepy.<br>     柔和的微风使他昏昏欲睡。<br>'),(12155,'sleet','sleeted','sleeted','sleeting','','n. 雨雪<br>\nv. 下雨雪,下冰雹',' The rain turned to sleet.<br>     雨变成了雨夹雪。<br>\n The quantity of water, expressed in inches, precipitated as rain, snow, hail, or sleet in a specified area and time interval.<br>     降雨量雨的数量以英寸表示，为某一地区在特定时间段内雨、雪、冰雹或霰的积累量<br>'),(12156,'sleeve','sleeved','sleeved','sleeving','sleeves','n. 袖子',' He rolled up his sleeves and got to work in the garden.<br>     他卷起了袖子，在花园里干起活来。<br>\n There\'s a big rip in my sleeve.<br>     我的袖子破了一大块.<br>'),(12157,'sleeves','','','','','袖子',' My mother tacked the sleeves on before sewing them.<br>     我妈妈在把袖子缝好之前，先用大针脚把它缝好。<br>\n He rolled up his sleeves and got to work in the garden.<br>     他卷起了袖子，在花园里干起活来。<br>'),(12158,'sleigh','sleighed','sleighed','sleighing','sleighs','n. 雪橇<br>\nvi. 坐雪橇',' My feet were cold as stone when I got out of the sleigh.<br>     我从雪橇上下来时，两只脚冻得像石头一样。<br>\n My feet were cold as a stone when I got out of the sleigh.<br>     我从雪橇上下来时，两脚冻得像石头一样。<br>'),(12159,'sleight','','','','','n. 手法,技巧,奇计',' Manual skill and dexterity in the execution of tricks; sleight of hand.<br>     手法敏捷变戏法时手法的熟练和敏捷；戏法<br>'),(12160,'slender','','','','','a. 细长的,苗条的',' All girls want to be slender.<br>     所有女孩都希望苗条。<br>\n The birch has smooth bark and slender branches.<br>     桦树有光滑的皮和细长的枝。<br>'),(12161,'slept','','','','','v. 睡,就寝,永眠<br>\nvbl. 睡,就寝,永眠',' I would have preferred a bed, but beggars can\'t be choosers so I slept on the sofa.<br>     我本想要张床, 但是叫花子不能挑肥拣瘦, 所以我就睡在沙发上了.<br>\n You slept right through the thunderstorm.<br>     你一直睡著, 这场雷雨都没把你吵醒.<br>'),(12162,'slew','slewed','slewed','slewing','','n. 沼地,极多,回转<br>\nv