n Snipers and irregulars fell on the hapless patrol.<br>     狙击兵和非正规军袭击了巡逻队<br>'),(12298,'snob','','','','','n. 势利小人',' He is not a snob and therein lay his downfall.<br>     他不是个势利小人，而他失败的原因正在于此。<br>\n This part of the town has a lot of snob appeal.<br>     该城的这一区很能吸引自视甚高的人.<br>'),(12299,'snobbery','','','','snobberies','n. 充绅士气派,俗不可耐的性格',' Is his distance a result of snobbery or shyness?<br>     他态度冷淡是因为他势利眼呢，还是因为他腼腆？<br>\n Her novel is a satire on social snobbery.<br>     她的小说是描写势利小人的讽刺作品.<br>'),(12300,'snobbish','','','','','a. 势利的',' Jane feels she can never compete with these snobbish, elegant people.<br>     简·爱感到她永远无法同这些高雅却势利的人们竞争。<br>\n It is strange that he should fall in love with such a snobbish girl.<br>     说来真怪，他居然与那位高傲的女孩子坠入情网。<br>'),(12301,'snooker','','','','','vt. 挫败(阻挠,把...置于困境)',' Our local pub has gone to the dogs since they put in the snooker tables and video jukeboxes.<br>     我们当地的酒店自从把落袋撞球戏桌子和电视自动电唱机摆进来后就垮了。<br>\n I don\'t understand the finer points of snooker but I enjoy watching it on TV.<br>     我不太懂落袋台球游戏, 但我喜欢看电视里的这种节目.<br>'),(12302,'snoop','snooped','snooped','snooping','','n. 窥探者<br>\nv. 窥伺,打听',' The house perfects often snoop around our campus at night.<br>     学生纠察队经常夜间在校园里巡逻。<br>\n I say you kiss my wife! what have you to say.- Do not let me catch you snoop again!<br>     我说你跟我老婆亲嘴！你有什么话说。——可别让我再看到你偷偷摸摸的探头头脑！<br>'),(12303,'Snoopy','','','','','a. 爱窥探者,爱管闲事者',' Given to prying into the affairs of others; snoopy.<br>     好管闲事的刺探别人事务的；爱探听的<br>'),(12304,'snooty','','','','','a. 自大的,傲慢的',''),(12305,'snore','snored','snored','snoring','snores','n. 鼾声<br>\nv. 打鼾',' The woman said that she could not sleep without her husband\'s snore after 20 years of marriage.<br>     那位妇人说结婚20年来，听不到她丈夫的呼噜声，她就睡不着觉。<br>\n Her husband snores loudly.<br>     她丈夫睡觉时打鼾很响。<br>'),(12306,'snorkel','','','','','n. 液压起重机(通气管)<br>\nvt 用通气管潜航',''),(12307,'snort','snorted','snorted','snorting','snorts','v. 喷著气弄响鼻子,哼著鼻子,嘶嘶响著排气<br>\nn. 鼻息,满杯',' The horse snorted and stamped its hoof impatiently.<br>     这匹马呼哧呼哧地喘着气，不耐烦地跺着蹄子。<br>\n He snorted out a reply.<br>     他气呼呼地回答。<br>'),(12308,'snout','','','','snouts','n. 鼻口部,鼻子,蛇管的前端',' The snout of the pig you drew on the picture is too long.<br>     这幅画上你画的猪鼻子太长了。<br>\n A leather or wire restraining appliance that, when fitted over an animal\'s snout, prevents biting and eating.<br>     动物的口套，口络套在动物的鼻口部以防止其咬和吃的一种皮质或者金属丝制成的限制装置<br>'),(12309,'snow','snowed','snowed','snowing','snows','n. 雪<br>\nv. 下雪',' It was snowing heavily.<br>     天正在下大雪。<br>\n He watched his woods filled up with snow.<br>     他眼看着他的树林渐渐被雪覆盖。<br>'),(12310,'snowboard','','','','','测雪板',''),(12311,'snowdrift','','','','','n. 雪堆',' The dad-blamed car got stuck in a snowdrift.<br>     该死的汽车陷在雪堆里了。<br>\n In the severe winter of1947, farmers had to dig their livestock out of huge snowdrifts.<br>     在1947年严峻的冬天，农民们不得不挖开大雪堆把他们的家畜救出来。<br>'),(12312,'snowfall','','','','','n. 降雪',' Such a snowfall is few and for between in our province.<br>     这样大的雪在我们省里是少有的。<br>\n A heavy snowfall block the main road.<br>     一次严重的降雪阻塞了主要公路。<br>'),(12313,'snowflake','','','','snowflakes','n. 雪花,雪片',' Snowflakes are melting as they reached the ground.<br>     雪花触地便融化了。<br>'),(12314,'snowman','','','','snowmen','n. 雪人',' The Abominable Snowman who haunts the imagination of climbers in the Himalayas is hardly more elusive.<br>     常使喜马拉雅山的攀登者浮想联翩的雪人也不比此更难以捉摸。<br>'),(12315,'snowmobile','','','','','n. 雪上车',''),(12316,'snowshoe','snowshoed','snowshoed','snowshoeing','snowshoes','n. 雪鞋<br>\nvi. 穿着雪鞋走',''),(12317,'snowstorm','','','','snowstorms','n. 暴风雪',' Because of the snowstorm, the churchgoer did not go to church.<br>     因为暴风雪，经常去做礼拜的人没有去教堂。<br>\n The roads were sanded after the snowstorm.<br>     道路在暴风雪之后铺上了沙子。<br>'),(12318,'snowy','','','','','a. 多雪的,被雪所覆盖著的,下雪的',' He looks kind with snowy hair.<br>     雪白的头发使他看上去很和善。<br>\n I like to go for a walk in the snowy streets.<br>     我喜欢去雪中的街道上散步。<br>'),(12319,'snub','snubbed','snubbed','snubbing','snubs','a. (鼻子等)短平而上翘<br>\nv. 冷落,不理睬',' The second snub settled his hash.<br>     第二次碰壁使他不敢再找麻烦了。<br>\n I know the way we were snubbed still rankles, but it\'s got to be put behind us now. We must cooperate with these people.<br>     我知道，他们过去那样冷落我们，至今仍然令人气愤，但是现在我们应该把它置之脑后，因为我们必须同这些人合作。<br>'),(12320,'snuff','','','','','n. 烛花(鼻烟)<br>\nvt 剪烛花(嗅)',' The leaves of this plant, dried and processed chiefly for use in cigarettes, cigars, or snuff or for smoking in pipes.<br>     烟草叶这种植物的叶子，晒干后加工，主要用于制作香烟、雪茄、鼻烟或在烟斗中抽<br>\n Her goal was to snuff out all political opposition to her empress ambitions.<br>     她的目的是要消除一切不利于她实现发女皇宏图的政治对抗。<br>'),(12321,'snuffle','snuffled','snuffled','snuffling','','v. 抽鼻子,嗅',' The dog was snuffling around the roots of a tree.<br>     那条狗在树根处嗅来嗅去.<br>'),(12322,'snuffling','','','','','a. 抽着鼻子的, 假装虔诚的',' The dog was snuffling around the roots of a tree.<br>     那条狗在树根处嗅来嗅去.<br>'),(12323,'snug','snugged','snugged','snugging','snugs','a. 舒适的,合身的<br>\nv. 使整洁干净',' He sat in a snug little room.<br>     他坐在一个舒适的小房间里。<br>\n Snug, comfortable, and warm.<br>     舒适的、惬意的和温暖的<br>'),(12324,'snuggle','snuggled','snuggled','snuggling','','v. 挨近,依偎',' They snuggled up (together) in bed.<br>     他们依偎著躺在床上.<br>\n The child snuggled up to her mother.<br>     那孩子紧贴在母亲身边.<br>'),(12325,'snugly','','','','','ad. 紧紧地,紧密地',' He fitted the map snugly into the bag.<br>     他把地图整齐地塞进包里。<br>\n Plane one side of the panel down until it fits snugly into place.<br>     把板条的一侧刨一刨，使它放在这儿刚好合适。<br>'),(12326,'so','','','','','ad. 如此,如是,如...那样<br>\nconj. 所以,因此,所以',' It was snowing, and so I could not go out.<br>     天在下雪，所以我无法外出。<br>\n You have pride and so have I.<br>     你有自尊心，我也有。<br>'),(12327,'so far as','','','','','a. 就...说(到...的程度)',' So far as English is concerned, it is not so difficult as you might think.<br>     就英文而言，它并不像你所认为的那样难。<br>\n The bus route goes so far as that, so you\'ll need to take a taxi.<br>     汽车路线到此为止了, 你得叫辆的士。<br>'),(12328,'so long','','','','','再见',' So long!<br>     再见！<br>\n My wife is expecting me at home. I must be off now. So long!<br>     我妻子正在家等着我呢。我必须要走了。再见！<br>'),(12329,'so long as','','','','','只要',' You may eat anything, so long as you don\'t eat too much.<br>     只要不吃得太多，你可以吃任何东西。<br>\n I don\'t care about the price, so long as the car is in good condition.<br>     我不计较价钱，只要车很好用就行了。<br>'),(12330,'So long!','','','','','再见！',''),(12331,'so much','','','','','ad. 这么(全然)',' She turned away in horror at the sight of so much blood.<br>     看到这么多的血, 她害怕地将脸扭向了一边。<br>\n Success lies not so much as in luck as in hard work.<br>     与其说成功在于运气不如说是辛勤努力。<br>'),(12332,'soak','soaked','soaked','soaking','soaks','n. 浸,湿透,大雨<br>\nv. 使上下湿透,浸,吸入',' Are you in favour of soaking the rich?<br>     你赞成向富人多徵税吗？<br>\n Don\'t stand out there: you\'ll get soaked through.<br>     你别站在外边，要不全身都要湿透了<br>'),(12333,'soaked','','','','','a. 湿透的',' The rain had soaked through his coat.<br>     雨把他的大衣淋透了.<br>\n The blood soaked through his shirt and stained his jacket.<br>     他的血透过衬衫染污了上衣.<br>'),(12334,'soaking','','','','','a. 浸湿的',' Are you in favour of soaking the rich?<br>     你赞成向富人多徵税吗？<br>\n The dirty clothes are soaking in soapy water.<br>     脏衣服都在肥皂水里泡著呢.<br>'),(12335,'soap','soaped','soaped','soaping','soaps','n. 肥皂',' He washed his hands with a toilet soap.<br>     他用香皂洗手。<br>\n The soap slipped out of my hand.<br>     肥皂从我手上滑落了。<br>'),(12336,'soap opera','','','','','n. 肥皂剧',' No soap opera fan can complain that the Senate Judiciary Committee hearings that usurped the network tales of sex and power could not deliver their daily emotional fix. It was an astounding day for television viewers, right up there with Watergate.<br>     喜欢看肥皂剧的人不会抱怨参议院司法委员会听证会不能提供每天的感情刺激。在色情与权力故事方面它取代了电视台。对电视观众那是令人耳目一新的一天，可与水门事件媲美。<br>\n What a sensational story! It has all the elements of a soap opera.<br>     多麽耸人听闻的事! 具备连续剧的一切要素.<br>'),(12337,'soapy','','','','','a. 像肥皂样的(肥皂质的,泖有肥皂的,滑腻的)',' The dirty clothes are soaking in soapy water.<br>     脏衣服都在肥皂水里泡著呢.<br>\n Soapy was tossed into prison without trial.<br>     苏比未经审叛就被投进了监狱。<br>'),(12338,'soar','soared','soared','soaring','','n. 高扬<br>\nv. 往上飞舞,高耸',' His imagination resemble the wing of an ostrich. it enabled him to run, though not to soar.<br>     他的想象力有类于鸵鸟的翅膀—虽未可以飞翔，犹可使他奔驰。<br>\n Set the bird\'s wings with gold and it will never again soar in the sky.<br>     鸟翼上系上了黄金，这鸟便永不能再在天上翱翔了。<br>'),(12339,'soaring','','','','','a. 猛增的,剧增的',' Inflation has sent food costs soaring.<br>     通货膨胀于食物价格飞涨。<br>\n The glider was soaring above the valley.<br>     那架滑翔机在山谷上空滑翔。<br>'),(12340,'sob','sobbed','sobbed','sobbing','sobs','n. 空间轨道的轰炸机；呜咽, 哭泣<br>\n<br>\nv. 哭诉, (风等)发呜咽声, 哭泣',' The child\'s sobs gradually died down.<br>     那孩子的啜泣声渐渐静了下来.<br>\n She sobbed out the story of her son\'s violent death.<br>     她哭著诉说儿子横死的经过.<br>'),(12341,'sober','sobered','sobered','sobering','','a. 清醒的,稳重的<br>\nv. 使沉著,从醉里醒来',' He sobered up quickly when he heard the terrible news.<br>     他听到这个坏消息，马上就清醒过来了。<br>\n The bad news had a sobering effect on all of us.<br>     对我们大家来说，这个坏消息是发人深省的。<br>'),(12342,'soberly','','','','','ad. 清醒地,严肃地',''),(12343,'sobriety','','','','','n. 清醒,严肃',''),(12344,'sobriquet','','','','','n. 绰号',''),(12345,'so-called','','','','','a. 所谓的',''),(12346,'soccer','','','','','n. 英式足球',' People love to play soccer.<br>     人们喜欢踢足球。<br>\n The boy who is speaking to Helen enjoys playing soccer.<br>     正在跟海伦谈话的那男孩喜爱踢足球。<br>'),(12347,'sociable','','','','sociables','a. 好交际的,社交的',' Her sociable manner is really a mask for a very shy nature.<br>     她那好交际的作风，实际上是她腼腆天性的伪装。<br>\n Shunning the society of others; not sociable.<br>     厌恶社交的避免与别人交往的；不爱社交的<br>'),(12348,'sociably','','','','','ad. 和蔼可亲地,善于应酬地',''),(12349,'social','','','','socials','a. 社会的',' Man is a social being.<br>     人是社会性的动物。<br>\n We are invited to a small social gathering.<br>     我们被邀请参加一个小型社交聚会。<br>'),(12350,'social climber','','','','','追求更高社会地位的人,向上爬的人',' Mrs Brown is known as a social climber.<br>     布朗太太是有名的趋炎附势的人。<br>'),(12351,'social studies','','','','','n. 社会学科',''),(12352,'socialism','','','','','n. 社会主义',' Who is the founder of the scientific socialism?<br>     谁是科学社会主义的奠基人？<br>\n Some say that capitalism and socialism will eventually converge.<br>     有人说资本主义和社会主义最终会合而为一。<br>'),(12353,'socialist','','','','socialists','a. 社会主义的<br>\nn. 社会主义者',' We\'ll have a subject of socialist principles this term.<br>     这个学期我们将学习社会主义原理。<br>\n They all support socialist policies.<br>     他们都拥护社会主义的政策。<br>'),(12354,'socialistic','','','','','a. 社会主义(者)的',' Some of her views are rather socialistic.<br>     她的观点颇有一些社会主义倾向.<br>\n That socialistic nation pay homage to the previous premier.<br>     那个社会主义国家向前任首相表达敬意。<br>'),(12355,'socialite','','','','','n. 社会名流,名士',''),(12356,'sociality','','','','','n. 社交, 交际, 社会性',''),(12357,'socialize','socialized','socialized','socializing','','vt. 使...社会化(使...社会主义化,使...公有)<br>\nv. 交际',''),(12358,'socialized','','','','','a. 社交化的',''),(12359,'socializing','','','','','n. 交往,交际',''),(12360,'socially','','','','','ad. 在社会上,在社交上,亲切地',' The white people here don\'t mix socially with the natives.<br>     这里的白种人不与土人交往.<br>\n The care of the baby naturally tied her down so that she was not so active socially as before.<br>     要照顾婴儿，自然拴住了她，使她不能像以前那样积极参加社会活动。<br>'),(12361,'society','','','','societies','n. 社会',' Society has a right to expect people to obey the law.<br>     社会有权要求人们守法。<br>\n She joined the university art society.<br>     她加入了大学里的艺术协会。<br>'),(12362,'socioeconomic','','','','','a. 社会经济的',' A host of compelling socioeconomic problems.<br>     许多令人不得不接受的社会经济问题<br>'),(12363,'sociological','','','','','a. 社会学的',' French social scientist and a founder of sociology who is known for his study of social values and alienation. His important works include The Rules of Sociological Method(1895).<br>     涂尔干，埃米尔1858－1917法国社会科学家，是社会学的创始人之一，以其对社会价值与异化的研究著称，他的重要著作包括社会方式的规则（1895年）<br>\n The study of the cultural, behavioral, and sociological aspects of spatial distances between individuals.<br>     人类空间统计学研究人与人之间空间距离的文化，行为，社会层面的学科<br>'),(12364,'sociologist','','','','','n. 社会学家',' Ms Lucy, as a professional sociologist and committed feminist, is, however, not surprised. Nor is she amused.<br>     但是，作为一位职业社会学家和女权运动者，露西小姐并不觉得奇怪。她也不在乎。<br>\n A sociologist who specializes in the problems of cities and urban life.<br>     都市学专家研究专业方向为城市问题和城市生活的社会学家<br>'),(12365,'sociology','','','','','n. 社会学',' French social scientist and a founder of sociology who is known for his study of social values and alienation. His important works include The Rules of Sociological Method(1895).<br>     涂尔干，埃米尔1858－1917法国社会科学家，是社会学的创始人之一，以其对社会价值与异化的研究著称，他的重要著作包括社会方式的规则（1895年）<br>\n Major courses contributing to management qualification: Management, accounting, economics, marketing, sociology.<br>     对管理资格有帮助的主要课程：管理学、会计学、经济学、市场学、社会学。<br>'),(12366,'sock','','','','','n. 短袜<br>\nv. 重击,痛打',' The speaker really socked it to them!<br>     发言的人给他们个迎头痛击!<br>\n Can\'t you put a sock in it? I\'m trying to work.<br>     别出声了好不好? 我要工作呢.<br>'),(12367,'socket','socketed','socketed','socketing','sockets','n. 插座,插口',' His eyes nearly jumped from their sockets in surprise.<br>     他惊讶得眼珠子差一点跳出来。<br>\n This type of bulb screws into the socket.<br>     这种灯是拧到灯座上的.<br>'),(12368,'socks','','','','','n. 袜子(复数)',' She rolled the socks into a ball.<br>     她把袜子卷成一团。<br>\n These socks retail at 1 dollar a pair.<br>     这些袜子零卖一美圆一双。<br>'),(12369,'Socrates','','','','','n. 苏格拉底[哲学家]',' Many ancient Greeks were followers of Socrates.<br>     许多古希腊人都是苏格拉底的追随者。<br>\n Socrates laid the foundations of logic.<br>     苏格拉底奠定了逻辑学的基础。<br>'),(12370,'Socratic','','','','','a. 苏格拉底问答法的',''),(12371,'sod','','','','','n. (一块)草皮,草地',' You stupid sod!<br>     你这个蠢蛋!<br>\n The new boss is a mean sod!<br>     新来的上司是个大坏蛋!<br>'),(12372,'soda','','','','sodas','n. 汽水,苏打',' He ordered two lime sodas.<br>     他要了两杯酸橙苏打汽水。<br>\n Two brandies and soda, please.<br>     劳驾，来两杯白兰地加苏打水。<br>'),(12373,'soda fountain','','','','','(美)冷饮柜,冷饮小卖部',' A soda fountain drink made by blending carbonated water with flavored syrup.<br>     磷酸果汁汽水将碳化水和调味果汁混合而成的一种苏打冷饮饮料<br>'),(12374,'soda pop','','','','','n. 汽水',''),(12375,'sodden','soddened','soddened','soddening','','a. 浑身湿透的,不成样子的,浸过酒的<br>\nv. 拿水浸,变柔软,腐败',' My shoes are sodden from walking in the rain.<br>     我在雨里这么一跑，鞋都湿了。<br>'),(12376,'sodium','','','','','n. 钠',' Sodium and water react (together).<br>     钠和水能起反应.<br>\n Common salt is a compound of sodium and chlorine.<br>     食盐是钠和氯的化合物.<br>'),(12377,'sofa','','','','sofas','n. 沙发',' The old man is dropping away in the sofa.<br>     这位老人在沙发上打起瞌睡来。<br>\n I nestled down on the big sofa and began to read novels.<br>     我舒适地靠在大沙发上，开始看小说。<br>'),(12378,'soft','','','','','a. 软的',' It\'s very comfortable to step on the soft ground in the spring.<br>     春天的时候，踩在松软的地面上非常舒服。<br>\n Don\'t be so soft there\'s nothing to be afraid of.<br>     别这麽窝囊，没什麽可怕的嘛。<br>'),(12379,'soft drink','','','','','软饮料',' I\'d prefer a soft drink.<br>     我喜欢喝软饮料.<br>\n A soft drink with ice cream floating in it.<br>     饮料一种上面浮有冰淇淋的软饮料<br>'),(12380,'softball','','','','','n. 垒球(与棒球相似,但球场较小,球大而软)',' I like to play softball.<br>     我喜欢玩垒球。<br>'),(12381,'soften','softened','softened','softening','','v. 使...变柔软,变柔和,减轻',' He was softened into tears.<br>     他被感动得流下了眼泪。<br>\n The more you soften a request, the more polite it becomes.<br>     你愈使请求柔婉，请求就愈变为客气。<br>'),(12382,'softener','','','','','n. 起软化作用的东西,软化剂,柔软剂',''),(12383,'softly','','','','','ad. 柔和地,静静地,温柔地',' A passage to be played softly or quietly.<br>     轻声演奏的乐段要轻轻或静静地演奏的段落<br>\n Speak softly and carry a big stick.<br>     说话要温和，但手里要拿着大棒。<br>'),(12384,'softness','','','','','n. 柔和,温柔',' The softness of his reply calmed her down.<br>     他温和的回答使她冷静下来。<br>\n The softness of the breeze made him feel sleepy.<br>     柔和的微风使他昏昏欲睡。<br>'),(12385,'soft-soap','','','soft-soaping','','v. 阿谀, 说恭维话',' Don\'t try to soft-soap me; I\'m not changing my mind.<br>     别给我灌米汤了, 反正我不改主意.<br>'),(12386,'software','','','','','n. 软件',' There are many sorts of software in my computer.<br>     我的计算机里有很多软件。<br>\n Our English software is an interactive educational software.<br>     我们的英语软件是一种交互式教育软件。<br>'),(12387,'soggy','','','','','a. 湿透的',' If you boil the vegetables too long, they\'ll go soggy.<br>     要是你把蔬菜煮得太久，菜就糊了。<br>\n Resembling a marsh; soggy.<br>     沼泽地的象沼泽地的；湿润的<br>'),(12388,'soil','','','','','n. 土地,土壤<br>\nv. 弄脏,(使)变脏<br>\nvi. 变脏<br>\nvt. 弄脏',' She makes her living from the soil.<br>     她以务农为生。<br>\n What shall we grow in this alkaline soil?<br>     我们应该在碱性土壤里种什么？<br>'),(12389,'sojourn','','','','','vt. 旅居(逗留)<br>\nn. 旅居(逗留)',' He sojourned with a friend in Wales for two weeks.<br>     他在威尔士一个朋友那儿住了两个星期.<br>'),(12390,'sojourner','','','','','n. 逗留者,旅居者',' The sojourner has been in Wales for two weeks.<br>     那个寄居者在威尔士已经逗留了两个星期。<br>\n I am a sojourner of that village.<br>     我是那个小村庄的逗留者。<br>'),(12391,'solace','solaced','solaced','solacing','solaces','n. 安慰<br>\nv. 使快乐<br>\nvt. 安慰(物),缓和',' I found solace from troubles in listening to music.<br>     我听音乐，以便在烦恼时得到安慰。<br>\n The sick man found solace in music.<br>     那男病人从音乐中获得了安慰.<br>'),(12392,'solar','','','','','a. 太阳的，太阳能',' We can use solar energy to do many things today.<br>     如今，我们可以利用太阳能做很多事情。<br>\n The solar cell can convert the energy of sunlight into electric energy.<br>     太阳能电池能把阳光的能量转化为电能。<br>'),(12393,'solar system','','','','','太阳系',' The planets of our solar system are Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus and Neptune.<br>     我们太阳系的行星有水星、金星、地球、火星、木星、土星、天王星、海王星。<br>\n One of the four brightest satellites of Jupiter and the eighth in distance from the planet. Originally sighted by Galileo, it is one of the largest satellites in the solar system.<br>     木卫三木星四颗最亮的卫星之一，距木星的远近程度是第八位。最早伽利略观察到，是太阳系最大的卫星之一<br>'),(12394,'sold','','','','','v. 卖,背叛,销售<br>\nvbl. 卖,背叛,销售',' The record was a big hit and sold a million copies.<br>     这张唱片非常成功，卖了一百万张。<br>\n The painting was sold at a profit.<br>     这幅图画可获利销售。<br>'),(12395,'solder','soldered','soldered','soldering','','n. 焊接剂,接合物,羁绊<br>\nv. 施以焊接,接合,补修',' He soldered the wire back on.<br>     他把金属丝重新焊上去了。<br>'),(12396,'soldier','soldiered','soldiered','soldiering','soldiers','n. 士兵,军人',' The trade of the soldier is war.<br>     士兵的职业是打仗。<br>\n The soldier saw a gun jutting out from a bush.<br>     那士兵看见一支枪从矮树丛伸出来。<br>'),(12397,'sole','','','','','a. 唯一的<br>\nn. 脚底,鞋底<br>\nn. sole 或soles 鳎鱼',' The sole survivor of the crash was a little boy.<br>     这次撞车事故的唯一幸存者是一个小男孩。<br>\n I\'m having my shoes soled and heeled.<br>     我要叫人给鞋子换鞋底和鞋跟。<br>'),(12398,'solecism','','','','','n. 语法错误, 谬误, 失礼',''),(12399,'solely','','','','','ad. 独自地,单独地',' He was actuated solely by greed.<br>     他完全是受了贪欲的驱使.<br>\n I did it solely for his sake.<br>     我完全为了他才做那件事。<br>'),(12400,'solemn','','','','','a. 庄严的,严肃的,隆重的',' He looked at her with a solemn expression.<br>     他表情严肃地望着她。<br>\n The hollies in the garden make it look solemn.<br>     冬青树使园子看上去很肃穆。<br>'),(12401,'solemnity','','','','solemnities','n. 严肃,一本正经',' The judge took up the gavel with solemnity.<br>     法官严肃地拿起了小木槌。<br>\n Solemnity is a trick of the body to hide the faults of the mind.<br>     一本正经的态度，是肉体为了掩饰精神上的缺陷而作出的一手花招。<br>'),(12402,'solemnly','','','','','ad. 严肃地, 庄严地',' As God is my witness (ie I solemnly swear), that\'s the truth!<br>     上帝为我作证, 一切属实!<br>\n On Saturday morning my father solemnly dispensed pocket money to each of the children.<br>     星期六上午我父亲郑重其事地给每个孩子发零花钱.<br>'),(12403,'Solferino','','','','','品红(一种染料)',''),(12404,'solicit','solicited','solicited','soliciting','','v. 请求,乞求,诱惑',' She was fined for soliciting.<br>     她因拉客而被罚款.<br>\n An employee who stands before the entrance to a show, as at a carnival, and solicits customers with a loud, colorful sales spiel.<br>     大声叫卖者在巡回演出时，站在入口处以大声叫喊或各种各样降价推销招徕顾客的雇员<br>'),(12405,'solicitation','','','','','n. 恳求,教唆',' I accepted the gifts at her solicitation.<br>     在她的恳求之下，我接受了礼物。<br>\n His selfishness caused him to refuse my solicitation.<br>     他的自私让他拒绝了我的请求。<br>'),(12406,'solicitor','','','','solicitors','n. 律师',' The solicitor is preparing a case in the court tomorrow.<br>     这位律师正在为明天法庭审理的案件做准备。<br>\n Her solicitor drew up her last will and testament.<br>     她的律师拟就了她的遗嘱。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (12407,'solicitous','','','','','a. 热心的,热切想要...的,热切期望',' She is so solicitous and persistent that she virtually kills you with kindness.<br>     她非常关心而固执，以致她的善意实际上反而使人感到尴尬。<br>\n I am solicitous of his help.<br>     我渴得到他的帮助。<br>'),(12408,'solicitude','','','','solicitudes','n. 担心(焦虑,渴望)',' Her letter showed deep solicitude for your welfare.<br>     她的来信表示对您的安康甚为挂念。<br>\n The solicitude of the caring husband for his wife made her feel unhappy.<br>     那位体贴的丈夫对妻子的关怀使她感觉很不高兴。<br>'),(12409,'solid','','','','solids','a. 固体的,结实的,可靠的,实心的<br>\nn. 固体',' Water becomes solid when it freezes.<br>     水结冰时便变成固体。<br>\n They were glad to leave the boat and put their feet on the solid ground.<br>     他们很高兴能离开海船，回到坚实的陆地上。<br>'),(12410,'solidarity','','','','solidarities','n. 团结',''),(12411,'solidify','solidified','solidified','solidifying','','v. 凝固,团结',' Solidifying chiefly as a minor intrusion, especially as a dike or sill, before reaching the earth\'s surface. Used of rocks.<br>     半深成的，浅成的在到达地球表面之前的主要作为小型岩石群固化的，尤其象岩脉或岩床的凝固用于指岩石<br>\n A process of rock alteration or mineral formation brought about by the action of gases emitted from solidifying magma.<br>     气成作用；气成通过从岩浆凝固中释放气体的作用下引起的岩石改变或矿物形成的过程<br>'),(12412,'solidly','','','','','ad. 坚硬地, 稳固地',' We are solidly united on this issue.<br>     我们在这个问题上是团结一致的.<br>\n It rained solidly for three hours.<br>     雨不停地下了三个小时.<br>'),(12413,'soliloquy','','','','soliloquies','n. 独白,自言自语',''),(12414,'solitaire','','','','','纸牌',' The lonely old lady filled up the time between supper and retiring with solitaire.<br>     那孤独的老妇人晚饭后至睡觉前以玩单人纸牌消磨时间。<br>\n The game solitaire.<br>     单人纸牌戏<br>'),(12415,'solitary','','','','solitaries','a. 孤独的,唯一的<br>\nn. 隐士',' A solitary rider was seen in the distance.<br>     远处有个孤零零的骑马的人。<br>\n The trapper leads a solitary life in the mountains.<br>     那个设陷阱捕猎的人孤独地生活在山里。<br>'),(12416,'solitude','','','','solitudes','n. 孤独<br>\n独居,荒僻之地,幽静的地方',' I am not fond of solitude.<br>     我不喜欢孤独。<br>\n The scientist has spent six months in the solitudes of the Antarctic.<br>     这位科学家已经在人迹罕至的南极待了六个月了。<br>'),(12417,'solo','soloed','soloed','soloing','solos','n. 独奏,独唱<br>\na. 单独的<br>\nv. 放单飞',' The piano solo was well rendered.<br>     那支钢琴独奏曲弹得真好。<br>\n The concert began with a piano solo.<br>     音乐会以钢琴独奏曲拉开序幕。<br>'),(12418,'soloist','','','','','n. 独奏者,独唱者',' The tenor soloist is unable to appear tonight because of illness.<br>     男高音独唱者因病今晚不能演出.<br>\n He often appears as a soloist.<br>     他经常作为独奏者上台演出。<br>'),(12419,'Solomon','','','','','所罗门 (男子名) 所罗门(古以色列国王大卫之子, 以智慧著称); [喻]圣人; 聪明人; 贤人',' The court of King Solomon was noted for its splendor.<br>     所罗门国王的宫廷以其华丽著称。<br>\n I am thinking about taking a fifth wife; why not? Solomon had a thousand wives and he is a synonym for wisdom.<br>     我在考虑娶第五个妻子；为什么不可以？所罗门王有妻妾一千，而他还是智慧的同义词哩。<br>'),(12420,'solon','','','','','n. 贤人,议员',''),(12421,'solstice','','','','','n. 至,至点,至日',' The summer solstice, about June21.<br>     夏至夏季的至点，大约为6月21日<br>\n A fabled bird, identified with the kingfisher, that was supposed to have had the power to calm the wind and the waves while it nested on the sea during the winter solstice.<br>     神翠鸟一种神话中的鸟，人们认为它即是翡翠鸟，据说当它在冬至期间在海上筑巢时，具有平息风浪的力量<br>'),(12422,'soluble','','','','','a. 可溶解的',' This kind of tablet is soluble in water.<br>     这种药片能溶于水。<br>\n These problems are not readily soluble.<br>     这些问题不容易解决。<br>'),(12423,'solution','','','','solutions','n. 解答,解决办法,溶解,溶液',' What color is copper sulfate solution?<br>     硫酸铜溶液是什么颜色？<br>\n It seems (to me) (to be) the best solution.<br>     （依我看）这似乎是最好的解决办法.<br>'),(12424,'solvability','','','','','可解性,溶解度',''),(12425,'solve','solved','solved','solving','','v. 解答(难题),解决<br>\nvt. 解答,解决',' I can\'t solve the problem.<br>     我解答不了这个难题。<br>\n The greatest scholar cannot solve this difficult problem.<br>     再伟大的学者也没有办法解答这个难题吧。<br>'),(12426,'solvency','','','','','n. 偿付能力',' Fears about the solvency of the banks precipitated the great economic crash.<br>     对银行偿付能力出现恐慌更加速了经济的崩溃。<br>'),(12427,'solvent','','','','solvents','n. 溶剂<br>\na. 有偿付能力的,有溶解力的',' The hypothetical universal solvent once sought by alchemists.<br>     万能溶剂炼金术士曾一度寻求的假想的万能溶剂<br>\n The chemical process by means of which a change in physical condition, as in pressure or temperature, or the action of a solvent causes a molecule to split into simpler groups of atoms, single atoms, or ions.<br>     离解（作用）在物理状态下，如在压力或温度下的变化，或在溶剂的作用下，使分子分离为更简单的一组原子、单原子或离子的化学过程<br>'),(12428,'solver','','','','','解算机,求解程序',''),(12429,'Somalia','','','','','n. 索马里',''),(12430,'somatic','','','','','a. 身体的,肉体的,身体的',''),(12431,'somber','','','','','a. 微暗的,阴天的,阴森的',' She looked up staring at the somber December sky.<br>     她抬起头来，凝望着十二月份阴沉沉的天空。<br>\n A funeral is a somber occasion.<br>     葬礼是个忧郁的场合。<br>'),(12432,'sombre','','','','','a. 昏暗的,忧郁的,悲观的',' She looked up staring at the sombre December sky.<br>     她抬起头来，凝望着十二月份阴沉沉的天空。<br>\n A funeral is a sombre occasion.<br>     葬礼是个忧郁的场合。<br>'),(12433,'some','','','','','a. 一些,少许,某一<br>\nint. 一些,一部份,若干',' Some man at the door is asking to see you.<br>     门口有个男人要求见你。<br>\n There is some ice in the bush.<br>     树丛里有些冰。<br>'),(12434,'somebody','','','','somebodies','n. 重要人物<br>\npron. 某人,有人',' He thinks himself to be somebody, while actually he is nobody.<br>     他自以为是个人物，其实他算不了什么。<br>\n He mistook me for somebody else.<br>     他把我错认为别人了。<br>'),(12435,'someday','','','','','ad. 有一天',' I never realized that someday I would be living in New York.<br>     我从来没有想到有一天我居然会住在纽约。<br>\n Perhaps someday I\'ll be rich.<br>     也许有一天我会富起来。<br>'),(12436,'somehow','','','','','ad. 不知怎么地,设法',' I always know I\'d get the job, somehow.<br>     也不知为什么，我总觉得能得到那份工作。<br>\n Somehow, I don\'t feel I can trust him.<br>     不知什么缘故，我觉得不能信任他。<br>'),(12437,'someone','','','','','pron. 某人,有人',' Someone has to lock up the house.<br>     总要有人把房子锁起来。<br>\n Someone in the audience began to laugh.<br>     观众中有人开始笑起来。<br>'),(12438,'somersault','somersaulted','somersaulted','somersaulting','somersaults','n. 跟斗',' A gymnast on the trampoline was turning (ie performing) somersaults.<br>     有个体操运动员正在蹦床上做空翻.<br>\n The child somersaulted across the gymnasium.<br>     那孩子翻著跟头从体育馆这头翻到那头.<br>'),(12439,'something','','','','','pron.某事（物），某东西',' I think I dropped something.<br>     我想我掉了东西。<br>\n I want something to eat.<br>     我想吃点东西。<br>'),(12440,'sometime','','','','','a. 以前的,某一时间<br>\nad. 改天,来日',' He is my sometime boss.<br>     他是我从前的上司。<br>\n I hope to see you again sometime next year.<br>     我希望明年某一时候再见到你。<br>'),(12441,'sometimes','','','','','ad. 有时',' Sometimes the patient cried for the pain.<br>     有时这个病人疼得哭起来。<br>\n The vowels in the English alphabet are a,e,i,o,u, and, sometimes, y.<br>     英语的元音字母有a，e，i，o，u，有时也包括y。<br>'),(12442,'somewhat','','','','','n. 某物,几分<br>\nad. 多少,几分',' The price was somewhat higher than I\'d expected.<br>     这价格比我预料的稍高一些。<br>\n The cake we made was somewhat of a failure.<br>     我们做的蛋糕不大成功。<br>'),(12443,'somewhere','','','','','ad. 在某处<br>\nn. (在)某处',' He lives somewhere in the neighborhood.<br>     他住在附近某处。<br>\n You will find the text somewhere in the Bible.<br>     你会在圣经里找到这段文章。<br>'),(12444,'somnambulist','','','','','n. 梦游者',''),(12445,'somnolence','','','','','n. 嗜睡,想睡,瞌睡',''),(12446,'somnolent','','','','','a. 想睡的,催眠的',' The noise of the stream had a pleasantly somnolent effect.<br>     小河潺潺的流水声有宜人的催眠效果.<br>'),(12447,'son','','','','sons','n. 儿子',' His wife born him a son.<br>     他妻子给他生了一个儿子。<br>\n The people in Christendom believe that the Christ was the Son of God.<br>     在基督教界人们相信基督是上帝之子。<br>'),(12448,'sonar','','','','','n. 声纳',''),(12449,'sonata','','','','sonatas','n. 奏鸣曲',' Her recital led off/She led off her recital with a Haydn sonata.<br>     她在独奏会上首先演出的是海顿的奏鸣曲.<br>\n The first part of a composition in sonata form that introduces the themes.<br>     呈示部奏呜曲式音乐作品中表现主旋律的第一部分<br>'),(12450,'song','','','','songs','n. 歌曲',' She is humming a popular song.<br>     她在哼一支流行歌曲。<br>\n This song is often ascribed to Bach.<br>     这首歌曲常被说成是巴赫做的。<br>'),(12451,'songwriter','','','','','n. 歌曲作家，歌曲作者',''),(12452,'sonic','','','','','a. 音波的,音速的',' Sonic booms can break windows.<br>     音爆可以震破窗户。<br>\n A trademark used for a sonic depth finder.<br>     回音测深仪一种声音测深仪的商标<br>'),(12453,'son-in-law','','','','sons-in-law','n. 女婿',''),(12454,'sonnet','','','','sonnets','n. 十四行诗',' Our teacher told us to recite this sonnet written by Shakespeare.<br>     老师要求我们背诵莎士比亚的这首十四行诗。<br>\n He read us a sonnet that celebrates love.<br>     他给我们读了一首歌颂爱情的十四行诗。<br>'),(12455,'sonority','','','','sonorities','n. 响亮,响亮程度',''),(12456,'sonorous','','','','','n. 宏亮的,响亮的,堂堂的',' There is a sonorous bell in the tower.<br>     塔里有一口洪亮的钟。<br>\n The sonorous voice of the priest resounded in the church.<br>     教士那圆润低沉的声音在教堂里回响。<br>'),(12457,'soon','','','','','ad. 不久,很快',' Let us start as soon as he comes.<br>     等他一来我们就动身。<br>\n I\'ll be back soon.<br>     我很快就回来。<br>'),(12458,'sooner','','','','','[美](在政府开放西部前)抢先取得占有权的人, 用不正当手段先下手的人',' A good name is sooner lost than won.<br>     【谚】美名易失，不易得。<br>\n The sooner the better.<br>     st. 越快越好.<br>'),(12459,'soot','sooted','sooted','sooting','','n. 煤烟,烟尘<br>\nv. 熏以煤烟',' She is sweeping the soot off the chimney.<br>     她正把烟筒里的黑灰扫掉。<br>\n You\'vegot a smudge of soot on your cheek.<br>     你脸上有块煤灰污迹.<br>'),(12460,'sooth','','','','','n. 真实',' Sooth to say, I got up late.<br>     说实话，我起来晚了。<br>\n Her tenderness soothed my anger.<br>     她的亲切平息了我的怒气。<br>'),(12461,'soothe','soothed','soothed','soothing','','v. 缓和,使...安静,安慰',' A bit of embrocation will soothe your bruised knee.<br>     用一点搽剂可使你那青肿的膝部消肿.<br>\n A nice cup of tea will soothe your nerves.<br>     一杯好茶可以使你的心绪平静下来。<br>'),(12462,'soothing','','','','','a. 安慰的,安慰性的',' Her words had a soothing effect.<br>     她的话起了安慰的作用。<br>\n Having the quality or fragrance of balm; soothing.<br>     香味的，安慰的有香膏、香油、香脂的品质或香味的；安慰的<br>'),(12463,'sop','sopped','sopped','sopping','sops','n. 车间超载部件(标准操作程序,测量点操作计划)',' The child is given a prize as a sop to her disappointed parents.<br>     给那孩子一个奖品是为了安慰她父母的失望心情。<br>\n The plan we were all sop enthusiastic about seems less attractive when viewed in the cold light of day.<br>     我们原先都对这计划抱有热望，但回过头来冷静地、切合实际地想一想，似乎计划的吸引力还不够。<br>'),(12464,'Sophia','','','','','n. 索菲娅（女子名）',' Sophia has it all over Olivia in looks and charm.<br>     索菲娅的长相和魅力都胜过奥利维亚。<br>\n Sophia said that she understood but this was not the case.<br>     索菲娅说她懂了，但事实并非如此。<br>'),(12465,'sophism','','','','','n. 诡辩',''),(12466,'sophist','','','','','n. 诡辩家',' Many politicians are cunning sophists.<br>     许多政客都是狡猾的诡辩家.<br>'),(12467,'sophisticated','','','','','a. 诡辩的,久经世故的',' As far as defense is concerned, we need to buy more sophisticated weapons.<br>     就防御的观点来说，我们需要购买更多精密的武器。<br>\n The electronics aboard the new aircraft are very sophisticated.<br>     安装在新飞行器上的电子器件非常复杂<br>'),(12468,'sophistication','','','','','n. 诡辩,强词夺理,混合',' Lacking sophistication or worldly experience; naive.<br>     幼稚的，天真的不世故的，天真的<br>\n The avionics on this spacecraft represent a new generation of sophistication.<br>     这架航天飞机上的电子设备代表了新一代的复杂水平<br>'),(12469,'sophistry','','','','sophistries','n. 诡辩',' He won the argument by sophistry.<br>     他靠诡辩赢了那场争论.<br>\n Deception by trickery or sophistry.<br>     圈套通过诡计或诡辩进行的欺骗<br>'),(12470,'sophomore','','','','sophomores','n. 大学二年级生(在企业中工作第二年的人)',' Lily is a Sophomore now.<br>     莉莉现在大学二年级。<br>'),(12471,'sophomoric','','','','','a. 一知半解的',''),(12472,'soporific','','','','','a. 催眠的,想睡的<br>\nn. 催眠剂',' Inducing sleep or sedation; soporific.<br>     安神的，麻醉的，镇静的<br>\n Inducing sleep; soporific.<br>     睡眠的产生睡眠的，引起酣睡的<br>'),(12473,'soprano','','','','sopranos','n. 女高音,最高音部,女高音歌手',' The young soprano was taken up by a famous conductor.<br>     那年轻的女高音歌手受到一著名指挥家的提携.<br>\n It\'s a soprano of great compass and of great purity.<br>     这是一种音域宽广，高度纯正的女高音。<br>'),(12474,'sorcerer','','','','sorcerers','n. 男巫士, 魔术师',' This story is about sor