ar you come in.<br>     你吓了我一跳--我没听见你进来.<br>'),(12886,'startling','','','','','a. 令人吃惊的',' That is a startling disclosure of police brutality.<br>     那是一个揭发警察暴行的惊人消息。<br>\n He describes the scene with startling reality.<br>     他对那景象的描述逼真得令人惊讶。<br>'),(12887,'starts','','','','','n. 开始',' After several false starts, she became a successful journalist.<br>     她开始时遇到几次挫折，後来才成为能干的记者<br>\n The film starts at 7.30 and lasts two hours.<br>     影片7点30分开演, 演两个小时.<br>'),(12888,'start-up','','','','','启动',''),(12889,'starvation','','','','','n. 饿死,饥饿',' The poor old man died of starvation.<br>     那个可怜的老人被饿死了。<br>\n The Smiths brushed up against starvation because Mr. Smith couldn\'t find a job.<br>     史密斯先生找不到工作，因此他们一家面临饥饿。<br>'),(12890,'starve','starved','starved','starving','','v. 使饿死,饿得要死',' They tried to starve him into submission.<br>     他们试图用饥饿来使他就范。<br>\n The plant was starved of light and died.<br>     这株植物因为极度缺乏光照而死了。<br>'),(12891,'starved','','','','','a. (=starving)饥饿的',' The plant was starved of light and died.<br>     这株植物因为极度缺乏光照而死了。<br>\n I\'m starved for money.<br>     我的钱不够用。<br>'),(12892,'starving','','','','','a. 饥饿的',' The politician found the piteous cries of the starving children unbearable.<br>     这个政治家发现饥饿的孩子们可怜的哭声让人不忍心听下去。<br>\n We saw the pathetic sight of starving children.<br>     我们看到挨饿的儿童悲惨可怜的样子。<br>'),(12893,'stash','stashed','stashed','stashing','','v. 藏起来,隐藏起来,结束',' He\'s got his life savings stashed (away) in an old suitcase.<br>     他把一辈子的积蓄保藏在一口旧箱子里.<br>'),(12894,'state','stated','stated','stating','states','n. 州,国,情形<br>\na. 国家的,正式的<br>\nv. 说,陈述,声明,规定',' State your name and address.<br>     请说出你的姓名和地址。<br>\n His general state of health is fairly satisfactory.<br>     他总的健康状况相当令人满意。<br>'),(12895,'statecraft','','','','','n. 治国本领',''),(12896,'stated','','','','','a. 决定了的,一定的,定期的<br>\nv. 陈述,说明<br>\nvbl. 陈述,说明',' Lydia briefly stated the business in hand, namely to choose a secretary and treasurer for the committee.<br>     莉迪亚简单地陈述了马上要做的