t obey the statutes in this country.<br>     我们必须遵守这个国家的法规。<br>\n A heading that names a document, statute, or proceeding.<br>     名称命名一份文件、法令或诉讼程序的名字<br>'),(12920,'statutory','','','','','a. 法令的,法定的,触犯法令的',' The constitutional or statutory right to vote.<br>     选举权宪法或法律规定的选举权<br>\n A decision of the local authority pursuant to the power and duties impose upon it by the statutory code.<br>     地方政府根据成文法（典）所给予的权力和义务所作出的决定。<br>'),(12921,'staunch','staunched','staunched','staunching','','v. 止住,止血<br>\na. 坚固的,坚强的,忠实',' They are staunch soldiers.<br>     他们是忠诚的战士。<br>\n I helped her staunch cut.<br>     我帮助她止住了伤口的血。<br>'),(12922,'stave','staved','staved','staving','staves','n. 桶材,窄板<br>\nv. 敲破',' He made a barrel with staves by himself.<br>     他自己用桶板做了一只桶。<br>\n The lost explorers ate birds\' eggs to stave off starvation.<br>     为了避免饿死，那些迷路的勘探人员吃鸟蛋充饥。<br>'),(12923,'stay','stayed','stayed','staying','stays','n. 停留,停止,依靠<br>\nv. 停留,留宿,制止',' The temperature has stayed hot this week.<br>     本周气温一直都很热。<br>\n I stayed late at the party last night.<br>     昨晚我在晚会上呆到很晚。<br>'),(12924,'stead','','','','','n. 代替,用处',' His anorak has stood him in good stead this winter.<br>     他这件带兜帽的夹克在今年冬天对他很有用。<br>\n His knowledge of the subject stood him in good stead.<br>     他的这门学科的知识对他很有好处。<br>'),(12925,'steadfast','','','','','a. 坚定的,踏实的',' Steadfast in allegiance to one\'s homeland, government, or sovereign.<br>     忠心的对自己的祖国，政府或主权无限忠诚的<br>\n Steadfast in purpose, loyalty, or affection; faithful.<br>     坚定在目的、忠诚或感情上坚定不移的；忠诚的<br>'),(12926,'steadfastly','','','','','ad. 固定地(坚定地,不变地,不动摇地)',''),(12927,'steadfastness','','','','','n. 固定不变,坚定',''),(12928,'steadily','','','','','ad. 稳定地,稳固地',' His health is getting steadily worse.<br>     他的健康正逐渐恶化。<br>\n The number of people going to the cinema seems to dwindle steadily.<br>     看电影的人数似乎在逐渐下降。<br>'),(12929,'steady','steadied','steadied','steadying','steadies','a. 稳定的,稳固的<br>\nad. 平稳地,稳固地<br>\nv. (使)稳固, (使)稳定',' The hunter steadied his rifle