assengers are sitting on the deck of the large steamboat chatting.<br>     有些旅客正坐在这只大轮船的甲板上聊天。<br>\n A steamship with the bow and upper deck rounded so as to shed water.<br>     鲸背甲板船一种蒸汽船，带有圆形的船头和上甲板以遮蔽雨水<br>'),(12942,'steel','steeled','steeled','steeling','steels','n. 钢,钢制品<br>\na. 钢的<br>\nv. 使...坚如钢',' This cup is made of stainless steel.<br>     这只杯子是不锈钢做的。<br>\n He steeled himself to tell her about her father\'s death.<br>     他硬起心肠把她父亲的死讯告诉了她。<br>'),(12943,'steep','','','','','a. 险峻的,陡峭的<br>\nv. 浸泡,浸透<br>\nvt. 浸,泡',' She steeped the stained cloth in bleach overnight.<br>     她把有污迹的衣服在洗衣粉里浸了一夜。<br>\n This hill is too steep to ride up on a bicycle.<br>     这山太陡了，骑自行车可上不去。<br>'),(12944,'steepen','steepened','steepened','steepening','','v. 使...陡峭,变陡峻',' The path steepens as you climb the hillside.<br>     沿著山坡往上爬时, 那条小径越来越陡.<br>'),(12945,'steeple','','','','steeples','n. 尖塔',' Orthodox Christian churches often have elaborate steeples.<br>     传统的基督教堂都有精致的尖塔。<br>\n Now they are ready for the steeple chase.<br>     现在他们已准备好进行障碍赛跑。<br>'),(12946,'steer','','','','','v. 引导,驾驶,航行',' He steered the car skillfully through the narrow streets.<br>     他熟练地驾驶着汽车穿过狭窄的街道。<br>\n The drift of a ship or an aircraft to leeward of the course being steered.<br>     偏航，漂移船只或航空器航行过程中向背风面而作的漂移<br>'),(12947,'steering','','','','','n. (汽车或船等的)转向装置',' Turn the wheel to the right to correct the steering.<br>     把方向盘往右边转转, 好修正驾驶上的偏差.<br>\n They found her slumped over the steering wheel.<br>     他们发现她倒伏在方向盘上.<br>'),(12948,'steering wheel','','','','','n. 舵轮(转向盘,驾驶盘,驾驶轮,操向轮)',''),(12949,'stein','','','','steins','n. 啤酒杯',''),(12950,'stele','','','','','n. 刻有碑文的石柱,石碑,匾额',''),(12951,'stellar','','','','','a. 星(状的)',''),(12952,'stem','','','','','n. 茎,干,船首<br>\nv. 堵住,阻止,起源于',' Our ship stemmed on against the current.<br>     我们的船逆流而上。<br>\n She bought some roses with long stems.<br>     她买了一些枝干很长的玫瑰花。<br>'),(12953,'stench','','','','','n. 臭气,恶臭',' From a steaming stench below, the banks were coated with a slimy mould that stuck to them like glue, disgusting to behold and worse to smell<br>     堤岸上铺着一层从下面来的臭气所凝结成的霉东西，使得眼睛和鼻子都感到憎恶。<br>\n Held my nose against the stench.<br>     掩住鼻子使不闻恶臭<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (12954,'stencil','stenciled','stenciled','stenciling','stencils','n. 模版(文字,蜡纸)<br>\nvt 用模版印刷',' Do you know how to cut a stencil?<br>     你会刻蜡版[打蜡纸]吗？<br>\n A fine powder, such as pulverized charcoal, dusted over a stencil to transfer a design to an underlying surface.<br>     印花粉撒于镂花模板上以便在其表面上印出图案的细粉末，如磨碎的木炭粉<br>'),(12955,'stenographer','','','','stenographers','n. 速记员',' She was elected a stenographer of that meeting.<br>     她被选为那次会议的速记员。<br>'),(12956,'stenography','','','','','n. 速记,速记法<br>\nv. 速记',''),(12957,'stentorian','','','','','a. 声音大的',''),(12958,'step','stepped','stepped','stepping','steps','n. 步骤,步,踏级<br>\nv. 踏,以步测量',' She stepped on a loose stone and twisted her ankle.<br>     她踩到一块松动的石头上，扭伤了脚踝。<br>\n We should take steps to prevent war.<br>     我们应当采取措施制止战争。<br>'),(12959,'step-','','','','','表示“后,继”之义',''),(12960,'stepchild','','','','stepchildren','n. 前夫所生子女',''),(12961,'stepfather','','','','stepfathers','n. 继父',''),(12962,'Stephen','','','','','n. 斯蒂芬（男子名）',' We\'ve developed the project from an original idea by Stephen.<br>     我们根据斯蒂芬的设想制定了这个计划.<br>\n Stephen acknowledged Henry as (ie recognized his claim to be) his heir.<br>     斯蒂芬接受亨利为他的继承人.<br>'),(12963,'stepladder','','','','','n. 四脚梯',''),(12964,'stepmother','','','','stepmothers','n. 继母,后母',' His stepmother is kind to her.<br>     他的继母对她很和善。<br>\n The judge said that nothing could mitigate the cruelty with which the stepmother had treated the girl.<br>     法官说没有任何理由可以把那个继母残忍虐待女孩的罪责减轻。<br>'),(12965,'stepparent','','','','stepparents','n. 继父(母)',''),(12966,'stepped-up','','','','','a. 加速的, 加强的',''),(12967,'stepsister','','','','stepsisters','n. 同父异母(或同母异父)的姐姐或妹妹',''),(12968,'step-up','','','','','a. 把电压升高的, 递升的',''),(12969,'stereo','','','','stereos','a. 立体声的<br>\nn. 立体声',' I have many stereo cassettes.<br>     我有很多立体声盒式磁带。<br>\n Where\'s your stereo?<br>     你的立体声音响在哪儿？<br>'),(12970,'stereophonic','','','','','立体声的',''),(12971,'stereotype','stereotyped','stereotyped','stereotyping','','n. 铅版,陈腔滥调,老套<br>\nv. 使用铅版,套用老套',' He doesn\'t conform to the usual stereotype of the city businessman with a dark suit and rolled umbrella.<br>     他不像典型的城市商人那样, 穿一身深色的套服、 带一把收好的雨伞.<br>'),(12972,'stereotyped','','','','','v. 定型(浇铅版,对...产生成见)<br>\na. 用铅版印的(老一套的)',' She has a stereotyped view of teachers, believing that they are all as bad as hers were.<br>     她对于教师有种一成不变的观念，认为他们都与她以前那些教师一样差。<br>'),(12973,'sterile','','','','','a. 不毛的,不孕的,无菌的',' Medical tests showed that he was sterile.<br>     医学检查表明他没有生育能力。<br>\n The high risk of infection put a premium on the use of sterile needle.<br>     由於受感染的风险很大，无菌注射针的使用受到了重视。<br>'),(12974,'sterilization','','','','','n. 消毒,灭菌',' A strong, pressurized, steam-heated vessel, as for laboratory experiments, sterilization, or cooking.<br>     高压灭菌器，高压锅一种用于实验室实验、灭菌或烧煮的高压加热蒸气作用的容器<br>'),(12975,'sterilize','sterilized','sterilized','sterilizing','','v. 使成不毛,断种,杀菌',' The doctor performs operations with sterilized surgical instruments.<br>     医生用消过毒的外科手术器械做手术。<br>\n After her fourth child she decided to have herself sterilized.<br>     她生了第四个孩子后决定做绝育手术。<br>'),(12976,'sterling','','','','','a. 英币的(纯粹的,货真价实的)<br>\nn. 英国货币(英镑)',' You can pay in sterling.<br>     你可以支付英镑。<br>\n They have some sterling silver cutlery.<br>     他们有一些标准纯银餐具。<br>'),(12977,'stern','','','','','n. 尾部,船尾<br>\na. 严厉的,坚决的,可怖的',' She seated herself in the stern.<br>     她坐进了船尾。<br>\n Stern as he is, he is full of sympathy.<br>     虽然他严格，却富有同情心。<br>'),(12978,'sternly','','','','','ad. 严格地,严肃地,严厉地',' He has very sternly admonished student.<br>     他十分严厉地训诫了学生。<br>'),(12979,'steroid','','','','','n. 类固醇,拟脂醇',' He\'s being treated with steroids for leukaemia.<br>     他因患白血病正在接受类固醇治疗.<br>'),(12980,'stertorous','','','','','a. 打鼾的',''),(12981,'stethoscope','','','','','n. 听诊器',' I take it you know what a stethoscope is.<br>     我想你知道听诊器是个什么东西。<br>\n The stethoscope is a medical instrument.<br>     听诊器是一种医疗器械。<br>'),(12982,'Steve','','','','','史蒂夫(男名)',' Steve got off with Tracey/Steve and Tracey got off (together) at Denise\'s party.<br>     史蒂夫和特蕾西在丹尼斯的聚会中搞上了.<br>\n Steve and Jack gave a talk about their trek across the Polar ice cap. It was very interesting but it made my hair stand on end just to hear about the dangers they faced.<br>     史蒂夫和杰克讲述了他们在极地冰盖的一段艰苦跋涉，故事津津有味，只是听到他们遇到种种险情时，我吓得很。<br>'),(12983,'stevedore','stevedored','stevedored','stevedoring','','n. 装卸工人,码头工人,脚夫<br>\nv. 装载货物',' Shipment cannot execute within period owing stevedore shortage<br>     因装卸工人不足，故无法在限定期间内完成装船。<br>'),(12984,'stew','','','','','n. 炖汤,焖,烦恼<br>\nv. 炖汤,焖,忧虑',' There is no need to get into a stew; everything will be all right.<br>     没有必要烦恼，一切都会好起来的。<br>\n Do you like stewed beef?<br>     你喜欢吃炖牛肉吗？<br>'),(12985,'steward','stewarded','stewarded','stewarding','stewards','n. 乘务员',' His neighbor is a chief steward.<br>     他的邻居是一个乘务员领班。<br>\n The stewards will inspect the course to see if racing is possible.<br>     那些干事将检视赛马场看是否适宜比赛。<br>'),(12986,'stewardess','','','','','n. 空中小姐,女管理人,女管家',' An air stewardess came and asked him if he would like some drink.<br>     一位空中小姐走过来，问他是否想要些饮料。<br>\n The stewardess will get you some water from the galley.<br>     空中小姐会从厨房给你拿些水来。<br>'),(12987,'stick','stuck','stuck','sticking','','n. 枝,杆,手杖<br>\nv. 插于,刺入,竖起<br>\nv. 钉住,粘贴,坚持',' The old man could not walk without a stick.<br>     这老人没有手杖就走不了路。<br>\n Someone has sticked a label on the crate.<br>     有人在板条箱上贴了标签。<br>'),(12988,'sticker','','','','','n. 尖刀(粘着剂,背面有粘胶的标签,张贴物,滞销物,难题)',' A paper sticker.<br>     纸制粘贴物<br>\n A decorative sticker.<br>     贴花纸一种装饰用的胶粘物<br>'),(12989,'sticking','','','','','a. 粘的<br>\nn. 粘,贴,粘胶',' Before sorting stamps, any paper sticking to the backs must be removed.<br>     在把邮票分类之前，任何粘在后面的别的纸都得去掉。<br>\n Sticking to but not fused with a part or an organ of the same kind.<br>     附着的与同类的部分或组织粘着但不融合的<br>'),(12990,'stick-in-the-mud','','','','','n. 守旧者；顽固者',''),(12991,'stickler','','','','','n. 坚持细节之人',' She\'s a stickler for the truth.<br>     她是个坚持实事求是的人。<br>\n My teacher is a stickler for the truth.<br>     我们的老师是一个坚持真理的人。<br>'),(12992,'stickpin','','','','','n. 领带夹',''),(12993,'sticky','','','','','a. 粘的,粘性的',' There\'s some sort of sticky fluid on the kitchen floor.<br>     厨房的地上有一种发黏的液体.<br>\n I am uncomfortable because my body is sticky.<br>     我身上粘粘的，很不舒服。<br>'),(12994,'stiff','','','','stiffs','a. 坚硬的,严厉的,呆板的<br>\nad. 僵硬地,彻底地',' Shoes are often stiff when they are new.<br>     新鞋刚穿起来常常都是硬邦邦的。<br>\n That was a shock I need a stiff drink!<br>     这可真吓人－－我得喝点烈酒了。<br>'),(12995,'stiffen','stiffened','stiffened','stiffening','','v. 使...坚硬,变为浓粘,变为猛烈',' He stiffened at the insult.<br>     他听到这些侮辱的话，态度强硬起来。<br>\n The promise of a reward might stiffen their resolve.<br>     答应给他们奖励可以坚定他们的决心。<br>'),(12996,'stiffly','','','','','ad. 顽固地,硬',' \"Please call me Virginia.\" Virginia said for the tenth time. Mrs. Allen bowed stiffly and continued to call her Miss Martin.<br>     \"请叫我弗吉尼亚。\"弗吉尼亚已经说过10遍了。可是艾伦太太很不自然地点点头，仍然称她马丁小姐。<br>'),(12997,'stiffness','','','','','n. 僵硬',' As I got about, the stiffness in my left leg gradually worked off.<br>     我走动走动，左腿渐渐地不再僵直了。<br>'),(12998,'stifle','','','','','v. 使不能呼吸,窒息,抑制',' Our ideas were stifled.<br>     我们的意见被压了下来。<br>\n The gas stifled them.<br>     他们被煤气熏得透不过气来。<br>'),(12999,'stifling','','','','','a. 令人窒息的',' We were stifling in that hot room with all the windows closed.<br>     我们在那间关著窗户的热屋子里, 简直透不过气来.<br>\n The atmosphere in the crowded hall became so stifling that two of the women passed out.<br>     拥挤不堪的大厅里闷得令人窒息，两个妇女晕了过去。<br>'),(13000,'stigma','','','','stigmata','n. 耻辱,污名<br>\nn. 柱头',' There is less stigma attached to illegitimacy now than there used to be.<br>     私生子女已经不象过去那样见不得人了。<br>\n There should be no stigma attached to being poor.<br>     贫穷不应该与耻辱扯上任何关系。<br>'),(13001,'stigmatize','stigmatized','stigmatized','stigmatizing','','v. 非难,使蒙上污名',''),(13002,'stile','','','','','n. 横蹬,横路栅栏',' I think they should make some stiles for people to cross the wall.<br>     我认为他们应该建些梯磴好让人们跨过墙去。<br>\n A poor man came to the door and asked for money for a cup of tea yesterday. My mother, always happy to help a lame dog over a stile, invited him in for a meal.<br>     昨天，有位穷人来到我家门口想讨点钱去喝杯茶，我母亲总是乐于助人于危难之中，请他进屋吃了一顿饭。<br>'),(13003,'stiletto','','','','stilettoes','n. 小剑,匕首,高跟鞋',''),(13004,'still','','','','','a. 静止的,不动的,静寂的<br>\nad. 仍然,更,静止地<br>\nconj. 然而,但是',' The food stilled the baby\'s cries.<br>     食物使婴儿停止了哭泣。<br>\n The room was still at the end of the speech.<br>     演讲结束的时候，房间里寂静无声。<br>'),(13005,'still life','','','','','n. 静物',' I prefer landscape to still life.<br>     我喜欢风景画，不喜欢静物画。<br>\n Drew a map of the area; drawing landscapes and still lifes.<br>     绘制该地区的地图；描绘风景与静物<br>'),(13006,'Still waters run deep','','','','','静水流深',''),(13007,'stillness','','','','','n. 静止,沉静',' The stillness was rent by thunderous applause.<br>     雷鸣般的掌声打破了寂静。<br>'),(13008,'stilt','','','','stilts','n. 高跷,支柱,脚柱',' He walked along on stilts.<br>     他踩着高跷走过去。<br>\n They built a house on stilts.<br>     他们建了一栋用桩子支撑的房子。<br>'),(13009,'stilted','','','','','a. 踩高跷的, 虚饰的',' He walked along on stilts.<br>     他踩着高跷走过去。<br>\n They built a house on stilts.<br>     他们建了一栋用桩子支撑的房子。<br>'),(13010,'stimulant','','','','stimulants','a. 兴奋性的,激励的,鼓舞的<br>\nn. 兴奋剂,酒精性饮料',' It is hoped that the tax cuts will act as a stimulant to further economic growth.<br>     希望降低税率这一措施能刺激经济进一步增长。<br>\n Coffee and tea are mild stimulants.<br>     咖啡和茶都是温和的兴奋剂。<br>'),(13011,'stimulate','stimulated','stimulated','stimulating','','vt. 刺激,激励,鼓舞',' I hoped my warning would stimulate her to greater efforts.<br>     我希望我的告诫会促使她作出更大的努力。<br>\n Light stimulates plant growth.<br>     光会刺激植物生长。<br>'),(13012,'stimulated','','','','','a. 刺激的',' The exhibition stimulated interest in the artist\'s work.<br>     这次展览引起人们对这位艺术家的作品的兴趣.<br>\n She was stimulated into new efforts.<br>     她受到鼓励，重新作出努力。<br>'),(13013,'stimulating','','','','','a. 刺激的,有刺激性的',' He looks sharp. Working with him shall be stimulating.<br>     他看起来精明。和他一起工作应该够刺激的。<br>\n They use television advertising as a device for stimulating demand.<br>     他们利用电视广告作为刺激需求的方法。<br>'),(13014,'stimulation','','','','','n. 刺激,激励,鼓舞',' Stimulation of the mind or emotions to a high level of feeling or activity.<br>     鼓舞使人的心灵或情感受到刺激而达到更高层次情感和行动的东西<br>\n The joy and moral stimulation of work no longer must be forgotten in the mad chase of evanescent profits.<br>     务必不能再忘记劳动带来的喜悦和激励，而去疯狂地追逐那转瞬即逝的利润。<br>'),(13015,'stimuli','','','','','n. 刺激(刺激物,刺激源,激励,激源,促进因素,色质)',' The capacity to respond to stimuli.<br>     反应力对刺激的反应能力<br>\n Less than the normal ability to respond to stimuli.<br>     敏感减轻对刺激反应能力低于正常水平<br>'),(13016,'stimulus','','','','stimuli','n. 刺激,激励,刺激品',' The nutrient in the soil acts as a stimulus to growth.<br>     土壤中的养分能促进植物生长。<br>\n Her words of praise were a stimulus for people to work harder.<br>     她赞扬的话鼓舞人们工作更努力。<br>'),(13017,'sting','stung','stung','stinging','stings','n. 刺,讽刺<br>\nv. 刺,长著刺,使苦恼',' His flattery carries a sting.<br>     他的奉承话中带刺。<br>\n Her ingratitude stung him.<br>     她的忘恩负义使他痛心。<br>'),(13018,'stinging cell','','','','','带刺的细胞',''),(13019,'stingy','','','','','a. 吝啬的,小气的',' The quality or state of being selfish or stingy.<br>     自私，吝啬自私或吝啬的品质或状况<br>\n A stingy person; a miser.<br>     吝啬吝啬小气的人；守财奴<br>'),(13020,'stink','stank','stunk','stinking','stinks','n. 臭味,臭气<br>\nv. 发臭味,使...发臭<br>\n坏透,招人讨厌',' There is a stink of cats in the room.<br>     屋子里有猫的臭味。<br>\n This whole affair really stinks.<br>     整件事情都让人讨厌。<br>'),(13021,'stinky','','','','','a. 恶臭的',''),(13022,'stint','','','','','v. 节省,限制,停止<br>\nn. 舍不得化,节约,限制<br>\nn. 连续不断的一段时间从事某件事',' She stinted herself of food in order to let the children have enough.<br>     她自己省着吃，好让孩子们吃饱。<br>\n Don\'t stint on the cream!<br>     不要舍不得放奶油！<br>'),(13023,'stipend','','','','','n. 薪水(薪金,定期生活津贴)',' Hopes to be awarded a stipend for further research.<br>     希望能被给予进一步研究的费用。<br>'),(13024,'stipple','stippled','stippled','stippling','','v. 点画,点描',''),(13025,'stipulate','','','','','v. 规定,明定',' The company fails to pay on the date stipulate in the contract.<br>     该公司没有按合同中规定的日期付款。<br>\n The Constitution stipulate that women shall have equal rights with men in voting and being elected.<br>     宪法规定妇女和男子一样，有同等的选举权和被选举权。<br>'),(13026,'stipulation','','','','','n. 约束,约定,契约',' A stipulation or qualification, especially a clause in a document or an agreement.<br>     条款一种规定或条件，尤其是指一个文件或协议中的条文<br>\n May I refer you to the contract stipulation about packing(or shipping..)?<br>     请您看看合同中有关包装（装运）的规定。<br>'),(13027,'stir','','','','','n. 搅动,惹起<br>\nv. 激起,惹起,搅和',' The story stirred her sympathy.<br>     这故事激起了她的同情心。<br>\n She stirred the sugar into her coffee.<br>     她把糖搅和到咖啡里。<br>'),(13028,'stirring','','','','','a. 活泼的,活耀的,忙碌的',' Who\'s been stirring?<br>     是谁搬弄是非?<br>\n He needs stirring up.<br>     他需要鼓励.<br>'),(13029,'stirrup','','','','stirrups','n. [机]镫形具,马蹬',' She tried to put her foot into the stirrup.<br>     她试图把脚放进马镫里。<br>\n The stirrup leathers rubbed raw patches on his legs.<br>     马蹬皮带把他腿上的皮肤擦伤引起疼痛.<br>'),(13030,'stitch','stitched','stitched','stitching','stitches','n. 一针,疼痛,碎布条',' The doctor put three stitches in my head.<br>     医生在我头上缝了三针。<br>\n Will you stitch a button on this shirt?<br>     请你在这件衬衫上钉一颗钮扣好吗？<br>'),(13031,'stock','stocked','stocked','stocking','stocks','n. 树干,血统,股份<br>\na. 存货的,平凡的,股票的<br>\nv. 进货,采购',' She is tired of her husband\'s stock jokes.<br>     她听厌了她丈夫那些陈腐的笑话。<br>\n That shop does not stock stationery.<br>     那家商店不卖文具。<br>'),(13032,'stock certificate','','','','','股票',''),(13033,'stock company','','','','','股份公司',''),(13034,'stock exchange','','','','','股票交易所',' The London Stock Exchange is in turmoil today.<br>     今天伦敦证券市场一片混乱。<br>\n The New York stock exchange crashed in1929.<br>     纽约股票交易所于一九二九年大崩溃。<br>'),(13035,'stock market','','','','','n. 股票市场',' She\'s made a killing on the stock market.<br>     她在股票市场上大发了一笔财.<br>\n Pani