 form of branching.<br>     一种或一组命令，根据前面的命令或者相关联命令的求值结果，有条件地执行。嵌套是分支的一种结构形式。<br>'),(13196,'struggle','struggled','struggled','struggling','struggles','n. 竞争,努力,奋斗<br>\r\nv. 努力,奋斗,挣扎',' He struggled with his assailants and eventually drove them off.<br>     他同攻击他的人进行搏斗，最后把他们赶走了。<br>\r\n Several people were hurt in the struggle.<br>     在打斗中，有几个人受伤。<br>'),(13197,'strum','strummed','strummed','strumming','','v. (漫不经心地)弹奏',' He sat there strumming a guitar.<br>     他坐在那儿漫不经心地弹吉他。<br>\r\n Mary can come home from any musical show and strum every tune on the piano.<br>     玛丽每听过一次音乐会，回到家里都能在钢琴上随意弹出其中的每一首曲子。<br>'),(13198,'strut','strutted','strutted','strutting','struts','n. 高视阔步,支柱,抗压材<br>\r\nv. 趾高气扬地走,用支柱支撑',' Beyond the river, supported on struts, rose the flat-topped house.<br>     河对岸那间平顶屋耸立在几根柱子上。<br>\r\n He strutted in front of me like a peacock.<br>     他像一只骄傲的孔雀一样在我前面趾高气扬地走着。<br>'),(13199,'strychnine','','','','','n. 马钱子碱',''),(13200,'stub','stubbed','stubbed','stubbing','stubs','n. 断株,烟蒂<br>\r\nv. 挖除断株,连根拔除',' The crayon had been worn down to a stub.<br>     这枝蜡笔用得只剩一小段了.<br>\r\n I\'ve stubbed my toe on a rock.<br>     我的脚趾碰到石头上了.<br>'),(13201,'stubble','','','','','n. 短须,麦茬',' Farmers often burn the stubble after they have cut the corn.<br>     农民们在收割完庄稼后常烧茬子。<br>\r\n The farmers are burning off the stubble from the fields.<br>     农民们正在把田里的庄稼残茬烧掉。<br>'),(13202,'stubborn','','','','','a. 顽固的,倔强的',' He is as stubborn as a mule.<br>     他非常固执。<br>\r\n You\'ll have to push hard; that door is a bit stubborn.<br>     你得使劲推，那扇门有点难开。<br>'),(13203,'stubbornly','','','','','ad. 顽固地,倔强地',' Stubbornly or perversely persistent.<br>     顽固的顽固地或刚愎地坚持的<br>\r\n Stubbornly resisting change or clinging to a seemingly hopeless or outdated cause.<br>     顽固地固执地坚持改变或抱定一看起来无希望或旧的理由<br>'),(13204,'stubbornness','','','','','n. 顽固(棘手)',''),(13205,'stucco','stuccoed','stuccoed','stuccoing','','n. 灰泥',' The house is red brick without a covering of stucco.<br>     那房子是红砖砌的，没有用灰泥粉刷。<br>'),(1