le; stylish.<br>     时髦的符合流行式样的；流行的<br>\r\n Being in or conforming to the prevailing or current fashion; stylish.<br>     流行的符合流行的或现时的式样的；时髦的<br>'),(13239,'stylist','','','','','n. 时装设计师',' The stylist did a real job on my hair.<br>     发型师把我的头发剪糟了<br>\r\n I am a stylist, and the most beautiful sentence I have ever heard is, \" Have one on the house.\"<br>     我是文体批评家，而迄今听过的最佳句子是：“请进一杯，免费的。”<br>'),(13240,'stylize','stylized','stylized','stylizing','','vt. 仿效...的风格(因袭)',''),(13241,'stylized','','','','','v. 仿效(因袭)<br>\r\na. 程式化的',' An ornamental device, as in stonework or weaving, consisting of stylized vine leaves and tendrils.<br>     螺层一种含有很风格化的藤叶和卷须的装饰结构，如石制品或纺织品上<br>\r\n A set of specified or traditional symbolic forms associated with the subject or theme of a stylized work of art.<br>     与某一风格固定的艺术作品的主题或描述对象相联系的特殊或传统的一系列象征形式<br>'),(13242,'stylus','','','','styli','n. 铁笔,尖笔,唱针',' A term sometimes applied to a stylus in a thermal matrix printer.<br>     有时用来指热敏点阵打印机的触针的一个术语。<br>\r\n An instrument for recording variations in pressure, as of the blood, or in tension, as of a muscle, by means of a pen or stylus that marks a rotating drum.<br>     压力记录器，记波器一种记录压力（如血压）或张力（如肌肉张力）变化的仪器，它通过一支笔或记录针的方式描出旋转的轨迹<br>'),(13243,'stymie','stymied','stymied','stymieing','stymies','n. 困难境地<br>\r\nvt 使...处于困难境地',' I was completely stymied by her refusal to help.<br>     由於她拒不相助, 我完全陷入了困境.<br>'),(13244,'styptic','','','','','a. 止血的<br>\r\nn. 止血剂',''),(13245,'suave','','','','','a. 柔和的,温和的,娴雅的',''),(13246,'suavity','','','','','n. 温和,殷勤',''),(13247,'sub','subbed','subbed','subbing','subs','n. 地铁,潜艇,替补队员<br>\r\nvi. (for)替代',' I had to sub for the referee, who was sick.<br>     裁判病了, 我得代为裁判.<br>'),(13248,'sub rosa','','','','','ad. 秘密地',''),(13249,'subaltern','','','','','n. 副官,僚属',' He found in India that subalterns were two a penny and invited nowhere.<br>     在印度，中尉和少尉军官多得不值钱，在哪儿也不会成为座上客。<br>'),(13250,'subarctic','','','','','a. 靠近北极的,亚北极的',''),(13251,'subassembly','','','','','部件,组