r. Population, 28,284.<br>     奈尔斯美国伊利诺斯州东北部的一个村落，是芝加哥河沿岸芝加哥市的一个工业郊区。人口28，284<br>\r\n An unincorporated village of west-central Florida, a residential suburb of Tampa. Population, 57,985.<br>     布兰登美国佛罗里达州中西部一未合并村庄。是坦帕城的居住郊区。人口57，985<br>'),(13342,'suburban','','','','','a. 市郊的(城郊的)',' I like to breathe the fresh air in suburban places.<br>     我喜欢在郊外呼吸新鲜空气。<br>\r\n The curtain goes up on (ie is raised to show) a suburban living-room.<br>     幕布升起, 展现的是市郊住宅的起居室.<br>'),(13343,'suburbanization','','','','','市郊化',''),(13344,'subvention','','','','','n. 补助金,津贴',''),(13345,'subversion','','','','','n. 颠覆,破坏',' The branch of an intelligence service charged with keeping sensitive information from an enemy, deceiving that enemy, preventing subversion and sabotage, and collecting political and military information.<br>     反情报组织情报组织的一个分支，任务是使敌人得不到高级机密，欺骗敌人，避免颠覆和阴谋破坏并收集政治和军事情况<br>\r\n Let al our neighbors know that we shall join with them to oppose aggression or subversion anywhere ill the Americas.<br>     我们要让所有邻国都知道，我们将和他们在一起，反对在美洲任何地区进行侵略和颠覆活动。<br>'),(13346,'subversive','','','','','a. 从事颠覆的,破坏性的<br>\r\nn. 破坏份子,危险份子',' They are contaminating the minds of our young people with these subversive ideas.<br>     他们这些颠覆性的思想是对我们年轻人的精神污染。<br>\r\n The new party has subversive ideas.<br>     新政党有颠覆的意图。<br>'),(13347,'subvert','subverted','subverted','subverting','','v. 推翻,颠覆,毁减',' A plot or scheme intended to subvert another plot.<br>     反计策意在破坏另一计谋的计策或计划<br>'),(13348,'subvocalize','','','','','v. 默读',''),(13349,'subway','subwayed','subwayed','subwaying','subways','n. 地铁',' I want to get there by subway.<br>     我想乘地铁去那儿。<br>\r\n Use the subway to cross the road.<br>     请走地下通道穿越马路。<br>'),(13350,'succeed','succeeded','succeeded','succeeding','','v. 成功,继承,继续',' If you work hard you will succeed.<br>     如果你努力工作，你就会成功。<br>\r\n When the duke dies, his eldest son will succeed to the title.<br>     公爵去世之后，他的长子将继承他的爵位。<br>'),(13351,'success','','','','successes','n. 成功',' She\'s just started up a new company; I hope she makes a success of it.<br>     她新开办了一家公司，我希望她取得成功。<br>\r\n Success lies not so much as in luck as in hard work.<br>     与其说成功在于运气不如说是辛勤努力。<br>'),(13352,'successful','','','','','a. 成功的',' They are highly successful in business.<br>     他们经商非常成功。<br>\r\n There is no doubt that we will be successful.<br>     毫无疑问我们会成功的。<br>'),(13353,'successfully','','','','','ad. 成功地',' At last he successfully solved the problem.<br>     最后他终于成功地解决了这个问题。<br>\r\n They have launched a man-made satellite successfully.<br>     他们成功地发射了一颗人造卫星。<br>'),(13354,'succession','','','','successions','n. 连续,继承权,继位',' There are a succession of rainy days here.<br>     这里一连好几天都是雨天。<br>\r\n He retrieved his losses by betting on a succession of winners.<br>     他下的赌注连续获胜才挽回了损失.<br>'),(13355,'successive','','','','','a. 接连的,连续的,接二连三的',' Continuity is ensured by using the same props in successive scenes.<br>     在连续的场景中使用同样的道具以确保前後衔接.<br>\r\n A distance estimated in fathoms between successive marks on a sounding line.<br>     水砣绳间距标示通过测深锤上连续的标记估计出来的以英寸计量的距离<br>'),(13356,'successively','','','','','ad. 一个接一个地',' Diana won five championships in women\'s high jump successively in the five years.<br>     戴安娜在五年内连续获得五次女子跳高冠军称号。<br>\r\n A shot in billiards in which the cue ball successively strikes two other balls.<br>     连着双球的一击打台球时的一击，主球接连撞击两球<br>'),(13357,'successor','','','','successors','n. 继承人',' His successor as the chairman will be at the conference.<br>     接替他担任主席的人将参加本次会议。<br>\r\n The chairman has designated that boy as his successor.<br>     主席已经指定那个男孩作他的继承人。<br>'),(13358,'succinct','','','','','a. 简洁的',' A short, succinct statement.<br>     简短，扼要的陈述<br>'),(13359,'succor','succored','succored','succoring','succors','n. 救援,援助者',' These refugees are very grateful to the government\'s succor.<br>     这些难民非常感激政府的救援。<br>\r\n The government has worked out a plan of succoring the needy.<br>     政府已经制定出了救济贫民的计划。<br>'),(13360,'succubus','','','','succubi','n. 女妖',''),(13361,'succulent','','','','','a. 多汁的,多水份的,多汁性的',''),(13362,'succumb','succumbed','succumbed','succumbing','','v. 屈从,死',' Several children have measles, and the others are bound to succumb (to it).<br>     有几个孩子患了麻疹, 其他孩子也必然传染上.<br>\r\n The driver has succumbed to (ie died of) his injuries.<br>     司机已受伤不治.<br>'),(13363,'such','','','','','a. 如此的,这样的',' Such people can help you a lot.<br>     这样的人对你大有帮助。<br>\r\n Such poets as Keats and Shelley wrote Romantic poetry.<br>     有些诗人，如济慈和雪莱，写的是浪漫主义的诗歌。<br>'),(13364,'suck','sucked','sucked','sucking','sucks','v. 啜,吸,吸入,吮吸<br>\r\n<俚>糟糕, 太烂了',' Don\'t suck your thumb; it\'s so dirty.<br>     别舔手指头，太脏了。<br>\r\n I don\'t want to get sucked into the row about school reform.<br>     我不愿意牵扯到这场学制改革的争论之中。<br>'),(13365,'sucker','suckered','suckered','suckering','','n. 乳儿,吸管',' I\'ve always been a sucker for romantic movies.<br>     我一向喜欢传奇性的影片。<br>\r\n You are a sucker to believe his stories.<br>     你居然相信他的说法，真是大傻瓜！<br>'),(13366,'suckle','suckled','suckled','suckling','','v. 哺乳',' She suckles her baby hardly.<br>     她艰难地哺育孩子。<br>'),(13367,'sucrose','','','','','n. 蔗糖',' A sucrose infusion.<br>     蔗糖输入液<br>'),(13368,'suction','','','','','n. 吸,吸入',' Some pumps and all vacuum cleaners work by suction.<br>     有些泵和所有真空吸尘器都是借吸力工作的。<br>\r\n Flies\' feet stick to surfaces by suction.<br>     苍蝇的脚借吸力可附着于物体表面上。<br>'),(13369,'Sudan','','','','','n. 苏丹',' A unit of currency in Egypt, Lebanon, Sudan, and Syria.<br>     皮阿斯特埃及、黎巴嫩、苏丹和叙利亚的一种货币单位<br>'),(13370,'sudd','','','','','n. (白尼罗河上游的)大块漂浮植物',''),(13371,'sudden','','','','','n. 突然,忽然<br>\r\na. 突然的,快速的',' His sudden death upset everybody.<br>     他的突然去世使大家深感悲伤。<br>\r\n The boy began crying all of a sudden.<br>     那男孩忽然哭了起来。<br>'),(13372,'sudden death','','','','','突然故障',' His sudden death upset everybody.<br>     他的突然去世使大家深感悲伤。<br>\r\n His wife\'s sudden death upset the balance ofhis mind.<br>     他妻子突然去世, 他感到六神无主.<br>'),(13373,'suddenly','','','','','ad. 突然地',' We were talking on the phone when, suddenly, the line went dead.<br>     我们正通着电话，突然电话断了。<br>\r\n I suddenly remembered that I didn\'t bring my key.<br>     我突然想起我没有带钥匙。<br>'),(13374,'sudorific','','','','','a. 使发汗的,促使发汗的<br>\r\nn. 发汗药',''),(13375,'sue','','','','','VI 要求、请求；控告 VT控告、起诉',' Jill and Sue are at variance (with each other) over/about their lodger.<br>     吉尔和休在对待房客的问题上（彼此）意见不和.<br>\r\n We invited Bill, Tom and Sue -- the last being Bill\'s sister.<br>     我们请了比尔、 汤姆和休--最後提到的这位是比尔的妹妹.<br>'),(13376,'suede','','','','','n. 小山羊皮(软羔皮)',''),(13377,'Suez Canal','','','','','苏伊士运河',' The Suez Canal joins the Mediterranean and the Red Sea.<br>     苏伊士运河连接著地中海和红海.<br>\r\n In July,1956, Egypt had seized the Suez Canal.<br>     一九五六年七月，埃及占领了苏伊士运河。<br>'),(13378,'suffer','suffered','suffered','suffering','','v. 遭受,经验,忍受',' They suffered huge losses in the financial crisis.<br>     他们在经济危机时遭受了巨大的损失。<br>\r\n She couldn\'t suffer criticism.<br>     她受不了批评。<br>'),(13379,'sufferer','','','','sufferers','n. 受难者,被害者,患者',' Relief was quickly sent to the sufferers from the great fire.<br>     救济品很快被送到遭受火灾的灾民手中。<br>\r\n There are many malaria sufferers in hospital.<br>     医院里有很多疟疾病人。<br>'),(13380,'suffering','','','','sufferings','n. 苦楚,受难<br>\r\nvbl. 蒙受,受苦',' She bore her sufferings bravely.<br>     她勇敢地承受艰难困苦。<br>\r\n The suffering of innocent people caused by the war cannot be compensated for by money.<br>     战争给无辜的人民带来的痛苦不是金钱可以补偿的。<br>'),(13381,'suffice','sufficed','sufficed','sufficing','','v. 足够,使...满足,合格',' An hour should suffice for the journey.<br>     这点路程一小时足够了。<br>\r\n The rations will suffice until next week.<br>     这些口粮足够吃到下星期。<br>'),(13382,'sufficiency','','','','sufficiencies','n. 充裕,充足',''),(13383,'sufficient','','','','','a. 足够的,充分的',' There is sufficient food for everybody.<br>     有足够的饭菜供大家吃。<br>\r\n Given sufficient goodwill on both sides, there\'s no reason why this dispute shouldn\'t be resolved.<br>     只要双方都有充分的善意，这种纠纷是没有理由解决不了的。<br>'),(13384,'sufficiently','','','','','ad. 足够地',' I don\'t think he\'s sufficiently dedicated to stay the course.<br>     我认为他不够坚定，不会坚持到底的。<br>\r\n She has not been sufficiently stretched at school this term.<br>     她本学期功课不太紧张.<br>'),(13385,'suffix','suffixed','suffixed','suffixing','suffixes','n. 后缀',' A diminutive suffix, word, or name.<br>     微小表微小的后缀、单词或名称<br>\r\n A verbal suffix.<br>     用于构成动词的后缀<br>'),(13386,'suffocate','suffocated','suffocated','suffocating','','a. 使窒息而死<br>\r\nv. (使)窒息而死<br>\r\nvt. 使窒息',' I\'m suffocating in here; can\'t we open a few windows?<br>     我觉得这儿很憋气, 咱们开几扇窗户好吗?<br>\r\n The fireman was suffocated by the fumes.<br>     那个消防队员让浓烟憋死了.<br>'),(13387,'suffocating','','','','','a. 使人窒息的',' The heat was tolerable at night but suffocating during the day.<br>     这种炎热的天气在夜晚尚能忍受，但白天就令人感到呼吸困难。<br>\r\n I\'m suffocating in here; can\'t we open a few windows?<br>     我觉得这儿很憋气, 咱们开几扇窗户好吗?<br>'),(13388,'suffrage','','','','suffrages','n. 投票,选举权,参政权',' When was universal suffrage introduced in your country?<br>     贵国是什么时候实行普选权的？<br>\r\n The question of woman suffrage sets them at variance.<br>     妇女参政的问题使他们发生争执。<br>'),(13389,'suffuse','suffused','suffused','suffusing','','v. 遍布...,弥漫,充满',' A blush suffused his cheeks.<br>     他瞬间满脸通红.<br>\r\n The evening sky was suffused with crimson.<br>     黄昏时分天空红霞灿灿.<br>'),(13390,'sugar','sugared','sugared','sugaring','sugars','n. 糖<br>\r\nv. 加糖于',' He put some sugar into his coffee.<br>     他往咖啡里加了些糖。<br>\r\n The pill is sugared.<br>     这药丸加上了糖衣。<br>'),(13391,'sugary','','','','','a. 含糖的,甜的',''),(13392,'suggest','suggested','suggested','suggesting','','v. 建议,提出',' His pale face suggests bad health.<br>     他面色苍白，说明他身体不好。<br>\r\n I suggested going for a walk.<br>     我建议去散步。<br>'),(13393,'suggested','','','','','暗示的',' I suggested putting the matter to a vote, but the chairman demurred to it.<br>     我建议对此事投票表决，但主席表示反对。<br>\r\n The article struck a pessimistic note; it suggested there would be no improvement.<br>     那篇文章不甚乐观, 暗示将无改进.<br>'),(13394,'suggestible','','','','','a. 易受影响的',' I did many stupid things when I was young and suggestible.<br>     我年轻时受外界的影响做过不少傻事。<br>\r\n She\'s at a suggestible age.<br>     她处于易受影响的年龄。<br>'),(13395,'suggestion','','','','suggestions','n. 建议',' Can you give me any suggestion on this matter?<br>     关于这件事，你能给我一些建议吗？<br>\r\n What a ridiculous suggestion!<br>     多么荒唐的建议！<br>'),(13396,'suggestive','','','','','a. 提示性的,影射的,暗示的',' There is an aroma suggestive of spring flowers in the room.<br>     这房间里有一种香气，使人想起春天的花朵。<br>\r\n He gave her a suggestive glance.<br>     他用挑逗的目光看了她一眼。<br>'),(13397,'suicidal','','','','','a. 自杀的,自杀性的,自我毁减的',' She\'s feeling suicidal today.<br>     她今天想自杀.<br>\r\n He was depressed, even suicidal. Even a child knows better.<br>     他很沮丧，甚至想去自杀。这甚至连孩子都知道得更清楚<br>'),(13398,'suicide','suicided','suicided','suiciding','suicides','a. 自杀(者)(的)<br>\r\nv.&n. 自杀',' She tried to commit suicide, but we saved her life by chance.<br>     她试图自杀，但我们碰巧救了她。<br>\r\n This article discussed the events that led to her suicide.<br>     这篇文章讨论了导致她自杀的一系列事件。<br>'),(13399,'suit','suited','suited','suiting','suits','n. 套装,诉讼,请求<br>\r\nv. 适合,取悦,满足',' He is wearing a black suit.<br>     他穿着一套黑西装。<br>\r\n I\'ve found a job that suits me down to the ground.<br>     我找到了一份工作，对我再合适不过了。<br>'),(13400,'suitable','','','','','a. 合适的,适宜的',' What time is suitable for us to meet?<br>     我们什么时候会面合适？<br>\r\n She is suitable for the job.<br>     她适合做这项工作。<br>'),(13401,'suitably','','','','','ad. 适当地,相称地',' Components must suitably packed for delivery to site.<br>     部件必须适应包装以便运送到目的地。<br>'),(13402,'suitcase','','','','suitcases','n. 手提箱',' Travelling is difficult when you\'re encumbered with two small children and a heavy suitcase.<br>     旅行时带着两个孩子和一个沉重的手提箱，真是寸步难行。<br>\r\n The suitcase burst open and its contents rained on the floor.<br>     手提箱裂开了，里面的东西纷纷落在地板上。<br>'),(13403,'suite','','','','suites','n. 随员,套房,一组',' He brought a three-piece suite.<br>     他买了三件一套的家具。<br>\r\n The suite is for the honeymoon couple.<br>     这套房是为新婚夫妇设的。<br>'),(13404,'suited','','','','','适合的',' He is better suited to a job with older pupils.<br>     他较适合教小学高年级学生。<br>\r\n The girl is quite suited for the position [work].<br>     这姑娘很适合担任这个职务[这个工作]。<br>'),(13405,'suitor','','','','suitors','n. 起诉者,请愿者,求婚者',' She refused her suitor.<br>     她拒绝了求婚者。<br>\r\n A Victorian suitor would be expected to satisfy a girl\'s father that he could support her in the manner to which she was accustomed.<br>     维多利亚时期总是希望求婚者向女方的父亲保证他能供养其女，让她过上和她以往一样的舒适讲究的生活。<br>'),(13406,'sulfa','','','','sulfas','a. 磺胺的<br>\r\nn. 磺胺类药物',''),(13407,'sulfa drug','','','','','磺胺类药',''),(13408,'sulfate','sulfated','sulfated','sulfating','sulfates','n. 硫酸盐',' What color is copper sulfate solution?<br>     硫酸铜溶液是什么颜色？<br>\r\n Barium sulfate is a radiopaque substance.<br>     钡硫酸盐是一种辐射光不能穿透的状之。<br>'),(13409,'sulfur','sulfured','sulfured','sulfuring','','n. 硫',' Sulfur can be used to make gunpowder.<br>     硫磺可以用来制造火药。<br>\r\n A sulfide compound containing at least two sulfur atoms per molecule.<br>     多硫化物每个分子中至少含有两个硫原子的一种硫化物<br>'),(13410,'sulk','sulked','sulked','sulking','sulks','a. 生气的<br>\r\nv. 不高兴,闷闷不乐,愠怒,生气',' He\'s been sulking for days about being left out of the team.<br>     他嗔怪队里没要他, 连日生著闷气.<br>\r\n She is in the sulks.<br>     她在发脾气；她在生气。<br>'),(13411,'sulky','','','','sulkies','a. 生气的(阴沉的)',''),(13412,'sullen','','','','','a. 愠怒的,沉沉不乐的,阴沉的',' She never laughed and became very sullen.<br>     她再也没有笑过，变得郁郁寡欢。<br>\r\n Susan is sullen in the morning because she had not sleep well.<br>     苏珊今天早上郁闷不乐，因为昨晚没睡好。<br>'),(13413,'sullenly','','','','','ad. 不高兴地',''),(13414,'sullenness','','','','','n. 赌气,情绪消沉',''),(13415,'Sullivan','','','','','萨莉文(人名)',' Before Anne Sullivan came to our house, one or two people had told my mother that I was an idiot.<br>     在安妮·莎莉文来到我们家之前，有些人曾对我母亲说过我是个白痴。<br>'),(13416,'sully','sullied','sullied','sullying','sullies','v. 沾污,弄脏,弄成无用<br>\r\nn. 污点,脏污',' I wouldn\'t sully my hands by acceptinga bribe.<br>     我决不接受贿赂, 一尘不染.<br>'),(13417,'sulphur','','','','','n. 硫',' Sulphur can be used to make gunpowder.<br>     硫磺可以用来制造火药。<br>\r\n Sulphur was not identified as an element until1810.<br>     1810年以前还没有认出硫是一种元素。<br>'),(13418,'sulphuric','','','','','a. [化](含)硫磺的',''),(13419,'sultan','','','','sultans','n. 回教君主,土耳其皇帝,鸡',' Sultan is sovereign ruler of certain Muslim countries.<br>     苏丹是某些穆斯林国家的最高统治者。<br>'),(13420,'sultry','','','','','a. 闷热的',' She is a sultry western beauty.<br>     她是位性感的西方美人。<br>\r\n I met her in a sultry summer afternoon.<br>     我在夏天一个闷热的下午遇见了她。<br>'),(13421,'sum','summed','summed','summing','sums','n. 总数,全部,概略<br>\r\nv. 总计,概括,合计',' I had to spend a large sum of money to get it back.<br>     我得花一大笔钱才把它弄回来。<br>\r\n The sum of 5 and 3 is 8.<br>     五加三的总和是八。<br>'),(13422,'summarily','','','','','ad. 概括地,仓促地',''),(13423,'summarization','','','','','n. 摘要,概要',''),(13424,'summarize','summarized','summarized','summarizing','','v. 概述,摘要而言',''),(13425,'summary','','','','summaries','n. 摘要,概要<br>\r\na. 摘要的,简略的',' Such an offence will lead to a summary fine.<br>     这类过错要当场予以罚款。<br>\r\n Your summary will need fleshing out before you present it.<br>     你的总结需要增加一些具体材料再交出.<br>'),(13426,'summation','','','','','n. 总和,和,合计',' The exhibition was a summation of his life\'s work.<br>     这次展览汇集了他一生中典型的作品.<br>\r\n After a dramatic pause, the lawyer finished her summation.<br>     在戏剧性的沉默之后，这位律师作完了她的总述<br>'),(13427,'summer','','','','','a. 夏季(的)<br>\r\nn. 夏季,夏天',' That was the high summer of English literature.<br>     当时是英国文学的全盛时期。<br>\r\n This city has a music festival every summer.<br>     本市每年举行一次夏季音乐节。<br>'),(13428,'summertime','','','','','n. 夏,夏季',''),(13429,'summit','','','','summits','n. 顶点<br>\r\nn.最高官阶;最高级会议',' The Hungarian view is magnificent from the summit of the mountains.<br>     从群山之颠看到的匈牙利景色非常壮丽。<br>\r\n It was a warm climb to the summit.<br>     向顶峰攀登时身上都热起来了。<br>'),(13430,'summon','summoned','summoned','summoning','','v. 召唤,召集,振奋',' He summoned his soldiers to fight.<br>     他号召部下战斗。<br>\r\n The shareholders were summoned to a general meeting.<br>     那些股东被召集去叁加股东大会。<br>'),(13431,'summons','summonsed','summonsed','summonsing','summonses','n. 召唤,传唤,召集<br>\r\nv. 传唤到法院,唤出,传到',' The shareholders were summoned to a general meeting.<br>     那些股东被召集去叁加股东大会。<br>\r\n The debtor was summoned (to appear before the magistrates).<br>     （地方法官）已传唤债务人出庭.<br>'),(13432,'sumptuary','','','','','a. 节省费用的',''),(13433,'sumptuous','','','','','a. 华丽的,奢侈的',' The poor girl was astonished by the sumptuous furnishings of the mansion.<br>     这个贫穷的女孩被大厦里的豪华的陈设惊呆了。<br>\r\n Of a sumptuous, costly, or rich variety.<br>     特等的豪华的、昂贵的或多种多样的<br>'),(13434,'sun','sunned','sunned','sunning','suns','n. 太阳<br>\r\nvt. 晒太阳',' The sun shines brightly.<br>     阳光灿烂。<br>\r\n He sat in a deck-chair sunning himself.<br>     他坐在帆布躺椅上晒太阳.<br>'),(13435,'sunbathe','sunbathed','sunbathed','sunbathing','','n. 日光浴',' He have a habit of sunbathe for two hours a day.<br>     他习惯每天做两小时日光浴。<br>\r\n The pool is surrounded by sunbathe.<br>     水池四周都是进行日光浴的人。<br>'),(13436,'sunbeam','','','','sunbeams','n. 日光',' My son is really a sunbeam.<br>     我儿子真是一个快乐的人。<br>\r\n We can see many molecules flying in the air when a sunbeam penetrated the dark room.<br>     当一束光线穿进暗淡的房间时，我们可以看到空气中有许多小颗粒在飞舞。<br>'),(13437,'sunburn','sunburned','sunburned','sunburning','sunburns','n. 日灼,晒伤<br>\r\nv. 晒黑',' Browned by the sun; sunburned.<br>     晒黑的被太阳晒成棕色的；晒黑的<br>\r\n Can you give me something for sunburn?<br>     能否给我治太阳炙伤的药？<br>'),(13438,'sunburnt','','','','','a. 晒黑的',' His hard hands and sinewy sunburnt limbs told of labor and endurance.<br>     他粗糙的双手，被太阳哂得发黑的健壮四肢，均表明他十分辛勤，非常耐劳。<br>'),(13439,'sundae','','','','','n. 圣代冰淇淋',''),(13440,'Sunday','','','','','n. 星期日',' Christians go to church on Sundays.<br>     基督教徒每个星期日到教堂去做礼拜。<br>\r\n Sunday is my rest day.<br>     星期日是我休息的日子。<br>'),(13441,'sunder','sundered','sundered','sundering','','v. 切开,分离',' The boat was sundered by the rock.<br>     船被岩石撞碎了。<br>'),(13442,'sundew','','','','','n. 毛毯苔',''),(13443,'sundial','','','','','n. 日规,日昝仪',''),(13444,'sundown','','','','','n. 日落',' It is getting along toward sundown.<br>     快到日落的时候了。<br>'),(13445,'sundries','','','','','杂货,杂物,杂项',' My expenses claim includes 15 for sundries.<br>     我的报销申请中包括 15 英镑杂项支出.<br>\r\n She invited all and sundry to her party.<br>     她邀请所有的人都来参加聚会.<br>'),(13446,'sundry','','','','sundries','n. 杂物,杂事',' They prepared rice, flour and sundry other items of food for the poor.<br>     他们为穷人准备了米，面及其它各种食物。<br>\r\n We can see the rich man on sundry occasions.<br>     我们能在各种场合见到那个富豪。<br>'),(13447,'sunflower','','','','sunflowers','n. 向日葵',' Sunflowers are large flowers with yellow petals.<br>     向日葵是长着黄色花瓣的大花。<br>\r\n The bird pecked seeds out of the sunflower.<br>     那只鸟用喙从向日葵中啄出种的。<br>'),(13448,'sung','','','','','sing的过去分词',' The last verse will be sung in unison.<br>     歌词的最后部分要齐唱。<br>\r\n Have you heard the opera sung in French?<br>     你听过用法语唱的这场歌剧吗？<br>'),(13449,'sunglasses','','','','','n. 墨镜(太阳镜)',''),(13450,'sunken','','','','','v. 使...下沉(降,挖,打进,丧失,不重视)',' Valuable raw materials were salvaged (from the sunken freighter).<br>     （从沉船中）打捞起许多贵重的原料.<br>\r\n Either of two usually sunken shelters at the side of a field where the players stay while not on the field.<br>     球员休息处运动场边稍低于地面的两个掩体之一，球员不上场时在此处休息<br>'),(13451,'sunlight','','','','','n. 日光,阳光',' Don\'t read in the sunlight.<br>     别在阳光下看书。<br>\r\n The sunlight was reflected in the water.<br>     日光由水面反射出来。<br>'),(13452,'sunlit','','','','','a. 被日光照射了的,阳光照射的',''),(13453,'sunny','','','','','a. 阳光充足的,睛朗的,明媚的',' It is sunny today.<br>     今天天气晴朗。<br>\r\n Sunny weather alternated with rain.<br>     天气晴雨相间。<br>'),(13454,'sunrise','','','','sunrises','n. 日出',' The beauty of the sunrise is beyond description.<br>     日出的美景难以描述。<br>\r\n The town came to life after sunrise.<br>     日出之后，这个市镇变得充满生气。<br>'),(13455,'sunroof','','','','sunroofs','n. 汽车顶蓬上可开合以透空气与光的孔',''),(13456,'sunset','','','','sunsets','n. 日落',' The sunset is gorgeous.<br>     落日辉煌。<br>\r\n The wind was strong all day, but it moderated after sunset.<br>     风猛烈地刮了一整天后，日落后变小了。<br>'),(13457,'sunshine','','','','','n. 阳光',' I was sitting in the garden enjoying the sunshine.<br>     我坐在庭院里享受明媚的阳光。<br>\r\n The baby has brought some sunshine into their life.<br>     孩子给他们的生活带来了几分快乐。<br>'),(13458,'suntan','','','','','n. 晒黑,卡其色军服',''),(13459,'sunup','','','','','n. 日出',''),(13460,'sup','','','','','v. 啜,尝<br>\r\nvi. 供给晚饭',' They supped on bread and cheese.<br>     他们吃面包和奶酪当晚餐。<br>\r\n Come on, sup up your tea.<br>     来, 把茶喝了吧.<br>'),(13461,'super','','','','','a. 超级的,极好的',' I\'ll be a super secretary for you.<br>     我将成为你极好的秘书。<br>\r\n I bought some pomegranates in the super market.<br>     我在超市上买了一些石榴。<br>'),(13462,'superannuated','','','','','a. 老朽的,退休的',' Are you still riding that superannuated old bike?<br>     你还骑那辆老掉牙的自行车吗?<br>'),(13463,'superb','','','','','a. 极好的',' I like our country\'s superb view.<br>     我喜欢我们国家壮丽的景色。<br>\r\n The sports facilities are superb in this city.<br>     这个城市的运动设施是一流的。<br>'),(13464,'superbly','','','','','ad. 壮丽地(最上等地)',''),(13465,'supercilious','','','','','a. 目中无人的,高傲的',' Affecting an attitude of disdain or conceit; haughty and supercilious.<br>     傲慢的摆出轻蔑或自满的样子的；高傲且盛气凌人的<br>\r\n The shop assistant was very supercilious towards me when I asked for some help.<br>     我要买东西招呼售货员时，那个售货员对我不屑一顾。<br>'),(13466,'superclass','','','','','超类',''),(13467,'supercomputer','','','','','n. 巨型电子计算机',''),(13468,'superficial','','','','','a. 表面的,肤浅的',' He is too superficial to appreciate great literature like this.<br>     他太肤浅，无法欣赏这类文学巨著。<br>\r\n Superficial scratches can be easily removed.<br>     表面的划痕很容易擦掉。<br>'),(13469,'superficially','','','','','ad. 表面地(表面上)',''),(13470,'superfluity','','','','superfluities','n. 多余,过剩',' The teacher pruned the student\'s article of its superfluities.<br>     老师删去这个学生文章中的多余内容。<br>'),(13471,'superfluous','','','','','a. 多余的',' He has already been told, so our comments are superfluous.<br>     早就有人同他说过，所以我们的意见是多余的。<br>\r\n A superfluous word or phrase.<br>     冗词多余的词或短语<br>'),(13472,'superhigh frequency','','','','','超高频',''),(13473,'superhighway','','','','','n. 超级高速公路',' A superhighway will be constructed next year.<br>     明年将要修建一条超级高速公路。<br>\r\n Streams of cars were belting along the superhighway.<br>     川流不息的车辆在高速公路上飞驰。<br>'),(13474,'superimpose','superimposed','superimposed','superimposing','','vt. 重叠(安装,添加)',''),(13475,'superintend','superintended','superintended','superintending','','v. 指挥,管理,监督',' He was appointed to superintend the toy department.<br>     他获任玩具部的负责人。<br>\r\n The manager is superintending the staff\'s work.<br>     经理正在监督工人的工作。<br>'),(13476,'superintendent','','','','superintendents','n. 监督人,管理人,所长',' \"I hope he went fishing and comes back tomorrow, but I wouldn\'t bet my paycheck on it, \" said state police superintendent Clinton Pagano….<br>     州警察局长帕加诺说，\"我希望他钓鱼去了，明天就回来。但是我可不愿意拿我的薪水打赌（并无十分把握）。\"……<br>'),(13477,'superior','','','','superiors','n. 长者,高手<br>\r\na. 上好的,出众的,高傲的',' He smiled a superior smile as he drove past in his expensive new car.<br>     他开着那辆豪华的新车驶过时，傲慢的微微一笑。<br>\r\n He always does what his superiors tell him.<br>     他惟上级之命是从。<br>'),(13478,'superiority','','','','','n. 优越性,优势',' British-born American anthropologist whose books, such as The Natural Superiority of Women(1953), helped popularize anthropology.<br>     蒙塔古，阿什利生于1905英裔美国人类学家，其著作如女性的自然优越性（1953年），促进了人类学的普及<br>\r\n Superiority in weight, force, importance, or influence.<br>     优势重量、力量、重要性或影响力方面的优势<br>'),(13479,'superlative','','','','superlatives','a. 最上的,无比的,过度的<br>\r\nn. 最高级的言辞,极致,完璧',''),(13480,'superman','','','','supermen','n. 超人',' He\'s a kind of intellectual superman.<br>     他是智力超常的人.<br>'),(13481,'supermarket','','','','supermarkets','n. 超级市场',' The supermarket sells goods of all descriptions.<br>     超级市场销售各种货物。<br>\r\n The supermarket rejected all spotted apples.<br>     超级市场丢弃了所有的烂苹果。<br>'),(13482,'supernal','','','','','a. 天堂的,天上的',''),(13483,'supernatural','','','','','a. 超自然的,神奇的',' An image of a female supernatural being; an idol.<br>     女性偶象一超自然的女性偶象；偶象<br>\r\n The system of thought holding that all phenomena can be explained in terms of natural causes and laws without attributing moral, spiritual, or supernatural significance to them.<br>     自然主义伦理学的观点认为所有的现象都可以不用归于道理上的，精神上的及超自然的重要性而被解释为自然起因和法则<br>'),(13484,'supernova','','','','supernovas','n. ［天］超新星',''),(13485,'supernumerary','','','','supernumeraries','n. 多余的人或物,冗员',''),(13486,'superorganism','','','','','n. [生]超个体(指群居昆虫等的群体)',''),(13487,'superpower','','','','','n. 超级大国',' The superpowers are unlikely to disarm completely.<br>     超级大国不太可能彻底裁军.<br>\r\n The superpowers are putting the arms race into reverse.<br>     超级大国正在把军备竞赛转换成相继裁军。<br>'),(13488,'superscript','','','','','上标',' Different words with the same spelling are distinguished in this dictionary by superscript numbers.<br>     本词典在同形异义词的右上角标注数字以资区别.<br>\r\n A mark used as a superscript to indicate the first derivative of a variable.<br>     撇号置于右上角的符号，用以标明变量的第一个导数<br>'),(13489,'supersede','superseded','superseded','superseding','','v. 代替,取代',' Motorways have largely superseded ordinary roads for long-distance travel.<br>     高速公路多已取代了普通公路.<br>\r\n Will factory workers be entirely superseded by machines one day?<br>     工人将来能完全由机器取代吗?<br>'),(13490,'superset','','','','','超集,扩展集',''),(13491,'supersonic','','','','','a. 超音波的',' Have you taken supersonic aircraft?<br>     你坐过超音速飞机吗?<br>\r\n The physics of supersonic flight.<br>     超音速飞行的物理性质<br>'),(13492,'superstar','','','','','n. 超级明星',' The newspaper puff up that new athlete into a superstar<br>     报界把那个新运动员吹捧成为超级明星。<br>\r\n That superstar wrestling really turn me on.<br>     那种摔跤超级明星赛我的确很感兴趣。<br>'),(13493,'superstition','','','','superstitions','n. 迷信',' It\'s a common superstition that black cats are unlucky.<br>     认为黑猫不吉利，这是一种普遍的迷信思想。<br>\r\n Frightened or intimidated by superstition.<br>     （因迷信而）恐惧被迷信吓倒或胆怯的<br>'),(13494,'superstitious','','','','','a. 迷信的',' He has a superstitious thought that black cat are unlucky.<br>     他有一种迷信的想法认为黑猫不吉祥。<br>\r\n I always put my left shoe on first; I\'m superstitious (about it).<br>     我穿鞋总是先左後右, 我是很迷信（这件事）的.<br>'),(13495,'superstructure','','','','','n. 上部构造,建筑物,上层构造',' The frame or body of a ship, exclusive of masts, engines, or superstructure.<br>     船壳，船体船的框架或主体，不包括桅杆、发动机和上层建筑<br>\r\n A superstructure at the stern of a ship.<br>     船楼，艉位于船尾部的上层结构<br>'),(13496,'superuser','','','','','超级用户',''),(13497,'supervise','supervised','supervised','supervising','','v. 监督,管理,指导',' The chief clerk supervises the work of the department.<br>     文书组长负责监督该部门的工作.<br>\r\n I supervised the workers loading the lorry.<br>     我监督工人把货物装上卡车.<br>'),(13498,'supervision','','','','','n. 监督,管理',' Children should not be left to play without supervision.<br>     孩子玩的时候不能无人照看。<br>\r\n This drug should only be taken under the supervision of a doctor.<br>     此药须遵医嘱服用。<br>'),(13499,'supervisor','','','','supervisors','n. 监督人, 管理人, 检查员, 督学, 主管人,导师',' The university students handed in their essays to their supervisor.<br>     大学生们把文章交给导师审阅。<br>\r\n The supervisor always start his new employee on the lobster shift.<br>     领导总是让刚开始工作的新职员值夜班。<br>'),(13500,'supervisory','','','','','管理的,监控的',' In telephony, the use of tones to transmit supervisory, address and alerting signals over a circuit.<br>     在电话技术中，利用音调在电路中传送监控、地址和报警信号的做法。<br>'),(13501,'supine','','','','','a. 仰卧的(掌心向上的,因循的)',''),(13502,'supper','','','','suppers','n. 晚餐',' Have you had your supper?<br>     你吃过晚饭了吗？<br>\r\n We had a buffet supper last evening.<br>     昨天晚上，我们吃了一次自助晚餐。<br>'),(13503,'suppertime','','','','','n. 晚饭时间',''),(13504,'supplant','supplanted','supplanted','supplanting','','v. 排挤,取代<br>\r\nvt. (用策略等)替换',' She has been supplanted by another in his affections.<br>     他爱上了另一个人，不再爱她了。<br>\r\n The party leader has been supplanted by his rival.<br>     那位政党领导已被他的对手取而代之了。<br>'),(13505,'supple','suppled','suppled','suppling','','a. 柔软的,逢迎的,顺从的',' Exercise keeps you supple.<br>     经常锻炼可使身体灵活。<br>\r\n She has a supple mind.<br>     她头脑灵活。<br>'),(13506,'supplement','','','','','n. 补充物,增刊<br>\r\nv. 补充,增补',' I supplement my scholarship by working in the evening.<br>     我除了享受奖学金外还打夜工以增加收入。<br>\r\n The money I got was a useful supplement to my ordinary income.<br>     我得到的那笔钱是很管用的外快。<br>'),(13507,'supplemental','','','','','a. 补充的,增补的',''),(13508,'supplementary','','','','supplementaries','a. 补充的,附加的',' A supplementary grant may be awarded at the discretion of the committee.<br>     委员会可能酌情追加一笔补助金.<br>\r\n A supplementary set of keys, usually numerical and arranged like a calculator, added to a keyboard.<br>     一组增设的键盘，通常是数字型的，其排列方式与计算器的排列方式相似，附设在主键盘上。<br>'),(13509,'suppliant','','','','suppliants','a. 哀恳的',' He asked for help in a suppliant attitude.<br>     他以恳求的态度要我帮忙。<br>\r\n He knelt as a suppliant at the altar.<br>     他跪在祭坛前祈祷。<br>'),(13510,'supplicant','','','','','n. 乞求者,恳求者',''),(13511,'supplicate','supplicated','supplicated','supplicating','','v. 恳求,乞求',' He supplicates me to help.<br>     他向我求助。<br>\r\n She supplicated for pardon.<br>     她恳求原谅。<br>'),(13512,'supplier','','','','','n. 供给的人,供给国,承制厂商',' The equipment must be bought from a supplier approved by the company.<br>     设备必须从公司认可的供应商那里购买。<br>\r\n If the goods I ordered don\'t arrive tomorrow, I\'ll have to contact the supplier and chase them up.<br>     如果我们订的货物明天还不到，我得与供货商联系，催促他们快办。<br>'),(13513,'supplies','','','','','物资,贮藏量',' At any rate, the medical supplies will reach you within a week.<br>     无论如何, 医疗物资会在一周内到达。<br>\r\n The merchant supplies goods to them.<br>     商人向他们供应货物。<br>'),(13514,'supply','','','','','n. 补给,供给<br>\r\nv. 补给,供给',' The merchant supplies goods to them.<br>     商人向他们供应货物。<br>\r\n The supply ships travelled in convoy.<br>     补给船结队航行.<br>'),(13515,'support','supported','supported','supporting','supports','n. 支持,援助,供养<br>\r\nvt. 支援,帮助,支持',' He needs a high income to support such a large family.<br>     他需要有高收入才能供养得起这样一个大家庭。<br>\r\n Which football team do you support?<br>     你支持哪个足球队？<br>'),(13516,'supporter','','','','supporters','n. 支持者',' The government\'s supporters welcomed the new law.<br>     拥护政府的人都欢迎新颁布的法规。<br>\r\n One that promotes, especially an active supporter or advocate.<br>     促进者促进的人，尤指活跃的支持者或倡导者<br>'),(13517,'supporters','','','','','支持者,载体',' The speaker\'s supporters were planted in the audience and applauded loudly.<br>     听众中安插了演讲人的支持者；他们使劲给他鼓掌。<br>\r\n They are mobilizing their supporters to vote at the election.<br>     他们正在组织其支持者向他们拉选票。<br>'),(13518,'supporting','','','','','a. 次要的,辅助性的',' The government should not waste money supporting lame ducks.<br>     政府不应浪费资金去扶持那些无望的企业.<br>\r\n The top portion of the front part of an automobile body, supporting the windshield and dashboard.<br>     外壳罩汽车车体前部的顶部，用以支撑挡风玻璃和遮泥板<br>'),(13519,'supportive','','','','','a. 支持的',' She has been very supportive during my illness.<br>     我患病期间她帮了我很大忙。<br>\r\n The author dedicated her new book to her supportive family.<br>     这位作家将她的新书献给支持她的家庭。<br>'),(13520,'suppose','supposed','supposed','supposing','','v. 推想,假设,以为,认为<br>\r\n应该,获准(be suppose to),让(虚拟语气)',' We suppose that the situation will improve.<br>     我们认为形势会好转。<br>\r\n Creation supposes a creator.<br>     有了创造者，才能有创造。<br>'),(13521,'supposed','','','','','v. 假定(必须以...为条件)<br>\r\na. 想象上的',' The supposed beggar was really a police officer in disguise.<br>     那个众人眼中的乞丐，其实是化了装的警察。<br>\r\n We are supposed to dress up as movie characters for the party, what a novel idea!<br>     我们在晚会上要装扮得像电影中的角色，这是一个多么新奇的主意啊！<br>'),(13522,'supposedly','','','','','ad. 想来(恐怕,按照推测)',' This picture is supposedly worth more than a million pounds.<br>     这幅画大概值一百万镑以上.<br>\r\n Supposedly, she\'s a rich woman.<br>     看上去她是一个有钱的女人。<br>'),(13523,'supposing','','','','','n. 假如,去...吧,不妨...吧',' Supposing we sign the contract tomorrow.<br>     让我们明天就签约吧。<br>\r\n Supposing that there is no pure water; what shall we drink?<br>     假如没有纯净的水，人们喝什么？<br>'),(13524,'supposition','','','','','n. 想像,推测,推想',' We must not condemn her on pure supposition.<br>     我们不能单凭猜测就谴责她。<br>\r\n Our suppositions were fully confirmed.<br>     我们猜测的事实已全部证实。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (13525,'supposititious','','','','','a. 假想的',''),(13526,'suppress','suppressed','suppressed','suppressing','','v. 镇压,使...止住,禁止',' All these movements were suppressed by the warlord government.<br>     所有这些运动都受到军阀政府的镇压。<br>\r\n The revolt was suppressed in a matter of hours.<br>     叛乱在几小时之内就镇压下去了。<br>'),(13527,'suppression','','','','','n. 抑压,镇压,抑制',' Suppression of the immune response, as by drugs or radiation, in order to prevent the rejection of grafts or transplants or control autoimmune diseases.<br>     免疫抑制通过药物或放射治疗实现的对免疫反应的抑制，目的在于阻止对移植物或移植的排斥或者来控制自身免疫病<br>\r\n A tribunal formerly held in the Roman Catholic Church and directed at the suppression of heresy.<br>     宗教法庭曾设于罗马天主教堂的法庭，目的是对异教进行压制<br>'),(13528,'suppurate','suppurated','suppurated','suppurating','','v. 生脓,化脓,流脓',''),(13529,'supremacy','','','','','n. 至高,主权',' That country achieved military supremacy over neighbouring countries.<br>     那个国家获得了超越邻边国家的军事优势。<br>\r\n They challenged that company\'s supremacy in the field of electronics.<br>     他们挑战那家公司在电子学领域中占据的领先地位。<br>'),(13530,'supreme','','','','','a. 最高的',' It was the supreme moment in his life.<br>     那是他一生中最重要的时刻。<br>\r\n The general was girded with the supreme power.<br>     将军被授予最高权力。<br>'),(13531,'Supreme Court','','','','','最高法院',' Some criticized Clinton\'s move as\"a slap in the face of the black community.\"Others said President Bush showed more guts when he stuck with Clarence Thomas during his Supreme Court nomination fight.<br>     有些人批评克林顿的做法是“对所有黑人的污辱。”另一些人说布什总统在支持托马斯争取最高法院提名时，表现了更大的魄力。<br>\r\n The Supreme Court gave a fair trial to the case.<br>     最高法院对这一案件作出了公正的审判。<br>'),(13532,'supremely','','','','','ad. 无上地, 崇高地',''),(13533,'surcease','surceased','surceased','surceasing','','n. 停止,完结',''),(13534,'surcharge','surcharged','surcharged','surcharging','','n. 装载过多,额外费',' They\'ve surcharged us 10% on the price of the holiday because of a rise in air fares.<br>     因飞机票涨价, 他们在度假费用中向我们增收了10%附加费.<br>'),(13535,'sure','','','','','a. 确信,必然的,必定的<br>\r\nad. 当然,确实地,无疑地',' She is sure to pass the examination.<br>     她一定会通过考试。<br>\r\n He is clever, to be sure, but not very hard-working.<br>     他聪明是聪明，但是不怎么勤奋。<br>'),(13536,'surefire','','','','','a. 一定会发生的,定成功的',''),(13537,'surely','','','','','ad. 的确地,安全地',' You\'re surely not asking 40 for this book?\' Yes it\'s cheap at the price!\'<br>     ｀这本书你绝不会要价40英镑吧?＇｀是40英镑--物有所值啊!＇<br>\r\n That\'s wrong, surely.<br>     这显然是错的。<br>'),(13538,'sureness','','','','','n. 千真万确,确实',' Sureness of occurrence or result; inevitability.<br>     必然发生或结局的确定性；必然性<br>'),(13539,'surf','surfed','surfed','surfing','','n. 海浪<br>\r\nvi. 冲浪',' If the waves are big enough, we\'ll go surfing.<br>     如果浪够大的话，我们就去冲浪。<br>\r\n They were splashing about in the surf.<br>     他们在拍岸的浪花中戏水。<br>'),(13540,'surface','surfaced','surfaced','surfacing','surfaces','n. 表面,平面<br>\r\na. 表面的,肤浅的<br>\r\nv. 使...成平面,被露出来,在表面工作',' Beneath that apparently calm surface is a man of fierce temper.<br>     文静的外表掩盖着的是一个火暴脾气的人。<br>\r\n The surface of the lake is quite still.<br>     湖面相当平静。<br>'),(13541,'surface tension','','','','','n. 表面张力',''),(13542,'surfeit','surfeited','surfeited','surfeiting','','n. 过食<br>\r\nv. 使腻,吃过份',' A surfeit of rich food is bad for you.<br>     多吃油腻食物对身体有害。<br>\r\n There has been a surfeit of plays about divorce on the TV recently.<br>     最近有关离婚的电视剧太多了。<br>'),(13543,'surfer','','','','','n. 冲浪者',''),(13544,'surfing','','','','','n. 冲浪运动',' If the waves are big enough, we\'ll go surfing.<br>     如果浪够大的话，我们就去冲浪。<br>\r\n They were splashing about in the surf.<br>     他们在拍岸的浪花中戏水。<br>'),(13545,'surge','surged','surged','surging','surges','n. 巨涌,汹涌,澎湃<br>\r\nv. 汹涌,澎湃',' Anger surged up within him.<br>     怒火在他心中燃烧。<br>\r\n The crowd surged past him.<br>     人们从他身边涌过。<br>'),(13546,'surgeon','','','','surgeons','n. 外科医生',' The surgeon asked him if he felt nervous.<br>     外科医生问他是否感到紧张。<br>\r\n The surgeon is performing a delicate operation.<br>     那位外科医生正在做一个很精细的手术。<br>'),(13547,'surgery','','','','surgeries','n. 外科,外科手术',' He underwent open-heart surgery.<br>     他接受了体外循环心脏手术。<br>\r\n We built ourselves a new surgery.<br>     我们给自己建了一间新的外科手术室。<br>'),(13548,'surgical','','','','','a. 外科的,外科医生的,手术上的',' The doctor performs operations with sterilized surgical instruments.<br>     医生用消过毒的外科手术器械做手术。<br>\r\n The hospital imported some surgical instruments.<br>     医院进口了一些外科器械。<br>'),(13549,'surly','','','','','a. 不和蔼的,板著面孔的,粗声暴气的',' Don\'t look so surly!<br>     别那么横眉立目的！<br>\r\n Surly the most sensible thing would be to stay away from the case.<br>     肯定地说，最合理的做法就是远离这个箱子。<br>'),(13550,'surmise','surmised','surmised','surmising','surmises','n. 推测<br>\r\nv. 推测,臆测',' Your first surmise was right.<br>     你第一次猜得对。<br>\r\n We surmised that he must have had an accident.<br>     我们猜想他一定出事了。<br>'),(13551,'surmount','surmounted','surmounted','surmounting','','v. 克服,越过',' I think most of these obstacles can be surmounted.<br>     我认为这些障碍大多数都是可以克服的。<br>\r\n Hard to traverse, climb, or surmount.<br>     难攀登的，陡峭的难以通过、攀登或克服的<br>'),(13552,'surname','surnamed','surnamed','surnaming','surnames','n. 姓',' What is your surname?<br>     你的姓是什么？<br>\r\n Just call me by my surname, cut out the Mr.<br>     就叫我的姓吧，去掉先生二字。<br>'),(13553,'surpass','surpassed','surpassed','surpassing','','v. 超越,凌驾,胜过',' Men surpass women in strength.<br>     男人比女人力气大。<br>\r\n Effort or ambition to equal or surpass another.<br>     竞争，好胜心争取赶上或超过另一个的努力或野心<br>'),(13554,'surplus','','','','surpluses','a. 多余的,过剩的<br>\r\nn. 过剩,剩余物,盈余,顺差',' We are giving away all our surplus apples.<br>     我们准备把多余的苹果全部送人。<br>\r\n Mexico has a large surplus of oil.<br>     墨西哥有大量过剩的石油。<br>'),(13555,'surprise','surprised','surprised','surprising','surprises','n. 惊奇<br>\r\nv. 使惊奇',' It was a pleasant surprise to learn of her marriage.<br>     得知她结婚是件令人惊喜的事。<br>\r\n The news greatly surprised them.<br>     这消息使他们大为吃惊。<br>'),(13556,'surprised','','','','','a. 感到惊讶的<br>\r\nvbl. 感到惊讶',' In fact I\'m rather surprised you haven\'t done so already.<br>     你还没有这样做，我实在感到惊讶。<br>\r\n The news greatly surprised them.<br>     这消息使他们大为吃惊。<br>'),(13557,'surprising','','','','','a. 令人惊讶的',' It\'s surprising: they lost!<br>     他们竟然失败了，真没想到！<br>\r\n Well, that\'s very surprising.<br>     唷，这真是叫人吃惊。<br>'),(13558,'surprisingly','','','','','ad. 惊人地(意外地)',' Swans are surprisingly awkward on land.<br>     天鹅在陆地上笨得出奇.<br>\r\n He\'s surprisingly sprightly for an old man.<br>     他这把年纪了, 还这麽精神, 真了不起.<br>'),(13559,'surreal','','','','','a. 不现实的,梦幻的,怪异的,可怕的',' Meeting you here like this is positively surreal!<br>     像这样与你在此相逢真好比一场梦!<br>\r\n Under the influence of the drug my mind was filled with surreal images.<br>     我受了麻醉药的刺激, 头脑里充满了稀奇古怪的幻觉.<br>'),(13560,'surrealist','','','','','n. 超现实主义者',' The lexicon of surrealist art.<br>     超现实主义艺术的词汇<br>'),(13561,'surrender','surrendered','surrendered','surrendering','surrenders','v. 投降,让与,屈服',' They surrendered to the enemy.<br>     他们向敌人投降了。<br>\r\n We would rather die than surrender.<br>     我们宁死而不投降。<br>'),(13562,'surreptitious','','','','','a. 鬼鬼祟祟的,保密的',' Characterized by stealth; surreptitious.<br>     秘密的偷偷摸摸的；鬼鬼祟祟的<br>\r\n His surreptitious behaviour naturally aroused suspicion.<br>     他那鬼鬼祟祟的行为自然引起了旁人的怀疑。<br>'),(13563,'surrey','','','','surreys','n. <美>(四轮双座通常有篷的)萨里式游览马车',' The girl went to the museum by a surrey.<br>     那个女孩坐着一辆四轮双座轻便马车去博物馆了。<br>\r\n Surrey scored only200 runs and had to follow on.<br>     萨里只得了200分，只好继续击球。<br>'),(13564,'surrogate','','','','','n. 代理,代理人,代用品',' Fiction is a poor surrogate for real experience.<br>     小说中的事远逊於实际体验.<br>'),(13565,'surround','surrounded','surrounded','surrounding','surrounds','n. 环绕物<br>\r\nv. 包围,环绕',' We are surrounded by dangers.<br>     我们的处境危机四伏。<br>\r\n Trees surround the pond.<br>     树木围绕著池塘.<br>'),(13566,'surrounding','','','','surroundings','a. 周围的<br>\r\nn. 环境,周围的事物',' The surrounding villages have been absorbed by/into the growing city.<br>     周围的村庄已经并入了那不断扩展的城市.<br>\r\n Gradually the surrounding farmland turned residential.<br>     周围的农田渐渐变成了住宅区。<br>'),(13567,'surroundings','','','','','n. 周围的事物,环境',' Animals in zoos are not in their natural surroundings.<br>     动物园里的动物不是生活在自然环境中。<br>\r\n We are living in pleasant surroundings.<br>     我们生活在舒适的环境中。<br>'),(13568,'surveillance','','','','','n. 监视,监督',' The act of observing closely or the condition of being closely observed; surveillance.<br>     密切注视密切注视的行为或被密切注视的状态；监视<br>\r\n The act or a period of observing; surveillance.<br>     观察；警戒观察或监视的行为或时间<br>'),(13569,'survey','surveyed','surveyed','surveying','surveys','n. 纵览,视察,测量<br>\r\nv. 审视,视察,通盘考虑,调查',' We stood on the top of the mountain and surveyed the countryside.<br>     我们站在山顶上，眺望乡村。<br>\r\n This survey is the work of a real professional.<br>     这份调查是真正内行人做的.<br>'),(13570,'surveying','','','','','n. (土地)测量',' A line established by sighting in surveying a tract of land.<br>     横断线在测量一块土地时通过目视确定的线<br>\r\n An instrument used in surveying, consisting of100 linked pieces of iron or steel and measuring66 feet(20.1 meters).<br>     测链测量用的一种工具，包含有100个相连的钢铁环，长66英尺（20。1米）<br>'),(13571,'surveyor','','','','surveyors','n. 测量员(检查员)',' A small flag for marking a position, used especially by surveyors or soldiers.<br>     测量旗用来标记位置的小旗，尤用于测量员或战士<br>\r\n The surveyor went over the house thoroughly and advised us not to buy it.<br>     房屋鉴定人彻底察看了房子以後, 劝我们不要买.<br>'),(13572,'survival','','','','survivals','n. 生存',' That fashion is a survival from the 1930s.<br>     那种时装是三十年代的遗风。<br>\r\n The miraculous survival of some people in the air crash was widely reported by the press.<br>     空难事件中有些人大难不死被新闻界广泛报导。<br>'),(13573,'survive','survived','survived','surviving','','v. 生存,生还',' The human race cannot survive.<br>     人类不能继续生存。<br>\r\n In the jungle, they were driven to extremes in order to survive.<br>     在丛林中, 他们为了生存被迫采取极端行动.<br>'),(13574,'survivor','','','','survivors','n. 幸存者',' He is the only survivor of the plane crash.<br>     他是那次飞机失事唯一的幸存者。<br>\r\n The sole survivor of the crash was a little boy.<br>     这次撞车事故的唯一幸存者是一个小男孩。<br>'),(13575,'Susan','','','','','n. 苏珊(女子名)',' Susan is in a thoughtful mood.<br>     苏珊心事重重。<br>\r\n Susan seems very quiet, but make no mistake (about it), she has a terrible temper!<br>     苏珊样子很文静, 可别产生误会, 她脾气坏极了!<br>'),(13576,'susceptibility','','','','susceptibilities','n. 感受性,感情',' Susceptibility to bribery or corruption, as in the use of a position of trust for dishonest gain.<br>     甘受贿赂，贪污腐化易受贿赂或腐败的影响性，如在使用不诚实的收益的信托状况时<br>\r\n The state of being predisposed; tendency, inclination, or susceptibility.<br>     倾向倾向于…的状态；趋势；倾向或敏感性<br>'),(13577,'susceptible','','','','','n. 易受影响者,易受感染者<br>\r\na. 易受影响的,易感动的,容许',' The plant is not susceptible to disease.<br>     这种植物不容易受病害侵袭。<br>\r\n He\'s so susceptible that she easily gained his affection.<br>     他易受感情影响，所以她很轻易就得到了他的爱。<br>'),(13578,'sushi','','','','','n. 寿司',''),(13579,'suspect','','','','','n. 嫌疑犯<br>\r\na. 令人怀疑的,不可信的<br>\r\nv. 怀疑,猜想',' She has more intelligence than we suspected her to possess.<br>     她的智慧比我们猜想的要高。<br>\r\n They suspected an ambush.<br>     他们怀疑有埋伏。<br>'),(13580,'suspend','suspended','suspended','suspending','','v. 推迟,悬(浮),挂,暂停,取消<br>\r\nvi. 吊,悬浮<br>\r\nvt. 悬,挂,吊,暂停,中止',' The policeman was suspended while the complaint was investigated.<br>     因该警察遭投诉，在调查期间已令其暂停职务。<br>\r\n A curved or sharply bent device, usually of metal, used to catch, drag, suspend, or fasten something else.<br>     钩呈曲线形或急剧弯曲的金属装置，用于抓、拉、挂或固定其他东西<br>'),(13581,'suspended','','','','','a. 被暂时搁置的',' His license was suspended for six months.<br>     他的执照被吊销6个月。<br>\r\n The driver\'s certificate was suspended by the police.<br>     这个司机的驾驶执照被警察吊销了。<br>'),(13582,'suspender','','','','suspenders','n. 吊的人,袜吊,吊裤带',' Some boys wear suspenders to keep their trousers up.<br>     有些孩子使用背带来吊住裤子。<br>'),(13583,'suspense','','','','','n. 悬疑,焦虑,悬念',' Don\'t keep us in suspense any longer!<br>     别再让我们着急了！<br>\r\n We waited in great suspense for the doctor\'s diagnosis.<br>     我们焦急万分地等候医生做出诊断。<br>'),(13584,'suspense account','','','','','暂记帐户',''),(13585,'suspension','','','','suspensions','n. 悬挂,未决,中止',' The headmaster has made a decision of suspension of a pupil from school.<br>     校长已经做出对一名学生停学处分的决定。<br>\r\n She appealed against her suspension.<br>     她对被停职一事已经上诉。<br>'),(13586,'suspension bridge','','','','','n. 悬桥(吊桥)',' And the suspension bridge from hanging vines.<br>     悬索桥受到了悬挂着的藤的启发。<br>'),(13587,'suspicion','suspicioned','suspicioned','suspicioning','suspicions','n. 猜疑,怀疑',' The talks have resulted in a lessening of suspicion.<br>     谈话消减了彼此的怀疑。<br>\r\n They had an uneasy suspicion that all was not well.<br>     他们有一种令人不安的猜疑，所有的事都不太妙。<br>'),(13588,'suspicious','','','','','a. 怀疑的',' His strange behavior made the police suspicious.<br>     他不寻常的举止引起了警察的怀疑。<br>\r\n Two suspicious characters were brought in.<br>     逮捕了两名嫌疑犯.<br>'),(13589,'suspiciously','','','','','ad. 猜疑地,可疑地',' The customs officer inspected my passport suspiciously.<br>     海关官员颇为怀疑地检查了我的护照.<br>\r\n The aforementioned (person/persons) was/were acting suspiciously.<br>     前面所述的人行动可疑.<br>'),(13590,'sustain','sustained','sustained','sustaining','','v. 承受,支持,经受,维持',' The foundations were not strong enough to sustain the weight of the house.<br>     这地基不够牢固，无法承受房屋的重量。<br>\r\n Hope alone sustained him in his struggle.<br>     在奋斗中，只有希望支持着他。<br>'),(13591,'sustained','','','','','a. 持久的,经久不衰的',' A system of physical conditioning designed to enhance circulatory and respiratory efficiency that involves vigorous, sustained exercise, such as jogging, swimming, or cycling, thereby improving the body\'s utilization of oxygen.<br>     有氧健身法旨在增强循环和呼吸功效的生理调节体系，包括有力的、持久的锻炼，例如慢跑、游泳或骑自行车，从而提高肌体对氧气的利用<br>\r\n The court sustained his claim that the contract was illegal.<br>     法庭确认他的要求正当，宣布该合同不合法。<br>'),(13592,'sustenance','','','','','n. 生计,食物',' She is weak from lack of sustenance.<br>     她因缺乏营养而虚弱。<br>\r\n There\'s not much sustenance in a glass of orange squash.<br>     一杯橙汁饮料没有什么营养。<br>'),(13593,'suture','sutured','sutured','suturing','','n. 缝合,缝合处,缝合用的线<br>\r\nv. 缝合',''),(13594,'svelte','','','','','a. 苗条的, 体态娇美的',''),(13595,'swab','swabbed','swabbed','swabbing','','擦净',' Little Tom swabbed up the gravy with crusty bread.<br>     小汤姆用硬面包把肉汁抹得干干净净。<br>'),(13596,'swag','swagged','swagged','swagging','','n. 摇动(松垂,挠度,洼地)<br>\r\nvt 摇动(松垂,挠度,洼地)',''),(13597,'swagger','swaggered','swaggered','swaggering','','v. 大摇大摆地走',' Don\'t swagger (around) just because you got the job.<br>     别因为得到了这份工作就得意忘形.<br>\r\n He took his prize and swaggered back to his seat.<br>     他领奖後洋洋得意地回到自己的座位上.<br>'),(13598,'swain','','','','swains','n. 情郎,乡下的年轻人',''),(13599,'swallow','','','','','n. 燕子<br>\r\nvt. 吞下,咽下,忍受<br>\r\nvi. 咽口水',' She was swallowed up by the crowd and we lost sight of her.<br>     她淹没在人群之中，我们看不到她了。<br>\r\n There are many swallows flying in the sky.<br>     天空中有许多燕子。<br>'),(13600,'swam','','','','','v. 游泳',' As he swam, he thrashed the water with his hand.<br>     他游泳时用手拍打水。<br>\r\n Swam downriver; a downriver canoe race.<br>     向下游游泳；顺流独木舟赛<br>'),(13601,'swamp','swamped','swamped','swamping','swamps','n. 沼泽,湿地<br>\r\nv. 淹没,陷于沼泽',' The heavy rain has turned the small garden into a swamp.<br>     大雨使这小花园变成了一块沼泽地。<br>\r\n In the swamp we were beset by mosquitoes.<br>     我们在沼泽地受到蚊子的围攻。<br>'),(13602,'swampland','','','','','n. 沼泽地(低湿地)',''),(13603,'swampy','','','','','a. 沼泽的,沼泽多的,湿地的',' Full of or resembling mire; swampy.<br>     沼泽般的充满了淤泥的或似沼泽的；泥沼的<br>\r\n Low, flat, swampy land; a bog or marsh.<br>     沼泽低平的沼泽地；泥塘或湿地<br>'),(13604,'swan','','','','','n. 天鹅<br>\r\nvi. 闲荡,游荡',' A black swan is rare.<br>     黑天鹅很稀有。<br>\r\n The swan sings when death comes.<br>     死期来到，天鹅歌声美妙。<br>'),(13605,'swank','swanked','swanked','swanking','','v. 夸耀,炫耀',' Don\'t be such a swank!<br>     别那麽招摇!<br>\r\n She\'s swanking just because they said her essay was the best.<br>     皆因人称她的文章最好, 她就忘乎所以了.<br>'),(13606,'Swansea','','','','','斯旺西[英国威尔士南部港市](西格拉摩根郡首府)',' A borough of southern Wales west-northwest of Cardiff. It is an industrial port on Swansea Bay, an inlet of the Bristol Channel. Population, 188,500.<br>     斯旺西威尔士南部市镇，位于卡迪夫西北偏西。是布里斯托尔海峡的小海湾斯旺西湾的一个工业港口。人口188，500<br>'),(13607,'swap','swapped','swapped','swapping','swaps','v.&n. 交换<br>\r\nvt. 交换,用...作交易',' As you like my dress and I like yours, shall we do a swap?<br>     既然你喜欢我的连衣裙而我也喜欢你的，咱们交换好吗？<br>\r\n They swapped (ie told each other) stories about their army days.<br>     他们互相讲述了他们在军队中的经历.<br>'),(13608,'swarm','','','','','n. 蜂窝<br>\r\nv. 云集、充满',' He has received a swarm of letters.<br>     他已经收到了一大批信件。<br>\r\n The crowd swarmed out of the cinema after the film ended.<br>     电影结束后，人们从电影院蜂拥而出。<br>'),(13609,'swarming','','','','','分蜂群<br>\r\n群飞<br>\r\n分蜂<br>\r\n群居',' The crowd was swarming out through the gates.<br>     人群一窝蜂地从出口涌出.<br>\r\n The beach was swarming with bathers.<br>     海滩上挤满了游泳的人.<br>'),(13610,'swarthy','','','','','a. 黑黝黝的,浅黑的',' She has a swarthy complexion.<br>     她的肤色黝黑。<br>'),(13611,'swathe','swathed','swathed','swathing','','v. 紧绑',' The farmer cut a swathe in the field with his scythe.<br>     农夫用镰刀在地里刈出一条路来。<br>'),(13612,'sway','swayed','swayed','swaying','','n. 摇,影响力,支配<br>\r\nv. 使摇动,支配',' His power sways the world.<br>     他称霸天下。<br>\r\n The branches of the trees were swaying in the wind.<br>     树枝在风中摇晃。<br>'),(13613,'swear','swore','sworn','swearing','','v. 发誓,宣誓,咒骂',' They swore an oath to carry out their duties faithfully.<br>     他们发誓要忠实履行自己的职责。<br>\r\n I swore her to secrecy about what I had told her.<br>     我要她起誓对我告诉她的事保守秘密。<br>'),(13614,'sweat','sweat','sweat','sweating','','n. 汗<br>\r\nv. 出汗',' I really sweated over my last essay.<br>     我的确下功夫写了上次那篇文章。<br>\r\n I am sweating all over.<br>     我浑身上下大汗淋漓。<br>'),(13615,'sweatband','','','','','n. (运动时系在额上或手腕上的)吸汗巾',''),(13616,'sweater','','','','sweaters','n. 毛衣',' I had to put on a sweater since it was raining hard outside.<br>     外面在下雨，我不得不套上一件厚运动衫。<br>\r\n This sweater washes well.<br>     这件套头毛衣耐洗.<br>'),(13617,'sweatshop','','','','sweatshops','n. 血汗工厂(工作条件恶劣而工资低的)',''),(13618,'sweaty','','','','','a. 汗流浃背的,热得令人发汗的',''),(13619,'Swede','','','','','n. 瑞典人<br>\r\nn. 瑞典甘蓝，一种黄色大头菜',' He is a Swede.<br>     他是瑞典人。<br>\r\n The Swede would answer with pride: \"Both, sir! \" For many days this practice continued.<br>     瑞典人会骄傲地答道：“两次，长官。”这样的练习进行了好多天。<br>'),(13620,'Sweden','','','','','n. 瑞典',' He was born in Sweden.<br>     他出生于瑞典。<br>\r\n Sweden has frontiers with Norway and Finland.<br>     瑞典与挪威和芬兰接壤。<br>'),(13621,'Swedish','','','','','n. 瑞典人,瑞典语<br>\r\na. 瑞典的,瑞典人的,瑞典语的',' She can understands Swedish quite well.<br>     她懂瑞典语。<br>\r\n Swedish director whose critically acclaimed films, such as The Silence(1963) and Fanny and Alexander(1983), are characterized by slow pace, laconic dialogue, and heavy use of symbolism to explore the psychological states of the characters.<br>     伯格曼，英马尔生于1918瑞典导演，其受到评论界赞扬的电影，如沉默（1963年）和芬尼和亚历山大（1983年），其特点是慢节奏、对话简洁和大量运用象征手法以揭示人物的心理状态<br>'),(13622,'sweep','swept','swept','sweeping','sweeps','n. 扫除,席卷,范围<br>\r\nv. 扫除,用手指弹,掠过',' She swept the floor clean.<br>     她把地板打扫干净。<br>\r\n This floor needs a good sweep.<br>     这地板需要好好清扫一下。<br>'),(13623,'sweeper','','','','sweepers','n. 清扫夫',' I want to buy a carpet sweeper.<br>     我想买一台地毯清扫器。<br>\r\n She is a pavement sweeper.<br>     她是一个打扫人行道的清扫工人。<br>'),(13624,'sweeping','','','','sweepings','n. 扫除,废屑<br>\r\na. 一扫而去的,凶猛的,广泛的<br>\r\nvbl. 扫除,打扫',' The streets have been swept free of leaves.<br>     街上的落叶已打扫乾净.<br>\r\n Such evil practice cannot be swept away at once.<br>     这种坏事不是一下能扫除干净的。<br>'),(13625,'sweet','','','','sweets','a. 甜的,可爱的,悦耳的<br>\r\nn. 糖果,甜点',' The dish tastes a bit sweet.<br>     这菜有点儿甜味。<br>\r\n The dentist told the boy not to eat too many sweets.<br>     牙医告诫这男孩不要吃太多糖果。<br>'),(13626,'sweet potato','','','','','白薯,山芋',''),(13627,'sweeten','sweetened','sweetened','sweetening','','v. 使甜,变舒适,净化',' Shall I sweeten your coffee?<br>     我给你的咖啡加点糖好吗？<br>\r\n A good meal sweetened his temper.<br>     吃了一顿好饭，他的脾气变得好多了。<br>'),(13628,'sweetener','','','','','n. 使变甜的东西,甜味剂',' The firm offers her a generous bonus as a sweetener.<br>     公司提出给她一笔可观的花红藉以拉拢她。<br>\r\n Love and scandal is the best sweetener of tea.<br>     恋爱与丑闻，是喝茶的最佳甜点心。<br>'),(13629,'sweetening','','','','','n. 变甜,使变甜之物',' Containing, full of, or sweetened with honey.<br>     多蜜液的含有蜜的，充满了蜜或因蜜变甜的<br>\r\n Shall I sweeten your coffee?<br>     我给你的咖啡加点糖好吗？<br>'),(13630,'sweetheart','sweethearted','sweethearted','sweethearting','sweethearts','n. 情人,爱人<br>\r\nv. 爱慕,求爱',' His sweetheart is a pretty girl.<br>     他的情人是一个可爱的女孩。<br>\r\n A favored female companion or sweetheart.<br>     女朋友最喜欢的女性同伴或爱人<br>'),(13631,'sweetly','','','','','ad. 甜美地',' The nightingale sings sweetly at night.<br>     这只夜莺夜里唱得很好听。<br>\r\n The choir sang sweetly, and none more so than the Welsh boy.<br>     唱诗班唱得很悦耳，尤其是没人比得上那个威尔士男孩儿。<br>'),(13632,'sweetness','','','','','n. 美味,芳香,美妙',' The slave has never experienced the sweetness of freedom.<br>     这个奴隶从未体验过自由的快乐。<br>\r\n Sweetness of thy name fills my heart when I forget mine- like thy morning sun when the mist is melted.<br>     您的名字的甜蜜充溢着我的心，而我忘掉了我自己的，——就象您的早晨的太阳升起时，那大雾便消失了。<br>'),(13633,'sweets','','','','','糖果',' The dentist told the boy not to eat too many sweets.<br>     牙医告诫这男孩不要吃太多糖果。<br>\r\n The bag of sweets on the table was too strong a temptation for the child to resist.<br>     桌上那包糖果对那孩子是个难以抗拒的诱惑.<br>'),(13634,'swell','swelled','swollen','swelling','swells','n. 增大,隆起的部分,巨浪<br>\r\na. 优秀的,上流的<br>\r\nv. 增大,使...膨胀,积聚',' The wind swelled out the sail.<br>     风吹得船帆鼓了起来。<br>\r\n Her ankle swelled up after the fall.<br>     她跌倒后脚踝肿了起来。<br>'),(13635,'swelling','','','','swellings','v. 膨胀(泡胀)<br>\r\na. 膨胀的(增大的)',' Wood often swells when wet.<br>     木材潮湿後往往会膨胀.<br>\r\n The swelling on her finger was caused by a foreign body in it.<br>     她的手指肿胀是手指内有异物引起的。<br>'),(13636,'swelter','sweltered','sweltered','sweltering','','v. 汗流浃背<br>\r\nvi. 酷热',' It\'s sweltering today.<br>     今天热叫人发昏。<br>\r\n Open the window; it\'s sweltering in here!<br>     打开窗户，这里热得要命！<br>'),(13637,'sweltering','','','','','a. 酷热的',''),(13638,'swept','','','','','sweep的过去式(分词)',' She swept the floor clean.<br>     她把地板打扫干净。<br>\r\n The flue should draw better once it\'s been swept.<br>     烟道一经清扫，通风情况应好些。<br>'),(13639,'swerve','swerved','swerved','swerving','swerves','vi.<br>\r\n1. 突然转向;转弯;偏离方向   2. 背离[(+from)]<br>\r\nvt.1. 使突然转向;使转弯  2. 使背离[(+from)]<br>\r\nn.[C]1. 转向;偏离方向  2. 偏离的程度',' I will never swerve from my declared policy on this matter.<br>     我决不背离我已经宣布的在这个问题上的政策。<br>\r\n The car swerved to the right.<br>     汽车突然向右转。<br>'),(13640,'swift','','','','swifts','a. 快的,迅速的<br>\r\nad. 快速地<br>\r\nn. 雨燕',' They\'ve been very swift to deny these rumors.<br>     他们在辟谣方面反应迅速。<br>\r\n The president promised swift and effective retribution against the terrorists.<br>     总统答应会迅速有效地惩罚恐怖分子。<br>'),(13641,'swiftly','','','','','ad. 很快地,即刻',' At a rapid pace; swiftly.<br>     飞快地；迅速地<br>\r\n A brief high-pitched humming or buzzing sound, such as that made by a swiftly passing object or a taut vibrating string.<br>     尖啸声一种短暂尖锐的嗡嗡声或滋滋声，例如高速运动的物体和拉紧的震颤的线发出的声音<br>'),(13642,'swiftness','','','','','n. 迅速,敏捷',' We condemned the violence in swiftness.<br>     我们立即谴责了那种暴行。<br>\r\n His reaction of swiftness surprised us.<br>     他迅速的反应让我们吃了一惊。<br>'),(13643,'swig','swigged','swigged','swigging','','n. 大喝,吞咽<br>\r\nv. 豪饮,大口地喝',' John kept swigging at the bottle of brandy.<br>     约翰对着那瓶白兰地酒大口地喝个不停。<br>\r\n Are they still swigging at that bottle? They\'ll soon be drunk.<br>     他们还在拿着瓶子暴饮吗？他们马上就会醉的。<br>'),(13644,'swill','swilled','swilled','swilling','','v. 冲洗,痛饮',' The rugby players were swilling mugs of beer at the bar.<br>     橄榄球运动员正在酒吧间痛饮啤酒。<br>\r\n Make sure the garage is well swilled out.<br>     请务必将车库里里外外都冲洗干净。<br>'),(13645,'swim','swam','swum','swimming','','游泳',' He can swim breaststroke, backstr