ted Persia through the medium of the Syrians.<br>     通过叙利亚人作媒介，希腊文化渗透到波斯。<br>'),(13734,'syringe','syringed','syringed','syringing','','n. 注射器',' An article, such as a paper diaper or hypodermic syringe, that can be disposed of after one use.<br>     用后即丢弃的物品，一次性物品用后即可丢弃的物品，如纸制尿布或皮下注射器<br>\r\n The child started to wail when the nurse come over with a syringe.<br>     当护士拿著针筒走过来时，孩子便嚎啕大哭起来。<br>'),(13735,'syrup','','','','','n. 糖浆',' Take one dose of this cough syrup three times a day.<br>     每天服三次这种止咳糖浆，每次服一剂量。<br>\r\n She dosed up the children with cough syrup.<br>     她把止咳糖浆给孩子们吃了。<br>'),(13736,'system','','','','systems','n. 系统,体系,制度,体制',' What are the difference between the American and British systems of government?<br>     英美两国的政府体制有什么不同？<br>\r\n She just blames it all on the system.<br>     她把这全归咎于制度。<br>'),(13737,'systematic','','','','','a. 有系统的,分类的,体系的',' The systematic arrangement of chairs makes the hall look spacious.<br>     座椅按照顺序排列，这使得礼堂里显得很宽敞。<br>\r\n He\'s very systematic in all he does.<br>     他做一切事情都很有条理。<br>'),(13738,'systematically','','','','','ad. 有系统地,有组织地,有条理地',' A structure through which individuals cooperate systematically to conduct business.<br>     组织一群人有系统地合作以开展活动的所建立的结构<br>\r\n The government was accused of having systematically distorted the protester\'s case.<br>     政府因为有计划地歪曲抗议者的观点而受到责难。<br>'),(13739,'systematize','systematized','systematized','systematizing','','v. 组织起来,体系化',' We must try to systematize the way we do the accounts.<br>     我们必须力求把记帐方法制度化.<br>'),(13740,'systemic','','','','','a. 全身的,系统的',' The main trunk of the systemic arteries, carrying blood from the left side of the heart to the arteries of all limbs and organs except the lungs.<br>     主动脉系统血管的主干道，将血液由心脏左侧输送到除肺部以外的所有肢体及器官的动脉里<br>'),(13741,'Szechwan','','','','','n. 四川省',' I\'ve tried Cantonese, Hunan and Szechwan food and they differ quite considerably.<br>     我试过广东，湖南和四川菜，他们都颇为不同。<br>'),(13742,'TAB','','','','','(tabulate)制表',' I\'ll pick up the tab.<br>  