an teachings could be heavily fined.<br>     反对英国国教教义的人在过去可判巨额罚款.<br>'),(13914,'teacup','','','','','n. 茶杯',' She has seen empty glass and teacup, and has known that has been three men inside the room.<br>     她看到了空玻璃杯和茶杯，知道房间里来过三个人。<br>\r\n Mary: Can you make the teacup, John?<br>     玛丽：你会做茶杯吗，约翰？<br>'),(13915,'teahouse','','','','teahouses','n. 茶室',' A man in the teahouse was laying the law down on politics.<br>     茶馆里有个人在非常自负地侃政治。<br>\r\n \"The Teahouse\" is playing at the Capital Theater.<br>     《茶馆》正在首都剧场上演。<br>'),(13916,'teal','','','','teal','n. 水鸭',''),(13917,'team','teamed','teamed','teaming','teams','n. 队,组<br>\r\nv. 协同工作',' Volleyball is a team game.<br>     排球是一项要求全队默契配合的运动。<br>\r\n I teamed up with him to do the work.<br>     我和他合作做这项工作。<br>'),(13918,'teammate','','','','','n. 队友',' A runner who intentionally sets a fast pace for a teammate during a long-distance race.<br>     带跑队员在长距离竞赛中故意为某一队友设定较快速度的选手<br>\r\n A pass of a basketball or an ice hockey puck that enables a teammate to score a goal.<br>     助杀，助攻在篮球赛或冰球比赛中传球以使同队伙伴进球得分<br>'),(13919,'teamwork','','','','','n. 合作,协同工作',' In football teamwork is even more important than individual skill.<br>     在橄榄球比赛中，全队的配合比个人技术甚至更加重要。<br>'),(13920,'teapot','','','','teapots','n. 茶壶',' The spout of the teapot is jammed by tea.<br>     茶壶的壶口被茶叶堵住了。<br>\r\n This teapot doesn\'t pour well.<br>     这个茶壶不好倒.<br>'),(13921,'tear','tore','torn','tearing','','n. 眼泪,撕破<br>\r\nv. 流泪,撕破',' She tore her skirt on the nail.<br>     钉子勾破了她的裙子。<br>\r\n My wife burst into tears when she heard the bad news.<br>     我太太听到这个坏消息就哭了起来。<br>'),(13922,'tearful','','','','','a. 含泪的,悲伤的',' But she hugged them to her chest, and at last she was able to look up with tearful eyes and a smile and say:\"My hair grows so fast, Jim! \"<br>     但是，她还是把这套梳子紧紧地包在怀里。最后，她终于抬起迷蒙的泪眼，含笑说道，“我的头发是长得很快的，吉姆！”<br>\r\n Her tearful family came to pay their last respects.<br>     她全家含泪前来向死者告别。<br>'),(13923,'tears','','','','','眼泪<br>\r\n泪液<br>\r\n泪水',' Tears distilled slowly from her eyes.<br>     泪水从她的眼睛里慢慢地滴下来。<br>\r\n She wiped her tears away.<br>     她擦掉了眼泪。<br>'),(13924,'tease','teased','teased','teasing','teases','n. 揶揄者,戏弄<br>\r\nv. 欺负,嘲弄',' He is a terrible tease.<br>     他特别爱戏弄人。<br>\r\n Don\'t take it seriously - he\'s only teasing.<br>     别把它当真，他只不过是在开玩笑。<br>'),(13925,'teaspoon','','','','teaspoons','n. 茶匙',' She mixed the sugar into the coffee with a teaspoon.<br>     她用茶匙把糖在咖啡里搅拌开。<br>\r\n Add a teaspoon of salt.<br>     加一小匙盐。<br>'),(13926,'teaspoonful','','','','teaspoonfuls','n. 一茶匙容量',''),(13927,'teat','','','','','n. 奶嘴,奶头',' A baby drinks milk from teats.<br>     婴儿用奶嘴喝牛奶。<br>'),(13928,'technical','','','','','a. 工艺的,技术的',' The flight was delayed owing to technical reasons.<br>     这次飞行由于技术的原因而被推迟。<br>\r\n This book is too technical for me.<br>     对我来说，这本书太专业了。<br>'),(13929,'technicality','','','','technicalities','n. 技术细节,技术性,术语,专门事项',' The book is full of scientific technicalities.<br>     这本书里尽是科学术语.<br>\r\n The lawyer explained the legal technicalities to his client.<br>     律师给委托人解释法律上的要点.<br>'),(13930,'technically','','','','','ad. 技术上,学术上,专门地',' It\'s quite clear that the electric car is technically feasible.<br>     很清楚，电动汽车在工艺技术上是可行的。<br>\r\n It is technically correct to use a phrase such as our late treasurer to refer to a person who is still alive but who no longer holds the relevant post, but the use of former in this context will ensure that no embarrassing misunderstanding is created.<br>     使用象我们的前任会计这样的词组来指仍然健在不过不掌管相关的职位的人，在字义上是正确的，但是在这样的情况下，former一词能够避免尴尬的误解发生<br>'),(13931,'technician','','','','technicians','n. 技术员,技师',' They need one laboratory technician.<br>     他们需要一名实验室技术员。<br>\r\n That technician is highly skilled.<br>     那位技师技术很好。<br>'),(13932,'technique','','','','techniques','n. 技术',' He displayed a flawless technique in the competition.<br>     他在竞赛中显示出了精湛的技艺。<br>\r\n The technique is still at the experimental stage.<br>     这项技术正处于实验阶段。<br>'),(13933,'technocracy','','','','technocracies','n. 专家政治论',' Is Britain becoming a technocracy?<br>     英国是否要成为实行专家政治的国家?<br>'),(13934,'technocrat','','','','','n. 技术人员,技术统治',''),(13935,'technological','','','','','a. 科技的',' The development of the information technology is the greatest technological advance of the 20th century.<br>     信息技术的发展是二十世纪工业技术上的最大进步。<br>\r\n A period of sequential technological development and innovation.<br>     阶段持续的技术发展和革新的一段时期<br>'),(13936,'technologically','','','','','ad. 技术上地',''),(13937,'technologist','','','','','n. 技术专家',''),(13938,'technology','','','','technologies','n. 技术,工艺',' The development of the information technology is the greatest technological advance of the 20th century.<br>     信息技术的发展是二十世纪工业技术上的最大进步。<br>\r\n Large scale industry emerged only gradually as technology evolved.<br>     大工业只是随着技术发展而逐渐开始存在的。<br>'),(13939,'tectonic','','','','','a. 筑造的,建筑的,构造的',''),(13940,'tectonics','','','','','n. 筑造学,构造学,构造地质学',''),(13941,'ted','tedded','tedded','tedding','','vt. 翻晒,撒,撒开',' Let\'s invite Ted -- he knows how to bring a party to life.<br>     我们邀请特德吧--有他到会就热闹了.<br>\r\n Thank you, but in all truth I feel the credit should go to Ted.<br>     谢谢，但是说实话我感觉应该归功于泰德。<br>'),(13942,'teddy','','','','','n. 妇女连衫裤, 泰迪(熊)',' The little boy go upstairs trailing his teddy bear behind him.<br>     那小男孩儿走上楼去，还拖著他的玩具熊。<br>\r\n He loved soft things, and would often smile at the touch of a soft teddy bear or other soft toy.<br>     他喜欢柔软的东西，在触摸软软的艾德熊和别的柔软的东西时经常露出微笑。<br>'),(13943,'teddy bear','','','','','n. 玩具熊',' The little boy go upstairs trailing his teddy bear behind him.<br>     那小男孩儿走上楼去，还拖著他的玩具熊。<br>\r\n He loved soft things, and would often smile at the touch of a soft teddy bear or other soft toy.<br>     他喜欢柔软的东西，在触摸软软的艾德熊和别的柔软的东西时经常露出微笑。<br>'),(13944,'tedious','','','','','a. 沉闷的, 单调乏味的',' He told me a tedious story.<br>     他给我讲了一个冗长乏味的故事。<br>\r\n He is an exceedingly tedious fellow.<br>     他是一个非常令人生厌的家伙。<br>'),(13945,'tedium','','','','','n. 单调乏味',''),(13946,'tee','teed','teed','teeing','','n. (高尔夫球)发球的球座',' The part of a golf course covered with short grass and extending from the tee to the putting green.<br>     球座与终点间的草地覆有剪平草的高尔夫球场的一部分，从球座到终点间的地带<br>\r\n A golf shot not tallied against the score, granted in informal play after a poor shot especially from the tee.<br>     加击非正式比赛的高尔夫球游戏中，由于击球不好特允许再多打一次，但不为得分，尤指在发球处进行<br>'),(13947,'tee shirt','','','','','n. 短袖圆领运动衫, T恤',' He wore his brother\'s evening dress to the function but looked very uncomfortable in his borrowed plumes instead of hi usual jeans and tee shirt.<br>     他穿着他兄弟的夜礼服去参加盛大的集会，但是穿着向别人借来的装门面的漂亮衣服看上去很不舒服，还不如他平时穿的牛仔裤和梯恤衫好。<br>'),(13948,'teem','','','','','v. 充满,富于',' The rain teemed down for hours.<br>     大雨一直下了好几个小时。<br>\r\n The river teems with all kinds of fish in summer.<br>     夏天这条河里各种各样的鱼多得很。<br>'),(13949,'teeming','','','','','a. 丰富的',' The river was teeming with fish.<br>     河里的鱼很多.<br>\r\n His mind was still teeming with various projects.<br>     他的脑子里依然塞满了各式各样的计划。<br>'),(13950,'teen','','','','','n. (=teenager)13岁到19岁的年轻人',' When I was in my teens, I liked playing football.<br>     少年时我喜欢踢足球。<br>\r\n She\'s in her teens.<br>     她正处于青少年时期。<br>'),(13951,'teenage','','','','','a. 青少年的(十三到十九岁的)',' Teenage is the period at which the body reaches maturity.<br>     青少年是身体成熟期。<br>\r\n This clothing sells well to the teenage market.<br>     这种衣服在青少年中间很畅销.<br>'),(13952,'teenager','','','','','n. 13岁到19岁的年轻人',' It is not easy to educate teenagers.<br>     教育青少年不是件容易的事。<br>\r\n That teenager singer is really dynamite!<br>     那个少年歌手真是轰动一时！<br>'),(13953,'teens','','','','','n. 青少年(十多岁,少年)',' My son did go off the rails for a while in his late teens but he has settled with a family.<br>     我儿子年轻时确实有些越轨行为，但现在安下心来，并已结婚成家。<br>\r\n All too many young people go off the rails during their teens but they seem to settle down after a few years.<br>     太多的年轻人在他们年轻时行为有些愚蠢，但几年后他们似乎就安顿了下来。<br>'),(13954,'teeny','','','','','a. 极小的(微小的)',' The store owner smiled