午收到了几份电传。<br>'),(13986,'tell','told','told','telling','','v. 告诉,分辨，辨别',' It\'s impossible to tell who will win the next election.<br>     下届选举谁能获胜无法预知。<br>\r\n I always tell my daughter a story before she goes to sleep.<br>     女儿睡觉之前，我总讲故事给她听。<br>'),(13987,'teller','','','','tellers','n. 讲话著,告诉的人,出纳员',' She worked as a teller in our bank.<br>     她在我们的银行里当出纳员。<br>\r\n As soon as I complete my training, I am going to be a bank teller.<br>     一旦我结束训练，我会成为一名银行出纳。<br>'),(13988,'telling','','','','','a. 有效的,显著的<br>\r\nvbl. 告诉,讲',' I quailed with fear at the thought of telling her the bad news.<br>     想到要告诉她这个坏消息，我就害怕得发抖。<br>\r\n What I\'m telling you is gospel.<br>     我告诉你的事千真万确。<br>'),(13989,'telltale','','','','telltales','a. 泄密的',' I can see from the telltale look in her eyes that she love him.<br>     我从她那无法掩饰的眼神里可以看出她爱他。<br>'),(13990,'telly','','','','tellies','n. 电视',''),(13991,'temblor','','','','temblors','n. 地震',''),(13992,'temerarious','','','','','a. 鲁莽的',''),(13993,'temerity','','','','temerities','n. 卤莽,蛮勇',' He had the temerity to call me a liar.<br>     他竟胆敢说我撒谎.<br>\r\n He had the temerity to ask for higher wages after only a day\'s work.<br>     只工作了一天，他就蛮不讲理地要求增加工资。<br>'),(13994,'temp','','','','','n. 温度(回过火的,样板,暂时的)',' He\'s been temping for over a year now and wants a permanent job.<br>     他做临时工作已一年多了, 想找个固定的工作.<br>'),(13995,'temper','tempered','tempered','tempering','tempers','n. 脾气,调剂,趋向<br>\r\nv. 锻练,调剂,缓和',' They are of congenial temper.<br>     他们的性情相投。<br>\r\n She coaxed him out of his bad temper.<br>     她循循善诱地劝他改掉坏脾气。<br>'),(13996,'tempera','','','','temperas','n. 涂料混上蛋白或其他物质的画法',''),(13997,'temperament','','','','temperaments','n. 气质,性质,性情',' The two brothers have entirely different temperaments.<br>     他们兄弟俩的性情完全不同。<br>\r\n I\'ve got a mild temperament.<br>     我的性情很温和。<br>'),(13998,'temperamental','','','','','a. 性情的,喜怒无常的',' Nigel is temperamental but he\'s very highly strung, you know.<br>     奈杰变化无常，但你知道他是很容易激动的。<br>\r\n A physiological or temperamental peculiarity.<br>     特异性格一种心理的或脾气上的特异性<br>'),(13999,'temperance','','','','','a. 温暖的,温和的,有节制的',' The patient had to practice temperance in eating and drinking.<br>     这个病人不得不节制饮食。<br>\r\n I would like some temperance drinks.<br>     我想要一些没有酒精的饮料。<br>'),(14000,'temperate','','','','','a. 温和的,适度的,有节制的',' Be more temperate in your language, please.<br>     言词上请节制一点儿。<br>\r\n Britain has a temperate climate.<br>     英国气候温和。<br>'),(14001,'temperature','','','','temperatures','n. 温度',' The food should be kept at low temperature.<br>     这种食品应低温保存。<br>\r\n There is an imperceptible change in temperature.<br>     温度有细微的变化。<br>'),(14002,'tempest','tempested','tempested','tempesting','tempests','n. 暴风雨,骚动',' It was a marvelous night with a tempest to rouse the gods.<br>     真是个美妙的夜晚，暴风雨惊天动地。<br>\r\n The scandal caused tempests in the newspaper.<br>     那件丑闻在报纸上引起阵阵风波。<br>'),(14003,'tempestuous','','','','','a. 有暴风雨的,暴乱的',' Their ship was sailing dangerously in the tempestuous sea.<br>     他们的船在浪急风高的海上危险地航行着。<br>'),(14004,'template','','','','','模板,样板',' Save the active document or template with its current name.<br>     以其目前的名字保存当前的文件或模板。<br>'),(14005,'temple','','','','','n. 庙宇,寺院<br>\r\nn.太阳穴',' Have you been to the Temple of Heaven in Beijing?<br>     你去过北京的天坛吗？<br>\r\n The man looks like a cartoon character with a plaster on his temple.<br>     那人太阳穴上贴了一块膏药，看上去像个卡通人物。<br>'),(14006,'tempo','','','','tempi','n. 拍子,速率',' Your tempo is too slow.<br>     你演奏的速度太慢了.<br>\r\n All this was comparatively slow until, with the coming of science, the tempo was suddenly raised.<br>     所有这些发展都比较缓慢，直到出现了科学，其速度才突然加快。<br>'),(14007,'temporal','','','','','a. 当时的,暂时的,现世的',' The Pope has no temporal power in modern society.<br>     教皇在当代社会没有世俗方面的权利。<br>\r\n The word is a temporal conjunction.<br>     该词是表示时间的连词。<br>'),(14008,'temporarily','','','','','a. 临时的<br>\r\nad. 暂时地,临时地',' The daily flight to the city has been temporarily suspended because of the earthquake.<br>