y arm with a tenacious grip.<br>     他紧紧抓住我的手臂不放。<br>'),(14019,'tenaciously','','','','','ad. 坚韧不拔地,执着地',''),(14020,'tenacity','','','','','n. 固执,不屈不挠,顽固',''),(14021,'tenancy','','','','tenancies','n. 租用(占有)',''),(14022,'tenant','tenanted','tenanted','tenanting','tenants','n. 房客,佃户',' The tenant was evicted for non-payment of rent.<br>     这个房客因为没有交房租而被赶出去了。<br>\r\n Are you an owner-occupier or a tenant?<br>     你住自己的房子还是租房住？<br>'),(14023,'tend','','','','','v. 有某种的倾向,易于,移向',' Weeds tend to displace other plants.<br>     杂草越来越多，有取代其他植物之势。<br>\r\n Does he tend to lose?<br>     他常常输吗?<br>'),(14024,'tendency','','','','tendencies','n. 趋势,倾向',' There is a growing tendency for people to work at home instead of in offices.<br>     人们在家里而不是在办公室里工作的趋势日益增长。<br>\r\n The belief that society has an innate tendency toward improvement and that this tendency may be furthered through conscious human effort.<br>     社会向善论认为社会具有变得更好的内在倾向和人类有力量促使其改善的信仰或学说<br>'),(14025,'tendentious','','','','','a. 有支持某种立场的倾向,宣传性的',' Such tendentious statements are likely to provoke strong opposition.<br>     这种有倾向性 的说法可能招致强烈的反对.<br>'),(14026,'tender','','','','','a. 温和的,亲切的,未成熟的<br>\r\nvt. 提供,投标',' This tender should be submitted by June 26th.<br>     此投标书应于六月二十六日前提交。<br>\r\n Don\'t mention his divorce---it\'s a very tender subject.<br>     别提他离婚的事---那是个敏感话题。<br>'),(14027,'tenderfoot','','','','tenderfeet','n. 生手,新手',''),(14028,'tenderly','','','','','ad. 柔软地(温和地)',' She embraced her son tenderly when he came home after ten years\' absence.<br>     她儿子离家十年后回家时她亲切地拥抱儿子。<br>\r\n She embraced her son tenderly.<br>     她亲切地拥抱儿子。<br>'),(14029,'tenderness','','','','','n. 柔软,亲切,柔和',' Her tenderness soothed my anger.<br>     她的亲切平息了我的怒气。<br>\r\n I dare not touch the flower for its tenderness.<br>     这花太娇嫩了，我不敢碰它。<br>'),(14030,'tendon','','','','tendons','n. 腱',' My tendon was strained.<br>     我扭伤了肌腱。<br>\r\n The tendon had been so skillfully grafted in that the boy was able to flex his finger quite normall