>     多亏这个倒霉天气，挺好的比赛取消了。<br>\r\n Thanks for the warning.<br>     谢谢你的提醒。<br>'),(14131,'Thanks a lot','','','','','非常感谢。',''),(14132,'Thanksgiving','','','','','n. 感恩节',' We invite her to have Thanksgiving dinner with us.<br>     我们邀请她和我们一起吃感恩节晚餐。<br>\r\n Thanksgiving is a movable holiday.<br>     感恩节的日期每年不同。<br>'),(14133,'Thanksgiving Day','','','','','n. 感恩节(美国是11月的第四个星期四,加拿大是10月的第二个星期一)',''),(14134,'that','','','','those','pron. 那<br>\r\na. pron. 那,那个<br>\r\nconj. 引导宾语从句',' I reached the gate that opened onto the lake.<br>     我走到临湖而开的那扇门前。<br>\r\n That pie tastes good.<br>     那个馅饼味道不错。<br>'),(14135,'thatch','thatched','thatched','thatching','thatches','n. 盖屋顶的材料,用草盖的屋顶,浓密的头发<br>\r\nv. 茸',' The family lived in a thatched cottage before liberation.<br>     解放前，他们一家住在茅屋里。<br>\r\n \"Are you sure it was Anderson? \"\"Of course I\'m sure. With his thatch of red hair there\'s no mistaking him.\"<br>     \"你敢肯定那是安德森吗？\"\"当然，我敢肯定，就凭那一头蓬乱的红头发就很容易把他辨别出来。\"<br>'),(14136,'thatcher','','','','thatchers','n. 盖屋顶者',' For many Britons accustomed to watching Thatcher browbeat enemies and dress down aides, it seemed like only a matter of time before her support for Major would cool.<br>     对很多看惯撒切尔向她的政敌怒目而视或斥责僚属的英国人来说，她对梅杰的支持迟早都会冷却。<br>\r\n Thatcher has said she will abolish the rating system. Watch this space, she won\'t. No one will. No ever.<br>     撒切尔说过她将废除评估财产的课税现值体制。注意：她不会这么做的。没有有人会这么做。从来没有哪位做过。<br>'),(14137,'That\'s for sure','','','','','那倒是.',''),(14138,'thaumaturgist','','','','','n. 魔术师,奇术士',''),(14139,'thaw','thawed','thawed','thawing','thaws','n. 融雪<br>\r\nv. 使融解,暖和',' Just give me a minute to thaw out in front of the fire, then we can talk.<br>     先让我烤烤火暖和一下，然后我们开始谈话。<br>\r\n The ground has thawed out.<br>     地上的冰雪已经融化了。<br>'),(14140,'the','','','','','ad. [用于比较级,最高级前]<br>\r\nart. 这(那),这(那)些',' The more he has, the more he wants.<br>     他得到越多，想要的也越多。<br>\r\n Turn to the left and you will find the post.<br>     向左转，你会找到邮局的。<br>'),(14141,'theater','','','','theate