ondly the secretary\'s reply and thirdly, the chairman\'s summing-up.<br>     主要活动如下: 第一项, 总裁讲话; 第二项, 秘书做解答; 第三项, 主席做总结.<br>'),(14219,'thirst','thirsted','thirsted','thirsting','','v. 渴望,渴求<br>\r\nvi. (for)渴望,渴求<br>\r\nvt.&n. 渴,渴望',' I satisfied my thirst with a glass of water.<br>     我喝了一杯水解渴。<br>\r\n Many boys have a thirst for adventure.<br>     许多男孩都渴望冒险。<br>'),(14220,'thirsty','','','','','a. 口渴的',' The travellers in the desert felt thirsty.<br>     沙漠中的旅行者感到口干舌燥。<br>\r\n He was thirsty for power.<br>     他渴望拥有权力。<br>'),(14221,'thirteen','','','','thirteens','十三',' He hadn\'t appeared in a film for thirteen years.<br>     他已有十三年未在电影中露面了。<br>\r\n How old is your sister? She is thirteen years old.<br>     你的姊妹几岁？她十三岁。<br>'),(14222,'thirteenth','','','','thirteenths','a. 第十三',''),(14223,'thirtieth','','','','thirtieths','num. 第三十',' Please hand in your paper before June thirtieth.<br>     请在六月三十日前交论文。<br>'),(14224,'thirty','','','','thirties','三十',' I\'ll be thirty next year.<br>     明年我就满三十岁了。<br>\r\n There were many people with leprosy around the age of thirty.<br>     在三十年代有很多麻疯病人。<br>'),(14225,'this','','','','these','a. pron. 这,这个',' Please look at this box here.<br>     请看这里的这个盒子。<br>\r\n We have had two world wars in this century.<br>     本世纪我们已经经历了两次世界大战。<br>'),(14226,'thistle','','','','thistles','n. [植]蓟',' The man made up his mind to grasp the thistle firmly.<br>     这个人痛下决心，毅然处理困难局面。<br>\r\n The thistle is the emblem of Scotland.<br>     蓟是苏格兰的标志.<br>'),(14227,'thither','','','','','a. 对岸的,那边的<br>\r\nad. 到那处,向那方',' Butterflies flit hither and thither.<br>     蝴蝶到处飞来飞去。<br>\r\n She ran hither and thither in the orchard.<br>     她在果园里到处跑。<br>'),(14228,'Thomas','','','','','n. 男子名,耶稣十二门徒之一',' Thomas Atkins, sometime vicar of this parish<br>     托马斯·阿特金斯, 本牧区从前的牧师.<br>\r\n Thomas, commonly known as Tom.<br>     托马斯, 通常称为汤姆.<br>'),(14229,'Thompson','','','','','汤普逊(姓)',' Thompson turned in a superb performance to win the decathlon.<br>     汤普森在十项全能比赛中表现十分出色.<br>\r\n \"Goodbye, Mrs. Thompson.\"<br>     ＂再见，汤普森太太。＂<br>'),(14230,'thong','thonged','thonged','thonging','thongs','v. 装皮带,用皮带打<br>\r\nn. 皮带,皮条',' He fastened the dog to the post with a thong.<br>     他用一根皮带把狗拴到柱子上。<br>\r\n A thong or whip of hide or leather.<br>     皮带，皮鞭皮或皮革制成的皮带或鞭子<br>'),(14231,'thorn','','','','thorns','n. 刺,荆棘',' His sister is a thorn in his flesh.<br>     他的妹妹使他伤透脑筋。<br>\r\n He stepped on a sharp thorn.<br>     他踩到一根尖刺。<br>'),(14232,'thorny','','','','','a. 多刺的,痛苦的',' Cacti are thorny.<br>     仙人掌多刺。<br>\r\n It\'s a thorny subject.<br>     这是个棘手的问题。<br>'),(14233,'thorough','','','','','a. 彻底的,完全的,精心的',' That has been a thorough waste of time.<br>     这是十足的浪费时间。<br>\r\n We are trying to get a thorough understanding of the government\'s fiscal policy.<br>     我们正努力对政府的财政政策进行全面的了解。<br>'),(14234,'thoroughbred','','','','thoroughbreds','n.&a. 优良种(动物,尤指马的)',''),(14235,'thoroughfare','','','','thoroughfares','n. 通路,大道',' The Strand is one of London\'s busiest thoroughfares.<br>     斯特兰德大街是伦敦最热闹的要道之一。<br>\r\n No thoroughfare!<br>     此路不通！<br>'),(14236,'thoroughly','','','','','ad. 彻底地',' Although she scrubbed the old pot thoroughly, she could not make it look completely clean.<br>     虽然她彻底地用力擦洗那只旧壶，但她无法把它完全洗干净。<br>\r\n He is surprised to find his room thoroughly clean.<br>     他惊讶得发现他的房间给彻底地打扫了。<br>'),(14237,'those','','','','','pron.&a. 那些',' Those trees have very beautiful white bark.<br>     那些树长着非常漂亮的白色树皮。<br>\r\n Those schoolboys like to play pranks on their teachers.<br>     那些小学生们喜欢作弄他们的老师。<br>'),(14238,'thou','','','','ye','n. 千个的',' Whither goest thou?<br>     汝欲何往?<br>\r\n But wilt thou accept not the worship the heart lifts above.<br>     难道你竟然会摈弃我呈上的虔诚崇拜。<br>'),(14239,'though','','','','','ad. 可是,然而,不过<br>\r\nconj. 尽管,虽然<br>\r\nprep. 但.',' I don\'t know him well though I\'ve known him for a long time.<br>     我对他并不了解，虽然我认识他已经很长时间了。<br>\r\n He said he would come, he didn\'t, though.<br>     他说他要来，可是并没有来。<br>'),(14240,'thought','','','','','n. 想法,思想<br>\r\nv. (think的过去式和过去分词)想,思考,认为<br>\r\nvbl. 想,思考,认为',' The old man was lost in thought and did not hear us come in.<br>     这个老人凝神沉思，没有听见我们进来。<br>\r\n What\'s the central thought of this article?<br>     这篇文章的中心思想是什么？<br>'),(14241,'thoughtful','','','','','a. 深思的,体贴的',' It was thoughtful of you to warn me of your arrival.<br>     你来之前先通知我，真是考虑得很周到。<br>\r\n You are very thoughtful.<br>     您想得真周到。<br>'),(14242,'thoughtfully','','','','','ad. 考虑周到的(思索的)',' She regarded him thoughtfully.<br>     她若有所思地看着他。<br>\r\n He drew thoughtfully on his pipe.<br>     他抽著烟斗，若有所思。<br>'),(14243,'thoughtfulness','','','','','n. 有思想性的',' Suggestive or expressive of melancholy thoughtfulness.<br>     忧心忡忡的，郁郁寡欢的让人联想起或表达忧郁的沉思的<br>'),(14244,'thoughtless','','','','','a. 没有考虑的,无深虑的,轻率的',' It was thoughtless of you to forget your mother\'s birthday.<br>     你太粗心了，居然连你妈妈的生日也忘了。<br>\r\n She forgave him his thoughtless remark.<br>     她原谅了他说的轻率的话.<br>'),(14245,'thousand','','','','thousands','a. 千,成千',' The little boy can count up to a thousand.<br>     这个小男孩能够数到一千。<br>\r\n Will we all survive until the year 2000? That\'s the sixty-four thousand dollar question.<br>     我们大家是否都能活到公元2000年? 这个问题很难回答.<br>'),(14246,'thousandfold','','','','','a. 千倍的<br>\r\nad. 千倍地,成千倍',''),(14247,'thousands','','','','','n. 数千',' Men have been making music for thousands of years.<br>     人类创作音乐已有数千年历史。<br>\r\n Thousands died in the disaster.<br>     数千人死於这场灾祸.<br>'),(14248,'thraldom','','','','','n. 奴役,束缚 [=thralldom]',''),(14249,'thrall','','','','thralls','n. 奴隶,束缚',' Her beauty held him in thrall.<br>     她的美貌征服了他。<br>'),(14250,'thrash','thrashed','thrashed','thrashing','thrashes','n. 打,逆行<br>\r\nv. 打扑,划水',' As he swam, he thrashed the water with his hand.<br>     他游泳时用手拍打水。<br>\r\n Let\'s thrash the matter over before putting it on the agenda.<br>     我们先把这件事仔细研究一下，再把它列入议事日程。<br>'),(14251,'thrashing','','','','thrashings','颠簸',' Swimmers thrashing about in the water.<br>     游泳的人在水中用力打水.<br>