abin has a flat stone for a threshold.<br>     这间小屋用一条扁平的石头做门槛。<br>'),(14263,'threw','','','','','throw的过去式',' His motion threw the meeting into an uproar.<br>     他的建议在会上引起了一片吵嚷。<br>\r\n I threw a life buoy to him when I saw his struggling.<br>     看到他在挣扎，我给他扔了一个救生圈过去。<br>'),(14264,'thrice','','','','','ad. 三倍地,三次',' My husband earns thrice the amount I earn.<br>     我丈夫挣的钱是我的三倍。<br>\r\n He flung off his opponent thrice.<br>     他把对手摔倒三次。<br>'),(14265,'thrift','','','','','a. 节约,节俭<br>\r\nn. 节俭,节约',' Thrift is the basement of richness.<br>     节约是富裕的基础。<br>'),(14266,'thrift shop','','','','','廉价旧货店',''),(14267,'thrifty','','','','','a. 节俭的,节约的',' Her mother is a thrifty housewife.<br>     她妈妈是一个节俭的主妇。<br>\r\n Only very thrifty children manage to fill up a money-box.<br>     只有非常节俭的儿童才会设法填满一个储蓄罐。<br>'),(14268,'thrill','thrilled','thrilled','thrilling','thrills','n. 震颤,激动<br>\r\nv. 震颤,抖颤,激动',' It\'s a sight that never fails to thrill me.<br>     那是一种永远让我激动不已的景象。<br>\r\n She was thrilled when the handsome filmstar kissed her.<br>     当那位英俊的电影明星吻她的时候，她欣喜若狂。<br>'),(14269,'thriller','','','','','n. 惊险小说',' He is at an absorbing thriller and can\'t be disturbed.<br>     他正在阅读一部引人入胜的惊险小说，什么也惊动不了他。<br>\r\n Our new serial thriller begins at 7.30 this evening.<br>     我们的新系列惊险故事於今晚 7 时 30 分开始播出.<br>'),(14270,'thrilling','','','','','a. 毛骨悚然的,令人兴奋的',' It was a real thrill to meet the Queen.<br>     能见到女王的确是令人兴奋的事.<br>\r\n The film works up to a thrilling climax.<br>     这电影逐渐发展到令人惊悚的高潮<br>'),(14271,'thrive','thrived','thrived','thriving','','v. 兴旺,繁荣',' Few plants or animals thrive in the desert.<br>     很少植物或动物能在沙漠中很好地生长。<br>\r\n A business cannot thrive without good management.<br>     没有良好的经营管理，事业就不会兴旺发达。<br>'),(14272,'thriving','','','','','a. 成功的,旺盛的',' Growing or thriving in water.<br>     水生（植物）的水中生长或繁殖的<br>\r\n Every trade is thriving.<br>     各行各业都欣欣向荣。<br>'),(14273,'throat','','','','throats','n. 喉咙',' I was off work because of a sore throat.<br>     我因为喉咙痛没有去上班。<br>