.<br>     他打开了手电筒，寻找钥匙。<br>\r\n His emblems are the spear and the burning torch; His chosen animals are haunters of the battle field, -- the vulture and the dog.<br>     他佩带的徽记是长矛和燃烧着的火炬；他的爱畜是兀鹰和猎犬－－－两种战场上的常客。<br>'),(14403,'torment','','','','','n. 苦痛,拷问<br>\r\nv. 使苦恼,拷问',' That child is a torment to his parents.<br>     这孩子对他的父母是一种折磨。<br>\r\n What a little torment that child is!<br>     这孩子真烦人!<br>'),(14404,'tornado','','','','tornadoes','n. 龙卷风',' The entire village was obliterated by the tornado.<br>     整个村庄被龙卷风摧毁了.<br>\r\n The tornado cut a swath through the town.<br>     龙卷风袭击该镇，留下破坏的痕迹。<br>'),(14405,'torpedo','torpedoed','torpedoed','torpedoing','torpedoes','n. 水雷,地雷<br>\r\nv. 用鱼雷破坏',' We all accused the union of torpedoing the negotiation.<br>     我们都谴责工会破坏谈判。<br>\r\n The ship was attacked by torpedo.<br>     那条船遭到鱼雷的攻击。<br>'),(14406,'torrent','','','','torrents','n. 激流,山洪',' She attacked him with a torrent of abuse.<br>     她用连珠炮似的谩骂来攻击他。<br>\r\n A torrent of water poured down the mountain.<br>     洪水从山上奔流而下。<br>'),(14407,'tortoise','','','','tortoise','n. 龟',' He bought two small tortoises for me.<br>     他给我买了两只小乌龟。<br>\r\n `Have you got any pets?\' `Yes, I\'ve got three rabbits and a tortoise.\'<br>     ｀你有什麽宠物吗?＇｀有, 我有三只兔子和一只乌龟.＇<br>'),(14408,'torture','tortured','tortured','torturing','tortures','n. 拷问,苦闷<br>\r\nv. 拷问,曲解',' She suffered the tortures of toothaches.<br>     她因牙痛而痛苦。<br>\r\n He tortured his prisoners.<br>     他拷打犯人。<br>'),(14409,'toss','tossed','tossed','tossing','tosses','n. 投掷,震荡<br>\r\nv. 投掷,摇荡,辗转',' Our team won the toss so we play first.<br>     我们的队扔硬币赢了， 因此由我们队先开球。<br>\r\n The children tossed the ball to each other.<br>     孩子们互相把球扔来扔去。<br>'),(14410,'total','totaled','totaled','totaling','totals','a. 全体的,总的,全然的<br>\r\nv. 总计,共计',' Add this numbers together and give me the total.<br>     把这些数字加起来，告诉我总数是多少。<br>\r\n We have debts totaling 5000 dollars.<br>     我们的债务总计为五千美元。<br>'),(14411,'totally','','','','','ad. 完全',' The children see