into what he\'s translating.<br>     译者不应该擅自把自己的意思加进译文中。<br>\r\n His love of languages inclined him towards a career as a translator.<br>     他对语言的热爱促使他从事翻译工作.<br>'),(14488,'transliterate','transliterated','transliterated','transliterating','','直译',''),(14489,'translucent','','','','','a. 半透明的',' She wears a translucent silk gown.<br>     她穿着半透明丝质长袍。<br>\r\n The lavatory windows are made of translucent glass.<br>     厕所窗户是用半透明玻璃做的。<br>'),(14490,'transmission','','','','transmissions','n. 传输,传送,变速器',' We now interrupt our normal transmissions to bring you a special news flash.<br>     我们现中断正常节目，播送一条特别新闻。<br>\r\n A means of one-way transmission.<br>     单向传输的一种手段。<br>'),(14491,'transmit','transmitted','transmitted','transmitting','','v. 传输,转送,传达',' This infection is transmitted by mosquitoes.<br>     这种传染病是由蚊子传染的。<br>\r\n The tension soon transmitted itself to all the members of the crowd.<br>     这种紧张情绪很快感染了人群中所有的人。<br>'),(14492,'transmitter','','','','transmitters','n. 转送的,传达人,让渡者',' A transmitter of disease; a transmitter of tall tales.<br>     疾病传播者；一个散布无稽之谈的人<br>\r\n The sending of a signal, picture, or other information from a transmitter.<br>     播送从一发射机发送信号、图像或其它信息<br>'),(14493,'transparency','','','','transparencies','透明度,幻灯片',' The transparency and luster of a gem.<br>     水色宝石的透明度及光洁度<br>\r\n A machine for projecting the images of opaque objects or transparencies on a screen.<br>     透反射两用幻灯机用于将不透明或透明物体的影象投影到屏幕上的机器<br>'),(14494,'transparent','','','','','a. 透明的',' Plain glass is transparent.<br>     普通的白玻璃是透明的。<br>\r\n The meaning of this passage seems quite transparent.<br>     这一段的意思看来是相当清楚的。<br>'),(14495,'transplant','','','','','v. 移居,移植',' He transplanted the seedlings into peaty soil.<br>     他把幼苗移栽到含泥炭的土壤里。<br>\r\n She had a bone-marrow transplant.<br>     她接受了骨髓移植手术。<br>'),(14496,'transport','','','','','n.运输、运输工具；(常用复数）强烈的情绪、狂喜或狂怒<br>\r\nv.运输；流放；为强烈的情绪所激动',' The transport of goods by air is very expensive.<br>     空运货物费用十分昂贵。<br>\r\n Wheat is transported from the farms to the mills.<br>     把小麦从农场运到面粉厂。<br>'),(14497,'transportation','','','','','n. 运输,运输系统,运输工具',' The railroad gives free transportation for a certain amount of baggage.<br>     铁路对一定数量行李免费运送。<br>\r\n The Panama Canal has played a very important role in transportation.<br>     巴拿马运河在运输上起到了非常重要的作用。<br>'),(14498,'transpose','transposed','transposed','transposing','','v. 调换,颠倒顺序,移项',''),(14499,'transship','transshipped','transshipped','transshipping','','v. 转运,转船',''),(14500,'transverse','','','','transverses','n. 横断物<br>\r\na. 横的',' Storm when we transverse is certainly very big.<br>     我们横渡时风浪一定很大。<br>\r\n A medal, emblem, or insignia in the form of an upright post with a transverse piece near the top of it, or a modification thereto.<br>     十字勋章用接近顶部的地方横梁上的一根立柱的形状制成的勋章或徽章或由此加以装饰的饰物<br>'),(14501,'trap','','','','','n. 圈套,陷阱<br>\r\nv. 设圈套,设陷阱',' The police set a trap to catch the thief.<br>     警察设下了捉拿窃贼的圈套。<br>\r\n By clever questioning they trapped him into making a confession.<br>     他们用巧妙的提问诱使他招认了。<br>'),(14502,'trash','trashed','trashed','trashing','','n. 废物,垃圾<br>\r\nvt. 捣毁',' Sue was troubled to see trash everywhere.<br>     苏看到到处是垃圾很苦恼。<br>\r\n Many things pollute water, such as tires, trash, and plastic bags.<br>     很多东西使水污染，例如轮胎、垃圾和塑胶袋。<br>'),(14503,'trauma','','','','traumas','n. 精神创伤,外伤',' A trauma center; a trauma team.<br>     外伤治疗中心；外伤治疗小组<br>\r\n A bodily injury, irritation, or trauma.<br>     身体的损伤，发炎或损伤<br>'),(14504,'travel','traveled','traveled','traveling','travels','v.&n.旅行,传播',' Nothing can travel faster than light.<br>     光比任何东西都传播得快。<br>\r\n He has traveled widely.<br>     他到过很多地方。<br>'),(14505,'traveler','','','','travelers','n. 旅行者(移式起重机,导丝钩,临时记帐单)',' She was too timid to talk with other travelers.<br>     她很害羞，不敢和其他旅行者交谈。<br>\r\n The traveler wrapped himself with a blanket.<br>     旅行者用毯子把自己裹上。<br>'),(14506,'traveller','','','','travellers','n. 旅行者',' The traveller carries about a camera.<br>     旅行者随身带着一只照相机。<br>\r\n The traveller had to fight his way out through the tropical forest with an axe.<br>     旅行者不得不用斧头在热带森林里砍出一条路来。<br>'),(14507,'traverse','traversed','traversed','traversing','traverses','n. 横贯,横木<br>\r\nv. 横过,铭刻',' They traversed the valley on foot.<br>     他们徒步走过这座山谷。<br>\r\n Searching lights traversed the sky.<br>     探照灯扫过天空。<br>'),(14508,'tray','','','','trays','n. 盘,托盘,碟',' He put the toast on the breakfast tray.<br>     他把烤面包片放到早餐托盘里。<br>\r\n She set a tray down on the table.<br>     她把托盘放在桌子上了.<br>'),(14509,'tread','trod','trodden','treading','treads','n. 踏,梯级<br>\r\nv. 踏,行走',' Every day the children tread the same path through the woods.<br>     每天孩子们走林中的同一条路。<br>\r\n We heard his heavy tread on the staircase.<br>     我们听到了他走在楼梯上沉重的脚步声。<br>'),(14510,'treason','','','','','n. 叛逆(通敌)',' They have committed treason against the state.<br>     他们已犯了叛国罪。<br>\r\n English politician and historian who was falsely accused of treason and banished(1667). While in France he wrote his major work, The History of the Rebellion and Civil Wars in England(1702-1704).<br>     克拉伦登英国政治家和历史学家，被错判叛国罪并流放（1667年）。在法国写出他的重要著作英国叛乱和内战史（1702－1704年）<br>'),(14511,'treasure','treasured','treasured','treasuring','treasures','n. 宝物,财富<br>\r\nv. 珍爱,重视,储藏',' This museum has many art treasures.<br>     这家博物馆收藏了许多艺术珍品。<br>\r\n Such a lesson should be treasured in our memories.<br>     这样的宝贵教训应该铭记在心。<br>'),(14512,'treasurer','','','','treasurers','n. 会计,出纳员',' The company decided to appoint a new treasurer.<br>     公司决定任命一位新司库。<br>\r\n We want to put you up for club treasurer.<br>     我们想请你担任俱乐部的司库.<br>'),(14513,'treasury','','','','treasuries','n. 财政部<br>\r\nn. 国库,宝库',' The Treasury was opposed in principle to the proposals.<br>     财政部原则上反对这些提议。<br>\r\n How much money is in the company\'s treasury?<br>     公司的金库里存有多少钱？<br>'),(14514,'treat','treated','treated','treating','treats','n. 宴飨,款待<br>\r\nv. 视为,对待,处理,治疗',' This meal is my treat, so put your money away.<br>     这顿饭我请客，你把钱收起来吧。<br>\r\n This boy is being treated for a heart condition.<br>     这个男孩正在接受心脏病治疗。<br>'),(14515,'treatise','','','','treatises','n. 论文,论述',' The treatise he wrote is excellent.<br>     他写的论文很优秀。<br>\r\n Our professor asked him to write a treatise on the subject.<br>     我们的教授要求他就这个课题写篇论文。<br>'),(14516,'treatment','','','','','n. 治疗',' I tried every treatment the doctor suggested.<br>     我试遍了医生建议的每一种疗法。<br>\r\n You should follow your treatment with plenty of rest in bed.<br>     你应该在治疗之後好好卧床休息.<br>'),(14517,'treaty','','','','treaties','n. 条约,协定',' The Government has signed a treaty with Moscow.<br>     政府已与莫斯科签了一项条约。<br>\r\n The house was sold by private treaty.<br>     这所房子以私人协议的方式售出。<br>'),(14518,'treble','trebled','trebled','trebling','trebles','n. 最高音部<br>\r\na. 三倍的,最高部的<br>\r\nv. 使...增为三倍',' Profits in our company have trebled in the last two years.<br>     我们公司的利润在这两年中增加了三倍。<br>\r\n He sings treble.<br>     他唱最高音部。<br>'),(14519,'tree','treed','treed','treeing','trees','n. 树',' We plant trees and flowers in spring.<br>     我们在春天种花种树。<br>\r\n In the storm I took shelter under the tree.<br>     暴风雨时，我正在树下躲避。<br>'),(14520,'trek','trekked','trekked','trekking','','vt. 艰苦跋涉(行军)<br>\r\nn. 艰苦跋涉',' Steve and Jack gave a talk about their trek across the Polar ice cap. It was very interesting but it made my hair stand on end just to hear about the dangers they faced.<br>     史蒂夫和杰克讲述了他们在极地冰盖的一段艰苦跋涉，故事津津有味，只是听到他们遇到种种险情时，我吓得很。<br>\r\n It took the climber a month to trek to the foot of the mountain before they even started their climb.<br>     登山者还未开始爬山，光是艰苦地跋涉到山脚下就花了1个月时间。<br>'),(14521,'trellis','trellised','trellised','trellising','trellises','框架,格式结构',''),(14522,'tremble','trembled','trembled','trembling','trembles','n. 战悚,颤抖<br>\r\nv. 战悚,忧虑,微动',' I tremble to think what\'s going to happen.<br>     我一想到即将发生的事就担心。<br>\r\n He was trembling with rage.<br>     他气得发抖。<br>'),(14523,'tremendous','','','','','a. 巨大的,惊人的',' He\'s a tremendous talker.<br>     他是一个非常健谈的人。<br>\r\n We got a tremendous surprise when she arrived.<br>     她的到来使我们大吃一惊。<br>'),(14524,'trench','trenched','trenched','trenching','trenches','n. 沟,沟渠<br>\r\nv. (挖)沟,(挖)战壕',' Grandfather was in the trenches during the First War.<br>     在第一次世界大战中，我祖父驻守在法国北部前线。<br>\r\n I forgot to dig a trench around the tent.<br>     我忘了在帐篷四周挖一条沟。<br>'),(14525,'trend','trended','trended','trending','trends','n. 趋势,倾向,方位<br>\r\nv. 倾向',' The prices of houses are trending upwards.<br>     房价趋于上涨。<br>\r\n The youth like to follow the latest trends in fashion.<br>     年轻人喜好追求最新的流行款式。<br>'),(14526,'trespass','trespassed','trespassed','trespassing','trespasses','n. 罪过,侵入,侵害<br>\r\nv. 侵夺,犯罪,侵入',' Are you familiar with the laws relating to trespass?<br>     你熟悉关于侵入私人领地的法律吗？<br>\r\n One who is guilty of a trespass or sin; a sinner.<br>     罪人犯有过失和罪过的人；罪人<br>'),(14527,'triad','','','','','三元组',' A group or set of three; a triad.<br>     三个一组三个人或物组成的小组，三个一套<br>'),(14528,'trial','','','','trials','a. 尝试性的<br>\r\nn. 尝试,努力,试验,试用,讯问,审讯<br>\r\nn.讨厌的事，人',' That child is a trial to his parents.<br>     那个孩子是他的父母的一块心病。<br>\r\n The murder trial lasted six weeks.<br>     法庭对这一谋杀案的审理为时六周。<br>'),(14529,'triangle','','','','triangles','n. 三角(形)',' The angles of a triangle total 180.<br>     三角形的三角之和等于180°。<br>\r\n He outlined the triangle in red.<br>     他用红笔画出三角形.<br>'),(14530,'triangular','','','','','a. 三角形的,三人间的',' She has a scarf made of a triangular piece of blue silk.<br>     她有一条用三角形蓝绸子做的围巾。<br>\r\n It\'s a film of triangular love affair.<br>     那是个三角恋爱的电影。<br>'),(14531,'tribal','','','','','a. 部落的,种族的',' Tribal lore and custom have been passed down orally.<br>     部落的知识和风俗口耳相传保存下来.<br>\r\n Tribal dancers were wearing grotesque masks.<br>     部落中跳舞的人戴着古怪的面具。<br>'),(14532,'tribe','','','','tribes','n. 部落',' That Indian man is a member of the neighbouring tribe.<br>     那个印第安人是临近部落的成员。<br>\r\n I have heard the cannibal tribe in stories.<br>     我在故事里听说过食人部落。<br>'),(14533,'tribunal','','','','tribunals','n. 法官席,法院,法庭',' The tribunal has authority to settle certain types of dispute.<br>     裁判所有权解决某些纠纷。<br>\r\n The tribunal will convene tomorrow.<br>     法庭将于明日开庭。<br>'),(14534,'tributary','','','','tributaries','a. 纳贡的,从属的,补助的<br>\r\nn. 纳贡者,属国,支流',' There was one street apart from a tributary road near the end of the village.<br>     除了村子尽头的岔道外，还有一条大路。<br>\r\n A tributary colony.<br>     进贡的殖民地<br>'),(14535,'tribute','','','','tributes','n. 贡品,颂词,称赞,(表示敬意的)礼物',' Many Greek cities had to send yearly tribute to Athens.<br>     许多希腊城市不得不每年向雅典进贡。<br>\r\n The musician gave full tribute to his former teacher.<br>     这位音乐家盛赞了他过去的老师。<br>'),(14536,'trick','tricked','tricked','tricking','tricks','n. 诡计,欺诈<br>\r\nv. 戏弄,欺骗<br>\r\nn. 恶作剧',' These children loved playing tricks on their teacher.<br>     孩子们喜欢捉弄老师。<br>\r\n He played some clever magic tricks.<br>     他表演了一些巧妙的魔术。<br>'),(14537,'trickle','trickled','trickled','trickling','','n. 滴,细流<br>\r\nv. 滴流,细细地流',' The stream is reduced to a mere trickle in summer.<br>     夏天那条小河的水量减少，成了涓涓溪流。<br>\r\n She trickles oil into the mixture.<br>     她把油一点点地注入混合物中。<br>'),(14538,'tricky','','','','','a. 狡猾的,机警的',' The interviewer cornered the politician with a particularly tricky question.<br>     采访者用一个极其巧妙的问题难住了那个政客.<br>\r\n She showed great tact in dealing with a tricky situation.<br>     她处理棘手的局面表现得十分老练.<br>'),(14539,'trifle','trifled','trifled','trifling','trifles','n. 琐事,少量<br>\r\nv. 浪费,闲聊',' He told her not to pester him with trifles.<br>     他告诉她别拿些琐事来烦他。<br>\r\n We trifled too long at the fair.<br>     我们在集市上逛得太久了。<br>'),(14540,'trifling','','','','','a. 些许的,不足道的,不足取的',' A small, trifling sum.<br>     一小笔少量，微不足道的数目<br>\r\n So trifling or trivial as to be beneath one\'s consideration.<br>     微小的，微不足道的如此微小或琐碎的以至于不值得考虑的<br>'),(14541,'trigger','triggered','triggered','triggering','triggers','n. 触发器,板机,制滑机<br>\r\nv. 触发(事件)',' A pulse to gate the output of a core memory sense amplifier into a trigger in a register.<br>     将磁心存储器读出放大器的输出选通到寄存器的触发器中的一种