wouldn\'t hand me a lemon.<br>     他为人可靠，我确信他不会把坏东西给我。<br>'),(14572,'truth','','','','truths','n. 事实,确实',' There is no truth in what he says.<br>     他说的没有一句实话。<br>\r\n We shall find out the truth early or late.<br>     我们迟早会查明事实真相。<br>'),(14573,'truthful','','','','','a. 符合实际的(真的,诚实的)',' The news he told me is truthful.<br>     他告诉我的消息是真实的。<br>\r\n He is a truthful child.<br>     他是个从不说谎的孩子。<br>'),(14574,'try','tried','tried','trying','tries','n. 尝试,试验<br>\r\nv. 试,尝试',' Would you like to try this jacket on for size, sir?<br>     先生，你要不要试穿一下这件夹克衫，看看尺寸是否合适？<br>\r\n After a few tries they decided to give up.<br>     试了几次后，他们决定放弃。<br>'),(14575,'trying','','','','','vbl. 试验,尝试<br>\r\nadj. 难受的, 费劲的, 令人厌烦的',' Though things went against Mary, she went on trying.<br>     虽然事情进行得不如意, 玛丽还是继续尝试。<br>\r\n We are trying to make a few economies.<br>     我们正想办法节省一些。<br>'),(14576,'tub','tubbed','tubbed','tubbing','tubs','n. 桶,浴盆<br>\r\nv. 装入桶,洗澡',' It\'s time for my dip in the tub.<br>     我该洗澡了。<br>\r\n A large vessel, such as a tub, cistern, or barrel, used to hold or store liquids.<br>     大桶；大盆；缸一种大容器，如大盆、水箱或大桶，用来装或贮存液体<br>'),(14577,'tube','tubed','tubed','tubing','tubes','n. 地铁,电子管,显像管,管,软管;电视',' Our television tube has broken.<br>     我们的电视机显像管坏了。<br>\r\n I go to work on the tube.<br>     我经常乘地铁去上班。<br>'),(14578,'tuberculosis','','','','','n. 肺结核',' In cases of tuberculosis blood is expectorated.<br>     肺结核病有咯血症状.<br>\r\n The formation of cavities in a body tissue or an organ, especially those formed in the lung as a result of tuberculosis.<br>     成洞身体组织或器官内空洞的形成，尤指那种因肺结核而在肺中形成的空洞<br>'),(14579,'tuck','tucked','tucked','tucking','tucks','n. 缝摺,船尾突出部下方,食品<br>\r\nv. 打摺,  卷起,挤进',' He tucked his shirt into his trousers.<br>     他把衬衫下摆塞入裤中。<br>\r\n The baby\'s dress was beautifully tucked with tiny stitches.<br>     婴儿衫的褶裥打得针脚细密，很漂亮。<br>'),(14580,'Tuesday','','','','','n. 星期二',' Next Tuesday is his birthday.<br>     下周二是他的生日。<br>\r\n Would next Tuesday be too late?<br>     下星期二会不会太迟了?<br>'),(14581,'tug','tugged','tugged','tugging','tugs','n. 用力拉,拖船<br>\r\nv. 用力拉',' Tom felt a tug at his sleeve.<br>     汤姆觉得有人拉了拉他的衣袖。<br>\r\n She tried to tug my hand away.<br>     她试图把我的手拉开。<br>'),(14582,'tuition','','','','','n. 学费',' I\'m considering studying calligraphy or Chinese painting. I will look for a teacher as soon as I find an apartment and pay my tuition at school.<br>     我正在考虑要学书法还是中国画，我找到一间公寓并付了学校的学费之后，会立刻找一位老师。<br>\r\n By pinch and scraping for the last five year, she have enough money to pay for her son\'s tuition.<br>     在过去的五年里，她省吃俭用，终於积足了钱可支付她儿子的学费。<br>'),(14583,'tulip','','','','tulips','n. 郁金香',' Tulip grows large brightly-colored cup-shaped flower in spring.<br>     郁金香在春天开出颜色鲜亮的杯状的花朵。<br>\r\n An onion bulb; a tulip bulb.<br>     洋葱球；郁金香球根<br>'),(14584,'tumble','tumbled','tumbled','tumbling','tumbles','n. 跌倒,翻斤斗<br>\r\nv. 翻倒,滚动',' The little girl stared at the little cats tumbling over each other in their basket.<br>     小女孩凝视着在篮子里互相翻来滚去的小猫。<br>\r\n She tumbled down the stairs.<br>     她滚下了楼梯。<br>'),(14585,'tumult','','','','tumults','n. 骚动,拥挤',' He could hear a great tumult in the street.<br>     他听到街上很响的嘈杂声。<br>\r\n Presently the tumult died down.<br>     一会儿工夫骚动平息了下来。<br>'),(14586,'tuna','','','','tunas','n. 金枪鱼',' I like to eat tinned tuna fish.<br>     我喜欢吃金枪鱼罐头。<br>'),(14587,'tune','tuned','tuned','tuning','tunes','n. 歌曲,旋律,心情<br>\r\nv. 调节,和谐',' He played a tune on the violin.<br>     他用小提琴演奏了一首曲子。<br>\r\n She calls the tune in their house.<br>     他们家中她说了算。<br>'),(14588,'tuner','','','','','调谐器',''),(14589,'tuning','','','','','调整',' The orchestra were tuning up as we entered the hall.<br>     我们进入大厅时, 管弦乐队正在调音.<br>\r\n Miss Ida took her car to the garage to have the engine tuned up.<br>     艾达小姐把车子开到修车厂去调整发动机。<br>'),(14590,'tunnel','tunneled','tunneled','tunneling','tunnels','n. 隧道,地下道<br>\r\nv. 挖隧道',' Moles make underground tunnels.<br>     鼹鼠常打地洞。<br>\r\n Suddenly the train roared into a tunnel and everything was black.<br>     突然火车轰隆隆地驶入一个隧道，四周的一切都漆黑一团。<br>'),(14591,'turbine','','','','','n. 涡轮',' A disadvantage of the turbine is that it is not reversible.<br>     涡轮机的一个缺点就是它不可以反转。<br>\r\n The gas turbine feeds on the fuel it pumps.<br>     燃气轮机以它所抽入的燃料为能源。<br>'),(14592,'turbulent','','','','','a. 狂暴的,吵闹的',' She tried to calm her turbulent thoughts.<br>     她试图平息一下紊乱的思绪。<br>\r\n The sea is too turbulent for sailing.<br>     海浪太大，不宜航行。<br>'),(14593,'turf','turfed','turfed','turfing','turfs','n. 草地,跑马场<br>\r\nv. 覆草皮',' He was busy leveling the ground and laying turves.<br>     他正忙于平整土地铺草皮。<br>\r\n She laid the bouquet on the newly turfed grave.<br>     她把这束花放置在新铺上草皮的坟墓上。<br>'),(14594,'turkey','','','','turkeys','n. 土耳其,火鸡',' People often drink white wine with turkey.<br>     人们经常边吃火鸡肉边喝白葡萄酒。<br>\r\n A native or inhabitant of Turkey.<br>     土耳其人土耳其的原住民或居民<br>'),(14595,'Turkish','','','','','n. 土耳其语<br>\r\na. 土耳其的,土耳其人的,土耳其语的',' A Turkish tobacco pipe with a long stem and a red clay bowl.<br>     土耳其长烟管一种有长杆和红色的黏土做的烟斗的土耳其的烟管<br>\r\n A medieval ruler of a Mongol, Tartar, or Turkish tribe.<br>     可汗蒙古族、鞑靼人或土耳其人在中世纪时的统治者<br>'),(14596,'turmoil','','','','','n. 骚动,混乱',' I couldn\'t think; my mind was in a complete turmoil.<br>     我无法思考，我的脑子里一片混乱。<br>\r\n The London Stock Exchange is in turmoil today.<br>     今天伦敦证券市场一片混乱。<br>'),(14597,'turn','turned','turned','turning','turns','n. 转弯<br>\r\nv. 旋转<br>\r\nn. 行为,举止,（依次轮流的）顺序',' The earth turns round the sun.<br>     地球绕日运行。<br>\r\n Caterpillars turned into butterflies.<br>     毛虫会变成蝴蝶。<br>'),(14598,'turnaround','','','','','转变,突然好转',''),(14599,'turner','','','','','n. 特纳(姓)',' He seems a lathe turner.<br>     他似乎是个旋工。<br>'),(14600,'turning','','','','','n. 旋转,回转,转向',' You take the wrong turning.<br>     你拐错弯了。<br>\r\n Take the second turning on the left.<br>     在第二个转弯处向左转。<br>'),(14601,'turnip','','','','turnips','n. 大头菜',' Would you like some turnip?<br>     吃点芜菁吗？<br>\r\n Human life and turnip remain cheap and plentiful.<br>     人命与萝卜依然是多而且便宜。<br>'),(14602,'turnkey','','','','turnkeys','n. 监狱的看守,狱吏',' A turnkey computer system; a turnkey housing project; a turnkey factory.<br>     一切齐全即可使用的计算机系统；一切齐全即可投入使用的房屋；一切齐全即可投产的工厂<br>'),(14603,'turnover','','','','turnovers','n. 翻覆,翻折,半圆卷饼,营业额,成交量<br>\r\na. 翻折的领子',' Why does your company have such a rapid turnover of staff?<br>     贵公司人员变动为什麽这麽快?<br>\r\n The firm has an annual turnover of 75 million.<br>     这家公司的年营业额为7500万英镑.<br>'),(14604,'turns','','','','','手动车床',' The factory turns out 900 cars a week.<br>     该厂每周生产900辆汽车.<br>\r\n The factory turns out more than a hundred cars a week.<br>     这家工厂每周生产品100多辆汽车。<br>'),(14605,'turquoise','','','','turquoises','n. 土耳其玉,蓝玉',' Corduroy dresses sizes8-16 in white, yellow, red, turquoise, black per100$1,845.<br>     条绒上衣尺码8至16号为白，黄，红，青绿及黑色，每100件价格为1，845美元。<br>'),(14606,'turtle','','','','turtle','n. 海龟',' They caught a large turtle on the shore.<br>     他们在海滩上捉到一只大海龟。<br>\r\n An old shellfish or turtle with a growth of algae on its back.<br>     绿毛龟一种背上有绿色水藻的老的水生贝壳类动物或海龟<br>'),(14607,'tutor','tutored','tutored','tutoring','tutors','n. 家庭教师,导师',' He tutored the child in physics.<br>     他给这小孩辅导物理。<br>\r\n For extra money, she tutors on weekends.<br>     为了多挣些钱，她在周末当家庭教师。<br>'),(14608,'TV','','','','','n. 电视,电视机',' Don\'t spend too much time watching TV.<br>     看电视不要看太长时间。<br>\r\n The kids glued their eyes to the TV set, watching a cartoon.<br>     孩子们目不转睛地盯着电视机看卡通片。<br>'),(14609,'tweezers','','','','','n. 镊子',''),(14610,'twelfth','','','','twelfths','a. 第十二的,十二分之一的<br>\r\nn. 第十二,十二日,第十二音',' He received a twelfth of the money.<br>     他得到了这笔钱中的十二分之一。<br>\r\n The former champion went down to a hammer-blow in the twelfth round.<br>     这位前冠军在第十二回合中受到一拳重击而败北了。<br>'),(14611,'twelve','','','','','a. 十二,12,12',' Twelve months constitute one year.<br>     十二个月构成一年。<br>\r\n I go out for lunch at twelve.<br>     我十二点出去吃午饭。<br>'),(14612,'twentieth','','','','twentieths','n. 二十分之一<br>\r\nnum.&a. 第二十',' He was the twentieth in the competition.<br>     他在竞赛中名列第二十。<br>\r\n That\'s the twentieth goal he\'s kicked this season.<br>     这是他本赛季踢进的第二十个球.<br>'),(14613,'twenty','','','','twenties','a. 二十,20,20',' He was a famous artist in the twenties.<br>     他在二十年代是一个著名的艺术家。<br>\r\n Twenty shillings were equal to one pound before 1971.<br>     1971年前，二十先令等于一英镑。<br>'),(14614,'twice','','','','','ad. 两倍,两次<br>\r\nn. 两次',' I\'ve seen this film twice.<br>     这部影片我已经看过两次了。<br>\r\n I am more than twice as old as he.<br>     我的年龄是他的两倍还不止。<br>'),(14615,'twig','','','','','n. 小枝,嫩枝<br>\r\nv. 理解',' She heard a twig snap.<br>     她听到一根细树枝的断裂声。<br>\r\n I kept dropping hints but he still didn\'t twig.<br>     我一直不停地暗示他，但他还是不懂。<br>'),(14616,'twilight','','','','','n. 黄昏,微光,略知<br>\r\nv. 使微明',' She often sits in the garden at twilight.<br>     黄昏时分她常常坐在花园里。<br>\r\n Twilight merged into total darkness.<br>     暮色四合, 渐而一片漆黑.<br>'),(14617,'twin','twinned','twinned','twinning','twins','a. 孪生的<br>\r\nn. 双胞胎之一',' She gave birth to twins.<br>     她生了一对双胞胎。<br>\r\n They have twin daughters.<br>     他们有一双孪生女儿。<br>'),(14618,'twinkle','twinkled','twinkled','twinkling','','n. 闪烁,闪耀,瞬息<br>\r\nv. 闪烁,使...闪耀',' He stared up at the stars twinkling in the sky above him.<br>     他抬眼凝视着头顶上方星光闪烁的天空。<br>\r\n He disappeared in a twinkling of an eye.<br>     转眼间他就无影无踪了。<br>'),(14619,'twirl','twirled','twirled','twirling','twirls','vt. 快速转动(扭转)<br>\r\nn. 扭转(复制的钥匙,旋转的东西)',' I watched the dancers twirling (across the floor).<br>     我注视著跳舞的人（在舞池中）旋转.<br>\r\n She did a twirl in front of the mirror.<br>     她对著镜子转了一圈.<br>'),(14620,'twist','twisted','twisted','twisting','twists','n. 一扭,扭曲<br>\r\nv. 拧,扭曲',' The accident happened at the twist in the road.<br>     这场事故发生在道路的拐弯处。<br>\r\n She twisted the long scarf round her head.<br>     她把那条长围巾围在头上。<br>'),(14621,'two','','','','twos','a. 二',' I have been away from Paris for two weeks.<br>     我离开巴黎已经两星期了。<br>\r\n We shall have meetings on two consecutive days, Monday and Tuesday.<br>     周一周二连续两天我们都将开会。<br>'),(14622,'type','typed','typed','typing','types','n. 类型,品种,样式,模范<br>\r\nv. 打字<br>\r\nn. 铅字,字体',' There are two types of rocks in this area.<br>     这个地区有两种类型的岩石。<br>\r\n Could you type this letter for me?<br>     你能为我打这封信吗？<br>'),(14623,'typeface','','','','','字型,铅字样',' In printing, a complete range of design variants of a particular typeface.<br>     在印刷技术中，一整套不同设计的特殊字样。<br>'),(14624,'typewriter','','','','typewriters','n. 打字机',' I did the letter on my electric typewriter.<br>     我是用电动打字机打这封信的。<br>\r\n She inserted a new sheet of paper into the typewriter.<br>     她把一张白纸插入打字机里。<br>'),(14625,'typhoid','','','','','a. 伤寒性的<br>\r\nn. 伤寒',' He developed typhoid fever.<br>     他染上了伤寒。<br>\r\n Typhoid is an example of a notifiable disease.<br>     伤寒是必须报告卫生当局的病例.<br>'),(14626,'typhoon','','','','typhoons','n. 台风',' There was a threat of typhoon.<br>     有刮台风的征兆。<br>\r\n The area is flooded, as frequently happens during the typhoon.<br>     这个地区淹了水，这是台风时经常发生的。<br>'),(14627,'typical','','','','','a. 典型的,有代表性的',' She is a typical Taurus/Taurean/has a typical Taurean personality.<br>     她有典型的金牛座性格.<br>\r\n They reacted to the appalling weather with typical British stoicism.<br>     他们忍受著恶劣天气的煎熬, 表现了英国人典型的坚忍不拔的精神.<br>'),(14628,'typically','','','','','ad. 代表性地, 作为特色地',' He is typically American.<br>     他是典型的美国人。<br>\r\n Typically, he would come in late and then say that he had to go early.<br>     他一向是来得很晚，然后又总说他得早走。<br>'),(14629,'typist','','','','typists','n. 打字员',' A good typist can finish typing the long article in a short while.<br>     一位好打字员可在短短时间内完成这一长长的文章。<br>\r\n The typist is away on holiday this week.<br>     打字员本周休假.<br>'),(14630,'tyrannical','','','','','a. 暴虐的,压制的,残暴的',' She works for a tyrannical new boss.<br>     她在一个专横的新上司手下工作。<br>\r\n He has a tyrannical reign on his empire.<br>     他是个残暴的皇帝。<br>'),(14631,'tyranny','','','','tyrannies','n. 压治统治,暴政',' The world has experienced many tyrannies.<br>     这个世界已经经历过许多个专政政权。<br>\r\n People will remember the tyrannies of his reign.<br>     人们不会忘记他统治时期的暴行。<br>'),(14632,'tyrant','','','','tyrants','n. 暴君',' The emperor was a tyrant.<br>     那皇帝是个暴君。<br>\r\n This ruler is a pitiless tyrant.<br>     这个统治者是一个冷酷的暴君。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (14633,'tyre','tyred','tyred','tyring','tyres','n. 轮胎',' There is no tread on the tyre - you should put on a new one.<br>     这条轮胎已经磨平了，你应该换一条新的。<br>\r\n The tyre is too hard reduce the pressure a bit.<br>     这轮胎太硬，要减少一点压力。<br>'),(14634,'UFO','','','','','n. 不明飞行物',' No, it can not be a ufo.<br>     不，不可能是个不明飞行物。<br>\r\n Have any of you actually seen a UFO?<br>     你们中间是不是有人确实看到过飞碟？<br>'),(14635,'ugly','','','','','a. 丑陋的,难看的',' His house looks terrible with those pieces of ugly furniture.<br>     那些难看的家具使得他的家看上去一团糟糕。<br>\r\n What an ugly mutt!<br>     多难看的杂种狗哇!<br>'),(14636,'ulcer','','','','ulcers','n.&a. 溃疡',' The old man has a stomach ulcer.<br>     那个老人得了胃溃疡。<br>\r\n My mouth has an ulcer.<br>     我的口腔出现了溃疡。<br>'),(14637,'ultimate','','','','ultimates','n. 终极,根本<br>\r\na. 终极的,根本的,极限的,最后的',' The sun is the ultimate source of energy.<br>     太阳是能量的最基本来源。<br>\r\n Our ultimate objective is the removal of all nuclear weapons.<br>     我们的最终目标是消除所有核武器。<br>'),(14638,'ultimately','','','','','ad. 最后,最终',' Ultimately, the success of the product depends on the good marketing.<br>     最终，产品的成功还是取决于高明的销售手段。<br>\r\n Every value they created ultimately redounded to his boss.<br>     他们创造的价值最后全进了他们老板的腰包。<br>'),(14639,'ultimatum','','','','ultimata','n. 最后通牒',''),(14640,'ultimo','','','','','a. 上月的',''),(14641,'ultrasonic','','','','','n. 超声波',' The doctors gave him an ultrasonic brain scan.<br>     医生给他做了脑部超声波扫描检查。<br>\r\n An instrument that in a painless and noninvasive manner uses the differential transmission and reflection of ultrasonic waves to create a detailed visual image of the brain.<br>     超声波心动描记器一种用来显示详细的大脑图象的仪器，利用超声波发送和反射的差异来测试并无伤无痛<br>'),(14642,'ultrasound','','','','','n. 超声',' Diagnostic imaging in which ultrasound is used to visualize an internal body structure or a developing fetus.<br>     超声波扫描术利用超声波来显示耳体结构或胚胎发育情况的诊断用的成像法<br>'),(14643,'ultraviolet','','','','','a. 紫外线的',' They use ultraviolet lamp to kill pests.<br>     他们使用紫外线灯杀死害虫。<br>\r\n Enhancing the effects of or inducing a toxic reaction to light, especially to ultraviolet light.<br>     光中毒的加强光的有毒反应影响的，或引起光的有毒反应的，尤指紫外线的光线<br>'),(14644,'umbrella','','','','umbrellas','n. 伞',' The wind blew my umbrella inside out.<br>     风把我的伞吹得翻过去了。<br>\r\n You should take an umbrella just as a precaution.<br>     你该带把伞，有备无患。<br>'),(14645,'umlaut','umlauted','umlauted','umlauting','','元音变音',''),(14646,'UN','','','','','United Nations 联合国',''),(14647,'unable','','','','','a. 不能的,不会的<br>\r\nv. 不能,不会',' I am unable to cycle to school because my bicycle is broken.<br>     我不能骑车上学，因为我的自行车坏了。<br>\r\n We are as yet unable to say when the train will arrive.<br>     我们还说不上火车什么时候到达。<br>'),(14648,'unacceptable','','','','','a. 不能接受的',' Such behavior is unacceptable in a civilized society.<br>     这样的行为在文明社会里是不能接受的。<br>\r\n The theory he put forward at the meeting was entirely at fault and was therefore unacceptable.<br>     他在会上提出的理论完全不可靠，因此是不能接受的。<br>'),(14649,'unaffected','','','','','a. 不矫揉造作的,自然的,不装饰的',' She felt her works are meaningful when she saw the unaffected delight of the children.<br>     当她看到孩子们自然流露出的喜悦时，她感到自己的工作很有意义。<br>\r\n These rights are unaffected by the new laws.<br>     这些权利不受新法规的影响。<br>'),(14650,'unaffordable','','','','','a. 买不起的',''),(14651,'unaided','','','','','a. 未受协助的',' The baby cannot sit unaided she has to be propped up on pillows.<br>     那婴儿还不会坐--得让她倚著枕头才行.<br>\r\n An optical instrument that uses a lens or a combination of lenses to produce magnified images of small objects, especially of objects too small to be seen by the unaided eye.<br>     显微镜用一个透镜或一些透镜的组合来制造小物体的放大形像的视力工具，通常用来观察肉眼看不到的物体<br>'),(14652,'unanimous','','','','','a. 全体一致的,一致同意的',' The committee were unanimous that the application should be turned down.<br>     委员会一致同意拒绝这项申请。<br>\r\n Politicians from all parties were completely unanimous in condemning his action.<br>     所有党派的政治家们都一致谴责他的行为。<br>'),(14653,'unassigned','','','','','未赋值的',''),(14654,'unattached','','','','','a. 未订婚的,未结婚的',' Not in love or married; unattached.<br>     未婚的没有谈恋爱或未结婚的；未婚的<br>\r\n An unattached body cell, such as a blood or lymph cell.<br>     活细胞孤立的身体细胞，例如血球细胞、淋巴细胞<br>'),(14655,'unattended','','','','','a. 无随员的,无侍从的,无伴的',' Telephone shrilled unattended in deserted office.<br>     在空无一人的办公室里电话铃突然地发出刺耳的尖叫声。<br>\r\n An unattended fire.<br>     没有注意的火灾<br>'),(14656,'unauthorized','','','','','非法的,越权的',' A term applied to a computer system, spaces, or operating procedures when considering the protection of data from corruption or unauthorized access.<br>     为了加强数据的保护，防止非法的存取，用于评价计算机系统、存储空间和运行过程完整程度的一种指标。<br>\r\n Containing information, the unauthorized disclosure of which poses the gravest threat to national security.<br>     绝密极其保密的信息，任何不经许可的揭密都会对国家安全造成最严重的危胁<br>'),(14657,'unavailable','','','','','a. 得不到的,不近便的,不能利用的',' I\'m afraid Mr. Smith is unavailable now.<br>     对不起，史密斯先生现在不在。<br>\r\n Her manuscript is unavailable.<br>     [美]她的稿件不拟采用。<br>'),(14658,'unavoidable','','','','','a. 不可避免的',' The blame is unavoidable.<br>     责备是不可避免的。<br>\r\n Something, such as corrective discipline or punishment, that is unpleasant but necessary or unavoidable.<br>     （喻）药某种令人不快的但却必需的或不可避免的东西，例如矫正性惩罚<br>'),(14659,'unaware','','','','','a. 没有发觉的,不知道的',' He drove into the ditch completely unaware.<br>     他不知不觉地把车开进了沟里。<br>\r\n They attacked him unaware when he was reading.<br>     他们趁他看书不注意时袭击了他。<br>'),(14660,'unbearable','','','','','a. 无法忍受的',' The heat outside is unbearable.<br>     外面的高温真让人难以忍受。<br>\r\n He is unbearable when he\'s in a bad temper.<br>     他发脾气时让人无法忍受。<br>'),(14661,'unbelievable','','','','','a. 难以置信的',' It\'s unbelievable that the event repeated itself years later in the same place.<br>     令人难以置信多年后在同一地区重又发生此类事件。<br>\r\n It is unbelievable how stupid he is.<br>     他真是笨得令人难以置信。<br>'),(14662,'unbind','unbound','unbound','unbinding','','切断,解开',' The unbound sheets of paper were piled up on the table.<br>     还没有装订成册的论文稿件堆放在桌子上。<br>'),(14663,'uncertain','','','','','a. 不确定的',' The uncertain weather delayed our departure.<br>     天气变换莫测，延误了我们启程。<br>\r\n I\'m uncertain whether to go or not.<br>     我不能肯定去还是不去。<br>'),(14664,'uncertainty','','','','uncertainties','n. 不确定,不可靠,半信半疑<br>\r\n(学术)不可信度；偏差',' The uncertainty is unbearable!<br>     事情定不下来真让人难以忍受！<br>\r\n They lived in the uncertainty on the dole.<br>     他们依靠救济金的生活不安定。<br>'),(14665,'unchanged','','','','','a. 无变化的',''),(14666,'unclassified','','','','','非保密的',' Pertaining to a signal or area which contains either encrypted classified or unclassified information.<br>     用于修饰或说明包含加密的保密或不保密信息的信号或区域。<br>'),(14667,'uncle','','','','uncles','n. 伯,姑父,舅,叔,姨父',' My uncle is a professor in this university.<br>     我的伯父是这所大学的一名教授。<br>\r\n Your uncle is very sick.<br>     你的叔叔病得很厉害。<br>'),(14668,'uncomfortable','','','','','a. 不舒服的,不自在的',' I am very uncomfortable lying on this hard, cold floor.<br>     我躺在又硬又冷的地上很不舒服。<br>\r\n Your intent gaze made her uncomfortable.<br>     你的注目凝视使她感到不自在。<br>'),(14669,'uncommon','','','','','a. 不寻常的,不凡的,罕有的<br>\r\nad. 非常地',' There was an uncommon likeness between the two boys.<br>     这两个男孩长得像极了。<br>\r\n Hurricanes are uncommon in England.<br>     飓风在英国非常罕见。<br>'),(14670,'uncomplicated','','','','','a. 不复杂的',''),(14671,'unconditional','','','','','a. 无条件的,无限制的,绝对的',' On the plaintiff\'s application for summary judgment the master give the defendant unconditional leave to defend.<br>     原告一提出即判决申请后，法院书记官无条件允许被告进行辩护。<br>'),(14672,'unconditionally','','','','','ad. 无条件地',''),(14673,'unconscious','','','','','a. 失去知觉的',' He was unconscious of his mistake.<br>     他没意识到自己犯了错误。<br>\r\n This wounded soldier was unconscious from his loss of blood.<br>     这名伤员由于失血过多而昏迷不醒。<br>'),(14674,'unconsciousness','','','','','n. 无意识,意识不清,人事不省',' Her words were inward and indistinct when she was in a state of half unconsciousness.<br>     ＂她处于半昏迷状态时，她说话的声音低沉，模糊不清。＂<br>'),(14675,'uncover','uncovered','uncovered','uncovering','','v. 揭露,脱帽',' Please uncover the pot.<br>     请揭开锅盖。<br>\r\n Everyone uncovered when the signal sounded.<br>     信号响时，人人脱帽致敬。<br>'),(14676,'undated','','','','','a. 无定期的',''),(14677,'undefined','','','','','未定义的',''),(14678,'under','','','','','prep. 在...之下,低于',' She sat very still under the tree.<br>     她在树底下静静地坐着。<br>\r\n If you take a deep breath you can stay under for more than a minute.<br>     只要深吸一口气就能在水里待上一分多钟。<br>'),(14679,'undercharge','undercharged','undercharged','undercharging','','n. (思想,情绪)暗流,潜流',' He undercharged me 1 for the book/for the book by 1.<br>     我买这本书他少收了我一英镑.<br>'),(14680,'underestimate','','','','','n. 低估<br>\r\nv. 低估',' Never underestimate your opponent.<br>     千万不要低估对手。<br>\r\n You shouldn\'t underestimate the risks of the enterprise.<br>     你不应低估这一计画的风险.<br>'),(14681,'underflow','','','','','下溢',''),(14682,'undergo','underwent','undergone','undergoing','','v. 遭受,经历,忍受',' She underwent a thorough examination at the hospital.<br>     她在医院里接受了全面检查。<br>\r\n I hope that I shall never again have to undergo such unpleasant experience.<br>     我希望我永远不会再遭遇到这种不愉快的经历。<br>'),(14683,'undergraduate','','','','undergraduates','n. 大学生<br>\r\na. 大学部的',' He is a Harvard undergraduate.<br>     他是哈佛大学的学生。<br>\r\n On one hand, one rule limits the women\'s colleges to300 members, and on the other hand, another rule allows the total number of women to be1/50 of the male undergraduate population.<br>     一方面一个规章制定在校的女生数限于300人，另一方面，另一规定又允许女生总数占男生人数的五分之一。<br>'),(14684,'underground','','','','','n. 地下,地铁,地道,秘密活动<br>\r\na. 地下的,秘密的<br>\r\nad. 在地下,秘密地',' There is an underground car park near the supermarket.<br>     这个超市附近有一个地下停车场。<br>\r\n The spy never told his family about his underground activities.<br>     这位间谍从未把他的秘密活动告诉家里人。<br>'),(14685,'underlie','underlay','underlain','underlying','','v. 位于...之下,成为...的基础',' A deep faith underlies her work among refugees.<br>     她在难民中工作是因为她有很深的信念.<br>'),(14686,'underline','','','','','v. 在...下面划线',' Strikes by prison officers underline the need for reform in our gaols.<br>     监狱工作人员罢工一事，突出地表明我们的监狱制度需要改革。<br>\r\n Those words are underlined in the English book.<br>     那本英语书中有些单词下画着线进行强调。<br>'),(14687,'underlying','','','','','a. 在下面的',' Upward pressure from underlying magma domes the surface.<br>     地下岩浆的向上推力使地面成圆顶形。<br>\r\n The mass of rock underlying a mineral deposit in a mine.<br>     矿藏底石位于一个矿中金属矿藏之下的大量石头<br>'),(14688,'undermine','undermined','undermined','undermining','','v. 渐渐破坏,挖掘地基',' An investigation carried out ostensibly to uncover subversive activities but actually used to harass and undermine those with differing views.<br>     政治迫害表面上是开展揭露颠覆的活动，但实际上用于扰乱和削弱持不同看法的人的调查<br>\r\n Beware of the fifth column. They often infiltrate into key positions and seek to undermine the body politic from within.<br>     要提防隐蔽的敌人，他们经常渗透到关键岗位企图从内部破坏国家政体。<br>'),(14689,'underneath','','','','','ad. 在下面<br>\r\nn. 下部,底部<br>\r\nprep. 在...下面',' The coin rolled underneath the piano.<br>     硬币滚到钢琴的下面了。<br>\r\n The underneath part felt damp.<br>     底层很潮湿。<br>'),(14690,'underscore','underscored','underscored','underscoring','','v. 划线于...下<br>\r\nv.强调',''),(14691,'undersigned','','','','','a. 下面的',''),(14692,'understand','understood','understood','understanding','','v. 理解,了解,领会,闻知',' If you can\'t do it, I will understand.<br>     如果你不会做这件事的话，我可以理解。<br>\r\n I don\'t understand what you are saying.<br>     我不知道你在说什么。<br>'),(14693,'understanding','','','','','n. 谅解,理解<br>\r\nvbl. 了解',' There is an understanding between us that we will not sell to each other\'s customers.<br>     我们有个协议，不向对方的顾客出售货物。<br>\r\n We should get a thorough understanding about the cultural diversity of the United States.<br>     我们应该对美国文化的多样性有一个全面的了解。<br>'),(14694,'undertake','undertook','undertaken','undertaking','','v. 从事,保证',' We could undertake the work for the time being.<br>     我们可暂时担当这项工作。<br>\r\n He undertook to finish the job by Friday.<br>     他答应星期五之前完成这项工作。<br>'),(14695,'undertaking','','','','undertakings','n. 事业,企业,保证',' He is too timid to venture upon a new undertaking.<br>     他太胆小，不敢从事新的事业。<br>\r\n An undertaking, especially one of some scope, complication, and risk.<br>     事业一项事业，尤其指一项雄心勃勃、复杂、且具危险性的事业<br>'),(14696,'underwear','','','','','n. 内衣',' She likes to wear expensive blue underwear.<br>     她喜欢穿昂贵的兰色内衣。<br>\r\n Fabric knitted of this thread, used especially for hosiery and underwear.<br>     里耳线织物用这种线织成的织物，尤指袜类及内衣<br>'),(14697,'underwrite','underwrote','underwritten','underwriting','','v. 签名于下,承诺支付,经营保险业',' The shares were underwritten by the Bank of England.<br>     这些股票由英格兰银行包销.<br>\r\n The government underwrotethe initial costs of the operation.<br>     政府为该项活动提供了开办时所需的费用.<br>'),(14698,'underwriter','','','','','n. 保险业者,承诺支付者',' One that insures, especially an insurance underwriter.<br>     保险人提供保险者，特别是保险商<br>'),(14699,'undesirable','','','','undesirables','a. 不受欢迎的,不良的',' Military intervention is highly undesirable.<br>     军事干涉极不相宜.<br>\r\n The drug has no undesirable side-effects.<br>     这种药没有什麽不良的副作用.<br>'),(14700,'undo','undid','undone','undoing','','v. 解开,取消',' Our folly has undone us.<br>     我们的愚蠢行为将自己毁了。<br>\r\n It\'s better for the doer to undo what he has done.<br>     解铃还需系铃人。<br>'),(14701,'undone','','','','','a. 未完成的,破减的,解开的<br>\r\nvbl. 恢复原状,解开',' One of your buttons is undone.<br>     你的一个扣子松开了。<br>\r\n What\'s done cannot be undone.<br>     st. 覆水难收.<br>'),(14702,'undoubtedly','','','','','ad. 无疑(毕定)',' That sort of thing, though it undoubtedly descends to the level of\"man bites dog\" journalism, is perhaps unavoidable nowadays.<br>     尽管那种东西毫无疑问已降格为诸如“人咬狗”之类的新闻写作，但在如今却是无法避免的。<br>\r\n His teachers told him to pull his socks up, or he\'d undoubtedly fail his exam.<br>     老师要他加把劲儿, 不然考试准不及格.<br>'),(14703,'undue','','','','','a. 过分的,不适当的',' He showed undue concern over her.<br>     他对她表现出过份的关心。<br>\r\n It would be wise not to give undue importance to his criticism.<br>     不过份看重他的批评是明智的。<br>'),(14704,'unduly','','','','','ad. 不适当地,过度地',' An eccentric person, especially one who is unduly zealous.<br>     异人古怪的人，尤指过分狂热的人<br>\r\n Don\'t be unduly worried about the exam.<br>     不要过分担心考试的事。<br>'),(14705,'uneasy','','','','','a. 不自在的,心神不安的,不稳定的,不舒服的',' I\'m uneasy in my mind about the future.<br>     我为前途而忧虑。<br>\r\n They had an uneasy suspicion that all was not well.<br>     他们有一种令人不安的猜疑，所有的事都不太妙。<br>'),(14706,'unemployed','','','','','a. 失业的',' The amount of unemployed capital is very large.<br>     未被利用的资金数量很大。<br>\r\n There are many unemployed workers in the city.<br>     这个城市里有很多失业工人。<br>'),(14707,'unemployment','','','','','n. 失业,失业人数',' In this period, unemployment reaches record levels.<br>     这段时间的失业人数又达到了创纪录水平。<br>\r\n Unemployment has gone up again.<br>     失业人数又上升了.<br>'),(14708,'unequivocal','','','','','a. 不含糊的,不模棱两可,明白的',''),(14709,'uneven','','','','','a. 不平顺的,不均匀的,奇数的',' My hair has been badly cut and the ends are uneven.<br>     我的头发剪得很糟，发端参差不齐。<br>\r\n The car bumped on the uneven surface of the gravel road.<br>     汽车在高低不平的砾石路面上颠簸着。<br>'),(14710,'unexpected','','','','','a. 想不到的,意外的',' The unexpected guest disordered his plans.<br>     这位不速之客打乱了他的计划。<br>\r\n What an unexpected pleasure!<br>     这真是个意外的惊喜！<br>'),(14711,'unexpectedly','','','','','ad. 未料到地,意外地',' I had just put the dinner on when Jim walked in unexpectedly.<br>     我刚把饭做好，吉姆出人意外地走了进来。<br>\r\n I finished work unexpectedly early.<br>     我的工作意外地提早做完。<br>'),(14712,'unexplained','','','','','a. 未得到解释的',''),(14713,'unfair','','','','','a. 不公平的',' If some athletes use drugs, it is unfair for the others.<br>     如果有的运动员使用兴奋剂，其他运动员就要吃亏。<br>\r\n She sued her employer for unfair dismissal.<br>     她控告雇主无理解雇工人。<br>'),(14714,'unfavorable','','','','','a. 不宜的,不理想的',' This situation is unfavorable for us.<br>     这样的局面对我们来说是不利的。<br>\r\n I got an unfavorable score.<br>     我得到一个不理想的成绩。<br>'),(14715,'unfit','unfitted','unfitted','unfitting','','a. 不合适的<br>\r\nv.&n. 不适合',' The army rejected him as medically unfit.<br>     由于体检不合格，部队未接收他。<br>\r\n You\'re very unfit; you ought to take up running.<br>     你身体很弱, 应该练练跑步.<br>'),(14716,'unfold','unfolded','unfolded','unfolding','','v. 展开,开放,显露',' The eagle unfolded its wings.<br>     雄鹰展开双翅。<br>\r\n She gradually unfolded her plan to him.<br>     她渐渐向他透露了自己的计划。<br>'),(14717,'unforgettable','','','','','a. 难忘的,不会忘记的',' It\'s an unforgettable experience.<br>     这是一次难忘的经历。<br>\r\n An unforgettable experience.<br>     一个不会被遗忘的经验<br>'),(14718,'unfortunate','','','','unfortunates','a. 不幸的,令人遗憾的',' He came at an unfortunate time.<br>     他来得不是时候。<br>\r\n I was unfortunate to lose my keys.<br>     我很倒霉，丢了钥匙。<br>'),(14719,'unfortunately','','','','','ad. 不幸地',' Unfortunately, I hurt my knee when I fell down on the ice.<br>     真不幸，我在冰上摔倒时摔伤了膝盖。<br>\r\n Unfortunately he won\'t be here tomorrow evening.<br>     可惜的是他明晚不在这儿。<br>'),(14720,'ungainly','','','','','a. 笨拙的,不雅的',' A large or ungainly automobile.<br>     大汽车巨大的或笨拙的汽车<br>\r\n An ungainly gesture.<br>     不雅的姿势。<br>'),(14721,'unhappy','','','','','a. 不快乐的,不幸的,不适当的',' We are unhappy about the way the doctor treated us.<br>     我们对医生这样对待我们感到不满。<br>\r\n He told me about his unhappy childhood.<br>     他对我讲了他不幸福的童年。<br>'),(14722,'unhealthy','','','','','a. 不健康的',' Their slavish devotion to the leader is unhealthy.<br>     他们对领导的盲目崇拜是不健康的。<br>\r\n Having a sickly or unhealthy pallor indicative of nausea or jealousy, for example.<br>     脸色难看的脸色呈病态或不健康的苍白色，可能由恶心或妒忌引起<br>'),(14723,'unidentified','','','','','a. 未经确认的',' An unidentified man shot the President.<br>     一个身份不明的人开枪射杀了总统。<br>'),(14724,'unidirectional','','','','','单向的',''),(14725,'unification','','','','','n. 统一,一致',' The unification of Italy resulted in a single country instead of several kingdoms.<br>     意大利统一的结果是出现了一个国家，而 不是好几个王国。<br>\r\n Europe\'s plans for further unification may be up in the air, but people from Helsinki to Rome have been learning an often painful lesson in recent weeks about how entwined their economies have already become.<br>     欧洲进一步统一的计划可以尚未定案，可是从赫尔辛基到罗马的人在最近几星期得到一个时常令人痛苦的教训：他们各国的经济已经如何地牵扯在一起了。<br>'),(14726,'uniform','uniformed','uniformed','uniforming','uniforms','a. 一致的,统一的<br>\r\nn. 制服',' The rows of houses were uniform in appearance.<br>     这一排排的房屋外表都是一样的。<br>\r\n The students are wearing school uniforms.<br>     学生们穿着校服。<br>'),(14727,'uniformly','','','','','ad. 一律地(均匀地,无变化地)',' The theory that all geologic phenomena may be explained as the result of existing forces having operated uniformly from the origin of the earth to the present time.<br>     （地）均变说一种理论，可以将所有地质现象解释为从地球起源到现在已均匀作用的现存力的结果<br>\r\n Force applied uniformly over a surface, measured as force per unit of area.<br>     压力；压强统一作用于物体表面的力量，用每一单位面积上的压力计量<br>'),(14728,'unify','unified','unified','unifying','','v. 统一,使成一体',' Is it possible to unify such scattered islands into a nation?<br>     有可能把这样一些散落在大海上的岛屿统一成一个国家吗？<br>\r\n It can be helped by the unifying of relief activities which today are of ten scattered, uneconomical, unequal.<br>     将现在常常是分散不经济、不平等的救济活动统一起来有助于任务的完成。<br>'),(14729,'unilateral','','','','','a. 单方面,单边的,片面的',' The candidates had to state their position on unilateral disarmament.<br>     候选人须 表明他们对单方面裁军所持的立场.<br>\r\n Either of two basic units in cultural anthropology that make up a tribe on the basis of unilateral descent.<br>     一个分支在文化人类学中，在单系血统基础上构成一个部落的两个基本的部落分支的任意一个<br>'),(14730,'unintelligible','','','','','a. 无法了解的,难解的,莫明其妙的',' Philosophy: unintelligible answers to insoluble problems.<br>     哲学：是对难以解释的问题作出的难以理解的答案。<br>\r\n Lacking meaning; unintelligible.<br>     不明白的；难以理解的<br>'),(14731,'uninterested','','','','','a. 不感兴趣的',' Lacking intellectual inquisitiveness or natural curiosity; uninterested.<br>     没好奇心的，不感兴趣的缺乏对知识的渴望或本能的好奇心的；不感兴趣的<br>\r\n She seemed completely uninterested in what I had to tell her about my new job.<br>     我想把我新工作的事告诉她，她好像丝毫不感兴趣。<br>'),(14732,'union','','','','unions','n. 联盟,结合,工会',' Do you belong to a union?<br>     你属于某个工会吗？<br>\r\n We all accused the union of torpedoing the negotiation.<br>     我们都谴责工会破坏谈判。<br>'),(14733,'unique','','','','','a. 独一无二的,独特的,稀罕的',' It\'s a unique work of art.<br>     这是独一无二的艺术作品。<br>\r\n He\'s caught the unique opportunity.<br>     他抓住了那唯一的机会。<br>'),(14734,'unit','','','','units','n. 单位,单元',' The family is the smallest social unit.<br>     家庭是社会最小的单位。<br>\r\n We were a unit on the question.<br>     在这个问题上，我们的意见是一致的。<br>'),(14735,'unitary','','','','','单',''),(14736,'unite','united','united','uniting','','v. 联合,合并,混合',' The more of the masses we unite with, the better.<br>     我们联合起来的群众越多，就越有利。<br>\r\n The oceans do not so much divide the world as unite it. (=The oceans do not divide the world so much as unite it.)<br>     与其说是海洋分割这个世界，不如说是统一这个世界。<br>'),(14737,'United','','','','','a. 联合的<br>\r\nv. 联合,统一<br>\r\nvbl. 统一',' The United Kingdom consists of Great Britain and Northern Ireland.<br>     联合王国由大不列颠和北爱尔兰组成。<br>\r\n Closely joined; grown together; united.<br>     密切联合的；生长在一起的；联合的<br>'),(14738,'unity','','','','','n. 个体,一致,结合',' The figure on the left spoils the unity of the painting.<br>     左边的人物有损于画面的效果。<br>\r\n National unity is essential in time of war.<br>     举国团结在战时是非常重要的。<br>'),(14739,'universal','','','','','a. 普遍的,通用的,宇宙的',' Television provides universal entertainment.<br>     电视提供大众化的娱乐。<br>\r\n When was universal suffrage introduced in your country?<br>     贵国是什么时候实行普选权的？<br>'),(14740,'universally','','','','','ad. 普遍地',' The rules do not apply universally.<br>     这些规则并非放诸四海而皆准.<br>\r\n It is universally acknowledged that...<br>     普遍认为...<br>'),(14741,'universe','','','','universes','n. 宇宙',' The Earth is only one of the numerous planets in the universe.<br>     地球只是宇宙中众多星球中的一个。<br>\r\n We begin to plumb the mysteries of the universe.<br>     我们开始探索宇宙的奥秘。<br>'),(14742,'university','','','','universities','n. 大学',' There are many foreign professors in this university.<br>     这所大学有许多外国教授。<br>\r\n I enrolled at the University of Vienna.<br>     我报名就读于维也纳大学。<br>'),(14743,'Unix','','','','','一种多任务多用户操作系统',''),(14744,'unjust','','','','','a. 不公平的',' He said that the people\'s accusation was unjust.<br>     他说人们的指控是不公正的。<br>\r\n It will be unjust to let me suffer for the folly of other people.<br>     让我因他人的愚昧而受罪是不公平的。<br>'),(14745,'unkind','','','','','a. 无情的,不厚道的,不亲切的',' Don\'t be so unkind to your brother.<br>     别对你兄弟这么刻薄。<br>\r\n Unkind isn\'t the word for it! He treats the animals appallingly!<br>     岂止是｀不好＇! 他对待动物是太不成话了!<br>'),(14746,'unknown','','','','unknowns','a. 未知的',' The director cast her in a leading part when she was a young unknown of 16.<br>     当她还是一个十六岁的无名少女时，导演选中她演主角。<br>\r\n He was an unknown painter one year ago.<br>     一年前，他还是一个不为人知的画家。<br>'),(14747,'unlawful','','','','','a. 非法的,私生的',' It\'s an unlawful assembly.<br>     那是非法集会。<br>\r\n The little boy is unlawful.<br>     那个小孩是私生的。<br>'),(14748,'unless','','','','','conj. 除非<br>\r\nprep. 除...外',' I won\'t go to the party unless I\'m invited.<br>     除非我被邀请，否则我不会去参加晚会的。<br>\r\n I sleep with the window open unless its really cold.<br>     我总是开著窗户睡觉, 除非天气非常冷才关上窗户.<br>'),(14749,'unlike','','','','','a. 不同的,不相似的<br>\r\nprep. 不像,和...不同',' Unlike my sister, I am a terrible cook.<br>     和我妹妹不同，我是一个糟糕的厨师。<br>\r\n Unlike his brother, he has a good sense of humor.<br>     和他兄弟不同，他有种幽默感。<br>'),(14750,'unlikely','','','','','a. 不大可能发生的,未必的,多半不可能的',' These tactics are unlikely to be helpful to you.<br>     这种方法对你未必有用。<br>\r\n He is very ill and unlikely to recover.<br>     他病得非常厉害，不大可能恢复健康了。<br>'),(14751,'unlimited','','','','','a. 无限的,不受限制的,无条件的',' It\'s unlimited to drive cars at high speed in country.<br>     在乡村开快车没有限制。<br>\r\n If only one had an unlimited supply of money!<br>     要是财源不断就好了！<br>'),(14752,'unlink','unlinked','unlinked','unlinking','','解链',''),(14753,'unload','unloaded','unloaded','unloading','','v. 卸货,摆脱...之负担,倾销',' Dockers started unloading the ship.<br>     码头工人开始卸货。<br>\r\n Lorries may only park here when loading or unloading.<br>     卡车非装卸货物时不得在此停车。<br>'),(14754,'unlock','unlocked','unlocked','unlocking','','v. 开启,显露,放开',' I unlocked the door and went into the room.<br>     我打开房门，然后走进屋里。<br>\r\n Scientists have unlocked the secret of the atom.<br>     科学家已经揭开了原子的秘密。<br>'),(14755,'unlucky','','','','','a. 不吉利的,不祥的,不幸的',' It\'s considered unlucky to walk under a ladder.<br>     从梯子下面走过被认为是不吉利的。<br>\r\n What an unlucky train of events!<br>     多么不幸的一连串事件!<br>'),(14756,'unmarked','','','','','无记号的',''),(14757,'unnatural','','','','','a. 不自然的,反常的,不近人情的',' His unnatural manner made her feel uncomfortable.<br>     他那做作的举止使她感觉很不舒服。<br>\r\n It\'s not unnatural that you should feel annoyed.<br>     你感到生气是不足为怪的。<br>'),(14758,'unnecessarily','','','','','ad. 不必要地(多余地,徒然)',''),(14759,'unnecessary','','','','','a. 不必要的,多余的<br>\r\nn. 不必要的东西',' All this is totally unnecessary.<br>     所有这些完全都是多余的。<br>\r\n You shouldn\'t expose the soldiers to unnecessary risks.<br>     你不应该让士兵们冒不必要的危险。<br>'),(14760,'unobtainable','','','','','a. 无法得到的',''),(14761,'unpack','unpacked','unpacked','unpacking','','v. 卸下',' Let\'s unpack before we go to bed.<br>     咱们打开行李再睡觉吧.<br>\r\n Our bags were packed and we were all set to leave when we received new instructions from our Government. We unpacked and stayed.<br>     我们打点完行装正准备出发，这时，接到了政府的新指示。我们又解开行装留下了。<br>'),(14762,'unpaid','','','','','a. 未付款的',' An unpaid, overdue debt or an unfulfilled obligation.<br>     欠帐未付的，逾期债款或未履行的职责<br>\r\n He\'s taken unpaid leave for a month.<br>     他请了一个月的停薪假。<br>'),(14763,'unpleasant','','','','','a. 使人不愉快的,讨厌的',' I found his manner extremely unpleasant.<br>     我发现他的态度非常讨厌！<br>\r\n He\'s making himself cheap by his unpleasant behaviour.<br>     他那令人讨厌的行为有损他自己的身份。<br>'),(14764,'unprecedented','','','','','a. 空前的',' Some economists showed their anxiety on unprecedented level of unemployment.<br>     一些经济学家对失业率达到前所未有的程度表示忧虑。<br>\r\n We are seeing unemployment on an unprecedented scale.<br>     我们现在正经历规模空前的失业现象。<br>'),(14765,'unpredictable','','','','','a. 不可预知的',' He is moody and unpredictable.<br>     他喜怒无常而又捉摸不定。<br>\r\n Irregular in course or behavior; unpredictable.<br>     不规律的在过程上或行为上无规律的；不可预测的<br>'),(14766,'unproductive','','','','','a. 无生产力的',' Not fertile; unproductive or barren.<br>     不肥沃的不肥沃的；不生产的或贫瘠的<br>'),(14767,'unquestionable','','','','','a. 无疑问的,确实的,无可挑剔的',' His honesty is unquestionable.<br>     他很诚实, 这是毫无疑问的.<br>\r\n An unquestionable antique.<br>     毫无疑问的文物<br>'),(14768,'unravel','unraveled','unraveled','unraveling','','v. 阐明,解释,解开',' My knitting has unravelled.<br>     我编织的东西散开了.<br>'),(14769,'unreasonable','','','','','a. 不合理的,过度的,不切实际的',' The price of this dress is unreasonable.<br>     这件衣服的价格太高了。<br>\r\n You know as well as I do that you\'re being unreasonable.<br>     你很清楚你不讲理.<br>'),(14770,'unrecognized','','','','','未被承认的',''),(14771,'unrest','','','','','n. 不安的状态,动荡的局面',' The increasing unemployment caused social unrest.<br>     不断增加的失业引起了社会骚乱。<br>\r\n The social unrest has its origins in economic problems.<br>     社会动荡是经济问题引起的。<br>'),(14772,'unrestrainedly','','','','','ad. 无限制地',''),(14773,'unsafe','','','','','a. 不安全的,不安稳的,危险的',' She lives in an unsafe city.<br>     她住在一个不安全的城市中。<br>\r\n It\'s unsafe for her to go alone.<br>     她单独去是很危险的。<br>'),(14774,'unsatisfactory','','','','','a. 不能令人满意的',' His answer is unsatisfactory.<br>     他的答案不能令人满意。<br>\r\n Reception of TV programmes is unsatisfactory here.<br>     这里电视节目的接收情况不佳。<br>'),(14775,'unsigned','','','','','无符号的',' I suppose that to a large extent I am the unsigned manuscript of the high school teacher.<br>     我认为自己在很大程度上就是那位中学老师的未署名的手稿。<br>'),(14776,'unsound','','','','','a. 腐烂变质的,谬误的',' He must be of unsound mind to pay so much for a house that is practically falling down.<br>     他一定疯了，竟然花那么多钱去购买一幢实际上快要倒塌的房子。<br>\r\n Buyer state cargo unsound condition and prepare claim is await result of our counter survey.<br>     买方说货物质量不高，准备提出索赔，并在等待我们提邮的相对检验结果。<br>'),(14777,'unstable','','','','','a. 不稳定的',' Liable to capsize; unstable.<br>     易于翻转的；不稳定的<br>\r\n 