rk was in vain.<br>     我们的工作全都白干了。<br>'),(14852,'vainly','','','','','ad. 徒劳地',' Taking just a little money with her, she wanders about the Midland moors, vainly seeking employment.<br>     她身上仅带了少许的钱，在英格兰中部荒原上四处漂泊徒劳地求职。<br>\r\n Before they fled the country, the enemy vainly attempted to destroy all the factories.<br>     敌人在逃往国外前，妄图把所有工厂都毁掉。<br>'),(14853,'valid','','','','','a. 有确实根据的,有效的,正当的',' A credit card is not a valid proof of identity.<br>     银行发的支票保付卡不是有效的身份证明文件。<br>\r\n The marriage was held to be valid.<br>     这一婚姻关系是有效的。<br>'),(14854,'validate','validated','validated','validating','','v. 使...有效,确认',''),(14855,'validation','','','','','确认',' A statement or an argument used in such a validation.<br>     证词，证言用于这种证实的陈述或辩论<br>'),(14856,'validity','','','','','n. 有效性,正确性',' Recognition of another\'s existence, validity, authority, or right.<br>     确认确认他人的存在、有效性、权威或权力<br>\r\n The belief that all religions are of equal validity.<br>     冷淡主义认为所有宗教具有相同的正确性<br>'),(14857,'valley','','','','valleys','a. 流域,山谷,峡谷<br>\r\nn. 山谷,溪谷',' He has a large farm in the Mississippi Valley.<br>     他在密西西比河流域拥有一个大农场。<br>\r\n Every spring the river floods the valley.<br>     每年春天河水把山谷淹没。<br>'),(14858,'valuable','','','','valuables','a. 贵重的,有价值的<br>\r\nn. (pl.)贵重物品',' Thank you for your valuable service.<br>     感谢你多年的宝贵服务。<br>\r\n Valuable raw materials were salvaged (from the sunken freighter).<br>     （从沉船中）打捞起许多贵重的原料.<br>'),(14859,'valuation','','','','valuations','n. 评价,估价,价值判断',' She asked for a valuation of her house.<br>     她要求对她的房舍作一估价。<br>\r\n An expert or official valuation, as for taxation.<br>     鉴定，估价如在税收方面专家或官方的估价<br>'),(14860,'valuator','','','','','评价者',''),(14861,'value','valued','valued','valuing','values','n. 价值,重要性,价格,(pl)价值观<br>\r\nvt. 评价,估价,重视',' He valued the house for me at 20000 pounds.<br>     那栋房子他替我估价两万英镑。<br>\r\n This book will be of great value to him in his study.<br>     这本书将对他的研究有很大价值。<br>'),(14862,'valued','','','','','a. 宝贵的',' The particip