'walnut','','','','walnuts','n. 胡桃',' This box is made of walnut.<br>     这个箱子是胡桃木做的。<br>\r\n A seed borne within a fruit having a hard shell, as in the peanut, almond, or walnut.<br>     坚果种子生长在有硬壳的果实之内的种子，如花生、杏或核桃<br>'),(15040,'WAN','','','','','(wide area network)广域网',' The child looked pale and wan.<br>     这孩子看上去脸色不好，一副有病的样子。<br>\r\n A wan expression.<br>     惨淡的表情<br>'),(15041,'wand','','','','wands','n. 棒,棍,杖',' The magician is waving a magic wand.<br>     魔术师在挥舞魔杖。<br>\r\n A rod, wand, or staff carried as an emblem of authority or office.<br>     权杖作为权力或职位的象征而携带的手杖、棒或短杖<br>'),(15042,'wander','wandered','wandered','wandering','','v. 游荡',' Please don\'t wander off the point.<br>     请不要离题。<br>\r\n The boy was wandering around.<br>     男孩在那周围徘徊。<br>'),(15043,'wane','waned','waned','waning','','n. 衰微,亏缺,变弱<br>\r\nv. 变小,亏缺,呈下弦',' By now the power of the Roman Empire was on the wane.<br>     到这时，罗马帝国已日益衰败。<br>\r\n The moon waxes and wanes every month.<br>     月亮每个月都有盈亏。<br>'),(15044,'want','wanted','wanted','wanting','wants','n. 缺乏,欲望,需要<br>\r\nv. 要,希望,必须',' He wants me to go with him.<br>     他希望我同他一起去。<br>\r\n He is wanted by the police.<br>     警察正通缉他。<br>'),(15045,'war','warred','warred','warring','wars','n. 战争<br>\r\nvi. 作战',' We have had two world wars in this century.<br>     本世纪我们已经经历了两次世界大战。<br>\r\n The prospect of another war appalled us.<br>     想到有可能发生另一场战争，我们不寒而栗。<br>'),(15046,'ward','warded','warded','warding','wards','n. 守卫,监护,病房<br>\r\nv. 守护,躲开<br>\r\nn. 由监护人或法院保护的人（尤指儿童）',' The patient lay quietly on his bed in the medical ward.<br>     病人安静地躺在内科病房的床上。<br>\r\n The hospital has a medical ward and a surgical ward.<br>     这医院有内科病房和外科病房.<br>'),(15047,'warden','','','','wardens','n. 典狱官,看守人,学监',' What are the duties of a traffic warden?<br>     街道停车管理员的职责是什麽?<br>\r\n It\'s interesting that the words guardian and warden have a common origin.<br>     有趣的是“guardian”与“warden”同出一源。<br>'),(15048,'wardrobe','','','','wardrobes','n. 衣柜',' He put all his clothes in the big wardrobe.<br>     他把所有的衣服都放在大衣柜里。<br>\r\n You\'d have more room in your wardrobe if you turfed out all your old clothes.<br>     你把所有的旧衣服都处理掉, 衣柜里地方就大了.<br>'),(15049,'ware','','','','','n. 制品,器具,货物<br>\r\nv. 留心,小心',' There are many small wares in the store.<br>     商店里有许多种小百货。<br>\r\n \"The Chairman\'s visiting the ware house today, so keep on your toes and be ready to answer any questions.\"<br>     \"董事长今天要来仓库参观，所以你们要小心点，准备回答任何问题。\"<br>'),(15050,'warehouse','warehoused','warehoused','warehousing','warehouses','n. 仓库<br>\r\nv. 存入仓库',' They stored their goods in a warehouse.<br>     他们把货物储存在一个仓库里。<br>\r\n If necessary, please warehouse the goods.<br>     如有必要，请将该货存入仓库。<br>'),(15051,'warehousing','','','','','n. 仓储',''),(15052,'warfare','','','','','n. 战争',' The naval warfare ended in our victory.<br>     这次海战以我们的胜利而告终。<br>\r\n Prepared for use or action, especially in warfare.<br>     有战斗力的，备战的为使用或行动准备的，尤指在战争中<br>'),(15053,'warm','warmed','warmed','warming','','a. 暖和的<br>\r\nv. (使)变暖<br>\r\nvt. (使)温暖',' He was pleased with their warm welcome.<br>     他们的热烈欢迎使他很高兴。<br>\r\n The weather has warmed up.<br>     天气转暖了。<br>'),(15054,'warmly','','','','','ad. 亲切地,温暖地,热心地',' The suggestion was warmly welcomed.<br>     这项建议受到热烈欢迎。<br>\r\n All the teachers and students are warmly welcome.<br>     热烈欢迎全体师生莅临指导。<br>'),(15055,'warmth','','','','','n. 暖和,温暖,热烈,热情,热心',' He was pleased by the warmth of his welcome.<br>     他因受到热烈欢迎而高兴。<br>\r\n He was touched by the warmth of their welcome.<br>     他受到他们热情欢迎，十分感动。<br>'),(15056,'warn','warned','warned','warning','','v. 警告,注意,通知',' He warned me against going there at night.<br>     他警告我晚上不要到那去。<br>\r\n I warned them that there might be snakes in the woods.<br>     我提醒他们树林里可能有蛇。<br>'),(15057,'warning','','','','warnings','n. 警告,预告,通知<br>\r\nvbl. 警告,注意,通知',' They attacked without a warning.<br>     他们不宣而战。<br>\r\n The sirens sounded an air-raid warning.<br>     汽笛响起了空袭警报。<br>'),(15058,'warrant','warranted','warranted','warranting','warrants','n. 正当理由,根据,委任状<br>\r\nv. 保证,辩解,担保',' That does not warrant you in doing so.<br>     那并不表明你有理由这样做。<br>\r\n You shouldn\'t arrest him without warrant.<br>     你不能毫无根据地逮捕他。<br>'),(15059,'warranted','','','','','a. 担保的,保证的',' Her interference was not warranted.<br>     她干涉得毫无道理.<br>\r\n The tour price is not warranted by the use of two-star hotel.<br>     旅游者花这么多的钱被安排住在二星级饭店是不合理的。<br>'),(15060,'warranty','','','','warranties','n. 担保,保证,根据',' The machine is still under warranty.<br>     这台机器仍在保修期内<br>\r\n The car is sold with a twelve- month warranty.<br>     汽车出售有12个月的担保。<br>'),(15061,'warrior','','','','warriors','n. 勇士,战士',' The Mongolians are a warrior race.<br>     蒙古民族是一个骁勇的民族。<br>\r\n Characteristic of or befitting a warrior.<br>     勇敢的，好战的具有战士、勇士特征的或适宜于勇士的<br>'),(15062,'warship','','','','warships','n. 军舰,战舰',' The Queen is to launch a new warship today.<br>     今天女王要主持新军舰下水仪式.<br>\r\n An ancient Greek or Roman galley or warship, having three tiers of oars on each side.<br>     三排桨古战舰古代希腊或罗马的一种两边各有三排桨的战舰或划艇<br>'),(15063,'wary','','','','','a. 小心的,机警的,周到的',' They kept a wary eye on the robber.<br>     他们密切注意那个强盗。<br>\r\n She was wary of strangers.<br>     她对陌生人很警惕。<br>'),(15064,'wash','washed','washed','washing','washes','n. 洗,洗濯;(美国西部)干河床<br>\r\nv. 洗,洗涤,洗清',' I must wash my hands before dinner.<br>     吃饭前，我必须洗手。<br>\r\n She has a large wash this week.<br>     这星期她有大量衣服要洗。<br>'),(15065,'wasp','','','','wasps','n. 黄蜂,胡蜂',' Wasps look similar to bees.<br>     黄蜂看上去很像蜜蜂。<br>\r\n Her face was covered in wasp stings.<br>     她脸上满是黄蜂蜇过的伤痕.<br>'),(15066,'wastage','','','','','n. 消瘦,衰老',' You must allow for five per cent wastage in transit.<br>     在运输中要允许有百分之五的损耗量.<br>\r\n The retailer has to absorb the cost of wastage.<br>     零售商须承受耗损的费用.<br>'),(15067,'waste','wasted','wasted','wasting','wastes','浪费<br>\r\n废料、垃圾。',' It\'s only a waste of time to speak to her.<br>     和她说话纯粹是浪费时间。<br>\r\n All his efforts were wasted.<br>     他的所有努力都白费了。<br>'),(15068,'wasteful','','','','','a. 浪费的,不经济的',' Recklessly wasteful; wildly extravagant.<br>     恣意挥霍的毫不在意地浪费的；极其奢侈的<br>\r\n Wasteful people usually end up in debt.<br>     挥霍浪费者最后往往负债。<br>'),(15069,'watch','watched','watched','watching','watches','n. 手表<br>\r\nv. 看,注视,照顾',' The soldiers were keeping close watch over the enemies.<br>     士兵们严密注意着敌人的行动。<br>\r\n We sat there watching basketball.<br>     我们坐在那看篮球比赛。<br>'),(15070,'watchful','','','','','a. 注意的,警惕的',' The guard should be watchful during the night.<br>     警卫在黑夜里也应该警醒。<br>\r\n We should be watchful of computer viruses.<br>     我们应该警惕计算机病毒。<br>'),(15071,'water','watered','watered','watering','waters','n. 水,雨水,海水<br>\r\nv. 浇水,供水,注水',' Water is changed into steam by heat and into ice by cold.<br>     水加热则成为蒸汽，冷却则成为冰。<br>\r\n The smoke made my eyes water.<br>     烟使我的眼睛流泪。<br>'),(15072,'waterfall','','','','waterfalls','n. 瀑布',' They took many pictures of the waterfall yesterday.<br>     昨天他们拍了许多瀑布的照片。<br>\r\n You can cross the river a short distance below (ie downstream from) the waterfall.<br>     在瀑布下游附近可以过河.<br>'),(15073,'waterfront','','','','waterfronts','n. 水边地码头区, 滨水地区',' A wall or embankment, as in a mine or along a waterfront, that acts as a protective barrier.<br>     （坑内的）堵壁、堤岸、挡土墙在矿井里或沿着水边的墙或堤，用来当作当保护物的障碍物<br>'),(15074,'waterproof','waterproofed','waterproofed','waterproofing','waterproofs','n. 防水材料<br>\r\na. 防水的<br>\r\nv. 使...能防水',' These are waterproof fabrics.<br>     这些是防水面料。<br>\r\n I bought a waterproof watch.<br>     我买了一块防水表。<br>'),(15075,'watertight','','','','','a. 不漏水的(无懈可击的)',' A watertight cylindrical vessel, open at the top and fitted with a handle; a bucket.<br>     桶一种不漏水的圆柱形容器，顶部敞开并安有把手；水桶<br>\r\n Is this roof completely watertight?<br>     这屋顶一点也不漏吗？<br>'),(15076,'watery','','','','','a. 水的,潮湿的,淡的',' A waiter brought him a watery coffee.<br>     一个侍者给他端来一杯稀咖啡。<br>\r\n Relating to, similar to, containing, or dissolved in water; watery.<br>     水的与水有关的，似水的，含水的或溶于水的；水的<br>'),(15077,'watt','','','','','n. 瓦特',' The lamp needs a 100-watt bulb.<br>     那盏灯需要100瓦的灯泡。<br>\r\n A unit of electric power equal to the product of one volt and one ampere, equivalent to one watt.<br>     伏安法功率单位，等于一伏特和一安培的乘积，等于一瓦特<br>'),(15078,'wave','waved','waved','waving','waves','n. 波,波浪,波动<br>\r\nv. 波动,挥动,起伏',' She has a natural wave in her hair.<br>     她的头发自然卷曲。<br>\r\n The flag waved in the wind.<br>     旗帜在风中飘扬。<br>'),(15079,'waveband','','','','','n. 波段',''),(15080,'waveform','','','','','波形',''),(15081,'wavelength','','','','wavelengths','n. 波长',' The ratio of luminous flux at a specific wavelength to the radiant flux at the same wavelength.<br>     发光效率一定波长的光量对同样波长的辐射光量的比例<br>\r\n The new general is not on the same wavelength as the other commanders.<br>     新上任的将军与其他指挥官们意见不合。<br>'),(15082,'waver','','','','','n. 动摇,踌躇<br>\r\nv. 摆动,摇曳,犹豫',' The disaster caused him to waver in his faith.<br>     这件灾难使他对信仰发生了动摇。<br>\r\n While we were wavering, somebody else bought the house.<br>     就在我们犹豫不决的时候, 别人把那所房子买下了.<br>'),(15083,'waving','','','','','a. 波浪状的',' The magician is waving a magic wand.<br>     魔术师在挥舞魔杖。<br>\r\n Her disheveled coat was waving in the wind.<br>     她蓬散的衣服在风中飘荡。<br>'),(15084,'wax','','','','','n. 蜡,蜡状物,震怒<br>\r\nv. 变大,增大,月亮满',' He lit up a wax candle.<br>     他点燃了一支蜡烛。<br>\r\n He that have a head of wax must not walk in the sun.<br>     自家头是蜡做成，休想太阳底下行。<br>'),(15085,'way','','','','','n. 方法,道路,方向',' The discussion wandered way off the point.<br>     这项讨论偏离了主题。<br>\r\n We lost the way in the dark.<br>     我们在黑夜中迷路了。<br>'),(15086,'we','','','','','pron. 我们',' We have seen the film.<br>     我们已经看过这部电影。<br>\r\n We are good friends.<br>     我们是好朋友。<br>'),(15087,'weak','','','','','a. 不充分的,淡薄的,弱的,虚弱的,无力的',' Your argument is too weak to convince me.<br>     你的论点太薄弱了，说服不了我。<br>\r\n The small weak child became the scorn of the class.<br>     这个瘦小软弱的孩子成为全班嘲笑的对象。<br>'),(15088,'weaken','weakened','weakened','weakening','','v. 使...弱,变弱,弄淡',' Nothing can weaken his resolve to become a lawyer.<br>     什么也动摇不了他要当律师的决心。<br>\r\n These internal disputes have weakened the party\'s power.<br>     这些内部纠纷削弱了这个政党的力量。<br>'),(15089,'weakness','','','','weaknesses','n. 软弱',' We all have our little weaknesses.<br>     我们都有些小缺点。<br>\r\n There is still some weakness in the legs, but her general condition is good.<br>     她双腿仍有些软弱无力, 但总的情况尚好.<br>'),(15090,'wealth','','','','','n. 财产,财富,大量,丰富',' How did he acquire his wealth?<br>     他的财富是怎样得来的？<br>\r\n This country\'s wealth comes from its oil.<br>     这个国家的财富来自石油。<br>'),(15091,'wealthy','','','','','a. 富有的<br>\r\nn. 富人',' He was born in a wealthy family.<br>     他出生在一个富裕的家庭。<br>\r\n This area is wealthy in fruits and flowers.<br>     这个地区盛产水果和鲜花。<br>'),(15092,'weapon','','','','weapons','n. 武器,兵器',' Whether a gun is a weapon of offence or a weapon of defense depends on which end of it you are at.<br>     枪是攻击武器还是防御武器，要看你的目的而定。<br>\r\n The fisher used a spear as his weapon.<br>     渔夫用矛作为武器。<br>'),(15093,'weapons','','','','','兵<br>\r\n兵器',' The soldiers were well equipped with weapons and ammunition.<br>     士兵们装备好了武器和弹药.<br>\r\n The combat arm that specializes in the use of such weapons.<br>     炮兵部队专门使用这类武器的战斗部队<br>'),(15094,'wear','wore','worn','wearing','','n. 穿著,磨损,耐久性<br>\r\nv. 穿著,用旧,耗损',' She never wears green.<br>     她从不穿绿色的衣服。<br>\r\n The inscription on the stone had worn away.<br>     刻在石头上的文字已磨损了。<br>'),(15095,'weary','wearied','wearied','wearying','','a. 疲倦的,厌烦的<br>\r\nv. 疲倦,厌烦,生厌',' I feel weary after such a long journey.<br>     经过这么长时间的旅行后，我觉得很累。<br>\r\n He began to weary of the work.<br>     他开始对工作感到厌倦。<br>'),(15096,'weather','weathered','weathered','weathering','weathers','n. 天气,气候,气象<br>\r\n经历……而幸存',' What is the weather like today?<br>     今天天气情况怎样？<br>\r\n What\'s the weather like?<br>     天气怎么样？<br>'),(15097,'weatherproof','weatherproofed','weatherproofed','weatherproofing','','不受气候影响的',''),(15098,'weave','wove','woven','weaving','','n. 编法,织法,编织<br>\r\nv. 编织,组合,编排',' The driver was weaving his way through the traffic.<br>     司机在车辆和人流中曲折前进。<br>\r\n I wove a garland of flowers.<br>     我编了一个花环。<br>'),(15099,'weaver','','','','weavers','n. 织布者,织工',' His sister is a weaver in this factory.<br>     他姐姐是这个工厂的一名纺织工。<br>\r\n The two weavers were cheats out and out.<br>     那两个织工是彻头彻尾的骗子。<br>'),(15100,'web','webbed','webbed','webbing','webs','n. 网',' Spiders weave webs.<br>     蜘蛛结网。<br>\r\n A web object can be a web page(or part thereof), an image, plain file, a directory, a Java applet, or CGI script.<br>     一个Web对象可以是一个网页（或其中的部分）、一幅图象、纯文本文件、一个目录，一个Java小程序或CGI手稿。<br>'),(15101,'wed','wedded','wedded','wedding','','v. 与...结婚,结婚',' He is wedded to his own opinion and nothing can change him.<br>     他固执己见，什么也不能让他改变。<br>\r\n She wedded a foreigner.<br>     她嫁给了一个外国人。<br>'),(15102,'wedding','','','','weddings','n. 婚礼',' He attended his brother\'s wedding.<br>     他参加了他弟弟的婚礼。<br>\r\n Her wedding brought us radiance.<br>     她的婚礼给我们带来喜悦。<br>'),(15103,'wedge','wedged','wedged','wedging','wedges','n. 楔子,楔形物<br>\r\nv. 楔住,嵌,挤进',' He cut the cake into pieces and gave each of us a wedge.<br>     他把蛋糕切成块，给我们每人分了一块。<br>\r\n I was so tightly wedged between two fat women that it was difficult for me to get up and leave the bus.<br>     我被两个肥胖的女人紧紧地挤在中间，以致于要站起来下公共汽车都很难。<br>'),(15104,'Wednesday','','','','','n. 星期三',' I have an appointment on Wednesday.<br>     我星期三有个约会。<br>\r\n What day is today? It\'s Wednesday.<br>     今天是星期几？今天是星期三。<br>'),(15105,'weed','','','','','n. 杂草,菸草<br>\r\nv. 除草',' I spent the whole day weeding in the garden.<br>     我一整天都在锄园子里的草。<br>\r\n There are so many weeds in his field!<br>     他的田里有那么多野草！<br>'),(15106,'week','','','','weeks','n. 星期,周',' He is very busy this week.<br>     这星期他会很忙。<br>\r\n The temperature has stayed hot this week.<br>     本周气温一直都很热。<br>'),(15107,'weekday','','','','weekdays','n. 工作日',' I don\'t stay out late on weekdays.<br>     工作日的时候我不在外面呆得很晚。<br>\r\n The library is open on weekdays only.<br>     这个图书馆星期一至星期六都开放。<br>'),(15108,'weekend','weekended','weekended','weekending','weekends','n. 周末',' Have you any plan to spend the weekend?<br>     这个周末有什么计划？<br>\r\n What are your plans for the weekend?<br>     你周末计划做什么？<br>'),(15109,'weekly','','','','weeklies','n. 周刊,周报<br>\r\na. 每周的,一周一次的,周刊的<br>\r\nad. 每周,一周一次',' Twice weekly I go swimming.<br>     每星期我去游泳两次。<br>\r\n There is an interesting article in this weekly.<br>     这期的周刊上有一篇有趣的文章。<br>'),(15110,'weep','wept','wept','weeping','weeps','n. 悲叹,哀悼,为...伤心<br>\r\nv. 哭泣,流泪<br>\r\nvi. 流泪,哭泣<br>\r\nvt. 为...而哭',' She wept bitter tears over her lost youth.<br>     她为自己逝去的青春痛苦地流泪。<br>\r\n His wound is weeping.<br>     他的伤口在出血。<br>'),(15111,'weigh','weighed','weighed','weighing','','v. 秤重量,衡量,重压',' He weighed the ideas in his mind.<br>     他在脑中权衡着这些想法。<br>\r\n I weigh less than I used to.<br>     我的体重比以前轻了。<br>'),(15112,'weight','weighted','weighted','weighting','weights','n. 重量,体重,重担',' He gained some weight recently.<br>     近来，他的体重增加了。<br>\r\n His opinion doesn\'t carry much weight.<br>     他的意见没多少影响。<br>'),(15113,'weird','','','','','a. 怪异的',' I heard weird shrieks in the darkness.<br>     我在黑暗中听到奇怪的尖叫声。<br>\r\n I found some of her poems a bit weird.<br>     我觉得她的诗有点怪。<br>'),(15114,'welcome','welcomed','welcomed','welcoming','welcomes','欢迎',' You are always welcome to our house.<br>     欢迎你随时到我们家。<br>\r\n Welcome to China!<br>     欢迎到中国来！<br>'),(15115,'weld','welded','welded','welding','welds','n. 焊接,焊缝<br>\r\nv. 焊接',' Some metals weld better than others.<br>     有些金属容易焊，有的不容易焊。<br>\r\n The car has had a new wing welded on.<br>     这辆汽车焊接了一个新的翼子板。<br>'),(15116,'welfare','','','','','n. 福利,社会保障',' The government decided to promote public welfare.<br>     政府决定发展公共福利。<br>\r\n These are matters that bear on the welfare of the community.<br>     这些都是与社会福利有关的问题。<br>'),(15117,'well','','','','','n. 井,源泉<br>\r\na. 健康的,良好的,适宜的<br>\r\nad. 很好地,适当地',' The police found the lost treasure in an abandoned well.<br>     警察在一口废弃的井里找到了丢失的财宝。<br>\r\n Tears welled out of her eyes.<br>     她泪如泉涌。<br>'),(15118,'west','','','','','a. 西方的<br>\r\nad. 向(在)西方<br>\r\nn. 西,西方',' I live in the west of the city.<br>     我住在该城市的西部。<br>\r\n The sun rises in the east and sets in the west.<br>     太阳从东方升起，在西方落下。<br>'),(15119,'western','','','','westerns','n. 西方人,西部片,西部小说<br>\r\na. 西方的,西洋的,西部的',' America is a western country.<br>     美国是一个西方国家。<br>\r\n Filming a Western on location in the Mexican desert.<br>     在墨西哥沙漠外景地拍摄一部西部片<br>'),(15120,'westerner','','','','','n. 西方人',' A native or inhabitant of an Occidental country; a westerner.<br>     西方人在西方国家居住的当地人或居住者<br>'),(15121,'westward','','','','','n. 西方,西部<br>\r\na. 西方的,向西的<br>\r\nad. 向西',' We\'d better go in the westward direction.<br>     我们最好向西走。<br>\r\n They went westward.<br>     他们向西走了。<br>'),(15122,'westwards','','','','','a. 向西的<br>\r\nad. 向西',' We\'d better go in the westward direction.<br>     我们最好向西走。<br>\r\n They went westward.<br>     他们向西走了。<br>'),(15123,'wet','wet','wet','wetting','','a. 湿的<br>\r\nn. 潮气,雨<br>\r\nv. (使)弄湿<br>\r\nvt. 弄湿',' I went out in the rain and got wet through.<br>     我冒雨出去，结果被淋得湿透了。<br>\r\n Come and walk on the dry road instead of going through the wet.<br>     来吧，捡干的路走，别走湿地。<br>'),(15124,'whale','','','','whales','n. 鲸<br>\r\nvi. 捕鲸',' The blue whale is the world\'s largest living animal.<br>     蓝鲸是当今最大的动物。<br>\r\n A flap from the tail of the whale upset the boat.<br>     鲸尾轻轻一拍便把小船打翻了。<br>'),(15125,'whaling','','','','','n. 捕鲸(业)',' One that hunts or processes whales.<br>     捕鲸人捕猎或加工鲸鱼的人<br>\r\n The poet whaled away at the critics.<br>     诗人对批评者们进行了猛烈的攻击<br>'),(15126,'wharf','wharfed','wharfed','wharfing','wharves','n. 码头',' The ship was allowed to unload cargo on the wharf.<br>     那艘船被允许在码头上卸货。<br>\r\n A landing platform attached to a wharf and floating on the water.<br>     浮台固定在码头且浮在水面上的着陆平台<br>'),(15127,'what','','','','','pron. 什么<br>\r\nint. 怎么,多么',' She is not what she was a few years ago.<br>     她已经不是几年前的她了。<br>\r\n What, do you really want to go?<br>     什么！你真的要去？<br>'),(15128,'whatever','','','','','a. 不管怎样的<br>\r\ndet. 不管什么,无论何事<br>\r\npron.&conj. 无论什么',' Goats eat whatever they can find.<br>     山羊什么都吃。<br>\r\n Whatever I say, he always disagrees.<br>     不管我说什么，他总是不同意。<br>');
INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (15129,'whatsoever','','','','','ad. (用于否定句中以加强语气)任何<br>\r\npron.&a. 无论什么',' Whatsoever nonsense the newspaper prints, some people always believe it.<br>     无论报纸上刊登什么荒谬的东西，总有人相信。<br>\r\n Take whatsoever measures you consider best.<br>     采取任何你认为最好的措施。<br>'),(15130,'wheat','','','','','n. 小麦',' They are grinding wheat into flour.<br>     他们正在把小麦磨成面粉。<br>\r\n Wheat is transported from the farms to the mills.<br>     把小麦从农场运到面粉厂。<br>'),(15131,'wheel','wheeled','wheeled','wheeling','wheels','n. 轮子,周期<br>\r\nv. 旋转,装以车轮,转动',' The sails of the windmill were wheeling round.<br>     风车的叶轮正在旋转。<br>\r\n There are four wheels in a car.<br>     一辆汽车有四只轮子。<br>'),(15132,'wheelchair','','','','','n. 轮椅',' His bad leg condemned him to a wheelchair.<br>     他的残腿使他离不开轮椅。<br>\r\n He collapse the wheelchair and put it on the boat.<br>     他将轮椅摺叠起来放在船上。<br>'),(15133,'when','','','','','conj. 当...时<br>\r\npron.&ad. 什么时候',' When did that happen?<br>     那件事是什么时候发生的？<br>\r\n Turn off the switch when anything goes wrong with the machine.<br>     如果机器出故障，就把开关关掉。<br>'),(15134,'whenever','','','','','ad. 无论何时<br>\r\nconj. 每当,无论何时,随时',' Come whenever you like.<br>     你什么时候想来就来。<br>\r\n I\'d like to see you whenever it\'s convenient.<br>     在你方便的时候我想来看看你。<br>'),(15135,'where','','','','','ad. 在哪里<br>\r\nconj. 在...地方<br>\r\npron.&int. 哪里',' Where did she get the news?<br>     她从哪儿得到这个消息的？<br>\r\n This is where he lives.<br>     这就是他居住的地方。<br>'),(15136,'whereabouts','','','','','n. 下落,所在之处<br>\r\nad. 在何处',' She won\'t tell me whereabouts she put it.<br>     她不告诉我她把它放在哪儿了。<br>\r\n She has told them nothing that could shed light on her husband\'s whereabouts.<br>     她没向他们提供任何有关她丈夫下落的线索。<br>'),(15137,'whereas','','','','','conj.&ad. 然而,却,反之',' Whereas we want a flat, they would rather live in a house.<br>     我们想住公寓房，而他们却想住一所房子。<br>\r\n Wise men love truth, whereas fools shun it.<br>     【谚】智者热爱真理，愚者回避真理。<br>'),(15138,'whereby','','','','','ad. 借此(在...旁,凭什么)',' Whereby shall we find fault with him?<br>     我们凭什么指责他呢？<br>\r\n He devised a plan whereby he might escape.<br>     他想出了一个可藉以逃脱的办法。<br>'),(15139,'wherein','','','','','int. 在何处,在其中',' Wherein does the difficulty lie?<br>     困难何在？<br>\r\n The condition or state in which human beings exist in a meaningless, irrational universe wherein people\'s lives have no purpose or meaning. Used chiefly with the.<br>     无价值，无意义人类生存在一个无意义或非理性世界的情况或状态下，在那里人类的生活既无目的又无意义。主要与the连用<br>'),(15140,'wherever','','','','','ad. 无论什么地方<br>\r\nconj. 无论在哪里',' Sit wherever you like.<br>     随便坐在哪里吧。<br>\r\n Wherever it is possible, he tries to help.<br>     只要有可能，他总是设法帮忙。<br>'),(15141,'whether','','','','','conj.&ad. 是否',' I don\'t know whether he is willing to come.<br>     我不知道他是否愿意来。<br>\r\n I don\'t care whether I get it or not.<br>     我不在乎我是否可以得到它。<br>'),(15142,'which','','','','','a. 哪一个,哪一些<br>\r\nint. 哪个<br>\r\npron. 哪一个',' He lost his way, which delayed him considerably.<br>     他迷了路，这使他耽搁了很久。<br>\r\n Which book have you read?<br>     哪一本书你读过了？<br>'),(15143,'whichever','','','','','a. 无论哪个,无论哪些<br>\r\npron. 无论哪个',' Whichever you buy, there is a six-month guarantee.<br>     不论买哪个都有六个月保质期。<br>\r\n It takes three hours, whichever route you take.<br>     不论走那条路都要三个小时。<br>'),(15144,'while','whiled','whiled','whiling','','conj. 当...的时候<br>\r\nn.&a. 一会儿<br>\r\nv. 消磨',' I haven\'t seen him for a long while.<br>     我已经很久没见到他了。<br>\r\n While Mary was writing a letter, the children were playing outside.<br>     玛丽写信时，孩子们在外面玩耍。<br>'),(15145,'whilst','','','','','conj. 当...时(可是,虽然,只要)',' In data security, the transmission of data to unauthorized users by processes with legitimate access to data. A compiler, for example, could leak a proprietary program whilst it is being compiled.<br>     在数据保密学中，通过合法访问数据的进程将数据传输给未授权的用户的过程。例如，编译程序在编译期间便可能泄漏专用程序。<br>'),(15146,'whip','whipped','whipped','whipping','whips','n. 鞭,车夫<br>\r\nv. 鞭打,挥动,突然攫取',' Their team really whipped ours at volleyball.<br>     他们的排球队彻底击败了我们队。<br>\r\n He cracked his whip and the horses began to trot.<br>     他噼噼啪啪地挥鞭策马狂跑。<br>'),(15147,'whirl','whirled','whirled','whirling','whirls','n. 回旋,旋转,急走<br>\r\nv. 使...旋转,循环而行',' His head whirled.<br>     他头昏了。<br>\r\n He can\'t adjust himself to the whirl of modern life in this big city.<br>     他无法适应这个大都市的现代生活的忙碌。<br>'),(15148,'whisker','','','','whiskers','n. 腮须胡须',' He has heavy whiskers.<br>     他长着很重的连鬓胡子。<br>\r\n The candidate lost the election by a whisker.<br>     该候选人以微弱劣势失去了竞选<br>'),(15149,'whisky','','','','whiskies','n. 威士忌酒',' This whisky is very good.<br>     这种威士忌非常好。<br>\r\n Whisky is marked up by 150%.<br>     威士忌在成本价上增加150%.<br>'),(15150,'whisper','whispered','whispered','whispering','whispers','n. 耳语,密谈,飒飒的声音<br>\r\nv. 耳语,密谈,飒飒地响',' The children were whispering in the corner.<br>     孩子们正在角落里低声耳语。<br>\r\n The wind was whispering in the roof.<br>     屋顶上风声飒飒。<br>'),(15151,'whistle','whistled','whistled','whistling','whistles','n. 口哨,汽笛,啸啸声<br>\r\nv. 吹口哨,鸣汽笛,用口哨通知',' He gave a loud whistle of gladness.<br>     他吹了一声响亮的口号表示高兴。<br>\r\n A bullet whistled past his head.<br>     一颗子弹从他头顶上呼啸而过。<br>'),(15152,'white','','','','whites','a. 白色的<br>\r\nn. 白色,白种人',' Her face turned white at the news.<br>     听到这个消息，她的脸色变白了。<br>\r\n She went as white as a sheet when she heard the news.<br>     她听到这个消息顿时脸色苍白。<br>'),(15153,'whitewash','whitewashed','whitewashed','whitewashing','whitewashes','n. 白色涂料,白粉胶泥水,化',' The opposition dismissed the report as a whitewash.<br>     反对党认为这份报告过于修饰而不予理会。<br>\r\n I\'ll have my little house whitewashed tomorrow.<br>     明天我找人用石灰水粉刷一下小屋。<br>'),(15154,'who','','','','','prep. …的,谁,他,她,他们<br>\r\npron. 谁',' This is the man who wanted to see you.<br>     这就是要见你的那个人。<br>\r\n Who do you think you are?<br>     你以为你是谁？<br>'),(15155,'whoever','','','','','ad. 无论是谁,任何人<br>\r\npron. 究竟是谁,谁,无论谁,不管谁',' Whoever can that be at the door?<br>     在门口的究竟是谁呢？<br>\r\n Whoever told you that was lying.<br>     谁对你说这话，谁就在说谎。<br>'),(15156,'whole','','','