ake a day to set up.<br>     所有这些电线架线要花一天时间安装好。<br>'),(15203,'wisdom','','','','','n. 智慧',' He is a man of great wisdom.<br>     他是一个才智超群的人。<br>\r\n According to conventional wisdom, voters usually make their choice on the basis of domestic issues.<br>     按一般人在这些问题上的看法，选民常常着眼于国内问题来选择候选人。<br>'),(15204,'wise','','','','','a. 明智的,有学问的,有智慧的,聪明的',' She is wise in money matters.<br>     她善于理财。<br>\r\n You are wise to remain silent.<br>     你保持沉默，这很明智。<br>'),(15205,'wish','wished','wished','wishing','wishes','n. 希望,愿望,祝颂<br>\r\nv. 愿,想要,希望',' His wish to be an actor has come true.<br>     他想当演员的愿望实现了。<br>\r\n I wish you a good journey.<br>     祝你一路平安。<br>'),(15206,'wit','wist','wist','witting','wits','n. 智力,才智',' Oscar Wilde was a famous wit.<br>     奥斯卡·王尔德是个著名的风趣的人。<br>\r\n He hadn\'t the wit to say no.<br>     他笨得连说一句拒绝的话都不会说。<br>'),(15207,'witch','witched','witched','witching','witches','n. 女巫,巫婆',' The witch turned the princess into a swan.<br>     巫婆把公主变成了一只天鹅。<br>\r\n The witch charmed the prince.<br>     女巫对王子施了魔法。<br>'),(15208,'with','','','','','prep. 和...一起,用',' You are either with me or against me.<br>     你不是支持我就是反对我。<br>\r\n She is friendly with them.<br>     她对他们很友好。<br>'),(15209,'withdraw','withdrew','withdrawn','withdrawing','','v. 撤回,取回,撤退',' He withdrew his horse from the race.<br>     他让他的马退出了比赛。<br>\r\n The troops have been withdrawn from the danger area.<br>     部队已经撤出危险地带。<br>'),(15210,'withdrawal','','','','','n. 撤退,退回,取消',' He has made several withdrawals from his account recently.<br>     最近他已经好几次从银行提取现款。<br>\r\n The committee decided to make a withdrawal of financial support for his scheme.<br>     委员会决定取消对他那项计划的资助。<br>'),(15211,'withdrawn','','','','','v. 提取(取出,分离,撤退,拉晶)<br>\r\na. 偏僻的',' She withdrew all her savings and left the country.<br>     她把全部存款取出後离开了那个国家.<br>\r\n The troops have been withdrawn from the danger area.<br>     部队已经撤出危险地带。<br>'),(15212,'wither','withered','withered','withering','','v. 使...凋谢,枯萎,衰退',' The cold withered the leaves.<br>     严寒使树叶凋落。<br>\r\n The grapes withered on the vine.<br>     葡萄藤上的葡萄都干瘪了。<br>'),(15213,'withhold','withheld','withheld','withholding','','v. 扣留,保留,抑制',' I withheld payment until they had fulfilled the contract.<br>     他们履行合同后，我才付钱。<br>\r\n How shall I withhold from tears when we part?<br>     我们离别时我如何忍得住眼泪呢？<br>'),(15214,'within','','','','','ad. 在内<br>\r\nn. 里面<br>\r\nprep. 在...里面',' I\'ll be coming within an hour.<br>     一小时之内我就会到。<br>\r\n This is a task well within your ability.<br>     这完全是你力所能及的工作。<br>'),(15215,'without','','','','','ad. 在外面<br>\r\nn. 外面,外部<br>\r\nprep. 无,没有',' The rumor was without foundation.<br>     那条谣言毫无根据。<br>\r\n Without the sun, nothing would grow.<br>     没有太阳，就不会有生物。<br>'),(15216,'withstand','withstood','withstood','withstanding','','v. 抵抗,对抗,经得起',' Children\'s furniture must withstand kicks and blows.<br>     孩子用的家具必须经得起拳打脚踢。<br>\r\n This dress material will withstand repeated washing.<br>     这种衣料经得住反复洗涤。<br>'),(15217,'witness','witnessed','witnessed','witnessing','witnesses','n. 目击者,证人<br>\r\nv. (为...)作证,目击<br>\r\nvt. 目击',' Police have appealed for witnesses to come forward.<br>     警方呼吁目击者挺身而出。<br>\r\n Did anyone witness the traffic accident?<br>     有谁目击了这场交通事故？<br>'),(15218,'witty','','','','','a. 富于机智的,诙谐的',' His witty remark caused a storm of laughter.<br>     他的妙语引起一阵哄堂大笑。<br>\r\n Although the subject-matter (of her talk) was rather dull her witty delivery kept the audience interested.<br>     尽管（她讲的）内容有些枯燥, 但由於她善於表达, 大家仍听得津津有味.<br>'),(15219,'wizard','','','','wizards','n. 男巫,术士,鬼才<br>\r\na. 男巫的,巫术的',' He is a wizard at playing the piano.<br>     他是个钢琴奇才。<br>\r\n Having the qualities or attributes of a wizard.<br>     魔法的，术士的有巫师的特点或性质的<br>'),(15220,'woe','','','','woes','n. 悲哀,悲痛,苦痛,不幸,困难',' Woe betide anyone who arrives late!<br>     谁迟到谁倒霉！<br>\r\n He told her all his woes.<br>     他把自己的辛酸事都告诉她了。<br>'),(15221,'wolf','wolfed','wolfed','wolfing','wolves','n. 狼',' It is said that there are wolves in this forest.<br>     据说这片森林里有狼。<br>\r\n He saw a hungry wolf on the prowl with his telescope.<br>     他通过望远镜看到了一头四处觅食的饿狼。<br>'),(15222,'woman','','','','women','n. 妇女,女人',' Woman is physically but not mentally weaker than man.<br>     女子在体力上而不是智力上比男子弱。<br>\r\n She is a career woman rather than a housewife.<br>     她是职业妇女而不是家庭主妇。<br>'),(15223,'wonder','wondered','wondered','wondering','wonders','n. 奇迹,惊奇,惊谔<br>\r\nv. 惊奇,想知道,怀疑<br>\r\nadj.奇妙的,非凡的',' They wondered at his learning.<br>     他们对他的学识感到惊奇。<br>\r\n They stared at the strange sight in silent wonder.<br>     他们惊讶地默默凝视那奇景。<br>'),(15224,'wonderful','','','','','a. 极好的,精彩的',' Autumn is a wonderful season.<br>     秋天是极好的季节。<br>\r\n The child\'s skill is wonderful for his age.<br>     这个孩子小小年纪，技巧令人称奇。<br>'),(15225,'wood','wooded','wooded','wooding','woods','n. 木材,木头',' You should put some more wood in the fire.<br>     你应该再往火里添些木料。<br>\r\n Pine is a soft wood and teak is a hard wood.<br>     松木是软木，柚木是硬木。<br>'),(15226,'wooden','','','','','a. 木制的',' The actress gave a rather wooden performance.<br>     那个女演员的表演相当呆板。<br>\r\n Our wooden sofa seems not very comfortable.<br>     我们的木头沙发似乎不太舒服。<br>'),(15227,'woodpecker','','','','woodpeckers','n. 啄木鸟',' Woodpeckers have long beaks.<br>     啄木鸟长着长嘴。<br>\r\n All the woodpeckers have scansorial feet.<br>     所有的啄木鸟都有适於攀爬的脚。<br>'),(15228,'woods','','','','','n. 树林',' The police searched all the woods within a six-mile radius.<br>     警察搜索了在周围六英里以内的树林各处。<br>\r\n Their family often picnics in the woods.<br>     他们一家常在树林里野餐。<br>'),(15229,'wool','','','','','n. 毛线,毛织品,羊毛',' This wool suit is very expensive.<br>     这套毛料套装十分昂贵。<br>\r\n The wool got in a fearful tangle.<br>     毛线乱成了一团。<br>'),(15230,'woolen','','','','woolens','n. 毛制品<br>\r\na. 羊毛的,羊毛制的,毛织的',' We have to wear woolen clothes in the cold winter.<br>     寒冷的冬天，我们不得不穿毛织品。<br>\r\n This woolen sweater may keep you warm in winter.<br>     这件羊毛衫在冬天可以保暖。<br>'),(15231,'woollen','','','','','n. 毛织品<br>\r\na. 羊毛制的',' A man was lying in the 