ing.<br>     农夫正在劳动的时候，耙子断了。<br>\r\n I\'m working on it.<br>     我正在努力。<br>'),(15242,'workman','','','','workmen','n. 工人,工匠,技工',' The workmen fixed the water system.<br>     工人们装好了供水系统。<br>\r\n Our new washing-machine keeps breaking down it\'s entirely due to shoddy workmanship.<br>     我们的新洗衣机老出毛病－－完全是因为做的质量太差。<br>'),(15243,'workmanship','','','','','n. 手艺,技巧',' Look at the workmanship on the carved desk.<br>     看这雕花桌子的工艺多么精湛。<br>\r\n They admired her workmanship.<br>     他们很钦佩她的手艺.<br>'),(15244,'works','','','','','结构物<br>\r\n厂<br>\r\n制造厂',' They are repairing the defense works.<br>     他们正在修防御工程。<br>\r\n She works in a sugar refinery.<br>     她在一家制糖厂工作。<br>'),(15245,'workshop','','','','','n. 车间,工场,研讨会,讲习班',' We\'ll have a poetry workshop.<br>     我们将开个诗歌研习会。<br>\r\n There are more than fifty workers in this workshop.<br>     这个车间里有五十多个工人。<br>'),(15246,'workstation','','','','','n. 工作站<br>\r\n工作站',''),(15247,'world','','','','worlds','n. 世界',' He is the richest man in the world.<br>     他是世界上最富有的人。<br>\r\n The travel enlarged my world.<br>     这次旅行扩大了我的眼界。<br>'),(15248,'worldwide','','','','','a. 全世界的',' That shall do it, thank you for call worldwide flowers. Bye.<br>     那好，谢谢你给我们打电话。再见。<br>\r\n Hello. worldwide flowers. Ers. Green speaking.<br>     喂，这是世界花卉公司，我是格林太太。<br>'),(15249,'worm','wormed','wormed','worming','worms','n. 虫,蠕虫',' You miserable worm!<br>     你这个可怜虫！<br>\r\n Many birds eat worms.<br>     很多鸟类都以虫子为食。<br>'),(15250,'worried','','','','','a. 担心的,烦恼的',' Small children are right to fear the night-- but it is shift- worker, not bogeyman, they shall be worried about.<br>     小孩子害怕晚上是正常的－但是他们应该担心的是上夜班的工人，而不是怪物。<br>\r\n You have no idea how worried I was.<br>     你想像不出来我有多么担心。<br>'),(15251,'worry','worried','worried','worrying','worries','n. 烦恼,忧虑,苦恼<br>\r\nv. 使...烦恼,焦虑,苦恼',' Don\'t worry about it.<br>     别担心/放松点。<br>\r\n There\'s nothing to worry about.<br>     没什么可担心的。<br>'),(15252,'worse','','','','','a. 更坏的,更差的<br>\r\nad. 更坏,更差',' I\'m afraid he 