r for years.<br>     我认识她好几年了。<br>\r\n He is 16 years old.<br>     他16 岁了。<br>'),(15291,'yearbook','','','','','n. 年鉴',' A periodical published yearly; a yearbook.<br>     年刊；年鉴每年出版一次的期刊；年刊<br>'),(15292,'yearly','','','','yearlies','a. 每年的<br>\r\nad. 每年,一年一次地',' The meeting is held yearly.<br>     会议每年举行一次。<br>\r\n The yearly conference will be held next month.<br>     年会下个月举行。<br>'),(15293,'yearn','yearned','yearned','yearning','','v. 渴望,想念',' He yearned to return to his native land.<br>     他渴望回到故乡。<br>\r\n He yearned for a sight of the old, familiar faces.<br>     他渴望一见那些熟悉的老面孔。<br>'),(15294,'years','','','','','n. 年',' The company doubled its size in nine years.<br>     9年来这家公司的规模扩大了一倍。<br>\r\n It took years of hard work to speak good English.<br>     讲一口流利的英语需要多年的刻苦操练。<br>'),(15295,'yeast','','','','','n. 酵母',' Yeast must be used in producing wine.<br>     制酒时必须使用酵母菌。<br>\r\n Made light and high by yeast or other leaven.<br>     发酵的用酵母或其它发酵剂使…轻而高<br>'),(15296,'yell','yelled','yelled','yelling','yells','v. 大叫',' Don\'t yell at me!<br>     别对我大喊大叫！<br>\r\n You don\'t have to yell; I can hear you.<br>     你用不著喊, 我听得见.<br>'),(15297,'yellow','yellowed','yellowed','yellowing','yellows','a. 黄色的<br>\r\nn. 黄色',' The leaves of the book had yellowed with age.<br>     书页因年久而变黄。<br>\r\n The leaves turn yellow in autumn.<br>     秋天时叶子变黄。<br>'),(15298,'yes','yessed','yessed','yessing','yeses','a. 是的<br>\r\nad. 是,是的<br>\r\nv. 是',' Answer with a plain \"yes\" if you agree with me.<br>     如果你同意我的意见，就明白地回答“是”。<br>\r\n Yes, you\'re quite right.<br>     是的，你很对。<br>'),(15299,'yesterday','','','','','n.&ad. 昨天',' He arrived yesterday.<br>     他昨天到达的。<br>\r\n Yesterday was Friday.<br>     昨天是星期五。<br>'),(15300,'yet','','','','','ad. 还,仍然<br>\r\nconj. 然而',' He hasn\'t done much yet.<br>     他做的还不很多。<br>\r\n She is vain and foolish, and yet people like her.<br>     她自负而愚蠢，然而人们喜欢她。<br>'),(15301,'yield','yielded','yielded','yielding','yields','n. 生产量,投资收益<br>\r\nv. 生产,屈服,投降,弯下去，凹下去',' These trees gave a high yield of fruit this year.<br>     这些果树今年获得了大丰收。<br>\r\n The soldiers had to yield.<br>     士兵们被迫投降。<br>'),(15302,'yoke','yoked','yoked','yoking','yoke','n. 轭, 轭状物, 套, 束缚, 支配<br>\r\nv. 把...套上轭, 结合, 连接',' His army never came under the yoke of invaders.<br>     他的军队从来不向侵略者屈服。<br>\r\n The farmer was yoking his oxen to a plough.<br>     农夫正在用轭把牛套到犁上。<br>'),(15303,'yolk','','','','yolks','n. 蛋黄',' The yolk is the yellow part in an egg.<br>     蛋黄是鸡蛋中的黄色部分.<br>\r\n One of two spiral bands of tissue in an egg that connect the yolk to the lining membrane at either end of the shell.<br>     卵黄系带鸡蛋内将蛋黄和蛋壳任一端的内膜连接的两个螺旋的带状组织之一<br>'),(15304,'you','','','','','pron. 你,你们',' You must all listen carefully.<br>     你们都必须仔细听着。<br>\r\n How late are you open?<br>     你们营业到几点？<br>'),(15305,'young','','','','','a. 年轻的<br>\r\nn. 青年人',' This young girl is my daughter.<br>     这个年轻的女孩是我的女儿。<br>\r\n The young in our society need careand protection.<br>     我们社会的年轻人需要受到关怀和爱护.<br>'),(15306,'younger','','','','','n. 少年,儿童',' He looks ten years younger.<br>     他看起来年轻了10岁。<br>\r\n If I were ten years younger, I\'d study harder.<br>     要是我年轻10岁，我就要更用功学习。<br>'),(15307,'youngster','','','','youngsters','n. 年青人,少年',' \"People, especially youngsters don\'t seem so polite these days.\"<br>     ＂如今人们，尤其是年青人好象不那么讲礼貌了。＂<br>\r\n It is hard for an old man to work as long as a youngster.<br>     老年人要工作得和年轻伙子一样久是困难的。<br>'),(15308,'your','','','','','pron. 你的,你们的',' Your hands are dirty.<br>     你的手很脏。<br>\r\n These are your books.<br>     这些是你们的书。<br>'),(15309,'yours','','','','','pron. 你的,你们的',' This is our room, and yours is down the passage.<br>     这是我们的房间，你们的在走廊的那一头。<br>\r\n His view of life is different from yours.<br>     他的人生观与你的不同。<br>'),(15310,'yourself','','','','yourselves','pron. 你自己',' You and your sister said so yourselves.<br>     你和你姐姐都这么说。<br>\r\n I believe that you can work out this problem by yourself.<br>     我相信你自己能做出这道题的。<br>'),(15311,'yourselves','','','','','pron. 你们自己',' You two have only yourselves to blame.<br>     你们俩只能怪自己。<br>\r\n Taken care of yourselves.<br>     照顾你们自己。<br>'),(15312,'youth','','','','youths','n. 年轻人,年轻',' In his youth, he had shown great promise.<br>     他在青少年时代就显得很有出息。<br>\r\n The youth of the country are being ignored by politicians.<br>     这个国家的青年没有受到政治家的重视。<br>'),(15313,'youthful','','','','','a. 年轻的',' No one can remain youthful forever.<br>     没有人能永保青春。<br>'),(15314,'yuan','','','','yuan','元朝',' Pay back the5,000 Yuan I loan you by today.<br>     我借给你的5，000元，今天还我吧。<br>\r\n The buy rate of US dollar note be846 yuan per hundred dollar.<br>     美元的买入价是100美元付864元人民币。<br>'),(15315,'zap','zapped','zapped','zapping','','击溃',' I really admire her she\'s so full of zap!<br>     我真佩服她--精力那麽充沛!<br>\r\n Have you seen him zapping around town on his new motor bike?<br>     你看见没看见他骑著自己的新摩托车在市区飞驰?<br>'),(15316,'zeal','','','','','n. 热情,热忱',' She shows great zeal for knowledge.<br>     她表现出强烈的求知欲。<br>\r\n Zeal without knowledge is fire without light.<br>     【谚】热情而无知，犹如无光之火。<br>'),(15317,'zealous','','','','','a. 热心的,热情的',' The zealous demonstrators were ignored by the media.<br>     热情的示威游行者被新闻媒介忽视了。<br>\r\n The doctors were zealous in their efforts to ensure the survival of premature babies.<br>     医生们在努力保证早产婴儿成活方面热情很高。<br>'),(15318,'zebra','','','','zebra','n. 斑马',' Seemingly everyone likes the zebra.<br>     似乎每个人都喜欢斑马。<br>\r\n Related to, resembling, or characteristic of a zebra.<br>     斑马的与斑马有关的、与斑马相似的或具有斑马特征的<br>'),(15319,'zero','zeroed','zeroed','zeroing','zeros','num.&n. 零',' It was five below zero last night.<br>     昨夜温度是零下五度。<br>\r\n His hope was reduced to zero.<br>     他的希望化为乌有。<br>'),(15320,'zest','','','','','n. 风味,强烈的兴味,风味',' The element of risk gave (an) added zest to the adventure.<br>     这种冒险成分更给探险活动平添几分乐趣.<br>\r\n Her zest for life is as great as ever.<br>     她对生活的极大乐趣一如既往.<br>'),(15321,'zigzag','zigzagged','zigzagged','zigzagging','zigzags','n. 曲折,Z字形<br>\r\na. 曲折的,锯齿形的<br>\r\nad. 曲折